h,0631,אָסַר,Verb,asar,(aw-sar'),to tie
column9: bind
column11: bind, fast, gird, harness, hold, keep, make ready, order,
column12: A primitive root; to yoke or hitch; by analogy, to fasten in any sense, to join battle -- bind, fast, gird, harness, hold, keep, make ready, order, prepare, prison(-er), put in bonds, set in array, tie.

column9: Or riccar {is-sawr'}; from (H631) 'acar; an obligation or vow (of abstinence) -- binding, bond. see HEBREW (H631) 'acar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H632) 'ecar in a legal sense; an interdict -- decree. see HEBREW (H632) 'ecar

column7: Ashur has given a brother, an Assyrian king
column9: Of foreign derivation; Esar- chaddon, an Assyrian king -- Esar-haddon.

column7: star, Ahasuerus\' queen who delivered Isr
column9: Of Persian derivation; Ester, the Jewish heroine -- Esther.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6086) ets; a tree or wood -- timber, wood. see HEBREW (H6086) ets

column8: also, although, and furthermore, yet, but, even, how much less more, rather than,
column9: A primitive particle; meaning accession (used as an adverb or conjunction); also or yea; adversatively though -- also, + although, and (furthermore, yet), but, even, + how much less (more, rather than), moreover, with, yea.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H637) 'aph -- also. see HEBREW (H637) 'aph

column8: angry, before, countenance, face, forbearing, forehead, longsuffering, nose,
column9: From (H599) 'anaph; properly, the nose or nostril; hence, the face, and occasionally a person; also (from the rapid breathing in passion) ire -- anger(-gry), + before, countenance, face, + forebearing, forehead, + (long-)suffering, nose, nostril, snout, X worthy, wrath. see HEBREW (H599) 'anaph
A primitive root (rather a denominative from (H646) 'ephowd); to gird on (the ephod) -- bind, gird. see HEBREW (H646) 'ephowd
The same as (H646) 'ephowd shortened; Ephod, an Israelite -- Ephod. see HEBREW (H646) 'ephowd
Feminine of (H646) 'ephowd; a girding on (of the ephod); hence, generally, a plating (of metal) -- ephod, ornament. see HEBREW (H646) 'ephowd
Apparently of foreign derivation; a pavilion or palace-tent -- palace.
A primitive root; to cook, especially to bake -- bake(-r, (-meats)).
Or hephowe {ay-fo'}; from (H6311) poh; strictly a demonstrative particle, here; but used of time, now or then -- here, now, where? see HEBREW (H6311) poh
Rarely oephod {ay-fode'}; probably of foreign derivation; a girdle; specifically the ephod or high-priest's shoulder- piece; also generally, an image -- ephod.
Perhaps from (H6315) puwach; breeze; Aphiach, an Israelite -- Aphiah. see HEBREW (H6315) puwach
From the same as (H651) 'aphel (in the sense of weakness); unripe -- not grown up. see HEBREW (H651) 'aphel
Dual of (H639) 'aph; two nostrils; Appajim, an Israelite -- Appaim. see HEBREW (H639) 'aph

column8: brook, channel, mighty, river, scale, stream, strong piece
column9: From (H622) 'acaph; properly, containing, i.e. A tube; also a bed or valley of a stream; also a strong thing or a hero -- brook, channel, mighty, river, + scale, stream, strong piece. see HEBREW (H622) 'acaph
From an unused root meaning to set as the sun; dusky -- very dark.
From the same as (H651) 'aphel; dusk -- darkness, obscurity, privily. see HEBREW (H651) 'aphel
Feminine of (H651) 'aphel; duskiness, figuratively, misfortune; concrete, concealment -- dark, darkness, gloominess, X thick. see HEBREW (H651) 'aphel
From (H6419) palal; judge; Ephlal, an Israelite -- Ephlal. see HEBREW (H6419) palal
From an unused root meaning to revolve; a turn, i.e. A season -- + fitly.

column7: to cease, fail, come to an end
column8: be clean gone at an end, brought to nothing, fail
column9: A primitive root; to disappear, i.e. Cease -- be clean gone (at an end, brought to nought), fail.

column8: ankle, but only, end, howbeit, less than nothing, nevertheless where, no, none beside,
column9: From (H656) 'aphec; cessation, i.e. An end (especially of the earth); often used adverb, no further; also (like (H6466) pa'al) the ankle (in the dual), as being the extremity of the leg or foot -- ankle, but (only), end, howbeit, less than nothing, nevertheless (where), no, none (beside), not (any, -withstanding), thing of nought, save(-ing), there, uttermost part, want, without (cause). see HEBREW (H656) 'aphec see HEBREW (H6466) pa'al

column7: the two extremities (i.e. the soles of the feet or the ankles)
column9: From (H657) 'ephec and the plural of (H1818) dam; boundary of blood-drops; Ephes-Dammim, a place in Palestine -- Ephes- dammim. see HEBREW (H657) 'ephec see HEBREW (H1818) dam
From an unused root probably meaning to breathe; properly, a breath, i.e. Nothing -- of nought.
From (H659) epha' (in the sense of hissing); an asp or other venomous serpent -- viper. see HEBREW (H659) epha'
A primitive root; to surround -- compass.
A primitive root; to contain, i.e. (reflex.) Abstain -- force (oneself), restrain.

column7: perhaps "fortress", the name of several places in Palestine
column9: Or raphiyq {af-eek'}; from (H662) 'aphaq (in the sense of strength); fortress; Aphek (or Aphik), the name of three places in Palestine -- Aphek, Aphik. see HEBREW (H662) 'aphaq
Feminine of (H663) 'Apheq; fortress; Aphekah, a place in Palestine -- Aphekah. see HEBREW (H663) 'Apheq
From an unused root meaning to bestrew; ashes -- ashes.
From the same as (H665) 'epher (in the sense of covering); a turban -- ashes. see HEBREW (H665) 'epher
From (H6524) parach (in the sense of bursting the shell); the brood of a bird -- young (one). see HEBREW (H6524) parach
Probably of Egyptian derivation; a palanquin -- chariot.

column7: a son of Joseph, also his desc. and their territory
column9: Dual of masculine form of (H672) 'Ephraath; double fruit; Ephrajim, a son of Joseph; also the tribe descended from him, and its territory -- Ephraim, Ephraimites. see HEBREW (H672) 'Ephraath
(Aramaic) of foreign origin (only in the plural); an Apherasite or inhabitant of an unknown region of Assyria -- Apharsite.
(Aramaic) or fapharcathkay (Aramaic) {af-ar-sath-kah'ee}; of foreign origin (only in the plural); an Apharsekite or Apharsathkite, an unknown Assyrian tribe -- Apharsachites, Apharasthchites.

column4: proper name; proper name, of a location; proper name, feminine
column7: an Israelite woman, also the name of several places in Palestine
column9: Or mephrathah {ef-raw'-thaw}; from (H6509) parah; fruitfulness; Ephrath, another name for Bethlehem; once (Psa. 132:6) perhaps for Ephraim; also of an Israelitish woman -- Ephrath, Ephratah. see HEBREW (H6509) parah

column7: a descendant of Ephraim, also an inhabitant of Ephrath
column9: Patrial form (H672) 'Ephraath; an Ephrathite or an Ephraimite -- Ephraimite, Ephrathite. see HEBREW (H672) 'Ephraath
(Aramaic) of Persian origin; revenue; others at the last -- revenue.
Or metsbon {ets-bone'}; of uncertain derivation; Etsbon, the name of two Israelites -- Ezbon.
From the same as (H6648) tseba' (in the sense of grasping); something to sieze with, i.e. A finger; by analogy, a toe -- finger, toe. see HEBREW (H6648) tseba'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H676) etsba' -- finger, toe. see HEBREW (H676) etsba'
From (H680) 'atsal (in its secondary sense of separation); an extremity (Isa. 41:9), also a noble -- chief man, noble. see HEBREW (H680) 'atsal
From (H680) 'atsal (in its primary sense of uniting); a joint of the hand (i.e. Knuckle); also (according to some) a party-wall (Ezek. 41:8) -- (arm) hole, great. see HEBREW (H680) 'atsal

column7: to lay aside, reserve, withdraw, withhold
column9: A primitive root; properly, to join; used only as a denominative from (H681) 'etsel; to separate; hence, to select, refuse, contract -- keep, reserve, straiten, take. see HEBREW (H681) 'etsel

column8: at, hard by, beside, near unto, toward, with
column9: From (H680) 'atsal (in the sense of joining); a side; (as a preposition) near -- at, (hard) by, (from) (beside), near (unto), toward, with. See also (H1018) Beyth ha-'etsel. see HEBREW (H680) 'atsal see HEBREW (H1018) Beyth ha-'etsel
From (H680) 'atsal; noble; Atsel, the name of an Israelite, and of a place in Palestine -- Azal, Azel. see HEBREW (H680) 'atsal
From (H680) 'atsal and (H3050) Yahh prolonged; Jah has reserved; Atsaljah, an Israelite -- Azaliah. see HEBREW (H680) 'atsal see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From an unused root probably meaning to be strong; strength (i.e. Strong); Otsem, the name of two Israelites -- Ozem.
A variation from (H6807) ts'adah; properly, a step- chain; by analogy, a bracelet -- bracelet, chain. see HEBREW (H6807) ts'adah

column8: lay up in store, make treasurer
column9: A primitive root; to store up -- (lay up in) store, + (make) treasure(-r).

column7: treasure, a chief of the Horites
column9: From (H686) 'atsar; treasure; Etser, an Idumaean -- Ezer. see HEBREW (H686) 'atsar
From (H6916) qiddah; burning, i.e. A carbuncle or other fiery gem -- carbuncle. see HEBREW (H6916) qiddah
Probably from (H602) 'anaq; slender, i.e. The ibex -- wild goat. see HEBREW (H602) 'anaq
Probably for (H738) 'ariy; lion; Ara, an Israelite -- Ara. see HEBREW (H738) 'ariy
Probably for (H739) 'ariy'el; a hero (collectively) -- valiant one. see HEBREW (H739) 'ariy'el

column7: a son of Gad, also his desc
column9: From (H691) 'er'el; heroic; Areli (or an Arelite, collectively), an Israelite and his descendants -- Areli, Arelites. see HEBREW (H691) 'er'el

column8: lie in ambush, lay lie in wait
column9: A primitive root; to lurk -- (lie in) ambush(-ment), lay (lie in) wait.
From (H693) 'arab; ambush; Arab, a place in Palestine -- Arab. see HEBREW (H693) 'arab

column7: a lying in wait, a covert, lair
column9: From (H693) 'arab; ambuscade -- den, lie in wait. see HEBREW (H693) 'arab
The same as (H695) 'ereb -- wait. see HEBREW (H695) 'ereb
From (H7235) rabah; a locust (from its rapid increase) -- grasshopper, locust. see HEBREW (H7235) rabah
Feminine of (H696) 'oreb (only in the plural); ambuscades -- spoils. see HEBREW (H696) 'oreb

Feminine participle passive of (H693) 'arab (as if for lurking); a lattice; (by implication) a window, dove-cot (because of the pigeon-holes), chimney (with its apertures for smoke), sluice (with openings for water) -- chimney, window. see HEBREW (H693) 'arab
Plural of (H699) 'arubbah; Arubboth, a place in Palestine -- Aruboth. see HEBREW (H699) 'arubbah
Patrial from (H694) 'Arab; an Arbite or native of Arab -- Arbite. see HEBREW (H694) 'Arab

column4: noun masculine; feminine; masculine; noun feminine; feminine; feminine; noun masculine; masculine
column9: Masculine oarbaah {ar-baw-aw'}; from (H7251) raba'; four -- four. see HEBREW (H7251) raba'

column4: noun masculine and feminine; feminine plural noun; noun feminine singular; feminine plural noun; feminine; masculine plural noun; masculine plural noun
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H702) arba' -- four. see HEBREW (H702) arba'
The same as (H702) arba'; Arba, one of the Anakim -- Arba. see HEBREW (H702) arba'
Multiple of (H702) arba'; forty -- -forty. see HEBREW (H702) arba'
Dual of (H702) arba'; fourfold -- fourfold. see HEBREW (H702) arba'
A primitive root; to plait or weave -- weaver(-r).
From (H707) 'arag; a weaving; a braid; also a shuttle -- beam, weaver's shuttle. see HEBREW (H707) 'arag
From the same as (H7263) regeb; stony; Argob, a district of Palestine -- Argob. see HEBREW (H7263) regeb
A variation for (H713) 'argaman; purple -- purple. see HEBREW (H713) 'argaman
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H710) 'argvan -- purple. see HEBREW (H710) 'argvan
Perhaps from (H7264) ragaz (in the sense of being suspended), a box (as a pannier) -- coffer. see HEBREW (H7264) ragaz
Of foreign origin; purple (the color or the dyed stuff) -- purple.

column8: Ard, the name of two Israelites
column9: From an unused root probably meaning to wander; fugitive; Ard, the name of two Israelites -- Ard.
From the same as (H714) Ard; roaming; Ardon, an Israelite -- Ardon. see HEBREW (H714) Ard
Patronymic from (H714) Ard; an Ardite (collectively) or descendant of Ard -- Ardites. see HEBREW (H714) Ard
A primitive root; to pluck -- gather, pluck.
(Aramaic) probably akin to (H431) 'aluw; lo! -- behold,lo. see HEBREW (H431) 'aluw
Probably from (H7300) ruwd; a refuge for the roving; Arvad, an island-city of Palestine -- Arvad. see HEBREW (H7300) ruwd
An orthographical variation of (H719) 'Arvad; fugitive; Arod, an Israelite -- Arod. see HEBREW (H719) 'Arvad
Patrial from (H719) 'Arvad; an Arvadite or citizen of Arvad -- Arvadite. see HEBREW (H719) 'Arvad

column7: a son of Gad, also descendant of Arod
column9: Patronymic from (H721) 'Arvadiy; an Arodite or descendant of Arod -- Arodi, Arodites. see HEBREW (H721) 'Arvadiy

column4: particle of relation; connecting link; conjunction; adverb; conjunction; adverb; conjunction; conjunction; relative particle; pronoun; conjunction
column8: after, alike, as soon as, because, every, for, forasmuch, from whence,

From (H874) ba'ar; a pit; especially a well -- pit, well. see HEBREW (H874) ba'ar

column7: well, a place in the desert, also one in Palestine
column9: The same as (H875) 'er; Beer, a place in the Desert, also one in Palestine -- Beer. see HEBREW (H875) 'er
From (H874) ba'ar; a cistern -- cistern. see HEBREW (H874) ba'ar
From (H875) 'er; a well; Beera, an Israelite -- Beera. see HEBREW (H875) 'er

column7: well of heroes, a city of Moab
column9: From (H875) 'er and the plural of (H410) 'el; well of heroes; Beer-Elim, a place in the Desert -- Beer-elim. see HEBREW (H875) 'er see HEBREW (H410) 'el
The same as (H878) b'era'; Beerah, an Israelite -- Beerah. see HEBREW (H878) b'era'
Feminine plural of (H875) 'er; wells; Beeroth, a place in Palestine -- Beeroth. see HEBREW (H875) 'er

column7: my well, the name of a Hittite, also of Hosea\'s father
column9: From (H875) 'er; fountained; Beeri, the name of a Hittite and of an Israelite -- Beeri. see HEBREW (H875) 'er

column7: well of the living One that sees me, a place in the desert
column9: From (H875) 'er and (H2416) chay (with prefix) and (H7203) ro'eh; well of a living (One) my Seer; Beer-Lachai-Roi, a place in the Desert -- Beer-lahai-roi. see HEBREW (H875) 'er see HEBREW (H2416) chay see HEBREW (H7203) ro'eh

column7: well of seven, a place in the Negev
column9: From (H875) 'er and (H7651) sheba' (in the sense of (H7650) shaba'); well of an oath; Beer-Sheba, a place in Palestine -- Beer-shebah. see HEBREW (H875) 'er see HEBREW (H7651) sheba' see HEBREW (H7650) shaba'

column7: wells of (the) sons of Jaakan, a place in the desert
column8: Beeroth of the children of Jaakan
column9: From the feminine plural of (H875) 'er, and the plural contraction of (H1121) ben, and (H3292) Ya'aqan; wells of (the) sons of Jaakan; Beeroth-Bene-Jaakan, a place in the Desert -- Beeroth of the children of Jaakan. see HEBREW (H875) 'er see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H3292) Ya'aqan
Patrial from (H881) b'erowth; a Beerothite or inhabitant of Beeroth -- Beerothite. see HEBREW (H881) b'erowth

column7: to have a bad smell, to stink
column8: make to be abhorred, loathsome, odious, cause a, make to stink, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to smell bad; figuratively, to be offensive morally -- (make to) be abhorred (had in abomination, loathsome, odious), (cause a, make to) stink(-ing savour), X utterly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H887) ba'ash -- displease. see HEBREW (H887) ba'ash
From (H877) bo'r; a stench -- stink. see HEBREW (H877) bo'r
Feminine of (H889) b'osh; stink-weed or any other noxious or useless plant -- cockle. see HEBREW (H889) b'osh
Plural of (H889) b'osh; poison-berries -- wild grapes. see HEBREW (H889) b'osh
Feminine active participle of an unused root meaning to hollow out; something hollowed (as a gate), i.e. Pupil of the eye -- apple (of the eye).
Probably of foreign origin; Bebai, an Israelite -- Bebai.

column7: an E. Mediterranean empire and its capital city
column9: From (H1101) balal; confusion; Babel (i.e. Babylon), including Babylonia and the Babylonian empire -- Babel, Babylon. see HEBREW (H1101) balal

column7: an E. Mediterranean empire and its capital city
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H894) Babel -- Babylon. see HEBREW (H894) Babel
(Aramaic) patrial from (H895) Babel; a Babylonian -- Babylonia. see HEBREW (H895) Babel
A Persian word; food -- spoil (from the margin for (H957) baz.) see HEBREW (H957) baz

column8: deal deceitfully, treacherously, unfaithfully, offend, transgressor, depart
column9: A primitive root; to cover (with a garment); figuratively, to act covertly; by implication, to pillage -- deal deceitfully (treacherously, unfaithfully), offend, transgress(-or), (depart), treacherous (dealer, -ly, man), unfaithful(-ly, man), X very.

column8: apparel, clothes, garment, lap, rag, raiment, robe, very treacherously,
column9: From (H898) bagad; a covering, i.e. Clothing; also treachery or pillage -- apparel, cloth(-es, ing), garment, lap, rag, raiment, robe, X very (treacherously), vesture, wardrobe. see HEBREW (H898) bagad
Feminine plural active participle of (H898) bagad; treacheries -- treacherous. see HEBREW (H898) bagad
From (H898) bagad; treacherous -- treacherous. see HEBREW (H898) bagad
Probably of foreign origin; Bigvai, an Israelite -- Bigvai.
Of Persian derivation; Bigtha, a eunuch of Xerxes -- Bigtha.
Or Bigthanad {big-thaw'naw}; of similar derivation to (H903) Bigtha'; Bigthan or Bigthana, a eunuch of Xerxes -- Bigthan, Bigthana. see HEBREW (H903) Bigtha'

column8: alone, apart, bar, besides, branch, by self, of each alike, except,
column9: From (H909) badad; properly, separation; by implication, a part of the body, branch of a tree, bar for carrying; figuratively, chief of a city; especially (with prepositional prefix) as an adverb, apart, only, besides -- alone, apart, bar, besides, branch, by self, of each alike, except, only, part, staff, strength. see HEBREW (H909) badad
Perhaps from (H909) badad (in the sense of divided fibres); flaxen thread or yarn; hence, a linen garment -- linen. see HEBREW (H909) badad
From (H908) bada'; a brag or lie; also a liar -- liar, lie. see HEBREW (H908) bada'
A primitive root; (figuratively) to invent -- devise, feign.
A primitive root; to divide, i.e. (reflex.) Be solitary -- alone.
From (H909) badad; separate; adverb, separately -- alone, desolate, only, solitary. see HEBREW (H909) badad
From (H909) badad; separation; Bedad, an Edomite -- Bedad. see HEBREW (H909) badad
Probably a shortened form (H5662) Obadyah; servant of Jehovah; Bedejah, an Israelite -- Bedeiah. see HEBREW (H5662) Obadyah
From (H914) badal; alloy (because removed by smelting); by analogy, tin -- + plummet, tin. see HEBREW (H914) badal

column8: make, put difference, divide asunder, make separate
column9: A primitive root; to divide (in variation senses literally or figuratively, separate, distinguish, differ, select, etc.) -- (make, put) difference, divide (asunder), (make) separate (self, -ation), sever (out), X utterly.
From (H914) badal; a part -- piece. see HEBREW (H914) badal
Probably from (H914) badal; something in pieces, i.e. Bdellium, a (fragrant) gum (perhaps amber); others a pearl -- bdellium. see HEBREW (H914) badal
Probably shortened for (H5658) Abdown; servile; Bedan, the name of two Israelites -- Bedan. see HEBREW (H5658) Abdown
A primitive root; to gap open; used only as a denominative from (H919) bedeq; to mend a breach -- repair. see HEBREW (H919) bedeq
From (H918) badaq; a gap or leak (in a building or a ship) -- breach, + calker. see HEBREW (H918) badaq
Probably from (H1856) daqar with a prepositional prefix; by stabbing, i.e. Assassin; Bidkar, an Israelite -- Bidkar. see HEBREW (H1856) daqar
(Aramaic) corresponding (by transposition) to (H6504) parad; to scatter -- scatter. see HEBREW (H6504) parad
From an unused root (meaning to be empty); a vacuity, i.e. (superficially) an undistinguishable ruin -- emptiness, void.
From an unused root (probably meaning to glisten); white marble or perhaps alabaster -- red (marble).
(Aramaic) from (H927) bhal; a hurry; only adverb, hastily -- in haste. see HEBREW (H927) bhal
From an unused root (meaning to be bright); shining -- bright.

column8: be make affrighted afraid, amazed, dismayed, rash, thrust out,
column9: A primitive root; to tremble inwardly (or palpitate), i.e. (figuratively) be (causative, make) (suddenly) alarmed or agitated; by implication to hasten anxiously -- be (make) affrighted (afraid, amazed, dismayed, rash), (be, get, make) haste(-n, -y, -ily), (give) speedy(-ily), thrust out, trouble, vex.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H926) bahal; to terrify, hasten -- in haste, trouble. see HEBREW (H926) bahal
From (H926) bahal; panic, destruction -- terror, trouble. see HEBREW (H926) bahal
From an unused root (probably meaning to be mute); properly, a dumb beast; especially any large quadruped or animal (often collective) -- beast, cattle.
In form a plural or (H929) bhemah, but really a singular of Egyptian derivation; a water-ox, i.e. The hippopotamus or Nile- horse -- Behemoth. see HEBREW (H929) bhemah
From an unused root apparently meaning to be thick; the thumb of the hand or great toe of the foot -- thumb, great toe.
An orthographical variation of (H931) bohen; thumb, Bohan, an Israelite -- Bohan. see HEBREW (H931) bohen
From an unused root meaning to be pale; white scurf -- freckled spot.
Feminine active participle of the same as (H925) bahiyr; a whitish spot on the skin -- bright spot. see HEBREW (H925) bahiyr

column7: to come in, come, go in, go
column8: abide, apply, attain, be, befall, besiege, bring forth, in,
column9: A primitive root; to go or come (in a wide variety of applications) -- abide, apply, attain, X be, befall, + besiege, bring (forth, in, into, to pass), call, carry, X certainly, (cause, let, thing for) to come (against, in, out, upon, to pass), depart, X doubtless again, + eat, + employ, (cause to) enter (in, into, -tering, -trance, -try), be fallen, fetch, + follow, get, give, go (down, in, to war), grant, + have, X indeed, (in-)vade, lead, lift (up), mention, pull in, put, resort, run (down), send, set, X (well) stricken (in age), X surely, take (in), way.
A primitive root; to disrespect -- contemn, despise, X utterly.
From (H936) buwz; disrespect -- contempt(-uously), despised, shamed. see HEBREW (H936) buwz
The same as (H937) buwz; Buz, the name of a son of Nahor, and of an Israelite -- Buz. see HEBREW (H937) buwz
Feminine passive participle of (H936) buwz; something scorned; an object of contempt -- despised. see HEBREW (H936) buwz
Patronymic from (H938) Buwz; a Buzite or descendant of Buz -- Buzite. see HEBREW (H938) Buwz
The same as (H940) Buwziy; Buzi, an Israelite -- Buzi. see HEBREW (H940) Buwziy
Probably of Persian origin; Bavvai, an Israelite -- Bavai.
A primitive root; to involve (literally or figuratively) -- be entangled, (perplexed).
For (H2981) ybuwl; produce (of the earth, etc.) -- food, stock. see HEBREW (H2981) ybuwl

column7: the eighth month of the Jewish calendar
column9: The same as (H944) buwl (in the sense of rain); Bul, the eighth Hebrew month -- Bul. see HEBREW (H944) buwl
From (H995) biyn; discretion; Bunah, an Israelite -- Bunah. see HEBREW (H995) biyn

column8: loath, tread down, under foot, be polluted
column9: A primitive root; to trample (literally or figuratively) -- loath, tread (down, under (foot)), be polluted.
From an unused root (of the same form) meaning to bleach, i.e. (intransitive) be white; probably cotton (of some sort) -- fine (white) linen.
From the same as (H948) buwts; shining; Botsets, a rock near Michmash -- Bozez. see HEBREW (H948) buwts
Feminine passive participle of an unused root (meaning to be hollow); emptiness (as adjective) -- empty.
Properly, active participle from (H1239) baqar as denominative from (H1241) baqar; a cattle-tender -- herdman. see HEBREW (H1239) baqar see HEBREW (H1241) baqar

column7: to make clear, clear up, explain
column9: A primitive root; to bore, i.e. (figuratively) examine -- declare.
From (H952) buwr (in the sense of (H877) bo'r); a pit hole (especially one used as a cistern or a prison) -- cistern, dungeon, fountain, pit, well. see HEBREW (H952) buwr see HEBREW (H877) bo'r

column8: make, bring to, cause, put to, with, ashamed, be put to confusion,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to pale, i.e. By implication to be ashamed; also (by implication) to be disappointed or delayed -- (be, make, bring to, cause, put to, with, a-)shamed(-d), be (put to) confounded(-fusion), become dry, delay, be long.
Feminine participle passive of (H954) buwsh; shame -- shame. see HEBREW (H954) buwsh
(Aramaic) apparent denominative from (H1005) bayith; to lodge over night -- pass the night. see HEBREW (H1005) bayith
From (H962) bazaz; plunder -- booty, prey, spoil(-ed). see HEBREW (H962) bazaz
A primitive root; probably to cleave -- spoil.

column8: despise, disdain, contemptible, think to scorn, vile person
column9: A primitive root; to disesteem -- despise, disdain, contemn(-ptible), + think to scorn, vile person.
From (H959) bazah; scorned -- despise. see HEBREW (H959) bazah
Feminine of (H957) baz; booty -- prey, spoil. see HEBREW (H957) baz

column8: catch, gather, take for a prey, robber, spoil, take away, spoil, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to plunder -- catch, gather, (take) for a prey, rob(-ber), spoil, take (away, spoil), X utterly.
From (H959) bazah -- disesteem -- contempt. see HEBREW (H959) bazah

column7: contempts of the LORD, a place near Beersheba
column9: From (H959) bazah and (H3050) Yahh; contempts of Jah; Bizjothjah, a place in Palestine -- Bizjothjah. see HEBREW (H959) bazah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From an unused root meaning to lighten; a flash of lightning -- flash of lightning.
From (H965) bazaq; lightning; Bezek, a place in Palestine -- Bezek. see HEBREW (H965) bazaq
A primitive root; to disperse -- scatter.
Of Persian origin; Biztha, a eunuch of Xerxes -- Biztha.
From (H974) bachan; an assayer or metals -- tower. see HEBREW (H974) bachan
Or bachur {baw-khoor'}; participle passive of (H977) bachar; properly, selected, i.e. A youth (often collective) -- (choice) young (man), chosen, X hole. see HEBREW (H977) bachar
Another form of (H975) bachan; a watch-tower of besiegers -- tower. see HEBREW (H975) bachan
From (H977) bachar; select -- choose, chosen one, elect. see HEBREW (H977) bachar
A primitive root; to loath -- abhor, get hastily (from the margin for (H926) bahal). see HEBREW (H926) bahal
A primitive root; to test (especially metals); generally and figuratively, to investigate -- examine, prove, tempt, try (trial).
From (H974) bachan (in the sense of keeping a look-out); a watch-tower -- tower. see HEBREW (H974) bachan
From (H974) bachan; trial -- tried. see HEBREW (H974) bachan

column8: acceptable, appoint, choose choice, excellent, join, be rather, require
column9: A primitive root; properly, to try, i.e. (by implication) select -- acceptable, appoint, choose (choice), excellent, join, be rather, require.
Patrial from (H980) Bachuriym (by transposition); a Bacharumite or inhabitant of Bachurim -- Baharumite. see HEBREW (H980) Bachuriym
Or bchuwrowth {bekh-oo-roth'}; feminine plural of (H970) bachuwr; also (masculine plural) bchuriym {bekh-oo-reem'}; youth (collectively and abstractly) -- young men, youth. see HEBREW (H970) bachuwr

column7: young men\'s village, a city in Benjamin
column9: Or Bachuwriym {bakh-oo-reem'}; masculine plural of (H970) bachuwr; young men; Bachurim, a place in Palestine -- Bahurim. see HEBREW (H970) bachuwr
Or batah {baw-taw'}; a primitive root; to babble; hence, to vociferate angrily -- pronounce, speak (unadvisedly).

column8: be bold confident, secure, sure, careless one, put confidence, make to hope, put,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to hie for refuge (but not so precipitately as (H2620) chacah); figuratively, to trust, be confident or sure -- be bold (confident, secure, sure), careless (one, woman), put confidence, (make to) hope, (put, make to) trust. see HEBREW (H2620) chacah

column8: assurance, boldly, without care, confidence, hope, safely secure, surely
column9: From (H982) batach; properly, a place of refuge; abstract, safety, both the fact (security) and the feeling (trust); often (adverb with or without preposition) safely -- assurance, boldly, (without) care(- less), confidence, hope, safe(-ly, -ty), secure, surely. see HEBREW (H982) batach
The same as (H983) betach; Betach, a place in Syria -- Betah. see HEBREW (H983) betach
Feminine of (H984) Betach; trust -- confidence. see HEBREW (H984) Betach
From (H982) batach; trust -- confidence, hope. see HEBREW (H982) batach
Feminine plural from (H982) batach; security -- secure. see HEBREW (H982) batach
A primitive root; to desist from labor -- cease.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H988) batel; to stop -- (cause, make to), cease, hinder. see HEBREW (H988) batel

column8: belly, body, as they be born, within, womb
column9: From an unused root probably meaning to be hollow; the belly, especially the womb; also the bosom or body of anything -- belly, body, + as they be born, + within, womb.
The same as (H990) beten; Beten. A place in Palestine -- Beten. see HEBREW (H990) beten
From (H990) beten; (only in plural) a pistachio-nut (from its form) -- nut. see HEBREW (H990) beten
Probably plural from (H992) boten; hollows: Betonim, a place in Palestine -- Betonim. see HEBREW (H992) boten

Perhaps from (H1158) ba'ah (in the sense of asking); properly, a request; used only adverbially (always with \"my Lord\"); Oh that!; with leave, or if it please -- alas, O, oh. see HEBREW (H1158) ba'ah

column8: attend, consider, be cunning, diligently, direct, discern, eloquent, feel,
column9: A primitive root; to separate mentally (or distinguish), i.e.(generally) understand -- attend, consider, be cunning, diligently, direct, discern, eloquent, feel, inform, instruct, have intelligence, know, look well to, mark, perceive, be prudent, regard, (can) skill(-full), teach, think, (cause, make to, get, give, have) understand(-ing), view, (deal) wise(-ly, man).

(sometimes in the plural masculine or feminine); properly, the constructive form of an otherwise unused noun from (H995) biyn; a distinction; but used only as a prep, between (repeated before each noun, often with other particles); also as a conjunction, either...or -- among, asunder, at, between (-twixt...and), + from (the widest), X in, out of, whether (it be...or), within. see HEBREW (H995) biyn
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H996) beyn -- among, between. see HEBREW (H996) beyn
From (H995) biyn; understanding -- knowledge, meaning, X perfectly, understanding, wisdom. see HEBREW (H995) biyn
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H998) biynah -- knowledge. see HEBREW (H998) biynah
From the same as (H948) buwts; an egg (from its whiteness) -- egg. see HEBREW (H948) buwts
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1002) biyrah; a palace -- palace. see HEBREW (H1002) biyrah
Of foreign origin; a castle or palace -- palace.
From (H1002) biyrah; a fortress -- castle. see HEBREW (H1002) biyrah

column8: court, door, dungeon, family, forth of, great as would contain, hangings,
column9: Probably from (H1129) banah abbreviated; a house (in the greatest variation of applications, especially family, etc.) -- court, daughter, door, + dungeon, family, + forth of, X great as would contain, hangings, home(born), (winter)house(-hold), inside(-ward), palace, place, + prison, + steward, + tablet, temple, web, + within(-out). see HEBREW (H1129) banah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1004) bayith -- house. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith
The same as (H1004) bayith; Bajith, a place in Palestine -- Bajith. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith
From (H1004) bayith and (H205) 'aven; house of vanity; Beth- Aven, a place in Palestine -- Beth-aven. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H205) 'aven

column7: house of God, a city in Ephraim, also a place in S. Judah
column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H410) 'el; house of God; Beth-El, a place in Palestine -- Beth-el. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: house of God\'s ambush, a place in Palestine
column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H695) 'ereb and (H410) 'el; house of God's ambush; Beth-Arbel, a place in Palestine -- Beth-Arbel. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H695) 'ereb see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: house of Baal of (the) habitation, a place East of the Jordan
column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H1168) Ba'al and (H4583) ma'own; house of Baal of (the) habitation of (apparently by transposition); or (shorter) Beyth M own {bayth me-own'}; house of habitation of (Baal); Beth- Baal-Meon, a place in Palestine -- Beth-baal-meon. Compare (H1186) Ba'al m'own and (H1194) b'on. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H4583) ma'own see HEBREW (H1186) Ba'al m'own see HEBREW (H1194) b'on

column7: house of a creative one, a place in Palestine
column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H1254) bara'; house of a creative one; Beth-Biri, a place in Palestine -- Beth-birei. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H1254) bara'

column7: place of ford, a place in Palestine
column9: Probably from (H1004) bayith and (H5679) abarah; house of (the) ford; Beth-Barah, a place in Palestine -- Beth-barah. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H5679) abarah

column7: place of a wall, a place in Judah
column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H1447) gader; house of (the) wall; Beth-Gader, a place in Palestine -- Beth-gader. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H1447) gader

column7: place of recompense, a place in Moab
column9: From (H1004) bayith and the passive participle of (H1576) gmuwl; house of (the) weaned; Beth-Gamul, a place East of the Jordan -- Beth- gamul. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H1576) gmuwl
From (H1004) bayith and the dual of (H1690) dbelah; house of (the) two figcakes; Beth-Diblathajim, a place East of the Jordan -- Beth-diblathaim. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H1690) dbelah

column7: house of Dagon, two places in Palestine
column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H1712) Dagown; house of Dagon; Beth-Dagon, the name of two places in Palestine -- Beth-dagon. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H1712) Dagown
Patrial from (H1008) Beyth-'El with the article interposed; a Beth-elite, or inhabitant of Bethel -- Bethelite. see HEBREW (H1008) Beyth-'El
From (H1004) bayith and (H681) 'etsel with the article interposed; house of the side; Beth-ha-Etsel, a place in Palestine -- Beth- ezel. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H681) 'etsel

column7: house of the Gilgal, a place in Palestine
column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H1537) Gilgal with the article interposed; house of Gilgal (or rolling); Beth-hag-Gilgal, a place in Palestine -- Beth-gilgal. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H1537) Gilgal

column7: place of the desert, a place East of the Jordan in Moab
column9: From (H1004) bayith and the plural of (H3451) yshiymah with the article interposed; house of the deserts; Beth-ha- Jeshimoth, a town East of the Jordan -- Beth-jeshimoth. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H3451) yshiymah

column7: vineyard place, a place in Judah
column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H3754) kerem with the article interposed; house of the vineyard; Beth-hak-Kerem, a place in Palestine -- Beth-haccerem. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H3754) kerem
Patrial from (H1035) Beyth Lechem with the article inserted; a Beth-lechemite, or native of Bethlechem -- Bethlehemite. see HEBREW (H1035) Beyth Lechem

column7: Beth-ham-Merchak, a place in Palestine -- place that was far off
column8: Beth-ham-Merchak, a place in Palestine -- place that was far off
column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H4801) merchaq with the article interposed; house of the breadth; Beth-ham-Merchak, a place in Palestine -- place that was far off. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H4801) merchaq

column7: place of chariots, a place in Simeon
column9: Or (shortened) Beyth Mar-kabowth {bayth mar-kaw-both'}; from (H1004) bayith and the plural of (H4818) merkabah (with or without the article interposed); place of (the) chariots; Beth-ham-Markaboth or Beth-Markaboth, a place in Palestine -- Beth-marcaboth. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H4818) merkabah

column7: valley house, a place on the border of Asher
column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H6010) emeq with the article interposed; house of the valley; Beth-ha-Emek, a place in Palestine -- Beth- emek. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H6010) emeq

column7: place of the depression, a place near the Dead Sea
column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H6160) arabah with the article interposed; house of the Desert; Beth-ha-Arabah, a place in Palestine -- Beth-arabah. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H6160) arabah

column7: house of the height, a place East of the Jordan

: from (H1004) bayith and (H6252) Ashtarowth; house of Ashtoreths; Beth-Ashtaroth, a place in Palestine -- house of Ashtaroth. Compare (H1203) b'eshtrah, (H6252) Ashtarowth. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H6252) Ashtarowth see HEBREW (H1203) b'eshtrah see HEBREW (H6252) Ashtarowth

column9: From (H1004) bayith and (H6465) p'owr; house of Peor; Beth- Peor, a place East of the Jordan -- Beth-peor. see HEBREW (H1004) bayith see HEBREW (H6465) p'owr

From (H1069) bakar; first-born; Bokeru, an Israelite -- Bocheru. see HEBREW (H1069) bakar

Patronymically from (H1071) Beker; a Bakrite (collectively) or descendants of Beker -- Bachrites. see HEBREW (H1071) Beker
From (H1086) balah; properly, a failure; by implication nothing; usually (adverb) not at all; also lest -- lest, neither, no, none (that...), not (any), nothing. see HEBREW (H1086) balah

(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1112) Belsha'tstsar -- Belshazzar. see HEBREW (H1112) Belsha'tstsar

column8: beside, but, continual, except, from, lest, neither,

From (H1129) banah; built up; Binnui, an Israelite -- Binnui. see HEBREW (H1129) banah

column7: son of Zoheth, a man of Judah
column9: From (H1121) ben and (H2105) Zowcheth; son of Zocheth; Ben- Zocheth, an Israelite -- Ben-zoketh. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H2105) Zowcheth

column9: From (H1121) ben and (H2354) Chuwr; son of Chur; Ben-Chur, an Israelite -- the son of Hur. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H2354) Chuwr

column9: From (H1121) ben and (H2428) chayil; son of might; Ben-Chail, an Israelite -- Ben-hail. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H2428) chayil

column9: From (H1121) ben and (H2605) Chanan; son of Chanan; Ben- Chanan, an Israelite -- Ben-hanan. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H2605) Chanan

column9: From (H1121) ben and (H2617) checed; son of kindness; Ben- Chesed, an Israelite -- the son of Hesed. see HEBREW (H1121) ben see HEBREW (H2617) checed
