Passive participle of (H1580) gamal; rewarded; Gamul, an Israelite -- Gamul. See also (H1014) Beyth Gamuwl. see HEBREW (H1580) gamal see HEBREW (H1014) Beyth Gamuwl
Feminine of (H1576) gmuwl; meaning the same -- deed, recompense, such a reward. see HEBREW (H1576) gmuwl
Of uncertain derivation; Gimzo, a place in Palestine -- Gimzo.

column7: to deal fully or adequately with, deal out to, wean, ripen
column8: bestow on, deal bountifully, do good, recompense, requite, reward, ripen, serve,
column9: A primitive root; to treat a person (well or ill), i.e. Benefit or requite; by implication (of toil), to ripen, i.e. (specifically) to wean -- bestow on, deal bountifully, do (good), recompense, requite, reward, ripen, + serve, mean, yield.
Apparently from (H1580) gamal (in the sense of labor or burden-bearing); a camel -- camel. see HEBREW (H1580) gamal
Probably from (H1581) gamal; camel-driver; Gemalli, an Israelite -- Gemalli. see HEBREW (H1581) gamal
From (H1580) gamal and (H410) 'el; reward of God; Gamliel, an Israelite -- Gamaliel. see HEBREW (H1580) gamal see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: to end, come to an end, complete
column8: cease, come to an end, fail, perfect, perform
column9: A primitive root; to end (in the sense of completion or failure) -- cease, come to an end, fail, perfect, perform.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1584) gamar -- perfect. see HEBREW (H1584) gamar

column7: a son of Japheth, also his desc., also the wife of Hosea
column9: From (H1584) gamar; completion; Gomer, the name of a son of Japheth and of his descendants; also of a Hebrewess -- Gomer. see HEBREW (H1584) gamar
Or Gmaryahuw {ghem-ar-yaw'-hoo}; from (H1584) gamar and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has perfected; Gemarjah, the name of two Israelites -- Gemariah. see HEBREW (H1584) gamar see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column4: noun masculine; feminine; proper name, of a location
column9: From (H1598) ganan; a garden (as fenced) -- garden. see HEBREW (H1598) ganan

column8: carry away, indeed, secretly bring, steal away, get by stealth
column9: A primitive root; to thieve (literally or figuratively); by implication, to deceive -- carry away, X indeed, secretly bring, steal (away), get by stealth.
From (H1589) ganab; a stealer -- thief. see HEBREW (H1589) ganab
From (H1589) ganab; stealing, i.e. (concretely) something stolen -- theft. see HEBREW (H1589) ganab
From (H1589) ganab; theft; Genubath, an Edomitish prince -- Genubath. see HEBREW (H1589) ganab
Feminine of (H1588) gan; a garden -- garden. see HEBREW (H1588) gan
Another form for (H1593) gannah -- garden. see HEBREW (H1593) gannah
From an unused root meaning to store; treasure; by implication, a coffer -- chest, treasury.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1595) genez; treasure -- treasure. see HEBREW (H1595) genez
Prolonged from (H1595) genez; a treasury -- treasury. see HEBREW (H1595) genez
A primitive root; to hedge about, i.e. (generally) protect -- defend.
Or Ginnthow {ghin-neth-o'}; from (H1598) ganan; gardener; Ginnethon or Ginnetho, an Israelite -- Ginnetho, Ginnethon. see HEBREW (H1598) ganan
A primitive root; to bellow (as cattle) -- low.
Feminine active participle of (H1600) ga'ah; lowing; Goah, a place near Jerusalem -- Goath. see HEBREW (H1600) ga'ah

column8: abhor, fail, loathe, vilely cast away
column9: A primitive root; to detest; by implication, to reject -- abhor, fail, lothe, vilely cast away.
From (H1602) ga'al; loathing; Gaal, an Israelite -- Gaal. see HEBREW (H1602) ga'al
From (H1602) ga'al; abhorrence -- loathing. see HEBREW (H1602) ga'al
A primitive root; to chide -- corrupt, rebuke, reprove.
From (H1605) ga'ar; a chiding -- rebuke(-ing), reproof. see HEBREW (H1605) ga'ar
A primitive root to agitate violently -- move, shake, toss, trouble.
From (H1607) ga'ash; a quaking; Gaash, a hill in Palestine -- Gaash. see HEBREW (H1607) ga'ash
Of uncertain derivation; Gatam, an Edomite -- Gatam.
From an unused root meaning to arch; the back; by extensive the body or self -- + highest places, himself.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1610) gaph; a wing -- wing. see HEBREW (H1610) gaph
From an unused root meaning to bend; a vine (as twining), especially the grape -- vine, tree.

column7: gopher (a kind of tree or wood)
column9: From an unused root, probably meaning to house in; a kind of tree or wood (as used for building), apparently the cypress -- gopher.
Probably feminine of (H1613) gopher; properly, cypress- resin; by analogy, sulphur (as equally inflammable) -- brimstone. see HEBREW (H1613) gopher
Perhaps from (H3564) kuwr; lime (from being burned in a kiln) -- chalk(-stone). see HEBREW (H3564) kuwr
Or (fully) geyr (gare); from (H1481) guwr; properly, a guest; by implication, a foreigner -- alien, sojourner, stranger. see HEBREW (H1481) guwr

column7: the name of several Israelites, also a Benjamite family
column9: Perhaps from (H1626) gerah; a grain; Gera, the name of six Israelites -- Gera. see HEBREW (H1626) gerah
From an unused root meaning to scratch; scurf (from itching) -- scab, scurvy.

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, of a location
column7: one of David\'s heroes, also a hill near Jer
column9: From the same as (H1618) garab; scabby; Gareb, the name of an Israelite, also of a hill near Jerusalem -- Gareb. see HEBREW (H1618) garab
By reduplication from (H1641) garar; a berry (as if a pellet of rumination) -- berry. see HEBREW (H1641) garar
Feminine plural from (H1641) garar; the throat (as used in rumination) -- neck. see HEBREW (H1641) garar
Patrial from an unused name (of uncertain derivation); a Girgashite, one of the native tribes of Canaan -- Girgashite, Girgasite.
A primitive root; to abrade -- scrape.

column7: to stir up (strife), engage in strife
column9: A primitive root; properly, to grate, i.e. (figuratively) to anger -- contend, meddle, stir up, strive.
From (H1641) garar; the cud (as scraping the throat) -- cud. see HEBREW (H1641) garar

From (H1641) garar (as in (H1625) gerah); properly, (like (H1620) gargar) a kernel (round as if scraped), i.e. A gerah or small weight (and coin) -- gerah. see HEBREW (H1641) garar see HEBREW (H1625) gerah see HEBREW (H1620) gargar

Or (shortened) garon {gaw-rone'}; from (H1641) garar; the throat (compare (H1621) gargrowth) (as roughened by swallowing) -- X aloud, mouth, neck, throat. see HEBREW (H1641) garar see HEBREW (H1621) gargrowth

column7: lodging place, a place near Bethlehem
column9: From (H1481) guwr; a (temporary) residence -- habitation. see HEBREW (H1481) guwr
A primitive root; to cut off -- cut off.
Plural of an unused noun from (H1629) garaz (compare (H1511) Gizriy), cut up (i.e. Rocky); Gerizim, a mountain of Palestine -- Gerizim. see HEBREW (H1629) garaz see HEBREW (H1511) Gizriy
From (H1629) garaz; an axe -- ax. see HEBREW (H1629) garaz
From the same as (H1486) gowral; harsh -- man of great (as in the margin which reads (H1419) gadowl). see HEBREW (H1486) gowral see HEBREW (H1419) gadowl

A primitive root; to be spare or skeleton-like; used only as a denominative from (H1634) gerem; (causative) to bone, i.e. Denude (by extensive, craunch) the bones -- gnaw the bones, break. see HEBREW (H1634) gerem
From (H1633) garam; a bone (as the skeleton of the body); hence, self, i.e. (figuratively) very -- bone, strong, top. see HEBREW (H1633) garam
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1634) gerem; a bone -- bone. see HEBREW (H1634) gerem

column7: bony, a name applied to Keilah
column9: From (H1634) gerem; bony, i.e. Strong -- Garmite. see HEBREW (H1634) gerem
From an unused root meaning to smooth; a threshing- floor (as made even); by analogy, any open area -- (barn, corn, threshing-)floor, (threshing-, void) place.
A primitive root; to crush; also (intransitively and figuratively) to dissolve -- break.

column8: abate, clip, diminish, do take away, keep back, restrain, make small, withdraw
column9: A primitive root; to scrape off; by implication, to shave, remove, lessen, withhold -- abate, clip, (di-)minish, do (take) away, keep back, restrain, make small, withdraw.
A primitive root; to bear off violently -- sweep away.
A primitive root; to drag off roughly; by implication, to bring up the cud (i.e. Ruminate); by analogy, to saw -- catch, chew, X continuing, destroy, saw.
Probably from (H1641) garar; a rolling country; Gerar, a Philistine city -- Gerar. see HEBREW (H1641) garar
From an unused root meaning to husk; a kernel (collectively), i.e. Grain -- beaten corn.

column8: cast up out, divorced woman, drive away forth, out, expel, trouble, thrust out
column9: A primitive root; to drive out from a possession; especially to expatriate or divorce -- cast up (out), divorced (woman), drive away (forth, out), expel, X surely put away, trouble, thrust out.

column7: a thing thrust, a thing put forth
column9: From (H1644) garash; produce (as if expelled) -- put forth. see HEBREW (H1644) garash
Feminine passive participle of (H1644) garash; (abstractly) dispossession -- exaction. see HEBREW (H1644) garash
For (H1648) Gershown; Gereshom, the name of four Israelites -- Gershom. see HEBREW (H1648) Gershown
Or Gershowm {gay-resh-ome'}; from (H1644) garash; a refugee; Gereshon or Gereshom, an Israelite -- Gershon, Gershom. see HEBREW (H1644) garash
Patronymically from (H1648) Gershown; a Gereshonite or descendant of Gereshon -- Gershonite, sons of Gershon. see HEBREW (H1648) Gershown

column7: a territory East of the upper Jordan, also inhab. of Geshur
column9: From an unused root (meaning to join); bridge; Geshur, a district of Syria -- Geshur, Geshurite.

column7: inhab. of Geshur, also a people South of Philistia
column9: Patrial from (H1650) Gshuwr; a Geshurite (also collectively) or inhabitants of Geshur -- Geshuri, Geshurites. see HEBREW (H1650) Gshuwr
A primitive root; to shower violently -- (cause to) rain.
From (H1652) gasham; a shower -- rain, shower. see HEBREW (H1652) gasham
Or (prolonged) Gashmuw {gash-moo'}; the same as (H1653) geshem; Geshem or Gashmu, an Arabian -- Geshem, Gashmu. see HEBREW (H1653) geshem
(Aramaic) apparently the same as (H1653) geshem; used in a peculiar sense, the body (probably for the (figuratively) idea of a hard rain) -- body. see HEBREW (H1653) geshem
From (H1652) gasham; equivalent to (H1653) geshem -- rained upon. see HEBREW (H1652) gasham see HEBREW (H1653) geshem

column7: a district in Egypt, also a city in S. Judah
column9: Probably of Egyptian origin; Goshen, the residence of the Israelites in Egypt; also a place in Palestine -- Goshen.
Of uncertain derivation; Gishpa, an Israelite -- Gispa.

column7: to feel with the hand, feel, stroke
column9: A primitive root; apparently to feel about -- grope.
Probably from (H5059) nagan (in the sense of treading out grapes); a wine-press (or vat for holding the grapes in pressing them) -- (wine-)press (fat). see HEBREW (H5059) nagan
The same as (H1660) gath; Gath, a Philistine city -- Gath. see HEBREW (H1660) gath

column7: wine press of digging, home of Jonah
column9: Or (abridged) Gittah-Chepher {ghit-taw-khay'-fer}; from (H1660) gath and (H2658) chaphar with the article inserted; wine- press of (the) well; Gath-Chepher, a place in Palestine -- Gath-kephr, Gittah-kephr. see HEBREW (H2658) chaphar
Patrial from (H1661) Gath; a Gittite or inhabitant of Gath -- Gittite. see HEBREW (H1661) Gath
Dual of (H1660) gath; double wine-press; Gittajim, a place in Palestine -- Gittaim. see HEBREW (H1660) gath

column7: a musical term of unc. meaning
column9: Feminine of (H1663) Gittiy; a Gittite harp -- Gittith. see HEBREW (H1663) Gittiy
Of uncertain derivation; Gether, a son of Aram, and the region settled by him -- Gether.

column7: wine press of a pomegranate, two places in Palestine
column9: From (H1660) gath and (H7416) rimmown; wine-press of (the) pomegranate; Gath-Rimmon, a place in Palestine -- Gath-rimmon. see HEBREW (H1660) gath see HEBREW (H7416) rimmown
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2088) zeh; this -- one..another, this. see HEBREW (H2088) zeh
A primitive root; to pine -- mourn, sorrow(-ful).
From (H1669) da'ab; properly, pining; by analogy, fear -- sorrow. see HEBREW (H1669) da'ab
From (H1669) da'ab; pining -- sorrow. see HEBREW (H1669) da'ab

column7: to be anxious or concerned, to fear
column8: be afraid careful, sorry, sorrow, take thought
column9: A primitive root; be anxious -- be afraid (careful, sorry), sorrow, take thought.
Or (fully) Dowoeg {do-ayg'}; active participle of (H1672) da'ag; anxious; Doeg, an Edomite -- Doeg. see HEBREW (H1672) da'ag
From (H1672) da'ag; anxiety -- care(-fulness), fear, heaviness, sorrow. see HEBREW (H1672) da'ag

column7: to fly swiftly, dart through the air
column9: A primitive root; to dart, i.e. Fly rapidly -- fly.
From (H1675) da'ah; the kite (from its rapid flight) -- vulture. See (H7201) ra'ah. see HEBREW (H1675) da'ah see HEBREW (H7201) ra'ah
Or (fully) dowb {dobe}; from (H1680) dabab; the bear (as slow) -- bear. see HEBREW (H1680) dabab
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1677) dob -- bear. see HEBREW (H1677) dob
From an unused root (compare (H1680) dabab) (probably meaning to be sluggish, i.e. Restful); quiet -- strength. see HEBREW (H1680) dabab

column7: to move gently, glide, glide over
column9: A primitive root (compare (H1679) dobe'); to move slowly, i.e. Glide -- cause to speak. see HEBREW (H1679) dobe'
From (H1680) dabab (in the sense of furtive motion); slander -- defaming, evil report, infamy, slander. see HEBREW (H1680) dabab
Or (shortened) dborah {deb-o-raw'}; from (H1696) dabar (in the sense of orderly motion); the bee (from its systematic instincts) -- bee. see HEBREW (H1696) dabar
Or (shortened) Dborah {deb-o-raw'}; the same as (H1682) dbowrah; Deborah, the name of two Hebrewesses -- Deborah. see HEBREW (H1682) dbowrah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2076) zabach; to sacrifice (an animal) -- offer (sacrifice). see HEBREW (H2076) zabach
(Aramaic) from (H1684) dbach; a sacrifice -- sacrifice. see HEBREW (H1684) dbach
In the margin for the textual reading, cheryown {kher-yone'}; both (in the plural only and) of uncertain derivation; probably some cheap vegetable, perhaps a bulbous root -- dove's dung.

column7: perhaps (a place of) speaking (the innermost room of Solomon\'s temple)
column9: Or (shortened) dbir {deb-eer'}; from (H1696) dabar (apparently in the sense of oracle); the shrine or innermost part of the sanctuary -- oracle. see HEBREW (H1696) dabar

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, of a location a.
column7: an Amorite king, also the name of several places in Palestine
column9: Or (shortened) Dbir (Josh. 13:26 (but see (H3810) Lo' Dbar)) {deb-eer'}; the same as (H1687) dbiyr; Debir, the name of an Amoritish king and of two places in Palestine -- Debir. see HEBREW (H3810) Lo' Dbar see HEBREW (H1687) dbiyr

column7: a place in Aram (Syria) or Northern Israel
column9: Probably an orthographical error for (H7247) Riblah; Diblah, a place in Syria -- Diblath. see HEBREW (H7247) Riblah

column7: a lump (of pressed figs), a pressed (fig) cake
column9: From an unused root (akin to (H2082) zabal) probably meaning to press together; a cake of pressed figs -- cake (lump) of figs. see HEBREW (H2082) zabal
Dual from the masculine of (H1690) dbelah; two cakes; Diblajim, a symbolic name -- Diblaim. see HEBREW (H1690) dbelah

column8: abide fast, cleave fast together, follow close hard after, be joined together
column9: A primitive root; properly, to impinge, i.e. Cling or adhere; figuratively, to catch by pursuit -- abide fast, cleave (fast together), follow close (hard after), be joined (together), keep (fast), overtake, pursue hard, stick, take.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1692) dabaq; to stick to -- cleave. see HEBREW (H1692) dabaq
From (H1692) dabaq; a joint; by implication, solder -- joint, solder. see HEBREW (H1692) dabaq
From (H1692) dabaq; adhering -- cleave, joining, stick closer. see HEBREW (H1692) dabaq

column8: answer, appoint, bid, command, commune, declare, destroy, give,
column9: A primitive root; perhaps properly, to arrange; but used figuratively (of words), to speak; rarely (in a destructive sense) to subdue -- answer, appoint, bid, command, commune, declare, destroy, give, name, promise, pronounce, rehearse, say, speak, be spokesman, subdue, talk, teach, tell, think, use (entreaties), utter, X well, X work.

column8: act, advice, affair, answer, any such thing, because of, book, business,
column9: From (H1696) dabar; a word; by implication, a matter (as spoken of) or thing; adverbially, a cause -- act, advice, affair, answer, X any such (thing), because of, book, business, care, case, cause, certain rate, + chronicles, commandment, X commune(-ication), + concern(-ing), + confer, counsel, + dearth, decree, deed, X disease, due, duty, effect, + eloquent, errand, (evil favoured-)ness, + glory, + harm, hurt, + iniquity, + judgment, language, + lying, manner, matter, message, (no) thing, oracle, X ought, X parts, + pertaining, + please, portion, + power, promise, provision, purpose, question, rate, reason, report, request, X (as hast) said, sake, saying, sentence, + sign, + so, some (uncleanness), somewhat to say, + song, speech, X spoken, talk, task, + that, X there done, thing (concerning), thought, + thus, tidings, what(-soever), + wherewith, which, word, work. see HEBREW (H1696) dabar
From (H1696) dabar (in the sense of destroying); a pestilence -- murrain, pestilence, plague. see HEBREW (H1696) dabar
From (H1696) dabar (in its original sense); a pasture (from its arrangement of the flock) -- fold, manner. see HEBREW (H1696) dabar
Feminine of (H1697) dabar; a reason, suit or style -- cause, end, estate, order, regard. see HEBREW (H1697) dabar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1700) dibrah -- intent, sake. see HEBREW (H1700) dibrah
Feminine active participle of (H1696) dabar in the sense of driving (compare (H1699) dober); a raft -- float. see HEBREW (H1696) dabar see HEBREW (H1699) dober
Intensive from (H1696) dabar; a word -- word. see HEBREW (H1696) dabar
From (H1697) dabar; wordy; Dibri, an Israelite -- Dibri. see HEBREW (H1697) dabar
From (H1697) dabar (perhaps in the sense of (H1699) dober); Daberath, a place in Palestine -- Dabareh, Daberath. see HEBREW (H1697) dabar see HEBREW (H1699) dober
From an unused root meaning to be gummy; honey (from its stickiness); by analogy, syrup -- honey((-comb)).
Intensive from the same as (H1706) dbash; a sticky mass, i.e. The hump of a camel -- hunch (of a camel). see HEBREW (H1706) dbash
The same as (H1707) dabbesheth; Dabbesheth, a place in Palestine -- Dabbesheth. see HEBREW (H1707) dabbesheth

Or (fully) dag (Nehemiah 13:16) {dawg}; from (H1711) dagah; a fish (as prolific); or perhaps rather from (H1672) da'ag (as timid); but still better from (H1672) da'ag (in the sense of squirming, i.e. Moving by the vibratory action of the tail); a fish (often used collectively) -- fish. see HEBREW (H1711) dagah see HEBREW (H1672) da'ag see HEBREW (H1672) da'ag
Feminine of (H1709) dag, and meaning the same -- fish. see HEBREW (H1709) dag
A primitive root; to move rapidly; used only as a denominative from (H1709) dag; to spawn, i.e. Become numerous -- grow. see HEBREW (H1709) dag

column7: a god and an idol of the Philistines
column9: From (H1709) dag; the fish-god; Dagon, a Philistine deity -- Dagon. see HEBREW (H1709) dag
A primitive root; to flaunt, i.e. Raise a flag; figuratively, to be conspicuous -- (set up, with) banners, chiefest.
From (H1713) dagal; a flag -- banner, standard. see HEBREW (H1713) dagal
From (H1711) dagah; properly, increase, i.e. Grain -- corn ((floor)), wheat. see HEBREW (H1711) dagah

column7: to gather together as a brood
column9: A primitive root, to brood over eggs or young -- gather, sit.
Apparently from the same as (H1730) dowd; the breast (as the seat of love, or from its shape) -- breast, teat. see HEBREW (H1730) dowd
A doubtful root; to walk gently -- go (softly, with).

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, of a location or a people
column7: a descendant of Ham, also a descendant of Abraham, also the tribes desc. from them
column9: Or (prolonged) Ddaneh (Ezek. 25:13) {deh-daw'- neh}; of uncertain derivation; Dedan, the name of two Cushites and of their territory -- Dedan.
Plural of (H1719) Ddan (as patrial); Dedanites, the descendants or inhabitants of Dedan -- Dedanim. see HEBREW (H1719) Ddan

column7: a son of Javan, also his desc
column9: Or (by orthographical error) Rodaniym (1 Chron. 1:7) {ro-daw-neem'}; a plural of uncertain derivation; Dodanites, or descendants of a son of Javan -- Dodanim.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2091) zahab; gold -- gold(- en). see HEBREW (H2091) zahab
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; Dahava, a people colonized in Samaria -- Dehavites.
A primitive root (compare (H1740) duwach); to be dumb, i.e. (figuratively) dumbfounded -- astonished. see HEBREW (H1740) duwach
A primitive root; to curvet or move irregularly -- pause.
By reduplication from (H1725) dahar; a gallop -- pransing. see HEBREW (H1725) dahar
A primitive root; to mope, i.e. (figuratively) pine -- sorrow.
An orthographical variation of (H1709) dag as a denominative ((H1771) dayag); a fisherman -- fisher. see HEBREW (H1709) dag see HEBREW (H1771) dayag
Feminine from the same as (H1728) davvag; properly, fishery, i.e. A hook for fishing -- fish (hook). see HEBREW (H1728) davvag

Or (shortened) dod {dode}; from an unused root meaning properly, to boil, i.e. (figuratively) to love; by implication, a love- token, lover, friend; specifically an uncle -- (well-)beloved, father's brother, love, uncle.
From the same as (H1730) dowd; a pot (for boiling); also (by resemblance of shape) a basket -- basket, caldron, kettle, (seething) pot. see HEBREW (H1730) dowd

column7: perhaps "beloved one", a son of Jesse
column9: Rarely (fully); Daviyd {daw-veed'}; from the same as (H1730) dowd; loving; David, the youngest son of Jesse -- David. see HEBREW (H1730) dowd
Feminine of (H1730) dowd; an aunt -- aunt, father's sister, uncle's wife. see HEBREW (H1730) dowd
From (H1730) dowd; loving; Dodo, the name of three Israelites -- Dodo. see HEBREW (H1730) dowd

column7: beloved of Yah, an Israelite name
column9: From (H1730) dowd and (H3050) Yahh; love of Jah; Dodavah, an Israelite -- Dodavah. see HEBREW (H1730) dowd see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H1731) duwd; a boiler or basket; also the mandrake (as an aphrodisiac) -- basket, mandrake. see HEBREW (H1731) duwd
Formed like (H1736) duwday; amatory; Dodai, an Israelite -- Dodai. see HEBREW (H1736) duwday
A primitive root; to be sick (as if in menstruation) -- infirmity.

column8: faint, menstruous cloth, she that is sick, having sickness
column9: From (H1738) davah; sick (especially in menstruation) -- faint, menstruous cloth, she that is sick, having sickness. see HEBREW (H1738) davah

column7: to rinse, cleanse away by rinsing or washing
column9: A primitive root; to thrust away; figuratively, to cleanse -- cast out, purge, wash.
From (H1739) daveh; sickness; figuratively, loathing -- languishing, sorrowful. see HEBREW (H1739) daveh
From (H1739) daveh; sick; figuratively, troubled -- faint. see HEBREW (H1739) daveh
A primitive root; to bruise in a mortar -- beat.
Of uncertain derivation; the hoopoe or else the grouse -- lapwing.
From an unused root meaning to be dumb (compare (H1820) damah); silence; figuratively, death -- silence. see HEBREW (H1820) damah

column7: a son of Ishmael, also a city in Judah and a name of Edom
column9: The same as (H1745) duwmah; Dumah, a tribe and region of Arabia -- Dumah. see HEBREW (H1745) duwmah

column7: a silence, a quiet waiting, repose
column9: From (H1820) damah; stillness; adverbially, silently; abstractly quiet, trust -- silence, silent, waiteth. see HEBREW (H1820) damah

column4: proper name; masculine; noun masculine; adverb
column9: From (H1826) damam; still; adverbially, silently -- dumb, silent, quietly wait. see HEBREW (H1826) damam
Of uncertain derivation; wax; -wax.
A primitive root; to leap -- be turned.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1854) daqaq; to crumble -- be broken to pieces. see HEBREW (H1854) daqaq
A primitive root; properly, to gyrate (or move in a circle), i.e. To remain -- dwell.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1752) duwr; to reside -- dwell. see HEBREW (H1752) duwr
From (H1752) duwr; a circle, ball or pile -- ball, turn, round about. see HEBREW (H1752) duwr
Or (shortened) dor {dore}; from (H1752) duwr; properly, a revolution of time, i.e. An age or generation; also a dwelling -- age, X evermore, generation, (n-)ever, posterity. see HEBREW (H1752) duwr
Or (by permutation) Dorr (Josh. 17:11; 1 Kings 4:11) {dore}; from (H1755) dowr; dwelling; Dor, a place in Palestine -- Dor. see HEBREW (H1755) dowr
(Aramaic) probably from (H1753) duwr; circle or dwelling; Dura, a place in Babylonia -- Dura. see HEBREW (H1753) duwr

column8: break, tear, thresh, tread out down, at grass Jer
column9: Or dowsh {dosh}; or diysh {deesh}; a primitive root; to trample or thresh -- break, tear, thresh, tread out (down), at grass (Jer. 50:11, by mistake for (H1877) deshe'). see HEBREW (H1877) deshe'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1758) duwsh; to trample -- tread down. see HEBREW (H1758) duwsh

column8: chase, drive away on, overthrow, outcast, sore, thrust, totter
column9: Or dachach {Jer. 23:12) {daw-khakh'}; a primitive root; to push down -- chase, drive away (on), overthrow, outcast, X sore, thrust, totter.
(Aramaic) from the equivalent of (H1760) dachah; probably a musical instrument (as being struck) -- instrument of music. see HEBREW (H1760) dachah
From (H1760) dachah; a push, i.e. (by implication) a fall -- falling. see HEBREW (H1760) dachah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2119) zachal; to slink, i.e. (by implication) to fear, or (causatively) be formidable -- make afraid, dreadful, fear, terrible. see HEBREW (H2119) zachal
Of uncertain derivation; millet -- millet.
A primitive root; to urge, i.e. Hasten -- (be) haste(-ned), pressed on.
A primitive root; to press, i.e. Oppress -- thrust, vex.

column8: able, according to, after ability, among, as oft as, more than enough, from, in,

Denominative from (H1709) dag; to fish -- fish. see HEBREW (H1709) dag
From (H1770) diyg; a fisherman -- fisher. see HEBREW (H1770) diyg

Of uncertain derivation; ink -- ink.

Or (Gen. 6:3) duwn {doon}; a primitive roy a straight course, i.e. Sail direct -- (come) with a straight course.

From (H1777) diyn; judgement (the suit, justice, sentence or tribunal); by impl. Also strife -- cause, judgement, plea, strife. see HEBREW (H1777) diyn
(Aramaic) corresp. To (H1779) duwn -- judgement. see HEBREW (H1779) duwn
From (H1777) diyn; a judge or advocate -- judge. see HEBREW (H1777) diyn
(Aramaic) corresp. To (H1781) dayan -- judge. see HEBREW (H1781) dayan
Fem. Of (H1779) duwn; justice; Dinah, the daughter of Jacob -- Dinah. see HEBREW (H1779) duwn
(Aramaic) partial from uncertain primitive; a Dinaite or inhabitant of some unknown Assyria province -- Dinaite.

From (H1758) duwsh; threshing-time -- threshing. see HEBREW (H1758) duwsh
(Diyshon, the same as (H1788) diyshon; Dishon, the name of two Edomites -- Dishon. see HEBREW (H1788) diyshon
From (H1758) duwsh; the leaper, i.e. An antelope -- pygarg. see HEBREW (H1758) duwsh

From an unused root (compare (H1794) dakah); crushed, i.e. (fig.) Injured -- afflicted, oppressed. see HEBREW (H1794) dakah
(Aramaic) or dak (Aramaic) {dawk}; prolonged from (H1668) da'; this -- the same, this. see HEBREW (H1668) da'

column9: A primitive root (compare (H1794) dakah); to crumble; transitively, to bruise (literally or figuratively) -- beat to pieces, break (in pieces), bruise, contrite, crush, destroy, humble, oppress, smite. see HEBREW (H1794) dakah
From (H1792) daka'; crushed (literally powder, or figuratively, contrite) -- contrite, destruction. see HEBREW (H1792) daka'

From (H1794) dakah like (H1793) dakka'; mutilated -- + wounded. see HEBREW (H1794) dakah see HEBREW (H1793) dakka'
From (H1794) dakah; a dashing of surf -- wave. see HEBREW (H1794) dakah
(Aramaic) prolonged from (H1791) dek; this -- same, that, this. see HEBREW (H1791) dek
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2145) zakar; properly, a male, i.e. Of sheep -- ram. see HEBREW (H2145) zakar

From (H1809) dalal; properly, dangling, i.e. (by implication) weak or thin -- lean, needy, poor (man), weaker. see HEBREW (H1809) dalal

From (H1802) dalah; properly, something dangling, i.e. A loose thread or hair; figuratively, indigent -- hair, pining sickness, poor(-est sort). see HEBREW (H1802) dalah
A primitive root; to roil water -- trouble.

From (H1809) dalal; languishing -- Delilah, a Philistine woman -- Delilah. see HEBREW (H1809) dalal
From (H1802) dalah; something dangling, i.e. A bough -- branch. see HEBREW (H1802) dalah

Of uncertain derivation; Dilan, a place in Palestine -- Dilean.

: from (H1814) dalaq; a burning fever -- inflammation. see HEBREW (H1814) dalaq
From (H1802) dalah; something swinging, i.e. The valve of a door -- door (two-leaved), gate, leaf, lid. (In Psa. 141:3, dal, irreg.). see HEBREW (H1802) dalah

From (H1819) damah; resemblance -- X like. see HEBREW (H1819) damah

Feminine from (H1826) damam; quiet -- calm, silence, still. see HEBREW (H1826) damam
Of uncertain derivation; manure -- dung.

By orthographical variation from (H1834) Dammeseq; damask (as a fabric of Damascus) -- in Damascus. see HEBREW (H1834) Dammeseq
Or Duwmeseq {doo-meh'-sek}; or Darmeseq {dar-meh'-sek}; of foreign origin; Damascus, a city of Syria -- Damascus.

Of uncertain derivation; Dannah, a place in Palestine -- Dannah.

From an unused root (meaning to push over); a stumbling-block -- slanderest.

From (H1854) daqaq; something crumbling, i.e. Fine (as a thin cloth) -- curtain. see HEBREW (H1854) daqaq

(also dor-bawn'); of uncertain derivation; a goad -- goad.

Of uncertain derivation; Dathan, an Israelite -- Dathan.
Or (Aramaic dual) Dothayin (Gen. 37:17) {do- thah'-yin}; of uncertain derivation; Dothan, a place in Palestine -- Dothan.
A primitive particle; lo! -- behold, lo.

From (H1887) he' and (H253) 'ach; aha! -- ah, aha, ha. see HEBREW (H1887) he' see HEBREW (H253) 'ach
By reduplication from (H3051) yahab; gift (in sacrifice), i.e. Holocaust -- offering. see HEBREW (H3051) yahab

column9: A primitive root (compare (H1901) hagiyg); to murmur (in pleasure or anger); by implication, to ponder -- imagine, meditate, mourn, mutter, roar, X sore, speak, study, talk, utter. see HEBREW (H1901) hagiyg
A primitive root; to remove -- stay, stay away.

From (H1897) hagah; musing -- meditation. see HEBREW (H1897) hagah

Intensive from (H1897) hagah; a murmuring sound, i.e. A musical notation (probably similar to the modern affettuoso to indicate solemnity of movement); by implication, a machination -- device, Higgaion, meditation, solemn sound. see HEBREW (H1897) hagah
Of uncertain derivation; perhaps suitable or turning -- directly.

column7: Sarah\'s Eg. maid, the mother of Ishmael
column9: Of uncertain (perhaps foreign) derivation; Hagar, the mother of Ishmael -- Hagar.

column4: proper name, of a people; Adjective, of a people; proper name, masculine
column7: a tribe East of the Jordan, also a member of the tribe, also an Israelite
column9: Or (prolonged) Hagris {hag-ree'}; perhaps patronymically from (H1904) Hagar; a Hagrite or member of a certain Arabian clan -- Hagarene, Hagarite, Haggeri. see HEBREW (H1904) Hagar
For (H1959) heydad; a shout -- sounding again. see HEBREW (H1959) heydad
(Aramaic) probably of foreign origin; a vizier -- counsellor.
Probably of foreign origin (compare (H111) 'Adad); Hadad, the name of an idol, and of several kings of Edom -- Hadad. see HEBREW (H111) 'Adad

From (H1908) Hadad and (H7417) Rimmown; Hadad-Rimmon, a place in Palestine -- Hadad-rimmon. see HEBREW (H1908) Hadad see HEBREW (H7417) Rimmown
A primitive root (compare (H3034) yadah); to stretch forth the hand -- put. see HEBREW (H3034) yadah
Of foreign origin; Hodu (i.e. Hindu-stan) -- India.

column7: a son of Joktan and his desc., also son of the king of Hamath, perhaps also an official of Rehoboam
column9: Or Hadoram {had-o-rawm'}; probably of foreign derivation; Hadoram, a son of Joktan, and the tribe descended from him -- Hadoram.
Of uncertain derivation; Hiddai, an Israelite -- Hiddai.
A primitive root (compare (H1854) daqaq); to crush with the foot -- tread down. see HEBREW (H1854) daqaq
From an unused root meaning to stamp upon; a foot stool -- (foot-)stool.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of (H1916) hadom; something stamped to pieces, i.e. A bit -- piece. see HEBREW (H1916) hadom
Of uncertain derivation; the myrtle -- myrtle (tree).
Feminine of (H1918) hadac; Hadassah (or Esther) -- Hadassah. see HEBREW (H1918) hadac

column7: to honor, adorn, perhaps to swell
column8: countenance, crooked place, glorious, honor, put forth
column9: A primitive root; to swell up (literally or figuratively, active or passive); by implication, to favor or honour, be high or proud -- countenance, crooked place, glorious, honour, put forth.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1921) hadar; to magnify (figuratively) -- glorify, honour. see HEBREW (H1921) hadar
(Aramaic) from (H1922) hadar; magnificence -- honour, majesty. see HEBREW (H1922) hadar
The same as (H1926) hadar; Hadar, an Edomite -- Hadar. see HEBREW (H1926) hadar
From (H1921) hadar; honour; used (figuratively) for the capital city (Jerusalem) -- glory. see HEBREW (H1921) hadar

column8: beauty, comeliness, glorious, glory, goodly, honor, majesty
column9: From (H1921) hadar; magnificence, i.e. Ornament or splendor -- beauty, comeliness, excellency, glorious, glory, goodly, honour, majesty. see HEBREW (H1921) hadar
Feminine of (H1926) hadar; decoration -- beauty, honour. see HEBREW (H1926) hadar

From (H1924) Hadar and (H5828) ezer; Hadar (i.e. Hadad, (H1908) Hadad) is his help; Hadarezer (i.e. Hadadezer, (H1909) Hadad'ezer), a Syrian king -- Hadarezer. see HEBREW (H1924) Hadar see HEBREW (H5828) ezer see HEBREW (H1908) Hadad see HEBREW (H1909) Hadad'ezer
A shortened form of (H162) 'ahahh; ah! Expressing grief -- woe worth. see HEBREW (H162) 'ahahh
By permutation from (H1929) hahh; oh! -- alas. see HEBREW (H1929) hahh

(Aramaic) or (feminine) hiyo (Aramaic) {he}; corresponding to (H1931) huw' -- X are, it, this. see HEBREW (H1931) huw'

Or havah {haw-vaw'}; a primitive root (compare (H183) 'avah, (H1961) hayah) supposed to mean properly, to breathe; to be (in the sense of existence) -- be, X have. see HEBREW (H183) 'avah see HEBREW (H1961) hayah

column7: to become, come to pass, be

: or hephek {hay'-fek}; from (H2015) haphak; a turn, i.e. The reverse -- contrary. see HEBREW (H2015) haphak

A primitive root; to be rancid, i.e. (transitively) to loathe -- abhor.
From (H2092) zaham; loathing; Zaham, an Israelite -- Zaham. see HEBREW (H2092) zaham
A primitive root; to gleam; figuratively, to enlighten (by caution) -- admonish, shine, teach, (give) warn(-ing).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2094) zahar; (passively) be admonished -- take heed. see HEBREW (H2094) zahar
From (H2094) zahar; brilliancy -- brightness. see HEBREW (H2094) zahar
For (H2088) zeh; this or that -- that, this. see HEBREW (H2088) zeh
For (H2088) zeh; this or that -- that, this, X wherein, which, whom. see HEBREW (H2088) zeh

column7: the second month of the Jewish calendar
column9: Probably from an unused root meaning to be prominent; properly, brightness (compare (H2122) ziyv), i.e. (figuratively) the month of flowers; Ziv (corresponding to Ijar or May) -- Zif. see HEBREW (H2122) ziyv

column8: flow, gush out, have a running issue, pine away, run
column9: A primitive root; to flow freely (as water), i.e. (specifically) to have a (sexual) flux; figuratively, to waste away; also to overflow -- flow, gush out, have a (running) issue, pine away, run.
From (H2100) zuwb; a seminal or menstrual flux -- issue. see HEBREW (H2100) zuwb

column7: to boil up, seethe, act proudly or presumptuously or rebelliously
column8: be proud, deal proudly, come presumptuously
column9: Or (by permutation) ziyd {zeed}; a primitive root; to seethe; figuratively, to be insolent -- be proud, deal proudly, &? Presume, (come) presumptuously, sod.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2102) zuwd; to be proud -- in pride. see HEBREW (H2102) zuwd

column7: a people East of the Jordan
column9: Plural probably from the same as (H2123) ziyz; prominent; Zuzites, an aboriginal tribe of Palestine -- Zuzims. see HEBREW (H2123) ziyz
Of uncertain origin; Zocheth, an Israelite -- Zoheth.
Apparently from the same root as (H2099) Ziv (in the sense of prominence); an angle (as projecting), i.e. (by implication) a corner-column (or anta) -- corner(stone). see HEBREW (H2099) Ziv
A primitive root (compare (H2151) zalal); probably to shake out, i.e. (by implication) to scatter profusely; figuratively, to treat lightly -- lavish, despise. see HEBREW (H2151) zalal
From (H2107) zuwl; probably scattering, i.e. Removal; used adverbially, except -- beside, but, only, save. see HEBREW (H2107) zuwl
A primitive root; perhaps properly, to be plump, i.e. (transitively) to nourish -- feed.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2109) zuwn -- feed. see HEBREW (H2109) zuwn
A primitive root; properly, to shake off, i.e. (figuratively) to agitate (as with fear) -- move, tremble, vex.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2111) zuwa'; to shake (with fear) -- tremble. see HEBREW (H2111) zuwa'

column7: a trembling, an object of trembling or terror
column9: From (H2111) zuwa'; agitation, fear -- be removed, trouble, vexation. Compare (H2189) za'avah. see HEBREW (H2111) zuwa' see HEBREW (H2189) za'avah

column8: come from another man, place, fanner, go away, estranger, thing, woman
column9: A primitive root; to turn aside (especially for lodging); hence to be a foreigner, strange, profane; specifically (active participle) to commit adultery -- (come from) another (man, place), fanner, go away, (e-)strange(-r, thing, woman).
A primitive root (compare (H6695) tsowq); to press together, &? Tighten -- close, rush, thrust together. see HEBREW (H6695) tsowq
From (H2115) zuwr; trodden on -- that which is crushed. see HEBREW (H2115) zuwr
Probably from the root of (H2123) ziyz; prominent; Zaza, an Israelite -- Zaza. see HEBREW (H2123) ziyz
A primitive root; to shove or displace -- loose.
A primitive root; to crawl; by implication, to fear -- be afraid, serpent, worm.
Feminine active participle of (H2119) zachal; crawling (i.e. Serpent); Zocheleth, a boundary stone in. Palestine -- Zoheleth. see HEBREW (H2119) zachal
From (H2102) zuwd; boiling of water, i.e. Wave -- proud. see HEBREW (H2102) zuwd
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2099) Ziv; (figuratively) cheerfulness -- brightness, countenance. see HEBREW (H2099) Ziv
From an unused root apparently meaning to be conspicuous; fulness of the breast; also a moving creature -- abundance, wild beast.
Apparently from the same as (H2123) ziyz; prominence; Ziza, the name of two Israelites -- Ziza. see HEBREW (H2123) ziyz
Another form for (H2124) Ziyza'; Zizah, an Israelite -- Zizah. see HEBREW (H2124) Ziyza'
From (H2109) zuwn; well-fed; or perhaps an orthographical error for (H2124) Ziyza'; Zina, an Israelite -- Zina. see HEBREW (H2109) zuwn see HEBREW (H2124) Ziyza'
From (H2111) zuwa'; agitation; Zia, an Israelite -- Zia. see HEBREW (H2111) zuwa'

column4: proper name; proper name, of a location a.; proper name, masculine; proper name, of a location
column7: a son of Judah, also a city Southeast of Hebron and a city in S. Judah
column9: From the same as (H2203) zepheth; flowing; Ziph, the name of a place in Palestine; also of an Israelite -- Ziph. see HEBREW (H2203) zepheth
Feminine of (H2128) Ziyph; a flowing; Ziphah, an Israelite -- Ziphah. see HEBREW (H2128) Ziyph
Patrial from (H2128) Ziyph; a Ziphite or inhabitant of Ziph -- Ziphim, Ziphite. see HEBREW (H2128) Ziyph

(Isa. (H50) 'Abiyshuwae: (feminine); and ziq {zeek}; or zeq {zake}; from (H2187) zanaq; properly, what leaps forth, i.e. Flash of fire, or a burning arrow; also (from the original sense of the root) a bond -- chain, fetter, firebrand, spark. see HEBREW (H50) 'Abiyshuwae see HEBREW (H2187) zanaq
Probably from an unused root (akin to (H2099) Ziv); an olive (as yielding illuminating oil), the tree, the branch or the berry -- olive (tree, -yard), Olivet. see HEBREW (H2099) Ziv
From (H2132) zayith; olive grove; Zethan, an Israelite -- Zethan. see HEBREW (H2132) zayith
From (H2141) zakak; clear -- clean, pure. see HEBREW (H2141) zakak

column7: to be clear, clean or pure
column8: be make clean, cleanse, be clear, count pure
column9: A primitive root (compare (H2141) zakak); to be translucent; figuratively, to be innocent -- be (make) clean, cleanse, be clear, count pure. see HEBREW (H2141) zakak
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H2135) zakah; purity -- innocency. see HEBREW (H2135) zakah
From (H2135) zakah; properly, transparency, i.e. Glass -- crystal. see HEBREW (H2135) zakah
Properly, passive participle of (H2142) zakar, but used for (H2145) zakar; a male (of man or animals) -- males, men-children. see HEBREW (H2142) zakar see HEBREW (H2145) zakar
From (H2142) zakar; mindful; Zakkur, the name of seven Israelites -- Zaccur, Zacchur. see HEBREW (H2142) zakar
From (H2141) zakak; pure; Zakkai, an Israelite -- Zaccai. see HEBREW (H2141) zakak

column7: to be bright, clean or pure
column9: A primitive root (compare (H2135) zakah); to be transparent or clean (phys. Or morally) -- be (make) clean, be pure(-r). see HEBREW (H2135) zakah

column8: burn incense, earnestly, be male, make mention of, be mindful, recount
column9: A primitive root; properly, to mark (so as to be recognized), i.e. To remember; by implication, to mention; also (as denominative from (H2145) zakar) to be male -- X burn (incense), X earnestly, be male, (make) mention (of), be mindful, recount, record(-er), remember, make to be remembered, bring (call, come, keep, put) to (in) remembrance, X still, think on, X well. see HEBREW (H2145) zakar
Or zeker {zeh'-ker}; from (H2142) zakar; a memento, abstr. Recollection (rarely if ever); by implication, commemoration -- memorial, memory, remembrance, scent. see HEBREW (H2142) zakar
The same as (H2143) zeker; Zeker, an Israelite -- Zeker. see HEBREW (H2143) zeker
From (H2142) zakar; properly, remembered, i.e. A male (of man or animals, as being the most noteworthy sex) -- X him, male, man(child, -kind). see HEBREW (H2142) zakar
From (H2142) zakar; a memento (or memorable thing, day or writing) -- memorial, record. see HEBREW (H2142) zakar
From (H2142) zakar; memorable; Zicri, the name of twelve Israelites -- Zichri. see HEBREW (H2142) zakar

column7: the name of a number of Isr
column9: Or Zkaryahuw {zek-ar-yaw'-hoo}; from (H2142) zakar and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has remembered; Zecarjah, the name of twenty-nine Israelites -- Zachariah, Zechariah. see HEBREW (H2142) zakar see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H2151) zalal; properly, a shaking, i.e. Perhaps a tempest -- vilest. see HEBREW (H2151) zalal
By reduplication from (H2151) zalal; tremulous, i.e. A twig -- sprig. see HEBREW (H2151) zalal

column8: blow down, glutton, riotous eater, vile
column9: A primitive root (compare (H2107) zuwl); to shake (as in the wind), i.e. To quake; figuratively, to be loose morally, worthless or prodigal -- blow down, glutton, riotous (eater), vile. see HEBREW (H2107) zuwl
Or ziliaphaph {zil-aw-faw'}; from (H2196) za'aph; a glow (of wind or anger); also a famine (as consuming) -- horrible, horror, terrible. see HEBREW (H2196) za'aph
: from an unused root apparently meaning to trickle, as myrrh; fragrant dropping; Zilpah, Leah's maid -- Zilpah.

column8: heinous crime, lewdly mischief, wicked device
column9: Or zammah {zam-maw'}; from (H2161) zamam; a plan, especially a bad one -- heinous crime, lewd(-ly, -ness), mischief, purpose, thought, wicked (device, mind, -ness). see HEBREW (H2161) zamam
The same as (H2154) zimmah; Zimmah, the name of two Israelites -- Zimmah. see HEBREW (H2154) zimmah
Or zmorah {zem-o-raw'} (feminine); and zmor {zem-ore'} (masculine); from (H2168) zamar; a twig (as pruned) -- vine, branch, slip. see HEBREW (H2168) zamar
From (H2161) zamam; intriguing; a Zamzumite, or native tribe of Palestine -- Zamzummim. see HEBREW (H2161) zamam
Or zamir {zaw-meer'}; and (feminine) zmirah {zem-ee-raw'}; from (H2167) zamar; a song to be accompanied with instrumental music -- psalm(-ist), singing, song. see HEBREW (H2167) zamar
From (H2168) zamar; a twig (as pruned) -- branch. see HEBREW (H2168) zamar
Feminine of (H2158) zamiyr; song; Zemirah, an Israelite -- Zemira. see HEBREW (H2158) zamiyr

column8: consider, devise, imagine, plot, purpose, think evil
column9: A primitive root; to plan, usually in a bad sense -- consider, devise, imagine, plot, purpose, think (evil).
From (H2161) zamam; a plot -- wicked device. see HEBREW (H2161) zamam
A primitive root; to fix (a time) -- appoint.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2163) zaman; to agree (on a time and place) -- prepare. see HEBREW (H2163) zaman
From (H2163) zaman; an appointed occasion -- season, time. see HEBREW (H2163) zaman
(Aramaic) from (H2165) zman; the same as (H2165) zman -- season, time. see HEBREW (H2165) zman see HEBREW (H2165) zman

column7: to make music (in praise of God)
column8: give praise, sing forth praises, psalms
column9: A primitive root (perhaps ident. With (H2168) zamar through the idea of striking with the fingers); properly, to touch the strings or parts of a musical instrument, i.e. Play upon it; to make music, accompanied by the voice; hence to celebrate in song and music -- give praise, sing forth praises, psalms. see HEBREW (H2168) zamar
A primitive root (compare (H2167) zamar, (H5568) camar, (H6785) tsemer); to trim (a vine) -- prune. see HEBREW (H2167) zamar see HEBREW (H5568) camar see HEBREW (H6785) tsemer

column7: perhaps a mountain sheep or goat
column9: Apparently from (H2167) zamar or (H2168) zamar; a gazelle (from its lightly touching the ground) -- chamois. see HEBREW (H2167) zamar see HEBREW (H2168) zamar
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H2167) zamar; instrumental music -- musick. see HEBREW (H2167) zamar
(Aramaic) from the same as (H2170) zmar; an instrumental musician -- singer. see HEBREW (H2170) zmar
From (H2167) zamar; a musical piece or song to be accompanied by an instrument -- melody, psalm. see HEBREW (H2167) zamar
From (H2168) zamar; pruned (i.e. Choice) fruit -- best fruit. see HEBREW (H2168) zamar

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, of a people
column9: From (H2167) zamar; musical; Zimri, the name of five Israelites, and of an Arabian tribe -- Zimri. see HEBREW (H2167) zamar
From (H2167) zamar; musical; Zimran, a son of Abraham by Keturah -- Zimran. see HEBREW (H2167) zamar
From (H2167) zamar; instrumental music; by implication, praise -- song. see HEBREW (H2167) zamar

column8: divers kinds, all manner of store
column9: From (H2109) zuwn; properly, nourished (or fully developed), i.e. A form or sort -- divers kinds, X all manner of store. see HEBREW (H2109) zuwn
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2177) zan; sort -- kind. see HEBREW (H2177) zan

column7: to cut off or smite the tail
column9: A primitive root meaning to wag; used only as a denominative from (H2180) zanab; to curtail, i.e. Cut off the rear -- smite the hindmost. see HEBREW (H2180) zanab
From (H2179) zanab (in the original sense of flapping); the tail (literally or figuratively) -- tail. see HEBREW (H2179) zanab

column7: to commit fornication, be a harlot
column8: cause to commit fornication, continually, great, be an, play the harlot
column9: A primitive root (highly-fed and therefore wanton); to commit adultery (usually of the female, and less often of simple fornication, rarely of involuntary ravishment); figuratively, to commit idolatry (the Jewish people being regarded as the spouse of Jehovah) -- (cause to) commit fornication, X continually, X great, (be an, play the) harlot, (cause to be, play the) whore, (commit, fall to) whoredom, (cause to) go a-whoring, whorish.
From (H2186) zanach; rejected; Zanoach, the name of two places in Palestine -- Zanoah. see HEBREW (H2186) zanach
From (H2181) zanah; adultery; figuratively, idolatry -- whoredom. see HEBREW (H2181) zanah
From (H2181) zanah; adultery, i.e. (figuratively) infidelity, idolatry -- whoredom. see HEBREW (H2181) zanah

Regarded by some as if from (H2109) zuwn or an unused root, and applied to military equipments; but evidently the feminine plural active participle of (H2181) zanah; harlots -- armour. see HEBREW (H2109) zuwn see HEBREW (H2181) zanah

column8: cast away off, remove far away off
column9: A primitive root meaning to push aside, i.e. Reject, forsake, fail -- cast away (off), remove far away (off).
A primitive root; properly, to draw together the feet (as an animal about to dart upon its prey), i.e. To spring forward -- leap.
From (H2111) zuwa' (in the sense of (H3154) yeza'); perspiration -- sweat. see HEBREW (H2111) zuwa' see HEBREW (H3154) yeza'
By transposition for (H2113) zva'ah; agitation, maltreatment -- X removed, trouble. see HEBREW (H2113) zva'ah
From (H2111) zuwa'; disquiet; Zaavan, an Idumaean -- Zaavan. see HEBREW (H2111) zuwa'
From an unused root (akin (by permutation) to (H6819) tsa'ar), meaning to dwindle; small -- little. see HEBREW (H6819) tsa'ar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2191) ze'eyr -- little. see HEBREW (H2191) ze'eyr
A primitive root; to extinguish -- be extinct.

column8: abhor, abominable, be angry, defy, have indignation
column9: A primitive root; properly, to foam at the mouth, i.e. To be enraged -- abhor, abominable, (be) angry, defy, (have) indignation.
From (H2194) za'am; strictly froth at the mouth, i.e. (figuratively) fury (especially of God's displeasure with sin) -- angry, indignation, rage. see HEBREW (H2194) za'am

column8: fret, sad, worse liking, be wroth
column9: A primitive root; properly, to boil up, i.e. (figuratively) to be peevish or angry -- fret, sad, worse liking, be wroth.
From (H2196) za'aph; anger -- indignation, rage(-ing), wrath. see HEBREW (H2196) za'aph
From (H2196) za'aph; angry -- displeased. see HEBREW (H2196) za'aph

column8: assemble, call together, make a cry out, come with such a company, gather together
column9: A primitive root; to shriek (from anguish or danger); by analogy, (as a herald) to announce or convene publicly -- assemble, call (together), (make a) cry (out), come with such a company, gather (together), cause to be proclaimed.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2199) za'aq; to make an outcry -- cry. see HEBREW (H2199) za'aq
And (feminine) zoaqah {zeh-aw-kaw'}; from (H2199) za'aq; a shriek or outcry -- cry(-ing). see HEBREW (H2199) za'aq

column7: a place on N. boundary of the promised land
column9: From an unused root (meaning to be fragrant); Ziphron, a place in Palestine -- Ziphron.
From an unused root (meaning to liquify); asphalt (from its tendency to soften in the sun) -- pitch.
A primitive root; to be old -- aged man, be (wax) old (man).

column8: aged, ancient man, elder, old man, men and
column9: From (H2204) zaqen; old -- aged, ancient (man), elder(-est), old (man, men and...women), senator. see HEBREW (H2204) zaqen
From (H2204) zaqen; the beard (as indicating age) -- beard. see HEBREW (H2204) zaqen
From (H2204) zaqen; old age -- age. see HEBREW (H2204) zaqen
Properly, passive participle of (H2204) zaqen (used only in the plural as a noun); old age:-old age. see HEBREW (H2204) zaqen
Feminine of (H2205) zaqen; old age -- old (age). see HEBREW (H2205) zaqen
A primitive root; to life, i.e. (figuratively) comfort -- raise (up).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2210) zaqaph; to hang, i.e. Impale -- set up. see HEBREW (H2210) zaqaph

column8: fine, pour down, purge, purify, refine
column9: A primitive root; to strain, (figuratively) extract, clarify -- fine, pour down, purge, purify, refine.
From (H2237) zarar (in the sense of scattering); a chaplet (as spread around the top), i.e. (specifically) a border moulding -- crown. see HEBREW (H2237) zarar
From (H2114) zuwr (in the sense of estrangement) (compare (H2219) zarah); disgust -- loathsome. see HEBREW (H2114) zuwr see HEBREW (H2219) zarah
A primitive root; to flow away -- wax warm.

column7: begotten in Babylon, a leader of returning Israelite exiles
column9: From (H2215) zarab and (H894) Babel; descended of (i.e. From) Babylon, i.e. Born there; Zerubbabel, an Israelite -- Zerubbabel. see HEBREW (H2215) zarab see HEBREW (H894) Babel

column7: begotten in Babylon, leader of returning Israelite exiles
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H2216) Zrubbabel -- Zerubbabel. see HEBREW (H2216) Zrubbabel

column7: a wadi East of the Dead Sea
column9: From an unused root meaning to be exuberant in growth; lined with shrubbery; Zered, a brook East of the Dead Sea -- Zared, Zered.

column8: cast away, compass, disperse, fan, scatter away, spread, strew, winnow
column9: A primitive root (compare (H2114) zuwr); to toss about; by implication, to diffuse, winnow -- cast away, compass, disperse, fan, scatter (away), spread, strew, winnow. see HEBREW (H2114) zuwr

column8: arm, help, mighty, power, shoulder, strength
column9: Or (shortened) zroao {zer-o'-ah}; and (feminine) zrowpah {zer-o-aw'}; or zrowah {zer-o-aw'}; from (H2232) zara'; the arm (as stretched out), or (of animals) the foreleg; figuratively, force -- arm, + help, mighty, power, shoulder, strength. see HEBREW (H2232) zara'
From (H2232) zara'; something sown, i.e. A plant -- sowing, thing that is sown. see HEBREW (H2232) zara'
By reduplication from an unused root meaning to flow; a pouring rain -- water.
By reduplication from (H2115) zuwr; properly, tightly girt, i.e. Probably a racer, or some fleet animal (as being slender in the waist) -- + greyhound. see HEBREW (H2115) zuwr

column8: arise, rise up, as soon as it is up
column9: A primitive root; properly, to irradiate (or shoot forth beams), i.e. To rise (as the sun); specifically, to appear (as a symptom of leprosy) -- arise, rise (up), as soon as it is up.
From (H2224) zarach; a rising of light -- rising. see HEBREW (H2224) zarach

column7: three Israelites, also an Edomite, also an Ethiopian
column9: The same as (H2225) zerach; Zerach, the name of three Israelites, also of an Idumaean and an Ethiopian prince -- Zarah, Zerah. see HEBREW (H2225) zerach
Patronymically from (H2226) Zerach; a Zarchite or descendant of Zerach -- Zarchite. see HEBREW (H2226) Zerach
From (H2225) zerach and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has risen: Zerachjah, the name of two Israelites -- Zerahiah. see HEBREW (H2225) zerach see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: to pour forth in floods, flood away
column8: gush, carry away as with a flood, pour out
column9: A primitive root; to gush (as water) -- carry away as with a flood, pour out.

column7: a flood of rain, rainstorm, downpour
column9: From (H2229) zaram; a gush of water -- flood, overflowing, shower, storm, tempest. see HEBREW (H2229) zaram
Feminine of (H2230) zerem; a gushing of fluid (semen) -- issue. see HEBREW (H2230) zerem

column8: bear, conceive seed, set with sower, yield
column9: A primitive root; to sow; figuratively, to disseminate, plant, fructify -- bear, conceive seed, set with sow(-er), yield.
From (H2232) zara'; seed; figuratively, fruit, plant, sowing-time, posterity -- X carnally, child, fruitful, seed(-time), sowing- time. see HEBREW (H2232) zara'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2233) zera'; posterity -- seed. see HEBREW (H2233) zera'
Or zerason {zay-raw-ohn'}; from (H2232) zara'; something sown (only in the plural), i.e. A vegetable (as food) -- pulse. see HEBREW (H2232) zara'

column7: be here and there, scatter, sprinkle, strew
column8: be here and there, scatter, sprinkle, strew
column9: A primitive root; to sprinkle (fluid or solid particles) -- be here and there, scatter, sprinkle, strew.
A primitive root (compare (H2114) zuwr); perhaps to diffuse, i.e. (specifically) to sneeze -- sneeze. see HEBREW (H2114) zuwr
Of Persian origin; Zeresh, Haman's wife -- Zeresh.
From (H2219) zarah; the spread of the fingers, i.e. A span -- span. see HEBREW (H2219) zarah
Of uncertain derivation; Zattu, an Israelite -- Zattu.
Apparently a variation for (H2133) Zeythan; Zetham, an &? Israelite -- Zetham. see HEBREW (H2133) Zeythan
Of Persian origin; Zethar, a eunuch of Xerxes -- Zethar.
By contraction from (H2245) chabab; properly, a cherisher, i.e. The bosom -- bosom. see HEBREW (H2245) chabab
A primitive root (compare (H2245) chabab); to secrete -- X held, hide (self), do secretly. see HEBREW (H2245) chabab
A primitive root (compare (H2244) chaba', (H2247) chabah); properly, to hide (as in the bosom), i.e. To cherish (with affection) -- love. see HEBREW (H2244) chaba' see HEBREW (H2247) chabah
From (H2245) chabab; cherished; Chobab, father-in-law of Moses -- Hobab. see HEBREW (H2245) chabab
A primitive root (compare (H2245) chabab); to secrete -- hide (self). see HEBREW (H2245) chabab
(Aramaic) from (H2255) chabal; properly, overthrown, i.e. (morally) crime -- hurt. see HEBREW (H2255) chabal
From (H2266) chabar; united; Chabor, a river of Assyria -- Habor. see HEBREW (H2266) chabar

Or chabburah {khab-boo-raw'}; or chaburah {khab-oo-raw'}; from (H2266) chabar; properly, bound (with stripes), i.e. A weal (or black-and-blue mark itself) -- blueness, bruise, hurt, stripe, wound. see HEBREW (H2266) chabar
A primitive root; to knock out or off -- beat (off, out), thresh.
Or Chabayah {khab-aw-yaw'}; from (H2247) chabah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has hidden; Chabajah, an Israelite -- Habaiah. see HEBREW (H2247) chabah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H2247) chabah; a concealment -- hiding. see HEBREW (H2247) chabah

column8: band, bring forth, deal corruptly, destroy, offend, spoil,
column9: A primitive root; to wind tightly (as a rope), i.e. To bind; specifically, by a pledge; figuratively, to pervert, destroy; also to writhe in pain (especially of parturition) -- X at all, band, bring forth, (deal) corrupt(-ly), destroy, offend, lay &? To (take a) pledge, spoil, travail, X very, withhold.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2254) chabal; to ruin -- destroy, hurt. see HEBREW (H2254) chabal

column8: band, coast, company, cord, country, destruction, line, lot,
column9: Or chebel {khay'-bel}; from (H2254) chabal; a rope (as twisted), especially a measuring line; by implication, a district or inheritance (as measured); or a noose (as of cords); figuratively, a company (as if tied together); also a throe (especially of parturition); also ruin -- band, coast, company, cord, country, destruction, line, lot, pain, pang, portion, region, rope, snare, sorrow, tackling. see HEBREW (H2254) chabal
(Aramaic) from (H2255) chabal; harm (personal or pecuniary) -- damage, hurt. see HEBREW (H2255) chabal
Or (feminine) chabolah {khab-o-law'}; from (H2254) chabal; a pawn (as security for debt) -- pledge. see HEBREW (H2254) chabal
Active participle from (H2254) chabal (in the sense of handling ropes); a sailor -- pilot, shipmaster. see HEBREW (H2254) chabal
From (H2254) chabal (in the sense of furnished with ropes); a mast -- mast. see HEBREW (H2254) chabal
Of uncertain derivation; probably meadow-saffron -- rose.
Of uncertain derivation; Chabatstsanjah, a Rechabite -- Habazaniah.
A primitive root; to clasp (the hands or in embrace) -- embrace, fold.
From (H2263) chabaq; a clasping of the hands (in idleness) -- fold. see HEBREW (H2263) chabaq
By reduplication from (H2263) chabaq; embrace; Chabakkuk, the prophet -- Habakkuk. see HEBREW (H2263) chabaq

column7: to unite, be joined, to tie a magic knot or spell, to charm
column8: compact, couple together, have fellowship with, heap up, join self, together, league
column9: A primitive root; to join (literally or figuratively); specifically (by means of spells) to fascinate -- charm(- er), be compact, couple (together), have fellowship with, heap up, join (self, together), league.
From (H2266) chabar; a society; also a spell -- + charmer(- ing), company, enchantment, X wide. see HEBREW (H2266) chabar
The same as (H2267) cheber; community; Cheber, the name of a Kenite and of three Israelites -- Heber. see HEBREW (H2267) cheber
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H2266) chabar; an associate -- companion, fellow. see HEBREW (H2266) chabar
From (H2266) chabar; an associate -- companion, fellow, knit together. see HEBREW (H2266) chabar
From (H2266) chabar; a partner -- companion. see HEBREW (H2266) chabar
By reduplication from (H2266) chabar; a streak (like a line), as on the tiger -- spot. see HEBREW (H2266) chabar
(Aramaic) feminine of (H2269) chabar; an associate -- other. see HEBREW (H2269) chabar
Feminine of (H2267) cheber; association -- company. see HEBREW (H2267) cheber

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine
column7: association, league, a city in S. Judah
column9: From (H2267) cheber; seat of association; Chebron, a place in Palestine, also the name of two Israelites -- Hebron. see HEBREW (H2267) cheber
Or Chebroniy {kheb-ro-nee'}; patronymically from (H2275) Chebrown; Chebronite (collectively), an inhabitant of Chebron -- Hebronites. see HEBREW (H2275) Chebrown
Patronymically from (H2268) Cheber; a Chebrite (collectively) or descendants of Cheber -- Heberites. see HEBREW (H2268) Cheber
Feminine of (H2270) chaber; a consort -- companion. see HEBREW (H2270) chaber

column7: a thing that joins or is joined
column9: Feminine active participle of (H2266) chabar; a joint -- which coupleth, coupling. see HEBREW (H2266) chabar

column7: to bind, bind on, bind up
column8: bind up, gird about, govern, healer, put, saddle, wrap about
column9: A primitive root; to wrap firmly (especially a turban, compress, or saddle); figuratively, to stop, to rule -- bind (up), gird about, govern, healer, put, saddle, wrap about.
From an unused root probably meaning to cook (compare (H4227) machabath); something fried, probably a griddle-cake -- pan. see HEBREW (H4227) machabath

column7: a festival gathering, feast, pilgrim feast
column9: Or chag {khawg}; from (H2287) chagag; a festival, or a victim therefor -- (solemn) feast (day), sacrifice, solemnity. see HEBREW (H2287) chagag
From an unused root meaning to revolve (compare (H2287) chagag); properly, vertigo, i.e. (figuratively) fear -- terror. see HEBREW (H2287) chagag
Of uncertain derivation; a locust -- locust.
The same as (H2284) chagab; locust; Chagab, one of the Nethinim -- Hagab. see HEBREW (H2284) chagab
Or Chagabah {khag-aw-baw'}; feminine of (H2285) Chagab; locust; Chagaba or Chagabah, one of the Nethinim -- Hagaba, Hagabah. see HEBREW (H2285) Chagab

column7: to make a pilgrimage, keep a pilgrim feast
column8: celebrate, dance, keep, hold a solemn feast holiday, reel to and fro
column9: A primitive root (compare (H2283) chagra', (H2328) chuwg); properly, to move in a circle, i.e. (specifically) to march in a sacred procession, to observe a festival; by implication, to be giddy -- celebrate, dance, (keep, hold) a (solemn) feast (holiday), reel to and fro. see HEBREW (H2283) chagra' see HEBREW (H2328) chuwg
From an unused root meaning to take refuge; a rift in rocks -- cleft.
From (H2296) chagar; belted -- girded with. see HEBREW (H2296) chagar
Or chagor {khag-ore'}; and (feminine) chagowrah {khag-o-raw'}; or chagorah {khag-o-raw'}; from (H2296) chagar; a belt (for the waist) -- apron, armour, gird(-le). see HEBREW (H2296) chagar

column4: proper name, masculine; Adjective, of a people
column7: festal, a son of Gad, also his desc
column9: From (H2287) chagag; festive, Chaggi, an Israelite; also (patronymically) a Chaggite, or descendant of the same -- Haggi, Haggites. see HEBREW (H2287) chagag
From (H2282) chag; festive; Chaggai, a Heb. Prophet -- Haggai. see HEBREW (H2282) chag
From (H2282) chag and (H3050) Yahh; festival of Jah; Chaggijah, an Israelite -- Haggiah. see HEBREW (H2282) chag see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Feminine of (H2291) Chaggiy; festive; Chaggith, a wife of David -- Haggith. see HEBREW (H2291) Chaggiy

column7: partridge, a female descendant of Manasseh
column9: Of uncertain derivation; probably a partridge; Choglah, an Israelitess -- Hoglah. See also (H1031) Beyth Choglah. see HEBREW (H1031) Beyth Choglah

column7: to gird, gird on, gird oneself
column8: be able to put on, be afraid, appointed, gird, restrain, on every side
column9: A primitive root; to gird on (as a belt, armor, etc.) -- be able to put on, be afraid, appointed, gird, restrain, X on every side.
Abridged from (H259) 'echad; one -- one. see HEBREW (H259) 'echad
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2297) chad; as card. One; as article single; as an ordinal, first; adverbially, at once -- a, first, one, together. see HEBREW (H2297) chad
From (H2300) chadad; sharp -- sharp. see HEBREW (H2300) chadad
A primitive root; to be (causatively, make) sharp or (figuratively) severe -- be fierce, sharpen.
From (H2300) chadad; fierce; Chadad, an Ishmaelite -- Hadad. see HEBREW (H2300) chadad
A primitive root; to rejoice -- make glad, be joined, rejoice.
From (H2300) chadad; a point -- sharp. see HEBREW (H2300) chadad
From (H2302) chadah; rejoicing -- gladness, joy. see HEBREW (H2302) chadah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2304) chedvah -- joy. see HEBREW (H2304) chedvah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2373) chazeh; a breast -- breast. see HEBREW (H2373) chazeh
From (H2300) chadad; a peak; Chadid, a place in Palestine -- Hadid. see HEBREW (H2300) chadad

column8: cease, end, fall, forbear, forsake, leave off, let alone, rest,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be flabby, i.e. (by implication) desist; (figuratively) be lacking or idle -- cease, end, fall, forbear, forsake, leave (off), let alone, rest, be unoccupied, want.
From (H2308) chadal; rest, i.e. The state of the dead -- world. see HEBREW (H2308) chadal
From (H2308) chadal; vacant, i.e. Ceasing or destitute -- he that forbeareth, frail, rejected. see HEBREW (H2308) chadal
From (H2309) chedel; idle; Chadlai, an Israelite -- Hadlai. see HEBREW (H2309) chedel
From an unused root meaning to sting; a prickly plant -- brier, thorn.

column7: Hiddekel, ancient name of a Mesopotamian river
column9: Probably of foreign origin; the Chiddekel (or Tigris) river -- Hiddekel.
A primitive root; properly, to inclose (as a room), i.e. (by analogy,) to beset (as in a siege) -- enter a privy chamber.

column8: inner chamber, innermost part, parlor, south, within
column9: From (H2314) chadar; an apartment (usually literal) -- ((bed) inner)chamber, innermost(-ward) part, parlour, + south, X within. see HEBREW (H2314) chadar
Another form for (H2315) cheder; chamber; Chadar, an Ishmaelite -- Hadar. see HEBREW (H2315) cheder
Of uncertain derivation; Chadrak, a Syrian deity -- Hadrach.
A primitive root; to be new; causatively, to rebuild -- renew, repair.
From (H2318) chadash; new -- fresh, new thing. see HEBREW (H2318) chadash
From (H2318) chadash; the new moon; by implication, a month -- month(-ly), new moon. see HEBREW (H2318) chadash
The same as (H2320) chodesh; Chodesh, an Israelitess -- Hodesh. see HEBREW (H2320) chodesh
Feminine of (H2319) chadash; new; Chadashah, a place in Palestine -- Hadashah. see HEBREW (H2319) chadash
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2319) chadash; new -- new. see HEBREW (H2319) chadash
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2331) chavah; to show -- shew. see HEBREW (H2331) chavah
Also chayab {khaw-yab'}; a primitive root; properly, perhaps to tie, i.e. (figuratively and reflexively) to owe, or (by implication) to forfeit -- make endanger.
From (H2325) chuwb; debt -- debtor. see HEBREW (H2325) chuwb
Feminine active participle of (H2247) chabah; hiding place; Chobah, a place in Syria -- Hobah. see HEBREW (H2247) chabah

column7: to draw around, make a circle
column9: A primitive root (compare (H2287) chagag); to describe a circle -- compass. see HEBREW (H2287) chagag
From (H2328) chuwg; a circle -- circle, circuit, compass. see HEBREW (H2328) chuwg
A primitive root; properly, to tie a knot, i.e. (figuratively) to propound a riddle -- put forth.
A primitive root; (compare (H2324) chava', (H2421) chayah); properly, to live; by implication (intensively) to declare or show -- show. see HEBREW (H2324) chava' see HEBREW (H2421) chayah
Causatively from (H2331) chavah; life-giver; Chavvah (or Eve), the first woman -- Eve. see HEBREW (H2331) chavah
Properly, the same as (H2332) Chavvah (life-giving, i.e. Living-place); by implication, an encampment or village -- (small) town. see HEBREW (H2332) Chavvah

column7: tent villages of Jair, an area East of the Jordan
column9: From the plural of (H2333) chavvah and a modification of (H3265) Ya'uwr; hamlets of Jair, a region of Palestine -- (Bashan-)Havoth-jair. see HEBREW (H2333) chavvah see HEBREW (H3265) Ya'uwr
From (H2374) chozeh; visionary; Chozai, an Israelite -- the seers. see HEBREW (H2374) chozeh
From an unused root apparently meaning to pierce; a thorn; by analogy, a ring for the nose -- bramble, thistle, thorn.
Perhaps the same as (H2336) chowach; a dell or crevice (as if pierced in the earth) -- thicket. see HEBREW (H2336) chowach
(Aramaic) corresponding to the root of (H2339) chuwt, perhaps as a denominative; to string together, i.e. (figuratively) to repair -- join. see HEBREW (H2339) chuwt
From an unused root probably meaning to sew; a string; by implication, a measuring tape -- cord, fillet, line, thread.
Perhaps from (H2333) chavvah; a villager; a Chivvite, one of the aboriginal tribes of Palestine -- Hivite. see HEBREW (H2333) chavvah

column7: a son of Cush, also a son of Joktan, also territories of unc. location
column9: Probably from (H2342) chuwl; circular; Chavilah, the name of two or three eastern regions; also perhaps of two men -- Havilah. see HEBREW (H2342) chuwl

column8: bear, make to bring forth, make to calve, dance, drive away, fall grievously with pain
column9: Or chiyl {kheel}; a primitive root; properly, to twist or whirl (in a circular or spiral manner), i.e. (specifically) to dance, to writhe in pain (especially of parturition) or fear; figuratively, to wait, to pervert -- bear, (make to) bring forth, (make to) calve, dance, drive away, fall grievously (with pain), fear, form, great, grieve, (be) grievous, hope, look, make, be in pain, be much (sore) pained, rest, shake, shapen, (be) sorrow(-ful), stay, tarry, travail (with pain), tremble, trust, wait carefully (patiently), be wounded.

column8: Chul, a son of Aram; also the region settled by him
column9: From (H2342) chuwl; a circle; Chul, a son of Aram; also the region settled by him -- Hul. see HEBREW (H2342) chuwl
From (H2342) chuwl; sand (as round or whirling particles) -- sand. see HEBREW (H2342) chuwl
From an unused root meaning to be warm, i.e. (by implication) sunburnt or swarthy (blackish) -- brown.
Feminine active participle of an unused root apparently meaning to join; a wall of protection -- wall, walled.

column7: to pity, look upon with compassion
column9: A primitive root; properly, to cover, i.e. (figuratively) to compassionate -- pity, regard, spare.

column8: coast of the sea, haven, shore, seaside
column9: From an unused root meaning to cover; a cove (as a sheltered bay) -- coast (of the sea), haven, shore, (sea-)side.
From the same as (H2348) chowph; protection: Chupham, an Israelite -- Hupham. see HEBREW (H2348) chowph
Patronymically from (H2349) Chuwpham; a Chuphamite or descendant of Chupham -- Huphamites. see HEBREW (H2349) Chuwpham

column8: abroad, field, forth, highway, more, outside street, without
column9: Or (shortened) chuts {khoots}; (both forms feminine in the plural) from an unused root meaning to sever; properly, separate by a wall, i.e. Outside, outdoors -- abroad, field, forth, highway, more, out(-side, -ward), street, without.
Or (shortened) chur {khoor}; from an unused root probably meaning to bore; the crevice of a serpent; the cell of a prison -- hole.
From (H2357) chavar; white linen -- white. see HEBREW (H2357) chavar
The same as (H2353) chuwr or (H2352) chuwr; Chur, the name of four Israelites and one Midianite -- Hur. see HEBREW (H2353) chuwr see HEBREW (H2352) chuwr
The same as (H2353) chuwr; white linen -- network. Compare (H2715) chor. see HEBREW (H2353) chuwr see HEBREW (H2715) chor
Or (shortened) chor {khore}; the same as (H2352) chuwr; a cavity, socket, den -- cave, hole. see HEBREW (H2352) chuwr

column7: to be or grow white or pale
column9: A primitive root; to blanch (as with shame) -- wax pale.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H2357) chavar; white -- white. see HEBREW (H2357) chavar
Probably from (H2353) chuwr; linen-worker; Churi, an Israelite -- Huri. see HEBREW (H2353) chuwr
Probably an orthographical variation for (H2359) Chuwriy; Churai, an Israelite -- Hurai. see HEBREW (H2359) Chuwriy
Probably from (H2353) chuwr; whiteness, i.e. Noble; Churam, the name of an Israelite and two Syrians -- Huram. Compare (H2438) Chiyram. see HEBREW (H2353) chuwr see HEBREW (H2438) Chiyram

column7: a district Southeast of Mount Hermon
column9: Apparently from (H2357) chavar (in the sense of (H2352) chuwr); cavernous; Chavran, a region East of the Jordan -- Hauran. see HEBREW (H2357) chavar see HEBREW (H2352) chuwr
A primitive root; to hurry; figuratively, to be eager with excitement or enjoyment -- (make) haste(-n), ready.
From (H2363) chuwsh; haste; Chushah, an Israelite -- Hushah. see HEBREW (H2363) chuwsh
From (H2363) chuwsh; hasty; Chushai, an Israelite -- Hushai. see HEBREW (H2363) chuwsh

column4: proper name, feminine; proper name, masculine
column9: Or Chushiym {khoo-shem'}; or Chushim {khoo- sheem'}; plural from (H2363) chuwsh; hasters; Chushim, the name of three Israelites -- Hushim. see HEBREW (H2363) chuwsh
Or Chusham {khoo-shawm'}; from (H2363) chuwsh; hastily; Chusham, an Idumaean -- Husham. see HEBREW (H2363) chuwsh
Or chotham {kho-thawm'}; from (H2856) chatham; a signature-ring -- seal, signet. see HEBREW (H2856) chatham
The same as (H2368) chowtham; seal; Chotham, the name of two Israelites -- Hotham, Hothan. see HEBREW (H2368) chowtham

column8: behold, have a dream, see, be wont
column9: (Aramaic) or chazah (Aramaic) {khaz-aw'}; corresponding to (H2372) chazah; to gaze upon; mentally to dream, be usual (i.e. Seem) -- behold, have (a dream), see, be wont. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah

column7: God sees, a king of Aram (Syria)
column9: Or Chazahoel {khaz-aw-ale'}; from (H2372) chazah and (H410) 'el; God has seen; Chazael, a king of Syria -- Hazael. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah see HEBREW (H410) 'el
A primitive root; to gaze at; mentally, to perceive, contemplate (with pleasure); specifically, to have a vision of -- behold, look, prophesy, provide, see.
From (H2372) chazah; the breast (as most seen in front) -- breast. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah

column8: agreement, prophet, see that, seer, stargazer
column9: Active participle of (H2372) chazah; a beholder in vision; also a compact (as looked upon with approval) -- agreement, prophet, see that, seer, (star-)gazer. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah
From (H2372) chazah; seer; Chazo, a nephew of Abraham -- Hazo. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah
(Aramaic) from (H2370) chaza'; a sight -- look, vision. see HEBREW (H2370) chaza'
From (H2372) chazah; a sight (mentally), i.e. A dream, revelation, or oracle -- vision. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah
From (H2372) chazah; a revelation -- vision. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah
(Aramaic) from (H2370) chaza'; a view -- sight. see HEBREW (H2370) chaza'
From (H2372) chazah; a look; hence (figuratively) striking appearance, revelation, or (by implication) compact -- agreement, notable (one), vision. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah
From (H2372) chazah and (H410) 'el; seen of God; Chaziel, a Levite -- Haziel. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: Yah has seen, a descendant of Judah
column9: From (H2372) chazah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has seen; Chazajah, an Israelite -- Hazaiah. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H2372) chazah; vision; Chezjon, a Syrian -- Hezion. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah
From (H2372) chazah; a revelation, expectation by dream -- vision. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah
From an unused root meaning to glare; a flash of lightning -- bright cloud, lightning.
From an unused root probably meaning to enclose; a hog (perhaps as penned) -- boar, swine.
From the same as (H2386) chaziyr; perhaps protected; Chezir, the name of two Israelites -- Hezir. see HEBREW (H2386) chaziyr

column7: to be or grow firm or strong, strengthen
column8: aid, amend, catch, cleave, confirm, be constant, constrain,
column9: A primitive root; to fasten upon; hence, to seize, be strong (figuratively, courageous, causatively strengthen, cure, help, repair, fortify), obstinate; to bind, restrain, conquer -- aid, amend, X calker, catch, cleave, confirm, be constant, constrain, continue, be of good (take) courage(-ous, -ly), encourage (self), be established, fasten, force, fortify, make hard, harden, help, (lay) hold (fast), lean, maintain, play the man, mend, become (wax) mighty, prevail, be recovered, repair, retain, seize, be (wax) sore, strengthen (self), be stout, be (make, shew, wax) strong(-er), be sure, take (hold), be urgent, behave self valiantly, withstand.

column8: harder, hottest, impudent, loud, mighty, sore, stiff-hearted, stronger
column9: From (H2388) chazaq; strong (usu. In a bad sense, hard, bold, violent) -- harder, hottest, + impudent, loud, mighty, sore, stiff(-hearted), strong(-er). see HEBREW (H2388) chazaq
From (H2388) chazaq; powerful -- X wax louder, stronger. see HEBREW (H2388) chazaq
From (H2388) chazaq; help -- strength. see HEBREW (H2388) chazaq
From (H2388) chazaq; power -- strength. see HEBREW (H2388) chazaq
Feminine of (H2391) chezeq; prevailing power -- strength(- en self), (was) strong. see HEBREW (H2391) chezeq
Feminine of (H2392) chozeq; vehemence (usually in a bad sense) -- force, mightily, repair, sharply. see HEBREW (H2392) chozeq
From (H2388) chazaq; strong; Chizki, an Israelite -- Hezeki. see HEBREW (H2388) chazaq

column5: Chizqiyyah or Chizqiyyahu or Yechizqiyyah or Yechizqiyyahu
column7: Yah has strengthened, a king of Judah, also several other Isr
column9: Or Chizqiyahuw {khiz-kee-yaw'-hoo}; also Ychizqiyah {yekh-iz-kee-yaw'}; or Ychizqiyahuw {yekh-iz-kee-yaw'-hoo}; from (H2388) chazaq and (H3050) Yahh; strengthened of Jah; Chizkijah, a king of Judah, also the name of two other Israelites -- Hezekiah, Hizkiah, Hizkijah. Compare (H3169) Ychizqiyah. see HEBREW (H2388) chazaq see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh see HEBREW (H3169) Ychizqiyah
Once (Ezek. 29:4) chachiy {khakh-ee'}; from the same as (H2336) chowach; a ring for the nose (or lips) -- bracelet, chain, hook. see HEBREW (H2336) chowach

column8: bear the blame, cleanse, commit sin, by fault, harm he hath done, loss, miss
column9: A primitive root; properly, to miss; hence (figuratively and generally) to sin; by inference, to forfeit, lack, expiate, repent, (causatively) lead astray, condemn -- bear the blame, cleanse, commit (sin), by fault, harm he hath done, loss, miss, (make) offend(-er), offer for sin, purge, purify (self), make reconciliation, (cause, make) sin(-ful, -ness), trespass.

column8: fault, grievously, offence, punishment of sin
column9: From (H2398) chata'; a crime or its penalty -- fault, X grievously, offence, (punishment of) sin. see HEBREW (H2398) chata'

column4: Adjective; noun masculine; Adjective; noun masculine
column9: Intensively from (H2398) chata'; a criminal, or one accounted guilty -- offender, sinful, sinner. see HEBREW (H2398) chata'
Feminine of (H2399) chet'; an offence, or a sacrifice for it -- sin (offering). see HEBREW (H2399) chet'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2401) chata'ah; an offence, and the penalty or sacrifice for it -- sin (offering). see HEBREW (H2401) chata'ah

column8: punishment of sin, purification for sin, offering
column9: Or chattacth {khat-tawth'}; from (H2398) chata'; an offence (sometimes habitual sinfulness), and its penalty, occasion, sacrifice, or expiation; also (concretely) an offender -- punishment (of sin), purifying(-fication for sin), sin(-ner, offering). see HEBREW (H2398) chata'
