Feminine of (an equivalent to) (H2905) tuwr; a wall; hence, a fortress or a hamlet -- (goodly) castle, habitation, palace, row. see HEBREW (H2905) tuwr
From (H2926) talal; dew (as covering vegetation) -- dew. see HEBREW (H2926) talal
(Aramaic) the same as (H2919) tal -- dew. see HEBREW (H2919) tal
A primitive root; properly, to cover with pieces; i.e. (by implication) to spot or variegate (as tapestry) -- clouted, with divers colours, spotted.
Apparently from (H2921) tala' in the (orig.) Sense of covering (for protection); a lamb (compare (H2924) taleh) -- lamb. see HEBREW (H2921) tala' see HEBREW (H2924) taleh

column7: a place where Saul mustered his forces
column9: From the plural of (H2922) tla'; lambs; Telaim, a place in Palestine -- Telaim. see HEBREW (H2922) tla'
By variation for (H2922) tla'; a lamb -- lamb. see HEBREW (H2922) tla'
From (H2904) tuwl; overthrow or rejection -- captivity. see HEBREW (H2904) tuwl
A primitive root; properly, to strew over, i.e. (by implication) to cover in or plate (with beams) -- cover.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2926) talal; to cover with shade -- have a shadow. see HEBREW (H2926) talal

column7: an Israelite, also a place in the desert of Judah
column9: From an unused root meaning to break up or treat violently; oppression; Telem, the name of a place in Idumaea, also of a temple doorkeeper -- Telem.
From the same as (H2728) chargol; oppressive; Talmon, a temple doorkeeper -- Talmon. see HEBREW (H2728) chargol

column8: defile self, pollute self, be make, make self, pronounce unclean, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to be foul, especially in a ceremial or moral sense (contaminated) -- defile (self), pollute (self), be (make, make self, pronounce) unclean, X utterly.
From (H2930) tame'; foul in a relig. Sense -- defiled, + infamous, polluted(-tion), unclean. see HEBREW (H2930) tame'
From (H2930) tame'; religious impurity -- filthiness, unclean(-ness). see HEBREW (H2930) tame'
A collateral form of (H2930) tame'; to be impure in a religious sense -- be defiled, be reputed vile. see HEBREW (H2930) tame'
A primitive root; to hide (by covering over) -- hide, lay privily, in secret.
From an unused root probably meaning to weave; a basket (of interlaced osiers) -- basket.
A primitive root; to soil -- defile.
A primitive root; to wander;,causatively to lead astray -- seduce.
A primitive root; to taste; figuratively, to perceive -- X but, perceive, taste.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2938) ta'am; to taste; causatively to feed -- make to eat, feed. see HEBREW (H2938) ta'am

column8: advice, behavior, decree, discretion, judgment, reason, taste, understanding
column9: From (H2938) ta'am; properly, a taste, i.e. (figuratively) perception; by implication, intelligence; transitively, a mandate -- advice, behaviour, decree, discretion, judgment, reason, taste, understanding. see HEBREW (H2938) ta'am

column7: account, to be commanded, commandment, matter
column8: account, to be commanded, commandment, matter
column9: (Aramaic) from (H2939) t'am; properly, a taste, i.e. (as in (H2940) ta'am) a judicial sentence -- account, X to be commanded, commandment, matter. see HEBREW (H2939) t'am see HEBREW (H2940) ta'am

column8: chancellor, command, commandment, decree, regard, taste, wisdom
column9: (Aramaic) from (H2939) t'am, and equivalent to (H2941) ta'am; properly, flavor; figuratively, judgment (both subjective and objective); hence, account (both subj. And obj.) -- + chancellor, + command, commandment, decree, + regard, taste, wisdom. see HEBREW (H2939) t'am see HEBREW (H2941) ta'am
A primitive root; to load a beast -- lade.
A primitive root; to stab -- thrust through.
From (H2952) taphaph (perhaps referring to the tripping gait of children); a family (mostly used collectively in the singular) -- (little) children (ones), families. see HEBREW (H2952) taphaph

A primitive root; to flatten out or extend (as a tent); figuratively, to nurse a child (as promotive of growth); or perhaps a denom. From (H2947) tephach, from dandling on the palms -- span, swaddle. see HEBREW (H2947) tephach
From (H2946) taphach; a spread of the hand, i.e. A palm- breadth (not \"span\" of the fingers); architecturally, a corbel (as a supporting palm) -- coping, hand-breadth. see HEBREW (H2946) taphach
From (H2946) taphach (the same as (H2947) tephach) -- hand-breadth (broad). see HEBREW (H2946) taphach see HEBREW (H2947) tephach
From (H2946) taphach; nursing -- span long. see HEBREW (H2946) taphach

column7: to smear, plaster over, stick, glue
column9: A primitive root; properly, to stick on as a patch; figuratively, to impute falsely -- forge(-r), sew up.
Of foreign derivation; a military governor -- captain.

column7: to trip, take small quick steps
column9: A primitive root; apparently to trip (with short steps) coquettishly -- mince.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H6852) tsaphar, and meaning the same as (H6856) tsipporen; a finger-nail; also a hoof or claw -- nail. see HEBREW (H6852) tsaphar see HEBREW (H6856) tsipporen
A primitive root; properly, apparently to be thick; figuratively, to be stupid -- be fat.
Probably from (H5197) nataph; a dropping (of ointment); Taphath, an Israelitess -- Taphath. see HEBREW (H5197) nataph
A primitive root; to drive on; figuratively, to follow close -- continual.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2956) tarad; to expel -- drive. see HEBREW (H2956) tarad
A variation of (H2962) terem; not yet -- before. see HEBREW (H2962) terem
A primitive root; to overburden -- weary.
From (H2959) tarach; a burden -- cumbrance, trouble. see HEBREW (H2959) tarach
From an unused root apparently meaning to be moist; properly, dripping; hence, fresh (i.e. Recently made such) -- new, putrefying.
From an unused root apparently meaning to interrupt or suspend; properly, non-occurrence; used adverbially, not yet or before -- before, ere, not yet.

column8: catch, without doubt, feed, rend in pieces, surely, tear in pieces
column9: A primitive root; to pluck off or pull to pieces; causatively to supply with food (as in morsels) -- catch, X without doubt, feed, ravin, rend in pieces, X surely, tear (in pieces).
From (H2963) taraph; something torn, i.e. A fragment, e.g. A fresh leaf, prey, food -- leaf, meat, prey, spoil. see HEBREW (H2963) taraph
From (H2963) taraph; recently torn off, i.e. Fresh -- pluckt off. see HEBREW (H2963) taraph
Feminine (collectively) of (H2964) tereph; prey, i.e. Flocks devoured by animals -- ravin, (that which was) torn (of beasts, in pieces). see HEBREW (H2964) tereph
(Aramaic) from a name of foreign derivation; a Tarpelite (collectively) or inhabitants of Tarpel, a place in Assyria -- Tarpelites.
A primitive root; to desire -- long.
A primitive root; to be suitable -- appertain.

column7: Yah hears, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or Ya.azanyahuw {yah-az-an-yaw'-hoo}; from (H238) 'azan and (H3050) Yahh; heard of Jah; Jaazanjah, the name of four Israelites -- Jaazaniah. Compare (H3153) Yzanyah. see HEBREW (H238) 'azan see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh see HEBREW (H3153) Yzanyah
From (H215) 'owr; enlightener; Jair, the name of four Israelites -- Jair. see HEBREW (H215) 'owr
Patronymically from (H2971) Ya'iyr; a Jairite or descendant of Jair -- Jairite. see HEBREW (H2971) Ya'iyr
A primitive root; properly, to be slack, i.e. (figuratively) to be foolish -- dote, be (become, do) foolish(-ly).

column7: to show willingness, be pleased, determine, undertake (to do anything)
column8: assay, begin, be content, please, take upon, willingly, would
column9: A primitive root (probably rather the same as (H2973) ya'al through the idea of mental weakness); properly, to yield, especially assent; hence (pos.) To undertake as an act of volition -- assay, begin, be content, please, take upon, X willingly, would. see HEBREW (H2973) ya'al

Of Egyptian origin; a channel, e.g. A fosse, canal, shaft; specifically the Nile, as the one river of Egypt, including its collateral trenches; also the Tigris, as the main river of Assyria -- brook, flood, river, stream.

column8: cause to despair, one that is desperate, be no hope
column9: A primitive root; to desist, i.e. (figuratively) to despond -- (cause to) despair, one that is desperate, be no hope.
Or {yo-she-yaw'-hoo}; from the same root as (H803) 'ashuwyah and (H3050) Yahh; founded of Jah; Joshijah, the name of two Israelites -- Josiah. see HEBREW (H803) 'ashuwyah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H857) 'athah; an entry -- entrance. see HEBREW (H857) 'athah
From the same as (H871) 'Athariym; stepping; Jeatherai, an Israelite -- Jeaterai. see HEBREW (H871) 'Athariym

column7: to cry in a shrill voice
column9: A primitive root; to bawl -- cry out.
From (H2986) yabal; produce, i.e. A crop or (figuratively) wealth -- fruit, increase. see HEBREW (H2986) yabal
From (H947) buwc; trodden, i.e. Threshing-place; Jebus, the aboriginal name of Jerusalem -- Jebus. see HEBREW (H947) buwc
Patrial from (H2982) Ybuwc; a Jebusite or inhabitant of Jebus -- Jebusite(-s). see HEBREW (H2982) Ybuwc

column7: He chooses, a son of David
column9: From (H977) bachar; choice; Jibchar, an Israelite -- Ibhar. see HEBREW (H977) bachar

column7: one who is intelligent, two Canaanite kings
column9: From (H995) biyn; intelligent; Jabin, the name of two Canaanitish kings -- Jabin. see HEBREW (H995) biyn
A primitive root; properly, to flow; causatively, to bring (especially with pomp) -- bring (forth), carry, lead (forth).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H2986) yabal; to bring -- bring, carry. see HEBREW (H2986) yabal
From (H2986) yabal; a stream -- (water-)course, stream. see HEBREW (H2986) yabal
The same as (H2988) yabal; Jabal, an antediluvian -- Jabal. see HEBREW (H2988) yabal
From (H2986) yabal; having running sores -- wen. see HEBREW (H2986) yabal
From (H1104) bala' and (H5971) am; devouring people; Jibleam, a place in Palestine -- Ibleam. see HEBREW (H1104) bala' see HEBREW (H5971) am

column7: to perform the duty of a husband\'s brother
column8: perform the duty of a husband\'s brother, marry
column9: A primitive root of doubtful meaning; used only as a denominative from (H2993) yabam; to marry a (deceased) brother's widow -- perform the duty of a husband's brother, marry. see HEBREW (H2993) yabam
From (the orig. Of) (H2992) yabam; a brother-in-law -- husband's brother. see HEBREW (H2992) yabam
Feminine participle of (H2992) yabam; a sister-in-law -- brother's wife, sister in law. see HEBREW (H2992) yabam

column7: El causes to build, two cities in Isr
column9: From (H1129) banah and (H410) 'el: built of God; Jabneel, the name of two places in Palestine -- Jabneel. see HEBREW (H1129) banah see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: he causes to build, a Philistine city
column9: From (H1129) banah; a building; Jabneh, a place in Palestine -- Jabneh. see HEBREW (H1129) banah
From (H1129) banah and (H3050) Yahh; built of Jah; Jibnejah, an Israelite -- Ibneiah. see HEBREW (H1129) banah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H1129) banah and (H3050) Yahh; building of Jah; Jibnijah, an Israelite -- Ibnijah. see HEBREW (H1129) banah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: a river East of the Jordan
column9: Probably from (H1238) baqaq; pouring forth; Jabbok, a river east of the Jordan -- Jabbok. see HEBREW (H1238) baqaq

column7: Yah blesses, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H1288) barak and (H3050) Yahh: blessed of Jah; Jeberekjah, an Israelite -- Jeberechiah. see HEBREW (H1288) barak see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: to be dry, dried up, or withered
column8: be ashamed, clean, be confounded, make dry up, do shamefully, utterly, wither away
column9: A primitive root; to be ashamed, confused or disappointed; also (as failing) to dry up (as water) or wither (as herbage) -- be ashamed, clean, be confounded, (make) dry (up), (do) shame(-fully), X utterly, wither (away).
From (H3001) yabesh; dry -- dried (away), dry. see HEBREW (H3001) yabesh

column4: proper name, of a location; location; person
column7: a place in Gilead, also an Israelite
column9: The same as (H3002) yabesh (also Yabeysh {yaw-bashe'}; often with the addition of (H1568) Gil'ad, i.e. Jabesh of Gilad); Jobesh, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine -- Jobesh ((-Gilead)). see HEBREW (H3002) yabesh see HEBREW (H1568) Gil'ad
From (H3001) yabesh; dry ground -- dry (ground, land). see HEBREW (H3001) yabesh
From the same as (H1314) besem; fragrant; Jibsam, an Israelite -- Jibsam. see HEBREW (H1314) besem
A variation of (H3004) yabbashah; dry ground -- dry land. see HEBREW (H3004) yabbashah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3006) yabbesheth; dry land -- earth. see HEBREW (H3006) yabbesheth
From (H1350) ga'al; avenger; Jigal, the name of three Israelites -- Igal, Igeal. see HEBREW (H1350) ga'al
A primitive root; to dig or plow -- husbandman.
From (H3009) yagab; a plowed field -- field. see HEBREW (H3009) yagab
Feminine from (H1361) gabahh; hillock; Jogbehah, a place East of the Jordan -- Jogbehah. see HEBREW (H1361) gabahh

column7: Yah is great, an Israelite prophet
column9: From (H1431) gadal and (H3050) Yahh; magnified of Jah; Jigdaljah, an Israelite -- Igdaliah. see HEBREW (H1431) gadal see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column8: afflict, cause grief, grieve, sorrowful, vex
column9: A primitive root; to grieve -- afflict, cause grief, grieve, sorrowful, vex.
A primitive root (probably rather the same as (H3013) yagah through the common idea of dissatisfaction); to push away; -be removed. see HEBREW (H3013) yagah
From (H3013) yagah; affliction -- grief, sorrow. see HEBREW (H3013) yagah
From (H3025) yagor; fearful -- afraid, fearest. see HEBREW (H3025) yagor
Probably from (H1481) guwr; a lodging; Jagur, a place in Palestine -- Jagur. see HEBREW (H1481) guwr
From (H3021) yaga'; toil; hence, a work, produce, property (as the result of labor) -- labour, work. see HEBREW (H3021) yaga'
From (H3021) yaga'; tired -- weary. see HEBREW (H3021) yaga'
From (H1540) galah; exiled; Jogli, an Israelite -- Jogli. see HEBREW (H1540) galah

column7: to toil, grow or be weary
column8: faint, make to labor, be weary
column9: A primitive root; properly, to gasp; hence, to be exhausted, to tire, to toil -- faint, (make to) labour, (be) weary.

column8: earnings as the product of toil
column9: From (H3021) yaga'; earnings (as the product of toil); -that which he laboured for. see HEBREW (H3021) yaga'
From (H3021) yaga'; tired; hence (transitive) tiresome -- full of labour, weary. see HEBREW (H3021) yaga'
Feminine of (H3019) yagiya'; fatigue -- weariness. see HEBREW (H3019) yagiya'
A primitive root; to fear -- be afraid, fear.

column7: heap (of stones) of the testimony,  a memorial of Jacob and Laban
column9: (Aramaic) from a word derived from an unused root (meaning to gather) and a derivation of a root corresponding to (H7717) sahed; heap of the testimony; Jegar-Sahadutha, a cairn East of the Jordan -- Jegar-Sahadutha. see HEBREW (H7717) sahed

column8: be able, about, armholes, at, axletree, because of, beside, border,

(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3027) yad -- hand, power. see HEBREW (H3027) yad
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3034) yadah; to praise -- (give) thank(-s). see HEBREW (H3034) yadah
Of uncertain derivation; Jidalah, a place in Palestine -- Idalah.
From the same as (H1706) dbash; perhaps honeyed; Jidbash, an Israelite -- Idbash. see HEBREW (H1706) dbash
A primitive root; properly, to handle (compare (H3034) yadah), i.e. To throw, e.g. Lots -- cast. see HEBREW (H3034) yadah
From (H3039) ydiyd; properly, affection; concretely, a darling object -- dearly beloved. see HEBREW (H3039) ydiyd

column8: cast out, make confession, praise, shoot, give thankful,
column9: A primitive root; used only as denominative from (H3027) yad; literally, to use (i.e. Hold out) the hand; physically, to throw (a stone, an arrow) at or away; especially to revere or worship (with extended hands); intensively, to bemoan (by wringing the hands) -- cast (out), (make) confess(-ion), praise, shoot, (give) thank(-ful, -s, -sgiving). see HEBREW (H3027) yad
From (H3034) yadah; praised; Jiddo, an Israelite -- Iddo. see HEBREW (H3034) yadah

column7: a builder of the Jerusalem wall
column9: From (H3034) yadah; thankful; Jadon, an Israelite -- Jadon. see HEBREW (H3034) yadah
From (H3045) yada'; knowing; Jaddua, the name of two Israelites -- Jaddua. see HEBREW (H3045) yada'

column7: leader of a choir of the temple
column9: Or Yduthuwn {yed-oo-thoon'}; or Ydiythuwn {yed-ee-thoon'}; probably from (H3034) yadah; laudatory; Jeduthun, an Israelite -- Jeduthun. see HEBREW (H3034) yadah
From the same as (H1730) dowd; loved -- amiable, (well-)beloved, loves. see HEBREW (H1730) dowd
Feminine of (H3039) ydiyd; beloved; Jedidah, an Israelitess -- Jedidah. see HEBREW (H3039) ydiyd

column9: From (H3039) ydiyd and (H3050) Yahh; beloved of Jah; Jedidejah, a name of Solomon -- Jedidiah. see HEBREW (H3039) ydiyd see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H3034) yadah and (H3050) Yahh; praised of Jah; Jedajah, the name of two Israelites -- Jedaiah. see HEBREW (H3034) yadah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H3045) yada' and (H410) 'el; knowing God; Jediael, the name of three Israelites -- Jediael. see HEBREW (H3045) yada' see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From (H1811) dalaph; tearful; Jidlaph, a Mesopotamian -- Jidlaph. see HEBREW (H1811) dalaph

column8: acknowledge, acquainted with, advise, answer, appoint, assuredly, be aware
column9: A primitive root; to know (properly, to ascertain by seeing); used in a great variety of senses, figuratively, literally, euphemistically and inferentially (including observation, care, recognition; and causatively, instruction, designation, punishment, etc.) (as follow) -- acknowledge, acquaintance(-ted with), advise, answer, appoint, assuredly, be aware, (un-)awares, can(-not), certainly, comprehend, consider, X could they, cunning, declare, be diligent, (can, cause to) discern, discover, endued with, familiar friend, famous, feel, can have, be (ig-)norant, instruct, kinsfolk, kinsman, (cause to let, make) know, (come to give, have, take) knowledge, have (knowledge), (be, make, make to be, make self) known, + be learned, + lie by man, mark, perceive, privy to, X prognosticator, regard, have respect, skilful, shew, can (man of) skill, be sure, of a surety, teach, (can) tell, understand, have (understanding), X will be, wist, wit, wot.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3045) yada' -- certify, know, make known, teach. see HEBREW (H3045) yada'

column7: the shrewd one, a man of Judah
column9: From (H3045) yada'; knowing; Jada, an Israelite -- Jada. see HEBREW (H3045) yada'

From (H3045) yada'; properly, a knowing one; specifically, a conjurer; (by impl) a ghost -- wizard. see HEBREW (H3045) yada'

column9: Contraction for (H3068) Yhovah, and meaning the same; Jah, the sacred name -- Jah, the Lord, most vehement. Compare names in \"-iah,\" \"- jah.\" see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah

column8: ascribe, bring, come on, give, go, set, take
column9: A primitive root; to give (whether literal or figurative); generally, to put; imperatively (reflexive) come -- ascribe, bring, come on, give, go, set, take.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3051) yahab; -deliver, give, lay, + prolong, pay, yield. see HEBREW (H3051) yahab
From (H3051) yahab; properly, what is given (by Providence), i.e. A lot -- burden. see HEBREW (H3051) yahab
Denominative from a form corresponding to (H3061) Yhuwd; to Judaize, i.e. Become Jewish -- become Jews. see HEBREW (H3061) Yhuwd
A briefer form of one corresponding to (H3061) Yhuwd; Jehud, a place in Palestine -- Jehud. see HEBREW (H3061) Yhuwd
Perhaps from a form corresponding to (H3061) Yhuwd; Judaistic; Jehdai, an Israelite -- Jehdai. see HEBREW (H3061) Yhuwd
Feminine of (H3064) Yhuwdiy; Jehudijah, a Jewess: see HEBREW (H3064) Yhuwdiy

column9: From (H3068) Yhovah and (H1931) huw'; Jehovah (is) He; Jehu, the name of five Israelites -- Jehu. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H1931) huw'

column7: Yah has grasped, the name of several Israelites

(Aramaic) patrial from (H3061) Yhuwd; a Jehudaite (or Judaite), i.e. Jew -- Jew. see HEBREW (H3061) Yhuwd

column7: probably "praised", a son of Jacob, also his desc., the S. kingdom, also four Israelites
column9: From (H3034) yadah; celebrated; Jehudah (or Judah), the name of five Israelites; also of the tribe descended from the first, and of its territory -- Judah. see HEBREW (H3034) yadah
Patronymically from (H3063) Yhuwdah; a Jehudite (i.e. Judaite or Jew), or descendant of Jehudah (i.e. Judah) -- Jew. see HEBREW (H3063) Yhuwdah
The same as (H3064) Yhuwdiy; Jehudi, an Israelite -- Jehudi. see HEBREW (H3064) Yhuwdiy
Feminine of (H3064) Yhuwdiy; the Jewish (used adverbially) language -- in the Jews' language. see HEBREW (H3064) Yhuwdiy

From (H3068) Yhovah and (H7200) ra'ah; Jehovah will see (to it); Jehovah-Jireh, a symbolical name for Mount Moriah -- Jehovah- jireh. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah

From (H3068) Yhovah and (H5251) nec with the prononimal suffix; Jehovah (is) my banner; Jehovah-Nissi, a symbolical name of an altar in the Desert -- Jehovah-nissi. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H5251) nec

From (H3068) Yhovah and (H7965) shalowm; Jehovah (is) peace; Jehovah-Shalom, a symbolical name of an altar in Palestine: see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H7965) shalowm

From (H3068) Yhovah and (H8033) sham with directive enclitic; Jehovah (is) thither; Jehovah-Shammah, a symbolic title of Jerusalem -- Jehovah-shammah. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H8033) sham

column9: From (H3068) Yhovah and (H3045) yada'; Jehovah-known; Jehojada, the name of three Israelites -- Jehoiada. Compare (H3111) Yowyada'. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H3045) yada' see HEBREW (H3111) Yowyada'

column7: the LORD is noble, a Rechabite, also a nephew of David

column9: Or Yhowaddan {yeh-ho-ad-dawn'}; from (H3068) Yhovah and (H5727) adan; Jehovah-pleased; Jehoaddin or Jehoaddan, an Israelitess -- Jehoaddan. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H5727) adan

column9: From (H3068) Yhovah and (H7311) ruwm; Jehovah-raised; Jehoram, the name of a Syrian and of three Israelites -- Jehoram, Joram. Compare (H3141) Yowram. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H7311) ruwm see HEBREW (H3141) Yowram

column9: From (H3068) Yhovah and (H7650) shaba'; Jehovah-sworn; Jehosheba, an Israelitess -- Jehosheba. Compare (H3090) Yhowshab'ath. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H7650) shaba' see HEBREW (H3090) Yhowshab'ath
A form of (H3089) Yhowsheba'; Jehoshabath, an Israelitess -- Jehoshabeath. see HEBREW (H3089) Yhowsheba'

column9: Or Yhowshua {yeh-ho-shoo'-ah}; from (H3068) Yhovah and (H3467) yasha'; Jehovah-saved; Jehoshua (i.e. Joshua), the Jewish leader -- Jehoshua, Jehoshuah, Joshua. Compare (H1954) Howshea', (H3442) Yeshuwa'. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H3467) yasha' see HEBREW (H1954) Howshea' see HEBREW (H3442) Yeshuwa'

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, of a location

column9: From (H1984) halal and (H410) 'el; praising God; Jehallelel, the name of two Israelites -- Jehalellel, Jehalelel. see HEBREW (H1984) halal see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: (a precious stone) perhaps jasper or onyx
column9: From (H1986) halam (in the sense of hardness); a precious stone, probably onyx -- diamond. see HEBREW (H1986) halam
Or Yahtsah {yah'-tsaw}; or (feminine) Yahtsah {yah-tsaw'}; from an unused root meaning to stamp; perhaps threshing-floor; Jahats or Jahtsah, a place East of the Jordan -- Jahaz, Jahazah, Jahzah.

column7: the LORD is father, three Israelites
column9: From (H3068) Yhovah and (H1) 'ab; Jehovah-fathered; Joab, the name of three Israelites -- Joab. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H1) 'ab

column9: From (H3068) Yhovah and (H251) 'ach; Jehovah-brothered; Joach, the name of four Israelites -- Joah. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H251) 'ach

column9: From (H3068) Yhovah and (H410) 'el; Jehovah (is his) God; Joel, the name of twelve Israelites -- Joel. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H410) 'el

Perhaps a form of (H3103) Yowbab, but more probably by erroneous transcription for (H3437) Yashuwb; Job, an Israelite -- Job. see HEBREW (H3103) Yowbab see HEBREW (H3437) Yashuwb

From (H2986) yabal; a stream -- river. see HEBREW (H2986) yabal
From (H2986) yabal; stream; Jubal, an antediluvian -- Jubal. see HEBREW (H2986) yabal
A form of (H3075) Yhowzabad; Jozabad, the name of ten Israelites -- Josabad, Jozabad. see HEBREW (H3075) Yhowzabad

column9: From (H3068) Yhovah and (H2142) zakar; Jehovah-remembered; Jozacar, an Israelite -- Jozachar. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H2142) zakar
Probably from (H3068) Yhovah and a variation of (H2421) chayah; Jehovah-revived; Jocha, the name of two Israelites -- Joha. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H2421) chayah

A form of (H3078) Yhowyakiyn; Jojakin, an Israelite king -- Jehoiachin. see HEBREW (H3078) Yhowyakiyn
A form of (H3079) Yhowyaqiym; Jojakim, an Israelite -- Joiakim. Compare (H3137) Yowqiym. see HEBREW (H3079) Yhowyaqiym see HEBREW (H3137) Yowqiym
A form of (H3080) Yhowyariyb; Jojarib, the name of four Israelites -- Joiarib. see HEBREW (H3080) Yhowyariyb

column9: From (H3068) Yhovah contracted and (H3513) kabad; Jehovah-gloried; Jokebed, the mother of Moses -- Jochebed. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H3513) kabad
A form of (H3081) Yhuwkal; Jukal, an Israelite -- Jucal. see HEBREW (H3081) Yhuwkal

column8: age, always, continually, daily, birth, each, today,
column9: From an unused root meaning to be hot; a day (as the warm hours), whether literal (from sunrise to sunset, or from one sunset to the next), or figurative (a space of time defined by an associated term), (often used adverb) -- age, + always, + chronicals, continually(-ance), daily, ((birth-), each, to) day, (now a, two) days (agone), + elder, X end, + evening, + (for) ever(-lasting, -more), X full, life, as (so) long as (... Live), (even) now, + old, + outlived, + perpetually, presently, + remaineth, X required, season, X since, space, then, (process of) time, + as at other times, + in trouble, weather, (as) when, (a, the, within a) while (that), X whole (+ age), (full) year(-ly), + younger.

From (H3117) yowm; daily -- daily, (by, in the) day(-time). see HEBREW (H3117) yowm

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, of a people

A form of (H3082) Yhownadab; Jonadab, the name of an Israelite and of a Rechabite -- Jonadab. see HEBREW (H3082) Yhownadab
Probably from the same as (H3196) yayin; a dove (apparently from the warmth of their mating) -- dove, pigeon. see HEBREW (H3196) yayin
The same as (H3123) yownah; Jonah, an Israelite -- Jonah. see HEBREW (H3123) yownah
Patronymically from (H3121) yaven; a Jevanite, or descendant of Javan -- Grecian. see HEBREW (H3121) yaven
Active participle of (H3243) yanaq; a sucker; hence, a twig (of a tree felled and sprouting) -- tender plant. see HEBREW (H3243) yanaq
Feminine of (H3126) yowneq; a sprout -- (tender) branch, young twig. see HEBREW (H3126) yowneq

column9: From (H3123) yownah and (H482) 'elem and the plural of (H7350) rachowq; dove of (the) silence (i.e. Dumb Israel) of (i.e. Among) distances (i.e. Strangers); the title of a ditty (used for a name of its melody) -- Jonath-elem-rechokim. see HEBREW (H3123) yownah see HEBREW (H482) 'elem see HEBREW (H7350) rachowq
A form of (H3083) Yhownathan; Jonathan, the name of ten Israelites -- Jonathan. see HEBREW (H3083) Yhownathan

column7: he increases, a son of Jacob, also the name of several Israelites
column9: Future of (H3254) yacaph; let him add (or perhaps simply active participle adding); Joseph, the name of seven Israelites -- Joseph. Compare (H3084) Yhowceph. see HEBREW (H3254) yacaph see HEBREW (H3084) Yhowceph
From active participle of (H3254) yacaph and (H3050) Yahh; Jah (is) adding; Josiphjah, an Israelite -- Josiphiah. see HEBREW (H3254) yacaph see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: may He avail, one of David\'s heroes
column9: Perhaps feminine active participle of (H3276) ya'al; furthermore; Joelah, an Israelite -- Joelah. see HEBREW (H3276) ya'al

column7: the LORD is a witness, a Benjamite
column9: Apparently the active participle of (H3259) ya'ad; appointer; Joed, an Israelite -- Joed. see HEBREW (H3259) ya'ad

column7: the LORD is a help, one of David\'s mighty men
column9: From (H3068) Yhovah and (H5828) ezer; Jehovah (is his) help; Joezer, an Israelite -- Joezer. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H5828) ezer

column7: the LORD has aided, two Israelites
column9: From (H3068) Yhovah and (H5789) uwsh; Jehovah-hastened; Joash, the name of two Israelites -- Joash. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H5789) uwsh
A form of (H3087) Yhowtsadaq; Jotsadak, an Israelite -- Jozadak. see HEBREW (H3087) Yhowtsadaq
A form of (H3113) Yowyaqiym; Jokim, an Israelite -- Jokim. see HEBREW (H3113) Yowyaqiym
Active participle of (H3384) yarah; sprinkling; hence, a sprinkling (or autumnal showers) -- first rain, former (rain). see HEBREW (H3384) yarah
From (H3384) yarah; rainy; Jorah, an Israelite -- Jorah. see HEBREW (H3384) yarah
From (H3384) yarah; rainy; Jorai, an Israelite -- Jorai. see HEBREW (H3384) yarah
A form of (H3088) Yhowram; Joram, the name of three Israelites and one Syrian -- Joram. see HEBREW (H3088) Yhowram
From (H7725) shuwb and (H2617) checed; kindness will be returned; Jushab-Chesed, an Israelite -- Jushab-hesed. see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb see HEBREW (H2617) checed

column7: Yah causes to dwell, a Simeonite
column9: From (H3427) yashab and (H3050) Yahh; Jehovah will cause to dwell; Josibjah, an Israelite -- Josibiah. see HEBREW (H3427) yashab see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Probably a form of (H3145) Yowshavyah; Joshah, an Israelite -- Joshah. see HEBREW (H3145) Yowshavyah
From (H3068) Yhovah and (H7737) shavah; Jehovah-set; Joshavjah, an Israelite -- Joshaviah. Compare (H3144) Yowshah. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H7737) shavah see HEBREW (H3144) Yowshah
A form of (H3092) Yhowshaphat; Joshaphat, an Israelite -- Joshaphat. see HEBREW (H3092) Yhowshaphat

column7: the LORD is perfect, three Israelites
column9: From (H3068) Yhovah and (H8535) tam; Jehovah (is) perfect; Jotham, the name of three Israelites -- Jotham. see HEBREW (H3068) Yhovah see HEBREW (H8535) tam
Active participle of (H3498) yathar; properly, redundant; hence, over and above, as adjective, noun, adverb or conjunction (as follows) -- better, more(-over), over, profit. see HEBREW (H3498) yathar
From an unused root (meaning to sprinkle) and (H410) 'el; sprinkled of God; Jezavel, an Israelite -- Jeziel (from the margin). see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From the same as the first part of (H3149) Yzav'el and (H3050) Yahh; sprinkled of Jah; Jizzijah, an Israelite -- Jeziah. see HEBREW (H3149) Yzav'el see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From the same as (H2123) ziyz; he will make prominent; Jaziz, an Israelite -- Jaziz. see HEBREW (H2123) ziyz
Perhaps from an unused root (meaning to draw up); he will draw out; Jizliah, an Israelite -- Jezliah.
Or Yzanyahuw {yez-an-yaw'-hoo}; probably for (H2970) Ya'azanyah; Jezanjah, an Israelite -- Jezaniah. see HEBREW (H2970) Ya'azanyah
From an unused root mean to ooze; sweat, i.e. (by implication) a sweating dress -- any thing that causeth sweat.

column7: a descriptive title for one of David\'s men
column9: A variation for (H250) 'Ezrachiy; a Jizrach (i.e. Ezrachite or Zarchite) or descendant of Zerach -- Izrahite. see HEBREW (H250) 'Ezrachiy
From (H2224) zarach and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will shine; Jizrachjah, the name of two Israelites -- Izrahiah, Jezrahiah. see HEBREW (H2224) zarach see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine a.
column7: God sows, two Israelites, also two cities in Isr., also a valley in Northern Israel
column9: From (H2232) zara' and (H410) 'el; God will sow; Jizreel, the name of two places in Palestine and of two Israelites -- Jezreel. see HEBREW (H2232) zara' see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Patronymically from (H3157) Yizr'e'l; a Jizreelite or native of Jizreel -- Jezreelite. see HEBREW (H3157) Yizr'e'l
Feminine of (H3158) Yizr'e'liy; a Jezreelitess -- Jezreelitess. see HEBREW (H3158) Yizr'e'liy
From (H2247) chabah; hidden; Jechubbah, an Israelite -- Jehubbah. see HEBREW (H2247) chabah
A primitive root; to be (or become) one -- join, unite.

column8: alike, at all once, both, likewise, only, altogether, withal
column9: From (H3161) yachad; properly, a unit, i.e. (adverb) unitedly -- alike, at all (once), both, likewise, only, (al-)together, withal. see HEBREW (H3161) yachad
From (H3162) yachad with pronominal suffix; his unity, i.e. (adverb) together; Jachdo, an Israelite -- Jahdo. see HEBREW (H3162) yachad
From (H3162) yachad and (H410) 'el; unity of God; Jachdiel, an Israelite -- Jahdiel. see HEBREW (H3162) yachad see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: may Yah give joy, two Israelites
column9: From (H3162) yachad and (H3050) Yahh; unity of Jah; Jechdijah, the name of two Israelites -- Jehdeiah. see HEBREW (H3162) yachad see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: God sees, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H2372) chazah and (H410) 'el; beheld of God; Jachaziel, the name of five Israelites -- Jahaziel, Jahziel. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From (H2372) chazah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will behold; Jachzejah, an Israelite -- Jahaziah. see HEBREW (H2372) chazah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H2388) chazaq and (H410) 'el; God will strengthen; Jechezkel, the name of two Israelites -- Ezekiel, Jehezekel. see HEBREW (H2388) chazaq see HEBREW (H410) 'el

Or Ychizqiyahuw {yekh-iz-kee-yaw'- hoo}; from (H3388) Yruwsha' and (H3050) Yahh; strengthened of Jah; Jechizkijah, the name of five Israelites -- Hezekiah, Jehizkiah. Compare (H2396) Chizqiyah. see HEBREW (H3388) Yruwsha' see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh see HEBREW (H2396) Chizqiyah
From the same as (H2386) chaziyr; perhaps protection; Jachzerah, an Israelite -- Jahzerah. see HEBREW (H2386) chaziyr

column7: may God live, the name of a number of Isr
column9: Or (2 Chron. 29:14) Ychavrel {yekh-av-ale'}; from (H2421) chayah and (H410) 'el; God will live; Jechiel (or Jechavel), the name of eight Israelites -- Jehiel. see HEBREW (H2421) chayah see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Patronymically from (H3171) Ychiy'el; a Jechielite or descendant of Jechiel -- Jehieli. see HEBREW (H3171) Ychiy'el

column8: darling, desolate, only child, son, solitary
column9: From (H3161) yachad; properly, united, i.e. Sole; by implication, beloved; also lonely; (feminine) the life (as not to be replaced) -- darling, desolate, only (child, son), solitary. see HEBREW (H3161) yachad
From (H2421) chayah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will live; Jechijah, an Israelite -- Jehiah. see HEBREW (H2421) chayah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H3176) yachal; expectant -- should hope. see HEBREW (H3176) yachal

column8: cause to, have, make to hope, be pained, stay, tarry, trust, wait
column9: A primitive root; to wait; by implication, to be patient, hope -- (cause to, have, make to) hope, be pained, stay, tarry, trust, wait.
From (H3176) yachal and (H410) 'el; expectant of God; Jachleel, an Israelite -- Jahleel. see HEBREW (H3176) yachal see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Patronymically from (H3177) Yachl'el; a Jachleelite or descendant of Jachleel -- Jahleelites. see HEBREW (H3177) Yachl'el

column8: get heat, be hot, conceive, be warm
column9: A primitive root; probably to be hot; figuratively, to conceive -- get heat, be hot, conceive, be warm.
From (H2560) chamar; a kind of deer (from the color; compare (H2543) chamowr) -- fallow deer. see HEBREW (H2560) chamar see HEBREW (H2543) chamowr

column7: may He protect, a man of Issachar
column9: Probably from (H3179) yacham; hot; Jachmai, an Israelite -- Jahmai. see HEBREW (H3179) yacham
From an unused root meaning to take off the shoes; unsandalled -- barefoot, being unshod.

column7: God apportions, a son of Naphtali
column9: From (H2673) chatsah and (H410) 'el; God will allot; Jachtseel, an Israelite -- Jahzeel. Compare (H3185) Yachtsiy'el. see HEBREW (H2673) chatsah see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3185) Yachtsiy'el
Patronymically from (H3183) Yachts'el; a Jachtseelite (collectively) or descendants of Jachtseel -- Jahzeelites. see HEBREW (H3183) Yachts'el
From (H2673) chatsah and (H410) 'el; allotted of God; Jachtsiel, an Israelite -- Jahziel. Compare (H3183) Yachts'el. see HEBREW (H2673) chatsah see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3183) Yachts'el
A primitive root; to delay -- tarry longer.

column7: to enroll oneself or be enrolled by genealogy
column8: number after, be reckoned by genealogies
column9: A primitive root; to sprout; used only as denominative from (H3188) yachas; to enroll by pedigree -- (number after, number throughout the) genealogy (to be reckoned), be reckoned by genealogies. see HEBREW (H3188) yachas
From (H3187) yachas; a pedigree or family list (as growing spontaneously) -- genealogy. see HEBREW (H3187) yachas

column7: He will snatch up, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H3161) yachad; unity; Jachath, the name of four Israelites -- Jahath. see HEBREW (H3161) yachad

column7: to be good, well, glad, or pleasing
column8: be accepted, amend, use aright, benefit, be make better, seem best
column9: A primitive root; to be (causative) make well, literally (sound, beautiful) or figuratively (happy, successful, right) -- be accepted, amend, use aright, benefit, be (make) better, seem best, make cheerful, be comely, + be content, diligent(-ly), dress, earnestly, find favour, give, be glad, do (be, make) good((-ness)), be (make) merry, please (+ well), shew more (kindness), skilfully, X very small, surely, make sweet, thoroughly, tire, trim, very, be (can, deal, entreat, go, have) well (said, seen).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3190) yatab -- seem good. see HEBREW (H3190) yatab

column7: pleasantness, a city probably in Judah
column9: From (H3190) yatab; pleasantness; Jotbah, a place in Palestine -- Jotbah. see HEBREW (H3190) yatab

column7: pleasantness, a place in the desert
column9: From (H3192) Yotbah; Jotbathah, a place in the Desert -- Jotbath, Jotbathah. see HEBREW (H3192) Yotbah
Or Yuwtah {yoo-taw'}; from (H5186) natah; extended; Juttah (or Jutah), a place in Palestine -- Juttah. see HEBREW (H5186) natah

column7: a son of Ishmael, also his desc. and the region where they lived
column9: Probably from the same as (H2905) tuwr; encircled (i.e. Inclosed); Jetur, a son of Ishmael -- Jetur. see HEBREW (H2905) tuwr
From an unused root meaning to effervesce; wine (as fermented); by implication, intoxication -- banqueting, wine, wine(-bibber).
By erroneous transcription for (H3027) yad; a hand or side -- (way-)side. see HEBREW (H3027) yad

column8: appoint, argue, chasten, convince, correction, dispute, judge,
column9: A primitive root; to be right (i.e. Correct); reciprocal, to argue; causatively, to decide, justify or convict -- appoint, argue, chasten, convince, correct(-ion), daysman, dispute, judge, maintain, plead, reason (together), rebuke, reprove(-r), surely, in any wise.

column7: He will establish, an Israelite name
column9: From (H3559) kuwn; he (or it) will establish; Jakin, the name of three Israelites and of a temple pillar -- Jachin. see HEBREW (H3559) kuwn
Patronymically from (H3199) Yakiyn; a Jakinite (collectively) or descendants of Jakin -- Jachinites. see HEBREW (H3199) Yakiyn

column8: be able, any at all ways, attain, can away with, not, could, endure, might,
column9: Or (fuller) yakowl {yaw-kole'}; a primitive root; to be able, literally (can, could) or morally (may, might) -- be able, any at all (ways), attain, can (away with, (-not)), could, endure, might, overcome, have power, prevail, still, suffer.
(Aramaic) or ykiyl (Aramaic) {yek-eel'}; to (H3201) yakol -- be able, can, couldest, prevail. see HEBREW (H3201) yakol

column7: Yah has been able, mother of King Azariah
column9: And Ykolyahuw {yek-ol-yaw'-hoo}; or (2 Chronicles 26:3) Ykiylyah {yek-ee-leh-yaw'}; from (H3201) yakol and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will enable; Jekoljah or Jekiljah, an Israelitess -- Jecholiah, Jecoliah. see HEBREW (H3201) yakol see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

And Ykonyahuw {yek-on-yaw'-hoo}; or (Jereremiah 27:20) Ykownyah {yek-o-neh-yaw'}; from (H3559) kuwn and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will establish; Jekonjah, a Jewish king -- Jeconiah. Compare (H3659) Konyahuw. see HEBREW (H3559) kuwn see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh see HEBREW (H3659) Konyahuw

column8: bear, beget, birthday, born, make to bring forth children, young, bring up, calve,
column9: A primitive root; to bear young; causatively, to beget; medically, to act as midwife; specifically, to show lineage -- bear, beget, birth((-day)), born, (make to) bring forth (children, young), bring up, calve, child, come, be delivered (of a child), time of delivery, gender, hatch, labour, (do the office of a) midwife, declare pedigrees, be the son of, (woman in, woman that) travail(-eth, -ing woman).

column8: boy, child, fruit, son, young man one
column9: From (H3205) yalad; something born, i.e. A lad or offspring -- boy, child, fruit, son, young man (one). see HEBREW (H3205) yalad
Feminine of (H3206) yeled; a lass -- damsel, girl. see HEBREW (H3206) yeled
Abstractly from (H3206) yeled; boyhood (or girlhood) -- childhood, youth. see HEBREW (H3206) yeled
Passive from (H3205) yalad; born -- born. see HEBREW (H3205) yalad
From (H3885) luwn; lodging; Jalon, an Israelite -- Jalon. see HEBREW (H3885) luwn
From (H3205) yalad; born -- ((home-))born, child, son. see HEBREW (H3205) yalad

column7: again, away, bear, bring, carry away, come away, depart, flow,
column8: again, away, bear, bring, carry away, come away, depart, flow,
column9: A primitive root (compare (H1980) halak); to walk (literally or figuratively); causatively, to carry (in various senses) -- X again, away, bear, bring, carry (away), come (away), depart, flow, + follow(-ing), get (away, hence, him), (cause to, made) go (away, -ing, -ne, one's way, out), grow, lead (forth), let down, march, prosper, + pursue, cause to run, spread, take away ((-journey)), vanish, (cause to) walk(-ing), wax, X be weak. see HEBREW (H1980) halak
A primitive root; to howl (with a wailing tone) or yell (with a boisterous one) -- (make to) howl, be howling.
From (H3213) yalal; a howl; -howling. see HEBREW (H3213) yalal
Feminine of (H3214) ylel; a howling. see HEBREW (H3214) ylel
A primitive root; to blurt or utter inconsiderately -- devour.
From an unused root apparently meaning to stick or scrape; scurf or tetter -- scabbed.
From an unused root meaning to lick up; a devourer; specifically, the young locust -- cankerworm, caterpillar.
From (H3950) laqat; a travelling pouch (as if for gleanings):-scrip. see HEBREW (H3950) laqat

From an unused root meaning to roar; a sea (as breaking in noisy surf) or large body of water; specifically (with the article), the Mediterranean Sea; sometimes a large river, or an artifical basin; locally, the west, or (rarely) the south -- sea (X -faring man, (-shore)), south, west (-ern, side, -ward).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3220) yam -- sea. see HEBREW (H3220) yam
From the same as (H3117) yowm; a warm spring -- mule. see HEBREW (H3117) yowm
From (H3117) yowm and (H410) 'el; day of God; Jemuel, an Israelite -- Jemuel. see HEBREW (H3117) yowm see HEBREW (H410) 'el

Perhaps from the same as (H3117) yowm; properly, warm, i.e. Affectionate; hence, dove (compare (H3123) yownah); Jemimah, one of Job's daughters -- Jemimah. see HEBREW (H3117) yowm see HEBREW (H3123) yownah

From (H3231) yaman; the right hand or side (leg, eye) of a person or other object (as the stronger and more dexterous); locally, the south -- + left-handed, right (hand, side), south. see HEBREW (H3231) yaman
The same as (H3225) yamiyn; Jamin, the name of three Israelites -- Jamin. See also (H1144) Binyamiyn. see HEBREW (H3225) yamiyn see HEBREW (H1144) Binyamiyn
For (H3225) yamiyn; right -- (on the) right (hand). see HEBREW (H3225) yamiyn
Patronymically from (H3226) Yamiyn; a Jeminite (collectively) or descendants of Jamin -- Jaminites. See also (H1145) Ben-ymiyniy. see HEBREW (H3226) Yamiyn see HEBREW (Hll45) #NAME?
Or Yimlah {yim-law'}; from (H4390) male'; full; Jimla or Jimlah, an Israelite -- Imla, Imlah. see HEBREW (H4390) male'
From (H4427) malak; he will make king; Jamlek, an Israelite -- Jamlech. see HEBREW (H4427) malak

column7: to go to or choose the right, to use the right hand
column8: go turn to on, use the right hand
column9: A primitive root; to be (physically) right (i.e. Firm); but used only as denominative from (H3225) yamiyn and transitive, to be right-handed or take the right-hand side -- go (turn) to (on, use) the right hand. see HEBREW (H3225) yamiyn

From (H3231) yaman; prosperity (as betokened by the right hand); Jimnah, the name of two Israelites; also (with the article) of the posterity of one of them -- Imna, Imnah, Jimnah, Jimnites. see HEBREW (H3231) yaman
From (H3231) yaman; right (i.e. At the right hand) -- (on the) right (hand). see HEBREW (H3231) yaman
From (H4513) mana'; he will restrain; Jimna, an Israelite: see HEBREW (H4513) mana'
A primitive root; to exchange; by implication, to change places -- boast selves, change.
Probably from (H3235) yamar; interchange; Jimrah, an Israelite -- Imrah. see HEBREW (H3235) yamar
A primitive root; to touch -- feel.

column8: destroy, thrust out by oppressing proud, vex, do violence
column9: A primitive root; to rage or be violent: by implication, to suppress, to maltreat -- destroy, (thrust out by) oppress(-ing, -ion, -or), proud, vex, do violence.
From (H3240) yanach; quiet; Janoach or Janochah, a place in Palestine -- Janoah, Janohah. see HEBREW (H3240) yanach

column7: bestow, cast down, lay down, up, leave off, let alone remain, pacify, place,
column8: bestow, cast down, lay down, up, leave off, let alone remain, pacify, place,
column9: A primitive root; to deposit; by implication, to allow to stay -- bestow, cast down, lay (down, up), leave (off), let alone (remain), pacify, place, put, set (down), suffer, withdraw, withhold. (The Hiphil forms with the dagesh are here referred to, in accordance with the older grammarians; but if any distinction of the kind is to be made, these should rather be referred to (H5117) nuwach, and the others here.) see HEBREW (H5117) nuwach
From (H5123) nuwm; asleep; Janim, a place in Palestine -- Janum (from the margin). see HEBREW (H5123) nuwm
From (H3243) yanaq; a sucker or sapling -- young twig. see HEBREW (H3243) yanaq

column8: give milk, nursing mother, give, make to sucking child,
column9: A primitive root; to suck; causatively, to give milk -- milch, nurse(-ing mother), (give, make to) suck(-ing child, -ling).

column7: (a ceremonially unclean bird) perhaps an owl
column9: Or yanshowph {yan-shofe'}; apparently from (H5398) nashaph; an unclean (acquatic) bird; probably the heron (perhaps from its blowing cry, or because the night-heron is meant (compare (H5399) nesheph))) -- (great) owl.s see HEBREW (H5398) nashaph see HEBREW (H5399) nesheph

column8: appoint, take counsel, establish, lay the, lay for a foundation, instruct, lay, ordain,
column9: A primitive root; to set (literally or figuratively); intensively, to found; reflexively, to sit down together, i.e. Settle, consult -- appoint, take counsel, establish, (lay the, lay for a) found(-ation), instruct, lay, ordain, set, X sure.
From (H3245) yacad; a foundation (figuratively, i.e. Beginning) -- X began. see HEBREW (H3245) yacad
From (H3245) yacad; a foundation (literally or figuratively) -- bottom, foundation, repairing see HEBREW (H3245) yacad
Feminine of (H3246) ycud; a foundation -- foundation. see HEBREW (H3246) ycud
From (H5493) cuwr; departing -- they that depart see HEBREW (H5493) cuwr
From (H3256) yacar; a reprover -- instruct. see HEBREW (H3256) yacar
A primitive root; to pour (intransitive) -- be poured.
From an unused root meaning to watch; observant; Jiskah, sister of Lot -- Iscah.
From (H5564) camak and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will sustain; Jismakjah, an Israelite -- Ismachiah. see HEBREW (H5564) camak see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column8: add, again, any more, cease, come more, conceive again, continue, exceed,
column9: A primitive root; to add or augment (often adverbial, to continue to do a thing) -- add, X again, X any more, X cease, X come more, + conceive again, continue, exceed, X further, X gather together, get more, give more-over, X henceforth, increase (more and more), join, X longer (bring, do, make, much, put), X (the, much, yet) more (and more), proceed (further), prolong, put, be (strong-) er, X yet, yield.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3254) yacaph -- add. see HEBREW (H3254) yacaph

column8: bind, chasten, chastise, correct, instruct, punish, reform, reprove,
column9: A primitive root; to chastise, literally (with blows) or figuratively (with words); hence, to instruct -- bind, chasten, chastise, correct, instruct, punish, reform, reprove, sore, teach.
From (H3261) ya'ah; a shovel -- shovel. see HEBREW (H3261) ya'ah

column7: a descendant of Judah, also a place in Judah
column8: Jabets, an Israelite, and also of a place in Palestine
column9: From an unused root probably meaning to grieve; sorrowful; Jabets, the name of an Israelite, and also of a place in Palestine:

column8: agree, make an appointment, a time, assemble selves, betroth, gather selves
column9: A primitive root; to fix upon (by agreement or appointment); by implication, to meet (at a stated time), to summon (to trial), to direct (in a certain quarter or position), to engage (for marriage) -- agree,(make an) appoint(-ment,a time), assemble (selves), betroth, gather (selves, together), meet (together), set (a time).
From (H3259) ya'ad; appointed; Jedi, an Israelite -- Iddo (from the margin) See (H3035) Yiddow. see HEBREW (H3259) ya'ad see HEBREW (H3035) Yiddow
A primitive root; apparently to brush aside -- sweep away.

column7: carried away by God, the name of several Israelites
column8: Jeuel, the name of four Israelites
column9: From (H3261) ya'ah and (H410) 'el; carried away of God; Jeuel, the name of four Israelites; -Jehiel, Jeiel, Jeuel. Compare (H3273) y'iy'el. see HEBREW (H3261) ya'ah see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3273) y'iy'el
From (H5779) uwts; counsellor; Jeuts, an Israelite -- Jeuz. see HEBREW (H5779) uwts
A variation of (H3298) Ya'areshyah; a forest -- wood. see HEBREW (H3298) Ya'areshyah
Apparently the passive participle of the same as (H3293) ya'ar; wooded; Jaur, an Israelite -- Jair(from the margin). see HEBREW (H3293) ya'ar

column7: he comes to help, an Edomite, also the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H5789) uwsh; hasty; Jeush, the name of an Edomite and of four Israelites -- Jehush, Jeush. Compare (H3274) y'iysh. see HEBREW (H5789) uwsh see HEBREW (H3274) y'iysh
A primitive root; to be bold or obstinate: d-fierce.
From (H3267) ya'az and (H410) 'el; emboldened of God; Jaaziel, an Israelite -- Jaaziel. see HEBREW (H3267) ya'az see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From (H3267) ya'az and (H3050) Yahh; emboldened of Jah; Jaazijah, an Israelite -- Jaaziah. see HEBREW (H3267) ya'az see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: a place East of the Jordan
column9: Or Yazer {yah-zare'}; from (H5826) azar; helpful; Jaazer or Jazer, a place East of the Jordan -- Jaazer, Jazer. see HEBREW (H5826) azar
A primitive root; to clothe -- cover.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3289) ya'ats; to counsel; reflexively, to consult -- counsellor, consult together. see HEBREW (H3289) ya'ats

From (H3261) ya'ah and (H410) 'el; carried away of God; Jeiel, the name of six Israelites -- Jeiel, Jehiel. Compare (H3262) y'uw'el. see HEBREW (H3261) ya'ah see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3262) y'uw'el
From (H5789) uwsh; hasty; Jeish, the name of an Edomite and of a an Israelite -- Jeush (from the margin). Compare (H3266) y'uwsh. see HEBREW (H5789) uwsh see HEBREW (H3266) y'uwsh
From the same as (H5912) Akan; troublesome; Jakan, an Israelite -- Jachan. see HEBREW (H5912) Akan

column7: to confer or gain profit or benefit
column8: set forward, can do good, be, have profit, able
column9: A primitive root; properly, to ascend; figuratively, to be valuable (objectively: useful, subjectively: benefited) -- X at all, set forward, can do good, (be, have) profit, (able).
From (H3276) ya'al; an ibex (as climbing) -- wild goat. see HEBREW (H3276) ya'al
The same as (H3277) ya'el; Jael, a Canaanite -- Jael. see HEBREW (H3277) ya'el
Or Yaaalah {yah-al-aw'}; the same as (H3280) ya'alah or direct from (H3276) ya'al; Jaala or Jaalah, one of the Nethinim -- Jaala, Jaalah. see HEBREW (H3280) ya'alah see HEBREW (H3276) ya'al
Feminine of (H3277) ya'el -- roe. see HEBREW (H3277) ya'el
From (H5956) alam; occult; Jalam, an Edomite -- Jalam. see HEBREW (H5956) alam

column4: preposition and conjunction; substantive; preposition; conjunction; preposition; conjunction
column8: because that, forasmuch as, seeing then, that, whereas, why
column9: From an unused root meaning to pay attention; properly, heed; by implication, purpose (sake or account); used adverbially to indicate the reason or cause -- because (that), forasmuch (+ as), seeing then, + that, + wheras, + why.
From the same as (H3282) ya'an; the ostrich (probably from its answering cry -- ostrich. see HEBREW (H3282) ya'an
Feminine of (H3283) ya'en, and meaning the same -- + owl. see HEBREW (H3283) ya'en
From the same as (H3283) ya'en; responsive; Jaanai, an Israelite -- Jaanai. see HEBREW (H3283) ya'en

column8: faint, cause to fly, be weary self
column9: A primitive root; to tire (as if from wearisome flight) -- faint, cause to fly, (be) weary (self).
From (H3286) ya'aph; fatigued; figuratively, exhausted -- faint, weary. see HEBREW (H3286) ya'aph
From (H3286) ya'aph; fatigue (adverb, utterly exhausted): see HEBREW (H3286) ya'aph

column8: advertise, take advise, advise well, consult, give, take counsel, determine, devise,
column9: A primitive root; to advise; reflexively, to deliberate or resolve -- advertise, take advise, advise (well), consult, (give, take) counsel(-lor), determine, devise, guide, purpose.

column7: a son of Isaac, also his desc
column9: From (H6117) aqab; heel-catcher (i.e. Supplanter); Jaakob, the Israelitish patriarch -- Jacob. see HEBREW (H6117) aqab
From (H3290) Ya'aqob; Jaakobah, an Israelite: see HEBREW (H3290) Ya'aqob
From the same as (H6130) Aqan; Jaakan, an Idumaean -- Jaakan. Compare (H1142) Bney Ya'aqan. see HEBREW (H6130) Aqan see HEBREW (H1142) Bney Ya'aqan
From an unused root probably meaning to thicken with verdure; a copse of bushes; hence, a forest; hence, honey in the comb (as hived in trees) -- (honey-)comb, forest, wood.
A form of (H3295) ya'arah; Jarah, an Israelite -- Jarah. see HEBREW (H3295) ya'arah
Feminine of (H3293) ya'ar, and meaning the same -- (honey-) comb, forest. see HEBREW (H3293) ya'ar

From the plural of (H3293) ya'ar and the masculine plural active participle of (H707) 'arag; woods of weavers; Jaare-Oregim, an Israelite -- Jaare-oregim. see HEBREW (H3293) ya'ar see HEBREW (H707) 'arag
Plural of (H3293) ya'ar; forests; Jearim, a place in Palestine -- Jearim. Compare (H7157) Qiryath y'ariym. see HEBREW (H3293) ya'ar see HEBREW (H7157) Qiryath y'ariym
From an unused root of uncertain signification and (H3050) Yahh; Jaareshjah, an Israelite -- Jaresiah. see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H6213) asah; they will do; Jaasu, an Israelite: see HEBREW (H6213) asah
From (H6213) asah and (H410) 'el; made of God; Jaasiel, an Israelite -- Jaasiel, Jasiel. see HEBREW (H6213) asah see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From (H6299) padah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will liberate; Jiphdejah, an Israelite -- Iphedeiah. see HEBREW (H6299) padah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
A primitive root; properly, to be bright, i.e. (by implication) beautiful -- be beautiful, be (make self) fair(-r), deck.

column8: beautiful, beauty, comely, fairest, one, goodly, pleasant, well
column9: From (H3302) yaphah; beautiful (literally or figuratively) -- + beautiful, beauty, comely, fair(-est, one), + goodly, pleasant, well. see HEBREW (H3302) yaphah
From (H3302) yaphah by reduplication; very beautiful -- very fair. see HEBREW (H3302) yaphah
Or Yaphow (Ezra 3:7) {yaw-fo'}; from (H3302) yaphah; beautiful; Japho, a place in Palestine -- Japha, Joppa. see HEBREW (H3302) yaphah
A primitive root; properly, to breathe hard, i.e. (by implication) to sigh -- bewail self.
From (H3306) yaphach; properly, puffing, i.e. (figuratively) meditating -- such as breathe out. see HEBREW (H3306) yaphach
From (H3302) yaphah; beauty -- beauty. see HEBREW (H3302) yaphah

column4: proper name, person and location; proper name, of a location
column7: a king of Lachish, also a son of David, also a place on the border of Zebulun
column9: From (H3313) yapha'; bright; Japhia, the name of a Canaanite, an Israelite, and a place in Palestine -- Japhia. see HEBREW (H3313) yapha'
From (H6403) palat; he will deliver; Japhlet, an Israelite -- Japhlet. see HEBREW (H6403) palat
Patronymically from (H3310) Yaphlet; a Japhletite or descendant of Japhlet -- Japhleti. see HEBREW (H3310) Yaphlet

column7: father of Caleb, also an Asherite
column9: From (H6437) panah; he will be prepared; Jephunneh, the name of two Israelites -- Jephunneh. see HEBREW (H6437) panah

column7: to shine out or forth, to send out beams, cause to shine
column8: be light, show self, cause to shine forth
column9: A primitive root; to shine -- be light, shew self, (cause to) shine (forth).
From (H3313) yapha'; splendor or (figuratively) beauty: see HEBREW (H3313) yapha'
From (H6601) pathah; expansion; Jepheth, a son of Noah; also his posterity -- Japheth. see HEBREW (H6601) pathah

column7: He opens, a Gileadite, also a city of Judah
column9: From (H6605) pathach; he will open; Jiphtach, an Israelite; also a place in Palestine -- Jephthah, Jiphtah. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach

column7: God opens, a valley between Zebulun and Asher
column9: From (H6605) pathach and (H410) 'el; God will open; Jiphtach-el, a place in Palestine -- Jiphthah-el. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column8: after, appear, assuredly, bear out, begotten, break out, bring forth out, up,
column9: A primitive root; to go (causatively, bring) out, in a great variety of applications, literally and figuratively, direct and proxim. -- X after, appear, X assuredly, bear out, X begotten, break out, bring forth (out, up), carry out, come (abroad, out, thereat, without), + be condemned, depart(-ing, -ure), draw forth, in the end, escape, exact, fail, fall (out), fetch forth (out), get away (forth, hence, out), (able to, cause to, let) go abroad (forth, on, out), going out, grow, have forth (out), issue out, lay (lie) out, lead out, pluck out, proceed, pull out, put away, be risen, X scarce, send with commandment, shoot forth, spread, spring out, stand out, X still, X surely, take forth (out), at any time, X to (and fro), utter.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3318) yatsa' -- finish. see HEBREW (H3318) yatsa'

column7: to set or station oneself, take one\'s stand
column8: present selves, remaining, resort, set selves, be able to, can, with stand fast, forth,
column9: A primitive root; to place (any thing so as to stay); reflexively, to station, offer, continue -- present selves, remaining, resort, set (selves), (be able to, can, with-) stand (fast, forth, -ing, still, up).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3320) yatsab; to be firm; hence, to speak surely -- truth. see HEBREW (H3320) yatsab

column8: establish, leave, make, present, put, set, stay
column9: A primitive root; to place permanently -- establish, leave, make, present, put, set, stay.
From (H6671) tsahar; oil (as producing light); figuratively, anointing -- + anointed oil. see HEBREW (H6671) tsahar
The same as (H3323) yitshar; Jitshar, an Israelite -- Izhar. see HEBREW (H3323) yitshar
Patronymically from (H3324) Yitshar; a Jitsharite or descendant of Jitshar -- Izeharites, Izharites. see HEBREW (H3324) Yitshar
Passive participle of (H3331) yatsa'; spread, i.e. A bed; (architecture) an extension, i.e. Wing or lean-to (a single story or collectively): see HEBREW (H3331) yatsa'

column7: he laughs, son of Abraham and Sarah
column9: From (H6711) tsachaq; laughter (i.e. Mochery); Jitschak (or Isaac), son of Abraham -- Isaac. Compare (H3446) Yischaq. see HEBREW (H6711) tsachaq see HEBREW (H3446) Yischaq
From the same as (H6713) tsachar; he will shine; Jitschar, an Israelite -- and Zehoar (from the margin). see HEBREW (H6713) tsachar
From (H3318) yatsa'; issue, i.e. Offspring -- those that came forth. see HEBREW (H3318) yatsa'
(Aramaic) from (H3321) ytseb; fixed, sure; concretely, certainty -- certain(-ty), true, truth. see HEBREW (H3321) ytseb
A primitive root; to strew as a surface -- make (one's) bed, X lie, spread.

column8: cast, cleave fast, be as firm, grow, be hard, lay out, molten, overflow,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to pour out (transitive or intransitive); by implication, to melt or cast as metal; by extension, to place firmly, to stiffen or grow hard -- cast, cleave fast, be (as) firm, grow, be hard, lay out, molten, overflow, pour (out), run out, set down, stedfast.
Passive participle feminine of (H3332) yatsaq; poured out, i.e. Run into a mould -- when it was cast. see HEBREW (H3332) yatsaq

column7: be distressed, be narrow, be straitened in straits, be vexed
column8: be distressed, be narrow, be straitened in straits, be vexed
column9: A primitive root; to press (intransitive), i.e. Be narrow; figuratively, be in distress -- be distressed, be narrow, be straitened (in straits), be vexed.

column8: earthen, fashion, form, frame, maker, potter, purpose
column9: Probably identical with (H3334) yatsar (through the squeezing into shape); ((compare (H3331) yatsa')); to mould into a form; especially as a potter; figuratively, to determine (i.e. Form a resolution) -- X earthen, fashion, form, frame, make(-r), potter, purpose. see HEBREW (H3334) yatsar see HEBREW (H3331) yatsa'

column8: frame, thing framed, imagination, mind, work
column9: From (H3335) yatsar; a form; figuratively, conception (i.e. Purpose) -- frame, thing framed, imagination, mind, work. see HEBREW (H3335) yatsar
The same as (H3336) yetser; Jetser, an Israelite -- Jezer. see HEBREW (H3336) yetser
Passive participle of (H3335) yatsar; structure, i.e. Limb or part -- member.ql see HEBREW (H3335) yatsar
From (H3335) yatsar; formative; Jitsri, an Israelite: see HEBREW (H3335) yatsar
: patronymically from (H3337) Yetser; a Jitsrite (collectively) or descendants of Jetser -- Jezerites. see HEBREW (H3337) Yetser

column8: burn up, be desolate, set on fire fire, kindle
column9: A primitive root; to burn or set on fire; figuratively, to desolate -- burn (up), be desolate, set (on) fire ((fire)), kindle.

From an unused root meaning to excavate; a trough (as dug out); specifically, a wine-vat (whether the lower one, into which the juice drains; or the upper, in which the grapes are crushed) -- fats, presses, press-fat, wine(-press).

From (H6908) qabats and (H410) 'el; God will gather; Jekabtseel, a place in Palestine -- Jekabzeel. Compare (H6909) Qabts'el. see HEBREW (H6908) qabats see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H6909) Qabts'el

column8: be burning, from the hearth, kindle
column9: A primitive root; to burn -- (be) burn(-ing), X from the hearth, kindle.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3344) yaqad -- burning. see HEBREW (H3344) yaqad
(Aramaic) from (H3345) yqad; a conflagration: see HEBREW (H3345) yqad
From (H3344) yaqad and (H5971) am; burning of (the) people; Jokdeam, a place in Palestine -- Jokdeam. see HEBREW (H3344) yaqad see HEBREW (H5971) am
From an unused root probably meaning to obey; obedient; Jakeh, a symbolical name (for Solomon) -- Jakeh.
From the same as (H3348) Yaqeh; obedience: see HEBREW (H3348) Yaqeh
From (H3344) yaqad; a burning -- burning. see HEBREW (H3344) yaqad
From (H6965) quwm; properly, standing (extant), i.e. By implication, a living thing -- (living) substance. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm
From (H3369) yaqosh; properly, entangling; hence, a snarer: see HEBREW (H3369) yaqosh
Passive participle of (H3369) yaqosh; properly, entangled, i.e. By implication (intransitively) a snare, or (transitive) a snarer -- fowler, snare. see HEBREW (H3369) yaqosh
From the same as (H3348) Yaqeh and (H410) 'el; obedience of God; Jekuthiel, an Israelite -- Jekuthiel. see HEBREW (H3348) Yaqeh see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: a descendant of Shem and ancestor of several Arabian tribes
column9: From (H6994) qaton; he will be made little; Joktan, an Arabian patriarch -- Joktan. see HEBREW (H6994) qaton
From (H6965) quwm; he will raise; Jakim, the name of two Israelites -- Jakim. Compare (H3079) Yhowyaqiym. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm see HEBREW (H3079) Yhowyaqiym
From (H3365) yaqar; precious -- dear. see HEBREW (H3365) yaqar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3357) yaqqiyr -- noble, rare. see HEBREW (H3357) yaqqiyr

From (H6965) quwm and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will rise; Jekamjah, the name of two Israelites -- Jekamiah. Compare (H3079) Yhowyaqiym. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh see HEBREW (H3079) Yhowyaqiym

From (H6965) quwm and (H5971) am; (the) people will rise; Jekamam, an Israelite -- Jekameam. Compare (H3079) Yhowyaqiym, (H3361) Yoqm'am. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm see HEBREW (H5971) am see HEBREW (H3079) Yhowyaqiym see HEBREW (H3361) Yoqm'am

column7: let the people be established, a city in Northern Israel
column9: From (H6965) quwm and (H5971) am; (the) people will be raised; Jokmeam, a place in Palestine -- Jokmeam. Compare (H3360) Yqam'am, (H3362) Yoqn'am. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm see HEBREW (H5971) am see HEBREW (H3360) Yqam'am see HEBREW (H3362) Yoqn'am
From (H6969) quwn and (H5971) am; (the) people will be lamented; Jokneam, a place in Palestine -- Jokneam. see HEBREW (H6969) quwn see HEBREW (H5971) am

column8: be alienated, depart, hang up, be out of joint
column9: A primitive root; properly, to sever oneself, i.e. (by implication) to be dislocated; figuratively, to abandon; causatively, to impale (and thus allow to drop to pieces by rotting) -- be alienated, depart, hang (up), be out of joint.
A primitive root; to awake (intransitive) -- (be) awake(-d).

column7: to be precious, prized or appraised
column8: be make precious, be prized, be set by, withdraw
column9: A primitive root; properly, apparently, to be heavy, i.e. (figuratively) valuable; causatively, to make rare (figuratively, to inhibit) -- be (make) precious, be prized, be set by, withdraw.
From (H3365) yaqar; value, i.e. (concretely) wealth; abstractly, costliness, dignity -- honour, precious (things), price. see HEBREW (H3365) yaqar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3366) yqar -- glory, honour. see HEBREW (H3366) yqar
From (H3365) yaqar; valuable (obj. Or subj.): see HEBREW (H3365) yaqar

column7: to lay a bait or lure
column9: A primitive root; to ensnare (literally or figuratively) -- fowler (lay a) snare.

column7: a son of Abraham and Keturah
column9: From (H3369) yaqosh; insidious; Jokshan, an Arabian patriarch -- Jokshan. see HEBREW (H3369) yaqosh

column7: a city in Judah, also a city in Edom
column9: Probably from the same as (H3348) Yaqeh and (H410) 'el; veneration of God (compare (H3354) Yquwthiy'el); Joktheel, the name of a place in Palestine, and of one in Idumaea -- Joktheel. see HEBREW (H3348) Yaqeh see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3354) Yquwthiy'el

column8: affright, be make afraid, dreadful, put in fearful reverence, terrible act,
column9: A primitive root; to fear; morally, to revere; caus. To frighten -- affright, be (make) afraid, dread(-ful), (put in) fear(-ful, -fully, -ing), (be had in) reverence(-end), X see, terrible (act, -ness, thing).
From (H3372) yare'; fearing; morally, reverent -- afraid, fear (-ful). see HEBREW (H3372) yare'
Feminine of (H3373) yare'; fear (also used as infinitive); morally, reverence -- X dreadful, X exceedingly, fear(-fulness). see HEBREW (H3373) yare'
From (H3372) yare'; fearfulness; Jiron, a place in Pal: see HEBREW (H3372) yare'

column7: Yah sees, an Israelite of Jeremiah\'s time
column9: From (H3373) yare' and (H3050) Yahh; fearful of Jah; Jirijah, an Israelite -- Irijah. see HEBREW (H3373) yare' see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: let him contend, the name of an Assyrian king
column9: From (H7378) riyb; he will contend; Jareb, a symbolical name for Assyria -- Jareb. Compare (H3402) Yariyb. see HEBREW (H7378) riyb see HEBREW (H3402) Yariyb

column7: let Baal contend, a name of Gideon
column9: From (H7378) riyb and (H1168) Ba'al; Baal will contend; Jerubbaal, a symbol. Name of Gideon -- Jerubbaal. see HEBREW (H7378) riyb see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al

column7: the people increase, the name of two Israelites kings
column9: From (H7378) riyb and (H5971) am; (the) people will contend; Jarobam, the name of two Israelite kings -- Jeroboam. see HEBREW (H7378) riyb see HEBREW (H5971) am

column7: shame will contend, a name of Gideon
column9: From (H7378) riyb and (H1322) bosheth; shame (i.e. The idol) will contend; Jerubbesheth, a symbol. Name for Gideon: see HEBREW (H7378) riyb see HEBREW (H1322) bosheth

column7: to come or go down, descend
column8: to descend, to go downwards to a lower region, as the shore
column9: A primitive root; to descend (literally, to go downwards; or conventionally to a lower region, as the shore, a boundary, the enemy, etc.; or figuratively, to fall); causatively, to bring down (in all the above applications); -X abundantly, bring down, carry down, cast down, (cause to) come(-ing) down, fall (down), get down, go(-ing) down(-ward), hang down, X indeed, let down, light (down), put down (off), (cause to, let) run down, sink, subdue, take down.

column7: a descendant of Seth, also a man of Judah
column9: From (H3381) yarad; a descent; Jered, the name of an antediluvian, and of an Israelite -- Jared. see HEBREW (H3381) yarad
From (H3381) yarad; a descender; Jarden, the principal river of Palestine -- Jordan. see HEBREW (H3381) yarad

column8: archer, cast, direct, inform, instruct, lay, show, shoot,
column9: Or (2 Chr. 26:15) yara; {yaw-raw'}; a primitive root; properly, to flow as water (i.e. To rain); transitively, to lay or throw (especially an arrow, i.e. To shoot); figuratively, to point out (as if by aiming the finger), to teach -- (+) archer, cast, direct, inform, instruct, lay, shew, shoot, teach(-er,-ing), through.
From (H3384) yarah and (H410) 'el; founded of God; Jeruel, a place in Palestine -- Jeruel. see HEBREW (H3384) yarah see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Perhaps denominative from (H3394) yareach; (born at the) new moon; Jaroach, an Israelite -- Jaroah. see HEBREW (H3394) yareach
From (H3417) yaraq; green, i.e. An herb -- green thing. see HEBREW (H3417) yaraq

column7: taken possession of, mother of King Jotham
column9: Or Yaruwshah {yer-oo-shaw'} feminine passive participle of (H3423) yarash; possessed; Jerusha or Jerushah, as Israelitess -- Jerusha, Jerushah. see HEBREW (H3423) yarash

column7: probably "foundation of peace", capital city of all Isr
column9: Rarely Yruwshalayim {yer-oo- shaw-lah'-yim}; a dual (in allusion to its two main hills (the true pointing, at least of the former reading, seems to be that of (H3390) Yruwshalem)); probably from (the passive participle of) (H3384) yarah and (H7999) shalam; founded peaceful; Jerushalaim or Jerushalem, the capital city of Palestine -- Jerusalem. see HEBREW (H3390) Yruwshalem see HEBREW (H3384) yarah see HEBREW (H7999) shalam

column7: the capital city of all Isr
column9: (Chald)
From a unused root of uncertain signification; a lunation, i.e. Month -- month, moon.

column7: a son of Joktan, also his desc
column9: The same as (H3391) yerach; Jerach, an Arabian patriarch -- Jerah. see HEBREW (H3391) yerach
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3391) yerach; a month -- month. see HEBREW (H3391) yerach
From the same as (H3391) yerach; the moon -- moon. Yrechow. See (H3405) Yriychow. see HEBREW (H3391) yerach see HEBREW (H3405) Yriychow

column7: may He be compassionate, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H7355) racham; compassionate; Jerocham, the name of seven or eight Israelites -- Jeroham. see HEBREW (H7355) racham

column7: may God have compassion, an Israelite name
column9: From (H7355) racham and (H410) 'el; God will compassionate; Jerachmeel, the name of three Israelites -- Jerahmeel. see HEBREW (H7355) racham see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Patronymically from (H3396) Yrachm'el; a Jerachmeelite or descendant of Jerachmeel -- Jerahmeelites. see HEBREW (H3396) Yrachm'el
Probably of Egyptian origin; Jarcha, an Egyptian -- Jarha.
A primitive root; to precipitate or hurl (rush) headlong; (intransitively) to be rash -- be perverse, turn over.

column7: thrown by God, a man of Issachar
column9: From (H3384) yarah and (H410) 'el; thrown of God; Jeriel, an Israelite -- Jeriel. Compare (H3385) Yruw'el. see HEBREW (H3384) yarah see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3385) Yruw'el
From (H7378) riyb; literally, he will contend; properly, adjective, contentious; used as noun, an adversary -- that content(-eth), that strive. see HEBREW (H7378) riyb
The same as (H3401) yariyb; Jarib, the name of three Israelites -- Jarib. see HEBREW (H3401) yariyb
From (H3401) yariyb; contentious; Jeribai, an Israelite -- Jeribai. see HEBREW (H3401) yariyb
Or Yriyahuw {yer-ee-yaw'-hoo}; from (H3384) yarah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will throw; Jerijah, an Israelite -- Jeriah, Jerijah. see HEBREW (H3384) yarah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: a city in the Jordan Valley captured by Joshua
column9: Or Yrechow {yer-ay-kho'}; or variation (1 Kings 16:34) Yriychoh {yer-ee-kho'}; perhaps from (H3394) yareach; its month; or else from (H7306) ruwach; fragrant; Jericho or Jerecho, a place in Palestine -- Jericho. see HEBREW (H3394) yareach see HEBREW (H7306) ruwach

column7: the name of a number of Isr
column9: Or Yreymowth {yer-ay-mohth'}; or Yremowth {yer-ay-mohth'}; feminine plural from (H7311) ruwm; elevations; Jerimoth or Jeremoth, the name of twelve Israelites -- Jermoth, Jerimoth, and Ramoth (from the margin). see HEBREW (H7311) ruwm
From (H3415) yara'; a hanging (as tremulous) -- curtain. see HEBREW (H3415) yara'
Plural of (H3407) yriy'ah; curtains; Jerioth, an Israelitess -- Jerioth. see HEBREW (H3407) yriy'ah
From an unused root meaning to be soft; the thigh (from its fleshy softness); by euphem. The generative parts; figuratively, a shank, flank, side -- X body, loins, shaft, side, thigh.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3411) yrekah; a thigh -- thigh. see HEBREW (H3411) yrekah
Feminine of (H3409) yarek; properly, the flank; but used only figuratively, the rear or recess -- border, coast, part, quarter, side. see HEBREW (H3409) yarek

column7: a Canaanite city in Judah, also a city in Issachar
column9: From (H7311) ruwm; elevation; Jarmuth, the name of two places in Palestine -- Jarmuth. see HEBREW (H7311) ruwm
From (H7311) ruwm; elevated; Jeremai, an Israelite: see HEBREW (H7311) ruwm

column7: Yah loosens, the name of a number of Isr
column9: Or Yirmyahuw {yir-meh-yaw'-hoo}; from (H7311) ruwm and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will rise; Jirmejah, the name of eight or nine Israelites -- Jeremiah. see HEBREW (H7311) ruwm see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
A primitive root; properly, to be broken up (with any violent action) i.e. (figuratively) to fear -- be grevious (only Isa. 15:4; the rest belong to (H7489) ra'a'). see HEBREW (H7489) ra'a'

column7: God will heal, a place in Benjamin
column9: From (H7495) rapha' and (H410) 'el; God will heal; Jirpeel, a place in Palestine -- Irpeel. see HEBREW (H7495) rapha' see HEBREW (H410) 'el
A primitive root; to spit -- X but, spit.

From (H3417) yaraq (in the sense of vacuity of color); properly, pallor, i.e. Hence, the yellowish green of young and sickly vegetation; concretely, verdure, i.e. Grass or vegetation -- grass, green (thing). see HEBREW (H3417) yaraq
From the same as (H3418) yereq; properly, green; concretely, a vegetable -- green, herbs. see HEBREW (H3418) yereq
From (H3418) yereq; paleness, whether of persons (from fright), or of plants (from drought) -- greenish, yellow. see HEBREW (H3418) yereq
From (H7324) ruwq and (H5971) am; people will be poured forth; Jorkeam, a place in Palestine -- Jorkeam. see HEBREW (H7324) ruwq see HEBREW (H5971) am
From the same as (H3418) yereq; yellowishness: see HEBREW (H3418) yereq

column7: to take possession of, inherit, dispossess
column8: cast out, consume, destroy, disinherit, dispossess, driving out, enjoy, expel,
column9: Or yaresh {yaw-raysh'}; a primitive root; to occupy (by driving out previous tenants, and possessing in their place); by implication, to seize, to rob, to inherit; also to expel, to impoverish, to ruin -- cast out, consume, destroy, disinherit, dispossess, drive(-ing) out, enjoy, expel, X without fail, (give to, leave for) inherit(-ance, -or) + magistrate, be (make) poor, come to poverty, (give to, make to) possess, get (have) in (take) possession, seize upon, succeed, X utterly.
From (H3423) yarash; occupancy -- possession. see HEBREW (H3423) yarash
From (H3423) yarash; something occupied; a conquest; also a patrimony -- heritage, inheritance, possession. see HEBREW (H3423) yarash

column8: there are, he, it, shall, there, there may, there shall, there should be,
column9: Perhaps from an unused root meaning to stand out, or exist; entity; used adverbially or as a copula for the substantive verb ((H1961) hayah); there is or are (or any other form of the verb to be, as may suit the connection) -- (there) are, (he, it, shall, there, there may, there shall, there should) be, thou do, had, hast, (which) hath, (I, shalt, that) have, (he, it, there) is, substance, it (there) was, (there) were, ye will, thou wilt, wouldest. see HEBREW (H1961) hayah

column8: make to abide, continue, cause to, make to dwelling, ease self, endure, establish, fail,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to sit down (specifically as judge. In ambush, in quiet); by implication, to dwell, to remain; causatively, to settle, to marry -- (make to) abide(-ing), continue, (cause to, make to) dwell(-ing), ease self, endure, establish, X fail, habitation, haunt, (make to) inhabit(-ant), make to keep (house), lurking, X marry(-ing), (bring again to) place, remain, return, seat, set(- tle), (down-)sit(-down, still, -ting down, -ting (place) -uate), take, tarry.
From (H3427) yashab and (H1) 'ab; seat of (his) father; Jeshebab, an Israelite -- Jeshebeab. see HEBREW (H3427) yashab see HEBREW (H1) 'ab

column7: sitting in the seat, one of David\'s heroes
column9: From the active participle of (H3427) yashab and (H7674) shebeth, with a preposition and the article interposed; sitting in the seat; Josheb-bash-Shebeth, an Israelite -- that sat in the seat. see HEBREW (H3427) yashab see HEBREW (H7674) shebeth

column7: his dwelling (is) in Nob, a Philistine
column9: From (H3427) yashab and (H5011) Nob, with a pronominal suffix and a preposition interposed; his dwelling (is) in Nob; Jishbo-be-Nob, a Philistine -- Ishbi-benob (from the margin). see HEBREW (H3427) yashab see HEBREW (H5011) Nob
From (H7623) shabach; he will praise; Jishbach, an Israelite -- Ishbah. see HEBREW (H7623) shabach
Patronymically from (H3437) Yashuwb; a Jashubite, or descendant of Jashub -- Jashubites. see HEBREW (H3437) Yashuwb

column7: returner of bread, a man of Judah
column9: From (H7725) shuwb and (H3899) lechem; returner of bread; Jashubi-Lechem, an Israelite -- Jashubi-lehem. (Prob. The text should be pointed Yoshbev Lechem {yo-sheh-bay' leh'-khem}, and rendered \"(they were) inhabitants of Lechem,\" i.e. Of Bethlehem (by contraction). Compare (H3902) Lachmiy). see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb see HEBREW (H3899) lechem see HEBREW (H3902) Lachmiy

column7: people will return, one of David\'s heroes
column9: From (H7725) shuwb and (H5971) am; people will return; Jashobam, the name of two or three Israelites -- Jashobeam. see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb see HEBREW (H5971) am

column7: a son of Abraham and Keturah
column9: From an unused root corresponding to (H7662) shbaq; he will leave; Jishbak, a son of Abraham -- Ishbak. see HEBREW (H7662) shbaq
