column7: a hard seat, a son of Heman
column9: From (H3427) yashab and (H7186) qasheh; a hard seat; Joshbekashah, an Israelite -- Joshbekashah. see HEBREW (H3427) yashab see HEBREW (H7186) qasheh
Or Yashiyb {yaw-sheeb'}; from (H7725) shuwb; he will return; Jashub, the name of two Israelites -- Jashub. see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb
From (H7737) shavah; he will level; Jishvah, an Israelite: see HEBREW (H7737) shavah
From the same as (H3445) yeshach and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will empty; Jeshochajah, an Israelite -- Jeshoaiah. see HEBREW (H3445) yeshach see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H7737) shavah; level; Jishvi, the name of two Israelites -- Ishuai, Ishvi, Isui, Jesui. see HEBREW (H7737) shavah
Patronymically from (H3440) Yishviy; a Jishvite (collectively) or descendants of Jishvi -- Jesuites. see HEBREW (H3440) Yishviy
For (H3091) Yhowshuwa'; he will save; Jeshua, the name of ten Israelites, also of a place in Palestine -- Jeshua. see HEBREW (H3091) Yhowshuwa'

column7: a high priest after the Bab. captivity
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H3442) Yeshuwa' -- Jeshua. see HEBREW (H3442) Yeshuwa'

column8: deliverance, health, helping, salvation, save, saving health, welfare
column9: Feminine passive participle of (H3467) yasha'; something saved, i.e. (abstractly) deliverance; hence, aid, victory, prosperity -- deliverance, health, help(-ing), salvation, save, saving (health), welfare. see HEBREW (H3467) yasha'
From an unused root meaning to gape (as the empty stomach); hunger -- casting down.
From (H7831) Shachatsowm; he will laugh; Jischak, the heir of Abraham -- Isaac. Compare (H3327) Yitschaq. see HEBREW (H7831) Shachatsowm see HEBREW (H3327) Yitschaq
A primitive root; to extend -- hold out.
By Aramaic Iyshay {ee-shah'-ee}; from the same as (H3426) yesh; extant; Jishai, David's father -- Jesse. see HEBREW (H3426) yesh

Or Yishshiyahuw {yish-shee-yaw'-hoo}; from (H5383) nashah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will lend; Jishshijah, the name of five Israelites -- Ishiah, Isshiah, Ishijah, Jesiah. see HEBREW (H5383) nashah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H7760) suwm and (H410) 'el; God will place; Jesimael, an Israelite -- Jesimael. see HEBREW (H7760) suwm see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From (H3456) yasham; desolation -- let death seize (from the margin). see HEBREW (H3456) yasham
From (H3456) yasham; a desolation -- desert, Jeshimon, solitary, wilderness. see HEBREW (H3456) yasham

column8: very aged man, ancient, very old
column9: From (H3486) yashesh; an old man -- (very) aged (man), ancient, very old. see HEBREW (H3486) yashesh
From (H3453) yashiysh; aged; Jeshishai, an Israelite -- Jeshishai. see HEBREW (H3453) yashiysh
A prim root; to place; intransitively, to be placed -- be put (set).
A primitive root; to lie waste -- be desolate.
From (H3456) yasham; desolate; Jishma, an Israelite: see HEBREW (H3456) yasham

column7: God hears, the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H8085) shama' and (H410) 'el; God will hear; Jishmael, the name of Abraham's oldest son, and of five Israelites -- Ishmael. see HEBREW (H8085) shama' see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Patronymically from (H3458) Yishma'e'l; a Jishmaelite or descendant of Jishmael -- Ishmaelite. see HEBREW (H3458) Yishma'e'l
Or Yishmacyahuw {yish-mah-yaw'-hoo}; from (H8085) shama' and (H3050) Yahh; Jah will hear; Jishmajah, the name of two Israelites -- Ishmaiah. see HEBREW (H8085) shama' see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H8104) shamar; preservative; Jishmerai, an Israelite -- Ishmerai. see HEBREW (H8104) shamar

column8: to be slack or languid, grow old
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be slack or languid, i.e. (by implication) sleep (figuratively, to die); also to grow old, stale or inveterate:
From (H3462) yashen; sleepy -- asleep, (one out of) sleep(-eth, -ing), slept. see HEBREW (H3462) yashen
The same as (H3463) yashen; Jashen, an Israelite -- Jashen. see HEBREW (H3463) yashen
From (H3462) yashen; old -- old. see HEBREW (H3462) yashen
Feminine of (H3465) yashan; Jeshanah, a place in Palestine -- Jeshanah. see HEBREW (H3465) yashan

column8: avenging, defend, deliverer, help, preserve, rescue, be safe,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be open, wide or free, i.e. (by implication) to be safe; causatively, to free or succor -- X at all, avenging, defend, deliver(-er), help, preserve, rescue, be safe, bring (having) salvation, save(-iour), get victory.
Or yeshai {yay'-shah}; from (H3467) yasha'; liberty, deliverance, prosperity -- safety, salvation, saving. see HEBREW (H3467) yasha'
From (H3467) yasha'; saving; Jishi, the name of four Israelites -- Ishi. see HEBREW (H3467) yasha'

Or Yshayahuw {yesh-ah-yaw'-hoo}; from (H3467) yasha' and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has saved; Jeshajah, the name of seven Israelites -- Isaiah, Jesaiah, Jeshaiah. see HEBREW (H3467) yasha' see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From an unused root meaning to polish; a gem supposed to be jasper (from the resemblance in name) -- jasper.
Perhaps from (H8192) shaphah; he will scratch; Jishpah, an Israelite -- Ispah. see HEBREW (H8192) shaphah
Probably from the same as (H8227) shaphan; he will hide; Jishpan, an Israelite -- Ishpan. see HEBREW (H8227) shaphan

column7: to be smooth, straight, or right
column8: direct, fit, seem good meet, please will, be esteem, go right on, bring look, make,
column9: A primitive root; to be straight or even; figuratively, to be (causatively, to make) right, pleasant, prosperous -- direct, fit, seem good (meet), + please (will), be (esteem, go) right (on), bring (look, make, take the) straight (way), be upright(-ly).
From (H3474) yashar; the right; Jesher, an Israelite: see HEBREW (H3474) yashar
From (H3474) yashar; the right -- equity, meet, right, upright(-ness). see HEBREW (H3474) yashar

column8: convenient, equity, just, well-pleased, righteous, straight, most uprightly,
column9: From (H3474) yashar; straight (literally or figuratively) -- convenient, equity, Jasher, just, meet(-est), + pleased well right(-eous), straight, (most) upright(-ly, -ness). see HEBREW (H3474) yashar

column7: God strives, another name of Jacob and his desc
column9: From (H8280) sarah and (H410) 'el; he will rule as God; Jisrael, a symbolical name of Jacob; also (typically) of his posterity: --Israel. see HEBREW (H8280) sarah see HEBREW (H410) 'el
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3478) Yisra'el -- Israel. see HEBREW (H3478) Yisra'el
By variation from (H3477) yashar and (H410) 'el with directive enclitic; right towards God; Jesarelah, an Israelite -- Jesharelah. see HEBREW (H3477) yashar see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Patronymically from (H3478) Yisra'el; a Jisreelite or descendant of Jisrael -- of Israel, Israelite. see HEBREW (H3478) Yisra'el
Feminine of (H3481) Yisr'eliy; a Jisreelitess or female descendant of Jisrael -- Israelitish. see HEBREW (H3481) Yisr'eliy
Feminine or (H3477) yashar; rectitude -- uprightness. see HEBREW (H3477) yashar

column7: upright one, poetic name for Isr
column9: From (H3474) yashar; upright; Jeshurun, a symbol. Name for Israel -- Jeshurun. see HEBREW (H3474) yashar

column7: perhaps "there is recompense", a son of Jacob and Leah, also a son of Obed-edom
column9: (strictly yis-saws-kawr'); from (H5375) nasa' and (H7939) sakar; he will bring a reward; Jissaskar, a son of Jacob -- Issachar. see HEBREW (H5375) nasa' see HEBREW (H7939) sakar
From an unused root meaning to blanch; gray-haired, i.e. An aged man -- stoop for age.

column4: Untranslatable mark of the direct object or the accusative
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H853) 'eth; a sign of the object of a verb: + whom. see HEBREW (H853) 'eth
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3427) yashab; to sit or dwell: see HEBREW (H3427) yashab
From an unused root meaning to pin through or fast; a peg -- nail, paddle, pin, stake.
From an unused root meaning to be lonely; a bereaved person -- fatherless (child), orphan.
Passive participle of (H3498) yathar; properly, what is left, i.e. (by implication) a gleaning -- range. see HEBREW (H3498) yathar
From (H3498) yathar; redundant; Jattir, a place in Palestine -- Jattir. see HEBREW (H3498) yathar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3492) Yattiyr; preeminent; as an adverb, very -- exceeding(-ly), excellent. see HEBREW (H3492) Yattiyr

column7: it will hang, a place in Dan
column9: Probably from (H8518) talah; it will hang, i.e. Be high; Jithlah, a place in Palestine -- Jethlah. see HEBREW (H8518) talah
From the same as (H3490) yathowm; orphanage; Jithmah, an Israelite -- Ithmah. see HEBREW (H3490) yathowm
From an unused root meaning to endure, and (H410) 'el; continued of God; Jathniel, an Israelite -- Jathniel. see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: a city in the desert of Judah
column9: From the same as (H8577) tanniyn; extensive; Jithnan, a place in Palestine -- Ithnan. see HEBREW (H8577) tanniyn

column8: excel, leave a remnant, left behind, too much, make plenteous, preserve
column9: A primitive root; to jut over or exceed; by implication, to excel; (intransitively) to remain or be left; causatively, to leave, cause to abound, preserve -- excel, leave (a remnant), left behind, too much, make plenteous, preserve, (be, let) remain(-der, -ing, - nant), reserve, residue, rest.

column8: abundant, cord, exceeding, excellent, plentifully, remnant, residue
column9: From (H3498) yathar; properly, an overhanging, i.e. (by implication) an excess, superiority, remainder; also a small rope (as hanging free) -- + abundant, cord, exceeding, excellancy(-ent), what they leave, that hath left, plentifully, remnant, residue, rest, string, with. see HEBREW (H3498) yathar

column7: Moses\' father-in-law, also the name of several Israelites
column9: The same as (H3499) yether; Jether, the name of five or six Israelites and of one Midianite -- Jether, Jethro. Compare (H3503) Yithrow. see HEBREW (H3499) yether see HEBREW (H3503) Yithrow
By variation for (H3502) yithrah; Jithra, an Israelite (or Ishmaelite) -- Ithra. see HEBREW (H3502) yithrah
Feminine of (H3499) yether; properly, excellence, i.e. (by implication) wealth -- abundance, riches. see HEBREW (H3499) yether
From (H3499) yether with pron. Suffix; his excellence; Jethro, Moses' father-in-law -- Jethro. Compare (H3500) Yether. see HEBREW (H3499) yether see HEBREW (H3500) Yether
From (H3498) yathar; preeminence, gain -- better, excellency(-leth), profit(-able). see HEBREW (H3498) yathar
Patronymically from (H3500) Yether; a Jithrite or descendant of Jether -- Ithrite. see HEBREW (H3500) Yether
From (H3498) yathar; excellent; Jithran, the name of an Edomite and of an Israelite -- Ithran. see HEBREW (H3498) yathar
From (H3499) yether and (H5971) am; excellence of people; Jithream, a son of David -- Ithream. see HEBREW (H3499) yether see HEBREW (H5971) am

column8: caul, the lobe or flap of the liver
column9: Feminine active participle of (H3498) yathar; the lobe or flap of the liver (as if redundant or outhanging) -- caul. see HEBREW (H3498) yathar
Of uncertain derivation; Jetheth, an Edomite:

column8: grieving, mar, have pain, make sad sore, be sorrowful
column9: A primitive root; properly, to feel pain; by implication, to grieve; figuratively, to spoil -- grieving, mar, have pain, make sad (sore), (be) sorrowful.
From (H3510) ka'ab; suffering (physical or mental), adversity -- grief, pain, sorrow. see HEBREW (H3510) ka'ab
A primitive root; to despond: causatively, to deject -- broken, be grieved, make sad.

column7: to be heavy, weighty, or burdensome
column8: abounding with, more grievously afflict, boast, be chargeable, be dim
column9: Or kabed {kaw-bade'}; a primitive root; to be heavy, i.e. In a bad sense (burdensome, severe, dull) or in a good sense (numerous, rich, honorable; causatively, to make weighty (in the same two senses) -- abounding with, more grievously afflict, boast, be chargeable, X be dim, glorify, be (make) glorious (things), glory, (very) great, be grievous, harden, be (make) heavy, be heavier, lay heavily, (bring to, come to, do, get, be had in) honour (self), (be) honourable (man), lade, X more be laid, make self many, nobles, prevail, promote (to honour), be rich, be (go) sore, stop.
From (H3513) kabad; weight, multitude, vehemence: see HEBREW (H3513) kabad

column8: so great, grievous, hardened, too heavier, laden, much, slow, sore,
column9: From (H3513) kabad; heavy; figuratively in a good sense (numerous) or in a bad sense (severe, difficult, stupid) -- (so) great, grievous, hard(-ened), (too) heavy(-ier), laden, much, slow, sore, thick. see HEBREW (H3513) kabad
The same as (H3515) kabed; the liver (as the heaviest of the viscera) -- liver. see HEBREW (H3515) kabed
Feminine of (H3515) kabed; difficulty -- X heavily. see HEBREW (H3515) kabed

column7: to be quenched or extinguished, to go out
column9: A primitive root; to expire or (causatively) to extinguish (fire, light, anger) -- go (put) out, quench.
Rarely kabod {kaw-bode'}; from (H3513) kabad; properly, weight, but only figuratively in a good sense, splendor or copiousness -- glorious(-ly), glory, honour(-able). see HEBREW (H3513) kabad
Irreg. Feminine passive participle of (H3513) kabad; weightiness, i.e. Magnificence, wealth -- carriage, all glorious, stately. see HEBREW (H3513) kabad

column7: a city in Asher, also a region in Galilee
column9: From the same as (H3525) kebel in the sense of limitation; sterile; Cabul, the name of two places in Palestine -- Cabul. see HEBREW (H3525) kebel
From an unused root meaning to heap up; hilly; Cabon, a place in Palestine -- Cabbon.

column7: (something woven) perhaps a quilt or net
column9: From (H3527) kabar in the original sense of plaiting; a matrass (of intertwined materials) -- pillow. see HEBREW (H3527) kabar

column8: feeble, mighty, most, much, strong, valiant
column9: From (H3527) kabar; vast, whether in extent (figuratively, of power, mighty; of time, aged), or in number, many -- + feeble, mighty, most, much, strong, valiant. see HEBREW (H3527) kabar
From an unused root meaning to twine or braid together; a fetter -- fetter.
A primitive root; to trample; hence, to wash (properly, by stamping with the feet), whether literal (including the fulling process) or figurative -- fuller, wash(-ing).
A primitive root; properly, to plait together, i.e. (figuratively) to augment (especially in number or quantity, to accumulate) -- in abundance, multiply.
From (H3527) kabar; properly, extent of time, i.e. A great while; hence, long ago, formerly, hitherto -- already, (seeing that which), now. see HEBREW (H3527) kabar
The same as (H3528) kbar; length; Kebar, a river of Mesopotamia -- Chebar. Compare (H2249) Chabowr. see HEBREW (H3528) kbar see HEBREW (H2249) Chabowr
Feminine of (H3528) kbar; properly, length, i.e. A measure (of uncertain dimension) -- X little. see HEBREW (H3528) kbar
From (H3527) kabar in its original sense; a sieve (as netted) -- sieve. see HEBREW (H3527) kabar
From an unused root meaning to dominate; a ram (just old enough to butt) -- lamb, sheep.

column8: bring into bondage, force, keep under, subdue, bring into subjection
column9: A primitive root; to tread down; hence, negatively, to disregard; positively, to conquer, subjugate, violate -- bring into bondage, force, keep under, subdue, bring into subjection.
From (H3533) kabash; a footstool (as trodden upon): see HEBREW (H3533) kabash
Or kabsah {kab-saw'}; feminine of (H3532) kebes; a ewe -- (ewe) lamb. see HEBREW (H3532) kebes
From (H3533) kabash; a smelting furnace (as reducing metals) -- furnace. see HEBREW (H3533) kabash
From an unused root meaning to deepen; properly, a pail; but generally of earthenware; a jar for domestic purposes -- barrel, pitcher.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H3576) kazab; false: see HEBREW (H3576) kazab
From the same as (H3537) kad in the sense of striking fire from a metal forged; a sparkling gem, probably the ruby -- agate. see HEBREW (H3537) kad
Of foreign origin; Kedorlaomer, an early Persian king -- Chedorlaomer.

column8: also, here, hitherto, like, on the other side, so and much, such, on that manner
column9: From the prefix k and (H1931) huw'; properly, like this, i.e. By implication, (of manner) thus (or so); also (of place) here (or hither); or (of time) now -- also, here, + hitherto, like, on the other side, so (and much), such, on that manner, (on) this (manner, side, way, way and that way), + mean while, yonder. see HEBREW (H1931) huw'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3541) koh -- hitherto. see HEBREW (H3541) koh

column7: to be or grow dim or faint
column8: darken, be dim, fail, faint, restrain, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to be weak, i.e. (figuratively) to despond (causatively, rebuke), or (of light, the eye) to grow dull -- darken, be dim, fail, faint, restrain, X utterly.

column8: somewhat dark, darkish, wax dim, heaviness, smoking
column9: From (H3543) kahah; feeble, obscure -- somewhat dark, darkish, wax dim, heaviness, smoking. see HEBREW (H3543) kahah
Feminine of (H3544) keheh; properly, a weakening; figuratively, alleviation, i.e. Cure -- healing. see HEBREW (H3544) keheh
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to (H3201) yakol and (H3557) kuwl; to be able -- be able, could. see HEBREW (H3201) yakol see HEBREW (H3557) kuwl

column8: deck, be do the office of a, execute the, minister in the priest\'s office
column9: A primitive root, apparently meaning to mediate in religious services; but used only as denominative from (H3548) kohen; to officiate as a priest; figuratively, to put on regalia -- deck, be (do the office of a, execute the, minister in the) priest('s office). see HEBREW (H3548) kohen

column8: chief ruler, own, priest, prince, principal officer
column9: Active participle of (H3547) kahan; literally, one officiating, a priest; also (by courtesy) an acting priest (although a layman) -- chief ruler, X own, priest, prince, principal officer. see HEBREW (H3547) kahan
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3548) kohen -- priest. see HEBREW (H3548) kohen
From (H3547) kahan; priesthood -- priesthood, priest's office. see HEBREW (H3547) kahan
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H3854) lahag in the sense of piercing; a window (as a perforation) -- window. see HEBREW (H3854) lahag
Of foreign derivation; Kub, a country near Egypt -- Chub.
From an unused root meaning to be high or rounded; a helmet (as arched) -- helmet. Compare (H6959) qowba'. see HEBREW (H6959) qowba'
A primitive root; properly, to prick or penetrate; hence, to blister (as smarting or eating into) -- burn.
From (H3554) kavah; a branding -- burning. see HEBREW (H3554) kavah

Probably from the same as (H3522) Kabbown (in the sense of rolling) or (H3554) kavah (in the sense of blazing); a star (as round or as shining); figuratively, a prince -- star((-gazer)). see HEBREW (H3522) Kabbown see HEBREW (H3554) kavah

column8: be able to, can abide, bear, comprehend, contain, feed, forbearing, guide,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to keep in; hence, to measure; figuratively, to maintain (in various senses) -- (be able to, can) abide, bear, comprehend, contain, feed, forbearing, guide, hold(-ing in), nourish(-er), be present, make provision, receive, sustain, provide sustenance (victuals).
From an unused root meaning to store away; a jewel (probably gold beads) -- tablet.

column8: certainty, confirm, direct, faithfulness, fashion, fasten, firm, be fitted,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be erect (i.e. Stand perpendicular); hence (causatively) to set up, in a great variety of applications, whether literal (establish, fix, prepare, apply), or figurative (appoint, render sure, proper or prosperous) -- certain(-ty), confirm, direct, faithfulness, fashion, fasten, firm, be fitted, be fixed, frame, be meet, ordain, order, perfect, (make) preparation, prepare (self), provide, make provision, (be, make) ready, right, set (aright, fast, forth), be stable, (e-)stablish, stand, tarry, X very deed.
Probably from (H3559) kuwn; established; Kun, a place in Syria -- Chun. see HEBREW (H3559) kuwn
From (H3559) kuwn; something prepared, i.e. A sacrificial wafer -- cake. see HEBREW (H3559) kuwn

From (H3559) kuwn and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has sustained; Conanjah, the name of two Israelites -- Conaniah, Cononiah. Compare (H3663) Knanyah. see HEBREW (H3559) kuwn see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh see HEBREW (H3663) Knanyah

From an unused root meaning to hold together; a cup (as a container), often figuratively, a lot (as if a potion); also some unclean bird, probably an owl (perhaps from the cup-like cavity of its eye) -- cup, (small) owl. Compare (H3599) kiyc. see HEBREW (H3599) kiyc
From an unused root meaning properly, to dig through; a pot or furnace (as if excavated) -- furnace. Compare (H3600) kiyr. see HEBREW (H3600) kiyr
From (H3564) kuwr and (H6227) ashan; furnace of smoke; Cor-Ashan, a place in Palestine -- Chor-ashan. see HEBREW (H3564) kuwr see HEBREW (H6227) ashan
Or (Ezra 1:1 (last time), Ezra 1:2) Koresh {ko'-resh}; from the Persians; Koresh (or Cyrus), the Persian king -- Cyrus. see HEBREW (H2) 'ab
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3566) Kowresh -- Cyrus. see HEBREW (H3566) Kowresh

column4: proper name, masculine person, of a people; proper name, masculine
column7: a son of Ham, also his desc., also a land in the S. Nile Valley
column9: Probably of foreign origin; Cush (or Ethiopia), the name of a son of Ham, and of his territory; also of an Israelite -- Chush, Cush, Ethiopia.
Patronymically from (H3568) Kuwsh; a Cushite, or descendant of Cush -- Cushi, Cushite, Ethiopian(-s). see HEBREW (H3568) Kuwsh
The same as (H3569) Kuwshiy; Cushi, the name of two Israelites -- Cushi. see HEBREW (H3569) Kuwshiy
Feminine of (H3569) Kuwshiy; a Cushite woman: see HEBREW (H3569) Kuwshiy
Perhaps from (H3568) Kuwsh; Cushan, a region of Arabia: see HEBREW (H3568) Kuwsh

Apparently from (H3572) Kuwshan and the dual of (H7564) rish'ah; Cushan of double wickedness; Cushan-Rishathajim, a Mesopotamian king -- Chushan-rishathayim. see HEBREW (H3572) Kuwshan see HEBREW (H7564) rish'ah
From (H3787) kasher; prosperity; in plural freedom: see HEBREW (H3787) kasher
Or (feminine) Kuwthah {koo-thaw'}; of foreign origin; Cuth or Cuthah, a province of Assyria -- Cuth.

column8: fail, be found a, make a liar, lie, lying, be in vain
column9: A primitive root; to lie (i.e. Deceive), literally or figuratively -- fail, (be found a, make a) liar, lie, lying, be in vain.

column8: deceitful, false, leasing, liar, lie, lying
column9: From (H3576) kazab; falsehood; literally (untruth) or figuratively (idol) -- deceitful, false, leasing, + liar, lie, lying. see HEBREW (H3576) kazab
From (H3576) kazab; fallacious; Cozeba, a place in Palestine -- Choseba. see HEBREW (H3576) kazab
From (H3576) kazab; false; Cozbi, a Midianitess -- Cozbi. see HEBREW (H3576) kazab

column7: a place in the plain of Judah
column9: From (H3576) kazab; falsified; Kezib, a place in Palestine -- Chezib. see HEBREW (H3576) kazab

column8: ability, able, chameleon, force, fruits, might, powerful, strength,
column9: Or (Dan. 11:6) kowach {ko'-akh}; from an unused root meaning to be firm; vigor, literally (force, in a good or a bad sense) or figuratively (capacity, means, produce); also (from its hardiness) a large lizard -- ability, able, chameleon, force, fruits, might, power(-ful), strength, substance, wealth.

column8: conceal, cut down off, desolate, hide
column9: A primitive root; to secrete, by act or word; hence (intensively) to destroy -- conceal, cut down (off), desolate, hide.
A primitive root; to paint (with stibium):

column7: to disappoint, deceive, fail, grow lean
column8: deceive, deny, dissemble, fail, deal falsely, be found liars, belie, lying,
column9: A primitive root; to be untrue, in word (to lie, feign, disown) or deed (to disappoint, fail, cringe) -- deceive, deny, dissemble, fail, deal falsely, be found liars, (be-)lie, lying, submit selves.
From (H3584) kachash; literally, a failure of flesh, i.e. Emaciation; figuratively, hypocrisy -- leanness, lies, lying. see HEBREW (H3584) kachash
From (H3584) kachash; faithless -- lying. see HEBREW (H3584) kachash
From (H3554) kavah; a brand or scar -- burning. see HEBREW (H3554) kavah

column8: forasmuch, inasmuch, whereas, assuredly, but, certainly, doubtless,
column9: A primitive particle (the full form of the prepositional prefix) indicating causal relations of all kinds, antecedent or consequent; (by implication) very widely used as a relative conjunction or adverb (as below); often largely modified by other particles annexed -- and, + (forasmuch, inasmuch, where-)as, assured(-ly), + but, certainly, doubtless, + else, even, + except, for, how, (because, in, so, than) that, + nevertheless, now, rightly, seeing, since, surely, then, therefore, + (al-)though, + till, truly, + until, when, whether, while, whom, yea, yet.
From a primitive root meaning to strike: a crushing; figuratively, calamity -- destruction.
From the same as (H3589) kiyd (compare (H3539) kadkod); properly, something struck off, i.e. A spark (as struck) -- spark. see HEBREW (H3589) kiyd see HEBREW (H3539) kadkod

From the same as (H3589) kiyd; properly, something to strike with, i.e. A dart (perhaps smaller that (H2595) chaniyth) -- lance, shield, spear, target. see HEBREW (H3589) kiyd see HEBREW (H2595) chaniyth
The same as (H3591) kiydown; Kidon, a place in Palestine: see HEBREW (H3591) kiydown
Of uncertain derivation; perhaps tumult -- battle.
From (H3559) kuwn; properly, a statue, i.e. Idol; but used (by euphemism) for some heathen deity (perhaps corresponding to Priapus or Baal-peor) -- Chiun. see HEBREW (H3559) kuwn

Or kiyor {kee-yore'}; from the same as (H3564) kuwr; properly, something round (as excavated or bored), i.e. A chafing-dish for coals or a caldron for cooking; hence (from similarity of form) a washbowl; also (for the same reason) a pulpit or platform -- hearth, laver, pan, scaffold. see HEBREW (H3564) kuwr
Or kelay {kay-lah'-ee}; from (H3557) kuwl in the sense of withholding; niggardly -- churl. see HEBREW (H3557) kuwl
From an unused root meaning to clap or strike with noise; a club or sledge-hammer -- hammer.
From the same as (H3558) kuwmaz; a cluster of stars, i.e. The Pleiades -- Pleiades, seven stars. see HEBREW (H3558) kuwmaz
A form for (H3563) kowc; a cup; also a bag for money or weights -- bag, cup, purse. see HEBREW (H3563) kowc
A form for (H3564) kuwr (only in the dual); a cooking range (consisting of two parallel stones, across which the boiler is set): see HEBREW (H3564) kuwr
From (H3787) kasher; literally, a director, i.e. The spindle or shank of a distaff ((H6418) pelek), by which it is twirled -- spindle. see HEBREW (H3787) kasher see HEBREW (H6418) pelek

column8: after that this manner, this matter, even so, in such a case, thus
column9: From (H3541) koh; just so, referring to the previous or following context -- after that (this) manner, this matter, (even) so, in such a case, thus. see HEBREW (H3541) koh

column7: a round, a round district, a round loaf, a round weight, a talent (a measure of weight or money)
column9: From (H3769) karar; a circle, i.e. (by implication) a circumjacent tract or region, expec. The Ghor or valley of the Jordan; also a (round) loaf; also a talent (or large (round) coin) -- loaf, morsel, piece, plain, talent. see HEBREW (H3769) karar

column7: a talent (a measure of weight or money)
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H3603) kikkar; a talent -- talent. see HEBREW (H3603) kikkar

column8: in all manner, ye, altogether, any manner, enough, every one, place, thing,
column9: Or (Jer. 33:8) kowl {kole}; from (H3634) kalal; properly, the whole; hence, all, any or every (in the singular only, but often in a plural sense) -- (in) all (manner, (ye)), altogether, any (manner), enough, every (one, place, thing), howsoever, as many as, (no-)thing, ought, whatsoever, (the) whole, whoso(-ever). see HEBREW (H3634) kalal

column8: all, any, forasmuch as, for this cause, every, though, where,
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H3605) kol -- all, any, + (forasmuch) as, + be-(for this) cause, every, + no (manner, -ne), + there (where)-fore, + though, what (where, who)-soever, (the) whole. see HEBREW (H3605) kol

column8: finish, forbid, keep back, refrain, restrain, retain, shut up, be stayed,
column9: A primitive root; to restrict, by act (hold back or in) or word (prohibit) -- finish, forbid, keep (back), refrain, restrain, retain, shut up, be stayed, withhold.
From (H3607) kala'; a prison -- prison. Compare (H3610) kil'ayim, (H3628) kliy'. see HEBREW (H3607) kala' see HEBREW (H3610) kil'ayim see HEBREW (H3628) kliy'
Apparently from (H3607) kala' and (H1) 'ab; restraint of (his) father; Kilab, an Israelite -- Chileab. see HEBREW (H3607) kala' see HEBREW (H1) 'ab

column8: divers seeds e kinds, mingled seed
column9: Dual of (H3608) kele' in the original sense of separation; two heterogeneities -- divers seeds (-e kinds), mingled (seed). see HEBREW (H3608) kele'
From an unused root means. To yelp, or else to attack; a dog; hence (by euphemism) a male prostitute -- dog.

column7: a son of Jephunneh and sent by Moses to spy out the land
column9: Perhaps a form of (H3611) keleb, or else from the same root in the sense of forcible; Caleb, the name of three Israelites -- Caleb. see HEBREW (H3611) keleb
From (H3612) Kaleb and (H672) 'Ephraath; Caleb- Ephrathah, a place in Egypt (if the text is correct) -- Caleb-ephrathah. see HEBREW (H3612) Kaleb see HEBREW (H672) 'Ephraath
Probably by erroneous transcription for Kalebiy {kaw-lay-bee'}; patronymically from (H3612) Kaleb; a Calebite or descendant of Caleb -- of the house of Caleb. see HEBREW (H3612) Kaleb

column7: to be complete, at an end, finished, accomplished, or spent
column8: accomplish, cease, consume away, determine, destroy utterly
column9: A primitive root; to end, whether intransitive (to cease, be finished, perish) or transitived (to complete, prepare, consume) -- accomplish, cease, consume (away), determine, destroy (utterly), be (when... Were) done, (be an) end (of), expire, (cause to) fail, faint, finish, fulfil, X fully, X have, leave (off), long, bring to pass, wholly reap, make clean riddance, spend, quite take away, waste.
From (H3615) kalah; pining -- fail. see HEBREW (H3615) kalah

column8: altogether, be, utterly consumed, consummation, was determined, utter end, riddance
column9: From (H3615) kalah; a completion; adverb, completely; also destruction -- altogether, (be, utterly) consume(-d), consummation(-ption), was determined, (full, utter) end, riddance. see HEBREW (H3615) kalah
From (H3634) kalal; a bride (as if perfect); hence, a son's wife -- bride, daughter-in-law, spouse. see HEBREW (H3634) kalal
From the same as (H3611) keleb; a bird-trap (as furnished with a clap-stick or treadle to spring it); hence, a basket (as resembling a wicker cage) -- basket, cage. see HEBREW (H3611) keleb
The same as (H3619) klub; Kelub, the name of two Israelites -- Chelub. see HEBREW (H3619) klub
A form of (H3612) Kaleb; Kelubai, an Israelite: see HEBREW (H3612) Kaleb
From (H3615) kalah; completed; Keluhai, an Israelite -- Chelluh. see HEBREW (H3615) kalah
Denominative passive participle from (H3618) kallah; bridehood (only in the plural) -- espousal. see HEBREW (H3618) kallah
From an unused root meaning to be complete; maturity -- full (old) age.
The same as (H3624) kelach; Kelach, a place in Assyria: see HEBREW (H3624) kelach
From (H3605) kol and (H2374) chozeh; every seer; Col- Chozeh, an Israelite -- Col-hozeh. see HEBREW (H3605) kol see HEBREW (H2374) chozeh

column8: armour bearer, artillery, bag, carriage, furnish, furniture, instrument, jewel,
column9: From (H3615) kalah; something prepared, i.e. Any apparatus (as an implement, utensil, dress, vessel or weapon) -- armour ((-bearer)), artillery, bag, carriage, + furnish, furniture, instrument, jewel, that is made of, X one from another, that which pertaineth, pot, + psaltery, sack, stuff, thing, tool, vessel, ware, weapon, + whatsoever. see HEBREW (H3615) kalah
Or kluwi {kel-oo'}; from (H3607) kala' (compare (H3608) kele'); a prison -- prison. see HEBREW (Hkluw1) #NAME? see HEBREW (H3607) kala' see HEBREW (H3608) kele'
Feminine of (H3627) kliy (only in the plural); a kidney (as an essential organ); figuratively, the mind (as the interior self) -- kidneys, reins. see HEBREW (H3627) kliy
A form of (H3631) killayown; Kiljon, an Israelite -- Chilion. see HEBREW (H3631) killayown
From (H3615) kalah; pining, destruction: see HEBREW (H3615) kalah

column8: all, every whit, flame, perfection, utterly, whole burnt offering sacrifice, wholly
column9: From (H3634) kalal; complete; as noun, the whole (specifically, a sacrifice entirely consumed); as adverb, fully -- all, every whit, flame, perfect(-ion), utterly, whole burnt offering (sacrifice), wholly. see HEBREW (H3634) kalal

column7: an Israelite noted for his wisdom
column9: From (H3557) kuwl; sustenance; Calcol, an Israelite -- Calcol, Chalcol. see HEBREW (H3557) kuwl
A primitive root; to complete -- (make) perfect.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3634) kalal; to complete -- finish, make (set) up. see HEBREW (H3634) kalal
From (H3634) kalal; complete; Kelal, an Israelite -- Chelal. see HEBREW (H3634) kalal

column8: be make ashamed, blush, be confounded, be put to confusion, hurt, reproach
column9: A primitive root; properly, to wound; but only figuratively, to taunt or insult -- be (make) ashamed, blush, be confounded, be put to confusion, hurt, reproach, (do, put to) shame.
Of foreign derivation; Kilmad, a place apparently in the Assyrian empire -- Chilmad.
From (H3637) kalam; disgrace -- confusion, dishonour, reproach, shame. see HEBREW (H3637) kalam
From (H3639) klimmah; disgrace -- shame. see HEBREW (H3639) klimmah
Or Kalneh {kal-nay'}; also Kalnow {kal-no'}; of foreign derivation; Calneh or Calno, a place in the Assyrian empire -- Calneh, Calno. Compare (H3656) Kanneh. see HEBREW (H3656) Kanneh
A primitive root; to pine after -- long.

column4: proper name, masculine ; noun, of location
column7: an attendant of David, also a place near Bethlehem
column9: From (H3642) kamahh; pining; Kimham, an Israelite -- Chimham. see HEBREW (H3642) kamahh

column8: according to, such as it were, well as, in comparison of, like as, to, unto, thus,
column9: Or kamow {kaw-mo'}; a form of the prefix \"k-\", but used separately (compare (H3651) ken); as, thus, so -- according to, (such) as (it were, well as), in comparison of, like (as, to, unto), thus, when, worth. see HEBREW (H3651) ken
Or (Jer. 48:7) Kmiysh {kem-eesh'}; from an unused root meaning to subdue; the powerful; Kemosh, the god of the Moabites -- Chemosh.

column7: cummin (a plant grown as a condiment)
column9: From an unused root meaning to store up or preserve; \"cummin\" (from its use as a condiment) -- cummin.
A primitive root; to store away, i.e. (figuratively) in the memory -- lay up in store.

column7: to grow warm and tender, to be or grow hot
column9: A primitive root; properly, to intertwine or contract, i.e. (by implication) to shrivel (as with heat); figuratively, to be deeply affected with passion (love or pity) -- be black, be kindled, yearn.
From (H3648) kamar; properly, an ascetic (as if shrunk with self-maceration), i.e. An idolatrous priest (only in plural) -- Chemarims (idolatrous) priests. see HEBREW (H3648) kamar
Redupl. From (H3648) kamar; obscuration (as if from shrinkage of light, i.e. An eclipse (only in plural) -- blackness. see HEBREW (H3648) kamar

From (H3559) kuwn; properly, set upright; hence (figuratively as adjective) just; but usually (as adverb or conjunction) rightly or so (in various applications to manner, time and relation; often with other particles) -- + after that (this, -ward, -wards), as... As, + (for-)asmuch as yet, + be (for which) cause, + following, howbeit, in (the) like (manner, -wise), X the more, right, (even) so, state, straightway, such (thing), surely, + there (where)-fore, this, thus, true, well, X you. see HEBREW (H3559) kuwn
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3651) ken; so -- thus. see HEBREW (H3651) ken

column8: base, estate, foot, office, place, well
column9: The same as (H3651) ken, used as a noun; a stand, i.e. Pedestal or station -- base, estate, foot, office, place, well. see HEBREW (H3651) ken

From (H3661) kanan in the sense of fastening; a gnat (from infixing its sting; used only in plural (and irreg. In Exod. 8:17, Exod. 8:18; Heb. 13:14)) -- lice, X manner. see HEBREW (H3661) kanan see HEBREW (H18) 'ebuwc
A primitive root; to address by an additional name; hence, to eulogize -- give flattering titles, surname (himself).
For (H3641) Kalneh; Canneh, a place in Assyria -- Canneh. see HEBREW (H3641) Kalneh
From (H3661) kanan; a plant (as set) -- X vineyard. see HEBREW (H3661) kanan
From a unused root meaning to twang; a harp:
For (H3204) Ykonyah; Conjah, an Israelite king -- Coniah. see HEBREW (H3204) Ykonyah

column8: so, in this manner sort, thus
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H3644) kmow; so or thus -- so, (in) this manner (sort), thus. see HEBREW (H3644) kmow
A primitive root; to set out, i.e. Plant -- X vineyard.
From (H3661) kanan; planted; Kenani, an Israelite: see HEBREW (H3661) kanan
Or Knanyahuw {ken-an-yaw'-hoo}; from (H3661) kanan and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has planted; Kenanjah, an Israelite -- Chenaniah. see HEBREW (H3661) kanan see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
A primitive root; to collect; hence, to enfold:

column8: bring down low, into subjection, under, humble self, subdue
column9: A primitive root; properly, to bend the knee; hence, to humiliate, vanquish -- bring down (low), into subjection, under, humble (self), subdue.
From (H3665) kana' in the sense of folding (compare (H3664) kanac); a package -- wares. see HEBREW (H3665) kana' see HEBREW (H3664) kanac

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, masculine; noun masculine
column7: a son of Ham, also his desc. and their land West of the Jordan
column9: From (H3665) kana'; humiliated; Kenaan, a son a Ham; also the country inhabited by him -- Canaan, merchant, traffick. see HEBREW (H3665) kana'
Feminine of (H3667) Kna'an; Kenaanah, the name of two Israelites -- Chenaanah. see HEBREW (H3667) Kna'an

column4: Adjective; name, of a people; substantive; noun masculine
column9: Patrial from (H3667) Kna'an; a Kenaanite or inhabitant of Kenaan; by implication, a pedlar (the Canaanites standing for their neighbors the Ishmaelites, who conducted mercantile caravans) -- Canaanite, merchant, trafficker. see HEBREW (H3667) Kna'an

column7: to be cornered or thrust into a corner
column9: A primitive root; properly, to project laterally, i.e. Probably (reflexive) to withdraw -- be removed.

column8: bird, border, corner, end, feathered, flying, one another, overspreading,
column9: From (H3670) kanaph; an edge or extremity; specifically (of a bird or army) a wing, (of a garment or bed-clothing) a flap, (of the earth) a quarter, (of a building) a pinnacle -- + bird, border, corner, end, feather(-ed), X flying, + (one an-)other, overspreading, X quarters, skirt, X sort, uttermost part, wing((-ed)). see HEBREW (H3670) kanaph

column7: a city in Galilee, also a lake near the city
column9: Or Kinnereth {kin-neh'-reth}; respectively plural and singular feminine from the same as (H3658) kinnowr; perhaps harp-shaped; Kinneroth or Kinnereth, a place in Palestine -- Chinnereth, Chinneroth, Cinneroth. see HEBREW (H3658) kinnowr
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3664) kanac; to assemble -- gather together. see HEBREW (H3664) kanac
From (H3655) kanah; a colleague (as having the same title) -- companion. see HEBREW (H3655) kanah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3674) knath -- companion. see HEBREW (H3674) knath
Apparently a contraction for (H3678) kicce', but probably by erroneous transcription for (H5251) nec -- sworn. see HEBREW (H3678) kicce' see HEBREW (H5251) nec
Or keceh {keh'-seh}; apparently from (H3680) kacah; properly, fulness or the full moon, i.e. Its festival -- (time) appointed. see HEBREW (H3680) kacah
Or kicceh {kis-say'}; from (H3680) kacah; properly, covered, i.e. A throne (as canopied) -- seat, stool, throne. see HEBREW (H3680) kacah
For (H3778) Kasdiy -- Chaldean. see HEBREW (H3778) Kasdiy

column8: clad self, close, conceal, cover self, flee to hide, overwhelm
column9: A primitive root; properly, to plump, i.e. Fill up hollows; by implication, to cover (for clothing or secrecy) -- clad self, close, clothe, conceal, cover (self), (flee to) hide, overwhelm. Compare (H3780) kasah. see HEBREW (H3780) kasah
Passive participle of (H3680) kacah; properly, covered, i.e. (as noun) a covering -- covering. see HEBREW (H3680) kacah
From (H3680) kacah; a cover (garment); figuratively, a veiling -- covering, raiment, vesture. see HEBREW (H3680) kacah
A primitive root; to cut off -- cut down (up).
From (H3688) kacal; properly, fat, i.e. (figuratively) stupid or silly -- fool(-ish). see HEBREW (H3688) kacal
The same as (H3684) kciyl; any notable constellation; specifically Orion (as if a burly one) -- constellation, Orion. see HEBREW (H3684) kciyl
The same as (H3684) kciyl; Kesil, a place in Palestine: see HEBREW (H3684) kciyl
From (H3684) kciyl; silliness -- foolish. see HEBREW (H3684) kciyl
A primitive root; properly, to be fat, i.e. (figuratively) silly -- be foolish.

From (H3688) kacal; properly, fatness, i.e. By implication (literally) the loin (as the seat of the leaf fat) or (generally) the viscera; also (figuratively) silliness or (in a good sense) trust -- confidence, flank, folly, hope, loin. see HEBREW (H3688) kacal
Feminine of (H3689) kecel; in a good sense, trust; in a bad one, silliness -- confidence, folly. see HEBREW (H3689) kecel

column7: the ninth month of the Jewish calendar
column9: Probably of foreign origin; Kisleu, the 9th Heb. Month -- Chisleu.
From (H3688) kacal; hopeful; Kislon, an Israelite -- Chislon. see HEBREW (H3688) kacal

column7: a place on the border of Judah
column9: From (H3688) kacal; fertile; Kesalon, a place in Palestine -- Chesalon. see HEBREW (H3688) kacal
Feminine plural of passive participle of (H3688) kacal; fattened; Kesulloth, a place in Palestine -- Chesulloth. see HEBREW (H3688) kacal

column7: a people desc. from Mizraim, probably ancestors of the Philistines
column9: A plural probably of foreign derivation; Casluchim, a people cognate to the Egyptians -- Casluhim.
From the feminine plural of (H3689) kecel and (H8396) Tabowr; flanks of Tabor; Kisloth-Tabor, a place in Palestine -- Chisloth- tabor. see HEBREW (H3689) kecel see HEBREW (H8396) Tabowr
A primitive root; to shear -- X only, poll. Compare (H3765) kircem. see HEBREW (H3765) kircem
From (H3697) kacam; spelt (from its bristliness as if just shorn) -- fitches, rie. see HEBREW (H3697) kacam
A primitive root; to estimate -- make count.

column8: have desire, be greedy, long, sore
column9: A primitive root; properly, to become pale, i.e. (by implication) to pine after; also to fear -- (have) desire, be greedy, long, sore.
From (H3700) kacaph; silver (from its pale color); by implication, money -- money, price, silver(-ling). see HEBREW (H3700) kacaph
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3701) keceph -- money, silver. see HEBREW (H3701) keceph
Perhaps from (H3701) keceph; silvery; Casiphja, a place in Bab. -- Casiphia. see HEBREW (H3701) keceph
From (H3680) kacah; a cushion or pillow (as covering a seat or bed) -- pillow. see HEBREW (H3680) kacah
(Aramaic) probably from (H3652) ken; now -- now. see HEBREW (H3652) ken
(Aramaic) or kaeth (Aramaic) {keh-eth'}; feminine of (H3705) k'an; thus (only in the formula \"and so forth\") -- at such a time. see HEBREW (H3705) k'an

column8: be angry, be grieved, take indignation, provoke to anger, unto wrath
column9: A primitive root; to trouble; by implication, to grieve, rage, be indignant -- be angry, be grieved, take indignation, provoke (to anger, unto wrath), have sorrow, vex, be wroth.
Or (in Job) kaoas {kah'-as}; from (H3707) ka'ac; vexation: see HEBREW (H3707) ka'ac

column7: hollow or flat of the hand, palm, sole (of the foot), a pan
column8: branch, foot, handful hollow, middle, palm, paw, power, sole,
column9: From (H3721) kaphaph; the hollow hand or palm (so of the paw of an animal, of the sole, and even of the bowl of a dish or sling, the handle of a bolt, the leaves of a palm-tree); figuratively, power -- branch, + foot, hand((-ful), -dle, (-led)), hollow, middle, palm, paw, power, sole, spoon. see HEBREW (H3721) kaphaph
From (H3721) kaphaph; a hollow rock -- rock. see HEBREW (H3721) kaphaph
A primitive root; properly, to bend, i.e. (figuratively) to tame or subdue -- pacify.

column7: a branch, frond (of a palm tree)
column9: Feminine of (H3709) kaph; a leaf of a palm-tree -- branch. see HEBREW (H3709) kaph
From (H3722) kaphar; properly, a cover, i.e. (by implication) a tankard (or covered goblet); also white frost (as covering the ground) -- bason, hoar(-y) frost. see HEBREW (H3722) kaphar
From an unused root meaning to connect; a girder -- beam.

From (H3722) kaphar; a village (as covered in by walls); also a young lion (perhaps as covered with a mane) -- (young) lion, village. Compare (H3723) kaphar. see HEBREW (H3722) kaphar see HEBREW (H3723) kaphar
Feminine of (H3715) kphiyr; the village (always with the art.); Kephirah, a place in Palestine -- Chephirah. see HEBREW (H3715) kphiyr
A primitive root; to fold together; figuratively, to repeat -- double.
From (H3717) kaphal; a duplicate -- double. see HEBREW (H3717) kaphal
A primitive root; to bend -- bend.
From (H3719) kaphan; hunger (as making to stoop with emptiness and pain) -- famine. see HEBREW (H3719) kaphan

column7: to bend, bend down, be bent or bowed
column9: A primitive root; to curve -- bow down (self).

column7: to cover over, pacify, make propitiation
column8: appease, make an atonement, cleanse, disannul, forgive, be merciful, pacify, pardon,
column9: A primitive root; to cover (specifically with bitumen); figuratively, to expiate or condone, to placate or cancel -- appease, make (an atonement, cleanse, disannul, forgive, be merciful, pacify, pardon, purge (away), put off, (make) reconcile(-liation).
From (H3722) kaphar; a village (as protected by walls) -- village. Compare (H3715) kphiyr. see HEBREW (H3722) kaphar see HEBREW (H3715) kphiyr

column7: the price of a life, ransom
column8: bribe, pitch, ransom, satisfaction, sum of money, village
column9: From (H3722) kaphar; properly, a cover, i.e. (literally) a village (as covered in); (specifically) bitumen (as used for coating), and the henna plant (as used for dyeing); figuratively, a redemption-price -- bribe, camphire, pitch, ransom, satisfaction, sum of money, village. see HEBREW (H3722) kaphar
From (H3722) kaphar; expiation (only in plural): see HEBREW (H3722) kaphar

column7: a village of the Ammonites, a village in Benjamin
column9: From (H3723) kaphar and (H5984) Ammowniy, with the article interposed; village of the Ammonite; Kefar-ha-Ammoni, a place in Palestine -- Chefar-haamonai. see HEBREW (H3723) kaphar see HEBREW (H5984) Ammowniy
From (H3722) kaphar; a lid (used only of the cover of the sacred Ark) -- mercy seat. see HEBREW (H3722) kaphar

column7: to make bent, press or bend together
column9: A primitive root; to tread down; figuratively, to humiliate -- cover.
(Aramaic) a root of uncertain correspondence; to fetter -- bind.

Or (Am. 9:1) kaphtowr {kaf-tore'}; probably from an unused root meaning to encircle; a chaplet; but used only in an architectonic sense, i.e. The capital of a column, or a wreath-like button or disk on the candelabrum: knop, (upper) lintel.
Or (Am. 9:7) Kaphtowr {kaf-tore'}; apparently the same as (H3730) kaphtor; Caphtor (i.e. A wreath-shaped island), the original seat of the Philistines -- Caphtor. see HEBREW (H3730) kaphtor

column7: descendant of Mizraim, also their land
column9: Patrial from (H3731) Kaphtor; a Caphtorite (collectively) or native of Caphtor -- Caphthorim, Caphtorim(-s). see HEBREW (H3731) Kaphtor

column8: captain, furniture, lamb, large pasture, ram
column9: From (H3769) karar in the sense of plumpness; a ram (as full-grown and fat), including a battering-ram (as butting); hence, a meadow (as for sheep); also a pad or camel's saddle (as puffed out) -- captain, furniture, lamb, (large) pasture, ram. See also (H1033) Beyth Kar, (H3746) kariy. see HEBREW (H3769) karar see HEBREW (H1033) Beyth Kar see HEBREW (H3746) kariy
From the same as (H3564) kuwr; properly, a deep round vessel, i.e. (specifically) a cor or measure for things dry -- cor, measure. Aramaic the same. see HEBREW (H3564) kuwr
(Aramaic) probably corresponding to (H3738) karah in the sense of piercing (figuratively); to grieve -- be grieved. see HEBREW (H3738) karah
From the same as (H3525) kebel; to gird or clothe: see HEBREW (H3525) kebel
(Aramaic) from a verb corresponding to that of (H3736) karbel; a mantle -- hat. see HEBREW (H3736) karbel
A primitive root; properly, to dig; figuratively, to plot; generally, to bore or open -- dig, X make (a banquet), open.

Usually assigned as a primitive root, but probably only a special application of (H3738) karah (through the common idea of planning implied in a bargain); to purchase -- buy, prepare. see HEBREW (H3738) karah
From (H3739) karah; a purchase -- provision. see HEBREW (H3739) karah
Feminine of (H3733) kar; a meadow -- cottage. see HEBREW (H3733) kar

column7: probably an order of angelic beings
column9: An angelic being -- cherub, (plural) cherubims.
The same as (H3742) kruwb; Kerub, a place in Bab.: see HEBREW (H3742) kruwb
(Aramaic) from (H3745) kraz; a herald -- herald. see HEBREW (H3745) kraz
(Aramaic) probably of Greek origin; to proclaim -- make a proclamation.
Perhaps an abridged plural of (H3733) kar in the sense of leader (of the flock); a life-guardsman -- captains, Cherethites (from the margin). see HEBREW (H3733) kar

column7: a brook where Elijah was hidden
column9: From (H3772) karath; a cut; Kerith, a brook of Palestine: see HEBREW (H3772) karath
From (H3772) karath; a cutting (of the matrimonial bond), i.e. Divorce -- divorce(-ment). see HEBREW (H3772) karath
Expanded from the same as (H3522) Kabbown; a rim or top margin -- compass. see HEBREW (H3522) Kabbown
Probably of foreign origin; the crocus -- saffron.
Of foreign derivation; Karkemish, a place in Syria -- Carchemish.

column8: Of Persian origin; Karkas, a eunuch of Xerxes:
column9: Of Persian origin; Karkas, a eunuch of Xerxes:
From (H3769) karar; a dromedary (from its rapid motion as if dancing) -- swift beast. see HEBREW (H3769) karar

column8: vines, increase of the vineyards, vintage
column9: From an unused root of uncertain meaning; a garden or vineyard -- vines, (increase of the) vineyard(-s), vintage. See also (H1021) Beyth hak-Kerem. see HEBREW (H1021) Beyth hak-Kerem

column8: vine dresser as one or two words
column9: Active participle of an imaginary denominative from (H3754) kerem; a vinedresser -- vine dresser (as one or two words). see HEBREW (H3754) kerem
From (H3754) kerem; gardener; Karmi, the name of three Israelites -- Carmi. see HEBREW (H3754) kerem

column8: a Karmite or descendant of Karmi -- Carmites
column9: Patronymically from (H3756) Karmiy; a Karmite or descendant of Karmi -- Carmites. see HEBREW (H3756) Karmiy
Probably of foreign origin; carmine, a deep red:

column7: a plantation, garden land, fruit, garden growth
column8: full green ears of corn, fruitful field place, plentiful field
column9: From (H3754) kerem; a planted field (garden, orchard, vineyard or park); by implication, garden produce -- full (green) ears (of corn), fruitful field (place), plentiful (field). see HEBREW (H3754) kerem

column7: a mountain promontory on the Mediterranean, also a city near Hebron
column9: The same as (H3759) karmel; Karmel, the name of a hill and of a town in Palestine -- Carmel, fruitful (plentiful) field, (place). see HEBREW (H3759) karmel
Patron from (H3760) Karmel; a Karmelite or inhabitant of Karmel (the town) -- Carmelite. see HEBREW (H3760) Karmel
Feminine of (H3761) Karmliy; a Karmelitess or female inhabitant of Karmel -- Carmelitess. see HEBREW (H3761) Karmliy
Of uncertain derivation; Keran, an aboriginal Idumaean -- Cheran.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3678) kicce'; a throne -- throne. see HEBREW (H3678) kicce'
From (H3697) kacam; to lay waste -- waste. see HEBREW (H3697) kacam

column8: bow down, self, bring down low, cast down, couch, fall, feeble, kneeling,
column9: A primitive root; to bend the knee; by implication, to sink, to prostrate -- bow (down, self), bring down (low), cast down, couch, fall, feeble, kneeling, sink, smite (stoop) down, subdue, X very.
From (H3766) kara'; the leg (from the knee to the ankle) of men or locusts (only in the dual) -- leg. see HEBREW (H3766) kara'
Of foreign origin; byssus or fine vegetable wool:
A primitive root; to dance (i.e. Whirl) -- dance(-ing).
By variation from (H7164) qarac; the paunch or belly (as swelling out) -- belly. see HEBREW (H7164) qarac
Of foreign origin; Karshena, a courtier of Xerxes -- Carshena.

column8: be chewed, be con-federate, covenant, cut down, off, destroy, fail, feller,
column9: A primitive root; to cut (off, down or asunder); by implication, to destroy or consume; specifically, to covenant (i.e. Make an alliance or bargain, originally by cutting flesh and passing between the pieces) -- be chewed, be con-(feder-)ate, covenant, cut (down, off), destroy, fail, feller, be freed, hew (down), make a league ((covenant)), X lose, perish, X utterly, X want.
Passive participle feminine of (H3772) karath; something cut, i.e. A hewn timber -- beam. see HEBREW (H3772) karath

column7: the foreign bodyguard of King David
column9: Probably from (H3772) karath in the sense of executioner; a Kerethite or life-guardsman (compare (H2876) tabbach) (only collectively in the singular as plural) -- Cherethims, Cherethites. see HEBREW (H3772) karath see HEBREW (H2876) tabbach
Apparently by transposition for (H3532) kebes; a young sheep -- lamb. see HEBREW (H3532) kebes
Feminine of (H3775) keseb; a young ewe -- lamb. see HEBREW (H3775) keseb
From an unused root of uncertain meaning; Kesed, a relative of Abraham -- Onesed.

column7: a region of S. Bab. and its inhab
column9: (occasionally with enclitic) Kasdiymah {kas-dee'- maw}; towards the Kasdites -- into Chaldea), patronymically from (H3777) Kesed (only in the plural); a Kasdite, or descendant of Kesed; by implication, a Chaldaean (as if so descended); also an astrologer (as if proverbial of that people -- Chaldeans, Chaldees, inhabitants of Chaldea.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3778) Kasdiy; a Chaldaean or inhabitant of Chaldaea; by implication, a Magian or professional astrologer -- Chaldean. see HEBREW (H3778) Kasdiy

column7: to be sated or gorged (with food)
column9: A primitive root; to grow fat (i.e. Be covered with flesh) -- be covered. Compare (H3680) kacah. see HEBREW (H3680) kacah
From (H3782) kashal; properly, a feller, i.e. An axe: see HEBREW (H3782) kashal

column8: bereave, cast down, be decayed, cause to fail, make to fall down feeble, be the ruined
column9: A primitive root; to totter or waver (through weakness of the legs, especially the ankle); by implication, to falter, stumble, faint or fall -- bereave (from the margin), cast down, be decayed, (cause to) fail, (cause, make to) fall (down, -ing), feeble, be (the) ruin(-ed, of), (be) overthrown, (cause to) stumble, X utterly, be weak.
From (H3782) kashal; properly, a tottering, i.e. Ruin -- fall. see HEBREW (H3782) kashal
A primitive root; properly, to whisper a spell, i.e. To inchant or practise magic -- sorcerer, (use) witch(-craft).
From (H3784) kashaph; magic -- sorcery, witchcraft. see HEBREW (H3784) kashaph
From (H3784) kashaph; a magician -- sorcerer. see HEBREW (H3784) kashaph

column7: to be advantageous, proper, or suitable, to succeed
column9: A primitive root properly, to be straight or right; by implication, to be acceptable; also to succeed or prosper -- direct, be right, prosper.
From (H3787) kasher; success, advantage -- equity, good, right. see HEBREW (H3787) kasher
A primitive root; to grave, by implication, to write (describe, inscribe, prescribe, subscribe) -- describe, record, prescribe, subscribe, write(-ing, -ten).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3789) kathab -- write(-ten). see HEBREW (H3789) kathab
From (H3789) kathab; something written, i.e. A writing, record or book -- register, scripture, writing. see HEBREW (H3789) kathab
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3791) kathab -- prescribing, writing(-ten). see HEBREW (H3791) kathab

column8: a letter or other mark branded on the skin
column9: From (H3789) kathab; a letter or other mark branded on the skin -- X any (mark). see HEBREW (H3789) kathab

column7: a son of Javan, also his desc. and their land
column9: Or Kittiyiy {kit-tee-ee'}; patrial from an unused name denoting Cyprus (only in the plural); a Kittite or Cypriote; hence, an islander in general, i.e. The Greeks or Romans on the shores opposite Palestine -- Chittim, Kittim.
From (H3807) kathath; beaten, i.e. Pure (oil): see HEBREW (H3807) kathath
From an unused root meaning to compact; a wall (as gathering inmates) -- wall.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3796) kothel -- wall. see HEBREW (H3796) kothel
From (H3796) kothel and (H376) 'iysh; wall of a man; Kithlish, a place in Palestine -- Kithlish. see HEBREW (H3796) kothel see HEBREW (H376) 'iysh
A primitive root; properly, to carve or engrave, i.e. (by implication) to inscribe indelibly -- mark.
From (H3799) katham; properly, something carved out, i.e. Ore; hence, gold (pure as originally mined) -- ((most) fine, pure) gold(-en wedge). see HEBREW (H3799) katham
Or kuttoneth {koot-to'-neth}; from an unused root meaning to cover (compare (H3802) katheph); a shirt -- coat, garment, robe. see HEBREW (H3802) katheph

From an unused root meaning to clothe; the shoulder (proper, i.e. Upper end of the arm; as being the spot where the garments hang); figuratively, side-piece or lateral projection of anything -- arm, corner, shoulder(-piece), side, undersetter.

column8: beset round, compass about, be crowne, suffer
column9: A primitive root; to enclose; hence (in a friendly sense) to crown, (in a hostile one) to besiege; also to wait (as restraining oneself) -- beset round, compass about, be crowned inclose round, suffer.
From (H3803) kathar; properly, a circlet, i.e. A diadem: see HEBREW (H3803) kathar
Feminine active participle of (H3803) kathar; the capital of a column -- chapiter. see HEBREW (H3803) kathar
A primitive root; to butt or pound -- bray.

column8: beat down, to pieces, break in pieces, crushed, destroy, discomfit, smite, stamp
column9: A primitive root; to bruise or violently strike -- beat (down, to pieces), break in pieces, crushed, destroy, discomfit, smite, stamp.

column8: before, or else, ere, except, ignorant, much, less, nay,
column9: Or lowi {lo}; or loh (Deut. 3:11) {lo}; a primitive particle; not (the simple or abs. Negation); by implication, no; often used with other particles (as follows) -- X before, + or else, ere, + except, ig(-norant), much, less, nay, neither, never, no((-ne), -r, (-thing)), (X as though...,(can-), for) not (out of), of nought, otherwise, out of, + surely, + as truly as, + of a truth, + verily, for want, + whether, without.

column8: or even, neither, none cannot, as nothing, without
column9: (Aramaic) or lah (Aramaic) (Dan. 4:32) {law}; corresponding to (H3808) lo' -- or even, neither, no(-ne, -r), ((can-))not, as nothing, without. see HEBREW (H3808) lo'

Or Low Dbar (2 Samuel 9:4, 2 Samuel 9:5) {lo deb-ar'}; or Lidbir (Joshua 13:26) {lid-beer'}; (probably rather Lodbar {lo-deb-ar'}); from (H3808) lo' and (H1699) dober; pastureless; Lo-Debar, a place in Palestine -- Debir, Lo-debar. see HEBREW (H5) 'Abagtha' see HEBREW (H3808) lo' see HEBREW (H1699) dober

column8: faint, grieve, loathe, be, make weary selves
column9: A primitive root; to tire; (figuratively) to be (or make) disgusted -- faint, grieve, lothe, (be, make) weary (selves).
From (H3811) la'ah; weary; Leah, a wife of Jacob -- Leah. see HEBREW (H3811) la'ah
A primitive root; to muffle -- cover.
From (H3813) la'at (or perhaps for active participle of (H3874) luwt); properly, muffled, i.e. Silently -- softly. see HEBREW (H3813) la'at see HEBREW (H3874) luwt
From the prepositional prefix and (H410) 'el; (belonging) to God; Lael an Israelite -- Lael. see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Or l owm {leh-ome'}; from an unused root meaning to gather; a community -- nation, people.
Plural of (H3816) lom; communities; Leum mim, an Arabian -- Leummim. see HEBREW (H3816) lom

column7: not my people, symbolic name of Hosea\'s son
column9: From (H3808) lo' and (H5971) am with pronominal suffix; not my people; Lo-Ammi, the symbolic name of a son of Hosea -- Lo-ammi. see HEBREW (H3808) lo' see HEBREW (H5971) am

column7: without compassion, symbolic name of Hosea\'s daughter
column9: From (H3808) lo' and (H7355) racham; not pitied; Lo- Ruchamah, the symbol. Name of a son of Hosea -- Lo-ruhamah. see HEBREW (H3808) lo' see HEBREW (H7355) racham

column8: care for, comfortably, consent, considered, courageous, friendly, broken, hard,
column9: A form of (H3824) lebab; the heart; also used (figuratively) very widely for the feelings, the will and even the intellect; likewise for the centre of anything -- + care for, comfortably, consent, X considered, courag(-eous), friend(-ly), ((broken-), (hard-), (merry-), (stiff-), (stout-), double) heart((-ed)), X heed, X I, kindly, midst, mind(-ed), X regard((-ed)), X themselves, X unawares, understanding, X well, willingly, wisdom. see HEBREW (H3824) lebab
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3820) leb -- heart. see HEBREW (H3820) leb
Plural of (H3833) labiy'; lionesses; Lebaoth, a place in Palestine -- Lebaoth. See also (H1034) Beyth Lba'owth. see HEBREW (H3833) labiy' see HEBREW (H1034) Beyth Lba'owth

column7: to get a mind or to encourage
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be enclosed (as if with fat); by implication (as denominative from (H3824) lebab) to unheart, i.e. (in a good sense) transport (with love), or (in a bad sense) stultify; also (as denominative from (H3834) labiybah) to make cakes -- make cakes, ravish, be wise. see HEBREW (H3824) lebab see HEBREW (H3834) labiybah

column8: bethink themselves, breast, comfortably, courage, faint, tenderhearted
column9: From (H3823) labab; the heart (as the most interior organ); used also like (H3820) leb -- + bethink themselves, breast, comfortably, courage, ((faint), (tender-)heart((-ed)), midst, mind, X unawares, understanding. see HEBREW (H3823) labab see HEBREW (H3820) leb
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3824) lebab -- heart. see HEBREW (H3824) lebab
Feminine of (H3820) leb; the heart -- heart. see HEBREW (H3820) leb
For (H3852) lehabah; flame -- flame. see HEBREW (H3852) lehabah
Or lbonah {leb-o-naw'}; from (H3836) laban; frankincense (from its whiteness or perhaps that of its smoke) -- (frank-)incense. see HEBREW (H3836) laban
The same as (H3828) lbownah; Lebonah, a place in Palestine -- Lebonah. see HEBREW (H3828) lbownah

column8: apparel, clothed with, clothing, garment, raiment, vestment, vesture
column9: Or lbush {leb-oosh'}; from (H3847) labash; a garment (literally or figuratively); by implication (euphem.) A wife -- apparel, clothed with, clothing, garment, raiment, vestment, vesture. see HEBREW (H3847) labash
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3830) lbuwsh -- garment. see HEBREW (H3830) lbuwsh

column7: to thrust down, out, or away
column9: A primitive root; to overthrow; intransposed, to fall -- fall.

column4: noun masculine, feminine; noun feminine; noun masculine; feminine
column8: great, old, stout lion, lioness, young lion
column9: Or (Ezek. 19:2) lbiyao {leb-ee-yaw'}; irreg. Masculine plural lbaviym {leb-aw-eem'}; irreg. Feminine plural lbaeowth {leb-aw-oth'}; from an unused root men. To roar; a lion (properly, a lioness as the fiercer (although not a roarer; compare (H738) 'ariy)) -- (great, old, stout) lion, lioness, young (lion). see HEBREW (H738) 'ariy
Or rather lbibah {leb-ee-baw'}; from (H3823) labab in its original sense of fatness (or perhaps of folding); a cake (either as fried or turned) -- cake. see HEBREW (H3823) labab

column8: make brick, be made, make whiter
column9: A primitive root; to be (or become) white; also (as denominative from (H3843) lbenah) to make bricks -- make brick, be (made, make) white(-r). see HEBREW (H3843) lbenah
Or (Gen. 49:12) laben {law-bane'}; from (H3835) laban; white -- white. see HEBREW (H3835) laban

column4: proper name, masculine; proper name, of a location
column9: The same as (H3836) laban; Laban, a Mesopotamian; also a place in the Desert -- Laban. see HEBREW (H3836) laban
Or Lbanah {leb-aw-naw'}; the same as (H3842) lbanah; Lebana or Lebanah, one of the Nethinim -- Lebana, Lebanah. see HEBREW (H3842) lbanah
From (H3835) laban; some sort of whitish tree, perhaps the storax -- poplar. see HEBREW (H3835) laban
From (H3835) laban; properly, whiteness, i.e. (by implication) transparency -- paved. see HEBREW (H3835) laban

column7: a city in S.W. Judah, also a place in the wilderness
column9: The same as (H3839) libneh; Libnah, a place in the Desert and one in Palestine -- Libnah. see HEBREW (H3839) libneh
From (H3835) laban; properly, (the) white, i.e. The moon -- moon. See also (H3838) Lbana'. see HEBREW (H3835) laban see HEBREW (H3838) Lbana'
From (H3835) laban; a brick (from the whiteness of the clay) -- (altar of) brick, tile. see HEBREW (H3835) laban

column7: a wooded mountain range on the N. border of Isr
column9: From (H3825) lbab; (the) white mountain (from its snow); Lebanon, a mountain range in Palestine -- Lebanon. see HEBREW (H3825) lbab
From (H3835) laban; white; Libni, an Israelite -- Libni. see HEBREW (H3835) laban
Patronymically from (H3845) Libniy; a Libnite or descendants of Libni (collectively) -- Libnites. see HEBREW (H3845) Libniy

column7: to put on, wear, clothe, be clothed
column8: in apparel, arm, array self, clothe self, come upon, put on, upon, wear
column9: Or labesh {law-bashe'}; a primitive root; properly, wrap around, i.e. (by implication) to put on a garment or clothe (oneself, or another), literally or figuratively -- (in) apparel, arm, array (self), clothe (self), come upon, put (on, upon), wear.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3847) labash -- clothe. see HEBREW (H3847) labash
From an unused root apparently meaning to deepen or hollow (like (H3537) kad); a log or measure for liquids -- log (of oil). see HEBREW (H3537) kad

column7: a city in Benjamin near Joppa
column9: From an unused root of uncertain signification; Lod, a place in Palestine -- Lod.
From an usused root meaning to gleam; a flash; figuratively, a sharply polished blade or point of a weapon -- blade, bright, flame, glittering.
Or lahebeth {lah-eh'-beth}; feminine of (H3851) lahab, and meaning the same -- flame(-ming), head (of a spear). see HEBREW (H3851) lahab
Plural of (H3851) lahab; flames; Lehabim, a son of Mizrain, and his descendants -- Lehabim. see HEBREW (H3851) lahab
From an unused root meaning to be eager; intense mental application -- study.
From an unused root meaning to glow (compare (H3851) lahab) or else to be earnest (compare (H3854) lahag); Lahad, an Israelite -- Lahad. see HEBREW (H3851) lahab see HEBREW (H3854) lahag
A primitive root meaning properly, to burn, i.e. (by implication) to be rabid (figuratively, insane); also (from the exhaustion of frenzy) to languish -- faint, mad.

column8: burn up, set on fire, flaming, kindle
column9: A primitive root; properly, to lick, i.e. (by implication) to blaze -- burn (up), set on fire, flaming, kindle.
From (H3857) lahat; a blaze; -- flaming. see HEBREW (H3857) lahat
A primitive root; properly, to burn in, i.e. (figuratively) to rankle -- wound.

column8: for them by mistake for prepositional suffix
column9: From the prepositional prefix meaning to or for and (H2005) hen; popularly for if; hence, therefore -- for them (by mistake for prepositional suffix). see HEBREW (H2005) hen
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3860) lahen; therefore; also except -- but, except, save, therefore, wherefore. see HEBREW (H3860) lahen
Probably from an unused root meaning to gather; an assembly -- company.

column8: if haply, peradventure, I pray thee, though, I would, would God that
column9: Or lu {loo}; or luw {loo}; a conditional particle; if; by implication (interj. As a wish) would that! -- if (haply), peradventure, I pray thee, though, I would, would God (that).

column8: A dry region; apparently a Libyan or inhabitant of interior Africa
column9: Or Lubbiy (Dan. 11:43) {loob-bee'}; partrial from a name probably derived from an unused root meaning to thirst, i.e. A dry region; apparently a Libyan or inhabitant of interior Africa (only in plural):

column4: proper name, masculine and of a people
column7: a son of Shem, also his desc. and their land
column9: Probably of foreign derivation; Lud, the name of two nations -- Lud, Lydia.
Or Luwdiyiy {loo-dee-ee'}; patrial from (H3865) Luwd; a Ludite or inhabitants of Lud (only in plural) -- Ludim. Lydians. see HEBREW (H3865) Luwd

column8: abide with, borrower, cleave, join self, lender
column9: A primitive root; properly, to twine, i.e. (by implication) to unite, to remain; also to borrow (as a form of obligation) or (caus.) To lend -- abide with, borrow(-er), cleave, join (self), lend(-er).

A primitive root; to turn aside (compare (H3867) lavah, (H3874) luwt and (H3885) luwn), i.e. (literally) to depart, (figuratively) be perverse -- depart, froward, perverse(-ness). see HEBREW (H3867) lavah see HEBREW (H3874) luwt see HEBREW (H3885) luwn
Probably of foreign origin; some kind of nut-tree, perhaps the almond -- hazel.

column7: earlier name of Bethel, also a Hittite city
column9: Probably from (H3869) luwz (as growing there); Luz, the name of two places in Palestine -- Luz. see HEBREW (H3869) luwz

column7: a tablet, board or plank, a plate
column9: Or luach {loo'-akh}; from a primitive root; probably meaning to glisten; a tablet (as polished), of stone, wood or metal -- board, plate, table.
Or Luchowth (Jer. 48:5) {loo-khoth'}; from the same as (H3871) luwach; floored; Luchith, a place East of the Jordan -- Luhith. see HEBREW (H3871) luwach
Active participle of (H3907) lachash; (the) enchanter; Lochesh, an Israelite -- Hallohesh, Haloshesh (includ. The article). see HEBREW (H3907) lachash

column7: to wrap closely or tightly, enwrap, envelop
column9: A primitive root; to wrap up -- cast, wrap.
From (H3874) luwt; a veil -- covering. see HEBREW (H3874) luwt
The same as (H3875) lowt; Lot, Abraham's nephew -- Lot. see HEBREW (H3875) lowt
From (H3875) lowt; covering; Lotan, an Idumaean: see HEBREW (H3875) lowt

column7: a son of Jacob, also the tribe descended from him
column9: From (H3867) lavah; attached; Levi, a son of Jacob -- Levi. See also (H3879) Leviy, (H3881) Leviyiy. see HEBREW (H3867) lavah see HEBREW (H3879) Leviy see HEBREW (H3881) Leviyiy
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3880) livyah -- Levite. see HEBREW (H3880) livyah
From (H3867) lavah; something attached, i.e. A wreath: see HEBREW (H3867) lavah
Or Leviy {lay-vee'}; patronymically from (H3878) Leviy; a Levite or descendant of Levi -- Leviite. see HEBREW (H3878) Leviy

column7: serpent, a sea monster or dragon
column9: From (H3867) lavah; a wreathed animal, i.e. A serpent (especially the crocodile or some other large sea- monster); figuratively, the constellation of the dragon; also as a symbol of Bab. -- leviathan, mourning. see HEBREW (H3867) lavah

column7: a shaft or enclosed space with steps or ladder
column9: From an unused root meaning to fold back; a spiral step -- winding stair. Compare (H3924) lula'ah. see HEBREW (H3924) lula'ah
Or luwley {loo lay'}; from (H3863) luw' and (H3808) lo'; if not -- except, had not, if (...not), unless, were it not that. see HEBREW (H3863) luw' see HEBREW (H3808) lo'

column7: to lodge, pass the night, abide
column8: abide all night, continue, dwell, endure, grudge, be left, lie all night
column9: Or liyn {leen}; a primitive root; to stop (usually over night); by implication, to stay permanently; hence (in a bad sense) to be obstinate (especially in words, to complain) -- abide (all night), continue, dwell, endure, grudge, be left, lie all night, (cause to) lodge (all night, in, -ing, this night), (make to) murmur, remain, tarry (all night, that night).
A primitive root; to gulp; figuratively, to be rash -- swallow down (up).

column7: ambassador, have in derision, interpreter, make a mock, mocker
column8: ambassador, have in derision, interpreter, make a mock, mocker
column9: A primitive root; properly, to make mouths at, i.e. To scoff; hence (from the effort to pronounce a foreign language) to interpret, or (generally) intercede -- ambassador, have in derision, interpreter, make a mock, mocker, scorn(-er, -ful), teacher.
A primitive root; to knead -- knead.
From (H3888) luwsh; kneading; Lush, a place in Palestine -- Laish (from the margin). Compare (H3919) Layish. see HEBREW (H3888) luwsh see HEBREW (H3919) Layish
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H3867) lavah; properly, adhesion, i.e. (as preposition) with -- X thee. see HEBREW (H3867) lavah
From (H3868) luwz; perverseness -- perverse. see HEBREW (H3868) luwz
From an unused root meaning to be new; fresh, i.e. Unused or undried -- green, moist.
From the same as (H3892) lach; freshness, i.e. Vigor: see HEBREW (H3892) lach
Or lachum {law-khoom'}; passive participle of (H3898) lacham; properly, eaten, i.e. Food; also flesh, i.e. Body -- while...is eating, flesh. see HEBREW (H3898) lacham
From an unused root meaning to be soft; the cheek (from its fleshiness); hence, the jaw-bone -- cheek (bone), jaw (bone).
A form of (H3895) lchiy; Lechi, a place in Palestine -- Lehi. Compare also (H7437) Ramath Lechiy. see HEBREW (H3895) lchiy see HEBREW (H7437) Ramath Lechiy
A primitive root; to lick -- lick (up).

column8: devour, eat, ever, fighting, overcome, prevail, make warring
column9: A primitive root; to feed on; figuratively, to consume; by implication, to battle (as destruction) -- devour, eat, X ever, fight(-ing), overcome, prevail, (make) war(-ring).

column8: showbread, eat, food, fruit, loaf, meat, victuals
column9: From (H3898) lacham; food (for man or beast), especially bread, or grain (for making it) -- ((shew-))bread, X eat, food, fruit, loaf, meat, victuals. See also (H1036) Beyth l-'Aphrah. see HEBREW (H3898) lacham see HEBREW (H1036) Beyth l-'Aphrah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3899) lechem -- feast. see HEBREW (H3899) lechem
From (H3898) lacham, battle -- war. see HEBREW (H3898) lacham

From (H3899) lechem; foodful; Lachmi, an Israelite; or rather probably a brief form (or perhaps erroneous transcription) for (H1022) Beyth hal-Lachmiy -- Lahmi. See also (H3433) Yashubiy Lechem. see HEBREW (H3899) lechem see HEBREW (H3433) Yashubiy Lechem see HEBREW (H1022) Beyth hal-Lachmiy
Probably by erroneous transcription for Lachmam {lakh-mawm'}; from (H3899) lechem; food-like; Lachmam or Lachmas, a place in Palestine -- Lahmam. see HEBREW (H3899) lechem
(Aramaic) from an unused root of uncertain meaning; a concubine -- concubine.

column8: afflict, crush, force, hold fast, oppressor, thrust self
column9: A primitive root; properly, to press, i.e. (figuratively) to distress -- afflict, crush, force, hold fast, oppress(-or), thrust self.
From (H3905) lachats; distress -- affliction, oppression. see HEBREW (H3905) lachats
A primitive root; to whisper; by implication, to mumble a spell (as a magician) -- charmer, whisper (together).

From (H3907) lachash; properly, a whisper, i.e. By implication, (in a good sense) a private prayer, (in a bad one) an incantation; concretely, an amulet -- charmed, earring, enchantment, orator, prayer. see HEBREW (H3907) lachash

A form of (H3814) la't or else participle from (H3874) luwt; properly, covered, i.e. Secret; by implication, incantation; also secrecy or (adverb) covertly: see HEBREW (H3814) la't see HEBREW (H3874) luwt
Probably from (H3874) luwt; a gum (from its sticky nature), probably ladanum -- myrrh. see HEBREW (H3874) luwt
From an unused root meaning to hide; a kind of lizard (from its covert habits) -- lizard.

column7: hammered ones, descendant of Abraham and Keturah
column9: Masculine plural of passive participle of (H3913) latash; hammered (i.e. Oppressed) ones; Letushim, an Arabian tribe -- Letushim. see HEBREW (H3913) latash
A primitive root; properly, to hammer out (an edge), i.e. To sharpen -- instructer, sharp(-en), whet.
A form of (H3880) livyah; a wreath -- addition. see HEBREW (H3880) livyah

Or (Isa. 21:11) leyl {lale}; also laylah {lah'- yel-aw}; from the same as (H3883) luwl; properly, a twist (away of the light), i.e. Night; figuratively, adversity -- ((mid-))night (season). see HEBREW (H3883) luwl
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3815) La'el -- night. see HEBREW (H3815) La'el
From (H3915) layil; a night spectre -- screech owl. see HEBREW (H3915) layil
From (H3888) luwsh in the sense of crushing; a lion (from his destructive blows) -- (old)lion. see HEBREW (H3888) luwsh

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine; proper name, of a location
column7: lion, a city and region in N. Canaan
column9: The same as (H3918) layish; Laish, the name of two places in Palestine -- Laish. Compare (H3889) Luwsh. see HEBREW (H3918) layish see HEBREW (H3889) Luwsh

column8: catch self, be frozen, stick together, take
column9: A primitive root; to catch (in a net, trap or pit); generally, to capture or occupy; also to choose (by lot); figuratively, to cohere -- X at all, catch (self), be frozen, be holden, stick together, take.
From (H3920) lakad; something to capture with, i.e. A noose -- being taken. see HEBREW (H3920) lakad

column8: a journey; Lekah, a place in Palestine
column9: From (H3212) yalak; a journey; Lekah, a place in Palestine: see HEBREW (H3212) yalak

column7: a Canaanite city Southwest of Jer
column9: From an unused root of uncertain meaning; Lakish, a place in Palestine -- Lachish.
From the same as (H3883) luwl; a loop -- loop. see HEBREW (H3883) luwl
A primitive root; properly, to goad, i.e. (by implication) to teach (the rod being an Oriental incentive):(un-) accustomed, X diligently, expert, instruct, learn, skilful, teach(-er, - ing).
A prol. And separable form of the prepositional prefix; to or for -- at, for, to, upon.

column8: Lemuel or Lemoel, a symbolic name of Solomon
column9: Or Lmow el {lem-o-ale'}; from (H3926) lmow and (H410) 'el; (belonging) to God; Lemuel or Lemoel, a symbolic name of Solomon: see HEBREW (H3926) lmow see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Or limmud {lim-mood'}; from (H3925) lamad; instructed: see HEBREW (H3925) lamad

column7: a descendant of Cain, also a descendant of Seth
column9: From an unused root of uncertain meaning; Lemek, the name of two antediluvian patriarchs -- Lamech.
From (H3886) luwa'; the gullet -- throat. see HEBREW (H3886) luwa'
A primitive root; to deride -- mock.
A primitive root; to deride; by implication (as if imitating a foreigner) to speak unintelligibly -- have in derision, laugh (to scorn), mock (on), stammering.
From (H3932) la'ag; derision, scoffing -- derision, scorn (-ing). see HEBREW (H3932) la'ag
From (H3932) la'ag; a buffoon; also a foreigner -- mocker, stammering. see HEBREW (H3932) la'ag
From an unused root of uncertain meaning; Ladah, an Israelite -- Laadah.
From the same as (H3935) La'dah; Ladan, the name of two Israelites -- Laadan. see HEBREW (H3935) La'dah

column8: to speak in a foreign tongue
column9: A primitive root; to speak in a foreign tongue:
A primitive root; to swallow greedily; causatively, to feed -- feed.
From an unused root supposed to mean to curse; wormwood (regarded as poisonous, and therefore accursed) -- hemlock, wormwood.
Or lappid {lap-peed'}; from an unused root probably meaning to shine; a flambeau, lamp or flame -- (fire-)brand, (burning) lamp, lightning, torch.
