Feminine plural of (H3940) lappiyd; Lappidoth, the husband of Deborah -- Lappidoth. see HEBREW (H3940) lappiyd
From the prepositional prefix (to or for) and (H6440) paniym; anterior -- before. see HEBREW (H6440) paniym

column7: to twist, turn, grasp with a twisting motion
column9: A primitive root; properly, to bend, i.e. (by implication) to clasp; also (reflexively) to turn around or aside -- take hold, turn aside (self).
From (H3887) luwts; derision -- scornful(-ning). see HEBREW (H3887) luwts
A primitive root; to deride -- scorn.

column7: a N. border town of Naphtali
column9: From an unused root thought to mean to stop up by a barricade; perhaps fortification; Lakkum, a place in Palestine -- Lakum.

column8: accept, bring, buy, carry away, drawn, fetch, get, infold,
column9: A primitive root; to take (in the widest variety of applications) -- accept, bring, buy, carry away, drawn, fetch, get, infold, X many, mingle, place, receive(-ing), reserve, seize, send for, take (away, -ing, up), use, win.

From (H3947) laqach; properly, something received, i.e. (mentally) instruction (whether on the part of the teacher or hearer); also (in an active and sinister sense) inveiglement -- doctrine, learning, fair speech. see HEBREW (H3947) laqach
From (H3947) laqach; learned; Likchi, an Israelite -- Likhi. see HEBREW (H3947) laqach

column7: to pick or gather up, glean
column9: A primitive root; properly, to pick up, i.e. (generally) to gather; specifically, to glean -- gather (up), glean.
From (H3950) laqat; the gleaning -- gleaning. see HEBREW (H3950) laqat
A primitive root; to lick or lap -- lap, lick.

column7: to take the second crop, to take everything
column9: A primitive root; to gather the after crop -- gather.
From (H3953) laqash; the after crop -- latter growth. see HEBREW (H3953) laqash

column7: juice, juicy or dainty bit, a dainty
column9: From an unused root of uncertain meaning; apparently juice, i.e. (figuratively) vigor; also a sweet or fat cake -- fresh, moisture.

column8: babbler, evil speaker, language, talker, tongue, wedge
column9: Or lashon {law-shone'}; also (in plural) feminine lshonah {lesh-o-naw'}; from (H3960) lashan; the tongue (of man or animals), used literally (as the instrument of licking, eating, or speech), and figuratively (speech, an ingot, a fork of flame, a cove of water) -- + babbler,bay, + evil speaker, language, talker, tongue, wedge. see HEBREW (H3960) lashan
From an unused root of uncertain meaning; a room in a building (whether for storage, eating, or lodging) -- chamber, parlour. Compare (H5393) nishkah. see HEBREW (H5393) nishkah

column7: (a precious stone) perhaps amber or jacinth
column9: From an unused root of uncertain meaning; a gem, perhaps the jacinth -- ligure.
The same as (H3958) leshem; Leshem, a place in Palestine: see HEBREW (H3958) leshem
A primitive root; properly, to lick; but used only as a denominative from (H3956) lashown; to wag the tongue, i.e. To calumniate -- accuse, slander. see HEBREW (H3956) lashown
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3956) lashown; speech, i.e. A nation -- language. see HEBREW (H3956) lashown

column7: a place on the boundary of Canaan
column9: From an unused root thought to mean to break through; a boiling spring; Lesha, a place probably East of the Jordan -- Lasha.
From an unused root of uncertain meaning; a measure for things dry -- half homer.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H4100) mah; (as indef.) That -- + what. see HEBREW (H4100) mah
From (H75) 'abac; a granary -- storehouse. see HEBREW (H75) 'abac

column8: diligently, especially, exceedingly, far, fast, good, greatly, louder and louder,
column9: From the same as (H181) 'uwd; properly, vehemence, i.e. (with or without preposition) vehemently; by implication, wholly, speedily, etc. (often with other words as an intensive or superlative; especially when repeated) -- diligently, especially, exceeding(-ly), far, fast, good, great(-ly), X louder and louder, might(-ily, -y), (so) much, quickly, (so) sore, utterly, very (+ much, sore), well. see HEBREW (H181) 'uwd
Or metyah {may-yaw'}; properly, a primitive numeral; a hundred; also as a multiplicative and a fraction -- hundred((-fold), -th), + sixscore.

column7: a tower on the N. wall of Jer
column9: The same as (H3967) me'ah; Meah, a tower in Jerusalem -- Meah. see HEBREW (H3967) me'ah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3967) me'ah -- hundred. see HEBREW (H3967) me'ah
From (H183) 'avah; a desire -- desire. see HEBREW (H183) 'avah
Usually muwm {moom}; as if passive participle from an unused root probably meaning to stain; a blemish (physically or morally) -- blemish, blot, spot.

column8: fault, nothing, ought, somewhat, any nothing
column9: Apparently a form of (H3971) m'uwm; properly, a speck or point, i.e. (by implication) something; with negative, nothing -- fault, + no(-ught), ought, somewhat, any ((no-))thing. see HEBREW (H3971) m'uwm
From (H3988) ma'ac; refuse -- refuse. see HEBREW (H3988) ma'ac

Or maor {maw-ore'}; also (in plural) feminine mpowrah {meh-o-raw'}; or morah {meh-o-raw'}; from (H215) 'owr; properly, a luminous body or luminary, i.e. (abstractly) light (as an element): figuratively, brightness, i.e.cheerfulness; specifically, a chandelier -- bright, light. see HEBREW (H215) 'owr
Feminine passive participle of (H215) 'owr; something lighted, i.e. An aperture; by implication, a crevice or hole (of a serpent) -- den. see HEBREW (H215) 'owr
From (H239) 'azan; (only in the dual) a pair of scales: see HEBREW (H239) 'azan
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3976) mo'zen -- balances. see HEBREW (H3976) mo'zen
From (H398) 'akal; an eatable (includ. Provender, flesh and fruit) -- food, fruit, ((bake-)) meat(-s), victual. see HEBREW (H398) 'akal
From (H398) 'akal; something to eat with,- i.e. A knife -- knife. see HEBREW (H398) 'akal
From (H398) 'akal; something eaten (by fire), i.e. Fuel -- fuel. see HEBREW (H398) 'akal
From (H553) 'amats; strength, i.e. (plural) resources -- force. see HEBREW (H553) 'amats
From (H559) 'amar; something (authoritatively) said, i.e. An edict -- commandment, decree. see HEBREW (H559) 'amar
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H3982) ma'amar -- appointment, word. see HEBREW (H3982) ma'amar
(Aramaic) probably from a root corresponding to (H579) 'anah in the sense of an inclosure by sides; a utensil -- vessel. see HEBREW (H579) 'anah
A primitive root; to refuse -- refuse, X utterly.
From (H3985) ma'en; unwilling -- refuse. see HEBREW (H3985) ma'en
From (H3985) ma'en; refractory -- refuse. see HEBREW (H3985) ma'en

column8: abhor, cast away off, contemn, despise, disdain, become loathsome, refuse,

From (H1129) banah; built up; Mebunnai, an Israelite -- Mebunnai. see HEBREW (H1129) banah

column8: most fenced, fortress, most strong hold
column9: Also (in plural) feminine (Dan. 11:15) mibtsarah {mib-tsaw-raw'}; from (H1219) batsar; a fortification, castle, or fortified city; figuratively, a defender -- (de-, most) fenced, fortress, (most) strong (hold). see HEBREW (H15) 'abeh see HEBREW (H1219) batsar

column9: From (H4026) migdal and (H410) 'el; tower of God; Migdal-El, a place in Palestine -- Migdal-el. see HEBREW (H4026) migdal see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: a sojourning place, dwelling place, a sojourning
column8: dwelling, pilgrimage, where sojourn, be a stranger
column9: Or magur {maw-goor'}; from (H1481) guwr in the sense of lodging; a temporary abode; by extension, a permanent residence -- dwelling, pilgrimage, where sojourn, be a stranger. Compare (H4032) magowr. see HEBREW (H1481) guwr see HEBREW (H4032) magowr

column8: armed, buckler, defense, ruler, scale, shield
column9: Also (in plural) feminine mginnah {meg-in-naw'}; from (H1598) ganan; a shield (i.e. The small one or buckler); figuratively, a protector; also the scaly hide of the crocodile -- X armed, buckler, defence, ruler, + scale, shield. see HEBREW (H1598) ganan

From (H5062) nagaph; a pestilence; by analogy, defeat -- (X be) plague(-d), slaughter, stroke. see HEBREW (H5062) nagaph

column8: armour, clothes, garment, judgment, measure, raiment, stature

(Aramaic) or mindah (Aramaic) {min-daw'}; corresponding to (H4060) middah; tribute in money -- toll, tribute. see HEBREW (H4060) middah
Perhaps from the equivalent of (H1722) dhab; goldmaking, i.e. Exactness -- golden city. see HEBREW (H1722) dhab
From an unused root meaning to stretch; properly, extent, i.e. Measure; by implication, a dress (as measured) -- garment.

From (H1760) dachah; overthrow -- ruin. see HEBREW (H1760) dachah
From (H1765) dachaph; a push, i.e. Ruin -- overthrow. see HEBREW (H1765) dachaph

From (H4100) mah and (H1767) day; what (is) enough, i.e. Sufficiently -- sufficiently. see HEBREW (H4100) mah see HEBREW (H1767) day

column8: how long, oft, what end, good, purpose, thing,
column9: Or mah {mah}; or ma {maw}; or ma {mah}; also meh {meh}; a primitive particle; properly, interrogative what? (including how? Why? When?); but also exclamation, what! (including how!), or indefinitely what (including whatever, and even relatively, that which); often used with prefixes in various adverbial or conjunctive senses -- how (long, oft, (- soever)), (no-)thing, what (end, good, purpose, thing), whereby(-fore, -in, -to, -with), (for) why.

From (H1980) halak; a walk, i.e. A passage or a distance -- journey, walk. see HEBREW (H1980) halak
From (H1984) halal; fame -- praise. see HEBREW (H1984) halal

column8: hasteth, hastily, at once, quickly, soon, speedily, suddenly

From (H2048) hathal; a delusion -- deceit. see HEBREW (H2048) hathal

column4: proper name, of a people and territory
column7: a son of Lot,also his desc. and the territory where they settled

By transp. For (H3996) mabow'; an entrance -- coming. see HEBREW (H3996) mabow'

column9: A primitive root; to melt, i.e. Literally (to soften, flow down, disappear), or figuratively (to fear, faint) -- consume, dissolve, (be) faint(-hearted), melt (away), make soft.
A primitive root; to shake -- measure.
Or rather modao {mo-daw'}; from (H3045) yada'; an acquaintance -- kinswoman. see HEBREW (H3045) yada'
From (H3045) yada'; acquaintance -- kindred. see HEBREW (H3045) yada'

column9: A primitive root; to waver; by implication, to slip, shake, fall -- be carried, cast, be out of course, be fallen in decay, X exceedingly, fall(-ing down), be (re-)moved, be ready, shake, slide, slip.

Feminine of (H4132) mowt; a pole; by implication, an ox-bow; hence, a yoke (either literal or figurative) -- bands, heavy, staves, yoke. see HEBREW (H4132) mowt

column7: to be low or depressed, to grow poor
column9: A primitive root; to become thin, i.e. (figuratively) be impoverished -- be (waxen) poor(-er).

column8: circumcising, selves, cut down in pieces, destroy, must needs

column5: mul or mol or mol or mul

column9: Or mowl (Deuteronomy 1:1) {mole}; or mowtl (Nehemiah 12:38) {mole}; or mul (Numbers 22:5) {mool}; from (H4135) muwl; properly, abrupt, i.e. A precipice; by implication, the front; used only adverbially (with prepositional prefix) opposite -- (over) against, before, (fore-)front, from, (God-)ward, toward, with. see HEBREW (H4135) muwl
From (H3205) yalad; birth; Moladah, a place in Palestine -- Moladah. see HEBREW (H3205) yalad
From (H3205) yalad; nativity (plural birth-place); by implication, lineage, native country; also offspring, family -- begotten, born, issue, kindred, native(-ity). see HEBREW (H3205) yalad

From (H2470) chalah; a disease -- disease. see HEBREW (H2470) chalah

From (H2790) charash; probably a hoe -- share. see HEBREW (H2790) charash

Probably from (H4229) machah; erasure; Machath, the name of two Israelites -- Mahath. see HEBREW (H4229) machah
From (H2846) chathah; properly, a dissolution; concretely, a ruin, or (abstractly) consternation -- destruction, dismaying, ruin, terror. see HEBREW (H2846) chathah
The same as (H4288) mchittah in the sense of removal; a pan for live coals -- censer, firepan, snuffdish. see HEBREW (H4288) mchittah
From (H2864) chathar; a burglary; figuratively, unexpected examination -- breaking up, secret search. see HEBREW (H2864) chathar

(Aramaic) or mtah (Aramaic) {met-aw'}; apparently corresponding to (H4672) matsa' in the intransitive sense of being found present; to arrive, extend or happen -- come, reach. see HEBREW (H4672) matsa'
Apparently a denominative from (H2916) tiyt; a broom (as removing dirt (compare Engl. \"to dust\", i.e. Remove dust)) -- besom. see HEBREW (H2916) tiyt
From (H2873) tabach; slaughter -- slaughter. see HEBREW (H2873) tabach

column7: a staff, rod, shaft, branch, a tribe
column9: Or (feminine) mattah {mat-taw'}; from (H5186) natah; a branch (as extending); figuratively, a tribe; also a rod, whether for chastising (figuratively, correction), ruling (a sceptre), throwing (a lance), or walking (a staff; figuratively, a support of life, e.g. Bread) -- rod, staff, tribe. see HEBREW (H5186) natah

column8: beneath, downward, less, very low, underneath
column9: From (H5786) avar with directive enclitic appended; downward, below or beneath; often adverbially with or without prefixes -- beneath, down(-ward), less, very low, under(-neath). see HEBREW (H5786) avar
From (H5186) natah; a bed (as extended) for sleeping or eating; by analogy, a sofa, litter or bier -- bed((-chamber)), bier. see HEBREW (H5186) natah

column7: that which is perverted, perverted justice
column9: From (H5186) natah; a stretching, i.e. Distortion (figuratively, iniquity) -- perverseness. see HEBREW (H5186) natah
From (H5186) natah; expansion -- stretching out. see HEBREW (H5186) natah
From (H2901) tavah; something spun -- spun. see HEBREW (H2901) tavah
From (H2904) tuwl in the sense of hammering out; an iron bar (as forged) -- bar. see HEBREW (H2904) tuwl

Or matmon {mat-mone'}; or matmun {mat-moon'}; from (H2934) taman; a secret storehouse; hence, a secreted valuable (buried); generally money -- hidden riches, (hid) treasure(-s). see HEBREW (H2934) taman

column7: place or act of planting, a plantation
column9: From (H5193) nata'; something planted, i.e. The place (a garden or vineyard), or the thing (a plant, figuratively or men); by implication, the act, planting -- plant(-ation, -ing). see HEBREW (H5193) nata'
Or (feminine) matiammah {mat-am-maw'}; from (H2938) ta'am; a delicacy -- dainty (meat), savoury meat. see HEBREW (H2938) ta'am
From (H2946) taphach; a wide cloak (for a woman) -- vail, wimple. see HEBREW (H2946) taphach
A primitive root; to rain -- (cause to) rain (upon).
From (H4305) matar; rain -- rain. see HEBREW (H4305) matar

column7: a guard, ward, prison, target, mark
column9: Or mattarah {mat-taw-raw'}; from (H5201) natar; a jail (as a guard-house); also an aim (as being closely watched) -- mark, prison. see HEBREW (H5201) natar
From (H2956) tarad; propulsive; Matred, an Edomitess -- Matred. see HEBREW (H2956) tarad
From (H4305) matar; rainy; Matri, an Israelite -- Matri. see HEBREW (H4305) matar

column8: any man, he, him, O that! What, which, whom would to God
column9: An interrogative pronoun of persons, as (H4100) mah is of things, who? (occasionally, by a peculiar idiom, of things); also (indefinitely) whoever; often used in oblique construction with prefix or suffix -- any (man), X he, X him, + O that! What, which, who(-m, -se, -soever), + would to God. see HEBREW (H4100) mah
From (H4325) mayim and (H1679) dobe'; water of quiet; Medeba, a place in Palestine -- Medeba. see HEBREW (H4325) mayim see HEBREW (H1679) dobe'
From (H3032) yadad in the sense of loving; affectionate; Medad, an Israelite -- Medad. see HEBREW (H3032) yadad

column7: a place in Dan near Joppa
column9: From (H4325) mayim and (H3420) yeraqown with the art. Interposed; water of the yellowness; Me-haj-Jarkon, a place in Palestine -- Me-jarkon. see HEBREW (H4325) mayim see HEBREW (H3420) yeraqown
From (H4325) mayim and (H2091) zahab, water of gold; Me-Zahab, an Edomite -- Mezahab. see HEBREW (H4325) mayim see HEBREW (H2091) zahab
From (H3190) yatab; the best part -- best. see HEBREW (H3190) yatab
A variation for (H4318) Miykah; Mica, the name of two Israelites -- Micha. see HEBREW (H4318) Miykah

column7: Who is like God? an angel, also a number of Isr
column9: From (H4310) miy and (the prefix derivative from) (H3588) kiy and (H410) 'el; who (is) like God?; Mikael, the name of an archangel and of nine Israelites -- Michael. see HEBREW (H4310) miy see HEBREW (H3588) kiy see HEBREW (H410) 'el
An abbrev. Of (H4320) Miykayah; Micah, the name of seven Israelites -- Micah, Micaiah, Michah. see HEBREW (H4320) Miykayah
A contr. For (H4321) Miykayhuw; Mikehu, an Israelite prophet -- Micaiah (2 Chronicles 18:8). see HEBREW (H4321) Miykayhuw

column7: Who is like Yah? the name of several Israelites
column9: From (H4310) miy and (the prefix derivative from) (H3588) kiy and (H3050) Yahh; who (is) like Jah?; Micajah, the name of two Israelites -- Micah, Michaiah. Compare (H4318) Miykah. see HEBREW (H4310) miy see HEBREW (H3588) kiy see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh see HEBREW (H4318) Miykah

column7: Who is like Yah? three Israelites
column9: Or Mikayhuw (Jeremiah 36:11) {me-kaw-yeh-hoo'}; abbrev. For (H4322) Miykayahuw; Mikajah, the name of three Israelites -- Micah, Micaiah, Michaiah. see HEBREW (H4322) Miykayahuw

column7: Who is like Yah? an Israelite, also an Israelite woman
column9: For (H4320) Miykayah; Mikajah, the name of an Israelite and an Israelitess -- Michaiah. see HEBREW (H4320) Miykayah
From (H3201) yakol; properly, a container, i.e. A streamlet -- brook. see HEBREW (H3201) yakol
Apparently the same as (H4323) miykal; revulet; Mikal, Saul's daughter -- Michal. see HEBREW (H4323) miykal
Dual of a primitive noun (but used in a singular sense); water; figuratively, juice; by euphemism, urine, semen -- + piss, wasting, water(-ing, (-course, -flood, -spring)).
A form for (H4509) Minyamiyn; Mijamin, the name of three Israelites -- Miamin, Mijamin. see HEBREW (H4509) Minyamiyn
From an unused root meaning to portion out; a sort, i.e. Species -- kind. Compare (H4480) min. see HEBREW (H4480) min
Properly, feminine passive participle of (H3245) yacad; something founded, i.e. A foundation -- foundation. see HEBREW (H3245) yacad
From (H5526) cakak; a portico (as covered) -- covert. see HEBREW (H5526) cakak
From (H4160) muwts; pressure -- churning, forcing, wringing. see HEBREW (H4160) muwts
From (H4185) muwsh; departure; Mesha, a place in Arabia; also an Israelite -- Mesha. see HEBREW (H4185) muwsh

column7: Who is what God is? three Israelites
column9: From (H4310) miy and (H410) 'el with the abbrev. Insep. Relatively (see (H834) 'aher) interposed; who (is) what God (is)?; Mishael, the name of three Israelites -- Mishael. see HEBREW (H4310) miy see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H834) 'aher

column7: Who is what God is? a companion of Daniel
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H4332) Miysha'el; Mishael, an Israelite -- Mishael. see HEBREW (H4332) Miysha'el

column8: equity, even place, plain, righteously, made straight, uprightness
column9: Or miyshor {mee-shore'}; from (H3474) yashar; a level, i.e. A plain (often used (with the article prefix) as a properly, name of certain districts); figuratively, concord; also straightness, i.e. (figuratively) justice (sometimes adverbially, justly) -- equity, even place, plain, right(-eously), (made) straight, uprightness. see HEBREW (H3474) yashar

column7: a Bab. name given to Mishael
column9: Borrowed from (H4336) Meyshak; Meshak, an Israelite -- Meshak. see HEBREW (H4336) Meyshak
(Aramaic) of foreign origin and doubtful significance; Meshak, the Babylonian name of (H4333) Miysha'el -- Meshak. see HEBREW (H4333) Miysha'el
From (H3467) yasha'; safety; Mesha, an Israelite -- Mesha. see HEBREW (H3467) yasha'
A variation for (H4337) Meysha'; safety; Mesha, a Moabite -- Mesha. see HEBREW (H4337) Meysha'

column8: agreement, aright, that are equal, equity, things that are righteously, things, sweetly
column9: From (H3474) yashar; evenness, i.e. (figuratively) prosperity or concord; also straightness, i.e. (figuratively) rectitude (only in plural with singular sense; often adverbially) -- agreement, aright, that are equal, equity, (things that are) right(-eously, things), sweetly, upright(-ly, -ness). see HEBREW (H3474) yashar
From (H3498) yathar; a cord (of a tent) (compare (H3499) yether) or the string (of a bow) -- cord, string. see HEBREW (H3498) yathar see HEBREW (H3499) yether
Sometimes makcowb {mak-obe'}; also (feminine Isaiah 53:3) makfobah {mak-o-baw'}; from (H3510) ka'ab; anguish or (figuratively) affliction -- grief, pain, sorrow. see HEBREW (H3510) ka'ab
Transitive participle of (H3527) kabar; plenty -- abundance. see HEBREW (H3527) kabar
From the same as (H3522) Kabbown; knoll; Macbena, a place in Palestine settled by him -- Machbenah. see HEBREW (H3522) Kabbown
Patrial from (H4343) Makbena'; a Macbannite or native of Macbena -- Machbanai. see HEBREW (H4343) Makbena'
From (H3527) kabar in the sense of covering (compare (H3531) kbarah); a grate -- grate. see HEBREW (H3527) kabar see HEBREW (H3531) kbarah
From (H3527) kabar in the sense of covering; a cloth (as netted (compare (H4345) makber)) -- thick cloth. see HEBREW (H3527) kabar see HEBREW (H4345) makber

column8: beaten, blow, plague, slaughter, smote, sore, stripe, stroke,
column9: Or (masculine) makkeh {muk-keh'}; (plural only) from (H5221) nakah; a blow (in 2 Chronicles 2:10, of the flail); by implication, a wound; figuratively, carnage, also pestilence -- beaten, blow, plague, slaughter, smote, X sore, stripe, stroke, wound((-ed)). see HEBREW (H5221) nakah

column7: a burnt spot, scar of a burn
column9: From (H3554) kavah; a burn -- that burneth, burning. see HEBREW (H3554) kavah

column7: a fixed or established place, foundation
column9: From (H3559) kuwn; properly, a fixture, i.e. A basis; generally a place, especially as an abode -- foundation, habitation, (dwelling-, settled) place. see HEBREW (H3559) kuwn
Or mkonah {mek-o-naw'}; feminine of (H4349) makown; a pedestal, also a spot -- base. see HEBREW (H4349) makown
Or mkorah {mek-o-raw'}; from the same as (H3564) kuwr in the sense of dipping; origin (as if a mine) -- birth, habitation, nativity. see HEBREW (H3564) kuwr
Probably from (H4134) muwk; pining; Maki, an Israelite -- Machi. see HEBREW (H4134) muwk
From (H4376) makar; salesman; Makir, an Israelite -- Machir. see HEBREW (H4376) makar
Patronymical from (H4353) Makiyr; a Makirite or descend. Of Makir -- of Machir. see HEBREW (H4353) Makiyr
A primitive root; to tumble (in ruins); figuratively, to perish -- be brought low, decay.
Or miklah {mik-law'}; from (H3607) kala'; a pen (for flocks) -- ((sheep-))fold. Compare (H4357) miklah. see HEBREW (H3607) kala' see HEBREW (H4357) miklah
From (H3615) kalah; completion (in plural concrete adverbial, wholly) -- perfect. Compare (H4356) mikla'ah. see HEBREW (H3615) kalah see HEBREW (H4356) mikla'ah
From (H3634) kalal; perfection (i.e. Concrete adverbial, splendidly) -- most gorgeously, all sorts. see HEBREW (H3634) kalal
From (H3634) kalal; perfection (of beauty) -- perfection. see HEBREW (H3634) kalal

column7: a thing made perfect, probably a gorgeous garment
column9: From (H3634) kalal; something perfect, i.e. A splendid garment -- all sorts. see HEBREW (H3634) kalal
From (H398) 'akal; nourishment -- food. see HEBREW (H398) 'akal
From the same as (H3646) kammon in the sense of hiding; treasure (as hidden) -- treasure. see HEBREW (H3646) kammon
(Ezra 2:2 or Mikmash {mik-mawsh'}; or Mikmash (Neh. 11:31) {mik-mash'}; from (H3647) kamac; hidden; Mikmas or Mikmash, a place in Palestine -- Mikmas, Mikmash. see HEBREW (H3647) kamac
Or mikmor {mik-more'}; from (H3648) kamar in the sense of blackening by heat; a (hunter's) net (as dark from concealment) -- net. see HEBREW (H3648) kamar
Or mikmoreth {mik-mo'-reth}; feminine of (H4364) makmar; a (fisher's) net -- drag, net. see HEBREW (H4364) makmar
Apparently from an unused root meaning to hide; concealment; Mikmethath, a place in Palestine -- Michmethath.
From (H4100) mah and (H5068) nadab with a particle interposed; what (is) like (a) liberal (man)?; Maknadbai, an Israelite -- Machnadebai. see HEBREW (H4100) mah see HEBREW (H5068) nadab
The same as (H4350) mkownah; a base; Mekonah, a place in Palestine -- Mekonah. see HEBREW (H4350) mkownah
The same as (H4350) mkownah; a spot -- base. see HEBREW (H4350) mkownah
From (H3647) kamac in the sense of hiding; (only in dual) drawers (from concealing the private parts) -- breeches. see HEBREW (H3647) kamac

column7: computation, proportion to be paid, tax
column9: Probably from an unused root meaning to enumerate; an assessment (as based upon a census) -- tribute.
From (H3680) kacah; a covering, i.e. Weather-boarding -- covering. see HEBREW (H3680) kacah
Feminine of (H4371) mekec; an enumeration; by implication, a valuation -- number, worth. see HEBREW (H4371) mekec

column8: clothing, to cover, that which covers
column9: From (H3680) kacah; a covering, i.e. Garment; specifically, a coverlet (for a bed), an awning (from the sun); also the omentum (as covering the intestines) -- clothing, to cover, that which covereth. see HEBREW (H3680) kacah
From (H3717) kaphal; a fold; Makpelah, a place in Palestine -- Machpelah. see HEBREW (H3717) kaphal
A primitive root; to sell, literally (as merchandise, a daughter in marriage, into slavery), or figuratively (to surrender) -- X at all, sell (away, -er, self).
From (H4376) makar; merchandise; also value -- pay, price, ware. see HEBREW (H4376) makar
From (H5234) nakar; an acquaintance -- acquaintance. see HEBREW (H5234) nakar
From (H3738) karah; a pit (for salt) -- (salt-)pit. see HEBREW (H3738) karah
Probably from the same as (H3564) kuwr in the sense of stabbing; a sword -- habitation. see HEBREW (H3564) kuwr
From (H4376) makar; salesman; Mikri, an Israelite -- Michri. see HEBREW (H4376) makar

column7: a descriptive name for one of David\'s men
column9: Patrial from an unused name (the same as (H4380) mkerah) of a place in Palestine: a Mekerathite, or inhabitant of Mekerah -- Mecherathite. see HEBREW (H4380) mkerah

column7: a stumbling, means or occasion of stumbling, a stumbling block
column8: caused to fall, offence, nothing offered, ruin, stumbling-block
column9: Or mikshol {mik-shole'}; masculine from (H3782) kashal; a stumbling-block, literally or figuratively (obstacle, enticement (specifically an idol), scruple) -- caused to fall, offence, X (no-)thing offered, ruin, stumbling-block. see HEBREW (H3782) kashal
Feminine from (H3782) kashal; a stumbling-block, but only figuratively (fall, enticement (idol)) -- ruin, stumbling-block. see HEBREW (H3782) kashal
From (H3789) kathab; a thing written, the characters, or a document (letter, copy, edict, poem) -- writing. see HEBREW (H3789) kathab

column7: something crushed or pulverized, crushed fragments
column9: From (H3807) kathath; a fracture -- bursting. see HEBREW (H3807) kathath

column7: a technical term in psalm titles
column9: From (H3799) katham; an engraving, i.e. (techn.) A poem -- Michtam. see HEBREW (H3799) katham
From (H3806) kathash; a mortar; by analogy, a socket (of a tooth) -- hollow place, mortar. see HEBREW (H3806) kathash
The same as (H4388) maktesh; dell; the Maktesh, a place in Jerusalem -- Maktesh. see HEBREW (H4388) maktesh

column8: accomplish, confirm, consecrate, be at an end, be expired, be fenced, fill, fulfill,
column9: Or malae (Esth. 7:5) {maw-law'}; a primitive root, to fill or (intransitively) be full of, in a wide application (literally and figuratively) -- accomplish, confirm, + consecrate, be at an end, be expired, be fenced, fill, fulfil, (be, become, X draw, give in, go) full(-ly, -ly set, tale), (over-)flow, fulness, furnish, gather (selves, together), presume, replenish, satisfy, set, space, take a (hand-)full, + have wholly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H4390) male'; to fill -- fill, be full. see HEBREW (H4390) male'

From (H4390) male'; full (literally or figuratively) or filling (literally); also (concretely) fulness; adverbially, fully -- X she that was with child, fill(-ed, -ed with), full(-ly), multitude, as is worth. see HEBREW (H4390) male'

column8: all along, all that is therein, fill, that whereof
column9: Rarely mlowf {mel-o'}; or mlow (Ezekiel 41:8), {mel-o'}; from (H4390) male'; fulness (literally or figuratively) -- X all along, X all that is (there-)in, fill, (X that whereof...was) full, fulness, (hand-)full, multitude. see HEBREW (H4390) male'

From (H4390) male'; a fulfilling (only in plural), i.e. (literally) a setting (of gems), or (technically) consecration (also concretely, a dedicatory sacrifice) -- consecration, be set. see HEBREW (H4390) male'
Feminine of (H4392) male'; something fulfilled, i.e. Abundance (of produce) -- (first of ripe) fruit, fulness. see HEBREW (H4392) male'
Feminine of (H4394) millu'; a filling, i.e. Setting (of gems) -- inclosing, setting. see HEBREW (H4394) millu'
From an unused root meaning to despatch as a deputy; a messenger; specifically, of God, i.e. An angel (also a prophet, priest or teacher) -- ambassador, angel, king, messenger.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H4397) mal'ak; an angel -- angel. see HEBREW (H4397) mal'ak

column8: business, cattle, industrious, occupation, officer, manner of workman,
column9: From the same as (H4397) mal'ak; properly, deputyship, i.e. Ministry; generally, employment (never servile) or work (abstractly or concretely); also property (as the result of labor) -- business, + cattle, + industrious, occupation, (+ -pied), + officer, thing (made), use, (manner of) work((-man), -manship). see HEBREW (H4397) mal'ak
From the same as (H4397) mal'ak; a message -- message. see HEBREW (H4397) mal'ak
From the same as (H4397) mal'ak; ministrative; Malaki, a prophet -- Malachi. see HEBREW (H4397) mal'ak
From (H4390) male'; fulness, i.e. (concretely) a plump socket (of the eye) -- X fitly. see HEBREW (H4390) male'
Or malbush {mal-boosh'}; from (H3847) labash; a garment, or (collectively) clothing -- apparel, raiment, vestment. see HEBREW (H3847) labash
From (H3835) laban (denominative); a brick-kiln -- brickkiln. see HEBREW (H3835) laban

column8: answer, by-word, matter, any thing what to say, to speaking, speak, talking, word
column9: From (H4448) malal (plural masculine as if from milleh {mil-leh'}; a word; collectively, a discourse; figuratively, a topic -- + answer, by-word, matter, any thing (what) to say, to speak(-ing), speak, talking, word. see HEBREW (H4448) malal
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H4405) millah; a word, command, discourse, or subject -- commandment, matter, thing. Word. see HEBREW (H4405) millah

column7: a place near Shechem, also a citadel in Jer
column9: Or mil-loe (2 Kings 12:20) {mil-lo'}; from (H4390) male'; a rampart (as filled in), i.e. The citadel -- Millo. See also (H1037) Beyth Millow'. see HEBREW (H4390) male' see HEBREW (H1037) Beyth Millow'
From (H4414) malach; sea-purslain (from its saltness) -- mallows. see HEBREW (H4414) malach
Or Malluwkiy (Neh. 12:14) {mal-loo-kee'}; from (H4427) malak; remnant; Malluk, the name of five Israelites -- Malluch, Melichu (from the margin). see HEBREW (H4427) malak
Feminine passive participle of (H4427) malak; something ruled, i.e. A realm -- kingsom, king's, X royal. see HEBREW (H4427) malak
From (H3885) luwn; a lodgment, i.e. Caravanserai or encampment -- inn, place where...lodge, lodging (place). see HEBREW (H3885) luwn
Feminine from (H3885) luwn; a hut, a hammock -- cottage, lodge. see HEBREW (H3885) luwn
Apparently from (H4448) malal; I have talked (i.e. Loquacious) -- Mallothi, an Israelite -- Mallothi. see HEBREW (H4448) malal

column8: salt, season, temper together, vanish away
column9: A primitive root; properly, to rub to pieces or pulverize; intransitively, to disappear as dust; also (as denominative from (H4417) melach) to salt whether internally (to season with salt) or externally (to rub with salt) -- X at all, salt, season, temper together, vanish away. see HEBREW (H4417) melach
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H4414) malach; to eat salt, i.e. (generally) subsist -- + have maintenance. see HEBREW (H4414) malach
(Aramaic) from (H4415) mlach; salt -- + maintenance, salt. see HEBREW (H4415) mlach
From (H4414) malach; properly, powder, i.e. (specifically) salt (as easily pulverized and dissolved -- salt((-pit)). see HEBREW (H4414) malach
From (H4414) malach in its original sense; a rag or old garment -- rotten rag. see HEBREW (H4414) malach
From (H4414) malach in its second. Sense; a sailor (as following \"the salt\") -- mariner. see HEBREW (H4414) malach

From (H4414) malach (in its denominative sense); properly, salted (i.e. Land ((H776) 'erets being understood)), i.e. A desert -- barren land(-ness), salt (land). see HEBREW (H4414) malach see HEBREW (H776) 'erets
From (H3898) lacham (in the sense of fighting); a battle (i.e. The engagement); generally, war (i.e. Warfare) -- battle, fight(-ing), war((-rior)). see HEBREW (H3898) lacham

column8: deliver self, escape, lay, leap out, let alone, let go, preserve, save,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be smooth, i.e. (by implication) to escape (as if by slipperiness); causatively, to release or rescue; specifically, to bring forth young, emit sparks -- deliver (self), escape, lay, leap out, let alone, let go, preserve, save, X speedily, X surely.
From (H4422) malat, cement (from its plastic smoothness) -- clay. see HEBREW (H4422) malat
From (H4423) melet and (H3050) Yahh; (whom) Jah has delivered; Melatjah, a Gibeonite -- Melatiah. see HEBREW (H4423) melet see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H4449) mlal (in the sense of cropping (compare (H4135) muwl)); a head of grain (as cut off) -- ear. see HEBREW (H4449) mlal see HEBREW (H4135) muwl
From (H3887) luwts; an aphorism; also a satire -- interpretation, taunting. see HEBREW (H3887) luwts

column7: to be or become king or queen, to reign
column8: consult, indeed, be make, set a, set up king, be make queen, begin to, make to reigning,
column9: A primitive root; to reign; inceptively, to ascend the throne; causatively, to induct into royalty; hence (by implication) to take counsel -- consult, X indeed, be (make, set a, set up) king, be (make) queen, (begin to, make to) reign(-ing), rule, X surely.
From (H4427) malak; a king -- king, royal. see HEBREW (H4427) malak
The same as (H4428) melek; king; Melek, the name of two Israelites -- Melech, Hammelech (by including the article). see HEBREW (H4428) melek

column7: habitation, a place in Judah, also a man of Judah, also an enemy of Isr
column9: The same as (H4583) ma'own; a residence; Maon, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine -- Maon, Maonites. Compare (H1010) Beyth Ba'al m'own, (H4586) m'uwniy. see HEBREW (H4583) ma'own see HEBREW (H1010) Beyth Ba'al m'own see HEBREW (H4586) m'uwniy
Or msonah {meh-o-naw'}; feminine of (H4583) ma'own, and meaning the same -- den, habitation, (dwelling) place, refuge. see HEBREW (H4583) ma'own

column7: a people Southeast of the Dead Sea
column9: Or Msiyniy {meh-ee-nee'}; probably patrial from (H4584) Ma'own; a Meunite, or inhabitant of Maon (only in plural) -- Mehunim(-s), Meunim. see HEBREW (H4584) Ma'own
Plural of (H4585) m'ownah; habitative; Meonothai, an Israelite -- Meonothai. see HEBREW (H4585) m'ownah
From (H5774) uwph in the sense of covering with shade (compare (H4155) muw'aph); darkness -- dimness. see HEBREW (H5774) uwph see HEBREW (H4155) muw'aph
From (H5783) uwr; nakedness, i.e. (in plural) the pudenda -- nakedness. see HEBREW (H5783) uwr

Or Ma.azyahuw {mah-az-yaw'-hoo}; probably from (H5756) uwz (in the sense of protection) and (H3050) Yahh; rescue of Jah; Maazjah, the name of two Israelites -- Maaziah. see HEBREW (H5756) uwz see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: to be or become small, diminished, or few
column8: suffer to decrease, diminish, borrow, give
column9: A primitive root; properly, to pare off, i.e. Lessen; intransitively, to be (or causatively, to make) small or few (or figuratively, ineffective) -- suffer to decrease, diminish, (be, X borrow a, give, make) few (in number, -ness), gather least (little), be (seem) little, (X give the) less, be minished, bring to nothing.

column8: almost some, very fewer lightly, little while, very small matter, thing, some, soon, very
column9: Or miat {meh-awt'}; from (H4591) ma'at; a little or few (often adverbial or compar.) -- almost (some, very) few(-er, -est), lightly, little (while), (very) small (matter, thing), some, soon, X very. see HEBREW (H4591) ma'at
Passive adjective of (H4591) ma'at; thinned (as to the edge), i.e. Sharp -- wrapped up. see HEBREW (H4591) ma'at
From (H5844) atah; a vestment -- garment. see HEBREW (H5844) atah
From (H5848) ataph; a cloak -- mantle. see HEBREW (H5848) ataph
From (H5753) avah; a pile of rubbish (as contorted), i.e. A ruin (compare (H5856) iy) -- heap. see HEBREW (H5753) avah see HEBREW (H5856) iy
Probably from (H4578) me'ah; sympathetic; Maai, an Israelite -- Maai. see HEBREW (H4578) me'ah
From (H4603) ma'al in the sense of covering; a robe (i.e. Upper and outer garment) -- cloke, coat, mantle, robe. see HEBREW (H4603) ma'al

Or ma ynow (Psa. 114:8) {mah-yen-o'}; or (feminine) ma yanah {mah-yaw-naw'}; from (H5869) ayin (as a denominative in the sense of a spring); a fountain (also collectively), figuratively, a source (of satisfaction) -- fountain, spring, well. see HEBREW (H5869) ayin
A primitive root; to press, i.e. To pierce, emasculate, handle -- bruised, stuck, be pressed.

column4: proper name, masculine, feminine and of a people; feminine; feminine; of a people
column7: an Israelite name, also a non-Israelite name, also a region in Syria
column9: Or Mamakath (Josh. 13:13) {mah-ak-awth'}; from (H4600) ma'ak; depression; Maakah (or Maakath), the name of a place in Syria, also of a Mesopotamian, of three Israelites, and of four Israelitesses and one Syrian woman -- Maachah, Maachathites. See also (H1038) Beyth Ma'akah. see HEBREW (H4600) ma'ak see HEBREW (H1038) Beyth Ma'akah
Patrial from (H4601) Ma'akah; a Maakathite, or inhabitant of Maakah -- Maachathite. see HEBREW (H4601) Ma'akah
A primitive root; properly, to cover up; used only figuratively, to act covertly, i.e. Treacherously -- transgress, (commit, do a) trespass(-ing).

column8: falsehood, grievously, sore, transgression, trespass, very
column9: From (H4603) ma'al; treachery, i.e. Sin -- falsehood, grievously, sore, transgression, trespass, X very. see HEBREW (H4603) ma'al

column8: above, exceedingly, forward, on very high, over, upon very
column9: From (H5927) alah; properly, the upper part, used only adverbially with prefix upward, above, overhead, from the top, etc. -- above, exceeding(-ly), forward, on (X very) high, over, up(-on, -ward), very. see HEBREW (H5927) alah
(Aramaic) from (H5954) alal; (only in plural as singular) the setting (of the sun) -- going down. see HEBREW (H5954) alal
From (H5927) alah; a raising (of the hands) -- lifting up. see HEBREW (H5927) alah

column8: ascent, cliff, going up, hill, mounting up,
column9: From (H5927) alah; an elevation, i.e. (concretely) acclivity or platform; abstractly (the relation or state) a rise or (figuratively) priority -- ascent, before, chiefest, cliff, that goeth up, going up, hill, mounting up, stairs. see HEBREW (H5927) alah

column8: things that come up, high degree, deal, go up, stair, step, story
column9: Feminine of (H4608) ma'aleh; elevation, i.e. The act (literally, a journey to a higher place, figuratively, a thought arising), or (concretely) the condition (literally, a step or grade-mark, figuratively, a superiority of station); specifically a climactic progression (in certain Psalms) -- things that come up, (high) degree, deal, go up, stair, step, story. see HEBREW (H4608) ma'aleh

column7: ascent of scorpions, a place on the S. border of Isr
column8: Maaleh-accrabim, the ascent going up of Akrabbim
column9: From (H4608) ma'aleh and (the plural of) (H6137) aqrab; Steep of Scorpions, a place in the Desert -- Maaleh- accrabim, the ascent (going up) of Akrabbim. see HEBREW (H4608) ma'aleh see HEBREW (H6137) aqrab
From (H5953) alal; an act (good or bad) -- doing, endeavour, invention, work. see HEBREW (H5953) alal
From (H5975) amad; (figuratively) a position -- attendance, office, place, state. see HEBREW (H5975) amad
From (H5975) amad; literally, a foothold -- standing. see HEBREW (H5975) amad
From (H6006) amac; burdensomeness -- burdensome. see HEBREW (H6006) amac
From (H6009) amaq; a deep -- deep, depth. see HEBREW (H6009) amaq

column8: because of, to the end intent that, for to,
column9: From (H6030) anah; properly, heed, i.e. Purpose; used only adverbially, on account of (as a motive or an aim), teleologically, in order that -- because of, to the end (intent) that, for (to,... 'S sake), + lest, that, to. see HEBREW (H6030) anah
From (H6030) anah; a reply (favorable or contradictory) -- answer, X himself. see HEBREW (H6030) anah
From (H6031) anah, in the sense of depression or tilling; a furrow -- + acre, furrow. see HEBREW (H6031) anah
From (H6095) atsah; closure; Maats, an Israelite -- Maaz. see HEBREW (H6095) atsah
From (H6087) atsab; anguish -- sorrow. see HEBREW (H6087) atsab
From an usused root meaning to hew; an axe -- ax, tongs.
From (H6113) atsar; objectively, a hindrance -- restraint. see HEBREW (H6113) atsar
From (H6113) atsar; subjectively, control -- rule. see HEBREW (H6113) atsar
From an unused root meaning to repress; a parapet -- battlement.
From (H6140) aqash; a crook (in a road) -- crooked thing. see HEBREW (H6140) aqash
From (H6168) arah; a nude place, i.e. (literally) the pudenda, or (figuratively) a vacant space -- nakedness, proportion. see HEBREW (H6168) arah
From (H6148) arab, in the sense of trading; traffic; by implication, mercantile goods -- market, merchandise. see HEBREW (H6148) arab
Or (feminine) maearabah {mah-ar-aw-baw'}; from (H6150) arab, in the sense of shading; the west (as a region of the evening sun) -- west. see HEBREW (H6150) arab
From (H6168) arah; a nude place, i.e. A common -- meadows. see HEBREW (H6168) arah
Feminine of (H4629) ma'areh; an open spot -- army (from the margin). see HEBREW (H4629) ma'areh
From (H5783) uwr; a cavern (as dark) -- cave, den, hole. see HEBREW (H5783) uwr
The same as (H4631) m'arah; cave; Mearah, a place in Palestine -- Mearah. see HEBREW (H4631) m'arah
From (H6186) arak; an arrangement, i.e. (figuratively) mental disposition -- preparation. see HEBREW (H6186) arak

column8: army, fight, be set in order, ordered place, rank, row
column9: Feminine of (H4633) ma'arak; an arrangement; concretely, a pile; specifically a military array -- army, fight, be set in order, ordered place, rank, row. see HEBREW (H4633) ma'arak
From (H6186) arak; an arrangement, i.e. (concretely) a pile (of loaves) -- row, shewbread. see HEBREW (H6186) arak
From (H6191) aram, in the sense of stripping; bare -- naked. see HEBREW (H6191) aram
From (H6206) arats; violence -- terror. see HEBREW (H6206) arats
A form of (H4630) ma'arah; waste; Maarath, a place in Palestine -- Maarath. see HEBREW (H4630) ma'arah

From (H6213) asah; an action (good or bad); generally, a transaction; abstractly, activity; by implication, a product (specifically, a poem) or (generally) property -- act, art, + bakemeat, business, deed, do(-ing), labor, thing made, ware of making, occupation, thing offered, operation, possession, X well, ((handy-, needle-, net-))work(ing, - manship), wrought. see HEBREW (H6213) asah
From (H6213) asah; operative; Maasai, an Israelite -- Maasiai. see HEBREW (H6213) asah

column7: work of Yah, the name of a number of Isr
column9: Or Maaseyahuw {mah-as-ay-yaw'-hoo}; from (H4639) ma'aseh and (H3050) Yahh; work of Jah; Maasejah, the name of sixteen Israelites -- Maaseiah. see HEBREW (H4639) ma'aseh see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H6231) ashaq; oppression -- oppression, X oppressor. see HEBREW (H6231) ashaq
Or maasar {mah-as-ar'}; and (in plural) feminine maasrah {mah-as-raw'}; from (H6240) asar; a tenth; especially a tithe -- tenth (part), tithe(-ing). see HEBREW (H6240) asar
Of Egyptian origin: Moph, the capital of Lower Egypt -- Memphis. Compare (H5297) Noph. see HEBREW (H5297) Noph
From (H6293) paga'; an object of attack -- mark. see HEBREW (H6293) paga'
From (H5301) naphach; a breathing out (of life), i.e. Expiring -- giving up. see HEBREW (H5301) naphach
From (H5301) naphach; the bellows (i.e. Blower) of a forge -- bellows. see HEBREW (H5301) naphach

Or Mphibosheth {mef-ee-bo'-sheth}; probably from (H6284) pa'ah and (H1322) bosheth; dispeller of shame (i.e. Of Baal); Mephibosheth, the name of two Israelites -- Mephibosheth. see HEBREW (H6284) pa'ah see HEBREW (H1322) bosheth
A plural apparently from (H5130) nuwph; wavings; Muppim, an Israelite -- Muppim. Compare (H8206) Shuppiym. see HEBREW (H5130) nuwph see HEBREW (H8206) Shuppiym
From (H6327) puwts; a breaker, i.e. Mallet -- maul. see HEBREW (H6327) puwts
From (H5307) naphal; a falling off, i.e. Chaff; also something pendulous, i.e. A flap -- flake, refuse. see HEBREW (H5307) naphal
From (H6381) pala'; a miracle -- wondrous work. see HEBREW (H6381) pala'
From (H6385) palag; a classification -- division. see HEBREW (H6385) palag
Or mappelah {map-pay-law'}; from (H5307) naphal; something fallen, i.e. A ruin -- ruin(-ous). see HEBREW (H5307) naphal
From (H6403) palat; an escape -- escape. see HEBREW (H6403) palat
From (H6426) palats; a terror, i.e. An idol -- idol. see HEBREW (H6426) palats
From an unused root meaning to balance; a poising -- balancing.
From (H5307) naphal; fall, i.e. Decadence; concretely, a ruin; specifically a carcase -- carcase, fall, ruin. see HEBREW (H5307) naphal
Or (feminine) miph.alah {mif-aw-law'}; from (H6466) pa'al; a performance -- work. see HEBREW (H6466) pa'al
From (H5310) naphats; a smiting to pieces -- slaughter. see HEBREW (H5310) naphats
From (H5310) naphats; a smiter, i.e. A war club -- battle ax. see HEBREW (H5310) naphats
From (H6485) paqad; an appointment, i.e. Mandate; concretely, a designated spot; specifically, a census -- appointed place, commandment, number. see HEBREW (H6485) paqad

column7: appointed place, a gate in Jer
column9: The same as (H4662) miphqad; assignment; Miphkad, the name of a gate in Jerusalem -- Miphkad. see HEBREW (H4662) miphqad
From (H6555) parats; a break (in the shore), i.e. A haven -- breach. see HEBREW (H6555) parats
From (H6561) paraq; properly, a fracture, i.e. Joint (vertebrae) of the neck -- neck. see HEBREW (H6561) paraq
From (H6566) paras; an expansion -- that which...spreadest forth, spreading. see HEBREW (H6566) paras
From (H6585) pasa'; a stride, i.e. (by euphemism) the crotch -- buttocks. see HEBREW (H6585) pasa'
From (H6605) pathach; an opener, i.e. A key -- key. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
From (H6605) pathach; an aperture, i.e. (figuratively) utterance -- opening. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
From the same as (H6620) pethen; a stretcher, i.e. A sill -- threshold. see HEBREW (H6620) pethen
Or mowts (Zephaniah 2:2) {motes}; from (H4160) muwts; chaff (as pressed out, i.e. Winnowed or (rather) threshed loose) -- chaff. see HEBREW (H4160) muwts

column8: be able, befall, being, catch, certainly, cause to come on, to, to hand,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to come forth to, i.e. Appear or exist; transitively, to attain, i.e. Find or acquire; figuratively, to occur, meet or be present -- + be able, befall, being, catch, X certainly, (cause to) come (on, to, to hand), deliver, be enough (cause to) find(-ing, occasion, out), get (hold upon), X have (here), be here, hit, be left, light (up-)on, meet (with), X occasion serve, (be) present, ready, speed, suffice, take hold on.
From (H5324) natsab; a fixed spot; figuratively, an office, a military post -- garrison, station, place where...stood. see HEBREW (H5324) natsab
From (H5324) natsab; a station, i.e. Military post -- mount. see HEBREW (H5324) natsab
Or mitstsabah {mits-tsaw-baw'}; feminine of (H4673) matstsab; a military guard -- army, garrison. see HEBREW (H4673) matstsab
Feminine (causatively) participle of (H5324) natsab; something stationed, i.e. A column or (memorial stone); by analogy, an idol -- garrison, (standing) image, pillar. see HEBREW (H5324) natsab

column7: descriptive title for one of David\'s men
column9: Apparently from (H4672) matsa' and (H3050) Yahh; found of Jah; Metsobajah, a place in Palestine -- Mesobaite. see HEBREW (H4672) matsa' see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H5324) natsab; something stationary, i.e. A monumental stone; also the stock of a tree -- pillar, substance. see HEBREW (H5324) natsab
Or mtsad {mets-awd'}; or (feminine) mtsadah {mets-aw-daw'}; from (H6679) tsuwd; a fastness (as a covert of ambush) -- castle, fort, (strong) hold, munition. see HEBREW (H6679) tsuwd
A primitive root; to suck out; by implication, to drain, to squeeze out -- suck, wring (out).
Active participle feminine of (H4680) matsah; drained; Motsah, a place in Palestine -- Mozah. see HEBREW (H4680) matsah

From (H4711) matsats in the sense of greedily devouring for sweetness; properly, sweetness; concretely, sweet (i.e. Not soured or bittered with yeast); specifically, an unfermented cake or loaf, or (elliptically) the festival of Passover (because no leaven was then used) -- unleaved (bread, cake), without leaven. see HEBREW (H4711) matsats
From (H5327) natsah; a quarrel -- contention, debate, strife. see HEBREW (H5327) natsah
From (H6670) tsahal; a whinnying (through impatience for battle or lust) -- neighing. see HEBREW (H6670) tsahal

column4: noun masculine; noun masculine; noun feminine; noun feminine
column9: Or (feminine) mtsowdah {mets-o-daw'}; or mtsodah {mets-o-daw'}; from (H6679) tsuwd; a net (for capturing animals or fishes) -- also (by interchange for (H4679) mtsad) a fastness or (beseiging) tower -- bulwark, hold, munition, net, snare. see HEBREW (H6679) tsuwd see HEBREW (H4679) mtsad

column8: castle, defense, fortress, strong hold, be hunted, net, snare, strong place
column9: Or (feminine) mtsuwdah {mets-oo-daw'}; or mtsudah {mets-oo-daw'}; for (H4685) matsowd; a net, or (abstractly) capture; also a fastness; --castle, defense, fort(-ress), (strong) hold, be hunted, net, snare, strong place. see HEBREW (H4685) matsowd

column8: which was commanded, law, ordinance, precept
column9: From (H6680) tsavah; a command, whether human or divine (collectively, the Law) -- (which was) commanded(-ment), law, ordinance, precept. see HEBREW (H6680) tsavah
Or mtsolah {mets-o-law'}; also mtsuwlah {mets-oo-law'}; or mtsulah {mets-oo-law'}; from the same as (H6683) tsuwlah; a deep place (of water or mud) -- bottom, deep, depth. see HEBREW (H6683) tsuwlah
From (H6693) tsuwq; a narrow place, i.e. (abstractly and figuratively) confinement or disability -- anguish, distress, straitness. see HEBREW (H6693) tsuwq
Or matsuq {maw-tsook'}; from (H6693) tsuwq; something narrow, i.e. A column or hilltop -- pillar, situate. see HEBREW (H6693) tsuwq
Or mtsuqah {mets-oo-kaw'}; feminine of (H4690) matsuwq; narrowness, i.e. (figuratively) trouble -- anguish, distress. see HEBREW (H4690) matsuwq

column8: besieged, bulwark, defense, fenced, fortress, siege, strong hold, tower
column9: Or matsuwr {maw-tsoor'}; from (H6696) tsuwr; something hemming in, i.e. (objectively) a mound (of besiegers), (abstractly) a siege, (figuratively) distress; or (subjectively) a fastness -- besieged, bulwark, defence, fenced, fortress, siege, strong (hold), tower. see HEBREW (H6696) tsuwr

column7: a country Southwest of the Red Sea
column9: The same as (H4692) matsowr in the sense of a limit; Egypt (as the border of Palestine) -- besieged places, defense, fortified. see HEBREW (H4692) matsowr

Or mtsurah {mets-oo-raw'}; feminine of (H4692) matsowr; a hemming in, i.e. (objectively) a mound (of siege), or (subjectively) a rampart (of protection), (abstractly) fortification -- fenced (city, fort, munition, strong hold. see HEBREW (H4692) matsowr
From (H5327) natsah; a quarrel -- that contended. see HEBREW (H5327) natsah
From an unused root meaning to be clear, i.e. Conspicuous; the forehead (as open and prominent) -- brow, forehead, + impudent.
From the same as (H4696) metsach; a shin-piece of armor (as prominent), only plural -- greaves. see HEBREW (H4696) metsach
From (H6750) tsalal; a tinkler, i.e. A bell -- bell. see HEBREW (H6750) tsalal
From (H6751) tsalal; shade -- bottom. see HEBREW (H6751) tsalal
From (H6750) tsalal; (only dual) double tinklers, i.e. Cymbals -- cymbals. see HEBREW (H6750) tsalal
From (H6801) tsanaph; a tiara, i.e. Official turban (of a king or high priest) -- diadem, mitre. see HEBREW (H6801) tsanaph
From (H3331) yatsa'; a couch -- bed. see HEBREW (H3331) yatsa'
From (H6805) tsa'ad; a step; figuratively, companionship -- going, step. see HEBREW (H6805) tsa'ad
Feminine of (H4705) mits'ar; properly, littleness; concretely, diminutive -- little. see HEBREW (H4705) mits'ar
From (H6819) tsa'ar; petty (in size or number); adverbially, a short (time) -- little one (while), small. see HEBREW (H6819) tsa'ar
The same as (H4705) mits'ar; Mitsar, a peak of Lebanon -- Mizar. see HEBREW (H4705) mits'ar
From (H6822) tsaphah; an observatory, especially for military purposes -- watch tower. see HEBREW (H6822) tsaphah

column7: the name of several places in Isr
column9: The same as (H4707) mitspeh; Mitspeh, the name of five places in Palestine -- Mizpeh, watch tower. Compare (H4709) Mitspah. see HEBREW (H4707) mitspeh see HEBREW (H4709) Mitspah

column7: the name of several places in Isr
column9: Feminine of (H4708) Mitspeh; Mitspah, the name of two places in Palestine -- Mitspah. (This seems rather to be only an orthographic variation of (H4708) Mitspeh when \"in pause\".) see HEBREW (H4708) Mitspeh see HEBREW (H4708) Mitspeh
From (H6845) tsaphan; a secret (place or thing, perhaps, treasure) -- hidden thing. see HEBREW (H6845) tsaphan
A primitive root; to suck -- milk.
From (H6896) qebah; something tight, i.e. (figuratively) trouble -- distress, pain, strait. see HEBREW (H6896) qebah
From (H4714) Mitsrayim; a Mitsrite, or inhabitant of Mitsrajim -- Egyptian, of Egypt. see HEBREW (H4714) Mitsrayim

column4: proper name, of a territory and people, feminine; masculine; masculine plural
column7: a son of Ham, also his desc. and their country in N.W. Africa
column9: Dual of (H4693) matsowr; Mitsrajim, i.e. Upper and Lower Egypt -- Egypt, Egyptians, Mizraim. see HEBREW (H4693) matsowr
From (H6884) tsaraph; a crucible -- fining pot. see HEBREW (H6884) tsaraph
From (H4743) maqaq; properly, a melting, i.e. Putridity -- rottenness, stink. see HEBREW (H4743) maqaq
From (H5344) naqab; properly, a perforatrix, i.e. A hammer (as piercing) -- hammer. see HEBREW (H5344) naqab
From (H5344) naqab; properly, a perforator, i.e. A hammer (as piercing); also (intransitively) a perforation, i.e. A quarry -- hammer, hole. see HEBREW (H5344) naqab
From the same as (H5348) naqod in the denominative sense of herding (compare (H5349) noqed); fold; Makkedah, a place in Palestine -- Makkedah. see HEBREW (H5348) naqod see HEBREW (H5349) noqed

column8: chapel, hallowed part, holy place, sanctuary
column9: Or miqqdash (Exod. 15:17) {mik-ked-awsh'}; from (H6942) qadash; a consecrated thing or place, especially, a palace, sanctuary (whether of Jehovah or of idols) or asylum -- chapel, hallowed part, holy place, sanctuary. see HEBREW (H6942) qadash
Or (feminine) maqhelah {mak-hay-law'}; from (H6950) qahal; an assembly -- congregation. see HEBREW (H6950) qahal

column7: place of assembly, a place in the desert
column9: Plural of (H4721) maqhel (feminine); assemblies; Makheloth, a place in the Desert -- Makheloth. see HEBREW (H4721) maqhel

column8: abiding, gathering together, hope, linen yarn, plenty of water, pool
column9: Or miqveh (1 Kings 10:28) {mik-vay'}; or miqvet (2 Chron. 1:16) {mik-vay'}; from (H6960) qavah; something waited for, i.e. Confidence (objective or subjective); also a collection, i.e. (of water) a pond, or (of men and horses) a caravan or drove -- abiding, gathering together, hope, linen yarn, plenty (of water), pool. see HEBREW (H6960) qavah
Feminine of (H4723) miqveh; a collection, i.e. (of water) a reservoir -- ditch. see HEBREW (H4723) miqveh

column8: country, home, open, place, room, space, whithersoever
column9: Or maqom {maw-kome'}; also (feminine) mqowmah {mek-o-mah'}; or mqomah {mek-o-mah'}; from (H6965) quwm; properly, a standing, i.e. A spot; but used widely of a locality (general or specific); also (figuratively) of a condition (of body or mind) -- country, X home, X open, place, room, space, X whither(-soever). see HEBREW (H6965) quwm

Or maqor {maw-kore'}; from (H6979) quwr; properly, something dug, i.e. A (general) source (of water, even when naturally flowing; also of tears, blood (by euphemism, of the female pudenda); figuratively, of happiness, wisdom, progeny) -- fountain, issue, spring, well(-spring). see HEBREW (H6979) quwr
From (H3947) laqach; reception -- taking. see HEBREW (H3947) laqach
From (H3947) laqach; something received, i.e. Merchandise (purchased) -- ware. see HEBREW (H3947) laqach
From (H6999) qatar; something to fume (incense) on i.e. A hearth place -- to burn...upon. see HEBREW (H6999) qatar
Feminine of (H4729) miqtar; something to fume (incense) in, i.e. A coal-pan -- censer. see HEBREW (H4729) miqtar
Or (feminine) maqqlah {mak-kel-aw'}; from an unused root meaning apparently to germinate; a shoot, i.e. Stick (with leaves on, or for walking, striking, guiding, divining) -- rod, ((hand-))staff.

column7: a Benjamite, also an officer of David
column9: (or perhaps mik-kel-ohth') plural of (feminine) (H4731) maqqel; rods; Mikloth, a place in the Desert -- Mikloth. see HEBREW (H4731) maqqel
From (H7038) qalat in the sense of taking in; an asylum (as a receptacle) -- refuge. see HEBREW (H7038) qalat
From (H7049) qala'; a sculpture (probably in bas-relief) -- carved (figure), carving, graving. see HEBREW (H7049) qala'

column8: cattle, flock, herd, possession, purchase, substance
column9: From (H7069) qanah; something bought, i.e. Property, but only livestock; abstractly, acquisition -- cattle, flock, herd, possession, purchase, substance. see HEBREW (H7069) qanah

column8: he that is bought, possession, piece, purchase
column9: Feminine of (H4735) miqneh; properly, a buying, i.e. Acquisition; concretely, a piece of property (land or living); also the sum paid -- (he that is) bought, possession, piece, purchase. see HEBREW (H4735) miqneh

column7: possession of Yah, a Levitical musician
column9: From (H4735) miqneh and (H3050) Yahh; possession of Jah; Miknejah, an Israelite -- Mikneiah. see HEBREW (H4735) miqneh see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H7080) qacam; an augury -- divination. see HEBREW (H7080) qacam
From (H7112) qatsats; end; Makats, a place in Palestine -- Makaz. see HEBREW (H7112) qatsats
Or maqtsoa {mak-tso-ah}; or (feminine) maqtso-ah {mak-tso-aw'}; from (H7106) qatsa' in the denominative sense of bending; an angle or recess -- corner, turning. see HEBREW (H7106) qatsa'
From (H7106) qatsa'; a scraper, i.e. A carving chisel -- plane. see HEBREW (H7106) qatsa'
From (H7106) qatsa' in the denominative sense of bending; an angle -- corner. see HEBREW (H7106) qatsa'

column7: to decay, rot, fester, pine away
column8: consume away, be corrupt, dissolve, pine away
column9: A primitive root; to melt; figuratively, to flow, dwindle, vanish -- consume away, be corrupt, dissolve, pine away.
From (H7121) qara'; something called out, i.e. A public meeting (the act, the persons, or the place); also a rehearsal -- assembly, calling, convocation, reading. see HEBREW (H7121) qara'

column8: something befallen, befall, chance, event, happen
column9: From (H7136) qarah; something met with, i.e. An accident or fortune -- something befallen, befalleth, chance, event, hap(-peneth). see HEBREW (H7136) qarah
From (H7136) qarah; properly, something meeting, i.e. A frame (of timbers) -- building. see HEBREW (H7136) qarah
From the same as (H7119) qar; a cooling off -- X summer. see HEBREW (H7119) qar
From (H7185) qashah in the sense of knotting up round and hard; something turned (rounded), i.e. A curl (of tresses) -- X well (set) hair. see HEBREW (H7185) qashah

column8: beaten out of one piece, work, upright, whole piece
column9: Feminine of (H4748) miqsheh; rounded work, i.e. Moulded by hammering (repousse) -- beaten (out of one piece, work), upright, whole piece. see HEBREW (H4748) miqsheh
Denominative from (H7180) qishshu'; literally, a cucumbered field, i.e. A cucumber patch -- garden of cucumbers. see HEBREW (H7180) qishshu'

column8: angry, bitterly chafed, discontented, great, heavy
column9: Or (feminine) marah {maw-raw'}; from (H4843) marar; bitter (literally or figuratively); also (as noun) bitterness, or (adverbially) bitterly -- + angry, bitter(-ly, -ness), chafed, discontented, X great, heavy. see HEBREW (H4843) marar
From (H4843) marar in its original sense of distillation; a drop -- drop. see HEBREW (H4843) marar
Or mowr {more}; from (H4843) marar; myrrh (as distilling in drops, and also as bitter) -- myrrh. see HEBREW (H4843) marar
A primitive root; to rebel; hence (through the idea of maltreating) to whip, i.e. Lash (self with wings, as the ostrich in running) -- be filthy, lift up self.
For (H4751) mar feminine; bitter; Mara, a symbolic name of Naomi -- Mara. see HEBREW (H4751) mar
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H4754) mara' in the sense of domineering; a master -- lord, Lord. see HEBREW (H4754) mara'
Of foreign derivation; Merodak-Baladan, a Babylonian king -- Merodach-baladan. Compare (H4781) Mrodak. see HEBREW (H4781) Mrodak

column8: apparently, appearance, beautifully, countenance, fair, favored, form, goodly,
column9: From (H7200) ra'ah; a view (the act of seeing); also an appearance (the thing seen), whether (real) a shape (especially if handsome, comeliness; often plural the looks), or (mental) a vision -- X apparently, appearance(-reth), X as soon as beautiful(-ly), countenance, fair, favoured, form, goodly, to look (up) on (to), look(-eth), pattern, to see, seem, sight, visage, vision. see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah
Feminine of (H4758) mar'eh; a vision; also (causatively) a mirror -- looking glass, vision. see HEBREW (H4758) mar'eh
Apparently feminine passive causative participle of (H7200) ra'ah; something conspicuous, i.e. The craw of a bird (from its prominence) -- crop. see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah
Denominative from (H7218) ro'sh; properly, headship, i.e. (plural for collective) dominion -- principality. see HEBREW (H7218) ro'sh

column7: a place in Judah, also two Israelites
column9: Or Mareshah {mar-ay-shaw'}; formed like (H4761) mar'ashah; summit; Mareshah, the name of two Israelites and of a place in Palestine -- Mareshah. see HEBREW (H4761) mar'ashah

column7: a place at the head, head place
column9: Formed like (H4761) mar'ashah; properly, a headpiece, i.e. (plural for adverbial) at (or as) the head-rest (or pillow) -- bolster, head, pillow. Compare (H4772) marglah. see HEBREW (H4761) mar'ashah see HEBREW (H4772) marglah
From (H7231) rabab; increase; Merab, a daughter of Saul -- Merab. see HEBREW (H7231) rabab
From (H7234) rabad; a coverlet -- covering of tapestry. see HEBREW (H7234) rabad
From (H7235) rabah; properly, increasing; as noun, greatness, or (adverbially) greatly -- great, increase. see HEBREW (H7235) rabah
From (H7235) rabah; abundance, i.e. A great quantity -- much. see HEBREW (H7235) rabah
From (H7235) rabah; a multitude; also offspring; specifically interest (on capital) -- greatest part, greatness, increase, multitude. see HEBREW (H7235) rabah

column8: couching place, place to lie down
column9: From (H7257) rabats; a reclining place, i.e. Fold (for flocks) -- couching place, place to lie down. see HEBREW (H7257) rabats
From an unused root meaning to tie up; a stall (for cattle) -- X fat(-ted), stall.
From (H7280) raga'; a resting place -- rest. see HEBREW (H7280) raga'

Denominative from (H7272) regel; (plural for collective) a footpiece, i.e. (adverbially) at the foot, or (direct.) The foot itself -- feet. Compare (H4763) mra'ashah. see HEBREW (H7272) regel see HEBREW (H4763) mra'ashah
From (H7275) ragam; a stone-heap -- sling. see HEBREW (H7275) ragam
From (H7280) raga'; rest -- refreshing. see HEBREW (H7280) raga'
A primitive root; to rebel -- rebel(-lious).
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H4775) marad; rebellion -- rebellion. see HEBREW (H4775) marad
From (H4775) marad; rebellion -- rebellion. see HEBREW (H4775) marad
The same as (H4777) mered; Mered, an Israelite -- Mered. see HEBREW (H4777) mered
(Aramaic) from the same as (H4776) mrad; rebellious -- rebellious. see HEBREW (H4776) mrad
From (H4775) marad; rebelliousness -- X rebellious. see HEBREW (H4775) marad

column7: a god worshiped by the Bab
column9: Of foreign derivation; Merodak, a Babylonian idol -- Merodach. Compare (H4757) Mro'dak Bal'adan. see HEBREW (H4757) Mro'dak Bal'adan

column7: a companion of Zerubbabel, also a cousin of Esther
column9: Of foreign derivation; Mordecai, an Israelite -- Mordecai.
From (H7291) radaph; persecuted -- persecuted. see HEBREW (H7291) radaph

column8: bitter, change, be disobedient, disobey, grievously, provocation, provoking
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, make) bitter (or unpleasant); (figuratively) to rebel (or resist; causatively, to provoke) -- bitter, change, be disobedient, disobey, grievously, provocation, provoke(-ing), (be) rebel (against, -lious).

column7: a bitter spring in the Sinai peninsula
column9: The same as (H4751) mar feminine; bitter; Marah, a place in the Desert -- Marah. see HEBREW (H4751) mar
From (H4843) marar; bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) trouble -- grief. see HEBREW (H4843) marar
A form of (H4786) morah; trouble -- bitterness. see HEBREW (H4786) morah
From (H7300) ruwd in the sense of maltreatment; an outcast; (abstractly) destitution -- cast out, misery. see HEBREW (H7300) ruwd
Of uncertain derivation; Meroz, a place in Palestine -- Meroz.
From (H4799) marach; bruised, i.e. Emasculated -- broken. see HEBREW (H4799) marach

column8: far above, dignity, haughty, height, most, on high one, place, loftily,
column9: From (H7311) ruwm; altitude, i.e. Concretely (an elevated place), abstractly (elevation, figuratively (elation), or adverbially (aloft) -- (far) above, dignity, haughty, height, (most, on) high (one, place), loftily, upward. see HEBREW (H7311) ruwm
Formed like (H4791) marowm; height; Merom, a lake in Palestine -- Merom. see HEBREW (H4791) marowm
From (H7323) ruwts; a run (the trial of speed) -- race. see HEBREW (H7323) ruwts

Or mrutsah {mer-oo-tsaw'}; feminine of (H4793) merowts; a race (the act), whether the manner or the progress -- course, running. Compare (H4835) mrutsah. see HEBREW (H4793) merowts see HEBREW (H4835) mrutsah
From (H4838) maraq; properly, rubbed; but used abstractly, a rubbing (with perfumery) -- purification. see HEBREW (H4838) maraq
Plural of (H4751) mar feminine; bitter springs; Maroth, a place in Palestine -- Maroth. see HEBREW (H4751) mar
From an unused root meaning to scream; a cry, i.e. (of job), a revel -- banquet.
Formed like (H4797) mirzach; a cry, i.e. (of grief) a lamentation -- mourning. see HEBREW (H4797) mirzach
A primitive root; properly, to soften by rubbing or pressure; hence (medicinally) to apply as an emollient -- lay for a plaister.
From (H7337) rachab; enlargement, either literally (an open space, usually in a good sense), or figuratively (liberty) -- breadth, large place (room). see HEBREW (H7337) rachab

From (H7368) rachaq; remoteness, i.e. (concretely) a distant place; often (adverbially) from afar -- (a-, dwell in, very) far (country, off). See also (H1023) Beyth ham-Merchaq. see HEBREW (H7368) rachaq see HEBREW (H1023) Beyth ham-Merchaq
From (H7370) rachash; a stew-pan -- fryingpan. see HEBREW (H7370) rachash

column7: to make smooth, bare or bald, to scour, polish
column8: bright, furbish, have his hair be fallen off, peeled, pluck off hair
column9: A primitive root; to polish; by implication, to make bald (the head), to gall (the shoulder); also, to sharpen -- bright, furbish, (have his) hair (be) fallen off, peeled, pluck off (hair).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H4803) marat; to pull off -- be plucked. see HEBREW (H4803) marat
From (H4784) marah; bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) rebellion; concretely, bitter, or rebellious -- bitter, (most) rebel(-lion, -lious). see HEBREW (H4784) marah

From (H4754) mara' in the sense of grossness, through the idea of domineering (compare (H4756) mare'); stall-fed; often (as noun) a beeve -- fat (fed) beast (cattle, -ling). see HEBREW (H4754) mara' see HEBREW (H4756) mare'

column7: perhaps "Baal is advocate", a son of Jonathan
column9: From (H7378) riyb and (H1168) Ba'al; quarreller of Baal, Merib-Baal, an epithet of Gideon -- Merib-baal. Compare (H4810) Mriy Ba'al. see HEBREW (H7378) riyb see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H4810) Mriy Ba'al
From (H7378) riyb; quarrel -- provocation, strife. see HEBREW (H7378) riyb

column7: place of strife, two places in the desert
column9: The same as (H4808) mriybah; Meribah, the name of two places in the Desert -- Meribah. see HEBREW (H4808) mriybah

From (H4805) mriy and (H1168) Ba'al; rebellion of (i.e. Against) Baal; Meri-Baal, an epithet of Gideon -- Meri-baal. Compare (H4807) Mriyb Ba'al. see HEBREW (H4805) mriy see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al see HEBREW (H4807) Mriyb Ba'al
From (H4784) marah; rebellion; Merajah, an Israelite -- Meraiah. Compare (H3236) Yimrah. see HEBREW (H4784) marah see HEBREW (H3236) Yimrah

column7: descendant of Aaron, also a priestly family
column9: Plural of (H4811) Mrayah; rebellious; Merajoth, the name of two Israelites -- Meraioth. see HEBREW (H4811) Mrayah

column7: a sister of Aaron, also a man of Judah
column9: From (H4805) mriy; rebelliously; Mirjam, the name of two Israelitesses -- Miriam. see HEBREW (H4805) mriy
From (H4843) marar; bitterness, i.e. (figuratively) grief -- bitterness. see HEBREW (H4843) marar
From (H4843) marar; bitter, i.e. Poisonous -- bitter. see HEBREW (H4843) marar
Perhaps from (H7401) rakak; softness, i.e. (figuratively) fear -- faintness. see HEBREW (H7401) rakak
From (H7392) rakab; a chariot; also a seat (in a vehicle) -- chariot, covering, saddle. see HEBREW (H7392) rakab
Feminine of (H4817) merkab; a chariot -- chariot. See also (H1024) Beyth ham-Marka-bowth. see HEBREW (H4817) merkab see HEBREW (H1024) Beyth ham-Marka-bowth
From (H7402) rakal; a mart -- merchandise. see HEBREW (H7402) rakal

column8: craft, deceitful false, feigned, guile, treachery
column9: From (H7411) ramah in the sense of deceiving; fraud -- craft, deceit(-ful, -fully), false, feigned, guile, subtilly, treachery. see HEBREW (H7411) ramah
The same as (H4820) mirmah; Mirmah, an Israelite -- Mirma. see HEBREW (H4820) mirmah

column7: two Israelites priests, also an Israelite
column9: Plural from (H7311) ruwm; heights; Meremoth, the name of two Israelites -- Meremoth. see HEBREW (H7311) ruwm

column8: tread down, to be trodden down under foot
column9: From (H7429) ramac; abasement (the act or the thing) -- tread (down)-ing, (to be) trodden (down) under foot. see HEBREW (H7429) ramac
Patrial from an unused noun; a Meronothite, or inhabitant of some (otherwise unknown) Meronoth. -- Meronothite.
Of foreign derivation; Meres, a Persian -- Meres.
Of foreign derivation; Marsena, a Persian -- Marsena.
From (H7489) ra'a'; used as (abstract) noun, wickedness -- do mischief. see HEBREW (H7489) ra'a'
From (H7462) ra'ah in the sense of companionship; a friend -- companion, friend. see HEBREW (H7462) ra'ah
From (H7462) ra'ah in the sense of feeding; pasture (the place or the act); also the haunt of wild animals -- feeding place, pasture. see HEBREW (H7462) ra'ah
From (H7462) ra'ah in the sense of feeding; pasturage; concretely, a flock -- flock, pasture. see HEBREW (H7462) ra'ah

column7: a place on the border of Zebulun
column9: From (H7477) ra'al; perhaps, earthquake; Maralah, a place in Palestine -- Maralah. see HEBREW (H7477) ra'al

column8: incurable, healing, remedy, sound, wholesome, yielding
column9: From (H7495) rapha'; properly, curative, i.e. Literally (concretely) a medicine, or (abstractly) a cure; figuratively (concretely) deliverance, or (abstractly) placidity -- ((in-))cure(-able), healing(-lth), remedy, sound, wholesome, yielding. see HEBREW (H7495) rapha'
From (H7515) raphas; muddled water -- that which...have fouled. see HEBREW (H7515) raphas
A primitive root; properly, to press, i.e. (figuratively) to be pungent or vehement; to irritate -- embolden, be forcible, grievous, sore.
From (H7533) ratsats; oppression -- violence. See also (H4794) mruwtsah. see HEBREW (H7533) ratsats see HEBREW (H4794) mruwtsah
From (H7527) ratsa'; an awl -- aul. see HEBREW (H7527) ratsa'
From (H7528) ratsaph; a pavement -- pavement. see HEBREW (H7528) ratsaph
A primitive root; to polish; by implication, to sharpen; also to rinse -- bright, furbish, scour.
From (H4838) maraq; soup (as if a rinsing) -- broth. See also (H6564) paraq. see HEBREW (H4838) maraq see HEBREW (H6564) paraq
From (H7543) raqach; a spicy herb -- X sweet. see HEBREW (H7543) raqach
Feminine of (H4840) merqach; abstractly, a seasoning (with spicery); concretely, an unguent-kettle (for preparing spiced oil) -- pot of ointment, X well. see HEBREW (H4840) merqach

column8: prepared by the apothecaries\' art, compound, ointment
column9: From (H7543) raqach; an aromatic unguent; also an unguent-pot -- prepared by the apothecaries' art, compound, ointment. see HEBREW (H7543) raqach

column8: be in, deal, have, make bitterly be moved with choler, have sorely, it grieved,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to trickle (see (H4752) mar); but used only as a denominative from (H4751) mar; to be (causatively, make) bitter (literally or figuratively) -- (be, be in, deal, have, make) bitter(-ly, - ness), be moved with choler, (be, have sorely, it) grieved(-eth), provoke, vex. see HEBREW (H4752) mar see HEBREW (H4751) mar
Or mrowr {mer-ore'}; from (H4843) marar; a bitter herb -- bitter(-ness). see HEBREW (H4843) marar
From (H4843) marar; bile (from its bitterness) -- gall. see HEBREW (H4843) marar
Or mrowrah {mer-o-raw'}; from (H4843) marar; properly, bitterness; concretely, a bitter thing; specifically bile; also venom (of a serpent) -- bitter (thing), gall. see HEBREW (H4843) marar
From (H4843) marar; bitter; Merari, an Israelite -- Merari. See also (H4848) Mrariy. see HEBREW (H4843) marar see HEBREW (H4848) Mrariy
From (H4847) Mrariy; a Merarite (collectively), or decendants of Merari -- Merarites. see HEBREW (H4847) Mrariy
From (H7561) rasha'; a female wicked doer -- wicked woman. see HEBREW (H7561) rasha'

column7: perhaps "double rebellion", another name for Bab
column9: Dual of (H4751) mar feminine; double bitterness; Merathajim, an epithet of Babylon -- Merathaim. see HEBREW (H4751) mar
Of foreign derivation; Mash, a son of Aram, and the people descended from him -- Mash.

column7: one extremity of the territory of the Joktanites
column9: Of foreign derivation; Mesha, a place in Arabia -- Mesha.

column7: a load, burden, lifting, bearing, tribute
column8: burden, carry away, prophecy, they set, song, tribute
column9: From (H5375) nasa'; a burden; specifically, tribute, or (abstractly) porterage; figuratively, an utterance, chiefly a doom, especially singing; mental, desire -- burden, carry away, prophecy, X they set, song, tribute. see HEBREW (H5375) nasa'

column4: proper name, of a people and territory
column7: a son of Ishmael, also the realm of King Lemuel
column9: The same as (H4853) massa'; burden; Massa, a son of Ishmael -- Massa. see HEBREW (H4853) massa'
From (H5383) nashah; a loan; by implication, interest on a debt -- exaction, usury. see HEBREW (H5383) nashah
From (H5375) nasa'; partiality (as a lifting up) -- respect. see HEBREW (H5375) nasa'
From (H7579) sha'ab; a trough for cattle to drink from -- place of drawing water. see HEBREW (H7579) sha'ab
From (H5375) nasa'; a conflagration (from the rising of smoke) -- burden. see HEBREW (H5375) nasa'
Feminine of (H4855) mashsha'; a loan -- X any(- thing), debt. see HEBREW (H4855) mashsha'
From (H5377) nasha'; dissimulation -- deceit. see HEBREW (H5377) nasha'
From (H7592) sha'al; request; Mishal, a place in Palestine -- Mishal, Misheal. Compare (H4913) Mashal. see HEBREW (H7592) sha'al see HEBREW (H4913) Mashal
From (H7592) sha'al; a request -- desire, petition. see HEBREW (H7592) sha'al
From (H7604) sha'ar in the original sense of swelling; a kneading-trough (in which the dough rises) -- kneading trough, store. see HEBREW (H7604) sha'ar

column8: burden, collection, sign of fire, great flame, gift, lifting up, mess, oblation,
column9: From (H5375) nasa'; properly, (abstractly) a raising (as of the hands in prayer), or rising (of flame); figuratively, an utterance; concretely, a beacon (as raised); a present (as taken), mess, or tribute; figuratively, a reproach (as a burden) -- burden, collection, sign of fire, (great) flame, gift, lifting up, mess, oblation, reward. see HEBREW (H5375) nasa'
From (H7660) shabats; a brocade; by analogy, a (reticulated) setting of a gem -- ouch, wrought. see HEBREW (H7660) shabats
From (H7665) shabar; the orifice of the womb (from which the fetus breaks forth) -- birth, breaking forth. see HEBREW (H7665) shabar
From (H7665) shabar; a breaker (of the sea) -- billow, wave. see HEBREW (H7665) shabar
From (H7673) shabath; cessation, i.e. Destruction -- sabbath. see HEBREW (H7673) shabath

column4: noun masculine; proper name, of a location
column9: From (H7682) sagab; properly, a cliff (or other lofty or inaccessible place); abstractly, altitude; figuratively, a refuge -- defence, high fort (tower), refuge, Misgab, a place in Moab -- Misgab. see HEBREW (H7682) sagab
From (H7686) shagah; an error -- oversight. see HEBREW (H7686) shagah
A primitive root; to pull out (literally or figuratively) -- draw(out).

column7: a great Israelite leader, prophet and lawgiver
column9: From (H4871) mashah; drawing out (of the water), i.e. Rescued; Mosheh, the Israelite lawgiver -- Moses. see HEBREW (H4871) mashah

column7: a great Israelite leader, prophet and lawgiver
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H4872) Mosheh -- Moses. see HEBREW (H4872) Mosheh
From (H5383) nashah; a debt -- + creditor. see HEBREW (H5383) nashah
Or mshoah {mesh-o-aw'}; from the same as (H7722) show'; (a) ruin, abstractly (the act) or concretely (the wreck) -- desolation, waste. see HEBREW (H7722) show'
Or mashshu ah {mash-shoo-aw'}; for (H4875) mshow'ah; ruin -- desolation, destruction. see HEBREW (H4875) mshow'ah
From (H7725) shuwb; returned; Meshobab, an Israelite -- Meshobab. see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb
Or mshubah {mesh-oo-baw'}; from (H7725) shuwb; apostasy -- backsliding, turning away. see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb
From an unused root meaning to stray; mistake -- error.
Or mishshowt {mish-shote'}; from (H7751) shuwt; an oar -- oar. see HEBREW (H7751) shuwt
Or msukah {mes-oo-kaw'}; from (H7753) suwk; a hedge -- hedge. see HEBREW (H7753) suwk
From an unused root meaning to plunder; spoilation -- spoil.
From an unused root meaning to rasp; a saw -- saw.
From an unused root meaning apparently to divide; a measure (for liquids) -- measure.
From (H7797) suws; delight, concretely (the cause or object) or abstractly (the feeling) -- joy, mirth, rejoice. see HEBREW (H7797) suws
A primitive root; to rub with oil, i.e. To anoint; by implication, to consecrate; also to paint -- anoint, paint.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H4886) mashach; oil -- oil. see HEBREW (H4886) mashach
Or moshchah {mosh-khaw'}; from (H4886) mashach; unction (the act); by implication, a consecratory gift -- (to be) anointed(-ing), ointment. see HEBREW (H4886) mashach

column8: corruption, to destroying, destruction, trap, utterly
