column9: A primitive root; properly, to swell out or up; used only as denominative from (H6119) aqeb, to seize by the heel; figuratively, to circumvent (as if tripping up the heels); also to restrain (as if holding by the heel) -- take by the heel, stay, supplant, X utterly. see HEBREW (H6119) aqeb

column7: consequence, as a consequence of, because
column8: because, by, end, for, if, reward
column9: From (H6117) aqab in the sense of (H6119) aqeb; a heel, i.e. (figuratively) the last of anything (used adverbially, for ever); also result, i.e. Compensation; and so (adverb with preposition or relatively) on account of -- X because, by, end, for, if, reward. see HEBREW (H6117) aqab see HEBREW (H6119) aqeb

column8: heel, horsehoof, last, lier in wait
column9: Or (feminine) hiqqbah {ik-keb-aw'}; from (H6117) aqab; a heel (as protuberant); hence, a track; figuratively, the rear (of an army) -- heel, (horse-)hoof, last, lier in wait (by mistake for (H6120) aqeb), (foot-)step. see HEBREW (H6117) aqab see HEBREW (H6120) aqeb
From (H6117) aqab in its denominative sense; a lier in wait -- heel (by mistake for (H6119) aqeb). see HEBREW (H6117) aqab see HEBREW (H6119) aqeb

From (H6117) aqab; in the original sense, a knoll (as swelling up); in the denominative sense (transitive) fraudulent or (intransitive) tracked -- crooked, deceitful, polluted. see HEBREW (H6117) aqab
Feminine of an unused form from (H6117) aqab meaning a trick; trickery -- subtilty. see HEBREW (H6117) aqab
A primitive root; to tie with thongs -- bind.
From (H6123) aqad; striped (with bands) -- ring straked. see HEBREW (H6123) aqad
From (H5781) uwq; constraint -- oppression. see HEBREW (H5781) uwq
From (H6117) aqab; insidious; Akkub, the name of five Israelites -- Akkub. see HEBREW (H6117) aqab
A primitive root; to wrest -- wrong.
From (H6127) aqal; winding -- by(-way), crooked way. see HEBREW (H6127) aqal
From (H6127) aqal; tortuous -- crooked. see HEBREW (H6127) aqal
From an unused root meaning to twist; tortuous; Akan, an Idummaean -- Akan. Compare (H3292) Ya'aqan. see HEBREW (H3292) Ya'aqan

column8: dig down, pluck up, root up
column9: A primitive root; to pluck up (especially by the roots); specifically, to hamstring; figuratively, to exterminate -- dig down, hough, pluck up, root up.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6131) aqar -- pluck up by the roots. see HEBREW (H6131) aqar
From (H6131) aqar. Figuratively, a transplanted person, i.e. Naturalized citizen -- stock. see HEBREW (H6131) aqar
The same as (H6133) eqer; Eker, an Israelite -- Eker. see HEBREW (H6133) eqer
From (H6131) aqar; sterile (as if extirpated in the generative organs) -- (X male or female) barren (woman). see HEBREW (H6131) aqar
(Aramaic) from (H6132) aqar; a stock -- stump. see HEBREW (H6132) aqar
Of uncertain derivation; a scorpion; figuratively, a scourge or knotted whip -- scorpion.
From (H6131) aqar; eradication; Ekron, a place in Palestine -- Ekron. see HEBREW (H6131) aqar
Or meqroniy {ek-ro-nee'; patrial from (H6138) Eqrown; an Ekronite or inhabitant of Ekron -- Ekronite. see HEBREW (H6138) Eqrown

column8: make crooked, prove, that is perverse
column9: A primitive root; to knot or distort; figuratively, to pervert (act or declare perverse) -- make crooked, (prove, that is) perverse(-rt).
From (H6140) aqash; distorted; hence, false -- crooked, froward, perverse. see HEBREW (H6140) aqash
The same as (H6141) iqqesh; perverse; Ikkesh, an Israelite -- Ikkesh. see HEBREW (H6141) iqqesh
From (H6141) iqqesh; perversity -- X froward. see HEBREW (H6141) iqqesh
The same as (H5892) iyr; a city; Ar, a place in Moab -- Ar. see HEBREW (H5892) iyr
From (H5782) uwr; a foe (as watchful for mischief) -- enemy. see HEBREW (H5782) uwr
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6145) ar -- enemy. see HEBREW (H6145) ar

column8: watchful; Er, the name of two Israelites
column9: From (H5782) uwr; watchful; Er, the name of two Israelites -- Er. see HEBREW (H5782) uwr

column7: to take on pledge, give in pledge, exchange
column8: engage, intermeddle with, mingle self, mortgage, occupy, give pledges,
column9: A primitive root; to braid, i.e. Intermix; technically, to traffic (as if by barter); also or give to be security (as a kind of exchange) -- engage, (inter-)meddle (with), mingle (self), mortgage, occupy, give pledges, be(-come, put in) surety, undertake.

column8: be pleasant, take pleasure in, be sweet
column9: A primitive root (identical with (H6148) arab through the idea of close association); to be agreeable -- be pleasant(-ing), take pleasure in, be sweet. see HEBREW (H6148) arab
A primitive root (identical with (H6148) arab through the idea of covering with a texture); to grow dusky at sundown -- be darkened, (toward) evening. see HEBREW (H6148) arab
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6148) arab; to commingle -- mingle (self), mix. see HEBREW (H6148) arab

column7: steppe-dwellers, a country East of Isr
column9: Or marab {ar-ab'}; from (H6150) arab in the figurative sense of sterility; Arab (i.e. Arabia), a country East of Palestine -- Arabia. see HEBREW (H6150) arab
From (H6150) arab; dusk -- + day, even(-ing, tide), night. see HEBREW (H6150) arab

column8: Arabia, mingled people, mixed multitude, woof
column9: Or mereb (1 Kings 10:15), (with the article prefix), {eh'-reb}; from (H6148) arab; the web (or transverse threads of cloth); also a mixture, (or mongrel race) -- Arabia, mingled people, mixed (multitude), woof. see HEBREW (H6148) arab

column7: (a kind of tree) perhaps poplar, also a wadi in Moab
column9: From (H6148) arab; a willow (from the use of osiers as wattles) -- willow. see HEBREW (H6148) arab
From (H6149) areb; pleasant -- sweet. see HEBREW (H6149) areb
From (H6148) arab; a mosquito (from its swarming) -- divers sorts of flies, swarm. see HEBREW (H6148) arab
Or mowreb {o-rabe'}; from (H6150) arab; a raven (from its dusky hue) -- raven. see HEBREW (H6150) arab
Or mowreb {o-rabe'}; the same as (H6158) oreb; Oreb, the name of a Midianite and of the cliff near the Jordan -- Oreb. see HEBREW (H6158) oreb

column7: a steppe or desert plain, also a desert valley running S. from the Sea of Galilee
column9: From (H6150) arab (in the sense of sterility); a desert; especially (with the article prefix) the (generally) sterile valley of the Jordan and its continuation to the Red Sea -- Arabah, champaign, desert, evening, heaven, plain, wilderness. See also (H1026) Beyth ha-'Arabah. see HEBREW (H6150) arab see HEBREW (H1026) Beyth ha-'Arabah

Feminine passive participle of (H6048) Anammelek in the sense of a bargain or exchange; something given as security, i.e. (literally) a token (of safety) or (metaphorically) a bondsman -- pledge, surety. see HEBREW (H6048) Anammelek
From (H6148) arab (in the sense of exchange); a pawn (given as security) -- pledge. see HEBREW (H6148) arab
Or marbiy {ar-bee'}; patrial from (H6152)  Arab; an Arabian or inhabitant of Arab (i.e. Arabia) -- Arabian. see HEBREW (H6152)  Arab
Patrial from (H1026) Beyth ha-'Arabah; an Arbathite or inhabitant of (Beth-)Arabah -- Arbahite. see HEBREW (H1026) Beyth ha-'Arabah
A primitive root; to long for -- cry, pant.

column4: verb; proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine
column7: a Canaanite city in the Negev
column9: From an unused root meaning to sequester itself; fugitive; Arad, the name of a place near Palestine, also of a Canaanite and an Israelite -- Arad.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6171) arowd; an onager -- wild ass. see HEBREW (H6171) arowd

column8: leave destitute, discover, empty, make naked, pour out, rase, spread self, uncover
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, make) bare; hence, to empty, pour out, demolish -- leave destitute, discover, empty, make naked, pour (out), rase, spread self, uncover.
Feminine from (H6168) arah; a naked (i.e. Level) plot -- paper reed. see HEBREW (H6168) arah
Or iarugah {ar-oo-gaw'}; feminine passive participle of (H6165) arag; something piled up (as if (figuratively) raised by mental aspiration), i.e. A paterre -- bed, furrow. see HEBREW (H6165) arag
From the same as (H6166) Arad; an onager (from his lonesome habits) -- wild ass. see HEBREW (H6166) Arad
From (H6168) arah; nudity, literally (especially the pudenda) or figuratively (disgrace, blemish) -- nakedness, shame, unclean(-ness). see HEBREW (H6168) arah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6172) ervah; nakedness, i.e. (figuratively) impoverishment -- dishonor. see HEBREW (H6172) ervah
Or marom {aw-rome'}; from (H6191) aram (in its original sense); nude, either partially or totally -- naked. see HEBREW (H6191) aram
Passive participle of (H6191) aram; cunning (usually in a bad sense) -- crafty, prudent, subtil. see HEBREW (H6191) aram

column7: (probably a tree or bush) perhaps juniper
column9: Or sarear {ar-awr'}; from (H6209) arar reduplicated; a juniper (from its nudity of situation) -- health. see HEBREW (H6209) arar
Or 'Aro'er {ar-o-ayr'}; or 'Ar'owr {ar-ore'}; the same as (H6176) arow'er; nudity of situation; Aroer, the name of three places in or near Palestine -- Aroer. see HEBREW (H6176) arow'er
Passive participle of (H6206) arats; feared, i.e. (concretely) a horrible place or chasm -- cliffs. see HEBREW (H6206) arats
From (H5782) uwr; watchful; Eri, an Israelite -- Eri. see HEBREW (H5782) uwr
Patronymically of (H6179) Eriy; a Erite (collectively) or descendants of Eri -- Erites. see HEBREW (H6179) Eriy
For (H6172) ervah; nudity -- bare, naked, X quite. see HEBREW (H6172) ervah
From an unused root meaning to comminute; meal -- dough.
From (H6201) araph; the sky (as dropping at the horizon) -- heaven. see HEBREW (H6201) araph

column8: mighty, oppressor, in great power, strong, terrible, violent
column9: From (H6206) arats; fearful, i.e. Powerful or tyrannical -- mighty, oppressor, in great power, strong, terrible, violent. see HEBREW (H6206) arats
From (H6209) arar; bare, i.e. Destitute (of children) -- childless. see HEBREW (H6209) arar

column7: to arrange or set in order
column8: set the battle, array, compare, direct, equal, esteem, estimate, expert in war,
column9: A primitive root; to set in a row, i.e. Arrange, put in order (in a very wide variety of applications) -- put (set) (the battle, self) in array, compare, direct, equal, esteem, estimate, expert (in war), furnish, handle, join (battle), ordain, (lay, put, reckon up, set) (in) order, prepare, tax, value.

column8: equal, estimation, things that are set in order, price, proportion, set at, suit, taxation,
column9: From (H6186) arak; a pile, equipment, estimate -- equal, estimation, (things that are set in) order, price, proportion, X set at, suit, taxation, X valuest. see HEBREW (H6186) arak

column8: count uncircumcised, foreskin to be uncovered
column9: A primitive root; properly, to strip; but used as denominative from (H6189) arel; to expose or remove the prepuce, whether literal (to go naked) or figurative (to refrain from using) -- count uncircumcised, foreskin to be uncovered. see HEBREW (H6189) arel

Rom (H6188) arel; properly, exposed, i.e. Projecting loose (as to the prepuce); used only technically, uncircumcised (i.e. Still having the prepuce uncurtailed) -- uncircumcised (person). see HEBREW (H6188) arel
Feminine of (H6189) arel; the prepuce -- foreskin, + uncircumcised. see HEBREW (H6189) arel

column8: very, beware, take crafty counsel, be prudent, deal subtilly
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be (or make) bare; but used only in the derivative sense (through the idea perhaps of smoothness) to be cunning (usually in a bad sense) -- X very, beware, take crafty (counsel), be prudent, deal subtilly.
A primitive root; to pile up -- gather together.
From (H6191) aram; a stratagem -- craftiness. see HEBREW (H6191) aram
(Jer. 50:26) or (feminine) aremah {ar-ay-maw'}; from (H6192) aram; a heap; specifically, a sheaf -- heap (of corn), sheaf. see HEBREW (H6192) aram
Feminine of (H6193) orem; trickery; or (in a good sense) discretion -- guile, prudence, subtilty, wilily, wisdom. see HEBREW (H6193) orem
Probably from (H6191) aram; the plane tree (from its smooth and shed bark) -- chestnut tree. see HEBREW (H6191) aram
Probably from (H5782) uwr; watchful; Eran, an Israelite -- Eran. see HEBREW (H5782) uwr
Patronymically from (H6197) Eran; an Eranite or descendant (collectively) of Eran -- Eranites. see HEBREW (H6197) Eran
From (H6209) arar; naked, i.e. (figuratively) poor -- destitute. See also (H6176) arow'er. see HEBREW (H6209) arar see HEBREW (H6176) arow'er
Patronymically from (H6177) Arow'er; an Aroerite or inhabitant of Aroer -- Aroerite. see HEBREW (H6177) Arow'er
A primitive root; to droop; hence, to drip -- drop (down).

column8: that is beheaded, break down, break cut off, strike off neck
column9: A primitive root (identical with (H6201) araph through the idea of sloping); properly, to bend downward; but used only as a denominative from (H6203) oreph, to break the neck; hence (figuratively) to destroy -- that is beheaded, break down, break (cut off, strike off) neck. see HEBREW (H6201) araph see HEBREW (H6203) oreph
From (H6202) araph; the nape or back of the neck (as declining); hence, the back generally (whether literal or figurative) -- back ((stiff-)neck((-ed). see HEBREW (H6202) araph
Feminine of (H6203) oreph; mane; Orpah, a Moabites -- Orpah. see HEBREW (H6203) oreph
Probably from (H6201) araph; gloom (as of a lowering sky) -- (gross, thick) dark (cloud, -ness). see HEBREW (H6201) araph

column8: be affrighted afraid, dread, feared, terrified, break, dread, fear, oppress,
column9: A primitive root; to awe or (intransitive) to dread; hence, to harass -- be affrighted (afraid, dread, feared, terrified), break, dread, fear, oppress, prevail, shake terribly.
A primitive root; to gnaw, i.e. (figuratively) eat (by hyberbole); also (participle) a pain -- fleeing, sinew.

column7: descendant of Canaan, inhab. of the city of Arka
column9: Patrial from an unused name meaning a tush; an Arkite or inhabitant of Erek -- Arkite.

column8: make bare, break, raise up perhaps by clerical error for raze, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to bare; figuratively, to demolish -- make bare, break, raise up (perhaps by clerical error for raze), X utterly.
From an unused root meaning perhaps to arch; a couch (properly, with a canopy) -- bed(-stead), couch.
From (H6244) ashesh; a moth -- moth. See also (H5906) Ayish. see HEBREW (H6244) ashesh see HEBREW (H5906) Ayish
From an unused root meaning to glisten (or be green); grass (or any tender shoot) -- grass, herb.

column8: accomplish, advance, appoint, apt, be at, become, bear, bestow,
column9: A primitive root; to do or make, in the broadest sense and widest application (as follows) -- accomplish, advance, appoint, apt, be at, become, bear, bestow, bring forth, bruise, be busy, X certainly, have the charge of, commit, deal (with), deck, + displease, do, (ready) dress(-ed), (put in) execute(-ion), exercise, fashion, + feast, (fight-)ing man, + finish, fit, fly, follow, fulfill, furnish, gather, get, go about, govern, grant, great, + hinder, hold ((a feast)), X indeed, + be industrious, + journey, keep, labour, maintain, make, be meet, observe, be occupied, offer, + officer, pare, bring (come) to pass, perform, pracise, prepare, procure, provide, put, requite, X sacrifice, serve, set, shew, X sin, spend, X surely, take, X thoroughly, trim, X very, + vex, be (warr-)ior, work(-man), yield, use.
From (H6213) asah and (H410) 'el; God has made; Asahel, the name of four Israelites -- Asahel. see HEBREW (H6213) asah see HEBREW (H410) 'el

Apparently a form of the passive participle of (H6213) asah in the original sense of handling; rough (i.e. Sensibly felt); Esav, a son of Isaac, including his posterity -- Esau. see HEBREW (H6213) asah
From (H6231) ashaq; oppressive (as noun, a tyrant) -- oppressor. see HEBREW (H6231) ashaq
Or mashuq {aw-shook'}; passive participle of (H6231) ashaq; used in plural masculine as abstractly, tyranny -- oppressed(-ion). (Doubtful.) see HEBREW (H6231) ashaq
Or masor {aw-sore'}; from (H6235) eser; ten; by abbrev. Ten strings, and so a decachord -- (instrument of) ten (strings, -th). see HEBREW (H6235) eser
From (H6245) ashath; shining, i.e. Polished -- bright. see HEBREW (H6245) ashath
For (H6219) ashowth; bright; Ashvath, an Israelite -- Ashvath. see HEBREW (H6219) ashowth
From (H6213) asah and (H410) 'el; made of God; Asiel, an Israelite -- Asiel. see HEBREW (H6213) asah see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From (H6213) asah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has made; Asajah, the name of three or four Israelites -- Asaiah. see HEBREW (H6213) asah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column4: Adjective; noun; Adjective masculine; noun masculine
column9: From (H6238) ashar; rich, whether literal or figurative (noble) -- rich (man). see HEBREW (H6238) ashar
From (H6235) eser; tenth; by abbreviation, tenth month or (feminine) part -- tenth (part). see HEBREW (H6235) eser

column8: be angry be on a smoke
column9: A primitive root; to smoke, whether literal or figurative -- be angry (be on a) smoke.
From (H6225) ashan; smoky -- smoking. see HEBREW (H6225) ashan
From (H6225) ashan; smoke, literally or figuratively (vapor, dust, anger) -- smoke(-ing). see HEBREW (H6225) ashan

column7: a place in Judah and later in Simeon
column9: The same as (H6227) ashan; Ashan, a place in Palestine -- Ashan. see HEBREW (H6227) ashan
A primitive root (identical with (H6231) ashaq); to press upon, i.e. Quarrel; --strive with. see HEBREW (H6231) ashaq
From (H6229) asaq; strife -- Esek. see HEBREW (H6229) asaq

column8: get deceitfully, deceive, defraud, drink up, use oppression do violence wrong
column9: A primitive root (compare (H6229) asaq); to press upon, i.e. Oppress, defraud, violate, overflow -- get deceitfully, deceive, defraud, drink up, (use) oppress((-ion)), -or), do violence (wrong). see HEBREW (H6229) asaq
From (H6231) ashaq; oppression; Eshek, an Israelite -- Eshek. see HEBREW (H6231) ashaq

column8: cruelly, extortion, oppression, thing deceitfully gotten
column9: From (H6231) ashaq; injury, fraud, (subjectively) distress, (concretely) unjust gain -- cruelly, extortion, oppression, thing (deceitfully gotten). see HEBREW (H6231) ashaq
Feminine of (H6233) osheq; anguish -- oppressed. see HEBREW (H6233) osheq
Masculine of term aasarah {as-aw-raw'}; from (H6237) asar; ten (as an accumulation to the extent of the digits) -- ten, (fif-, seven-)teen. see HEBREW (H6237) asar
(Aramaic) masculine aasrah (Aramaic). {as-raw'}; corresponding to (H6235) eser; ten -- ten, + twelve. see HEBREW (H6235) eser

column7: to take the tenth of, tithe
column8: give the tenth, have, take tithing truly
column9: A primitive root (ident. With (H6238) ashar); to accumulate; but used only as denominative from (H6235) eser; to tithe, i.e. To take or give a tenth -- X surely, give (take) the tenth, (have, take) tithe(-ing, -s), X truly. see HEBREW (H6238) ashar see HEBREW (H6235) eser

column8: become rich, make rich, wax rich
column9: A primitive root; properly, to accumulate; chiefly (specifically) to grow (causatively, make) rich -- be(-come, en-, make, make self, wax) rich, make (1 Kings 22:48 marg). See (H6240) asar. see HEBREW (H6240) asar
From (H6238) ashar; wealth -- X far (richer), riches. see HEBREW (H6238) ashar

For (H6235) eser; ten (only in combination), i.e. -teen; also (ordinal) -teenth -- (eigh-, fif-, four-, nine-, seven-, six-, thir-)teen(-th), + eleven(-th), + sixscore thousand, + twelve(-th). see HEBREW (H6235) eser
Or oissaron {is-saw-rone'}; from (H6235) eser; (fractional) a tenth part -- tenth deal. see HEBREW (H6235) eser
From (H6235) eser; twenty; also (ordinal) twentieth -- (six-)score, twenty(-ieth). see HEBREW (H6235) eser
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6242) esriym -- twenty. see HEBREW (H6242) esriym
A primitive root; probably to shrink, i.e. Fail -- be consumed.
A primitive root; probably to be sleek, i.e. Glossy; hence (through the idea of polishing) to excogitate (as if forming in the mind) -- shine, think.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6245) ashath; to purpose -- think. see HEBREW (H6245) ashath
From (H6245) ashath; a fabric -- bright. see HEBREW (H6245) ashath
From (H6245) ashath; cogitation -- thought. see HEBREW (H6245) ashath

Apparently masculine plural construction of (H6247) esheth in the sense of an afterthought (used only in connection with (H6240) asar in lieu of (H259) 'echad) eleven or (ordinal) eleventh -- + eleven(-th). see HEBREW (H6247) esheth see HEBREW (H6240) asar see HEBREW (H259) 'echad
From (H6245) ashath; thinking -- thought. see HEBREW (H6245) ashath
Probably from (H6238) ashar; increase -- flock. see HEBREW (H6238) ashar

column7: a place East of the Jordan
column9: Or bashtaroth {ash-taw-roth'}; plural of (H6251) ashtrah; Ashtaroth, the name of a Sidonian deity, and of a place East of the Jordan -- Asharoth, Astaroth. See also (H1045) Beyth 'Ashtarowth, (H6253) Ashtoreth, (H6255) Ashtroth Qarnayim. see HEBREW (H6251) ashtrah see HEBREW (H1045) Beyth 'Ashtarowth see HEBREW (H6253) Ashtoreth see HEBREW (H6255) Ashtroth Qarnayim
Probably for (H6251) ashtrah; Ashtoreth, the Phoenician goddess of love (and increase) -- Ashtoreth. see HEBREW (H6251) ashtrah
Patrial from (H6252) Ashtarowth; an Ashterathite or inhabitant of Ashtaroth -- Ashterathite. see HEBREW (H6252) Ashtarowth

column7: Ashtaroth of the double horns, a place East of the Jordan
column9: From (H6252) Ashtarowth and the dual of (H7161) qeren; Ashtaroth of (the) double horns (a symbol of the deity); Ashteroth-Karnaim, a place East of the Jordan -- Ashtoreth Karnaim. see HEBREW (H6252) Ashtarowth see HEBREW (H7161) qeren

column8: after, always, certain, continually, evening, long, due season, so long as,
column9: From (H5703) ad; time, especially (adverb with preposition) now, when, etc. -- + after, (al-)ways, X certain, + continually, + evening, long, (due) season, so (long) as, (even-, evening-, noon-)tide, ((meal-)), what) time, when. see HEBREW (H5703) ad

column8: make fit, be ready to become
column9: A primitive root; to prepare -- make fit, be ready to become.

column8: henceforth, now, straightway, this time, whereas
column9: From (H6256) eth; at this time, whether adverb, conjunction or expletive -- henceforth, now, straightway, this time, whereas. see HEBREW (H6256) eth
Passive participle of (H6257) athad; prepared -- ready. see HEBREW (H6257) athad

Or sattud {at-tood'}; from (H6257) athad; prepared, i.e. Full grown; spoken only (in plural) of he-goats, or (figuratively) leaders of the people -- chief one, (he) goat, ram. see HEBREW (H6257) athad
From (H6256) eth; timely -- fit. see HEBREW (H6256) eth
For (H6261) ittiy; Attai, the name of three Israelites -- Attai. see HEBREW (H6261) ittiy
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6264) athiyd; prepared -- ready. see HEBREW (H6264) athiyd

column8: things that shall come, ready, treasures
column9: From (H6257) athad; prepared; by implication, skilful; feminine plural the future; also treasure -- things that shall come, ready, treasures. see HEBREW (H6257) athad
From (H5790) uwth and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has helped; Athajah, an Israelite -- Athaiah. see HEBREW (H5790) uwth see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H6275) athaq; properly, antique, i.e. Venerable or splendid -- durable. see HEBREW (H6275) athaq
From (H6275) athaq; removed, i.e. Weaned; also antique -- ancient, drawn. see HEBREW (H6275) athaq

column7: aged, a part of a name of God
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H6267) attiyq; venerable -- ancient. see HEBREW (H6267) attiyq
From an unused root meaning to sojourn; lodging; Athak, a place in Palestine -- Athach.
From an unused root meaning to compress; constringent; Athlai, an Israelite -- Athlai.

column7: daughter of Ahab, also three Israelites
column9: Or mathalyahuw {ath-al-yaw'-hoo}; from the same as (H6270) Athlay and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has constrained; Athaljah, the name of an Israelitess and two Israelites -- Athaliah. see HEBREW (H6270) Athlay see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
A primitive root; probably to glow, i.e. (figuratively) be desolated -- be darkened.
From an unused root meaning to force; forcible; Othni, an Israelite -- Othni.
From the same as (H6273) Otnniy and (H410) 'el; force of God; Othniel, an Israelite -- Othniel. see HEBREW (H6273) Otnniy see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column8: copy out, leave off, become wax old, remove
column9: A primitive root; to remove (intransitive or transitive) figuratively, to grow old; specifically, to transcribe -- copy out, leave off, become (wax) old, remove.
From (H6275) athaq; antique, i.e. Valued -- durable. see HEBREW (H6275) athaq
From (H6275) athaq in the sense of license; impudent -- arrogancy, grievous (hard) things, stiff. see HEBREW (H6275) athaq

column7: time of a ruler, a place on the border of Zebulun
column9: From (H6256) eth and (H7011) qayam; time of a judge; Eth-Katsin, a place in Palestine -- Ittah-kazin (by including directive enclitic). see HEBREW (H6256) eth see HEBREW (H7011) qayam
A primitive root (rather denominative from (H6281) Ether); to burn incense in worship, i.e. Intercede (reciprocally, listen to prayer) -- intreat, (make) pray(-er). see HEBREW (H6281) Ether
A primitive root; to be (causatively, make) abundant -- deceitful, multiply.
From (H6280) athar; abundance; Ether, a place in Palestine -- Ether. see HEBREW (H6280) athar
From (H6280) athar; incense (as increasing to a volume of smoke); hence (from (H6279) athar) a worshipper -- suppliant, thick. see HEBREW (H6280) athar see HEBREW (H6279) athar
From (H6280) athar; copiousness -- abundance. see HEBREW (H6280) athar
A primitive root; to puff, i.e. Blow away -- scatter into corners.
Feminine of (H6311) poh; properly, mouth in a figurative sense, i.e. Direction, region, extremity -- corner, end, quarter, side. see HEBREW (H6311) poh

column8: beautify, boast self, go over the boughs, glorify self, glory, vaunt self
column9: A primitive root; to gleam, i.e. (causatively) embellish; figuratively, to boast; also to explain (i.e. Make clear) oneself; denominative from (H6288) p'orah, to shake a tree -- beautify, boast self, go over the boughs, glorify (self), glory, vaunt self. see HEBREW (H6288) p'orah
From (H6286) pa'ar; an embellishment, i.e. Fancy head-dress -- beauty, bonnet, goodly, ornament, tire. see HEBREW (H6286) pa'ar
Or pora'h {po-raw'}; or pu'rah {poo-raw'}; from (H6286) pa'ar; properly, ornamentation, i.e. (plural) foliage (including the limbs) as bright green -- bough, branch, sprig. see HEBREW (H6286) pa'ar
From (H6286) pa'ar; properly, illuminated, i.e. A glow; as noun, a flush (of anxiety) -- blackness. see HEBREW (H6286) pa'ar
From (H6286) pa'ar; ornamental; Paran, a desert of Arabia -- Paran. see HEBREW (H6286) pa'ar
From an unused root meaning to be torpid, i.e. Crude; an unripe fig -- green fig.
Or piggul {pig-gool'}; from an unused root meaning to stink; properly, fetid, i.e. (figuratively) unclean (ceremonially) -- abominable(-tion, thing).

column8: come between, cause to entreat, fall upon, make intercession, intercessor, entreat
column9: A primitive root; to impinge, by accident or violence, or (figuratively) by importunity -- come (betwixt), cause to entreat, fall (upon), make intercession, intercessor, intreat, lay, light (upon), meet (together), pray, reach, run.
From (H6293) paga'; impact (casual) -- chance, occurent. see HEBREW (H6293) paga'
From (H6294) pega' and (H410) 'el; accident of God; Pagiel, an Israelite -- Pagiel. see HEBREW (H6294) pega' see HEBREW (H410) 'el
A primitive root; to relax, i.e. Become exhausted -- be faint.
From (H6296) pagar; a carcase (as limp), whether of man or beast; figuratively, an idolatrous image -- carcase, corpse, dead body. see HEBREW (H6296) pagar
A primitive root; to come in contact with, whether by accident or violence; figuratively, to concur -- meet (with, together).

column8: deliver, by any means, ransom, that are to be, let be redeemed, rescue, surely
column9: A primitive root; to sever, i.e. Ransom; gener. To release, preserve -- X at all, deliver, X by any means, ransom, (that are to be, let be) redeem(-ed), rescue, X surely.

column7: God has ransomed, a man of Naphtali
column9: From (H6299) padah and (H410) 'el; God has ransomed; Pedahel, an Israelite -- Pedahel. see HEBREW (H6299) padah see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: the rock has ransomed, a Manassite
column9: From (H6299) padah and (H6697) tsuwr; a rock (i.e. God) has ransomed; Pedahtsur, an Israelite -- Pedahzur. see HEBREW (H6299) padah see HEBREW (H6697) tsuwr

column7: that are to be that were redeemed
column8: that are to be that were redeemed
column9: Passive participle of (H6299) padah. Ransomed (and so occurring under (H6299) padah); as abstractly (in plural masculine) a ransom -- (that are) to be (that were) redeemed. see HEBREW (H6299) padah see HEBREW (H6299) padah

column7: ransom, head of a family of Nethinim
column9: From (H6299) padah; ransom; Padon, one of the Nethinim. -- Padon. see HEBREW (H6299) padah
Or pduth {ped-ooth'}; from (H6929) Qedmah; distinction; also deliverance -- division, redeem, redemption. see HEBREW (H6929) Qedmah

column7: Yah has ransomed, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or Pdayahuw {ped-aw-yaw'-hoo}; from (H6299) padah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has ransomed; Pedajah, the name of six Israelites -- Pedaiah. see HEBREW (H6299) padah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Or pidyom {pid-yome'}; also pidyown {pid-yone'}; or pidyon {pid-yone'}; from (H6299) padah; a ransom; --ransom, that were redeemed, redemption. see HEBREW (H6299) padah

From an unused root meaning to extend; a plateau; or Paddan param {pad-dan' ar-awm'}; from the same and (H758) 'Aram; the table-land of Aram; Paddan or Paddan-Aram, a region of Syria -- Padan, Padan-aram. see HEBREW (H758) 'Aram
A primitive root; to retrieve -- deliver.
From an unused root meaning to be greasy; suet -- fat.

column8: according as after, appointment, assent, collar, commandment, eat, edge, end,
column9: From (H6284) pa'ah; the mouth (as the means of blowing), whether literal or figurative (particularly speech); specifically edge, portion or side; adverbially (with preposition) according to -- accord(-ing as, -ing to), after, appointment, assent, collar, command(-ment), X eat, edge, end, entry, + file, hole, X in, mind, mouth, part, portion, X (should) say(-ing), sentence, skirt, sound, speech, X spoken, talk, tenor, X to, + two-edged, wish, word. see HEBREW (H6284) pa'ah

column8: here, hither, the one other, this, that side
column9: Or po (Job 38:11) {po}; or pow {po}; probably from a primitive inseparable particle \"p\" (of demonstrative force) and (H1931) huw'; this place (French ici), i.e. Here or hence -- here, hither, the one (other, this, that) side. see HEBREW (H1931) huw'
Or Puvvah {poov-vaw'}; from (H6284) pa'ah; a blast; Puah or Puvvah, the name of two Israelites -- Phuvah, Pua, Puah. see HEBREW (H6284) pa'ah

column8: cease, be feeble, faint, be slacked
column9: A primitive root; to be sluggish -- cease, be feeble, faint, be slacked.
From (H6313) puwg; intermission -- rest. see HEBREW (H6313) puwg

column8: blow upon, break, puff, bring into a snare, speak, utter
column9: A primitive root; to puff, i.e. Blow with the breath or air; hence, to fan (as a breeze), to utter, to kindle (a fire), to scoff -- blow (upon), break, puff, bring into a snare, speak, utter.

column7: a son of Ham, also his desc. and their land
column9: Of foreign origin; Put, a son of Ham, also the name of his descendants or their region, and of a Persian tribe -- Phut, Put.
From an unused root (probably meaning to disparage) and (H410) 'el; contempt of God; Putiel, an Israelite -- Putiel. see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Of Egyptian derivation: Potiphar, an Egyptian -- Potiphar.
Of Egyptian derivation; Poti-Phera, an Egyptian -- Poti-pherah.
From an unused root meaning to paint; dye (specifically, stibium for the eyes) -- fair colours, glistering, paint(-ed) (-ing).
From an unused root meaning to be thick; a bean (as plump) -- beans.

column8: Pul, the name of an Assyrian king and of an Ethiopian tribe
column9: Of foreign origin; Pul, the name of an Assyrian king and of an Ethiopian tribe -- Pul.
A primitive root meaning to turn, i.e. Be perplexed -- be distracted.
Patronymically from an unused name meaning a turn; a Punite (collectively) or descendants of an unknown Pun -- Punites.
From (H6323) puwn; perplexity; Punon, a place in the Desert -- Punon. see HEBREW (H6323) puwn
From an unused root meaning to glitter; brilliancy; Puah, an Israelitess -- Puah.

column8: break dash, shake in to pieces, cast abroad, disperse selves, drive, scatter abroad, spread abroad
column9: A primitive root; to dash in pieces, literally or figuratively (especially to disperse) -- break (dash, shake) in (to) pieces, cast (abroad), disperse (selves), drive, retire, scatter (abroad), spread abroad.
A primitive root; to waver -- stumble, move.

column8: afford, draw out, further, get, obtain
column9: A primitive root (identical with (H6328) puwq through the idea of dropping out; compare (H5312) nphaq); to issue, i.e. Furnish; causatively, to secure; figuratively, to succeed -- afford, draw out, further, get, obtain. see HEBREW (H6328) puwq see HEBREW (H5312) nphaq
From (H6328) puwq; a stumbling-block -- grief. see HEBREW (H6328) puwq

column7: break, bring to nothing, utterly take
column8: break, bring to nothing, utterly take
column9: A primitive root; to crush -- break, bring to nought, X utterly take.
Also (plural) Puwriym {poo-reem'}; or Puriym {poo-reem'}; from (H6331) puwr; a lot (as by means of a broken piece) -- Pur, Purim. see HEBREW (H6331) puwr
From (H6331) puwr; a wine-press (as crushing the grapes) -- winepress. see HEBREW (H6331) puwr
Of Persian origin; Poratha, a son of Haman -- Poratha.

column8: grow up, be grown fat, spread selves, be scattered
column9: A primitive root; to spread; figuratively, act proudly -- grow up, be grown fat, spread selves, be scattered.

column8: Puhites, descendants of an unknown Puth
column9: Patronymically from an unused name meaning a hinge; a Puthite (collectively) or descendants of an unknown Puth -- Puhites (as if from (H6312) Puw'ah). see HEBREW (H6312) Puw'ah
From (H6338) pazaz; pure (gold); hence, gold itself (as refined) -- fine (pure) gold. see HEBREW (H6338) pazaz
A primitive root; to refine (gold) -- best (gold).
A primitive root (identical with (H6338) pazaz); to solidify (as if by refining); also to spring (as if separating the limbs) -- leap, be made strong. see HEBREW (H6338) pazaz
A primitive root; to scatter, whether in enmity or bounty -- disperse, scatter (abroad).
From (H6351) pachach; a (metallic) sheet (as pounded thin); also a spring net (as spread out like a lamina) -- gin, (thin) plate, snare. see HEBREW (H6351) pachach

column7: to dread, be in dread or in awe
column8: be afraid, stand in awe, be in fear, make to shake
column9: A primitive root; to be startled (by a sudden alarm); hence, to fear in general -- be afraid, stand in awe, (be in) fear, make to shake.

column8: dreadful, fear, thing great fear terror
column9: From (H6342) pachad; a (sudden) alarm (properly, the object feared, by implication, the feeling) -- dread(-ful), fear, (thing) great (fear, -ly feared), terror. see HEBREW (H6342) pachad
The same as (H6343) pachad; a testicle (as a cause of shame akin to fear) -- stone. see HEBREW (H6343) pachad
Feminine of (H6343) pachad; alarm (i.e. Awe) -- fear. see HEBREW (H6343) pachad
Of foreign origin; a prefect (of a city or small district) -- captain, deputy, governor.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6346) pechah -- captain, governor. see HEBREW (H6346) pechah
A primitive root; to bubble up or froth (as boiling water), i.e. (figuratively) to be unimportant -- light.
From (H6348) pachaz; ebullition, i.e. Froth (figuratively, lust) -- unstable. see HEBREW (H6348) pachaz
From (H6348) pachaz; frivolity -- lightness. see HEBREW (H6348) pachaz
A primitive root; to batter out; but used only as denominative from (H6341) pach, to spread a net -- be snared. see HEBREW (H6341) pach
Perhaps from an unused root probably meaning to be black; a coal, whether charred or live -- coals.
(Aramaic) from an unused root probably meaning to fashion; a potter -- potter.
Probably from an unused root apparently meaning to dig; a pit, especially for catching animals -- hole, pit, snare.
From (H6354) pachath and (H4124) Mow'ab; pit of Moab; Pachath-Moab, an Israelite -- Pahath-moab. see HEBREW (H6354) pachath see HEBREW (H4124) Mow'ab
From the same as (H6354) pachath; a hole (by mildew in a garment) -- fret inward. see HEBREW (H6354) pachath
Of foreign derivation; a gem, probably the topaz -- topaz.
Passive participle of (H6362) patar; opened, i.e. (as noun) a bud -- open. see HEBREW (H6362) patar
From (H6362) patar; open, i.e. Unoccupied -- free. see HEBREW (H6362) patar
Intensively from an unused root meaning to pound; a hammer -- hammer.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to that of (H6360) pattiysh; a gown (as if hammered out wide) -- hose. see HEBREW (H6360) pattiysh

column8: dismiss, free, let shoot out, slip away
column9: A primitive root; to cleave or burst through, i.e. (causatively) to emit, whether literal or figurative (gape) -- dismiss, free, let (shoot) out, slip away.

column7: that which separates or first opens
column9: Or pitrah {pit-raw'}; from (H6362) patar; a fissure, i.e. (concretely) firstling (as opening the matrix) -- firstling, openeth, such as open. see HEBREW (H6362) patar
Of Egyptian origin; Pi-Beseth, a place in Egypt -- Pi-beseth.
From an unused root probably meaning to pierce; (figuratively) misfortune -- destruction, ruin.
Or piyah {pee-yaw'}; feminine of (H6310) peh; an edge -- (two-)edge(-d). see HEBREW (H6310) peh

column7: a place on the E. border of Egypt
column9: From (H6310) peh and the feminine plural of a noun (from the same root as (H2356) chowr), with the article interpolated; mouth of the gorges; Pi-ha-Chiroth, a place in Egypt -- Pi-hahiroth. (In Numbers 14:19 without Pi-.) see HEBREW (H6310) peh see HEBREW (H2356) chowr
From (H6315) puwach; a powder (as easily puffed away), i.e. Ashes or dust -- ashes. see HEBREW (H6315) puwach
Apparently from (H6310) peh and (H3605) kol; mouth of all; Picol, a Philistine -- Phichol. see HEBREW (H6310) peh see HEBREW (H3605) kol
Or pilegesh {pee-leh'-ghesh}; of uncertain derivation; a concubine; also (masculine) a paramour -- concubine, paramour.

column7: (a measure of weight) two-thirds of a shekel (approximately)
column9: Probably from an unused root meaning to be plump; obesity -- collops.
Apparently from (H6310) peh and a variation of (H5175) nachash; mouth of a serpent; Pinechas, the name of three Israelites -- Phinehas. see HEBREW (H6310) peh see HEBREW (H5175) nachash
Probably the same as (H6325) Puwnon; Pinon, an Idumaean -- Pinon. see HEBREW (H6325) Puwnon
For (H6366) peyah; an edge or tooth -- tooth, X two-edged. see HEBREW (H6366) peyah
From (H6329) puwq; a tottering -- smite together. see HEBREW (H6329) puwq

column7: one of the rivers of Eden
column9: From (H6335) puwsh; dispersive; Pishon, a river of Eden -- Pison. see HEBREW (H6335) puwsh
Probably from the same as (H6596) poth; expansive; Pithon, an Israelite -- Pithon. see HEBREW (H6596) poth
From (H6379) pakah; a flask (from which a liquid may flow) -- box, vial. see HEBREW (H6379) pakah
A primitive root; to pour -- run out.

column7: bindress of the gazelles, head of a postexilic family
column8: Pokereth-Tsebajim, one of the servants of Solomon
column9: From the active participle (of the same form as the first word) feminine of an unused root (meaning to entrap) and plural of (H6643) tsbiy; trap of gazelles; Pokereth-Tsebajim, one of the \"servants of Solomon\" -- Pochereth of Zebaim. see HEBREW (H6643) tsbiy

A primitive root; properly, perhaps to separate, i.e. Distinguish (literally or figuratively); by implication, to be (causatively, make) great, difficult, wonderful -- accomplish, (arise...too, be too) hard, hidden, things too high, (be, do, do a, shew) marvelous(-ly, -els, things, work), miracles, perform, separate, make singular, (be, great, make) wonderful(-ers, -ly, things, works), wondrous (things, works, -ly).
From (H6381) pala'; a miracle -- marvellous thing, wonder(-ful, -fully). see HEBREW (H6381) pala'
Or paliy {paw-lee'}; from (H6381) pala'; remarkable -- secret, wonderful. see HEBREW (H6381) pala'
Patronymically from (H6396) Palluw'; a Palluite (collectively) or descendants of Pallu -- Palluites. see HEBREW (H6396) Palluw'
A primitive root; to split (literally or figuratively) -- divide.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6385) palag -- divided. see HEBREW (H6385) palag
(Aramaic) from (H6386) plag; a half -- dividing. see HEBREW (H6386) plag
From (H6385) palag; a rill (i.e. Small channel of water, as in irrigation) -- river, stream. see HEBREW (H6385) palag
The same as (H6388) peleg; earthquake; Peleg, a son of Shem -- Peleg. see HEBREW (H6388) peleg
From (H6385) palag; a runlet, i.e. Gully -- division, river. see HEBREW (H6385) palag
From (H6385) palag; a section -- division. see HEBREW (H6385) palag
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6391) pluggah -- division. see HEBREW (H6391) pluggah
From an unused root meaning to divide; a cleaver, i.e. Iron armature (of a chariot) -- torch.
Of uncertain derivation; Pildash, a relative of Abraham -- Pildash.
A primitive root; to distinguish (literally or figuratively) -- put a difference, show marvellous, separate, set apart, sever, make wonderfully.
From (H6395) palah; distinguished; Pallu, an Israelite -- Pallu, Phallu. see HEBREW (H6395) palah

column7: descriptive title of two of David\'s men
column9: Patronymically from an unused name (from (H6395) palah) meaning separate; a Pelonite or inhabitant of an unknown Palon -- Pelonite. see HEBREW (H6395) palah

column8: bring forth, cleave, cut, shred, strike through
column9: A primitive root; to slice, i.e. Break open or pierce -- bring forth, cleave, cut, shred, strike through.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6398) palach; to serve or worship -- minister, serve. see HEBREW (H6398) palach
From (H6398) palach; a slice -- piece. see HEBREW (H6398) palach
From (H6400) pelach; slicing; Pilcha, an Israelite -- Pilcha. see HEBREW (H6400) pelach
(Aramaic) from (H6399) plach; worship -- service. see HEBREW (H6399) plach

column8: calve, carry away safe, deliver, cause to escape
column9: A primitive root; to slip out, i.e. Escape; causatively, to deliver -- calve, carry away safe, deliver, (cause to) escape.
From (H6403) palat; escape; Pelet, the name of two Israelites -- Pelet. See also (H1046) Beyth Pelet. see HEBREW (H6403) palat see HEBREW (H1046) Beyth Pelet
From (H6403) palat; escape -- deliverance, escape. see HEBREW (H6403) palat
From (H6403) palat; delivered; Palti, the name of two Israelites -- Palti, Phalti. see HEBREW (H6403) palat

column7: escape, a descriptive title for one of David\'s men
column9: Patronymically from (H6406) Paltiy; a Paltite or descendant of Palti -- Paltite. see HEBREW (H6406) Paltiy
For (H6407) Paltiy; Piltai, an Israelite -- Piltai. see HEBREW (H6407) Paltiy
From the same as (H6404) Pelet and (H410) 'el; deliverance of God; Paltiel, the name of two Israelites -- Paltiel, Phaltiel. see HEBREW (H6404) Pelet see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Or Platyahuw {pel-at-yaw'-hoo}; from (H6403) palat and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has delivered; Pelatjah, the name of four Israelites -- Pelatiah. see HEBREW (H6403) palat see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Or Pla.yah {pel-aw-yaw'}; from (H6381) pala' and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has distinguished; Pelajah, the name of three Israelites -- Pelaiah. see HEBREW (H6381) pala' see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Or paleyt {paw-late'}; or palet {paw-late'}; from (H6403) palat; a refugee -- (that have) escape(-d, -th), fugitive. see HEBREW (H6403) palat
Or pletah {pel-ay-taw'}; feminine of (H6412) paliyt; deliverance; concretely, an escaped portion -- deliverance, (that is) escape(-d), remnant. see HEBREW (H6412) paliyt
From (H6419) palal; a magistrate -- judge. see HEBREW (H6419) palal
Feminine of (H6414) paliyl; justice -- judgment. see HEBREW (H6414) paliyl

column7: for a judge, calling for judgment
column9: From (H6414) paliyl; judicial -- judge. see HEBREW (H6414) paliyl
Feminine of (H6416) pliyliy; judicature -- judgment. see HEBREW (H6416) pliyliy

column7: whorl of a spindle, a district
column9: From an unused root meaning to be round; a circuit (i.e. District); also a spindle (as whirled); hence, a crutch -- (di-)staff, participle

column8: entreat, judgment, make prayer make supplication
column9: A primitive root; to judge (officially or mentally); by extension, to intercede, pray -- intreat, judge(-ment), (make) pray(-er, -ing), make supplication.

column7: a builder of the Jerusalem wall
column9: From (H6419) palal; judge; Palal, an Israelite -- Palal. see HEBREW (H6419) palal

column7: Yah has interposed, an Israelite priest
column9: From (H6419) palal and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has judged; Pelaljah, an Israelite -- Pelaliah. see HEBREW (H6419) palal see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Probably for (H6423) ploniy; a certain one, i.e. So-and-so -- certain. see HEBREW (H6423) ploniy
From (H6395) palah; such a one, i.e. A specified peccrson -- such. see HEBREW (H6395) palah
A primitive root; properly, to roll flat, i.e. Prepare (a road); also to revolve, i.e. Weigh (mentally) -- make, ponder, weigh.
From (H6424) palac; a balance -- scales, weight. see HEBREW (H6424) palac
A primitive root; properly, perhaps to rend, i.e. (by implication) to quiver -- tremble.
From (H6426) palats; affright -- fearfulness, horror, trembling. see HEBREW (H6426) palats

column7: (act of mourning) perhaps to roll in
column9: A primitive root; to roll (in dust) -- roll (wallow) self.

column7: a territory on the S. Mediterranean coast of Isr
column9: From (H6428) palash; rolling, i.e. Migratory; Pelesheth, a region of Syria -- Palestina, Palestine, Philistia, Philistines. see HEBREW (H6428) palash
Patrial from (H6429) Plesheth; a Pelishtite or inhabitant of Pelesheth -- Philistine. see HEBREW (H6429) Plesheth
From an unused root meaning to flee; swiftness; Peleth, the name of two Israelites -- Peleth.
From the same form as (H6431) Peleth; a courier (collectively) or official messenger -- Pelethites. see HEBREW (H6431) Peleth
(Aramaic) probably for (H6310) peh; the mouth (literally or figuratively) -- mouth. see HEBREW (H6310) peh
From an unused root meaning to turn; an angle (of a street or wall) -- corner.
From (H6437) panah; properly, removal; used only (in the construction) adverb as conjunction, lest -- (lest) (peradventure), that...not. see HEBREW (H6437) panah

column7: (probably a kind of food) perhaps cake
column9: Of uncertain derivation; probably pastry -- Pannag.

column8: appear, at eventide, behold, cast out, come on, corner, dawning, empty,
column9: A primitive root; to turn; by implication, to face, i.e. Appear, look, etc. -- appear, at (even-)tide, behold, cast out, come on, X corner, dawning, empty, go away, lie, look, mark, pass away, prepare, regard, (have) respect (to), (re-)turn (aside, away, back, face, self), X right (early).
Feminine of (H6434) pen; an angle; by implication, a pinnacle; figuratively, a chieftain -- bulwark, chief, corner, stay, tower. see HEBREW (H6434) pen

column7: face of God, a place East of the Jordan, also two Israelites
column9: Or (more properly,) Pniylel {pen-oo-ale'}; from (H6437) panah and (H410) 'el; face of God; Penuel or Peniel, a place East of Jordan; also (as Penuel) the name of two Israelites -- Peniel, Penuel. see HEBREW (H6437) panah see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column8: accept, anger, as long as, battle, because of, beseech, countenance
column9: Plural (but always as singular) of an unused noun (paneh {paw-neh'}; from (H6437) panah); the face (as the part that turns); used in a great variety of applications (literally and figuratively); also (with prepositional prefix) as a preposition (before, etc.) -- + accept, a-(be-)fore(-time), against, anger, X as (long as), at, + battle, + because (of), + beseech, countenance, edge, + employ, endure, + enquire, face, favour, fear of, for, forefront(-part), form(-er time, -ward), from, front, heaviness, X him(-self), + honourable, + impudent, + in, it, look(-eth) (- s), X me, + meet, X more than, mouth, of, off, (of) old (time), X on, open, + out of, over against, the partial, person, + please, presence, propect, was purposed, by reason of, + regard, right forth, + serve, X shewbread, sight, state, straight, + street, X thee, X them(-selves), through (+ - out), till, time(-s) past, (un-)to(-ward), + upon, upside (+ down), with(- in, + -stand), X ye, X you. see HEBREW (H6437) panah

column7: toward the side or inside, within
column9: From (H6440) paniym with directive enclitic; faceward, i.e. Indoors -- (with-)in(-ner part, -ward). see HEBREW (H6440) paniym
From (H6440) paniym; interior -- (with-)in(-ner, - ward). see HEBREW (H6440) paniym
Or paniy {paw-nee'}; from the same as (H6434) pen; probably a pearl (as round) -- ruby. see HEBREW (H6434) pen
Probably feminine from (H6443) paniyn contr.; Peninnah, an Israelitess -- Peninnah. see HEBREW (H6443) paniyn
A primitive root; to enervate -- bring up.

From (H6461) pacac; properly, the palm (of the hand) or sole (of the foot) (compare (H6447) pac); by implication (plural) a long and sleeved tunic (perhaps simply a wide one; from the original sense of the root, i.e. Of many breadths) -- (divers) colours. see HEBREW (H6461) pacac see HEBREW (H6447) pac
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H6461) pacac; the palm (of the hand, as being spread out) -- participle see HEBREW (H6461) pacac
A primitive root; to cut up, i.e. (figuratively) contemplate -- consider.
From (H6448) pacag; a cleft; Pisgah, a mt. East of Jordan -- Pisgah. see HEBREW (H6448) pacag

column7: palm of blood, a place in Judah
column9: From (H6446) pac and the plural of (H1818) dam; palm (i.e. Dell) of bloodshed; Pas-Dammim, a place in Palestine -- Pas-dammim. Compare (H658) 'Ephec Dammiym. see HEBREW (H6446) pac see HEBREW (H1818) dam see HEBREW (H658) 'Ephec Dammiym
From (H6461) pacac; expansion, i.e. Abundance -- handful. see HEBREW (H6461) pacac

column8: halt, become lame, leap, pass over
column9: A primitive root; to hop, i.e. (figuratively) skip over (or spare); by implication, to hesitate; also (literally) to limp, to dance -- halt, become lame, leap, pass over.
From (H6452) pacach; a pretermission, i.e. Exemption; used only techically of the Jewish Passover (the festival or the victim) -- passover (offering). see HEBREW (H6452) pacach
From (H6452) pacach; limping; Paseach, the name of two Israelites -- Paseah, Phaseah. see HEBREW (H6452) pacach
From (H6452) pacach; lame -- lame. see HEBREW (H6452) pacach
From (H6458) pacal; an idol -- carved (graven) image, quarry. see HEBREW (H6458) pacal
From an unused root meaning to divide; divider; Pasak, an Israelite -- Pasach.
A primitive root; to carve, whether wood or stone -- grave, hew.
From (H6458) pacal; an idol -- carved (graven) image. see HEBREW (H6458) pacal
(Aramaic) or pcanteriyn {pes-an-tay-reen'}; a transliteration of the Gr. Psalterion; a lyre -- psaltery.
A primitive root; probably to disperse, i.e. (intransitive) disappear -- cease.
Perhaps from (H6461) pacac; dispersion; Pispah, an Israelite -- Pispah. see HEBREW (H6461) pacac
A primitive root; to scream -- cry.
Or Pamiy {paw-ee'}; from (H6463) pa'ah; screaming; Pau or Pai, a place in Edom -- Pai, Pau. see HEBREW (H6463) pa'ah

column7: a mountain in Moab, also a god worshiped there
column9: From (H6473) pa'ar; a gap; Peor, a mountain East of Jordan; also (for (H1187) Ba'al p'owr) a deity worshipped there -- Peor. See also (H1047) Beyth p'owr. see HEBREW (H6473) pa'ar see HEBREW (H1187) Ba'al p'owr see HEBREW (H1047) Beyth p'owr

column8: commit, evil doer, maker, ordain, worker
column9: A primitive root; to do or make (systematically and habitually), especially to practise -- commit, (evil-) do(-er), make(-r), ordain, work(-er).

column8: act, deed, do, getting, maker, work
column9: From (H6466) pa'al; an act or work (concretely) -- act, deed, do, getting, maker, work. see HEBREW (H6466) pa'al
Feminine passive participle of (H6466) pa'al; (abstractly) work -- labour, reward, wages, work. see HEBREW (H6466) pa'al
From (H6468) p'ullah; laborious; Peullethai, an Israelite -- Peulthai. see HEBREW (H6468) p'ullah
A primitive root; to tap, i.e. Beat regularly; hence (generally) to impel or agitate -- move, trouble.

column8: anvil, corner, footstep, going, hundredfold, now, this once, order,
column9: Or (feminine) pa;amah {pah-am-aw'}; from (H6470) pa'am; a stroke, literally or figuratively (in various applications, as follow) -- anvil, corner, foot(-step), going, (hundred-)fold, X now, (this) + once, order, rank, step, + thrice, ((often-)), second, this, two) time(-s), twice, wheel. see HEBREW (H6470) pa'am
From (H6471) pa'am; a bell (as struck) -- bell. see HEBREW (H6471) pa'am
A primitive root; to yawn, i.e. Open wide (literally or figuratively) -- gape, open (wide).
From (H6473) pa'ar; yawning; Paarai, an Israelite -- Paarai. see HEBREW (H6473) pa'ar
A primitive root; to rend, i.e. Open (especially the mouth) -- deliver, gape, open, rid, utter.

column7: to cause to break or burst forth, break forth with
column8: break forth, forth into joy, make a loud noise
column9: A primitive root; to break out (in joyful sound) -- break (forth, forth into joy), make a loud noise.
From (H6484) patsar; bluntness -- + file. see HEBREW (H6484) patsar
A primitive root; to peel -- pill.
From (H6478) patsal; a peeling -- strake. see HEBREW (H6478) patsal
A primitive root; to rend (by earthquake) -- break.
A primitive root; to split, i.e. Wound -- wound.
From (H6481) patsa'; a wound -- wound(-ing). see HEBREW (H6481) patsa'
From an unused root meaning to dissever; dispersive; Pitstsets, a priest -- Apses (including the article).
A primitive root; to peck at, i.e. (figuratively) stun or dull -- press, urge, stubbornness.

column7: to attend to, visit, muster, appoint
column8: appoint, at all, avenge, bestow, appoint to have the, give a charge, commit, count,
column9: A primitive root; to visit (with friendly or hostile intent); by analogy, to oversee, muster, charge, care for, miss, deposit, etc. -- appoint, X at all, avenge, bestow, (appoint to have the, give a) charge, commit, count, deliver to keep, be empty, enjoin, go see, hurt, do judgment, lack, lay up, look, make, X by any means, miss, number, officer, (make) overseer, have (the) oversight, punish, reckon, (call to) remember(-brance), set (over), sum, X surely, visit, want.

column8: account, that have the charge, custody, that which
column9: Feminine passive participle of (H6485) paqad; visitation (in many senses, chiefly official) -- account, (that have the) charge, custody, that which...laid up, numbers, office(-r), ordering, oversight, + prison, reckoning, visitation. see HEBREW (H6485) paqad
From (H6485) paqad; a deposit -- that which was delivered (to keep), store. see HEBREW (H6485) paqad
From (H6496) paqiyd; supervision -- ward. see HEBREW (H6496) paqiyd
From (H6485) paqad; punishment; Pekod, a symbolic name for Bab. -- Pekod. see HEBREW (H6485) paqad
Or piqqud {pik-kood'}; from (H6485) paqad; properly, appointed, i.e. A mandate (of God; plural only, collectively, for the Law) -- commandment, precept, statute. see HEBREW (H6485) paqad
A primitive root; to open (the senses, especially the eyes); figuratively, to be observant -- open.
From (H6491) paqach; watch; Pekach, an Israelite king -- Pekah. see HEBREW (H6491) paqach
From (H6491) paqach; clear-sighted; figuratively, intelligent -- seeing, wise. see HEBREW (H6491) paqach

column7: Yah has opened (the eyes), a king of Isr
column9: From (H6491) paqach and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has observed; Pekachjah, an Israelite king -- Pekahiah. see HEBREW (H6491) paqach see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H6491) paqach redoubled; opening (of a dungeon), i.e. Jail-delivery (figuratively, salvation for sin) -- opening of the prison. see HEBREW (H6491) paqach

column8: which had the charge, governor, office, overseer, that was set
column9: From (H6485) paqad; a superintendent (civil, military or religious) -- which had the charge, governor, office, overseer, (that) was set. see HEBREW (H6485) paqad
From an unused root meaning to burst; only used as an architectural term of an ornament similar to (H6498) paqqu'ah, a semi-globe -- knop. see HEBREW (H6498) paqqu'ah
From the same as (H6497) peqa'; the wild cucumber (from splitting open to shed its seeds) -- gourd. see HEBREW (H6497) peqa'
Or par {pawr}; from (H6565) parar; a bullock (apparently as breaking forth in wild strength, or perhaps as dividing the hoof) -- (+ young) bull(-ock), calf, ox. see HEBREW (H6565) parar
A primitive root; to bear fruit -- be fruitful.
Or pereh (Jeremiah 2:24) {peh'-reh}; from (H6500) para' in the secondary sense of running wild; the onager -- wild (ass). see HEBREW (H6500) para'
From (H6501) pere'; wildly; Piram, a Canaanite -- Piram. see HEBREW (H6501) pere'

column7: probably a structure on the west side of Solomon\'s temple
column9: Or Parvar {par-vawr'}; of foreign origin; Parbar or Parvar, a quarter of Jerusalem -- Parbar, suburb.

column8: disperse, divide, be out of joint, part, scatter abroad, separate self, sever self, stretch,
column9: A primitive root; to break through, i.e. Spread or separate (oneself) -- disperse, divide, be out of joint, part, scatter (abroad), separate (self), sever self, stretch, sunder.
From (H6504) parad; a mule (perhaps from his lonely habits) -- mule. see HEBREW (H6504) parad
Feminine of (H6505) pered; a she-mule -- mule. see HEBREW (H6505) pered
Feminine passive participle of (H6504) parad; something separated, i.e. A kernel -- seed. see HEBREW (H6504) parad
Of foreign origin; a park -- forest, orchard.

column8: bear, bring forth fruit, be, cause to be, make fruitful, grow, increase
column9: A primitive root; to bear fruit (literally or figuratively) -- bear, bring forth (fruit), (be, cause to be, make) fruitful, grow, increase.
Feminine of (H6499) par; a heifer -- cow, heifer, kine. see HEBREW (H6499) par
The same as (H6510) parah; Parah, a place in Palestine -- Parah. see HEBREW (H6510) parah
From (H6331) puwr; a hole (as broken, i.e. Dug) -- + mole. Compare (H2661) chaphor. see HEBREW (H6331) puwr see HEBREW (H2661) chaphor
For (H6288) p'orah; foliage; Purah, an Israelite -- Phurah. see HEBREW (H6288) p'orah
Or Priyda {per-ee-daw'}; from (H6504) parad; dispersion; Peruda or Perida, one of \"Solomon's servants\" -- Perida, Peruda. see HEBREW (H6504) parad
Passive participle of (H6524) parach; blossomed; Paruach, an Israelite -- Paruah. see HEBREW (H6524) parach

column7: a region from which Solomon obtained gold for the temple
column9: Of foreign origin; Parvajim, an Oriental region -- Parvaim.
Passive participle of (H6565) parar in the sense of spreading out (compare (H6524) parach); a skillet (as flat or deep) -- pan, pot. see HEBREW (H6565) parar see HEBREW (H6524) parach
From an unused root meaning to separate, i.e. Decide; a chieftain -- village.

column8: unwalled town, without walls, unwalled village
column9: From the same as (H6518) paraz; an open country -- (unwalled) town (without walls), unwalled village. see HEBREW (H6518) paraz
From the same as (H6518) paraz; magistracy, i.e. Leadership (also concretely, chieftains) -- village. see HEBREW (H6518) paraz
Or prowziy {per-o-zee'}; from (H6519) prazah; a rustic -- village. see HEBREW (H6519) prazah

column7: a people in the land of Canaan
column9: For (H6521) praziy; inhabitant of the open country; a Perizzite, one of the Canaanitish tribes -- Perizzite. see HEBREW (H6521) praziy
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H1270) barzel; iron -- iron. see HEBREW (H1270) barzel

column8: abroad, abundantly, blossom, break forth out, bud, flourish, make fly, grow,
column9: A primitive root; to break forth as a bud, i.e. Bloom; generally, to spread; specifically, to fly (as extending the wings); figuratively, to flourish -- X abroad, X abundantly, blossom, break forth (out), bud, flourish, make fly, grow, spread, spring (up).
From (H6524) parach; a calyx (natural or artificial); generally, bloom -- blossom, bud, flower. see HEBREW (H6524) parach
From (H6524) parach; progeny, i.e. A brood -- youth. see HEBREW (H6524) parach
A primitive root; to scatter words, i.e. Prate (or hum) -- chant.
From (H6527) parat; a stray or single berry -- grape. see HEBREW (H6527) parat
From (H6509) parah; fruit (literally or figuratively) -- bough, ((first-)) fruit((-ful)), reward. see HEBREW (H6509) parah
From (H6555) parats; violent, i.e. A tyrant -- destroyer, ravenous, robber. see HEBREW (H6555) parats
From an unused root meaning to break apart; fracture, i.e. Severity -- cruelty, rigour.
Feminine active participle of the same as (H6531) perek; a separatrix, i.e. (the sacred) screen -- vail. see HEBREW (H6531) perek
A primitive root; to tear -- rend.
Of Persian origin; Parmashta, a son of Haman -- Parmasta.
Of uncertain derivation; Parnak, an Israelite -- Parnach.

column8: deal, divide, have hoofs, part, tear
column9: A primitive root; to break in pieces, i.e. (usually without violence) to split, distribute -- deal, divide, have hoofs, part, tear.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6536) parac; to split up -- divide, (U-)pharsin. see HEBREW (H6536) parac

column7: (a bird of prey) perhaps bearded vulture
column9: From (H6536) parac; a claw; also a kind of eagle -- claw, ossifrage. see HEBREW (H6536) parac

column7: a country in west Asia which conquered Bab
column9: Of foreign origin; Paras (i.e. Persia), an Eastern country, including its inhabitants -- Persia, Persians.

column7: a country in west Asia which conquered Bab
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H6539) Parac -- Persia, Persians. see HEBREW (H6539) Parac
Feminine of (H6538) perec; a claw or split hoof -- claw, (cloven-)footed, hoof. see HEBREW (H6538) perec
Patrial from (H6539) Parac; a Parsite (i.e. Persian), or inhabitant of Peres -- Persian. see HEBREW (H6539) Parac
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6542) Parciy -- Persian. see HEBREW (H6542) Parciy

column8: avenge, avoid, bare, go back, make naked, perish,
column9: A primitive root; to loosen; by implication, to expose, dismiss; figuratively, absolve, begin -- avenge, avoid, bare, go back, let, (make) naked, set at nought, perish, refuse, uncover.
From (H6544) para'; the hair (as dishevelled) -- locks. see HEBREW (H6544) para'
Feminine of (H6545) pera' (in the sense of beginning); leadership (plural concretely, leaders) -- + avenging, revenge. see HEBREW (H6545) pera'
Of Egyptian derivation; Paroh, a general title of Egyptian kings -- Pharaoh.
Of Egyptian derivation; Paroh- Chophra, an Egyptian king -- Pharaoh-hophra.
Or Parpoh Nkow {par-o' nek-o'}; of Egyptian derivation; Paroh-Nekoh (or -Neko), an Egyptian king:
Probably from (H6544) para' and (H6211) ash; a flea (as the isolated insect) -- flea. see HEBREW (H6544) para' see HEBREW (H6211) ash
The same as (H6550) par'osh; Parosh, the name of our Israelite -- Parosh, Pharosh. see HEBREW (H6550) par'osh
From (H6546) par'ah; chieftaincy; Pirathon, a place in Palestine -- Pirathon. see HEBREW (H6546) par'ah
Or Pirathoniy {pir-aw-tho-nee'}; patrial from (H6552) Pir'athown; a Pirathonite or inhabitant of Pirathon -- Pirathonite. see HEBREW (H6552) Pir'athown
Probably from (H6565) parar in the sense of rushing; rapid; Parpar, a river of Syria -- Pharpar. see HEBREW (H6565) parar

column8: abroad, make a breach, break away, down burst out, come spread abroad, compel, disperse, grow,
column9: A primitive root; to break out (in many applications, direct and indirect, literal and figurative) -- X abroad, (make a) breach, break (away, down, -er, forth, in, up), burst out, come (spread) abroad, compel, disperse, grow, increase, open, press, scatter, urge.

column8: breach, breaking forth in, forth, gap
column9: From (H6555) parats; a break (literally or figuratively) -- breach, breaking forth (in), X forth, gap. see HEBREW (H6555) parats
The same as (H6556) perets; Perets, the name of two Israelites -- Perez, Pharez. see HEBREW (H6556) perets
Patronymically from (H6557) Perets; a Partsite (collectively) or descendants of Perets -- Pharzites. see HEBREW (H6557) Perets
Plural of (H6556) perets; breaks; Peratsim, a mountain in Palestine -- Perazim. see HEBREW (H6556) perets
From (H6556) perets and (H5798) Uzza'; break of Uzza; Perets-Uzza, a place in Palestine -- Perez-uzza. see HEBREW (H6556) perets see HEBREW (H5798) Uzza'

column8: break off, deliver, redeem, rend in pieces, tear in pieces
column9: A primitive root; to break off or crunch; figuratively, to deliver -- break (off), deliver, redeem, rend (in pieces), tear in pieces.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6561) paraq; to discontinue -- break off. see HEBREW (H6561) paraq
From (H6561) paraq; rapine; also a fork (in roads) -- crossway, robbery. see HEBREW (H6561) paraq
From (H6561) paraq; soup (as full of crumbed meat) -- broth. See also (H4832) marpe'. see HEBREW (H6561) paraq see HEBREW (H4832) marpe'

column8: break asunder, cast off, cause to cease, clean, defeat, disannul, disappoint,
column9: A primitive root; to break up (usually figuratively, i.e. To violate, frustrate -- X any ways, break (asunder), cast off, cause to cease, X clean, defeat, disannul, disappoint, dissolve, divide, make of none effect, fail, frustrate, bring (come) to nought, X utterly, make void.

column8: break, chop in pieces, lay open, scatter, spread abroad, forth, selves, out,
column9: A primitive root; to break apart, disperse, etc. -- break, chop in pieces, lay open, scatter, spread (abroad, forth, selves, out), stretch (forth, out).
A primitive root; to separate, literally (to disperse) or figuratively (to specify); also (by implication) to wound -- scatter, declare, distinctly, shew, sting.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6567) parash; to specify -- distinctly. see HEBREW (H6567) parash
From (H6567) parash; excrement (as eliminated) -- dung. see HEBREW (H6567) parash
The same as (H6569) peresh; Peresh, an Israelite -- Peresh. see HEBREW (H6569) peresh

From (H6567) parash; a steed (as stretched out to a vehicle, not single nor for mounting (compare (H5483) cuwc)); also (by implication) a driver (in a chariot), i.e. (collectively) cavalry -- horseman. see HEBREW (H6567) parash see HEBREW (H5483) cuwc
Or pathshegen {path-sheh'-gen}; of foreign origin; a transcript -- copy.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6572) parshegen -- copy. see HEBREW (H6572) parshegen

Perhaps by compounding (H6567) parash and (H6504) parad (in the sense of straddling) (compare (H6576) parshez); the crotch (or anus) -- dirt. see HEBREW (H6567) parash see HEBREW (H6504) parad see HEBREW (H6576) parshez
From (H6567) parash; exposition -- declaration, sum. see HEBREW (H6567) parash
A root apparently formed by compounding (H6567) parash and that of (H6518) paraz (compare (H6574) parshdon); to expand -- spread. see HEBREW (H6567) parash see HEBREW (H6574) parshdon
Of Persian origin; Parshandatha, a son of Haman -- Parshandatha.
From an unused root meaning to break forth; rushing; Perath (i.e. Euphrates), a river of the East -- Euphrates.
Of Persian origin; a grandee -- (most) noble, prince.
Probably from an unused root meaning to disintegrate; stupidity (as a result of grossness or of degeneracy) -- extremity.
A primitive root; to spread -- spread.
A primitive root; to tear in pieces -- pull in pieces.
Probably from (H6582) pashach; liberation; Pashchur, the name of four Israelites -- Pashur. see HEBREW (H6582) pashach

column7: to strip off, make a dash, raid
column8: fall upon, flay, invade, make an invasion, pull off, put off, make a road, run upon,
column9: A primitive root; to spread out (i.e. Deploy in hostile array); by analogy, to strip (i.e. Unclothe, plunder, flay, etc.) -- fall upon, flay, invade, make an invasion, pull off, put off, make a road, run upon, rush, set, spoil, spread selves (abroad), strip (off, self).
A primitive root; to stride (from spreading the legs), i.e. Rush upon -- go.

A primitive root (identical with (H6585) pasa' through the idea of expansion); to break away (from just authority), i.e. Trespass, apostatize, quarrel -- offend, rebel, revolt, transgress(-ion, -or). see HEBREW (H6585) pasa'
From (H6585) pasa'; a stride -- step. see HEBREW (H6585) pasa'
From (H6586) pasha'; a revolt (national, moral or religious) -- rebellion, sin, transgression, trespass. see HEBREW (H6586) pasha'
A primitive root; to dispart (the feet or lips), i.e. Become licentious -- open (wide).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6622) pathar; to interpret -- make (interpretations), interpreting. see HEBREW (H6622) pathar
(Aramaic) from (H6590) pshar; an interpretation -- interpretation. see HEBREW (H6590) pshar
Corresponding to (H6591) pshar -- interpretation. see HEBREW (H6591) pshar
From the same as (H6580) pash as in the sense of comminuting; linen (i.e. The thread, as carded) -- flax, linen. see HEBREW (H6580) pash
Feminine of (H6593) pishteh; flax; by implication, a wick -- flax, tow. see HEBREW (H6593) pishteh
From (H6626) pathath; a bit -- meat, morsel, piece. see HEBREW (H6626) pathath
Or pothah (Ezek. 13:19) {po-thaw'}; from an unused root meaning to open; a hole, i.e. Hinge or the female pudenda -- hinge, secret participle
Or pith.om {pith-ome'}; from (H6621) petha'; instantly -- straightway, sudden(-ly). see HEBREW (H6621) petha'
Of Persian origin; a dainty -- portion (provision) of meat.
Of Persian origin; a (judicial) sentence -- decree, sentence.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6599) pithgam; a word, answer, letter or decree -- answer, letter, matter, word. see HEBREW (H6599) pithgam

column7: to be spacious, wide or open
column8: allure, deceive, enlarge, entice, flatter, persuade, silly one
column9: A primitive root; to open, i.e. Be (causatively, make) roomy; usually figuratively (in a mental or moral sense) to be (causatively, make) simple or (in a sinister way) delude -- allure, deceive, enlarge, entice, flatter, persuade, silly (one).
From (H6601) pathah and (H410) 'el; enlarged of God; Pethuel, an Israelite -- Pethuel. see HEBREW (H6601) pathah see HEBREW (H410) 'el
Or pittuach {pit-too'-akh; passive participle of (H6605) pathach; sculpture (in low or high relief or even intaglio) -- carved (work) (are, en-)grave(-ing, -n). see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
Of foreign origin; Pethor, a place in Mesopotamia -- Pethor.

column8: appear, break forth, draw out, let go free, engrave, loose self, be, be set opening,
column9: A primitive root; to open wide (literally or figuratively); specifically, to loosen, begin, plough, carve -- appear, break forth, draw (out), let go free, (en-)grave(-n), loose (self), (be, be set) open(-ing), put off, ungird, unstop, have vent.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6605) pathach; to open -- open. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach

column8: door, entering in, entrance ry, gate, opening, place
column9: From (H6605) pathach; an opening (literally), i.e. Door (gate) or entrance way -- door, entering (in), entrance (-ry), gate, opening, place. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
From (H6605) pathach; opening (figuratively) i.e. Disclosure -- entrance. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
From (H6605) pathach; something opened, i.e. A drawn sword -- drawn sword. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
From (H6605) pathach; opening (the act) -- open(-ing). see HEBREW (H6605) pathach
From (H6605) pathach and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has opened; Pethachjah, the name of four Israelites -- Pethakiah. see HEBREW (H6605) pathach see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Or pethiy {peh'-thee}; or pthaeiy {peth-aw-ee'}; from (H6601) pathah; silly (i.e. Seducible) -- foolish, simple(-icity, one). see HEBREW (H6601) pathah
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H6601) pathah; open, i.e. (as noun) width -- breadth. see HEBREW (H6601) pathah
Of uncertain derivation; probably a figured mantle for holidays -- stomacher.
From (H6612) pthiy; silliness (i.e. Seducibility) -- simple. see HEBREW (H6612) pthiy

column8: bound, bracelet, lace, line, ribbon, thread, wire

From (H6617) pathal; tortuous (i.e. Crafty) -- crooked. see HEBREW (H6617) pathal
Of Egyptian derivation; Pithom, a place in Egypt -- Pithom.
From an unused root meaning to twist; an asp (from its contortions) -- adder.

A primitive root; to open up, i.e. (figuratively) interpret (a dream) -- interpret(-ation, -er).
Or pithron {pith-rone'}; from (H6622) pathar; interpretation (of a dream) -- interpretation. see HEBREW (H6622) pathar
Of Egyptian derivation; Pathros, a part of Egypt -- Pathros.

column7: a tribe, desc. from Mizraim, which inhab. S. Eg
column9: Patrial from (H6624) Pathrowc; a Pathrusite, or inhabitant of Pathros -- Pathrusim. see HEBREW (H6624) Pathrowc
A primitive root; to open, i.e. Break -- participle
From (H3318) yatsa'; issue, i.e. (human) excrement -- that (which) cometh from (out). see HEBREW (H3318) yatsa'
From an unused root meaning to be slender; the lotus tree -- shady tree.

column7: small cattle, sheep and goats, flock

column7: a place perhaps in the Shephelah of Judah
column9: From the same as (H6629) tso'n used denominatively; sheep pasture; Zaanan, a place in Palestine -- Zaanan. see HEBREW (H6629) tso'n

column9: From (H3318) yatsa'; issue, i.e. Produce, children -- that which cometh forth (out), offspring. see HEBREW (H3318) yatsa'
From an unused root meaning to establish; a palanquin or canopy (as a fixture); also a species of lizard (probably as clinging fast) -- covered, litter, tortoise.

column8: assemble, fight, perform, muster, wait upon, war
column9: A primitive root; to mass (an army or servants) -- assemble, fight, perform, muster, wait upon, war.

column7: to be inclined, desire, be pleased
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H6623) pithrown in the figurative sense of summoning one's wishes; to please -- will, would. see HEBREW (H6623) pithrown
