Or (more correctly) Tsbiyiym {tseb-ee-yeem'}; or Tsbiyim {tseb-ee-yeem'}; plural of (H6643) tsbiy; gazelles; Tseboim or Tsebijim, a place in Palestine -- Zeboiim, Zeboim. see HEBREW (H6643) tsbiy
Feminine active participle of the same as (H6632) tsab; the canopier (with the article); Tsobebah, an Israelitess -- Zobebah. see HEBREW (H6632) tsab
A primitive root; to amass, i.e. Grow turgid; specifically, to array an army against -- fight swell.
From (H6638) tsabah; turgid -- swell. see HEBREW (H6638) tsabah
(Aramaic) from (H6634) tsba'; properly, will; concretely, an affair (as a matter of determination) -- purpose. see HEBREW (H6634) tsba'
Passive participle of the same as (H6648) tseba'; dyed (in stripes), i.e. The hyena -- speckled. see HEBREW (H6648) tseba'
A primitive root; to grasp, i.e. Hand out -- reach.
From (H6638) tsabah in the sense of prominence; splendor (as conspicuous); also a gazelle (as beautiful) -- beautiful(-ty), glorious, goodly, pleasant, roe(-buck). see HEBREW (H6638) tsabah
For (H6645) Tsibyah; Tsibja, an Israelite -- Zibia. see HEBREW (H6645) Tsibyah
For (H6646) tsbiyah; Tsibjah, an Israelitess -- Zibiah. see HEBREW (H6646) tsbiyah
Feminine of (H6643) tsbiy; a female gazelle -- roe. see HEBREW (H6643) tsbiy
(Aramaic) a root corresponding to that of (H6648) tseba'; to dip -- wet. see HEBREW (H6648) tseba'
From an unused root meaning to dip (into coloring fluid); a dye -- divers, colours.
From the same as (H6648) tseba'; variegated; Tsibon, an Idumaean -- Zibeon. see HEBREW (H6648) tseba'

column7: a place probably at S. end of the Dead Sea
column9: Plural of (H6641) tsabuwa'; hyenas; Tseboim, a place in Palestine -- Zeboim. see HEBREW (H6641) tsabuwa'

column8: gather together, heap up, lay up
column9: A primitive root; to aggregate -- gather (together), heap (up), lay up.
From (H6551) Par'osh; a pile -- heap. see HEBREW (H6551) Par'osh
From an unused root apparently meaning to grip; a lock of stalks -- handful.
Contr. From an unused root meaning to sidle off; a side; figuratively, an adversary -- (be-)side.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6654) tsad; used adverbially (with preposition) at or upon the side of -- against, concerning. see HEBREW (H6654) tsad
(Aramaic) from an unused root corresponding to (H6658) tsadah in the sense of intentness; a (sinister) design -- true. see HEBREW (H6658) tsadah

column7: a place on the N. border of Canaan
column9: From the same as (H6654) tsad; a siding; Tsedad, a place near Palestine -- Zedad. see HEBREW (H6654) tsad
A primitive root; to chase; by implication, to desolate -- destroy, hunt, lie in wait.
From (H6663) tsadaq; just; Tsadok, the name of eight or nine Israelites -- Zadok. see HEBREW (H6663) tsadaq
From (H6658) tsadah; design (compare (H6656) tsda') -- lying in wait. see HEBREW (H6658) tsadah see HEBREW (H6656) tsda'
Plural of (H6654) tsad; sides; Tsiddim (with the article), a place in Palestine -- Ziddim. see HEBREW (H6654) tsad
From (H6663) tsadaq; just -- just, lawful, righteous (man). see HEBREW (H6663) tsadaq

column8: cleanse, clear self, be, do justice be turn to righteousness
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, make) right (in a moral or forensic sense) -- cleanse, clear self, (be, do) just(-ice, -ify, -ify self), (be turn to) righteous(-ness).

From (H6663) tsadaq; the right (natural, moral or legal); also (abstractly) equity or (figuratively) prosperity -- X even, (X that which is altogether) just(-ice), ((un-))right(-eous) (cause, -ly, - ness). see HEBREW (H6663) tsadaq
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6666) tsdaqah; beneficence -- righteousness. see HEBREW (H6666) tsdaqah

From (H6663) tsadaq; rightness (abstractly), subjectively (rectitude), objectively (justice), morally (virtue) or figuratively (prosperity) -- justice, moderately, right(-eous) (act, -ly,-ness). see HEBREW (H6663) tsadaq
Or Tsidqiyahuw {tsid-kee-yaw'-hoo}; from (H6664) tsedeq and (H3050) Yahh; right of Jah; Tsidkijah, the name of six Israelites -- Zedekiah, Zidkijah. see HEBREW (H6664) tsedeq see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
A primitive root; to glitter, i.e. Be golden in color -- X fine.
From (H6668) tsahab; golden in color -- yellow. see HEBREW (H6668) tsahab

column8: bellow, cry aloud out, lift up, neigh, rejoice, make to shine, shout
column9: A prim root; to gleam, i.e. (figuratively) be cheerful; by transf. To sound clear (of various animal or human expressions) -- bellow, cry aloud (out), lift up, neigh, rejoice, make to shine, shout.
A primitive root; to glisten; used only as denominative from (H3323) yitshar, to press out oil -- make oil. see HEBREW (H3323) yitshar
From (H6671) tsahar; a light (i.e. Window): dual double light, i.e. Noon -- midday, noon(-day, -tide), window. see HEBREW (H6671) tsahar
Or tsav {tsawv}; from (H6680) tsavah; an injunction -- commandment, precept. see HEBREW (H6680) tsavah
Or tsov {tso}; from an unused root meaning to issue; soiled (as if excrementitious) -- filthy.

Or tsovah {tso-aw'}: feminine of (H6674) tsow'; excrement; generally, dirt; figuratively, pollution -- dung, filth(-iness). Marg. For (H2716) chere'. see HEBREW (H6674) tsow' see HEBREW (H2716) chere'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6677) tsavva'r -- neck. see HEBREW (H6677) tsavva'r

Or tsavvar (Nehemiah 3:5) {tsav-vawr'}; or tsavvaron (Song of Solomon 4:9) {tsav-vaw-rone'}; or (feminine) tsavva.rah (Micah 2:3) {tsav-vaw-raw'}; intensively from (H6696) tsuwr in the sense of binding; the back of the neck (as that on which burdens are bound) -- neck. see HEBREW (H6696) tsuwr
Or Tsowbah {tso-baw'}; or Tsobah {tso-baw'}; from an unused root meaning to station; a station; Zoba or Zobah, a region of Syria -- Zoba, Zobah.

A primitive root; to lie alongside (i.e. In wait); by implication, to catch an animal (figuratively, men); (denominative from (H6718) tsayid) to victual (for a journey) -- chase, hunt, sore, take (provision). see HEBREW (H6718) tsayid

column7: to lay charge (upon), give charge (to), command, order
column8: appoint, forbid, give a charge, give a, give in, send with commander send a messenger, put, set in order
column9: A primitive root; (intensively) to constitute, enjoin -- appoint, (for-)bid, (give a) charge, (give a, give in, send with) command(-er, -ment), send a messenger, put, (set) in order.
A primitive root; to screech (exultingly) -- shout.
From (H6681) tsavach; a screech (of anguish) -- cry(-ing). see HEBREW (H6681) tsavach
From an unused root meaning to sink: an abyss (of the sea) -- deep.
A primitive root; to cover over (the mouth), i.e. To fast -- X at all, fast.
Or tsom {tsome}; from from (H6684) tsuwm; a fast -- fast(-ing). see HEBREW (H6684) tsuwm

column7: little one, a man of Issachar
column9: From (H6819) tsa'ar; small; Tsuar, an Israelite -- Zuar. see HEBREW (H6819) tsa'ar
A primitive root; to overflow -- (make to over-)flow, swim.
From (H6687) tsuwph; comb of honey (from dripping) -- honeycomb. see HEBREW (H6687) tsuwph

column4: noun masculine; Adjective, of a people
column9: Or Tsowphay {tso-fah'-ee}; or Tsiyph {tseef}; from (H6688) tsuwph; honey-comb; Tsuph or Tsophai or Tsiph, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine -- Zophai, Zuph. see HEBREW (H6688) tsuwph
From an unused root meaning to expand, breadth; Tsophach, an Israelite -- Zophah.
From (H6852) tsaphar; departing; Tsophar, a friend of Job -- Zophar. see HEBREW (H6852) tsaphar
A primitive root; to twinkle, i.e. Glance; by analogy, to blossom (figuratively, flourish) -- bloom, blossom, flourish, shew self.

column7: to constrain, bring into straits, press upon
column8: constrain, distress, lie sore, oppressor, straiten
column9: A primitive root; to compress, i.e. (figuratively) oppress, distress -- constrain, distress, lie sore, (op-)press(-or), straiten.
A primitive root (identical with (H6693) tsuwq through the idea of narrowness (of orifice)); to pour out, i.e. (figuratively) smelt, utter -- be molten, pour. see HEBREW (H6693) tsuwq
Or (feminine) tsuwqah {tsoo-kaw'}; from (H6693) tsuwq; a strait, i.e. (figuratively) distress -- anguish, X troublous. see HEBREW (H6693) tsuwq

column8: adversary, assault, beset, besiege, bind up, cast, distress, fashion,
column9: A primitive root; to cramp, i.e. Confine (in many applications, literally and figuratively, formative or hostile) -- adversary, assault, beset, besiege, bind (up), cast, distress, fashion, fortify, inclose, lay siege, put up in bags.

column8: edge, mighty God one, rock, sharp, stone, strength, strong
column9: Or tsur {tsoor}; from (H6696) tsuwr; properly, a cliff (or sharp rock, as compressed); generally, a rock or boulder; figuratively, a refuge; also an edge (as precipitous) -- edge, X (mighty) God (one), rock, X sharp, stone, X strength, X strong. See also (H1049) Beyth Tsuwr. see HEBREW (H6696) tsuwr see HEBREW (H1049) Beyth Tsuwr

column7: rock, a Midianite, also a Gibeonite

column7: a city assigned to Judah, also to Simeon

From an unused root meaning to wind; a sack (as tied at the mouth) -- husk.

column8: adversary, affliction, anguish, close, distress, enemy, flint, foe,
column9: Or tsar {tsawr}; from (H6887) tsarar; narrow; (as a noun) a tight place (usually figuratively, i.e. Trouble); also a pebble (as in (H6864) tsor); (transitive) an opponent (as crowding) -- adversary, afflicted(-tion), anguish, close, distress, enemy, flint, foe, narrow, small, sorrow, strait, tribulation, trouble. see HEBREW (H6887) tsarar see HEBREW (H6864) tsor

column8: rock; Tser, a place in Palestine
column9: From (H6887) tsarar; rock; Tser, a place in Palestine -- Zer. see HEBREW (H6887) tsarar
From (H6696) tsuwr; a stone (as if pressed hard or to a point); (by implication, of use) a knife -- flint, sharp stone. see HEBREW (H6696) tsuwr
Or Tsowr {tsore}; the same as (H6864) tsor; a rock; Tsor, a place in Palestine -- Tyre, Tyrus. see HEBREW (H6864) tsor
A primitive root; to burn -- burn.
From (H6686) Tsaw'ar; conflagration (of fire or disease) -- burning, inflammation. see HEBREW (H6686) Tsaw'ar
Or Tsredathah {tser-ay-daw'-thaw}; apparently from an unused root meaning to pierce; puncture; Tseredah, a place in Palestine -- Zereda, Zeredathah.

column8: adversary, adversity, affliction, anguish, distress, tribulation, trouble
column9: Feminine of (H6862) tsar; tightness (i.e. Figuratively, trouble); transitively, a female rival -- adversary, adversity, affliction, anguish, distress, tribulation, trouble. see HEBREW (H6862) tsar
Feminine passive participle from the same as (H6875) tsriy; wounded; Tserujah, an Israelitess -- Zeruiah. see HEBREW (H6875) tsriy
Feminine passive participle of (H6879) tsara'; leprous; Tseruah, an Israelitess -- Zeruah. see HEBREW (H6879) tsara'

column8: bag, bendeth, bundle, least grain, small stone
column9: Or (shorter) tsror {tser-ore'}; from (H6887) tsarar; a parcel (as packed up); also a kernel or particle (as if a package) -- bag, X bendeth, bundle, least grain, small stone. see HEBREW (H6887) tsarar
A primitive root; to be clear (in tone, i.e. Shrill), i.e. To whoop -- cry, roar.
The same as (H6875) tsriy; Tseri, an Israelite -- Zeri. Compare (H3340) Yitsriy. see HEBREW (H6875) tsriy see HEBREW (H3340) Yitsriy
Or tsoriy {tsor-ee'}; from an unused root meaning to crack (as by pressure), hence, to leak; distillation, i.e. Balsam -- balm.
Patrial from (H6865) Tsor; a Tsorite or inhabitant of Tsor (i.e. Syrian) -- (man) of Tyre. see HEBREW (H6865) Tsor
From (H6873) tsarach in the sense of clearness of vision; a citadel -- high place, hold. see HEBREW (H6873) tsarach
From an unused root meaning to need; need -- need.

column7: to be struck with leprosy, to be leprous
column9: A primitive root; to scourge, i.e. (intransitive and figurative) to be stricken with leprosy -- leper, leprous.
From (H6879) tsara'; a wasp (as stinging) -- hornet. see HEBREW (H6879) tsara'

column7: a city exchanged by Judah and Dan
column9: Apparently another form for (H6880) tsir'ah; Tsorah, a place in Palestine -- Zareah, Zorah, Zoreah. see HEBREW (H6880) tsir'ah
Or Tsortathiy {tsor-aw-thee'}; patrial from (H6881) Tsor'ah; a Tsorite or Tsorathite, i.e. Inhabitants of Tsorah -- Zorites, Zareathites, Zorathites. see HEBREW (H6881) Tsor'ah
From (H6879) tsara'; leprosy -- leprosy. see HEBREW (H6879) tsara'

column8: cast, refiner, founder, goldsmith, melt, pure, purge away, try
column9: A primitive root; to fuse (metal), i.e. Refine (literally or figuratively) -- cast, (re-)fine(-er), founder, goldsmith, melt, pure, purge away, try.
From (H6884) tsaraph; refiner; Tsorephi (with the article), an Israelite -- goldsmith's. see HEBREW (H6884) tsaraph

column7: smelting place, a city South of Sidon
column9: From (H6884) tsaraph; refinement; Tsarephath, a place in Palestine -- Zarephath. see HEBREW (H6884) tsaraph

column7: to bind, tie up, be restricted, narrow, scant, or cramped
column8: adversary, be in affliction, besiege, bind up, be in, bring distress, narrower,
column9: A primitive root; to cramp, literally or figuratively, transitive or intransitive (as follows) -- adversary, (be in) afflict(-ion), beseige, bind (up), (be in, bring) distress, enemy, narrower, oppress, pangs, shut up, be in a strait (trouble), vex.

column7: a city toward which Gideon\'s enemies fled
column9: Apparently by erroneous transcription for (H6868) Tsredah; Tsererah for Tseredah -- Zererath. see HEBREW (H6868) Tsredah
Perhaps from (H6671) tsahar; splendor; Tsereth, an Israelite -- Zereth. see HEBREW (H6671) tsahar

column7: Zereth of the dawn, a city in Reuben
column9: From the same as (H6889) Tsereth and (H7837) shachar with the article interposed; splendor of the dawn; Tsereth-hash-Shachar, a place in Palestine -- Zareth-shahar. see HEBREW (H6889) Tsereth see HEBREW (H7837) shachar

column7: a city in the Jordan Valley
column9: Perhaps for (H6868) Tsredah; Tsarethan, a place in Palestine -- Zarthan. see HEBREW (H6868) Tsredah
Or qiys {kee}; from (H6958) qow'; vomit -- vomit. see HEBREW (H6958) qow'
From (H6958) qow'; probably the pelican (from vomiting) -- cormorant. see HEBREW (H6958) qow'
From (H6895) qabab; a hollow, i.e. Vessel used as a (dry) measure -- cab. see HEBREW (H6895) qabab

column7: to utter a curse against, curse
column9: A primitive root; to scoop out, i.e. (figuratively) to malign or execrate (i.e. Stab with words) -- X at all, curse.
From (H6895) qabab; the paunch (as a cavity) or first stomach of ruminants -- maw. see HEBREW (H6895) qabab
From (H6895) qabab; the abdomen (as a cavity) -- belly. see HEBREW (H6895) qabab
From (H6895) qabab; a pavilion (as a domed cavity) -- tent. see HEBREW (H6895) qabab
From (H6908) qabats; a throng -- company. see HEBREW (H6908) qabats
Or qburah {keb-oo-raw'}; feminine passive participle of (H6912) qabar; sepulture; (concretely) a sepulchre -- burial, burying place, grave, sepulchre. see HEBREW (H6912) qabar
A primitive root; to admit, i.e. Take (literally or figuratively) -- choose, (take) hold, receive, (under-)take.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6901) qabal; to acquire -- receive, take. see HEBREW (H6901) qabal

column4: substantive; preposition; conjunction; conjunction; preposition; conjunction
column7: in front of, before, because of, because that
column8: according to, as, because, before, for this cause, forasmuch as
column9: (Aramaic) or qobel (Aramaic) {kob-ale'}; (corresponding to (H6905) qabal; (adverbially) in front of; usually (with other particles) on account of, so as, since, hence -- + according to, + as, + because, before, + for this cause, + forasmuch as, + by this means, over against, by reason of, + that, + therefore, + though, + wherefore. see HEBREW (H6905) qabal

column7: something in front, a military siege engine
column9: From (H6901) qabal in the sense of confronting (as standing opposite in order to receive); a battering-ram -- war. see HEBREW (H6901) qabal
From (H6901) qabal in the sense of opposite (see (H6904) qobel); the presence, i.e. (adverbially) in front of -- before. see HEBREW (H6901) qabal see HEBREW (H6904) qobel
A primitive root; to cover, i.e. (figuratively) defraud -- rob, spoil.
From (H6906) qaba'; a goblet (as deep like a cover) -- dregs. see HEBREW (H6906) qaba'

column8: assemble selves, gather bring together, heap
column9: A primitive root; to grasp, i.e. Collect -- assemble (selves), gather (bring) (together, selves together, up), heap, resort, X surely, take up.

column7: God gathers, a city in S. Judah
column9: From (H6908) qabats and (H410) 'el; God has gathered; Kabtseel, a place in Palestine -- Kabzeel. Compare (H3343) Yqabts'el. see HEBREW (H6908) qabats see HEBREW (H410) 'el see HEBREW (H3343) Yqabts'el
Feminine passive participle of (H6908) qabats; a hoard -- X gather. see HEBREW (H6908) qabats

column7: two heaps, a city in Ephraim
column9: Dual from (H6908) qabats; a double heap; Kibtsajim, a place in Palestine -- Kibzaim. see HEBREW (H6908) qabats
A primitive root; to inter -- X in any wise, bury(-ier).
Or (feminine) qibrah {kib-raw'}; from (H6912) qabar; a sepulchre -- burying place, grave, sepulchre. see HEBREW (H6912) qabar

column7: the graves of desire, a place in the desert
column9: From the feminine plural of (H6913) qeber, and (H8378) ta'avah with the article interposed; graves of the longing; Kibroth-hat-Taavh, a place in the Desert -- Kibroth-hattaavah. see HEBREW (H6913) qeber, see HEBREW (H8378) ta'avah
A primitive root; to shrivel up, i.e. Contract or bend the body (or neck) in deference -- bow (down) (the) head, stoop.
From (H6915) qadad; cassia bark (as in shrivelled rolls) -- cassia. see HEBREW (H6915) qadad
Passive participle of (H6923) qadam; a pristine hero -- ancient. see HEBREW (H6923) qadam
Or qadosh {kaw-doshe'}; from (H6942) qadash; sacred (ceremonially or morally); (as noun) God (by eminence), an angel, a saint, a sanctuary -- holy (One), saint. see HEBREW (H6942) qadash
A primitive root to inflame -- burn, kindle.
From (H6919) qadach; inflammation, i.e. Febrile disease -- burning ague, fever. see HEBREW (H6919) qadach

Or qadim {kaw-deem'}; from (H6923) qadam; the fore or front part; hence (by orientation) the East (often adverbially, eastward, for brevity the east wind) -- east(-ward, wind). see HEBREW (H6923) qadam
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6918) qadowsh. --holy (One), saint. see HEBREW (H6918) qadowsh

column7: to come or be in front, meet
column8: go, flee before, disappoint, meet, prevent
column9: A primitive root; to project (one self), i.e. Precede; hence, to anticipate, hasten, meet (usually for help) -- come (go, (flee)) before, + disappoint, meet, prevent.

column8: aforetime, ancient time, before, east end, part, side eternal, everlasting, forward,
column9: Or qedmah {kayd'-maw}; from (H6923) qadam; the front, of place (absolutely, the fore part, relatively the East) or time (antiquity); often used adverbially (before, anciently, eastward) -- aforetime, ancient (time), before, east (end, part, side, -ward), eternal, X ever(-lasting), forward, old, past. Compare (H6926) qidmah. see HEBREW (H6923) qadam see HEBREW (H6926) qidmah

column8: before, from, I thought, me, of, it pleased, presence
column9: (Aramaic) or qdam (Aramaic) (Daniel 7:13) {ked-awm'}; corresponding to (H6924) qedem; before -- before, X from, X I (thought), X me, + of, X it pleased, presence. see HEBREW (H13) 'obdan see HEBREW (H6924) qedem
Feminine of (H6924) qedem; the forward part (or relatively) East (often adverbially, on the east or in front) -- east(-ward). see HEBREW (H6924) qedem
From (H6923) qadam; priority (in time); also used adverbially (before) -- afore, antiquity, former (old) estate. see HEBREW (H6923) qadam
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6927) qadmah; former time -- afore(-time), ago. see HEBREW (H6927) qadmah
From (H6923) qadam; precedence; Kedemah, a son of Ishmael -- Kedemah. see HEBREW (H6923) qadam
From (H6923) qadam; eastern -- east. see HEBREW (H6923) qadam

column8: ancient, they that went before, east, thing of old
column9: Or qadmoniy {kad-mo-nee'}; from (H6930) qadmown; (of time) anterior or (of place) oriental -- ancient, they that went before, east, (thing of) old. see HEBREW (H6930) qadmown
From (H6923) qadam; beginnings; Kedemoth, a place in eastern Palestine -- Kedemoth. see HEBREW (H6923) qadam
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H6923) qadam; first -- first. see HEBREW (H6923) qadam

column7: God is the ancient one, a Levite name
column9: From (H6924) qedem and (H410) 'el; presence of God; Kadmiel, the name of three Israelites -- Kadmiel. see HEBREW (H6924) qedem see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: easterners, a tribe whose land Abraham was to inherit
column9: The same as (H6931) qadmowniy; ancient, i.e. Aboriginal; Kadmonite (collectively), the name of a tribe in Palestine -- Kadmonites. see HEBREW (H6931) qadmowniy

column8: crown of the head, pate, scalp, top of the head
column9: From (H6915) qadad; the crown of the head (as the part most bowed) -- crown (of the head), pate, scalp, top of the head. see HEBREW (H6915) qadad

column8: be blackish, be make darken, heavily, cause to mourn
column9: A primitive root; to be ashy, i.e. Dark-colored; by implication, to mourn (in sackcloth or sordid garments) -- be black(-ish), be (make) dark(-en), X heavily, (cause to) mourn.

column7: perhaps "swarthy", a son of Ishmael, also his desc
column9: From (H6937) qadar; dusky (of the skin or the tent); Kedar, a son of Ishmael; also (collectively) Bedouin (as his descendants or representatives) -- Kedar. see HEBREW (H6937) qadar

column7: perhaps "dusky", a wadi East of Jer
column9: From (H6937) qadar; dusky place; Kidron, a brook near Jerusalem -- Kidron. see HEBREW (H6937) qadar
From (H6937) qadar; duskiness -- blackness. see HEBREW (H6937) qadar
Adverb from (H6937) qadar; blackish ones (i.e. In sackcloth); used adverbially, in mourning weeds -- mournfully. see HEBREW (H6937) qadar

column7: to be set apart or consecrated
column8: appoint, bid, consecrate, dedicate, defile, hallow, be holy,
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, make, pronounce or observe as) clean (ceremonially or morally) -- appoint, bid, consecrate, dedicate, defile, hallow, (be, keep) holy(-er, place), keep, prepare, proclaim, purify, sanctify(-ied one, self), X wholly.

column7: sanctuary, the name of several places in Isr
column9: From (H6942) qadash; a sanctum; Kedesh, the name of four places in Palestine -- Kedesh. see HEBREW (H6942) qadash

column8: consecrated thing, dedicated thing, hallowed thing, holiness, most holy day, portion, thing, saint,
column9: From (H6942) qadash; a sacred place or thing; rarely abstract, sanctity -- consecrated (thing), dedicated (thing), hallowed (thing), holiness, (X most) holy (X day, portion, thing), saint, sanctuary. see HEBREW (H6942) qadash
From (H6942) qadash; a (quasi) sacred person, i.e. (technically) a (male) devotee (by prostitution) to licentious idolatry -- sodomite, unclean. see HEBREW (H6942) qadash

column7: sacred, a place in the desert
column9: The same as (H6945) qadesh; sanctuary; Kadesh, a place in the Desert -- Kadesh. Compare (H6947) Qadesh Barnea'. see HEBREW (H6945) qadesh see HEBREW (H6947) Qadesh Barnea'

From the same as (H6946) Qadesh and an otherwise unused word (apparently compounded of a correspondent to (H1251) bar and a derivative of (H5128) nuwa') meaning desert of a fugitive; Kadesh of (the) Wilderness of Wandering; Kadesh-Barnea, a place in the Desert -- Kadesh-barnea. see HEBREW (H6946) Qadesh see HEBREW (H1251) bar see HEBREW (H5128) nuwa'
Feminine of (H6945) qadesh; a female devotee (i.e. Prostitute) -- harlot, whore. see HEBREW (H6945) qadesh

column8: be set on edge, be blunt
column9: A primitive root; to be dull -- be set on edge, be blunt.

column7: to gather as an assembly or congregation
column8: assemble selves together, gather selves together
column9: A primitive root; to convoke -- assemble (selves) (together), gather (selves) (together).
From (H6950) qahal; assemblage (usually concretely) -- assembly, company, congregation, multitude. see HEBREW (H6950) qahal
From (H6950) qahal; an assemblage -- assembly, congregation. see HEBREW (H6950) qahal

column7: a collector (of sentences), "a preacher", a son of David
column9: Feminine of active participle from (H6950) qahal; a (female) assembler (i.e. Lecturer): abstractly, preaching (used as a \"nom de plume\", Koheleth) -- preacher. see HEBREW (H6950) qahal

column7: assembly, a place in the desert
column9: From (H6950) qahal; convocation; Kehelathah, a place in the Desert -- Kehelathah. see HEBREW (H6950) qahal
From an unused root meaning to ally oneself; allied; Kehath, an Israelite -- Kohath.
Patronymically from (H6955) Qhath; a Kohathite (collectively) or descendants of Kehath -- Kohathites. see HEBREW (H6955) Qhath

Or qav {kawv}; from (H6960) qavah (compare (H6961) qaveh); a cord (as connecting), especially for measuring; figuratively, a rule; also a rim, a musical string or accord -- line. Compare (H6978) qav-qav. see HEBREW (H6960) qavah see HEBREW (H6961) qaveh see HEBREW (H6978) qav-qav

column7: spue out, vomit out, up, up again
column8: spue out, vomit out, up, up again
column9: Or qayah (Jer. 25:27) {kaw-yaw'}; a primitive root; to vomit -- spue (out), vomit (out, up, up again).
A form collateral to (H3553) kowba'; a helmet -- helmet. see HEBREW (H3553) kowba'

column8: gather together, look, patiently, tarry, wait for, on, upon
column9: A primitive root; to bind together (perhaps by twisting), i.e. Collect; (figuratively) to expect -- gather (together), look, patiently, tarry, wait (for, on, upon).
From (H6960) qavah; a (measuring) cord (as if for binding) -- line. see HEBREW (H6960) qavah
A primitive root; properly, to cut off, i.e. (figuratively) detest -- begrieved, loathe self.

column8: aloud, bleating, crackling, cry out, fame, lightness, lowing, noise,
column9: Or qol {kole}; from an unused root meaning to call aloud; a voice or sound -- + aloud, bleating, crackling, cry (+ out), fame, lightness, lowing, noise, + hold peace, (pro-)claim, proclamation, + sing, sound, + spark, thunder(-ing), voice, + yell.
From (H6963) qowl and (H3050) Yahh; voice of Jah; Kolajah, the name of two Israelites -- Kolaiah. see HEBREW (H6963) qowl see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

A primitive root; to rise (in various applications, literal, figurative, intensive and causative) -- abide, accomplish, X be clearer, confirm, continue, decree, X be dim, endure, X enemy, enjoin, get up, make good, help, hold, (help to) lift up (again), make, X but newly, ordain, perform, pitch, raise (up), rear (up), remain, (a-)rise (up) (again, against), rouse up, set (up), (e-)stablish, (make to) stand (up), stir up, strengthen, succeed, (as-, make) sure(-ly), (be) up(-hold, - rising).

column8: appoint, establish, make, raise up self, arise up, make to stand, set up
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H6965) quwm -- appoint, establish, make, raise up self, (a-)rise (up), (make to) stand, set (up). see HEBREW (H6965) quwm
From (H6965) quwm; height -- X along, height, high, stature, tall. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm
From (H6965) quwm; elevation, i.e. (adverbially) erectly (figuratively): upright. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm

column7: to chant an elegy or dirge
column9: A primitive root; to strike a musical note, i.e. Chant or wail (at a funeral) -- lament, mourning woman.
Probably from (H6972) quwts in the original sense of cutting off; curtailment; Koa, a region of Bab. -- Koa. see HEBREW (H6972) quwts
Or qoph {kofe}; probably of foreign origin; a monkey -- ape.
A primitive root; to clip off; used only as denominative from (H7019) qayits; to spend the harvest season -- summer. see HEBREW (H7019) qayits

column7: to feel a loathing, abhorrence, or sickening dread
column8: abhor, be distressed, be grieved, loathe, vex, be weary
column9: A primitive root (identical with (H6972) quwts through the idea of severing oneself from (compare (H6962) quwt)); to be (causatively, make) disgusted or anxious -- abhor, be distressed, be grieved, loathe, vex, be weary. see HEBREW (H6972) quwts see HEBREW (H6962) quwt

A primitive root (identical with (H6972) quwts through the idea of abruptness in starting up from sleep (compare (H3364) yaqats)); to awake (literally or figuratively) -- arise, (be) (a-)wake, watch. see HEBREW (H6972) quwts see HEBREW (H3364) yaqats
Or qots {kotse}; from (H6972) quwts (in the sense of pricking); a thorn -- thorn. see HEBREW (H6972) quwts
The same as (H6975) qowts; Kots, the name of two Israelites -- Koz, Hakkoz (including the article). see HEBREW (H6975) qowts
Feminine passive participle of (H6972) quwts in its original sense; a forelock (as shorn) -- lock. see HEBREW (H6972) quwts
From (H6957) qav (in the sense of a fastening); stalwart -- X meted out. see HEBREW (H6957) qav

column8: break down, cast out, destroy, dig
column9: A primitive root; to trench; by implication, to throw forth; also (denominative from (H7023) qiyr) to wall up, whether literal (to build a wall) or figurative (to estop) -- break down, cast out, destroy, dig. see HEBREW (H7023) qiyr
From (H6979) quwr; (only plural) trenches, i.e. A web (as if so formed) -- web. see HEBREW (H6979) quwr
Or Qore (1 Chronicles 26:1) {ko-ray'}; active participle of (H7121) qara'; crier; Kore, the name of two Israelites -- Kore. see HEBREW (H7121) qara'
Or qorah {ko-raw'}; from (H6979) quwr; a rafter (forming trenches as it were); by implication, a roof -- beam, roof. see HEBREW (H6979) quwr
A primitive root; to bend; used only as denominative for (H3369) yaqosh, to set a trap -- lay a snare. see HEBREW (H3369) yaqosh
From the passive participle of (H6983) qowsh and (H3050) Yahh; entrapped of Jah; Kushajah, an Israelite -- Kushaiah. see HEBREW (H6983) qowsh see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H6990) qatat in the sense of abbreviation; a little, i.e. (adverbially) merely -- very. see HEBREW (H6990) qatat
From an unused root meaning to cut off; ruin -- destroying, destruction.
From the same as (H6986) qeteb; extermination -- destruction. see HEBREW (H6986) qeteb
From (H6999) qatar; perfume -- incense. see HEBREW (H6999) qatar
Feminine passive participle of (H6999) qatar; perfumed; Keturah, a wife of Abraham -- Keturah. see HEBREW (H6999) qatar
A primitive root; to clip off, i.e. (figuratively) destroy -- be cut off.
A primitive root; properly, to cut off, i.e. (figuratively) put to death -- kill, slay.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6991) qatal; to kill -- slay. see HEBREW (H6991) qatal
From (H6991) qatal; a violent death -- slaughter. see HEBREW (H6991) qatal

column8: be a make small thing, be not worthy
column9: A primitive root (rather denominative from (H6996) qatan); to diminish, i.e. Be (causatively, make) diminutive or (figuratively) of no account -- be a (make) small (thing), be not worthy. see HEBREW (H6996) qatan
From (H6994) qaton; a pettiness, i.e. The little finger -- little finger. see HEBREW (H6994) qaton

column8: least, lesser, little one, smallest, one, quantity, thing, younger,
column9: Or qaton {kaw-tone'}; from (H6962) quwt; abbreviated, i.e. Diminutive, literally (in quantity, size or number) or figuratively (in age or importance) -- least, less(-er), little (one), small(-est, one, quantity, thing), young(-er, -est). see HEBREW (H6962) quwt

column7: the small, father of a postexilic Isr
column9: The same as (H6996) qatan; small; Katan, an Israelite -- Hakkatan (including the article). see HEBREW (H6996) qatan

column8: crop off, cut down up, pluck
column9: A primitive root; to strip off -- crop off, cut down (up), pluck.

column8: burn incense, sacrifice upon, altar for incense, kindle, offer incense, a sacrifice
column9: A primitive root (identical with (H7000) qatar through the idea of fumigation in a close place and perhaps thus driving out the occupants); to smoke, i.e. Turn into fragrance by fire (especially as an act of worship) -- burn (incense, sacrifice) (upon), (altar for) incense, kindle, offer (incense, a sacrifice). see HEBREW (H7000) qatar
A primitive root; to inclose -- join.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H7000) qatar; a knot (as tied up), i.e. (figuratively) a riddle; also a vertebra (as if a knot) -- doubt, joint. see HEBREW (H7000) qatar
From (H6999) qatar; perfume -- incense. see HEBREW (H6999) qatar
From (H6999) qatar; fumigative; Kitron, a place in Palestine -- Kitron. see HEBREW (H6999) qatar
From (H6999) qatar; a fumigation -- (sweet) incense, perfume. see HEBREW (H6999) qatar
From (H6996) qatan; littleness; Kattath, a place in Palestine -- Kattath. see HEBREW (H6996) qatan
A primitive root; to vomit -- spue.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7019) qayits; harvest -- summer. see HEBREW (H7019) qayits
Or qiytor {kee-tore'}; from (H6999) qatar; a fume, i.e. Cloud -- smoke, vapour. see HEBREW (H6999) qatar
From (H6965) quwm; an opponent (as rising against one), i.e. (collectively) enemies -- substance. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm
(Aramaic) from (H6966) quwm; an edict (as arising in law) -- decree, statute. see HEBREW (H6966) quwm
(Aramaic) from (H6966) quwm; permanent (as rising firmly) -- stedfast, sure. see HEBREW (H6966) quwm
From (H6965) quwm; an arising -- rising up. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm
From (H6969) quwn in the original sense of fixity; a lance (as striking fast) -- spear. see HEBREW (H6969) quwn

column4: proper name; of a people; location; proper name, masculine
column9: The same as (H7013) qayin (with a play upon the affinity to (H7069) qanah); Kajin, the name of the first child, also of a place in Palestine, and of an Oriental tribe -- Cain, Kenite(-s). see HEBREW (H7013) qayin see HEBREW (H7069) qanah
From (H6969) quwn; a dirge (as accompanied by beating the breasts or on instruments) -- lamentation. see HEBREW (H6969) quwn
The same as (H7015) qiynah; Kinah, a place in Palestine -- Kinah. see HEBREW (H7015) qiynah

column7: members of the tribe of Kenites
column9: Or Qiyniy (1 Chron. 2:55) {kee-nee'}; patronymic from (H7014) Qayin; a Kenite or member of the tribe of Kajin -- Kenite. see HEBREW (H7014) Qayin
From the same as (H7064) qen; fixed; Kenan, an antediluvian -- Cainan, Kenan. see HEBREW (H7064) qen
From (H6972) quwts; harvest (as the crop), whether the product (grain or fruit) or the (dry) season -- summer (fruit, house). see HEBREW (H6972) quwts
From (H6972) quwts; terminal -- out- (utter-)most. see HEBREW (H6972) quwts
Perhaps from (H7006) qayah; the gourd (as nauseous) -- gourd. see HEBREW (H7006) qayah
From (H7036) qalown; intense disgrace -- shameful spewing. see HEBREW (H7036) qalown
Or qir (Isa. 22:5) {keer}; or (feminine) qiyrah {kee-raw'}; from (H6979) quwr; a wall (as built in a trench) -- + mason, side, town, X very, wall. see HEBREW (H6979) quwr
The same as (H7023) qiyr; fortress; Kir, a place in Assyrian; also one in Moab -- Kir. Compare (H7025) Qiyr Cheres. see HEBREW (H7023) qiyr see HEBREW (H7025) Qiyr Cheres

column7: wall of earthenware, a fortified city in Moab
column9: Or (feminine of the latter word) Qiyr Chareseth {keer khar-eh'-seth}; from (H7023) qiyr and (H2789) cheres; fortress of earthenware; Kir-Cheres or Kir-Chareseth, a place in Moab -- Kir-haraseth, Kir-hareseth, Kir-haresh, Kir-heres. see HEBREW (H7023) qiyr see HEBREW (H2789) cheres

column7: father of some postexilic temple servants
column9: Or Qeroc {kay-roce'}; from the same as (H7166) qarcol; ankled; Keros, one of the Nethinim -- Keros. see HEBREW (H7166) qarcol

column7: father of Saul, also the name of several other Isr
column9: From (H6983) qowsh; a bow; Kish, the name of five Israelites -- Kish. see HEBREW (H6983) qowsh

column7: a wadi in the plain of Megiddo
column9: From (H6983) qowsh; winding; Kishon, a river of Palestine -- Kishon, Kison. see HEBREW (H6983) qowsh
From (H6983) qowsh; bowed; Kishi, an Israelite -- Kishi. see HEBREW (H6983) qowsh
(Aramaic) of Greek origin; a lyre -- harp.
Contracted from (H7043) qalal; light; (by implication) rapid (also adverbial) -- light, swift(-ly). see HEBREW (H7043) qalal
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H6963) qowl -- sound, voice. see HEBREW (H6963) qowl
A primitive root (rather identical with (H7034) qalah through the idea of shrinkage by heat); to toast, i.e. Scorch partially or slowly -- dried, loathsome, parch, roast. see HEBREW (H7034) qalah

column7: to be lightly esteemed or dishonored
column8: base, contemn, despise, lightly esteem, set light, seem vile
column9: A primitive root; to be light (as implied in rapid motion), but figuratively, only (be (causatively, hold) in contempt) -- base, contemn, despise, lightly esteem, set light, seem vile.
For (H6950) qahal; to assemble -- gather together. see HEBREW (H6950) qahal
From (H7034) qalah; disgrace; (by implication) the pudenda -- confusion, dishonour, ignominy, reproach, shame. see HEBREW (H7034) qalah
Apparently but a form for (H6747) tsallachath; a kettle -- caldron. see HEBREW (H6747) tsallachath
A primitive root; to maim -- lacking in his parts.
Or qaliyi {kaw-lee'}; from (H7033) qalah; roasted ears of grain -- parched corn. see HEBREW (H7033) qalah
From (H7043) qalal; frivolous; Kallai, an Israelite -- Kallai. see HEBREW (H7043) qalal
From (H7034) qalah; insignificance; Kelajah, an Israelite -- Kelaiah. see HEBREW (H7034) qalah
From (H7038) qalat; maiming; Kelita, the name of three Israelites -- Kelita. see HEBREW (H7038) qalat

column7: to be slight, swift or trifling
column8: abate, make bright, bring into contempt, accurse, despise, be easy
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, make) light, literally (swift, small, sharp, etc.) Or figuratively (easy, trifling, vile, etc.) -- abate, make bright, bring into contempt, (ac-)curse, despise, (be) ease(-y, -ier), (be a, make, make somewhat, move, seem a, set) light(-en, -er, -ly, -ly afflict, -ly esteem, thing), X slight(-ly), be swift(-er), (be, be more, make, re-)vile, whet.
From (H7043) qalal; brightened (as if sharpened) -- burnished, polished. see HEBREW (H7043) qalal
From (H7043) qalal; vilification -- (ac-)curse(-d, - ing). see HEBREW (H7043) qalal
A primitive root; to disparage, i.e. Ridicule -- mock, scoff, scorn.
From (H7046) qalac; a laughing-stock -- derision. see HEBREW (H7046) qalac
Intensive from (H7046) qalac; ridicule -- mocking. see HEBREW (H7046) qalac
A primitive root: to sling: also to carve (as if a circular motion, or into light forms) -- carve, sling (out).
From (H7049) qala'; a sling; also a (door) screen (as if slung across), or the valve (of the door) itself -- hanging, leaf, sling. see HEBREW (H7049) qala'
Intensive from (H7049) qala'; a slinger -- slinger. see HEBREW (H7049) qala'
From (H7043) qalal; insubstantial -- light. see HEBREW (H7043) qalal
From an unused root meaning to prick; a prong, i.e. Hay-fork -- fork.
Feminine of active participle of (H6965) quwm; something that rises, i.e. A stalk of grain -- (standing) corn, grown up, stalk. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm

column7: a relative of Abraham, also two Israelites
column9: From (H6965) quwm and (H410) 'el; raised of God; Kemuel, the name of a relative of Abraham, and of two Israelites -- Kemuel. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From (H6965) quwm; an elevation; Kamon, a place East of the Jordan -- Camon. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm
Or qiymowsh {kee-moshe'}; from an unused root meaning to sting; a prickly plant -- nettle. Compare (H7063) qimmashown. see HEBREW (H7063) qimmashown
From an unused root probably meaning to grind; flour -- flour, meal.
A primitive root; to pluck, i.e. Destroy -- cut down, fill with wrinkles.
A primitive root; to wither -- hew down, wither.
A primitive root; to grasp with the hand -- take an handful.
From (H7061) qamats; a grasp, i.e. Handful -- handful. see HEBREW (H7061) qamats
From the same as (H7057) qimmowsh; a prickly plant -- thorn. see HEBREW (H7057) qimmowsh
Contracted from (H7077) qanan; a nest (as fixed), sometimes including the nestlings; figuratively, a chamber or dwelling -- nest, room. see HEBREW (H7077) qanan

column8: be envious, be move to, provoke to jealousy, very, be zealous
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, make) zealous, i.e. (in a bad sense) jealous or envious -- (be) envy(-ious), be (move to, provoke to) jealous(-y), X very, (be) zeal(-ous).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7069) qanah; to purchase -- buy. see HEBREW (H7069) qanah
From (H7065) qana'; jealous -- jealous. Compare (H7072) qannow'. see HEBREW (H7065) qana' see HEBREW (H7072) qannow'
From (H7065) qana'; jealousy or envy -- envy(-ied), jealousy, X sake, zeal. see HEBREW (H7065) qana'

column8: attain, buyer, teach to keep cattle, get, provoke to jealousy, possessor, purchase
column9: A primitive root; to erect, i.e. Create; by extension, to procure, especially by purchase (causatively, sell); by implication to own -- attain, buy(-er), teach to keep cattle, get, provoke to jealousy, possess(-or), purchase, recover, redeem, X surely, X verily.

column8: balance, bone, branch, cane, reed, spearman, stalk
column9: From (H7069) qanah; a reed (as erect); by resemblance a rod (especially for measuring), shaft, tube, stem, the radius (of the arm), beam (of a steelyard) -- balance, bone, branch, calamus, cane, reed, X spearman, stalk. see HEBREW (H7069) qanah

column7: a wadi between Ephraim and Manasseh, also a city in Asher
column9: Feminine of (H7070) qaneh; reediness; Kanah, the name of a stream and of a place in Palestine -- Kanah. see HEBREW (H7070) qaneh
For (H7067) qanna'; jealous or angry -- jealous. see HEBREW (H7067) qanna'
Probably from an unused root meaning to hunt; hunter; Kenaz, the name of an Edomite and of two Israelites -- Kenaz.
Patronymic from (H7073) Qnaz, a Kenizzite or descendant of Kenaz -- Kenezite, Kenizzites. see HEBREW (H7073) Qnaz

column8: getting, goods, with money, riches, substance
column9: From (H7069) qanah; creation, i.e. (concretely) creatures; also acquisition, purchase, wealth -- getting, goods, X with money, riches, substance. see HEBREW (H7069) qanah
From an unused root (meaning to erect); cinnamon bark (as in upright rolls) -- cinnamon.
A primitive root; to erect; but used only as denominative from (H7064) qen; to nestle, i.e. Build or occupy as a nest -- make...nest. see HEBREW (H7064) qen
From an unused root probably meaning to wrench; perversion -- end.

column7: a city East of the Jordan
column9: From (H7069) qanah; possession; Kenath, a place East of the Jordan -- Kenath. see HEBREW (H7069) qanah
A primitive root; properly, to distribute, i.e. Determine by lot or magical scroll; by implication, to divine -- divine(-r, -ation), prudent, soothsayer, use (divination).
From (H7080) qacam; a lot: also divination (including its fee), oracle -- (reward of) divination, divine sentence, witchcraft. see HEBREW (H7080) qacam
A primitive root; to lop off -- cut off.
From the same as (H3563) kowc (or as (H7185) qashah); properly, a cup, i.e. An ink-stand -- inkhorn. see HEBREW (H3563) kowc see HEBREW (H7185) qashah
Perhaps from (H7049) qala' in the sense of inclosing; citadel; Keilah, a place in Palestine -- Keilah. see HEBREW (H7049) qala'
From the same as (H6970) Qowa'; an incision or gash -- + mark. see HEBREW (H6970) Qowa'
Probably from (H7167) qara'; a bowl (as cut out hollow) -- charger, dish. see HEBREW (H7167) qara'
A primitive root; to shrink, i.e. Thicken (as unracked wine, curdled milk, clouded sky, frozen water) -- congeal, curdle, dark, settle.
A primitive root; to contract, i.e. Roll together -- cut off.
From (H7088) qaphad; shrinking, i.e., terror -- destruction. see HEBREW (H7088) qaphad
Or qippod {kip-pode'}; from (H7088) qaphad; a species of bird, perhaps the bittern (from its contracted form) -- bittern. see HEBREW (H7088) qaphad
From an unused root meaning to contract, i.e. Spring forward; an arrow-snake (as darting on its prey) -- great owl.

column8: shut up, skip, stop, take out of the way
column9: A primitive root; to draw together, i.e. Close; by implication, to leap (by contracting the limbs); specifically, to die (from gathering up the feet) -- shut (up), skip, stop, take out of the way.

column8: after, utmost border, end, infinite, process
column9: Contracted from (H7112) qatsats; an extremity; adverbially (with prepositional prefix) after -- + after, (utmost) border, end, (in-)finite, X process. see HEBREW (H7112) qatsats
A primitive root; to clip, or (generally) chop -- cut down, shorn.
From (H7094) qatsab; shape (as if cut out); base (as if there cut off) -- bottom, size. see HEBREW (H7094) qatsab

column8: cut off, cut short, scrape off
column9: A primitive root; to cut off; (figuratively) to destroy; (partially) to scrape off -- cut off, cut short, scrape (off).

column8: after, border, brim, brink, edge, end, infinite, frontier,
column9: Or (negative only) qetseh {kay'-tseh}; from (H7096) qatsah; an extremity (used in a great variety of applications and idioms; compare (H7093) qets) -- X after, border, brim, brink, edge, end, (in-)finite, frontier, outmost coast, quarter, shore, (out-)side, X some, ut(-ter-)most (part). see HEBREW (H7096) qatsah see HEBREW (H7093) qets
Feminine of (H7097) qatseh; a termination (used like (H7097) qatseh) -- coast, corner, (selv-)edge, lowest, (uttermost) participle see HEBREW (H7097) qatseh see HEBREW (H7097) qatseh

And (feminine) qitsvah {kits-vaw'}; from (H7096) qatsah; a limit (used like (H7097) qatseh, but with less variety) -- end, edge, uttermost participle see HEBREW (H7096) qatsah see HEBREW (H7097) qatseh
From an unused root apparently meaning to incise; fennelflower (from its pungency) -- fitches.

From (H7096) qatsah in the sense of determining; a magistrate (as deciding) or other leader -- captain, guide, prince, ruler. Compare (H6278) Eth Qatsiyn. see HEBREW (H7096) qatsah see HEBREW (H6278) Eth Qatsiyn
From (H7106) qatsa'; cassia (as peeled; plural the bark) -- cassia. see HEBREW (H7106) qatsa'
The same as (H7102) qtsiy'ah; Ketsiah, a daughter of Job -- Kezia. see HEBREW (H7102) qtsiy'ah
From (H7112) qatsats; abrupt; Keziz, a valley in Palestine -- Keziz. see HEBREW (H7112) qatsats

From (H7114) qatsar; severed, i.e. Harvest (as reaped), the crop, the time, the reaper, or figuratively; also a limb (of a tree, or simply foliage) -- bough, branch, harvest (man). see HEBREW (H7114) qatsar
A primitive root; to strip off, i.e. (partially) scrape; by implication, to segregate (as an angle) -- cause to scrape, corner.

column8: be angry, displease, fret self, provoke to wrath come, be wroth
column9: A primitive root; to crack off, i.e. (figuratively) burst out in rage -- (be) anger(-ry), displease, fret self, (provoke to) wrath (come), be wroth.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7107) qatsaph; to become enraged -- be furious. see HEBREW (H7107) qatsaph
(Aramaic) from (H7108) qtsaph; rage -- wrath. see HEBREW (H7108) qtsaph
From (H7107) qatsaph; a splinter (as chipped off); figuratively, rage or strife -- foam, indignation, X sore, wrath. see HEBREW (H7107) qatsaph
From (H7107) qatsaph; a fragment -- bark(-ed). see HEBREW (H7107) qatsaph

column8: cut asunder, in pieces, in sunder, off, utmost
column9: A primitive root; to chop off (literally or figuratively) -- cut (asunder, in pieces, in sunder, off), X utmost.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7112) qatsats -- cut off. see HEBREW (H7112) qatsats

column8: cut down, much discouraged, grieve, harvestman, loathe, mourn, reaper,
column9: A primitive root; to dock off, i.e. Curtail (transitive or intransitive, literal or figurative); especially to harvest (grass or grain) -- X at all, cut down, much discouraged, grieve, harvestman, lothe, mourn, reap(-er), (be, wax) short(-en, -er), straiten, trouble, vex.
From (H7114) qatsar; shortness (of spirit), i.e. Impatience -- anguish. see HEBREW (H7114) qatsar
From (H7114) qatsar; short (whether in size, number, life, strength or temper) -- few, hasty, small, soon. see HEBREW (H7114) qatsar
From (H7096) qatsah; a termination (literally or figuratively); also (by implication) a portion; adverbially (with prepositional prefix) after -- end, part, X some. see HEBREW (H7096) qatsah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7117) qtsath -- end, partly. see HEBREW (H7117) qtsath
Contracted from an unused root meaning to chill; cool; figuratively, quiet -- cold, excellent (from the margin).
From the same as (H7119) qar; cold -- cold. see HEBREW (H7119) qar

column8: bewray self, that are bidden, call for, forth, self, upon, cry unto, be famous,
column9: A primitive root (rather identical with (H7122) qara' through the idea of accosting a person met); to call out to (i.e. Properly, address by name, but used in a wide variety of applications) -- bewray (self), that are bidden, call (for, forth, self, upon), cry (unto), (be) famous, guest, invite, mention, (give) name, preach, (make) proclaim(- ation), pronounce, publish, read, renowned, say. see HEBREW (H7122) qara'

column8: befall, by chance, cause to come upon, fall out, happen, meet
column9: A primitive root: to encounter, whether accidentally or in a hostile manner -- befall, (by) chance, (cause to) come (upon), fall out, happen, meet.

column7: to call, read out or aloud
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H7121) qara' -- call, cry, read. see HEBREW (H7121) qara'
Properly, active participle of (H7121) qara'; a caller, i.e. Partridge (from its cry) -- partridge. See also (H6981) Qowre'. see HEBREW (H7121) qara' see HEBREW (H6981) Qowre'

column7: against he come, help, meet, seek, to, in the way
column8: against he come, help, meet, seek, to, in the way
column9: From (H7122) qara'; an encountering, accidental, friendly or hostile (also adverbially, opposite) -- X against (he come), help, meet, seek, X to, X in the way. see HEBREW (H7122) qara'

column8: cause to approach, cause to bring forth, near, cause to come near, nigh
column9: A primitive root; to approach (causatively, bring near) for whatever purpose -- (cause to) approach, (cause to) bring (forth, near), (cause to) come (near, nigh), (cause to) draw near (nigh), go (near), be at hand, join, be near, offer, present, produce, make ready, stand, take.

column8: approach, come near, nigh, draw near
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H7126) qarab -- approach, come (near, nigh), draw near. see HEBREW (H7126) qarab
From (H7126) qarab; hostile encounter -- battle, war. see HEBREW (H7126) qarab
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7128) qrab -- war. see HEBREW (H7128) qrab

column8: among, before, bowels, unto charge, eat up, heart, him, in,
column9: From (H7126) qarab; properly, the nearest part, i.e. The center, whether literal, figurative or adverbial (especially with preposition) -- X among, X before, bowels, X unto charge, + eat (up), X heart, X him, X in, inward (X -ly, part, -s, thought), midst, + out of, purtenance, X therein, X through, X within self. see HEBREW (H7126) qarab

column8: approach, come near, nigh, draw near
column9: From (H7126) qarab; near -- approach, come (near, nigh), draw near. see HEBREW (H7126) qarab
From (H7126) qarab; approach -- approaching, draw near. see HEBREW (H7126) qarab
Or qurban {koor-bawn'}; from (H7126) qarab; something brought near the altar, i.e. A sacrificial present -- oblation, that is offered, offering. see HEBREW (H7126) qarab
Perhaps from (H6923) qadam in the sense of striking upon; an axe -- ax. see HEBREW (H6923) qadam
Feminine of (H7119) qar; coolness -- cold. see HEBREW (H7119) qar

column8: appoint, lay make beams, befall, bring, come to pass unto, floor, hap was, happen unto,
column9: A primitive root; to light upon (chiefly by accident); causatively, to bring about; specifically, to impose timbers (for roof or floor) -- appoint, lay (make) beams, befall, bring, come (to pass unto), floor, (hap) was, happen (unto), meet, send good speed.
From (H7136) qarah; an (unfortunate) occurrence, i.e. Some accidental (ceremonial) disqualification -- uncleanness that chanceth. see HEBREW (H7136) qarah

column8: allied, approach, at hand, any of kin, that is near of kin, neighbor, that is next,
column9: Or qarob {kaw-robe'}; from (H7126) qarab; near (in place, kindred or time) -- allied, approach, at hand, + any of kin, kinsfold(-sman), (that is) near (of kin), neighbour, (that is) next, (them that come) nigh (at hand), more ready, short(-ly). see HEBREW (H7126) qarab
A primitive root; to depilate -- make (self) bald.
Or qorach {ko'-rakh}; from (H7139) qarach; ice (as if bald, i.e. Smooth); hence, hail; by resemblance, rock crystal -- crystal, frost, ice. see HEBREW (H7139) qarach

column7: an Edomite name, also an Israelite name
column9: From (H7139) qarach; ice; Korach, the name of two Edomites and three Israelites -- Korah. see HEBREW (H7139) qarach
From (H7139) qarach; bald (on the back of the head) -- bald (head). see HEBREW (H7139) qarach

column7: bald one, a man of Judah
column9: From (H7139) qarach; bald; Kareach, an Israelite -- Careah, Kareah. see HEBREW (H7139) qarach
Or qorcha; (Ezek. 27:31) {kor-khaw'}; from (H7139) qarach; baldness -- bald(-ness), X utterly. see HEBREW (H7139) qarach

column8: Korahite, Korathite, sons of Kore, Korhite
column9: Patronymic from (H7141) Qorach; a Korchite (collectively) or descendants of Korach -- Korahite, Korathite, sons of Kore, Korhite. see HEBREW (H7141) Qorach
From (H7139) qarach; a bald spot (on the back of the head); figuratively, a threadbare spot (on the back side of the cloth) -- bald head, bare within. see HEBREW (H7139) qarach
From (H7136) qarah; hostile encounter -- contrary. see HEBREW (H7136) qarah
From (H7121) qara'; called, i.e. Select -- famous, renowned. see HEBREW (H7121) qara'
(Aramaic) or qiryah (Aramaic) {keer-yaw'}; corresponding to (H7151) qiryah -- city. see HEBREW (H7151) qiryah
From (H7121) qara'; a proclamation -- preaching. see HEBREW (H7121) qara'
From (H7136) qarah in the sense of flooring, i.e. Building; a city -- city. see HEBREW (H7136) qarah

column7: a city in Judah, also a city in Moab
column9: Plural of (H7151) qiryah; buildings; Kerioth, the name of two places in Palestine -- Kerioth, Kirioth. see HEBREW (H7151) qiryah

column7: city of the four, an older name of Hebron
column9: Or (with the article interposed) Qiryath ha- Arbaw (Neh. 11:25) {keer-yath' haw-ar-bah'}; from (H7151) qiryah and (H704) Arba' or (H702) arba'; city of Arba, or city of the four (giants); Kirjath-Arba or Kirjath-ha-Arba, a place in Palestine -- Kirjath-arba. see HEBREW (H7151) qiryah see HEBREW (H704) Arba' see HEBREW (H702) arba'

column7: city of Baal, another name for Kiriath-jearim
column9: From (H7151) qiryah and (H1168) Ba'al; city of Baal; Kirjath-Baal, a place in Palestine -- Kirjath-baal. see HEBREW (H7151) qiryah see HEBREW (H1168) Ba'al

column7: city of streets, a city in Moab
column9: From (H7151) qiryah and the feminine plural of (H2351) chuwts; city of streets; Kirjath-Chutsoth, a place in Moab -- Kirjath-huzoth. see HEBREW (H7151) qiryah see HEBREW (H2351) chuwts

column7: a city in Moab, also a place in Naphtali
column9: Dual of (H7151) qiryah; double city; Kirjathaim, the name of two placed in Palestine -- Kiriathaim, Kirjathaim. see HEBREW (H7151) qiryah

column7: city of forests, a city given to Judah, then to Benjamin
column9: Or (Jer. 26:20) with the article interposed; or (Josh. 18:28) simply the former part of the word; or Qiryath tariym {keer-yath' aw-reem'}; from (H7151) qiryah and the plural of (H3293) ya'ar or (H5892) iyr; city of forests, or city of towns; Kirjath-Jearim or Kirjath-Arim, a place in Palestine -- Kirjath, Kirjath-jearim, Kirjath-arim. see HEBREW (H7151) qiryah see HEBREW (H3293) ya'ar see HEBREW (H5892) iyr

column7: city of writing, a city in Judah
column9: Or Qiryath Cepher {keer-yath' say-fer}; from (H7151) qiryah and a simpler feminine from the same as (H5577) cancin, or (for the latter name) (H5612) cepher; city of branches, or of a book; Kirjath-Sannah or Kirjath-Sepher, a place in Palestine -- Kirjath-sannah, Kirjath-sepher. see HEBREW (H7151) qiryah see HEBREW (H5577) cancin see HEBREW (H5612) cepher
A primitive root; to cover -- cover.
A primitive root; to push or gore; used only as denominative from (H7161) qeren, to shoot out horns; figuratively, rays -- have horns, shine. see HEBREW (H7161) qeren

column4: noun feminine; proper name, of a location; noun feminine
column9: From (H7160) qaran; a horn (as projecting); by implication, a flask, cornet; by resembl. An elephant's tooth (i.e. Ivory), a corner (of the altar), a peak (of a mountain), a ray (of light); figuratively, power -- X hill, horn. see HEBREW (H7160) qaran
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7161) qeren; a horn (literally or for sound) -- horn, cornet. see HEBREW (H7161) qeren

column7: horn of antimony, a daughter of Job
column9: From (H7161) qeren and (H6320) puwk; horn of cosmetic; Keren-hap-Puk, one of Job's daughters -- Keren-happuch. see HEBREW (H7161) qeren see HEBREW (H6320) puwk

A primitive root; properly, to protrude; used only as denominative from (H7165) qerec (for alliteration with (H7167) qara'), to hunch, i.e. Be hump-backed -- stoop. see HEBREW (H7165) qerec see HEBREW (H7167) qara'
From (H7164) qarac; a knob or belaying-pin (from its swelling form) -- tache. see HEBREW (H7164) qarac
From (H7164) qarac; an ankle (as a protuberance or joint) -- foot. see HEBREW (H7164) qarac
A primitive root; to rend, literally or figuratively (revile, paint the eyes, as if enlarging them) -- cut out, rend, X surely, tear.
From (H7167) qara'; a rag -- piece, rag. see HEBREW (H7167) qara'

A primitive root; to pinch, i.e. (partially) to bite the lips, blink the eyes (as a gesture of malice), or (fully) to squeeze off (a piece of clay in order to mould a vessel from it) -- form, move, wink.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7171) qerets in the sense of a bit (to \"eat the morsels of\" any one, i.e. Chew him up (figuratively) by slander) -- + accuse. see HEBREW (H7171) qerets
From (H7169) qarats; extirpation (as if by constriction) -- destruction. see HEBREW (H7169) qarats

column8: bottom, one side of the floor
column9: From (H7167) qara'; floor (as if a pavement of pieces or tesseroe), of a building or the sea -- bottom, (X one side of the) floor. see HEBREW (H7167) qara'

column7: floor, a place on S. border of Judah
column9: The same as (H7172) qarqa'; ground-floor; Karka (with the article prefix), a place in Palestine -- Karkaa. see HEBREW (H7172) qarqa'

column7: a place East of the Jordan
column9: From (H6979) quwr; foundation; Karkor, a place East of the Jordan -- Karkor. see HEBREW (H6979) quwr
From an unused root meaning to split off; a slab or plank; by implication, a deck of a ship -- bench, board.
From (H7136) qarah in the sense of building; a city -- city. see HEBREW (H7136) qarah
From (H7176) qereth; city; Kartah, a place in Palestine -- Kartah. see HEBREW (H7176) qereth
From (H7176) qereth; city-plot; Kartan, a place in Palestine -- Kartan. see HEBREW (H7176) qereth
From (H7197) qashash; straw (as dry) -- stubble. see HEBREW (H7197) qashash
From an unused root (meaning to be hard); a cucumber (from the difficulty of digestion) -- cucumber.

column8: attend, cause to hearken, give heed, incline, mark well, regard
column9: A primitive root; to prick up the ears, i.e. Hearken -- attend, (cause to) hear(-ken), give heed, incline, mark (well), regard.

column8: diligently, hearing, much heed, that regarded
column9: From (H7181) qashab; a hearkening -- X diligently, hearing, much heed, that regarded. see HEBREW (H7181) qashab
Or qashshub {kash-shoob'}; from (H7181) qashab; hearkening -- attent(-ive). see HEBREW (H7181) qashab
Or qasvah {kas-vaw'}; from an unused root meaning to be round; a jug (from its shape) -- cover, cup.

column7: to be hard, severe or fierce
column8: be cruel, be fiercer, make grievous, be in, have, seem, harden, labor, be sore,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to be dense, i.e. Tough or severe (in various applications) -- be cruel, be fiercer, make grievous, be ((ask a), be in, have, seem, would) hard(-en, (labour), -ly, thing), be sore, (be, make) stiff(-en, (-necked)).

column8: churlish, cruel, grievous, hardhearted, thing, heavy, impudent, obstinate,
column9: From (H7185) qashah; severe (in various applications) -- churlish, cruel, grievous, hard((-hearted), thing), heavy, + impudent, obstinate, prevailed, rough(-ly), sore, sorrowful, stiff((necked)), stubborn, + in trouble. see HEBREW (H7185) qashah
(Aramaic) or qshot (Aramaic) {kesh-ote'}; corresponding to (H7189) qoshet; fidelity -- truth. see HEBREW (H7189) qoshet
A primitive root; to be (causatively, make) unfeeling -- harden.
Or qosht {kosht}; from an unused root meaning to balance; equity (as evenly weighed), i.e. Reality -- truth.
From (H7185) qashah; obstinacy -- stubbornness. see HEBREW (H7185) qashah
From (H7190) qshiy; hard ground; Kishjon, a place in Palestine -- Kishion, Keshon. see HEBREW (H7190) qshiy
From an unused root (probably meaning to weigh out); an ingot (as definitely estimated and stamped for a coin) -- piece of money (silver).
By reduplication from an unused root meaning to shale off as bark; a scale (of a fish); hence a coat of mail (as composed of or covered with jointed plates of metal) -- mail, scale.

column8: bind up, make a conspiracy join together, knit, stronger, work treason
column9: A primitive root: to tie, physically (gird, confine, compact) or mentally (in love, league) -- bind (up), (make a) conspire(-acy, -ator), join together, knit, stronger, work (treason).
From (H7194) qashar; an (unlawful) alliance -- confederacy, conspiracy, treason. see HEBREW (H7194) qashar
From (H7194) qashar; an (ornamental) girdle (for women) -- attire, headband. see HEBREW (H7194) qashar

A primitive root; to become sapless through drought; used only as denominative from (H7179) qash; to forage for straw, stubble or wood; figuratively, to assemble -- gather (selves) (together). see HEBREW (H7179) qash

From (H7185) qashah in the original sense (of (H6983) qowsh) of bending: a bow, for shooting (hence, figuratively, strength) or the iris -- X arch(-er), + arrow, bow((-man, -shot)). see HEBREW (H7185) qashah see HEBREW (H6983) qowsh
Intensive (as denominative) from (H7198) qesheth; a bowman -- X archer. see HEBREW (H7198) qesheth

column8: advise cause to, show self, sight of others, espy, stare, surely, think, view,
column9: A primitive root; to see, literally or figuratively (in numerous applications, direct and implied, transitive, intransitive and causative) -- advise self, appear, approve, behold, X certainly, consider, discern, (make to) enjoy, have experience, gaze, take heed, X indeed, X joyfully, lo, look (on, one another, one on another, one upon another, out, up, upon), mark, meet, X be near, perceive, present, provide, regard, (have) respect, (fore-, cause to, let) see(-r, -m, one another), shew (self), X sight of others, (e-)spy, stare, X surely, X think, view, visions.
From (H7200) ra'ah; a bird of prey (probably the vulture, from its sharp sight) -- glede. Compare (H1676) da'ah. see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah see HEBREW (H1676) da'ah
From (H7200) ra'ah; seeing, i.e. Experiencing -- see. see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah
Active participle of (H7200) ra'ah; a seer (as often rendered); but also (abstractly) a vision -- vision. see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah
For (H7203) ro'eh; prophet; Roeh, an Israelite -- Haroeh (including the article). see HEBREW (H7203) ro'eh

column7: behold a son! oldest son of Jacob, also his desc
column9: From the imperative of (H7200) ra'ah and (H1121) ben; see ye a son; Reuben, a son of Jacob -- Reuben. see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah see HEBREW (H1121) ben
Patronymic from (H7205) r'uwben; a Reubenite or descendant of Reuben -- children of Reuben, Reubenites. see HEBREW (H7205) r'uwben
From (H7200) ra'ah; sight, i.e. Satisfaction -- behold. see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah
Feminine passive participle of (H7213) ra'am; raised; Reumah, a Syrian woman -- Reumah. see HEBREW (H7213) ra'am
From (H7200) ra'ah; a mirror (as seen) -- looking glass. see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah
From (H7200) ra'ah; sight, whether abstractly (vision) or concretely (a spectacle) -- gazingstock, look to, (that) see(-th). see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah
From (H7200) ra'ah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has seen; Reajah, the name of three Israelites -- Reaia, Reaiah. see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H7200) ra'ah; sight -- beholding. see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah
A primitive root; to rise -- be lifted up.
Or rieym {reh-ame'}; or reym {rame}; or rem {rame}; from (H7213) ra'am; a wild bull (from its conspicuousness) -- unicorn. see HEBREW (H7213) ra'am
From (H7213) ra'am; something high in value, i.e. Perhaps coral -- coral. see HEBREW (H7213) ra'am

column7: heights, the name of several cities in Isr
column9: Or Ramoth {raw-moth'}; plural of (H7215) ra'mah; heights; Ramoth, the name of two places in Palestine -- Ramoth. see HEBREW (H7215) ra'mah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7218) ro'sh; the head; figuratively, the sum -- chief, head, sum. see HEBREW (H7218) ro'sh

From an unused root apparently meaning to shake; the head (as most easily shaken), whether literal or figurative (in many applications, of place, time, rank, itc.) -- band, beginning, captain, chapiter, chief(-est place, man, things), company, end, X every (man), excellent, first, forefront, ((be-))head, height, (on) high(-est part, (priest)), X lead, X poor, principal, ruler, sum, top.

Or rowsh (Deut. 32:32) {roshe}; apparently the same as (H7218) ro'sh; a poisonous plant, probably the poppy (from its conspicuous head); generally poison (even of serpents) -- gall, hemlock, poison, venom. see HEBREW (H7218) ro'sh

column4: noun masculine; proper name, of a people
column9: Probably the same as (H7218) ro'sh; Rosh, the name of an Israelite and of a foreign nation -- Rosh. see HEBREW (H7218) ro'sh
From the same as (H7218) ro'sh; a beginning -- beginning. see HEBREW (H7218) ro'sh
Feminine of (H7218) ro'sh; the head -- head(-stone). see HEBREW (H7218) ro'sh

column8: ancestor, that were beforetime, beginning, eldest, first, forefather most, former thing, of old time,
column9: Or riishon {ree-shone'}; from (H7221) ri'shah; first, in place, time or rank (as adjective or noun) -- ancestor, (that were) before(-time), beginning, eldest, first, fore(-father) (-most), former (thing), of old time, past. see HEBREW (H7221) ri'shah
From (H7223) ri'shown; first -- first. see HEBREW (H7223) ri'shown

column8: beginning, chiefest, firstfruits, part, time, principal thing
column9: From the same as (H7218) ro'sh; the first, in place, time, order or rank (specifically, a firstfruit) -- beginning, chief(-est), first(-fruits, part, time), principal thing. see HEBREW (H7218) ro'sh
From (H7218) ro'sh; a pillow (being for the head) -- bolster. see HEBREW (H7218) ro'sh

column8: in abundance, elder, enough, exceedingly, full, greatly, man, one,
column9: By contracted from (H7231) rabab; abundant (in quantity, size, age, number, rank, quality) -- (in) abound(-undance, -ant, -antly), captain, elder, enough, exceedingly, full, great(-ly, man, one), increase, long (enough, (time)), (do, have) many(-ifold, things, a time), ((ship-))master, mighty, more, (too, very) much, multiply(-tude), officer, often(-times), plenteous, populous, prince, process (of time), suffice(-lent). see HEBREW (H7231) rabab
By contraction from (H7232) rabab; an archer (or perhaps the same as (H7227) rab) -- archer. see HEBREW (H7232) rabab see HEBREW (H7227) rab

column8: captain, chief, great, lord, master, stout
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H7227) rab -- captain, chief, great, lord, master, stout. see HEBREW (H7227) rab

column8: abundance, all, common sort, excellent, greatly huge, be increased
column9: From (H7231) rabab; abundance (in any respect) -- abundance(- antly), all, X common (sort), excellent, great(-ly, -ness, number), huge, be increased, long, many, more in number, most, much, multitude, plenty(-ifully), X very (age). see HEBREW (H7231) rabab

column7: to be or become many or much
column8: increase, be manifold, be more, multiply, ten thousands
column9: A primitive root; properly, to cast together (compare (H7241) rabiyb), i.e. Increase, especially in number; also (as denominative from (H7233) rbabah) to multiply by the myriad -- increase, be many(-ifold), be more, multiply, ten thousands. see HEBREW (H7241) rabiyb see HEBREW (H7233) rbabah
A primitive root (rather identical with (H7231) rabab through the idea of projection); to shoot an arrow -- shoot. see HEBREW (H7231) rabab
From (H7231) rabab; abundance (in number), i.e. (specifically) a myriad (whether definite or indefinite) -- many, million, X multiply, ten thousand. see HEBREW (H7231) rabab
A primitive root; to spread -- deck.

column7: to be or become much, many or great
column9: A primitive root; to increase (in whatever respect) -- (bring in) abundance (X -antly), + archer (by mistake for (H7232) rabab), be in authority, bring up, X continue, enlarge, excel, exceeding(-ly), be full of, (be, make) great(-er, -ly, X -ness), grow up, heap, increase, be long, (be, give, have, make, use) many (a time), (any, be, give, give the, have) more (in number), (ask, be, be so, gather, over, take, yield) much (greater, more), (make to) multiply, nourish, plenty(-eous), X process (of time), sore, store, thoroughly, very. see HEBREW (H7232) rabab
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7235) rabah -- make a great man, grow. see HEBREW (H7235) rabah
Feminine of (H7227) rab; great; Rabbah, the name of two places in Palestine, East and West -- Rabbah, Rabbath. see HEBREW (H7227) rab
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H7235) rabah; increase (of dignity) -- greatness, majesty. see HEBREW (H7235) rabah

From (H7231) rabab; or ribbow {rib-bo'} from (H7231) rabab; a myriad, i.e. Indefinitely, large number -- great things, ten ((eight)-een, (for)-ty, + sixscore, + threescore, X twenty, (twen)-ty) thousand. see HEBREW (H7231) rabab see HEBREW (H7231) rabab
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7239) ribbow -- X ten thousand times ten thousand. see HEBREW (H7239) ribbow
From (H7231) rabab; a rain (as an accumulation of drops) -- shower. see HEBREW (H7231) rabab
From (H7234) rabad; a collar (as spread around the neck) -- chain. see HEBREW (H7234) rabad
Or rbiiy {reb-ee-ee'}; from (H7251) raba'; fourth; also (fractionally) a fourth -- foursquare, fourth (part). see HEBREW (H7251) raba'
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7243) rbiy'iy -- fourth. see HEBREW (H7243) rbiy'iy
From (H7231) rabab; multitude; Rabbith, a place in Palestine -- Rabbith. see HEBREW (H7231) rabab
A primitive root; to soak (bread in oil) -- baken, (that which is) fried.

column7: a city in Hamath, also one on N.E. border of Isr
column9: From an unused root meaning to be fruitful; fertile; Riblah, a place in Syria -- Riblah.

column7: perhaps "chief soothsayer", an official of the Bab. king
column9: From (H7227) rab and a foreign word for a Magian; chief Magian; Rab-Mag, a Bab. Official -- Rab-mag. see HEBREW (H7227) rab

column7: perhaps "chief eunuch", an official of the Assyr. and Bab. kings
column9: From (H7227) rab and a foreign word for a eunuch; chief chamberlain; Rab-Saris, a Babylonian official -- Rab-saris. see HEBREW (H7227) rab

column7: to lie stretched out, lie down
column9: A primitive root; to squat or lie out flat, i.e. (specifically) in copulation -- let gender, lie down.

A primitive root (rather identical with (H7250) raba' through the idea of sprawling \"at all fours\" (or possibly the reverse is the order of deriv.); compare (H702) arba'); properly, to be four (sided); used only as denominative of (H7253) reba'; to be quadrate -- (four-)square(-d). see HEBREW (H7250) raba' see HEBREW (H702) arba' see HEBREW (H7253) reba'
From (H7250) raba'; prostration (for sleep) -- lying down. see HEBREW (H7250) raba'
From (H7251) raba'; a fourth (part or side) -- fourth part, side, square. see HEBREW (H7251) raba'
The same as (H7253) reba'; Reba, a Midianite -- Reba. see HEBREW (H7253) reba'
From (H7251) raba'; a quarter -- fourth participle see HEBREW (H7251) raba'
From (H7251) raba'; a descendant of the fourth generation, i.e. Great great grandchild -- fourth. see HEBREW (H7251) raba'

column7: stretch oneself out, lie down, lie stretched out
column8: crouch down, fall down, make a fold, lay, cause to, make to lie down, make to rest, sit
column9: A primitive root; to crouch (on all four legs folded, like a recumbent animal); be implication, to recline, repose, brood, lurk, imbed -- crouch (down), fall down, make a fold, lay, (cause to, make to) lie (down), make to rest, sit.

column7: (place of) lying down, resting place, dwelling place
column8: where each lay, lie down in, resting place
column9: From (H7257) rabats; a couch or place of repose -- where each lay, lie down in, resting place. see HEBREW (H7257) rabats
From an unused root probably meaning to clog by tying up the fetlock; fettering (by beauty); Ribkah, the wife of Isaac -- Rebekah.
(Aramaic) from (H7229) rab; huge (in size); domineering (in character) -- (very) great (things). see HEBREW (H7229) rab
(Aramaic) from (H7260) rabrab; a magnate -- lord, prince. see HEBREW (H7260) rabrab

column7: perhaps "chief of the officers", an Assyr. military leader
column9: From (H7227) rab and (H8248) shaqah; chief butler; Rabshakeh, a Bab. Official -- Rabshakeh. see HEBREW (H7227) rab see HEBREW (H8248) shaqah
From an unused root meaning to pile together; a lump of clay -- clod.

column7: to be agitated, quiver, quake, be excited, perturbed
column8: be afraid, stand in awe, disquiet, fall out, fret, move, provoke, quake,
column9: A primitive root; to quiver (with any violent emotion, especially anger or fear) -- be afraid, stand in awe, disquiet, fall out, fret, move, provoke, quake, rage, shake, tremble, trouble, be wroth.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7264) ragaz -- provoke unto wrath. see HEBREW (H7264) ragaz
(Aramaic) from (H7265) rgaz; violent anger -- rage. see HEBREW (H7265) rgaz
From (H7264) ragaz; commotion, restlessness (of a horse), crash (of thunder), disquiet, anger -- fear, noise, rage, trouble(-ing), wrath. see HEBREW (H7264) ragaz
Intensive from (H7264) ragaz; timid -- trembling. see HEBREW (H7264) ragaz
Feminine of (H7267) rogez; trepidation -- trembling. see HEBREW (H7267) rogez

column8: backbite, slander, espy out, teach to go, view
column9: A primitive root; to walk along; but only in specifically, applications, to reconnoiter, to be a tale-bearer (i.e. Slander); also (as denominative from (H7272) regel) to lead about -- backbite, search, slander, (e-)spy (out), teach to go, view. see HEBREW (H7272) regel
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7272) regel -- foot. see HEBREW (H7272) regel

column8: be able to endure, according as, after, coming, follow, haunt, journey,
column9: From (H7270) ragal; a foot (as used in walking); by implication, a step; by euphem. The pudenda -- X be able to endure, X according as, X after, X coming, X follow, ((broken-))foot((-ed, -stool)), X great toe, X haunt, X journey, leg, + piss, + possession, time. see HEBREW (H7270) ragal
From (H7272) regel; a footman (soldier) -- (on) foot(- man). see HEBREW (H7272) regel

column7: (place of) fullers, a place in Gilead
column9: Plural of active participle of (H7270) ragal; fullers (as tramping the cloth in washing); Rogelim, a place East of the Jordan -- Rogelim. see HEBREW (H7270) ragal

A primitive root (compare (H7263) regeb, (H7321) ruwa', (H7551) raqam); to cast together (stones), i.e. To lapidate -- X certainly, stone. see HEBREW (H7263) regeb see HEBREW (H7321) ruwa' see HEBREW (H7551) raqam
From (H7275) ragam; stoneheap; Regem, an Israelite -- Regem. see HEBREW (H7275) ragam
Feminine of the same as (H7276) Regem; a pile (of stones), i.e. (figuratively) a throng -- council. see HEBREW (H7276) Regem
From (H7276) Regem and (H4428) melek; king's heap; Regem-Melek, an Israelite -- Regem-melech. see HEBREW (H7276) Regem see HEBREW (H4428) melek
A primitive root; to grumble, i.e. Rebel -- murmur.

column8: break, divide, find ease, be a moment, cause, give, make to rest, make suddenly
column9: A primitive root; properly, to toss violently and suddenly (the sea with waves, the skin with boils); figuratively (in a favorable manner) to settle, i.e. Quiet; specifically, to wink (from the motion of the eye-lids) -- break, divide, find ease, be a moment, (cause, give, make to) rest, make suddenly.
From (H7280) raga'. A wink (of the eyes), i.e. A very short space of time -- instant, moment, space, suddenly. see HEBREW (H7280) raga'
From (H7280) raga'; restful, i.e. Peaceable -- that are quiet. see HEBREW (H7280) raga'

column7: to be in tumult or commotion
column9: A primitive root; to be tumultuous -- rage.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7283) ragash; to gather tumultuously -- assemble (together). see HEBREW (H7283) ragash
Or (feminine) rigshah {rig-shaw'}; from (H7283) ragash; a tumultuous crowd -- company, insurrection. see HEBREW (H7283) ragash

column7: to beat out, beat down, subdue
column9: A primitive root; to tread in pieces, i.e. (figuratively) to conquer, or (specifically) to overlay -- spend, spread, subdue.

column8: make to have dominion, prevail against, reign, bear
column9: A primitive root; to tread down, i.e. Subjugate; specifically, to crumble off -- (come to, make to) have dominion, prevail against, reign, (bear, make to) rule,(-r, over), take.
Intensive from (H7287) radah; domineering; Raddai, an Israelite -- Raddai. see HEBREW (H7287) radah
From (H7286) radad in the sense of spreading; a veil (as expanded) -- vail, veil. see HEBREW (H7286) radad

column7: to be in or fall into heavy sleep
column8: be be in a deep, cast into a dead, that sleeper,
column9: A primitive root; to stun, i.e. Stupefy (with sleep or death) -- (be fast a-, be in a deep, cast into a dead, that) sleep(-er, -eth).

column8: chase, put to flight, follow after, hunt, be under persecution, pursuer
column9: A primitive root; to run after (usually with hostile intent; figuratively (of time) gone by) -- chase, put to flight, follow (after, on), hunt, (be under) persecute(-ion, -or), pursue(-r).

column7: to act stormily, boisterously or arrogantly
column8: overcome, behave self proudly, make sure, strengthen
column9: A primitive root; to urge severely, i.e. (figuratively) importune, embolden, capture, act insolently -- overcome, behave self proudly, make sure, strengthen.
From (H7292) rahab, bluster(-er) -- proud, strength. see HEBREW (H7292) rahab
The same as (H7293) rahab; Rahab (i.e. Boaster), an epithet of Egypt -- Rahab. see HEBREW (H7293) rahab
From (H7292) rahab; insolent -- proud. see HEBREW (H7292) rahab
From (H7292) rahab; pride -- strength. see HEBREW (H7292) rahab
A primitive root; to fear -- be afraid.
From an unused root apparently meaning to hollow out; a channel or watering-box; by resemblance a ringlet of hair (as forming parallel lines) -- gallery, gutter, trough.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H7200) ra'ah; aspect -- form. see HEBREW (H7200) ra'ah

column8: have the dominion, be lord, mourn, rule
column9: A primitive root; to tramp about, i.e. Ramble (free or disconsolate) -- have the dominion, be lord, mourn, rule.

column7: to be saturated, drink one\'s fill
column8: bathe, make drunk, take the fill, satiate, abundantly satisfy, soak, water abundantly
column9: A primitive root; to slake the thirst (occasionally of other appetites) -- bathe, make drunk, (take the) fill, satiate, (abundantly) satisfy, soak, water (abundantly).
From (H7301) ravah; sated (with drink) -- drunkenness, watered. see HEBREW (H7301) ravah
From an unused root probably meaning to cry out; outcry; Rohagah, an Israelite -- Rohgah.
A primitive root (identical with (H7306) ruwach); properly, to breathe freely, i.e. Revive; by implication, to have ample room -- be refreshed, large. see HEBREW (H7306) ruwach
From (H7304) ravach; room, literally (an interval) or figuratively (deliverance) -- enlargement, space. see HEBREW (H7304) ravach

column7: accept, smell, touch, make of quick understanding
column8: accept, smell, touch, make of quick understanding
