From the same as (H7830) shachats; proudly; Shachatsom, a place in Palestine -- Shahazimah (from the margin). see HEBREW (H7830) shachats

column8: deride, have in derision, laugh, make merry, mocker, play, rejoice, laugh to scorn,
column9: A primitive root; to laugh (in pleasure or detraction); by implication, to play -- deride, have in derision, laugh, make merry, mock(-er), play, rejoice, (laugh to) scorn, be in (make) sport.

column7: to rub away, beat fine, pulverize
column9: A primitive root; to comminate (by trituration or attrition) -- beat, wear.
From (H7833) shachaq; a powder (as beaten small): by analogy, a thin vapor; by extension, the firmament -- cloud, small dust, heaven, sky. see HEBREW (H7833) shachaq
A primitive root (identical with (H7836) shachar through the idea of the duskiness of early dawn); to be dim or dark (in color) -- be black. see HEBREW (H7836) shachar

column7: to look early or diligently for
column8: do something betimes, enquire early, seek betimes, seek diligently early, in the morning
column9: A primitive root; properly, to dawn, i.e. (figuratively) be (up) early at any task (with the implication of earnestness); by extension, to search for (with painstaking) -- (do something) betimes, enquire early, rise (seek) betimes, seek diligently) early, in the morning).

column8: dayspring, early, light, morning, whence rises
column9: From (H7836) shachar; dawn (literal, figurative or adverbial) -- day(-spring), early, light, morning, whence riseth. see HEBREW (H7836) shachar
Or shachowr {shaw-khore'}; from (H7835) shachar; properly, dusky, but also (absol.) Jetty -- black. see HEBREW (H7835) shachar
From (H7836) shachar; a dawning, i.e. (figuratively) juvenescence -- youth. see HEBREW (H7836) shachar
From (H7835) shachar; swarthy -- black. see HEBREW (H7835) shachar
From (H7836) shachar and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has sought; Shecharjah, an Israelite -- Shehariah. see HEBREW (H7836) shachar see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Dual of (H7837) shachar; double dawn; Shacharajim, an Israelite -- Shaharaim. see HEBREW (H7837) shachar

column8: batter, cast off, corrupter, thing, destroyer lose, mar, perish, spill,
column9: A primitive root; to decay, i.e. (causatively) ruin (literally or figuratively) -- batter, cast off, corrupt(-er, thing), destroy(-er, -uction), lose, mar, perish, spill, spoiler, X utterly, waste(-r).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7843) shachath -- corrupt, fault. see HEBREW (H7843) shachath
From (H7743) shuwach; a pit (especially as a trap); figuratively, destruction -- corruption, destruction, ditch, grave, pit. see HEBREW (H7743) shuwach

column7: swerver, perhaps revolter, deeds that swerve
column9: Or cet {sayt}; from (H7750) suwt; a departure from right, i.e. Sin -- revolter, that turn aside. see HEBREW (H7750) suwt
A primitive root; to deviate from duty -- decline, go aside, turn.

Feminine of a derivative (only in the plural shittiym {shit-teem'}; meaning the sticks of wood) from the same as (H7850) shotet; the acacia (from its scourging thorns) -- shittah, shittim. See also (H1029) Beyth hash-Shittah. see HEBREW (H7850) shotet see HEBREW (H1029) Beyth hash-Shittah

column8: all abroad, enlarge, spread, stretch out
column9: A primitive root; to expand -- all abroad, enlarge, spread, stretch out.
Active participle of an otherwise unused root meaning (properly, to pierce; but only as a denominative from (H7752) showt) to flog; a goad -- scourge. see HEBREW (H7752) showt

column7: a place East of the Jordan, also a wadi perhaps West of Jer
column9: The same as the plural of (H7848) shittah; acacia trees; Shittim, a place East of the Jordan -- Shittim. see HEBREW (H7848) shittah

column7: to bear a grudge or cherish animosity against
column9: A primitive root; properly, to lurk for, i.e. Persecute -- hate, oppose self against.

column7: to be or act as adversary
column9: A primitive root; to attack, (figuratively) accuse -- (be an) adversary, resist.

column7: adversary, also the name of the superhuman adversary of God
column9: From (H7853) satan; an opponent; especially (with the article prefixed) Satan, the arch-enemy of good -- adversary, Satan, withstand. see HEBREW (H7853) satan
From (H7853) satan; opposition (by letter) -- accusation. see HEBREW (H7853) satan

column7: hostility, the name of a well near Gerar
column9: The same as (H7855) sitnah; Sitnah, the name of a well in Pal -- Sitnah. see HEBREW (H7855) sitnah

column7: to overflow, rinse or wash off
column8: drown, overflow whelm, rinse, run, rush, thoroughly wash away
column9: A primitive root; to gush; by implication, to inundate, cleanse; by analogy, to gallop, conquer -- drown, (over-)flow(- whelm, rinse, run, rush, (throughly) wash (away).
Or sheteph {shay'-tef}; from (H7857) shataph; a deluge (literally or figuratively) -- flood, outrageous, overflowing. see HEBREW (H7857) shataph
(Aramaic) of uncertain derivation; a side -- side.
Active participle of an otherwise unused root probably meaning to write; properly, a scribe, i.e. (by analogy or implication) an official superintendent or magistrate -- officer, overseer, ruler.
From the same as (H7860) shoter; magisterial; Shitrai, an Israelite -- Shitrai. see HEBREW (H7860) shoter
Probably from (H7737) shavah; a gift (as available) -- present. see HEBREW (H7737) shavah
From the same as (H7721) sow' by permutation; elevation -- excellency. see HEBREW (H7721) sow'
For (H7724) Shva'; Sheja, an Israelite -- Sheva (from the margin). see HEBREW (H7724) Shva'
From (H7863) siy'; peak; Sion, the summit of Mt. Hermon -- Sion. see HEBREW (H7863) siy'
From the same as (H7722) show'; ruin; Shijon, a place in Palestine --Shihon. see HEBREW (H7722) show'
A primitive root; properly, to become aged, i.e. (by implication) to grow gray -- (be) grayheaded.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7867) siyb -- elder. see HEBREW (H7867) siyb
From (H7867) siyb; old age -- age. see HEBREW (H7867) siyb
By permutation from (H7725) shuwb; a return (of property) -- captivity. see HEBREW (H7725) shuwb
From (H3427) yashab; residence -- while...lay. see HEBREW (H3427) yashab

column8: be gray grey hoar, old age
column9: Feminine of (H7869) seyb; old age -- (be) gray (grey hoar,-y) hairs (head,-ed), old age. see HEBREW (H7869) seyb
From (H7734) suwg; a withdrawal (into a private place) -- pursuing. see HEBREW (H7734) suwg
A primitive root probably meaning to boil up (compare (H7736) shuwd); used only as denominative from (H7875) siyd; to plaster -- plaister. see HEBREW (H7736) shuwd see HEBREW (H7875) siyd
From (H7874) siyd; lime (as boiling when slacked) -- lime, plaister. see HEBREW (H7874) siyd
A primitive root; to keep in memory -- be unmindful. (Render Deuteronomy 32:18, \"A Rock bore thee, thou must recollect; and (yet) thou hast forgotten,\" etc.)
Of unknown derivation; Shiza, an Is. -- Shiza.

column8: commune, complain, declare, meditate, muse, pray, speak, talk with
column9: A primitive root; to ponder, i.e. (by implication) converse (with oneself, and hence, aloud) or (transitively) utter -- commune, complain, declare, meditate, muse, pray, speak, talk (with).

column8: babbling, communication, complaint, meditation, prayer, talk
column9: From (H7878) siyach; a contemplation; by implication, an utterance -- babbling, communication, complaint, meditation, prayer, talk. see HEBREW (H7878) siyach
From (H7878) siyach; a shoot (as if uttered or put forth), i.e. (generally) shrubbery -- bush, plant, shrub. see HEBREW (H7878) siyach
Feminine of (H7879) siyach; reflection; be extension, devotion -- meditation, prayer. see HEBREW (H7879) siyach
For (H7745) shuwchah; a pit-fall -- pit. see HEBREW (H7745) shuwchah

column7: a stream on the border of Egypt
column9: Or Shichowr {shee-khore'}; or Shichor {shee-khore'}; probably from (H7835) shachar; dark, i.e. Turbid; Shichor, a stream of Egypt -- Shihor, Sihor. see HEBREW (H7835) shachar
From the same as (H7883) Shiychowr and (H3835) laban; darkish whiteness; Shichor-Libnath, a stream of Palestine -- Shihor-libnath. see HEBREW (H7883) Shiychowr see HEBREW (H3835) laban
From (H7751) shuwt; an oar; also (compare (H7752) showt) a scourge (figuratively) -- oar, scourge. see HEBREW (H7751) shuwt see HEBREW (H7752) showt

column7: perhaps "he whose it is", a Messianic title
column9: From (H7951) shalah; tranquil; Shiloh, an epithet of the Messiah -- Shiloh. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
Or Shiloh {shee-lo'}; or Shiylow {shee-lo'}; or Shilow {shee-lo'}; from the same as (H7886) Shiyloh; Shiloh, a place in Palestine -- Shiloh. see HEBREW (H7886) Shiyloh
Or Shiyloniy {shee-lo-nee'}; or Shiloniy {shee-lo-nee'}; from (H7887) Shiyloh; a Shilonite or inhabitant of Shiloh -- Shilonite. see HEBREW (H7887) Shiyloh
Apparently for (H3452) yshiymown; desert; Shimon, an Israelite -- Shimon. see HEBREW (H3452) yshiymown
From an unused root meaning to urinate; urine -- piss.

Or (the original form) shuwr (1 Sam. 18:6) {shoor}; a primitive root (identical with (H7788) shuwr through the idea of strolling minstrelsy); to sing -- behold (by mistake for (H7789) shuwr), sing(-er, -ing man, - ing woman). see HEBREW (H7788) shuwr see HEBREW (H7789) shuwr
Or feminine shiyrah {shee-raw'}; from (H7891) shiyr; a song; abstractly, singing -- musical(-ick), X sing(-er, -ing), song. see HEBREW (H7891) shiyr
From an unused root meaning to bleach, i.e. Whiten; white, i.e. Marble. See (H8336) shesh. see HEBREW (H8336) shesh
From the same as (H7893) shayish; whiteness; Shisha, an Israelite -- Shisha. see HEBREW (H7893) shayish
Or Shuwshaq {shoo-shak'}; of Egyptian derivation; Shishak, an Egyptian king -- Shishak.

column8: apply, appoint, array, bring, consider, lay up, let alone, look,
column9: A primitive root; to place (in a very wide application) -- apply, appoint, array, bring, consider, lay (up), let alone, X look, make, mark, put (on), + regard, set, shew, be stayed, X take.
From (H7896) shiyth; a dress (as put on) -- attire. see HEBREW (H7896) shiyth
From (H7896) shiyth; scrub or trash, i.e. Wild growth of weeds or briers (as if put on the field) -- thorns. see HEBREW (H7896) shiyth
From (H5526) cakak in the sense of (H7753) suwk; a brier (as of a hedge) -- prick. see HEBREW (H5526) cakak see HEBREW (H7753) suwk
From (H5526) cakak in the sense of (H7753) suwk; a booth (as interlaced) -- tabernacle. see HEBREW (H5526) cakak see HEBREW (H7753) suwk

column8: cast down, lay self down, make to lie down, down to sleep, still with, lodge, ravish,
column9: A primitive root; to lie down (for rest, sexual connection, decease or any other purpose) -- X at all, cast down, ((lover-))lay (self) (down), (make to) lie (down, down to sleep, still with), lodge, ravish, take rest, sleep, stay.
From (H7901) shakab; a lying down (of dew, or for the sexual act) -- X carnally, copulation, X lay, seed. see HEBREW (H7901) shakab
From (H7901) shakab; a (sexual) lying with -- X lie. see HEBREW (H7901) shakab
A primitive root; to roam (through lust) -- in the morning (by mistake for (H7925) shakam). see HEBREW (H7925) shakam
Feminine of (H7900) sok in the sense of (H7899) sek; a dart (as pointed like a thorn) -- barbed iron. see HEBREW (H7900) sok see HEBREW (H7899) sek
From an unused root apparently meaning to surmount; an observatory (with the article); Seku, a place in Palestine -- Sechu.
From the same as (H7906) Sekuw; observant, i.e. (concretely) the mind -- heart. see HEBREW (H7906) Sekuw
Infinitive of (H7921) shakol; bereavement -- loss of children, spoiling. see HEBREW (H7921) shakol

column8: barren, bereaved robbed of children whelps
column9: Or shakkul {shak-kool'}; from (H7921) shakol; bereaved -- barren, bereaved (robbed) of children (whelps). see HEBREW (H7921) shakol
Or shikkor {shik-kore'}; from (H7937) shakar; intoxicated, as a state or a habit -- drunk(-ard, -en, -en man). see HEBREW (H7937) shakar
Or shakeach {shaw-kay'-akh}; a primitive root; to mislay, i.e. To be oblivious of, from want of memory or attention -- X at all, (cause to) forget.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7911) shakach through the idea of disclosure of a covered or forgotten thing; to discover (literally or figuratively) -- find. see HEBREW (H7911) shakach
From (H7911) shakach; oblivious -- forget. see HEBREW (H7911) shakach
Feminine from the same as (H7906) Sekuw; a conspicuous object -- picture. see HEBREW (H7906) Sekuw
Intensive perhaps from the same as (H7906) Sekuw in the sense of (H7753) suwk; a knife (as pointed or edged) -- knife. see HEBREW (H7906) Sekuw see HEBREW (H7753) suwk
From (H7936) sakar; a man at wages by the day or year -- hired (man, servant), hireling. see HEBREW (H7936) sakar
Feminine of (H7916) sakiyr; a hiring -- that is hired. see HEBREW (H7916) sakiyr

column8: appease, assuage, make to cease, pacify, set
column9: A primitive root; to weave (i.e. Lay) a trap; figuratively, (through the idea of secreting) to allay (passions; physically, abate a flood) -- appease, assuage, make to cease, pacify, set.

column8: consider, expert, instruct, prosper, deal prudently, give skillful, have good success, teach,
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, make or act) circumspect and hence, intelligent -- consider, expert, instruct, prosper, (deal) prudent(-ly), (give) skill(-ful), have good success, teach, (have, make to) understand(-ing), wisdom, (be, behave self, consider, make) wise(- ly), guide wittingly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7919) sakal -- consider. see HEBREW (H7919) sakal

column8: bereave of children, barren, cast calf fruit, make childless, deprive, destroy
column9: A primitive root; properly, to miscarry, i.e. Suffer abortion; by analogy, to bereave (literally or figuratively) -- bereave (of children), barren, cast calf (fruit, young), be (make) childless, deprive, destroy, X expect, lose children, miscarry, rob of children, spoil.

column8: discretion, knowledge, policy, prudence, sense, understanding, wisdom, wise
column9: Or sekel {say'-kel}; from (H7919) sakal; intelligence; by implication, success -- discretion, knowledge, policy, prudence, sense, understanding, wisdom, wise. see HEBREW (H7919) sakal

column8: to have after loss of others
column9: Plural from (H7921) shakol; childlessness (by continued bereavements) -- to have after loss of others. see HEBREW (H7921) shakol
(Aramaic) from (H7920) skal; intelligence -- understanding. see HEBREW (H7920) skal

column8: arise, be up, get oneself up, rise up early betimes, morning
column9: A primitive root; properly, to incline (the shoulder to a burden); but used only as denominative from (H7926) shkem; literally, to load up (on the back of man or beast), i.e. To start early in the morning -- (arise, be up, get (oneself) up, rise up) early (betimes), morning. see HEBREW (H7926) shkem
From (H7925) shakam; the neck (between the shoulders) as the place of burdens; figuratively, the spur of a hill -- back, X consent, portion, shoulder. see HEBREW (H7925) shakam

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine
column7: ridge, a district in Northern Palestine, also a son of Hamor
column9: The same as (H7926) shkem; ridge; Shekem, a place in Palestine -- Shechem. see HEBREW (H7926) shkem
For (H7926) shkem; Shekem, the name of a Hivite and two Israelites -- Shechem. see HEBREW (H7926) shkem
Feminine of (H7926) shkem; the shoulder-bone -- shoulder blade. see HEBREW (H7926) shkem
Patronymic from (H7928) Shekem; a Shikmite (collectively), or descendants of Shekem -- Shichemites. see HEBREW (H7928) Shekem

column8: abide, continue, cause to, make to dweller, have habitation, inhabit, lay, place,
column9: A primitive root (apparently akin (by transmission) to (H7901) shakab through the idea of lodging; compare (H5531) cikluwth, (H7925) shakam); to reside or permanently stay (literally or figuratively) -- abide, continue, (cause to, make to) dwell(-er), have habitation, inhabit, lay, place, (cause to) remain, rest, set (up). see HEBREW (H5531) cikluwth see HEBREW (H7925) shakam
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7931) shakan -- cause to dwell, have habitation. see HEBREW (H7931) shakan
From (H7931) shakan; a residence -- habitation. see HEBREW (H7931) shakan
From (H7931) shakan; a resident; by extension, a fellow-citizen -- inhabitant, neighbour, nigh. see HEBREW (H7931) shakan

column7: Yah has taken up His abode, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or (prol.) Shkanyahuw {shek-an-yaw'-hoo}; from (H7931) shakan and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has dwelt; Shekanjah, the name of nine Israelites -- Shecaniah, Shechaniah. see HEBREW (H7931) shakan see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column8: earn wages, hire out self, reward, surely
column9: Or (by permutation) cakar (Ezra 4:5) {saw-kar'}; a primitive root (apparently akin (by prosthesis) to (H3739) karah through the idea of temporary purchase; compare (H7937) shakar); to hire -- earn wages, hire (out self), reward, X surely. see HEBREW (H3739) karah see HEBREW (H7937) shakar

column7: to be or become drunk or drunken
column8: be filled with drink abundantly, be, make drunken, be merry
column9: A primitive root; to become tipsy; in a qualified sense, to satiate with a stimulating drink or (figuratively) influence -- (be filled with) drink (abundantly), (be, make) drunk(-en), be merry. (Superlative of (H8248) shaqah.) see HEBREW (H8248) shaqah
From (H7936) sakar; wages -- reward, sluices. see HEBREW (H7936) sakar
From (H7936) sakar; payment of contract; concretely, salary, fare, maintenance; by implication, compensation, benefit -- hire, price, reward(-ed), wages, worth. see HEBREW (H7936) sakar
The same as (H7939) sakar; recompense; Sakar, the name of two Israelites -- Sacar. see HEBREW (H7939) sakar
From (H7937) shakar; an intoxicant, i.e. Intensely alcoholic liquor -- strong drink, + drunkard, strong wine. see HEBREW (H7937) shakar

column7: a city on N.W. border of Judah
column9: For (H7943) shikkarown; drunkenness, Shikkeron, a place in Palestine -- Shicron. see HEBREW (H7943) shikkarown
From (H7937) shakar; intoxication -- (be) drunken(-ness). see HEBREW (H7937) shakar
From (H7952) shalah abbrev.; a fault -- error. see HEBREW (H7952) shalah
For the rel. (H834) 'aher; used with prepositional prefix, and often followed by some pronominal affix; on account of, whatsoever, whichsoever -- cause, sake. see HEBREW (H834) 'aher
For (H7600) sha'anan; tranquil -- being at ease. see HEBREW (H7600) sha'anan
A primitive root; to space off; intensive (evenly) to make equidistant -- equally distant, set in order.
From (H7947) shalab; a spacer or raised interval, i.e. The stile in a frame or panel -- ledge. see HEBREW (H7947) shalab
A primitive root; properly, meaning to be white; used only as denominative from (H7950) sheleg; to be snow-white (with the linen clothing of the slain) -- be as snow. see HEBREW (H7950) sheleg
From (H7949) shalag; snow (probably from its whiteness) -- snow(-y). see HEBREW (H7949) shalag

column7: to be quiet or at ease
column8: be happy, prosper, be in safety
column9: Or shalav (Job 3:26) {shaw-lav'}; a primitive root; to be tranquil, i.e. Secure or successful -- be happy, prosper, be in safety.
A primitive root (probably identical with (H7953) shalah through the idea of educing); to mislead -- deceive, be negligent. see HEBREW (H7953) shalah

A primitive root (rather cognate (by contraction) to the base of (H5394) nashal, (H7997) shalal and their congeners through the idea of extracting); to draw out or off, i.e. Remove (the soul by death) -- take away. see HEBREW (H5394) nashal see HEBREW (H7997) shalal
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7951) shalah; to be secure -- at rest. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H7952) shalah; a wrong -- thing amiss. see HEBREW (H7952) shalah
The same as (H7596) sh'elah (shortened); request; Shelah, the name of a postdiluvian patriarch and of an Israelite -- Shelah. see HEBREW (H7596) sh'elah
From the same as (H3851) lahab with sibilant prefix; a flare of fire -- (flaming) flame. see HEBREW (H3851) lahab
Or slayv {sel-awv'}; by orthographical variation from (H7951) shalah through the idea of sluggishness; the quail collectively (as slow in flight from its weight) -- quails.
From (H7951) shalah; security -- prosperity. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
(Aramaic) or shaluwth (Aramaic) {shaw-looth'}; from the same as (H7955) shalah; a fault -- error, X fail, thing amiss. see HEBREW (H7955) shalah

column8: being at ease, peaceable, in prosperity, quietness, wealthy
column9: Or shaleyv {shaw-lave'}; feminine shlevah {shel-ay-vaw'}; from (H7951) shalah; tranquil; (in a bad sense) careless; abstractly, security -- (being) at ease, peaceable, (in) prosper(-ity), quiet(-ness), wealthy. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
From (H7951) shalah; security (genuine or false) -- abundance, peace(-ably), prosperity, quietness. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7962) shalvah; safety -- tranquillity. See also (H7961) shalev. see HEBREW (H7962) shalvah see HEBREW (H7961) shalev

Or shilluach {shil-loo'-akh}; from (H7971) shalach; (only in plural) a dismissal, i.e. (of a wife) divorce (especially the document); also (of a daughter) dower -- presents, have sent back. see HEBREW (H7971) shalach

column8: well,  favor, friend, great, good health, perfect,
column9: Or shalom {shaw-lome'}; from (H7999) shalam; safe, i.e. (figuratively) well, happy, friendly; also (abstractly) welfare, i.e. Health, prosperity, peace -- X do, familiar, X fare, favour, + friend, X great, (good) health, (X perfect, such as be at) peace(-able, -ably), prosper(-ity, -ous), rest, safe(-ty), salute, welfare, (X all is, be) well, X wholly. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam
Or shillum {shil-loom'}; from (H7999) shalam; a requital, i.e. (secure) retribution, (venal) a fee -- recompense, reward. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam

column7: the name of a number of Isr
column9: Or (shorter) Shallum {shal-loom'}; the same as (H7966) shilluwm; Shallum, the name of fourteen Israelites -- Shallum. see HEBREW (H7966) shilluwm

column7: one of the postexilic wall builders
column9: Probably for (H7967) Shalluwm; Shallun, an Israelite -- Shallum. see HEBREW (H7967) Shalluwm

column8: fork, oftentimes, third, thirteen three, thrice
column9: Or shalosh {shaw-loshe'}; masculine shlowshah {shel-o-shaw'}; or shloshah {shel-o-shaw'}; a primitive number; three; occasionally (ordinal) third, or (multipl.) Thrice -- + fork, + often(-times), third, thir(-teen, -teenth), three, + thrice. Compare (H7991) shaliysh. see HEBREW (H7991) shaliysh
Or shloshiym {shel-o-sheem'}; multiple of (H7969) shalowsh; thirty; or (ordinal) thirtieth -- thirty, thirtieth. Compare (H7991) shaliysh. see HEBREW (H7969) shalowsh see HEBREW (H7991) shaliysh

A primitive root; to send away, for, or out (in a great variety of applications) -- X any wise, appoint, bring (on the way), cast (away, out), conduct, X earnestly, forsake, give (up), grow long, lay, leave, let depart (down, go, loose), push away, put (away, forth, in, out), reach forth, send (away, forth, out), set, shoot (forth, out), sow, spread, stretch forth (out).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7971) shalach -- put, send. see HEBREW (H7971) shalach

column8: dart, plant, put off, sword, weapon
column9: From (H7971) shalach; a missile of attack, i.e. Spear; also (figuratively) a shoot of growth; i.e. Branch -- dart, plant, X put off, sword, weapon. see HEBREW (H7971) shalach
The same as (H7973) shelach; Shelach, a postdiluvian patriarch -- Salah, Shelah. Compare (H7975) Shiloach. see HEBREW (H7973) shelach see HEBREW (H7975) Shiloach

Or (in imitation of (H7974) Shelach) Shelach (Neh. 3:15) {sheh'-lakh}; from (H7971) shalach; rill; Shiloach, a fountain of Jerusalem -- Shiloah, Siloah. see HEBREW (H7974) Shelach see HEBREW (H7971) shalach
Feminine of (H7964) shilluwach; a shoot -- branch. see HEBREW (H7964) shilluwach
From (H7973) shelach; missive, i.e. Armed; Shilchi, an Israelite -- Shilhi. see HEBREW (H7973) shelach
Plural of (H7973) shelach; javelins or sprouts; Shilchim, a place in Palestine -- Shilhim. see HEBREW (H7973) shelach
From (H7971) shalach; a table (as spread out); by implication, a meal -- table. see HEBREW (H7971) shalach

column8: bear, have rule, have dominion, give have power
column9: A primitive root; to dominate, i.e. Govern; by implication, to permit -- (bear, have) rule, have dominion, give (have) power.

column8: have the mastery, have power, bear rule, be make ruler
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H7980) shalat -- have the mastery, have power, bear rule, be (make) ruler. see HEBREW (H7980) shalat
From (H7980) shalat; probably a shield (as controlling, i.e. Protecting the person) -- shield. see HEBREW (H7980) shalat
(Aramaic) from (H7980) shalat; a potentate; --power. see HEBREW (H7980) shalat
(Aramaic) or shilton {shil-tone'}; corresponding to (H7983) shiltown -- ruler. see HEBREW (H7983) shiltown
(Aramaic) from (H7981) shlet; empire (abstractly or concretely) -- dominion. see HEBREW (H7981) shlet
Feminine from (H7980) shalat; a vixen -- imperious. see HEBREW (H7980) shalat
From (H7951) shalah; privacy -- + quietly. see HEBREW (H7951) shalah
Feminine from (H7953) shalah; a fetus or babe (as extruded in birth) -- young one. see HEBREW (H7953) shalah

column8: governor, mighty, that hath power, ruler
column9: From (H7980) shalat; potent; concretely, a prince or warrior -- governor, mighty, that hath power, ruler. see HEBREW (H7980) shalat
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7989) shalliyt; mighty; abstractly, permission; concretely, a premier -- captain, be lawful, rule(- r). see HEBREW (H7989) shalliyt

column8: captain, instrument of music, great lord, great measure, prince, three
column9: Or shalowsh (1 Chron. 11:11; 12:18) {shaw- loshe'}; or shalosh (2 Sam. 23:13) {shaw-loshe'}; from (H7969) shalowsh; a triple, i.e. (as a musical instrument) a triangle (or perhaps rather three-stringed lute); also (as an indefinite, great quantity) a three-fold measure (perhaps a treble ephah); also (as an officer) a general of the third rank (upward, i.e. The highest) -- captain, instrument of musick, (great) lord, (great) measure, prince, three (from the margin). see HEBREW (H7969) shalowsh

column8: third part, rank, time, three years old
column9: Ordinal from (H7969) shalowsh; third; feminine a third (part); by extension, a third (day, year or time); specifically, a third-story cell) -- third (part, rank, time), three (years old). see HEBREW (H7969) shalowsh

column8: adventure, cast away, down, forth, off, out, hurl, pluck,
column9: A primitive root; to throw out, down or away (literally or figuratively) -- adventure, cast (away, down, forth, off, out), hurl, pluck, throw.
From (H7993) shalak; bird of prey, usually thought to be the pelican (from casting itself into the sea) -- cormorant. see HEBREW (H7993) shalak
From (H7993) shalak; a felling (of trees) -- when cast. see HEBREW (H7993) shalak

column7: (gate of) casting forth, a temple gate on the west side
column9: The same as (H7995) shalleketh; Shalleketh, a gate in Jerusalem -- Shalleketh. see HEBREW (H7995) shalleketh

column8: let fall, make self a prey, of purpose, make a, take spoil
column9: A primitive root; to drop or strip; by implication, to plunder -- let fall, make self a prey, X of purpose, (make a, (take)) spoil.
From (H7997) shalal; booty -- prey, spoil. see HEBREW (H7997) shalal

column8: make amends, make an end, finish, full, give again, make good, repay again
column9: A primitive root; to be safe (in mind, body or estate); figuratively, to be (causatively, make) completed; by implication, to be friendly; by extension, to reciprocate (in various applications) -- make amends, (make an) end, finish, full, give again, make good, (re-)pay (again), (make) (to) (be at) peace(-able), that is perfect, perform, (make) prosper(-ous), recompense, render, requite, make restitution, restore, reward, X surely.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7999) shalam; to complete, to restore -- deliver, finish. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7965) shalowm; prosperity -- peace. see HEBREW (H7965) shalowm

column7: a sacrifice for alliance or friendship, peace offering
column9: From (H7999) shalam; properly, requital, i.e. A (voluntary) sacrifice in thanks -- peace offering. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam

column8: full, just, made ready, peaceable, perfected, quiet
column9: From (H7999) shalam; complete (literally or figuratively); especially friendly -- full, just, made ready, peaceable, perfect(-ed), quiet, Shalem (by mistake for a name), whole. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam

column7: peaceful, an early name of Jer
column9: The same as (H8003) shalem; peaceful; Shalem, an early name of Jerusalem -- Salem. see HEBREW (H8003) shalem
From (H7999) shalam; requital -- recompense. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam
The same as (H8005) shillem; Shillem, an Israelite -- Shillem. see HEBREW (H8005) shillem

column7: father of Boaz, also the founder of Bethlehem
column9: Probably for (H8008) salmah; clothing; Salma, the name of two Israelites -- Salma. see HEBREW (H8008) salmah
Transp. For (H8071) simlah; a dress -- clothes, garment, raiment. see HEBREW (H8071) simlah
The same as (H8008) salmah; clothing; Salmah, an Israelite -- Salmon. Compare (H8012) Salmown. see HEBREW (H8008) salmah see HEBREW (H8012) Salmown

column7: David\'s son and successor to his throne
column9: From (H7965) shalowm; peaceful; Shelomah, David's successor -- Solomon. see HEBREW (H7965) shalowm
Feminine of (H7966) shilluwm; retribution -- recompense. see HEBREW (H7966) shilluwm
From (H8008) salmah; investiture; Salmon, an Israelite -- Salmon. Compare (H8009) Salmah. see HEBREW (H8008) salmah see HEBREW (H8009) Salmah

Feminine plural of (H7965) shalowm; pacifications; Shelomoth, the name of two Israelites -- Shelomith (from the margin), Shelomoth. Compare (H8019) Shlomiyth. see HEBREW (H7965) shalowm see HEBREW (H8019) Shlomiyth
From (H8008) salmah; clothed; Salmai, an Israelite -- Shalmai. see HEBREW (H8008) salmah
From (H7965) shalowm; peaceable; Shelomi, an Israelite -- Shelomi. see HEBREW (H7965) shalowm
Patronymically from (H8006) Shillem; a Shilemite (collectively) or descendants of Shillem -- Shillemites. see HEBREW (H8006) Shillem
From (H7965) shalowm and (H410) 'el; peace of God; Shelumiel, an Israelite -- Shelumiel. see HEBREW (H7965) shalowm see HEBREW (H410) 'el

column7: friend of Yah, the name of several Israelites
column9: Or Shelemyahuw {shel-em-yaw'-hoo}; from (H8002) shelem and (H3050) Yahh; thank-offering of Jah; Shelemjah, the name of nine Israelites -- Shelemiah. see HEBREW (H8002) shelem see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Or Shlowmiyth (Ezra 8:10) {shel-o- meeth'}; from (H7965) shalowm; peaceableness; Shelomith, the name of five Israelites and three Israelitesses -- Shelomith. see HEBREW (H7965) shalowm
Of foreign derivation; Shalman, a king apparently of Assyria -- Shalman. Compare (H8022) Shalman'ecer. see HEBREW (H8022) Shalman'ecer
From (H7999) shalam; a bribe -- reward. see HEBREW (H7999) shalam
Of foreign derivation; Shalmaneser, an Assyrian king -- Shalmaneser. Comp (H8020) Shalman. see HEBREW (H8020) Shalman
The same as (H7888) Shiylowniy; Shiloni, an Israelite -- Shiloni. see HEBREW (H7888) Shiylowniy
From (H7956) Shelah; a Shelanite (collectively), or descendants of Shelah -- Shelanites. see HEBREW (H7956) Shelah

column8: draw off, grow up, pluck off
column9: A primitive root; to pull out, up or off -- draw (off), grow up, pluck off.

column7: drawn out, a son of Joktan and his desc
column9: From (H8025) shalaph; extract; Sheleph, a son of Jokthan -- Sheleph. see HEBREW (H8025) shalaph

column7: to do a third time, divide into three parts
column8: do the third time, divide into, stay three days,
column9: A primitive root perhaps originally to intensify, i.e. Treble; but apparently used only as denominative from (H7969) shalowsh, to be (causatively, make) triplicate (by restoration, in portions, strands, days or years) -- do the third time, (divide into, stay) three (days, - fold, parts, years old). see HEBREW (H7969) shalowsh
From (H8027) shalash; triplet; Shelesh, an Israelite -- Shelesh. see HEBREW (H8027) shalash
From (H8027) shalash; a descendant of the third degree, i.e. Great grandchild -- third (generation). see HEBREW (H8027) shalash
Feminine from the same as (H8028) Shelesh; triplication; Shilshah, an Israelite -- Shilshah. see HEBREW (H8028) Shelesh

column7: an area of Israel searched by Saul
column9: Feminine from (H8027) shalash; trebled land; Shalishah, a place in Palestine -- Shalisha. see HEBREW (H8027) shalash

column7: three days ago, day before, yesterday
column8: before that time, heretofore, three days, time past
column9: Or shilshom {shil-shome'}; from the same as (H8028) Shelesh; trebly, i.e. (in time) day before yesterday -- + before (that time, - time), excellent things (from the margin), + heretofore, three days, + time past. see HEBREW (H8028) Shelesh

column8: in it, thence, there in, of, out, thither, whither
column9: A primitive particle (rather from the relative pronoun, (H834) 'aher); there (transferring to time) then; often thither, or thence -- in it, + thence, there (-in, + of, + out), + thither, + whither. see HEBREW (H834) 'aher

A primitive word (perhaps rather from (H7760) suwm through the idea of definite and conspicuous position; compare (H8064) shamayim); an appellation, as a mark or memorial of individuality; by implication honor, authority, character -- + base, (in-)fame(-ous), named(-d), renown, report. see HEBREW (H7760) suwm see HEBREW (H8064) shamayim
The same as (H8034) shem; name; Shem, a son of Noah (often includ. His posterity) -- Sem, Shem. see HEBREW (H8034) shem
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8034) shem -- name. see HEBREW (H8034) shem
From (H8074) shamem; desolation; Shamma, an Israelite -- Shamma. see HEBREW (H8074) shamem

column7: name of pinion, king of Zeboiim
column9: Apparently from (H8034) shem and (H83) 'eber; name of pinion, i.e. Illustrious; Shemeber, a king of Zeboim -- Shemeber. see HEBREW (H8034) shem see HEBREW (H83) 'eber
Perhaps for (H8093) Shim'ah; Shimah, an Israelite -- Shimah. Compare (H8043) Shim'am. see HEBREW (H8093) Shim'ah see HEBREW (H8043) Shim'am

Or smosl {sem-ole'}; a primitive word (rather perhaps from the same as (H8071) simlah (by insertion of the aleph) through the idea of wrapping up); properly, dark (as enveloped), i.e. The north; hence (by orientation), the left hand -- left (hand, side). see HEBREW (H8071) simlah

column8: go, turn on the, to the left
column9: A primitive root (denominative from (H8040) smo'wl); to use the left hand or pass in that direction) -- (go, turn) (on the, to the) left. see HEBREW (H8040) smo'wl
From (H8040) smo'wl; situated on the left side -- left. see HEBREW (H8040) smo'wl
For (H8039) Shim'ah (compare (H38) 'Abiyam); Shimam, an Israelite -- Shimeam. see HEBREW (H8039) Shim'ah see HEBREW (H38) 'Abiyam
Of uncertain derivation; Shamgar, an Israelite judge -- Shamgar.

column8: destruction, bring to nothing, overthrow, perish, pluck down, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to desolate -- destory(- uction), bring to nought, overthrow, perish, pluck down, X utterly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8045) shamad -- consume. see HEBREW (H8045) shamad
From (H8074) shamem; ruin; by implication, consternation -- astonishment, desolate(-ion), waste, wonderful thing. see HEBREW (H8074) shamem
The same as (H8047) shammah; Shammah, the name of an Edomite and four Israelites -- Shammah. see HEBREW (H8047) shammah
For (H8048) Shammah; desolation; Shamhuth, an Israelite -- Shamhuth. see HEBREW (H8048) Shammah

column7: name of God, a prophet of Isr
column9: From the passive participle of (H8085) shama' and (H410) 'el; heard of God; Shemuel, the name of three Israelites -- Samuel, Shemuel. see HEBREW (H8085) shama' see HEBREW (H410) 'el
From (H8074) shamem; renowned; Shammua, the name of four Israelites -- Shammua, Shammuah. see HEBREW (H8074) shamem

column8: bruit, doctrine, fame, mentioned, news, report, rumor, tidings
column9: Feminine passive participle of (H8074) shamem; something heard, i.e. An announcement -- bruit, doctrine, fame, mentioned, news, report, rumor, tidings. see HEBREW (H8074) shamem
Passive participle of (H8103) shimtsah; observed; Shamur, an Israelite -- Shamir (from the margin). see HEBREW (H8103) shimtsah
Plural of (H8047) shammah; ruins; Shammoth, an Israelite -- Shamoth. see HEBREW (H8047) shammah

column8: cheer up, be make glad, have, make joyful, be make merry, cause to, make to rejoice, very
column9: A primitive root; probably to brighten up, i.e. (figuratively) be (causatively, make) blithe or gleesome -- cheer up, be (make) glad, (have, make) joy(-ful), be (make) merry, (cause to, make to) rejoice, X very.

column8: be glad, joyful, making merry-hearted, rejoicing
column9: From (H8055) samach; blithe or gleeful -- (be) glad, joyful, (making) merry((-hearted), -ily), rejoice(-ing). see HEBREW (H8055) samach

column8: exceedingly, gladness, joyfulness, mirth, pleasure, rejoicing
column9: From (H8056) sameach; blithesomeness or glee, (religious or festival) -- X exceeding(-ly), gladness, joy(-fulness), mirth, pleasure, rejoice(-ing). see HEBREW (H8056) sameach

column8: discontinue, overthrow, release, let rest, shake, stumble, throw down
column9: A primitive root; to fling down; incipiently to jostle; figuratively, to let alone, desist, remit -- discontinue, overthrow, release, let rest, shake, stumble, throw down.
From (H8058) shamat; remission (of debt) or suspension of labor) -- release. see HEBREW (H8058) shamat
From (H8073) Shamlay; destructive; Shammai, the name of three Israelites -- Shammai. see HEBREW (H8073) Shamlay

column7: name of knowing, a man of Manasseh
column9: Apparently from (H8034) shem and (H3045) yada'; name of knowing; Shemida, an Israelite -- Shemida, Shemidah. see HEBREW (H8034) shem see HEBREW (H3045) yada'
Patronymically from (H8061) Shmiyda'; a Shemidaite (collectively) or descendants of Shemida -- Shemidaites. see HEBREW (H8061) Shmiyda'
From (H5564) camak; a run (as sustaining the Oriental sitter) -- mantle. see HEBREW (H5564) camak

Dual of an unused singular shameh {shaw-meh'}; from an unused root meaning to be lofty; the sky (as aloft; the dual perhaps alluding to the visible arch in which the clouds move, as well as to the higher ether where the celestial bodies revolve) -- air, X astrologer, heaven(-s).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8064) shamayim -- heaven. see HEBREW (H8064) shamayim
From (H8083) shmoneh; eight -- eight. see HEBREW (H8083) shmoneh
Feminine of (H8066) shmiyniy; probably an eight-stringed lyre -- Sheminith. see HEBREW (H8066) shmiyniy
From (H8104) shamar in the original sense of pricking; a thorn; also (from its keenness for scratching) a gem, probably the diamond -- adamant (stone), brier, diamond. see HEBREW (H8104) shamar

column7: a city in Judah, also a city in Ephraim
column9: The same as (H8068) shamiyr; Shamir, the name of two places in Palestine -- Shamir. Compare (H8053) Shamuwr. see HEBREW (H8068) shamiyr see HEBREW (H8053) Shamuwr

Or Shmariymowth {shem-aw-ree- moth'}; probably from (H8034) shem and plural of (H7413) ramah; name of heights; Shemiramoth, the name of two Israelites -- Shemiramoth. see HEBREW (H8034) shem see HEBREW (H7413) ramah

Perhaps by permutation for the feminine of (H5566) cemel (through the idea of a cover assuming the shape of the object beneath); a dress, especially a mantle -- apparel, cloth(-es, -ing), garment, raiment. Compare (H8008) salmah. see HEBREW (H5566) cemel see HEBREW (H8008) salmah
Probably for the same as (H8071) simlah; Samlah, an Edomite -- Samlah. see HEBREW (H8071) simlah
For (H8014) Salmay; Shamlai, one of the Nethinim -- Shalmai (from the margin). see HEBREW (H8014) Salmay

column8: make amazed, be astonished, be an astonishment, be, bring into, unto, lay, lie,
column9: A primitive root; to stun (or intransitively, grow numb), i.e. Devastate or (figuratively) stupefy (both usually in a passive sense) -- make amazed, be astonied, (be an) astonish(-ment), (be, bring into, unto, lay, lie, make) desolate(-ion, places), be destitute, destroy (self), (lay, lie, make) waste, wonder.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8074) shamem -- be astonied. see HEBREW (H8074) shamem
From (H8074) shamem; ruined -- desolate. see HEBREW (H8074) shamem
Or shimamah {shee-mam-aw'}; feminine of (H8076) shamem; devastation; figuratively, astonishment -- (laid, X most) desolate(- ion), waste. see HEBREW (H8076) shamem
From (H8074) shamem; stupefaction -- astonishment. see HEBREW (H8074) shamem
Probably from (H8074) shamem (in the sense of poisoning); a lizard (from the superstition of its noxiousness) -- spider. see HEBREW (H8074) shamem
A primitive root; to shine, i.e. (by analogy) be (causatively, make) oily or gross -- become (make, wax) fat.

column8: anointing, fat things, fruitful, oiled, ointment, olive, pine
column9: From (H8080) shaman; grease, especially liquid (as from the olive, often perfumed); figuratively, richness -- anointing, X fat (things), X fruitful, oil((-ed)), ointment, olive, + pine. see HEBREW (H8080) shaman
From (H8080) shaman; greasy, i.e. Gross; figuratively, rich -- fat, lusty, plenteous. see HEBREW (H8080) shaman

Or shmowneh {shem-o-neh'}; feminine shmonah {shem-o-naw'}; or shmownah {shem-o-naw'}; apparently from (H8082) shamen through the idea of plumpness; a cardinal number, eight (as if a surplus above the \"perfect\" seven); also (as ordinal) eighth -- eight((-een, -eenth)), eighth. see HEBREW (H8082) shamen
Or shmowniym {shem-o-neem'}; mult. From (H8083) shmoneh; eighty, also eightieth -- eighty(-ieth), fourscore. see HEBREW (H8083) shmoneh

column8: attentively, call gather together, carefully, certainly, consent, consider
column9: A primitive root; to hear intelligently (often with implication of attention, obedience, etc.; causatively, to tell, etc.) -- X attentively, call (gather) together, X carefully, X certainly, consent, consider, be content, declare, X diligently, discern, give ear, (cause to, let, make to) hear(-ken, tell), X indeed, listen, make (a) noise, (be) obedient, obey, perceive, (make a) proclaim(-ation), publish, regard, report, shew (forth), (make a) sound, X surely, tell, understand, whosoever (heareth), witness.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8085) shama' -- hear, obey. see HEBREW (H8085) shama'
For the same as (H8088) shema'; Shema, the name of a place in Palestine and of four Israelites -- Shema. see HEBREW (H8088) shema'

column8: bruit, fame, hearing, loud, report, speech, tidings
column9: From (H8085) shama'; something heard, i.e. A sound, rumor, announcement; abstractly, audience -- bruit, fame, hear(-ing), loud, report, speech, tidings. see HEBREW (H8085) shama'
From (H8085) shama'; a report -- fame. see HEBREW (H8085) shama'
For (H8087) Shema'; Shema, a place in Palestine -- Shema. see HEBREW (H8087) Shema'
From (H8085) shama'; obedient; Shama, an Israelite -- Shama. see HEBREW (H8085) shama'
For (H8093) Shim'ah; Shima, the name of four Israelites -- Shimea, Shimei, Shamma. see HEBREW (H8093) Shim'ah
Feminine of (H8088) shema'; annunciation; Shimah, an Israelite -- Shimeah. see HEBREW (H8088) shema'

column7: father of two of David\'s warriors
column9: For (H8093) Shim'ah; Shemaah, an Israelite -- Shemaah. see HEBREW (H8093) Shim'ah

column7: a son of Jacob, also his tribe, also an Israelite with a foreign wife
column9: From (H8085) shama'; hearing; Shimon, one of Jacob's sons, also the tribe descended from him -- Simeon. see HEBREW (H8085) shama'

column7: the name of a number of Isr
column9: From (H8088) shema'; famous; Shimi, the name of twenty Israelites -- Shimeah (from the margin), Shimei, Shimhi, Shimi. see HEBREW (H8088) shema'
Patronymically from (H8096) Shim'iy; a Shimite (collectively) or descendants of Shimi -- of Shimi, Shimites. see HEBREW (H8096) Shim'iy

column7: Yah hears, the name of a number of Isr
column9: Or Shmamyahuw {shem-aw-yaw'-hoo}; from (H8085) shama' and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has heard; Shemajah, the name of twenty-five Israelites -- Shemaiah. see HEBREW (H8085) shama' see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Patronymically from (H8095) Shim'own; a Shimonite (collectively) or descendants of Shimon -- tribe of Simeon, Simeonites. see HEBREW (H8095) Shim'own
Feminine of (H8088) shema'; annunciation; Shimath, an Ammonitess -- Shimath. see HEBREW (H8088) shema'
Patronymically from (H8093) Shim'ah; a Shimathite (collectively) or descendants of Shimah -- Shimeathites. see HEBREW (H8093) Shim'ah
From an unused root meaning to emit a sound; an inkling -- a little.
Feminine of (H8102) shemets; scornful whispering (of hostile spectators) -- shame. see HEBREW (H8102) shemets

column8: beward, be circumspect, take heed to self, keeper, self, mark, look narrowly, observe,
column9: A primitive root; properly, to hedge about (as with thorns), i.e. Guard; generally, to protect, attend to, etc. -- beward, be circumspect, take heed (to self), keep(-er, self), mark, look narrowly, observe, preserve, regard, reserve, save (self), sure, (that lay) wait (for), watch(-man).
From (H8104) shamar; something preserved, i.e. The settlings (plural only) of wine -- dregs, (wines on the) lees. see HEBREW (H8104) shamar
The same as (H8105) shemer; Shemer, the name of three Israelites -- Shamer, Shemer. see HEBREW (H8105) shemer
From (H8104) shamar; an observance -- X be (much) observed. see HEBREW (H8104) shamar
Feminine of an unused noun from (H8104) shamar meaning a guard; watchfulness -- watch. see HEBREW (H8104) shamar
Feminine of passive participle of (H8104) shamar; something guarded, i.e. An eye-lid -- waking. see HEBREW (H8104) shamar

column4: proper name, of a location; proper name, masculine
column9: From (H8105) shemer in its original sense; guardianship; Shimron, the name of an Israelite and of a place in Palestine -- Shimron. see HEBREW (H8105) shemer

column7: capital of N. kingdom of Isr
column9: From the active participle of (H8104) shamar; watch-station; Shomeron, a place in Palestine -- Samaria. see HEBREW (H8104) shamar

column7: a Canaanite city conquered by Joshua
column9: From (H8110) Shimrown and a derivative of (H4754) mara'; guard of lashing; Shimron-Meron, a place in Palestine -- Shimon-meron. see HEBREW (H8110) Shimrown see HEBREW (H4754) mara'
From (H8105) shemer in its original sense; watchful; Shimri, the name of four Israelites -- Shimri. see HEBREW (H8105) shemer

Or Shmaryahuw {shem-ar-yaw'-hoo}; from (H8104) shamar and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has guarded; Shemarjah, the name of four Israelites -- Shamariah, Shemariah. see HEBREW (H8104) shamar see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh

column7: capital of N. kingdom of Isr
column9: (Aramaic) corresponding to (H8111) Shomrown; Shomrain, a place in Palestine -- Samaria. see HEBREW (H8111) Shomrown
Feminine of (H8113) Shimriy; female guard; Shimrith, a Moabitess -- Shimrith. see HEBREW (H8113) Shimriy
Patronymically from (H8110) Shimrown; a Shimronite (collectively) or descendants of Shimron -- Shimronites. see HEBREW (H8110) Shimrown
Patrial from (H8111) Shomrown; a Shomeronite (collectively) or inhabitants of Shomeron -- Samaritans. see HEBREW (H8111) Shomrown
From (H8104) shamar; guardship; Shimrath, an Israelite -- Shimrath. see HEBREW (H8104) shamar
(Aramaic) corresponding to the root of (H8121) shemesh through the idea of activity implied in day-light; to serve -- minister. see HEBREW (H8121) shemesh

column8: east sideward, sun rising, westward, window
column9: From an unused root meaning to be brilliant; the sun; by implication, the east; figuratively, a ray, i.e. (arch.) A notched battlement -- + east side(-ward), sun ((rising)), + west(-ward), window. See also (H1053) Beyth Shemesh. see HEBREW (H1053) Beyth Shemesh
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8121) shemesh; the sun -- sun. see HEBREW (H8121) shemesh
From (H8121) shemesh; sunlight; Shimshon, an Israelite -- Samson. see HEBREW (H8121) shemesh
(Aramaic) from (H8122) shemesh; sunny; Shimshai, a Samaritan -- Shimshai. see HEBREW (H8122) shemesh
Apparently from (H8121) shemesh; sunlike; Shamsherai, an Israelite -- Shamsherai. see HEBREW (H8121) shemesh
Patronymically from an unused name from (H7762) shuwm probably meaning garlic-smell; a Shumathite (collectively) or descendants of Shumah -- Shumathites. see HEBREW (H7762) shuwm

From (H8150) shanan; a tooth (as sharp); specifically (for (H8143) shenhabbiym) ivory; figuratively, a cliff -- crag, X forefront, ivory, X sharp, tooth. see HEBREW (H8150) shanan see HEBREW (H8143) shenhabbiym
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8127) shen; a tooth -- tooth. see HEBREW (H8127) shen
The same as (H8127) shen; crag; Shen, a place in Palestine -- Shen. see HEBREW (H8127) shen

column8: enemy, foe, be hateful odious, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to hate (personally) -- enemy, foe, (be) hate(-ful, -r), odious, X utterly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8130) sane' -- hate. see HEBREW (H8130) sane'
A primitive root; to alter -- change.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8132) shana -- alter, change, (be) diverse. see HEBREW (H8132) shana
Probably from (H8132) shana and (H1) 'ab; a father has turned; Shinab, a Canaanite -- Shinab. see HEBREW (H8132) shana see HEBREW (H1) 'ab
From (H8130) sane'; hate -- + exceedingly, hate(-ful, - red). see HEBREW (H8130) sane'
From (H8132) shana; change, i.e. Repetition -- X angels. see HEBREW (H8132) shana
Apparently of Babylonian origin; Shenatstsar, an Israelite -- Senazar.

column8: do speak, strike again, alter, double, be given to change, disguise, be diverse, pervert,
column9: A primitive root; to fold, i.e. Duplicate (literally or figuratively); by implication, to transmute (transitive or intransitive) -- do (speak, strike) again, alter, double, (be given to) change, disguise, (be) diverse, pervert, prefer, repeat, return, do the second time.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8142) shehah -- sleep. see HEBREW (H8142) shehah
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8141) shaneh -- year. see HEBREW (H8141) shaneh
(in plura or (feminine) shanah {shaw-naw'}; from (H8138) shanah; a year (as a revolution of time) -- + whole age, X long, + old, year(X -ly). see HEBREW (H8138) shanah
Or shena (Psa. 127:2) {shay-naw'}; from (H3462) yashen; sleep -- sleep. see HEBREW (H3462) yashen
From (H8127) shen and the plural apparently of a foreign word; probably, tooth of elephants, i.e. Ivory tusk -- ivory. see HEBREW (H8127) shen
Of uncertain derivation; crimson, properly, the insect or its color, also stuff dyed with it -- crimson, scarlet (thread).

column8: again, either of them, another, second time
column9: From (H8138) shanah; properly, double, i.e. Second; also adverbially, again -- again, either (of them), (an-)other, second (time). see HEBREW (H8138) shanah
From (H8130) sane'; hated -- hated. see HEBREW (H8130) sane'

Dual of (H8145) sheniy; feminine shttayim {shet-tah'-yim}; two; also (as ordinal) twofold -- both, couple, double, second, twain, + twelfth, + twelve, + twenty (sixscore) thousand, twice, two. see HEBREW (H8145) sheniy
From (H8150) shanan; something pointed, i.e. A gibe -- byword, taunt. see HEBREW (H8150) shanan
Or Sniyr {sen-eer'}; from an unused root meaning to be pointed; peak; Shenir or Senir, a summit of Lebanon -- Senir, Shenir.
A primitive root; to point (transitive or intransitive); intensively, to pierce; figuratively, to inculcate -- prick, sharp(-en), teach diligently, whet.
A primitive root; to compress (with a belt) -- gird up.
Probably of foreign derivation; Shinar, a plain in Babylonia -- Shinar.
From (H3462) yashen; sleep -- sleep. see HEBREW (H3462) yashen
Or shasah (Isa. 10:13) {shaw-saw'}; a primitive root; to plunder -- destroyer, rob, spoil(-er).
A primitive root; to plunder -- rifle, spoil.

column8: cleave, be cloven footed, rend, stay
column9: A primitive root; to split or tear; figuratively, to upbraid -- cleave, (be) cloven ((footed)), rend, stay.
From (H8156) shaca'; a fissure -- cleft, clovenfooted. see HEBREW (H8156) shaca'
A primitive root; to cut in pieces, i.e. Slaughter -- hew in pieces.

column8: depart, be dim, be dismayed, look away, regard, have respect, spare, turn
column9: A primitive root; to gaze at or about (properly, for help); by implication, to inspect, consider, compassionate, be nonplussed (as looking around in amazement) or bewildered -- depart, be dim, be dismayed, look (away), regard, have respect, spare, turn.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H8159) sha'ah; properly, a look, i.e. A moment -- hour. see HEBREW (H8159) sha'ah
Feminine from an unused root meaning to stamp; a clatter (of hoofs) -- stamping.

column8: garment of divers sorts, linen and wollen
column9: Probably of foreign derivation; linsey- woolsey, i.e. Cloth of linen and wool carded and spun together -- garment of divers sorts, linen and wollen.

column8: devil, goat, hairy, kid, rough, satyr
column9: Or sabir {saw-eer'}; from (H8175) sa'ar; shaggy; as noun, a he-goat; by analogy, a faun -- devil, goat, hairy, kid, rough, satyr. see HEBREW (H8175) sa'ar
Formed the same as (H8163) sa'iyr; a shower (as tempestuous) -- small rain. see HEBREW (H8163) sa'iyr

column4: proper name; mont.; of a people; masculine; mont.
column7: a mountain range in Edom, also its inhab., also a mountain in Judah
column9: Formed like (H8163) sa'iyr; rough; Seir, a mountain of Idumaea and its aboriginal occupants, also one in Palestine -- Seir. see HEBREW (H8163) sa'iyr
Feminine of (H8163) sa'iyr; a she-goat -- kid. see HEBREW (H8163) sa'iyr
Formed as (H8166) s'iyrah; roughness; Seirah, a place in Palestine -- Seirath. see HEBREW (H8166) s'iyrah
From an unused root meaning to hollow out; the palm; by extension, a handful -- handful, hollow of the hand.

column7: perhaps "(haunt of) foxes", a city in Dan
column9: Or Sha.alabbiyn {shah-al-ab-been'}; plural from (H7776) shuw'al; fox-holes; Shaalbim or Shaalabbin, a place in Palestine -- Shaalabbin, Shaalbim. see HEBREW (H7776) shuw'al
Patrial from (H8169) Sha'albiym; a Shaalbonite or inhabitant of Shaalbin -- Shaalbonite. see HEBREW (H8169) Sha'albiym
Plural of (H7776) shuw'al; foxes; Shaalim, a place in Palestine -- Shalim. see HEBREW (H7776) shuw'al

column8: lean, lie, rely, rest on, self, stay
column9: A primitive root; to support one's self -- lean, lie, rely, rest (on, self), stay.

A primitive root; (in a good acceptation) to look upon (with complacency), i.e. Fondle, please or amuse (self); (in a bad one) to look about (in dismay), i.e. Stare -- cry (out) (by confusion with (H7768) shava'), dandle, delight (self), play, shut. see HEBREW (H7768) shava'
From (H5586) ca'aph; fluctuation; Shaaph, the name of two Israelites -- Shaaph. see HEBREW (H5586) ca'aph

column8: be horribly afraid, fear, hurl as a storm, be tempestuous
column9: A primitive root; to storm; by implication, to shiver, i.e. Fear -- be (horribly) afraid, fear, hurl as a storm, be tempestuous, come like (take away as with) a whirlwind.

A primitive root; to split or open, i.e. (literally, but only as denominative from (H8179) sha'ar) to act as gate-keeper (see (H7778) show'er): (figuratively) to estimate -- think. see HEBREW (H8179) sha'ar see HEBREW (H7778) show'er
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8181) se'ar; hair -- hair. see HEBREW (H8181) se'ar
From (H8175) sa'ar; a tempest; also a terror -- affrighted, X horribly, X sore, storm. See (H8181) se'ar. see HEBREW (H8175) sa'ar see HEBREW (H8181) se'ar
From (H8176) sha'ar in its original sense; an opening, i.e. Door or gate -- city, door, gate, port (X -er). see HEBREW (H8176) sha'ar
From (H8176) sha'ar; a measure (as a section) -- (hundred-)fold. see HEBREW (H8176) sha'ar
Or sa.ar (Isaiah 7:20) {sah'-ar}; from (H8175) sa'ar in the sense of dishevelling; hair (as if tossed or bristling) -- hair(-y), X rough. see HEBREW (H8175) sa'ar
From (H8176) sha'ar; harsh or horrid, i.e. Offensive -- vile. see HEBREW (H8176) sha'ar
Feminine of (H8178) sa'ar; a hurricane -- storm, tempest. see HEBREW (H8178) sa'ar

Or snowrah {seh-o-raw'} (feminine meaning the plant); and (masculine meaning the grain); also s or {seh-ore'}; or s-owr {seh-ore'}; from (H8175) sa'ar in the sense of roughness; barley (as villose) -- barley. see HEBREW (H8175) sa'ar
Feminine of (H8181) se'ar; hairiness -- hair. see HEBREW (H8181) se'ar

Or shanariyriyah {shah-ar-ee-ree-yaw'}; or shaparurith {shah-ar-oo-reeth'}; feminine from (H8176) sha'ar in the sense of (H8175) sa'ar; something fearful -- horrible thing. see HEBREW (H8176) sha'ar see HEBREW (H8175) sa'ar
From (H8176) sha'ar and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has stormed; Shearjah, an Israelite -- Sheariah. see HEBREW (H8176) sha'ar see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
Masculine plural of (H8184) s'orah; barley grains; Seorim, an Israelite -- Seorim. see HEBREW (H8184) s'orah
Dual of (H8179) sha'ar; double gates; Shaarajim, a place in Palestine -- Shaaraim. see HEBREW (H8179) sha'ar
Of Persian derivation; Shaashgaz, a eunuch of Xerxes -- Shaashgaz.
From (H8173) sha'a'; enjoyment -- delight, pleasure. see HEBREW (H8173) sha'a'
A primitive root; to abrade, i.e. Bare -- high, stick out.

column8: band, bank, binding, border, brim, brink, edge, language,
column9: Or (in dual and plural) sepheth {sef-eth'}; probably from (H5595) caphah or (H8192) shaphah through the idea of termination (compare (H5490) cowph); the lip (as a natural boundary); by implication, language; by analogy, a margin (of a vessel, water, cloth, etc.) -- band, bank, binding, border, brim, brink, edge, language, lip, prating, ((sea-))shore, side, speech, talk, (vain) words. see HEBREW (H5595) caphah see HEBREW (H8192) shaphah see HEBREW (H5490) cowph
From (H8192) shaphah in the sense of clarifying; a cheese (as strained from the whey) -- cheese. see HEBREW (H8192) shaphah
Or Shphiy {shef-ee'}; from (H8192) shaphah; baldness (compare (H8205) shphiy); Shepho or Shephi, an Idumaean -- Shephi, Shepho. see HEBREW (H8192) shaphah see HEBREW (H8205) shphiy
Or shphuwt {shef-oot'}; from (H8199) shaphat; a judicial sentence, i.e. Punishment -- judgment. see HEBREW (H8199) shaphat
Or Shphuwphan {shef-oo-fawn'}; from the same as (H8207) shphiyphon; serpent-like; Shephupham or Shephuphan, an Israelite -- Shephuphan, Shupham. see HEBREW (H8207) shphiyphon

Feminine from an unused root meaning to spread out (as a family; see (H4940) mishpachah); a female slave (as a member of the household) -- (bond-, hand-)maid(-en, -servant), wench, bondwoman, womanservant. see HEBREW (H4940) mishpachah

column8: avenge, that condemn, contend, defend, execute judgment, be a judgment
column9: A primitive root; to judge, i.e. Pronounce sentence (for or against); by implication, to vindicate or punish; by extenssion, to govern; passively, to litigate (literally or figuratively) -- + avenge, X that condemn, contend, defend, execute (judgment), (be a) judge(-ment), X needs, plead, reason, rule.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8199) shaphat; to judge -- magistrate. see HEBREW (H8199) shaphat
From (H8199) shaphat; a sentence, i.e. Infliction -- judgment. see HEBREW (H8199) shaphat
From (H8199) shaphat; judge; Shaphat, the name of four Israelites -- Shaphat. see HEBREW (H8199) shaphat

column7: Yah has judged, the name of a number of Isr
column9: Or Shphatyahuw {shef-at-yaw'-hoo}; from (H8199) shaphat and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has judged; Shephatjah, the name of ten Israelites -- Shephatiah. see HEBREW (H8199) shaphat see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From (H8199) shaphat; judge-like; Shiphtan, an Israelite -- Shiphtan. see HEBREW (H8199) shaphat

column7: bareness, a smooth or bare height
column9: From (H8192) shaphah; bareness; concretely, a bare hill or plain -- high place, stick out. see HEBREW (H8192) shaphah
Plural of an unused noun from the same as (H8207) shphiyphon and meaning the same; serpents; Shuppim, an Israelite -- Shuppim. see HEBREW (H8207) shphiyphon
From an unused root meaning the same as (H7779) shuwph; a kind of serpent (as snapping), probably the cerastes or horned adder -- adder. see HEBREW (H7779) shuwph

column7: beauty, a place perhaps in Philistia
column9: From (H8231) shaphar; beautiful; Shaphir, a place in Palestine -- Saphir. see HEBREW (H8231) shaphar
(Aramaic) intensive of a form corresponding to (H8208) Shaphiyr; beautiful -- fair. see HEBREW (H8208) Shaphiyr

column8: cast up, gush out, pour out, shedder, out, slip
column9: A primitive root; to spill forth (blood, a libation, liquid metal; or even a solid, i.e. To mound up); also (figuratively) to expend (life, soul, complaint, money, etc.); intensively, to sprawl out -- cast (up), gush out, pour (out), shed(-der, out), slip.
From (H8210) shaphak; an emptying place, e.g. An ash-heap -- are poured out. see HEBREW (H8210) shaphak
Feminine of a derivative from (H8210) shaphak; a pipe (for pouring forth, e.g. Wine), i.e. The penis -- privy member. see HEBREW (H8210) shaphak

column7: to be or become low, to be abased
column8: abase, bring cast, put down, debase, humble self, be bring, lay, make,
column9: A primitive root; to depress or sink (expec. Figuratively, to humiliate, intransitive or transitive) -- abase, bring (cast, put) down, debase, humble (self), be (bring, lay, make, put) low(-er).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8213) shaphel -- abase, humble, put down, subdue. see HEBREW (H8213) shaphel
(Aramaic) from (H8214) shphal; low -- basest. see HEBREW (H8214) shphal
From (H8213) shaphel; an humble rank -- low estate (place). see HEBREW (H8213) shaphel
From (H8213) shaphel; depressed, literally or figuratively -- base(-st), humble, low(-er, -ly). see HEBREW (H8213) shaphel
Feminine of (H8216) shephel; depression -- low place. see HEBREW (H8216) shephel
From (H8213) shaphel; Lowland, i.e. (with the article) the maritime slope of Palestine -- low country, (low) plain, vale(-ley). see HEBREW (H8213) shaphel
From (H8213) shaphel; remissness -- idleness. see HEBREW (H8213) shaphel

column7: a place on the E. border of Isr
column9: Probably from (H8192) shaphah; bare spot; Shepham, a place in or near Palestine -- Shepham. see HEBREW (H8192) shaphah
From (H8193) saphah; the beard (as a lip-piece) -- beard, (upper) lip. see HEBREW (H8193) saphah
Formed like (H8221) Shpham; baldly; Shapham, an Israelite -- Shapham. see HEBREW (H8221) Shpham
Feminine plural of (H8221) Shpham; Siphmoth, a place in Palestine -- Siphmoth. see HEBREW (H8221) Shpham
Patrial from (H8221) Shpham; a Shiphmite or inhabitant of Shepham -- Shiphmite. see HEBREW (H8221) Shpham
A primitive root; to conceal (as a valuable) -- treasure.
From (H8226) saphan; a species of rock-rabbit (from its hiding), i.e. Probably the hyrax -- coney. see HEBREW (H8226) saphan
From an unused root meaning to abound; resources -- abundance.
Feminine of (H8228) shepha'; copiousness -- abundance, company, multitude. see HEBREW (H8228) shepha'
From (H8228) shepha'; copious; Shiphi, an Israelite -- Shiphi. see HEBREW (H8228) shepha'
A primitive root; to glisten, i.e. (figuratively) be (causatively, make) fair -- X goodly.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8231) shaphar; to be beautiful -- be acceptable, please, + think good. see HEBREW (H8231) shaphar
From (H8231) shaphar; beauty -- X goodly. see HEBREW (H8231) shaphar

column7: beauty, a mountain in the desert
column9: The same as (H8233) shepher; Shepher, a place in the Desert -- Shapper. see HEBREW (H8233) shepher
From (H8231) shaphar; brightness -- garnish. see HEBREW (H8231) shaphar
The same as (H8235) shiphrah; Shiphrah, an Israelitess -- Shiphrah. see HEBREW (H8235) shiphrah
From (H8231) shaphar; splendid, i.e. A tapestry or canopy -- royal pavilion. see HEBREW (H8231) shaphar
(Aramaic) from (H8231) shaphar; the dawn (as brilliant with aurora) -- X very early in the morning. see HEBREW (H8231) shaphar
A primitive root; to locate, i.e. (generally) hang on or (figuratively) establish, reduce -- bring, ordain, set on.
From (H8239) shaphath; a (double) stall (for cattle); also a (two-pronged) hook (for flaying animals on) -- hook, pot. see HEBREW (H8239) shaphath
From (H7857) shataph (for alliteration with (H7110) qetseph); an outburst (of anger) -- little. see HEBREW (H7857) shataph see HEBREW (H7110) qetseph

From (H8264) shaqaq; properly, a mesh (as allowing a liquid to run through), i.e. Coarse loose cloth or sacking (used in mourning and for bagging); hence, a bag (for grain, etc.) -- sack(-cloth, -clothes). see HEBREW (H8264) shaqaq
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7785) showq; the leg -- leg. see HEBREW (H7785) showq
A primitive root; to fasten -- bind.
A primitive root; to be alert, i.e. Sleepless; hence to be on the lookout (whether for good or ill) -- hasten, remain, wake, watch (for).

column8: make like unto, after the fashion of almonds
column9: A denominative from (H8247) shaqed; to be (intensively, make) almond-shaped -- make like (unto, after the fashion of) almonds. see HEBREW (H8247) shaqed
From (H8245) shaqad; the almond (tree or nut; as being the earliest in bloom) -- almond (tree). see HEBREW (H8245) shaqad

column7: cause to drink water, give to drink
column8: cause to give, give to, let, make to drink, drown, moisten, water
column9: A primitive root; to quaff, i.e. (causatively) to irrigate or furnish a potion to -- cause to (give, give to, let, make to) drink, drown, moisten, water. See (H7937) shakar, (H8354) shathah. see HEBREW (H7937) shakar see HEBREW (H8354) shathah
From (H8248) shaqah; (plural collective) a draught -- drink. see HEBREW (H8248) shaqah
From (H8248) shaqah; a beverage; moisture, i.e. (figuratively) refreshment -- drink, marrow. see HEBREW (H8248) shaqah

Or shiqquts {shik-koots'}; from (H8262) shaqats; disgusting, i.e. Filthy; especially idolatrous or (concretely) an idol -- abominable filth (idol, -ation), detestable (thing). see HEBREW (H8262) shaqats

column8: appease, idleness, at, be at, be in, give quietness, be at, be in,
column9: A primitive root; to repose (usually figurative) -- appease, idleness, (at, be at, be in, give) quiet(-ness), (be at, be in, give, have, take) rest, settle, be still.
From (H8252) shaqat; tranquillity -- quietness. see HEBREW (H8252) shaqat
A primitive root; to suspend or poise (especially in trade) -- pay, receive(-r), spend, X throughly, weigh.
From (H8254) shaqal; probably a weight; used as a commercial standard -- shekel. see HEBREW (H8254) shaqal
Or (feminine) shiqmah {shik-maw'}; of uncertain derivation; a sycamore (usually the tree) -- sycamore (fruit, tree).

column8: make deep, let down, drown, quench, sink
column9: (abbreviated Am. 8:8); a primitive root; to subside; by implication, to be overflowed, cease; causatively, to abate, subdue -- make deep, let down, drown, quench, sink.
From (H8257) shaqa'; a depression -- hollow strake. see HEBREW (H8257) shaqa'

column7: to overhang, look out or down
column9: A primitive root; properly, to lean out (of a window), i.e. (by implication) peep or gaze (passively, be a spectacle) -- appear, look (down, forth, out).
From (H8259) shaqaph; a loophole (for looking out), to admit light and air -- window. see HEBREW (H8259) shaqaph
Passive participle of (H8259) shaqaph; an embrasure or opening (compare (H8260) sheqeph) with bevelled jam -- light, window. see HEBREW (H8259) shaqaph see HEBREW (H8260) sheqeph

column8: abhor, make abominable, have in abomination, detest, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to be filthy, i.e. (intensively) to loathe, pollute -- abhor, make abominable, have in abomination, detest, X utterly.
From (H8262) shaqats; filth, i.e. (figuratively and specifically) an idolatrous object -- abominable(-tion). see HEBREW (H8262) shaqats

column8: have appetite, long, range, run to and fro
column9: A primitive root; to course (like a beast of prey); by implication, to seek greedily -- have appetite, justle one against another, long, range, run (to and fro).
A primitive root; to ogle, i.e. Blink coquettishly -- wanton.
A primitive root; to cheat, i.e. Be untrue (usually in words) -- fail, deal falsely, lie.

column8: without a cause, deceitful, falsehood feignedly, liar, lie, lying, vain thing, wrongfully
column9: From (H8266) shaqar; an untruth; by implication, a sham (often adverbial) -- without a cause, deceit(-ful), false(-hood, -ly), feignedly, liar, + lie, lying, vain (thing), wrongfully. see HEBREW (H8266) shaqar
From (H8248) shaqah; a trough (for watering) -- trough. see HEBREW (H8248) shaqah

column7: chieftain, chief, ruler, official, captain, prince
column8: chief captain, general, governor, keeper, lord, taskmaster, principal,
column9: From (H8323) sarar; a head person (of any rank or class) -- captain (that had rule), chief (captain), general, governor, keeper, lord, ((-task-))master, prince(-ipal), ruler, steward. see HEBREW (H8323) sarar

From (H8324) sharar; a string (as twisted (compare (H8306) shariyr)), i.e. (specifically) the umbilical cord (also figuratively, as the centre of strength) -- navel. see HEBREW (H8324) sharar see HEBREW (H8306) shariyr

(Aramaic) a root corresponding to that of (H8293) sheruwth; to free, separate; figuratively, to unravel, commence; by implication (of unloading beasts) to reside -- begin, dissolve, dwell, loose. see HEBREW (H8293) sheruwth

column7: an Assyr., also perhaps an Israelite
column9: Of foreign derivation; Sharetser, the name of an Assyrian and an Israelite -- Sharezer.
From an unused root meaning to glare; quivering glow (of the air), expec. The mirage -- heat, parched ground.

column7: Yah has sent burning heat, an Israelite name
column9: From (H8273) sharab and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has brought heat; Sherebjah, the name of two Israelites -- Sherebiah. see HEBREW (H8273) sharab see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
For (H7626) shebet; a rod of empire -- sceptre. see HEBREW (H7626) shebet
A primitive root; to intwine -- wrap together, wreath.
A primitive root; properly, to puncture (compare (H8279) sered), i.e. (figuratively through the idea of slipping out) to escape or survive -- remain. see HEBREW (H8279) sered
From (H8277) sarad; stitching (as pierced with a needle) -- service. see HEBREW (H8277) sarad
From (H8277) sarad; a (carpenter's) scribing-awl (for pricking or scratching measurements) -- line. see HEBREW (H8277) sarad
A primitive root; to prevail -- have power (as a prince).
A primitive root; to free -- direct.
Feminine of (H8269) sar; a mistress, i.e. Female noble -- lady, princess, queen. see HEBREW (H8269) sar
The same as (H8282) sarah; Sarah, Abraham's wife -- Sarah. see HEBREW (H8282) sarah
Probably feminine of (H7791) shuwr; a fortification (literally or figuratively) -- sing (by mistake for (H7891) shiyr), wall. see HEBREW (H7791) shuwr see HEBREW (H7891) shiyr
From (H8324) sharar in its original sense of pressing; a wrist-band (as compact or clasping) -- bracelet. see HEBREW (H8324) sharar
From (H8276) sarag; tendril; Serug, a postdiluvian patriarch -- Serug. see HEBREW (H8276) sarag

Probably from (H8281) sharah (in the sense of dwelling (compare (H8271) shre') and (H2580) chen; abode of pleasure; Sharuchen, a place in Palestine -- Sharuhen. see HEBREW (H8281) sharah see HEBREW (H8271) shre' see HEBREW (H2580) chen
From (H8308) sarak; a thong (as laced or tied) -- ((shoe-)) latchet. see HEBREW (H8308) sarak

column4: proper name, of a location; noun masculine; proper name, of a location; Adjective, of a people
column7: a plain on the Mediterranean Sea, perhaps also a region East of the Jordan
column9: Probably abridged from (H3474) yashar; plain, Sharon, the name of a place in Palestine -- Lasharon, Sharon. see HEBREW (H3474) yashar
Patrial from (H8289) Sharown; a Sharonite or inhabitant of Sharon -- Sharonite. see HEBREW (H8289) Sharown
Passive participle from the same as (H8321) soreq; a grapevine -- principal plant. See (H8320) saruq, (H8321) soreq. see HEBREW (H8321) soreq see HEBREW (H8320) saruq see HEBREW (H8321) soreq
Or (by permutation) shriyqah {sher-ee- kaw'}; feminine passive participle of (H8319) sharaq; a whistling (in scorn); by analogy, a piping -- bleating, hissing. see HEBREW (H8319) sharaq
From (H8281) sharah abbreviated; freedom -- remnant. see HEBREW (H8281) sharah
By permutation for (H5629) cerach; superfluity; Serach, an Israelitess -- Sarah, Serah. see HEBREW (H5629) cerach

column8: cut in pieces, make cuttings pieces
column9: A primitive root; to gash -- cut in pieces, make (cuttings) pieces.
And sareteth {saw-reh'-teth}; from (H8295) sarat; an incision -- cutting. see HEBREW (H8295) sarat
From (H8269) sar; dominative; Sarai, the wife of Abraham -- Sarai. see HEBREW (H8269) sar

column7: an Israelite with a foreign wife
column9: Probably from (H8324) sharar; hostile; Sharay, an Israelite -- Sharai. see HEBREW (H8324) sharar
From (H8276) sarag; a tendril (as entwining) -- branch. see HEBREW (H8276) sarag
From (H8277) sarad; a survivor -- X alive, left, remain(- ing), remnant, rest. see HEBREW (H8277) sarad

column7: a city on the border of Zebulun
column9: The same as (H8300) sariyd; Sarid, a place in Palestine -- Sarid. see HEBREW (H8300) sariyd

column8: breastplate, coat of mail, habergeon, harness
column9: Or shiryon {shir-yone'}; and shiryan {shir- yawn'}; also (feminine) shiryah {shir-yaw'}; and shiryonah {shir-yo-naw'}; from (H8281) sharah in the original sense of turning; a corslet (as if twisted) -- breastplate, coat of mail, habergeon, harness. See (H5630) ciyron. see HEBREW (H8281) sharah see HEBREW (H5630) ciyron

column7: a Sidonian name for Mount Hermon
column9: And Siryon {sir-yone'}; the same as (H8304) Srayah (i.e. Sheeted with snow); Shirjon or Sirjon, a peak of the Lebanon -- Sirion. see HEBREW (H8304) Srayah

column7: Yah persists, the name of a number of Isr
column9: Or Srayahuw {ser-aw-yaw'-hoo}; from (H8280) sarah and (H3050) Yahh; Jah has prevailed; Serajah, the name of nine Israelites -- Seraiah. see HEBREW (H8280) sarah see HEBREW (H3050) Yahh
From the same as (H8321) soreq in the original sense of piercing; hetchelling (or combing flax), i.e. (concretely) tow (by extension, linen cloth) -- fine. see HEBREW (H8321) soreq

From (H8324) sharar in the original sense as in (H8270) shor (compare (H8326) shorer); a cord, i.e. (by analogy) sinew -- navel. see HEBREW (H8324) sharar see HEBREW (H8270) shor see HEBREW (H8326) shorer
From (H8324) sharar in the sense of twisted, i.e. Firm; obstinacy -- imagination, lust. see HEBREW (H8324) sharar
A primitive root; to interlace -- traverse.
Probably by an orthographical error for (H7709) shdemah; a common -- field. see HEBREW (H7709) shdemah
Of foreign derivation; Sarsekim, a Babylonian general -- Sarsechim.

column8: stretch out self, have any superfluous thing
column9: A primitive root; to prolong, i.e. (reflex) be deformed by excess of members -- stretch out self, (have any) superfluous thing.
For (H5587) ca'iph; cogitation -- thought. see HEBREW (H5587) ca'iph

column8: cause to, make a burning, up kindle, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to be (causatively, set) on fire -- (cause to, make a) burn((-ing), up) kindle, X utterly.
From (H8313) saraph; burning, i.e. (figuratively) poisonous (serpent); specifically, a saraph or symbolical creature (from their copper color) -- fiery (serpent), seraph. see HEBREW (H8313) saraph
The same as (H8314) saraph; Saraph, an Israelite -- Saraph. see HEBREW (H8314) saraph
From (H8313) saraph; cremation -- burning. see HEBREW (H8313) saraph

column8: breed bring forth, increase abundantly in abundance, creep, move
column9: A primitive root; to wriggle, i.e. (by implication) swarm or abound -- breed (bring forth, increase) abundantly (in abundance), creep, move.
From (H8317) sharats; a swarm, i.e. Active mass of minute animals -- creep(-ing thing), move(-ing creature). see HEBREW (H8317) sharats
A primitive root; properly, to be shrill, i.e. To whistle or hiss (as a call or in scorn) -- hiss.
From (H8319) sharaq; bright red (as piercing to the sight), i.e. Bay -- speckled. See (H8291) saruwq. see HEBREW (H8319) sharaq see HEBREW (H8291) saruwq

Or sowreq {so-rake'}; and (feminine) soreqah {so- ray-kaw'}; from (H8319) sharaq in the sense of redness (compare (H8320) saruq); a vine stock (properly, one yielding purple grapes, the richest variety) -- choice(-st, noble) wine. Compare (H8291) saruwq. see HEBREW (H8319) sharaq see HEBREW (H8320) saruq see HEBREW (H8291) saruwq
From (H8319) sharaq; a derision -- hissing. see HEBREW (H8319) sharaq

column7: to be or act as prince, rule
column8: altogether, make self a prince, bear rule
column9: A primitive root; to have (transitively, exercise; reflexively, get) dominion -- X altogether, make self a prince, (bear) rule.
A primitive root; to be hostile (only active participle an opponent) -- enemy.

column7: father of one of David\'s heroes
column9: From (H8324) sharar; hostile; Sharar, an Israelite -- Sharar. see HEBREW (H8324) sharar
From (H8324) sharar in the sense of twisting (compare (H8270) shor); the umbilical cord, i.e. (by extension) a bodice -- navel. see HEBREW (H8324) sharar see HEBREW (H8270) shor

column8: take, cause to take root out
column9: A primitive root; to root, i.e. Strike into the soil, or (by implication) to pluck from it -- (take, cause to take) root (out).
From (H8327) sharash; a root (literally or figuratively) -- bottom, deep, heel, root. see HEBREW (H8327) sharash
The same as (H8328) sheresh; Sheresh, an Israelite -- Sharesh. see HEBREW (H8328) sheresh
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8328) sheresh -- root. see HEBREW (H8328) sheresh
From (H8327) sharash; a chain (as rooted, i.e. Linked) -- chain. Compare (H8333) sharahrah. see HEBREW (H8327) sharash see HEBREW (H8333) sharahrah
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H8327) sharash; eradication, i.e. (figuratively) exile -- banishment. see HEBREW (H8327) sharash
From (H8327) sharash (compare (H8331) sharshah); a chain; (arch.) Probably a garland -- chain. see HEBREW (H8327) sharash see HEBREW (H8331) sharshah
A primitive root; to attend as a menial or worshipper; figuratively, to contribute to -- minister (unto), (do) serve(- ant, -ice, -itor), wait on.
Infinitive of (H8334) sharath; service (in the Temple) -- minister(-ry). see HEBREW (H8334) sharath

column8: blue, fine twined linen, marble, silk
column9: Or (for alliteration with (H4897) meshiy) shshiy {shesh-ee'}; for (H7893) shayish; bleached stuff, i.e. White linen or (by analogy) marble -- X blue, fine ((twined)) linen, marble, silk. see HEBREW (H4897) meshiy see HEBREW (H7893) shayish

Masculine shishshah {shish-shaw'}; a primitive number; six (as an overplus (see (H7797) suws) beyond five or the fingers of the hand); as ord. Sixth -- six((-teen, -teenth)), sixth. see HEBREW (H7797) suws

column8: annihilate -- leave by the sixth part

column9: Patrial or patronymically from an unused noun of uncertain meaning; a Titsite or descendant or inhabitant of an unknown Tits -- Tizite.
