Probably from (H3372) yare'; fearful, Tirja, an Israelite -- Tiria. see HEBREW (H3372) yare'

column7: a son of Japheth and his desc
column9: Probably of foreign derivation; Tiras, a son of Japheth -- Tiras.
From an unused root meaning to butt; a buck or he-goat (as given to butting) -- he goat.
Or towk (Psa. 72:14) {toke}; from the same base as (H8432) tavek (in the sense of cutting to pieces); oppression -- deceit, fraud. see HEBREW (H8432) tavek
A primitive root; to strew, i.e. Encamp -- sit down.
Feminine passive participle of (H8505) takan; adjustment, i.e. Structure; by implication, equipage -- fashion, store. see HEBREW (H8505) takan
From (H3559) kuwn; or probably ident. With (H8498) tkuwnah; something arranged or fixed, i.e. A place -- seat. see HEBREW (H3559) kuwn see HEBREW (H8498) tkuwnah
Or tuwkkiy {took-kee'}; probably of foreign derivation; some imported creature, probably a peacock -- peacock.
From an unused root meaning to dissever, i.e. Crush -- deceitful.
From (H3615) kalah; completeness -- perfection. see HEBREW (H3615) kalah
From (H3615) kalah; completion; by implication, an extremity -- end, perfect(-ion). see HEBREW (H3615) kalah
Probably for (H7827) shcheleth; the cerulean mussel, i.e. The color (violet) obtained therefrom or stuff dyed therewith -- blue. see HEBREW (H7827) shcheleth

column8: bear up, direct, be unequal, mete, ponder, tell, weigh
column9: A primitive root; to balance, i.e. Measure out (by weight or dimension); figuratively, arrange, equalize, through the idea of levelling (ment. Estimate, test) -- bear up, direct, be ((un-))equal, mete, ponder, tell, weigh.
From (H8505) takan; a fixed quantity -- measure, tale. see HEBREW (H8505) takan
The same as (H8506) token; Token, a place in Palestine -- Tochen. see HEBREW (H8506) token
From (H8506) token; admeasurement, i.e. Consummation -- pattern, sum. see HEBREW (H8506) token
Apparently from an unused root meaning to encompass; a wrapper or robe -- garment.
By contraction from (H8524) talal; a mound -- heap, X strength. see HEBREW (H8524) talal
A primitive root; to suspend; figuratively (through hesitation) to be uncertain; by implication (of mental dependence) to habituate -- be bent, hang (in doubt).

column7: hill of grain, a place in Babylon
column9: From (H8510) tel and (H24) 'abiyb; mound of green growth; Tel-Abib, a place in Chaldaea -- Tel-abib. see HEBREW (H8510) tel see HEBREW (H24) 'abiyb
From (H3811) la'ah; distress -- travail, travel, trouble. see HEBREW (H3811) la'ah
From (H3851) lahab; desiccation -- great drought. see HEBREW (H3851) lahab
Or Tlassar {tel-as-sar'}; of foreign derivation; Telassar, a region of Assyria -- Telassar.
From (H3847) labash; a garment -- clothing. see HEBREW (H3847) labash
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H7950) sheleg; snow -- snow. see HEBREW (H7950) sheleg
A primitive root; to suspend (especially to gibbet) -- hang (up).
Or tlunnah {tel-oon-naw'}; from (H3885) luwn in the sense of obstinacy; a grumbling -- murmuring. see HEBREW (H3885) luwn
Probably from an unused root meaning to dissever; breach; Telach, an Israelite -- Telah.

column7: mound of a craftsman, a city in Babylon
column9: From (H8510) tel and the feminine of (H2798) Charashiym; mound of workmanship; Tel-Charsha, a place in Babylonia -- Tel-haresha, Tel-harsa. see HEBREW (H8510) tel see HEBREW (H2798) Charashiym
Probably from (H8518) talah; a quiver (as slung) -- quiver. see HEBREW (H8518) talah
(Aramaic) or taltiy (Aramaic) {tal-tee'}; ordinal from (H8532) tlath; third -- third. see HEBREW (H8532) tlath
A primitive root; to pile up, i.e. Elevate -- eminent. Compare (H2048) hathal. see HEBREW (H2048) hathal
From an unused root meaning to accumulate; a bank or terrace -- furrow, ridge.

column7: plowman, a father-in-law of David, also a descendant of Anak
column9: From (H8525) telem; ridged; Talmai, the name of a Canaanite and a Syrian -- Talmai. see HEBREW (H8525) telem
From (H3925) lamad; a pupil -- scholar. see HEBREW (H3925) lamad

column7: mound of salt, a place in Babylon
column9: From (H8510) tel and (H4417) melach; mound of salt; Tel-Melach, a place in Babylonia -- Tel-melah. see HEBREW (H8510) tel see HEBREW (H4417) melach
A denominative from (H8438) towla'; to crimson, i.e. Dye that color -- X scarlet. see HEBREW (H8438) towla'
Feminine from an unused root meaning to tower; something tall, i.e. (plural collective) slenderness -- armoury.
(Aramaic) from (H8532) tlath; a tertiary rank -- third. see HEBREW (H8532) tlath
(Aramaic) masculine tlathah (Aramaic) {tel-aw-thaw'}; or tlatha (Aramaic) {tel-aw-thaw'}; corresponding to (H7969) shalowsh; three or third -- third, three. see HEBREW (H7969) shalowsh
(Aramaic) mult. Of (H8532) tlath; ten times three -- thirty. see HEBREW (H8532) tlath
By reduplication, from (H8524) talal through the idea of vibration; a trailing bough (as pendulous) -- bushy. see HEBREW (H8524) talal

column8: coupled together, perfect, plain, undefiled, upright
column9: From (H8552) tamam; complete; usually (morally) pious; specifically, gentle, dear -- coupled together, perfect, plain, undefiled, upright. see HEBREW (H8552) tamam
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8033) sham; there -- X thence, there, X where. see HEBREW (H8033) sham

column7: completeness, integrity, also part of the high priest\'s breastplate
column8: full, integrity, perfection, simplicity, uprightly at a venture
column9: From (H8552) tamam; completeness; figuratively, prosperity; usually (morally) innocence -- full, integrity, perfect(-ion), simplicity, upright(-ly, -ness), at a venture. See (H8550) Tummiym. see HEBREW (H8552) tamam see HEBREW (H8550) Tummiym
Feminine of (H8537) tom; innocence -- integrity. see HEBREW (H8537) tom

column8: be amazed, be astonished, marvelously, wonder
column9: A primitive root; to be in consternation -- be amazed, be astonished, marvel(-lously), wonder.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to (H8539) tamahh; a miracle -- wonder. see HEBREW (H8539) tamahh
From (H8539) tamahh; consternation -- astonishment. see HEBREW (H8539) tamahh
Of uncertain derivation; Tammuz, a Phoenician deity -- Tammuz.

column8: before time, these three days, heretofore, time past, yesterday
column9: Or tmol {tem-ole'}; probably for (H865) 'ethmowl; properly, ago, i.e. A (short or long) time since; especially yesterday, or (with (H8032) shilshowm) day before yesterday -- + before (-time), + these (three) days, + heretofore, + time past, yesterday. see HEBREW (H865) 'ethmowl see HEBREW (H8032) shilshowm

Or tmunah {tem-oo-naw'}; from (H4327) miyn; something portioned (i.e. Fashioned) out, as a shape, i.e. (indefinitely) phantom, or (specifically) embodiment, or (figuratively) manifestation (of favor) -- image, likeness, similitude. see HEBREW (H4327) miyn
From (H4171) muwr; barter, compensation -- (ex-)change(-ing), recompense, restitution. see HEBREW (H4171) muwr
From (H4191) muwth; execution (as a doom) -- death, die. see HEBREW (H4191) muwth
Of uncertain derivation; Temach, one of the Nethinim -- Tamah, Thamah.

column8: always, continual employment daily, nevermore, perpetual
column9: From an unused root meaning to stretch; properly, continuance (as indefinite extension); but used only (attributively as adjective) constant (or adverbially, constantly); ellipt. The regular (daily) sacrifice -- alway(-s), continual (employment, -ly), daily, ((n-))ever(-more), perpetual.

column8: without blemish, complete, full, perfect, sincerely ity, sound, without spot, undefiled,
column9: From (H8552) tamam; entire (literally, figuratively or morally); also (as noun) integrity, truth -- without blemish, complete, full, perfect, sincerely (-ity), sound, without spot, undefiled, upright(-ly), whole. see HEBREW (H8552) tamam
Plural of (H8537) tom; perfections, i.e. (techn.) One of the epithets of the objects in the high-priest's breastplate as an emblem of complete Truth -- Thummim. see HEBREW (H8537) tom

column8: take, uphold up, maintain, retain, stay up
column9: A primitive root; to sustain; by implication, to obtain, keep fast; figuratively, to help, follow close -- (take, up-)hold (up), maintain, retain, stay (up).

column8: accomplish, cease, be clean passed, consume, have done, come to an end
column9: A primitive root; to complete, in a good or a bad sense, literal, or figurative, transitive or intransitive (as follows) -- accomplish, cease, be clean (pass-)ed, consume, have done, (come to an, have an, make an) end, fail, come to the full, be all gone, X be all here, be (make) perfect, be spent, sum, be (shew self) upright, be wasted, whole.
From (H4487) manah; a portion assigned; Timnah, the name of two places in Palestine -- Timnah, Timnath, Thimnathah. see HEBREW (H4487) manah
Patrial from (H8553) Timnah; a Timnite or inhabitant of Timnah -- Timnite. see HEBREW (H8553) Timnah

column4: proper name, masculine and feminine; proper name, masculine; feminine
column9: From (H4513) mana'; restraint; Timna, the name of two Edomites -- Timna, Timnah. see HEBREW (H4513) mana'

column7: territory of the sun, a village in the hill country of Ephraim
column9: Or Timnath Cerach {tim-nath seh'-rakh}; from (H8553) Timnah and (H2775) cherec; portion of (the) sun; Timnath-Cheres, a place in Palestine -- Timnath-heres, Timnath-serah. see HEBREW (H8553) Timnah see HEBREW (H2775) cherec
From (H4529) macah; liquefaction, i.e. Disappearance -- melt. see HEBREW (H4529) macah
From an unused root meaning to be erect; a palm tree -- palm (tree).

column7: daughter-in-law of Judah, also two Israelite women, also a place South of the Dead Sea
column9: The same as (H8558) tamar; Tamar, the name of three women and a place -- Tamar. see HEBREW (H8558) tamar
From the same root as (H8558) tamar; a palm trunk -- palm tree. see HEBREW (H8558) tamar
(plural o or (feminine) timmorah (singular and plural) {tim-mo-raw'}; from the same root as (H8558) tamar; (arch.) A palm-like pilaster (i.e. Umbellate) -- palm tree. see HEBREW (H8558) tamar

Or tamruq {tam-rook'}; or tamriyq {tam-reek'}; from (H4838) maraq; properly, a scouring, i.e. Soap or perfumery for the bath; figuratively, a detergent -- X cleanse, (thing for) purification(-fying). see HEBREW (H4838) maraq
From (H4843) marar; bitterness (plural as collective) -- X most bitter(-ly). see HEBREW (H4843) marar
From the same root as (H8558) tamar; an erection, i.e. Pillar (probably for a guide-board) -- high heap. see HEBREW (H8558) tamar

From an unused root probably meaning to elongate; a monster (as preternaturally formed), i.e. A sea-serpent (or other huge marine animal); also a jackal (or other hideous land animal) -- dragon, whale. Compare (H8577) tanniyn. see HEBREW (H8577) tanniyn
A primitive root; to present (a mercenary inducement), i.e. Bargain with (a harlot) -- hire.
A primitive root (identical with (H8566) tanah through the idea of attributing honor); to ascribe (praise), i.e. Celebrate, commemorate -- lament, rehearse. see HEBREW (H8566) tanah
Probably feminine of (H8565) tan; a female jackal -- dragon. see HEBREW (H8565) tan
From (H5106) nuw'; alienation; by implication, enmity -- breach of promise, occasion. see HEBREW (H5106) nuw'
From (H5107) nuwb; produce -- fruit, increase. see HEBREW (H5107) nuwb
Perhaps from the same as (H594) 'anak through the idea of protraction; a pinnacle, i.e. Extremity -- tip. see HEBREW (H594) 'anak
From (H5123) nuwm; drowsiness, i.e. Sleep -- slumber(-ing). see HEBREW (H5123) nuwm

column7: a swinging, waving, wave offering, offering
column9: From (H5130) nuwph; a brandishing (in threat); by implication, tumult; specifically, the official undulation of sacrificial offerings -- offering, shaking, wave (offering). see HEBREW (H5130) nuwph
From (H5216) niyr; a fire-pot -- furnace, oven. see HEBREW (H5216) niyr
Or tanchum {tan-khoom'}; and (feminine) tanchuwmah {tan-khoo-maw'}; from (H5162) nacham; compassion, solace -- comfort, consolation. see HEBREW (H5162) nacham
For (H8575) tanchuwm (feminine); Tanchumeth, an Israelite -- Tanhumeth. see HEBREW (H8575) tanchuwm
Or tanniym (Ezek. 29:3) {tan-neem'}; intensive from the same as (H8565) tan; a marine or land monster, i.e. Sea-serpent or jackal -- dragon, sea-monster, serpent, whale. see HEBREW (H8565) tan
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8147) shnayim; second -- second. see HEBREW (H8147) shnayim
(Aramaic) from (H8578) tinyan; a second time -- again. see HEBREW (H8578) tinyan

From (H5395) nasham; properly, a hard breather, i.e. The name of two unclean creatures, a lizard and a bird (both perhaps from changing color through their irascibility), probably the tree-toad and the water-hen -- mole, swan. see HEBREW (H5395) nasham

column8: make to be abhorred, be, commit more, utterly
column9: A primitive root; to loathe, i.e. (morally) detest -- (make to be) abhor(-red), (be, commit more, do) abominable(-y), X utterly.

column8: cause to go astray, deceive, dissemble, cause to, make to err, seduce
column9: A primitive root; to vacillate, i.e. Reel or stray (literally or figuratively); also causative of both -- (cause to) go astray, deceive, dissemble, (cause to, make to) err, pant, seduce, (make to) stagger, (cause to) wander, be out of the way.
Or Tomiy {to'-ee}; from (H8582) ta'ah; error, Tou or Toi, a Syrian king -- Toi, Tou. see HEBREW (H8582) ta'ah
From (H5749) uwd; attestation, i.e. A precept, usage -- testimony. see HEBREW (H5749) uwd

column8: conduit, cured, healing, little river, trench, watercourse
column9: From (H5927) alah; a channel (into which water is raised for irrigation); also a bandage or plaster (as placed upon a wound) -- conduit, cured, healing, little river, trench, watercourse. see HEBREW (H5927) alah
From (H5953) alal; caprice (as a fit coming on), i.e. Vexation; concretely a tyrant -- babe, delusion. see HEBREW (H5953) alal
From (H5956) alam; a secret -- thing that is hid, secret. see HEBREW (H5956) alam
Or taanug {tah-an-oog'}; and (feminine) taeanugah {tah-ah-oog-aw'}; from (H6026) anag; luxury -- delicate, delight, pleasant. see HEBREW (H6026) anag
From (H6031) anah; affliction (of self), i.e. Fasting -- heaviness. see HEBREW (H6031) anah

column7: a Canaanite city assigned to Manasseh
column9: Or Tanak {tah-nawk'}; of uncertain derivation; Taanak or Tanak, a place in Palestine -- Taanach, Tanach.
A primitive root; to cheat; by analogy, to maltreat -- deceive, misuse.
From (H6105) atsam; might (plural collective) -- power. see HEBREW (H6105) atsam
From (H6168) arah; a knife or razor (as making bare): also a scabbard (as being bare, i.e. Empty) -- (pen-)knife, razor, scabbard, shave, sheath. see HEBREW (H6168) arah
From (H6148) arab; suretyship, i.e. (concretely) a pledge -- + hostage. see HEBREW (H6148) arab
From (H8591) ta'a'; a fraud -- error. see HEBREW (H8591) ta'a'
From (H8608) taphaph contracted; a tambourine -- tabret, timbrel. see HEBREW (H8608) taphaph

column8: beautiful, brave, comely, fair, glorious, honor, majesty
column9: Or tiphereth {tif-eh'-reth}; from (H6286) pa'ar; ornament (abstractly or concretely, literally or figuratively) -- beauty(- iful), bravery, comely, fair, glory(-ious), hono; ornament (abstractly or concretely, literally or figuratively) -- beauty(-iful), bravery, comely, fair, glory(-ious), honour, majesty. see HEBREW (H6286) pa'ar

From (H5301) naphach; an apple (from its fragrance), i.e. The fruit or the tree (probably includ. Others of the pome order, as the quince, the orange, etc.) -- apple (tree). See also (H1054) Beth Tappuwach. see HEBREW (H5301) naphach see HEBREW (H1054) Beth Tappuwach

column7: A city in Judah, also a city on the border between Ephraim and Manasseh
column9: The same as (H8598) tappuwach; Tappuach, the name of two places in Palestine, also of an Israelite -- Tappuah. see HEBREW (H8598) tappuwach
From (H6327) puwts; a dispersal -- dispersion. see HEBREW (H6327) puwts
From (H644) 'aphah; cookery, i.e. (concretely) a cake -- baked piece. see HEBREW (H644) 'aphah
From an unused root meaning to smear; plaster (as gummy) or slime; (figuratively) frivolity -- foolish things, unsavoury, untempered.

column7: a place Southeast of the Dead Sea
column9: From the same as (H8602) taphel; quagmire; Tophel, a place near the Desert -- Tophel. see HEBREW (H8602) taphel
From the same as (H8602) taphel; frivolity -- folly, foolishly. see HEBREW (H8602) taphel
From (H6419) palal; intercession, supplication; by implication, a hymn -- prayer. see HEBREW (H6419) palal
From (H6426) palats; fearfulness -- terrible. see HEBREW (H6426) palats
From (H6452) pacach; ford; Tiphsach, a place in Mesopotamia -- Tipsah. see HEBREW (H6452) pacach
A primitive root; to drum, i.e. Play (as) on the tambourine -- taber, play with timbrels.
A primitive root; to sew -- (women that) sew (together).

column8: catch, handle, lay, take hold on, over, stop, surely, surprise,
column9: A primitive root; to manipulate, i.e. Seize; chiefly to capture, wield, specifically, to overlay; figuratively, to use unwarrantably -- catch, handle, (lay, take) hold (on, over), stop, X surely, surprise, take.
From the base of (H8608) taphaph; a smiting, i.e. (figuratively) contempt -- tabret. see HEBREW (H8608) taphaph
The same as (H8611) topheth; Topheth, a place near Jerusalem -- Tophet, Topheth. see HEBREW (H8611) topheth

column7: a place of burning, probably the same as Topheth
column9: Probably a form of (H8612) Topheth; Tophteh, a place of cremation -- Tophet. see HEBREW (H8612) Topheth
(Aramaic) perhaps from (H8199) shaphat; judicial, i.e. A lawyer -- sheriff. see HEBREW (H8199) shaphat

column8: expectation ted, hope, live, thing that I long for
column9: From (H6960) qavah; literally, a cord (as an attachment (compare (H6961) qaveh)); figuratively, expectancy -- expectation ((-ted)), hope, live, thing that I long for. see HEBREW (H6960) qavah see HEBREW (H6961) qaveh
The same as (H8615) tiqvah; Tikvah, the name of two Israelites -- Tikvah. see HEBREW (H8615) tiqvah
From (H6965) quwm; resistfulness -- power to stand. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm
From (H6965) quwm; an opponent -- rise up against. see HEBREW (H6965) quwm
From (H8628) taqa' (in the musical sense); a trumpet -- trumpet. see HEBREW (H8628) taqa'
A form of (H8619) taqowa'; Tekoa, a place in Palestine -- Tekoa, Tekoah. see HEBREW (H8619) taqowa'
Or Tqo iy {tek-o-ee'}; patronymically from (H8620) Tqowa'; a Tekoite or inhabitant of Tekoah -- Tekoite. see HEBREW (H8620) Tqowa'
Or tquphah {tek-oo-faw'}; from (H5362) naqaph; a revolution, i.e. (of the sun) course, (of time) lapse -- circuit, come about, end. see HEBREW (H5362) naqaph
From (H8630) taqaph; powerful -- mightier. see HEBREW (H8630) taqaph
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8623) taqqiyph -- mighty, strong. see HEBREW (H8623) taqqiyph
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8254) shaqal; to balance -- Tekel, be weighed. see HEBREW (H8254) shaqal
A primitive root; to equalize, i.e. Straighten (intransitive or transitive); figuratively, to compose -- set in order, make straight.
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8626) taqan; to straighten up, i.e. Confirm -- establish. see HEBREW (H8626) taqan

column7: to thrust, clap, give a blow, blast
column8: blow a trumpet, cast, clap, fasten, pitch tent, smite, sound, strike,
column9: A primitive root; to clatter, i.e. Slap (the hands together), clang (an instrument); by analogy, to drive (a nail or tent-pin, a dart, etc.); by implication, to become bondsman by handclasping) -- blow ((a trumpet)), cast, clap, fasten, pitch (tent), smite, sound, strike, X suretiship, thrust.
From (H8628) taqa'; a blast of a trumpet -- sound. see HEBREW (H8628) taqa'
A primitive root; to overpower -- prevail (against).
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8630) taqaph; to become (causatively, make) mighty or (figuratively) obstinate -- make firm, harden, be(-come) strong. see HEBREW (H8630) taqaph
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8633) toqeph; power -- might, strength. see HEBREW (H8633) toqeph
From (H8630) taqaph; might or (figuratively) positiveness -- authority, power, strength. see HEBREW (H8630) taqaph
Probably for (H8653) tar'elah; a reeling; Taralah, a place in Palestine -- Taralah. see HEBREW (H8653) tar'elah
From (H7235) rabah; multiplication, i.e. Progeny -- increase. see HEBREW (H7235) rabah
From (H7235) rabah; multiplication, i.e. Percentage or bonus in addition to principal -- increase, unjust gain. see HEBREW (H7235) rabah
A denominative from (H7270) ragal; to cause to walk -- teach to go. see HEBREW (H7270) ragal
A denominative from (H7275) ragam in the sense of throwing over; to transfer, i.e. Translate -- interpret. see HEBREW (H7275) ragam
From (H7290) radam; a lethargy or (by implication) trance -- deep sleep. see HEBREW (H7290) radam
Of foreign derivation; Tirhakah, a king of Kush -- Tirhakah.

column8: gift, heave offering shoulder, oblation, offering
column9: Or trumah (Deut 12:11) {ter-oo-maw'}; from (H7311) ruwm; a present (as offered up), especially in sacrifice or as tribute -- gift, heave offering ((shoulder)), oblation, offered(-ing). see HEBREW (H7311) ruwm

column7: what belongs to a contribution, a contribution
column9: Formed as (H8641) truwmah; a sacrificial offering -- oblation. see HEBREW (H8641) truwmah

column7: a shout or blast of war, alarm, or joy
column8: alarm, blowing of, the trumpets, joy, jubilee, loud noise, rejoicing, shouting,
column9: From (H7321) ruwa'; clamor, i.e. Acclamation of joy or a battle-cry; especially clangor of trumpets, as an alarum -- alarm, blow(- ing) (of, the) (trumpets), joy, jubile, loud noise, rejoicing, shout(-ing), (high, joyful) sound(-ing). see HEBREW (H7321) ruwa'
From (H7322) ruwph in the sense of its congener (H7495) rapha'; a remedy -- medicine. see HEBREW (H7322) ruwph see HEBREW (H7495) rapha'
Probably from (H7329) razah; a species of tree (apparently from its slenderness), perhaps the cypress -- cypress. see HEBREW (H7329) razah

column7: Abraham\'s father, also a place in the desert
column9: Of uncertain derivation; Terach, the father of Abraham; also a place in the Desert -- Tarah, Terah.
Of uncertain derivation; Tirchanah, an Israelite -- Tirhanah.
(Aramaic) feminine tarteyn {tar-tane'}; corresponding to (H8147) shnayim; two -- second, + twelve, two. see HEBREW (H8147) shnayim
And tarmuwth {tar-mooth'}; or tarmiyth {tar-meeth'}; from (H7411) ramah; fraud -- deceit(-ful), privily. see HEBREW (H7411) ramah
Probably for (H766) 'oren; a pole (as a mast or flag-staff) -- beacon, mast. see HEBREW (H766) 'oren
(Aramaic) corresponding to (H8179) sha'ar; a door; by implication, a palace -- gate mouth. see HEBREW (H8179) sha'ar
(Aramaic) from (H8651) tra'; a doorkeeper -- porter. see HEBREW (H8651) tra'
From (H7477) ra'al; reeling -- astonishment, trembling. see HEBREW (H7477) ra'al
Patrial from an unused name meaning gate; a Tirathite or inhabitant of an unknown Tirah -- Tirathite.

column7: (a kind of idol) perhaps household idol
column9: Plural from (H7495) rapha'; a healer; Teraphim (singular or plural) a family idol -- idols(-atry), images, teraphim. see HEBREW (H7495) rapha'

column7: daughter of Zelophehad, also a Canaanite city

From  (G134) aineo; a praising (the act), i.e. (specially) a thank(-offering) -- praise. see GREEK  (G134) aineo
From  (G136) ainos; to praise (God) -- praise. see GREEK  (G136) ainos
From a derivative of  (G136) ainos (in its primary sense); an obscure saying ("enigma"), i.e. (abstractly) obscureness -- X darkly. see GREEK  (G136) ainos
Apparently a prime word; properly, a story, but used in the sense of  (G1868) epainos; praise (of God) -- praise. see GREEK  (G1868) epainos

column7: Aenon, a place in the Jordan Valley
column9: Of Hebrew origin (a derivative of  (H5869) ayin, place of springs); ?Non, a place in Palestine -- ?Non. see HEBREW  (H5869) ayin
Probably akin to  (G142) airo; to take for oneself, i.e. To prefer -- choose. Some of the forms are borrowed from a cognate hellomai hel'-lom-ahee; which is otherwise obsolete. see GREEK  (G142) airo
From  (G138) haireomai; properly, a choice, i.e. (specially) a party or (abstractly) disunion -- heresy (which is the Greek word itself), sect. see GREEK  (G138) haireomai
From a derivative of  (G138) haireomai; to make a choice -- choose. see GREEK  (G138) haireomai
From the same as  (G140) hairetizo; a schismatic -- heretic (the Greek word itself). see GREEK  (G140) hairetizo

A primary root; to lift up; by implication, to take up or away; figuratively, to raise (the voice), keep in suspense (the mind), specially, to sail away (i.e. Weigh anchor); by Hebraism (compare  (H5375) nasa') to expiate sin -- away with, bear (up), carry, lift up, loose, make to doubt, put away, remove, take (away, up). see HEBREW  (H5375) nasa'
Of uncertain derivation; to apprehend (properly, by the senses) -- perceive.
From  (G143) aisthanomai; perception, i.e. (figuratively) discernment -- judgment. see GREEK  (G143) aisthanomai
From a derivative of  (G143) aisthanomai; properly, an organ of perception, i.e. (figuratively) judgment -- senses. see GREEK  (G143) aisthanomai
From  (G150) aischros and kerdos (gain); sordid -- given to (greedy of) filthy lucre. see GREEK  (G150) aischros

column8: for the sake of dishonest gain.
column9: Adverb from  (G146) aischrokerdes; sordidly -- for filthy lucre's sake. see GREEK  (G146) aischrokerdes
From  (G150) aischros and  (G3056) logos; vile conversation -- filthy communication. see GREEK  (G150) aischros see GREEK  (G3056) logos
Neuter of  (G150) aischros; a shameful thing, i.e. Indecorum -- shame. see GREEK  (G150) aischros
From the same as  (G153) aischunomai; shameful, i.e. Base (specially, venal) -- filthy. see GREEK  (G153) aischunomai
From  (G150) aischros; shamefulness, i.e. Obscenity -- filthiness. see GREEK  (G150) aischros
From  (G153) aischunomai; shame or disgrace (abstractly or concretely) -- dishonesty, shame. see GREEK  (G153) aischunomai
From aischos (disfigurement, i.e. Disgrace); to feel shame (for oneself) -- be ashamed.

column8: ask, beg, call for, crave, desire.
column9: Of uncertain derivation; to ask (in genitive case) -- ask, beg, call for, crave, desire, require. Compare  (G4441) punthanomai. see GREEK  (G4441) punthanomai
From  (G154) aiteo; a thing asked or (abstractly) an asking -- petition, request, required. see GREEK  (G154) aiteo

From the same as  (G154) aiteo; a cause (as if asked for), i.e. (logical) reason (motive, matter), (legal) crime (alleged or proved) -- accusation, case, cause, crime, fault, (wh-)ere(-fore). see GREEK  (G154) aiteo
From a derivative of  (G156) aitia; a thing charged -- complaint. see GREEK  (G156) aitia
Neuter of  (G159) aitios; a reason or crime (like  (G156) aitia) -- cause, fault. see GREEK  (G159) aitios see GREEK  (G156) aitia
From the same as  (G154) aiteo; causative, i.e. (concretely) a causer -- author. see GREEK  (G154) aiteo

From a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G5316) phaino (compare  (G1810) exaiphnes) (meaning non-apparent); unexpected, i.e. (adverbially) suddenly -- sudden, unawares. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G5316) phaino see GREEK  (G1810) exaiphnes
From  (G164) aichmalotos; captivity -- captivity. see GREEK  (G164) aichmalotos
From  (G164) aichmalotos; to capture (like  (G163) aichmalotizo) -- lead captive. see GREEK  (G164) aichmalotos see GREEK  (G163) aichmalotizo

column8: lead away captive, bring into captivity.
column9: From  (G164) aichmalotos; to make captive -- lead away captive, bring into captivity. see GREEK  (G164) aichmalotos
From aichme (a spear) and a derivative of the same as  (G259) halosis; properly, a prisoner of war, i.e. (genitive case) a captive -- captive. see GREEK  (G259) halosis

column7: a space of time, an age
column9: From the same as  (G104) aei; properly, an age; by extension, perpetuity (also past); by implication, the world; specially (Jewish) a Messianic period (present or future) -- age, course, eternal, (for) ever(-more), (n-)ever, (beginning of the, while the) world (began, without end). Compare  (G5550) chronos. see GREEK  (G104) aei see GREEK  (G5550) chronos
From  (G165) aion; perpetual (also used of past time, or past and future as well) -- eternal, for ever, everlasting, world (began). see GREEK  (G165) aion
From  (G169) akathartos; impurity (the quality), physically or morally -- uncleanness. see GREEK  (G169) akathartos
From  (G169) akathartos; impurity (the state), morally -- filthiness. see GREEK  (G169) akathartos

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G2508) kathairo (meaning cleansed); impure (ceremonially, morally (lewd) or specially, (demonic)) -- foul, unclean. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2508) kathairo

From a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2540) kairos (meaning unseasonable); to be inopportune (for oneself), i.e. To fail of a proper occasion -- lack opportunity. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2540) kairos
Adverb from the same as  (G170) akaireomai; inopportunely -- out of season. see GREEK  (G170) akaireomai
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2556) kakos; not bad, i.e. (objectively) innocent or (subjectively) unsuspecting -- harmless, simple. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2556) kakos
Probably from the same as  (G188) akmen; a thorn -- thorn. see GREEK  (G188) akmen
From  (G173) akantha; thorny -- of thorns. see GREEK  (G173) akantha
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2590) karpos; barren (literally or figuratively) -- without fruit, unfruitful. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2590) karpos

column7: not to be condemned, beyond reproach
column9: From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2607) kataginosko; unblamable -- that cannot be condemned. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2607) kataginosko
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of a compound of  (G2596) kata and  (G2572) kalupto; unveiled -- uncovered. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G2572) kalupto
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2632) katakrino; without (legal) trial -- uncondemned. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2632) katakrino
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2647) kataluo; indissoluble, i.e. (figuratively) permanent -- endless. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2647) kataluo
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2664) katapauo; unrefraining -- that cannot cease. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2664) katapauo
From  (G182) akatastatos; instability, i.e. Disorder -- commotion, confusion, tumult. see GREEK  (G182) akatastatos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2525) kathistemi; inconstant -- unstable. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2525) kathistemi
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2722) katecho; unrestrainable -- unruly. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2722) katecho

column7: Hakeldama, a field apparantly located south of the valley of Hinnom
column9: Of Chaldee origin (meaning field of blood; corresponding to  (G2506) kathairesis and  (G1818) exapatao); Akeldama, a place near Jerusalem -- Aceldama. see HEBREW  (H2506) cheleq see HEBREW  (H1818) dam
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G2767) kerannumi; unmixed, i.e. (figuratively) innocent -- harmless, simple. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2767) kerannumi
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2827) klino; not leaning, i.e. (figuratively) firm -- without wavering. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2827) klino
From the same as  (G188) akmen; to make a point, i.e. (figuratively) mature -- be fully ripe. see GREEK  (G188) akmen

column7: at the present point of time
column9: Accusative case of a noun ("acme") akin to ake (a point) and meaning the same; adverbially, just now, i.e. Still -- yet.
From  (G191) akouo; hearing (the act, the sense or the thing heard) -- audience, ear, fame, which ye heard, hearing, preached, report, rumor. see GREEK  (G191) akouo
From  (G1) a (as a particle of union) and keleuthos (a road); properly, to be in the same way with, i.e. To accompany (specially, as a disciple) -- follow, reach. see GREEK  (G1) a

column8: give audience, come to the ears, be reported
column9: A primary verb; to hear (in various senses) -- give (in the) audience (of), come (to the ears), (shall) hear(-er, -ken), be noised, be reported, understand.
From  (G193) akrates; want of self-restraint -- excess, incontinency. see GREEK  (G193) akrates
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2904) kratos; powerless, i.e. Without self-control -- incontinent. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2904) kratos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G2767) kerannumi; undiluted -- without mixture. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2767) kerannumi
From the same as  (G196) akribestatos; exactness -- perfect manner. see GREEK  (G196) akribestatos
Superlative of akribes (a derivative of the same as  (G206) akron); most exact -- most straitest. see GREEK  (G206) akron
Neuter of the comparative of the same as  (G196) akribestatos; (adverbially) more exactly -- more perfect(-ly). see GREEK  (G196) akribestatos
From the same as  (G196) akribestatos; to be exact, i.e. Ascertain -- enquire diligently. see GREEK  (G196) akribestatos
Adverb from the same as  (G196) akribestatos; exactly -- circumspectly, diligently, perfect(-ly). see GREEK  (G196) akribestatos
Apparently from the same as  (G206) akron; a locust (as pointed, or as lighting on the top of vegetation) -- locust. see GREEK  (G206) akron
From  (G202) akroates; an audience-room -- place of hearing. see GREEK  (G202) akroates
From akroaomai (to listen; apparently an intensive of  (G191) akouo); a hearer (merely) -- hearer. see GREEK  (G191) akouo

From  (G206) akron and probably a modified form of posthe (the penis or male sexual organ); the prepuce; by implication, an uncircumcised (i.e. Gentile, figuratively, unregenerate) state or person -- not circumcised, uncircumcised (with  (G2192) echo), uncircumcision. see GREEK  (G206) akron see GREEK  (G2192) echo

column7: at the extreme angle or corner
column9: From  (G206) akron and  (G1137) gonia; belonging to the extreme corner -- chief corner. see GREEK  (G206) akron see GREEK  (G1137) gonia

column7: the top of a heap, the best of the spoils
column9: From  (G206) akron and this (a heap); properly (in the plural) the top of the heap, i.e. (by implication) best of the booty -- spoils. see GREEK  (G206) akron
Neuter of an adjective probably akin to the base of  (G188) akmen; the extremity -- one end... Other, tip, top, uttermost participle see GREEK  (G188) akmen
Probably for Latin aquila (an eagle); Akulas, an Israelite -- Aquila.
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2964) kuroo; to invalidate -- disannul, make of none effect. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2964) kuroo

Adverb from a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2967) koluo; in an unhindered manner, i.e. Freely -- no man forbidding him. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2967) koluo
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G1635) hekon; unwilling -- against the will. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G1635) hekon
Neuter of alabastros (of uncertain derivation), the name of a stone; properly, an "alabaster" box, i.e. (by extension) a perfume vase (of any material) -- (alabaster) box.
From  (G213) alazon; braggadocio, i.e. (by implication) self-confidence -- boasting, pride. see GREEK  (G213) alazon
From ale (vagrancy); braggart -- boaster.
From alale (a shout, "halloo"); to vociferate, i.e. (by implication) to wail; figuratively, to clang -- tinkle, wail.
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G2980) laleo; unspeakable -- unutterable, which cannot be uttered. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2980) laleo
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2980) laleo; mute -- dumb. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2980) laleo
From  (G251) hals; salt; figuratively, prudence -- salt. see GREEK  (G251) hals
From  (G1) a (as particle of union) and the base of  (G3045) liparos; to oil (with perfume) -- anoint. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3045) liparos
From  (G220) alektor and  (G5456) phone; cock-crow, i.e. The third night-watch -- cockcrowing. see GREEK  (G220) alektor see GREEK  (G5456) phone
From aleko (to ward off); a cock or male fowl -- cock.
From Alexandreia (the city so called); an Alexandreian or inhabitant of Alexandria -- of Alexandria, Alexandrian.
From the same as  (G221) Alexandreus; Alexandrine, or belonging to Alexandria -- of Alexandria. see GREEK  (G221) Alexandreus

column7: Alexander, a son of Simon of Cyrene, also a coppersmith, also two Jews
column9: From the same as (the first part of)  (G220) alektor and  (G435) aner; man-defender; Alexander, the name of three Israelites and one other man -- Alexander. see GREEK  (G220) alektor see GREEK  (G435) aner
From aleo (to grind); flour -- meal.
From  (G227) alethes; truth -- true, X truly, truth, verity. see GREEK  (G227) alethes
From  (G227) alethes; to be true (in doctrine and profession) -- speak (tell) the truth. see GREEK  (G227) alethes
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2990) lanthano; true (as not concealing) -- true, truly, truth. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2990) lanthano
From  (G227) alethes; truthful -- true. see GREEK  (G227) alethes
From the same as  (G224) aleuron; to grind -- grind. see GREEK  (G224) aleuron
Adverb from  (G227) alethes; truly -- indeed, surely, of a surety, truly, of a (in) truth, verily, very. see GREEK  (G227) alethes
From  (G251) hals; a sailor (as engaged on the salt water), i.e. (by implication) a fisher -- fisher(-man). see GREEK  (G251) hals
From  (G231) halieus; to be a fisher, i.e. (by implication) to fish -- go a-fishing. see GREEK  (G231) halieus
From  (G251) hals; to salt -- salt. see GREEK  (G251) hals
From alisgeo (to soil); (ceremonially) defilement -- pollution.

column7: otherwise, on the other hand, but
column9: Neuter plural of  (G243) allos; properly, other things, i.e. (adverbially) contrariwise (in many relations) -- and, but (even), howbeit, indeed, nay, nevertheless, no, notwithstanding, save, therefore, yea, yet. see GREEK  (G243) allos
From  (G243) allos; to make different -- change. see GREEK  (G243) allos

column8: some other way, from somewhere else
column9: From  (G243) allos; from elsewhere -- some other way. see GREEK  (G243) allos
From  (G243) allos and agoreo (to harangue (compare  (G58) agora)); to allegorize -- be an allegory (the Greek word itself). see GREEK  (G243) allos see GREEK  (G58) agora
Of Hebrew origin (imperative of  (H1984) halal and  (H3050) Yahh); praise ye Jah!, an adoring exclamation -- alleluiah. see HEBREW  (H1984) halal see HEBREW  (H3050) Yahh

Genitive plural from  (G243) allos reduplicated; one another -- each other, mutual, one another, (the other), (them-, your-)selves, (selves) together (sometimes with  (G3326) meta or  (G4314) pros). see GREEK  (G243) allos see GREEK  (G3326) meta see GREEK  (G4314) pros
From  (G243) allos and  (G1085) genos; foreign, i.e. Not a Jew -- stranger. see GREEK  (G243) allos see GREEK  (G1085) genos
Middle voice of apparently a primary verb; to jump; figuratively, to gush -- leap, spring up.
A primary word; "else," i.e. Different (in many applications) -- more, one (another), (an-, some an-)other(-s, -wise).

column7: one who meddles in things alien to his calling
column9: From  (G245) allotrios and  (G1985) episkopos; overseeing others' affairs, i.e. A meddler (specially, in Gentile customs) -- busybody in other men's matters. see GREEK  (G245) allotrios see GREEK  (G1985) episkopos
From  (G243) allos; another's, i.e. Not one's own; by extension foreign, not akin, hostile -- alien, (an-)other (man's, men's), strange(-r). see GREEK  (G243) allos
From  (G243) allos and  (G5443) phule; foreign, i.e. (specially) Gentile -- one of another nation. see GREEK  (G243) allos see GREEK  (G5443) phule
Adverb from  (G243) allos; differently -- otherwise. see GREEK  (G243) allos
From the same as  (G257) halon; to tread out grain -- thresh, tread out the corn. see GREEK  (G257) halon
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3056) logos; irrational -- brute, unreasonable. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3056) logos
Of foreign origin (compare  (G174) akanthinos); aloes (the gum) -- aloes. see GREEK  (G174) akanthinos
A primary word; "salt" -- salt.
From  (G251) hals; briny -- salt. see GREEK  (G251) hals
Comparative of a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3077) lupe; more without grief -- less sorrowful. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3077) lupe
Of uncertain derivation; a fetter or manacle -- bonds, chain.
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and the base of  (G3081) lusitelei; gainless, i.e. (by implication) pernicious -- unprofitable. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3081) lusitelei
Of Hebrew origin (compare  (H2501) Cheleph); Alphoeus, an Israelite -- Alpheus. see HEBREW  (H2501) Cheleph
Probably from the base of  (G1507) heilisso; a threshing-floor (as rolled hard), i.e. (figuratively) the grain (and chaff, as just threshed) -- floor. see GREEK  (G1507) heilisso
Of uncertain derivation; a fox, i.e. (figuratively) a cunning person -- fox.
From a collateral form of  (G138) haireomai; capture, be taken. see GREEK  (G138) haireomai
A primary particle; properly, at the "same" time, but freely used as a preposition or adverb denoting close association -- also, and, together, with(-al).
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3129) manthano; ignorant -- unlearned. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3129) manthano
From  (G263) amarantos; "amaranthine", i.e. (by implication) fadeless -- that fadeth not away. see GREEK  (G263) amarantos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G3133) maraino; unfading, i.e. (by implication) perpetual -- that fadeth not away. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3133) maraino

column7: to miss the mark, do wrong, sin
column9: Perhaps from  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and the base of  (G3313) meros; properly, to miss the mark (and so not share in the prize), i.e. (figuratively) to err, especially (morally) to sin -- for your faults, offend, sin, trespass. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3313) meros
From  (G264) hamartano; a sin (properly concrete) -- sin. see GREEK  (G264) hamartano
From  (G264) hamartano; a sin (properly abstract) -- offence, sin(-ful). see GREEK  (G264) hamartano
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a form of  (G3144) martus; unattested -- without witness. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3144) martus
From  (G264) hamartano; sinful, i.e. A sinner -- sinful, sinner. see GREEK  (G264) hamartano
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3163) mache; peaceable -- not a brawler. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3163) mache
From  (G260) hama; properly, to collect, i.e. (by implication) reap -- reap down. see GREEK  (G260) hama
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G3184) methuo; the "amethyst" (supposed to prevent intoxication) -- amethyst. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3184) methuo

column8: make light of, neglect, show no regard.
column9: From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3199) melo; to be careless of -- make light of, neglect, be negligent, no regard. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3199) melo
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G3201) memphomai; irreproachable -- blameless, faultless, unblamable. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3201) memphomai
Adverb from  (G273) amemptos; faultlessly -- blameless, unblamably. see GREEK  (G273) amemptos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3308) merimna; not anxious -- without care(-fulness), secure. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3308) merimna

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G3346) metatithemi; unchangeable, or (neuter as abstract) unchangeability -- immutable(-ility). see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3346) metatithemi
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G3334) metakineo; immovable -- unmovable. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3334) metakineo
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G3338) metamellomai; irrevocable -- without repentance, not to be repented of. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3338) metamellomai
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G3340) metanoeo; unrepentant -- impenitent. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3340) metanoeo
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3358) metron; immoderate -- (thing) without measure. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3358) metron
Of Hebrew origin ( (H543) 'amen); properly, firm, i.e. (figuratively) trustworthy; adverbially, surely (often as interjection, so be it) -- amen, verily. see HEBREW  (H543) 'amen
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3384) meter; motherless, i.e. Of unknown maternity -- without mother. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3384) meter
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G3392) miaino; unsoiled, i.e. (figuratively) pure -- undefiled. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3392) miaino

column7: Amminadab, an Israelite ancestor of Christ
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H5992) Ammiynadab); Aminadab, an Israelite -- Aminadab. see HEBREW  (H5992) Ammiynadab
Perhaps from  (G260) hama; sand (as heaped on the beach) -- sand. see GREEK  (G260) hama
Apparently a primary word; a lamb -- lamb.
From ameibo (to exchange); requital -- requite.
Probably from the base of  (G297) amphoteros and that of  (G257) halon; a vine (as coiling about a support) -- vine. see GREEK  (G297) amphoteros see GREEK  (G257) halon

From  (G288) ampelos; a vineyard -- vineyard. see GREEK  (G288) ampelos

Adverb from  (G459) anomos; lawlessly, i.e. (specially) not amenable to (the Jewish) law -- without law. see GREEK  (G459) anomos

From  (G473) anti and  (G378) anapleroo; to supplement -- fill up. see GREEK  (G473) anti see GREEK  (G378) anapleroo

From  (G473) anti and  (G2036) epo; to refute or deny -- gainsay, say against. see GREEK  (G473) anti see GREEK  (G2036) epo

Prolonged from  (G473) anti; opposite -- over against. see GREEK  (G473) anti

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3982) peitho; unpersuadable, i.e. Contumacious -- disobedient. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3982) peitho
Of uncertain derivation; to menace; by implication, to forbid -- threaten.

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G3984) peira; inexperienced, i.e. Ignorant -- unskilful. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G3984) peira
From  (G575) apo and  (G1551) ekdechomai; to expect fully -- look (wait) foreign see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1551) ekdechomai

From  (G554) apekduomai; divestment -- putting off. see GREEK  (G554) apekduomai
From  (G575) apo and  (G1643) elauno; to dismiss -- drive. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1643) elauno
From a compound of  (G575) apo and  (G1651) elegcho; refutation, i.e. (by implication) contempt -- nought. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1651) elegcho

From  (G575) apo and  (G1725) enanti; from in front, i.e. Opposite, before or against -- before, contrary, over against, in the presence of. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1725) enanti
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a secondary derivative of  (G4008) peran; unfinished, i.e. (by implication) interminable -- endless. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G4008) peran

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G4059) peritemno; uncircumcised (figuratively) -- uncircumcised. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G4059) peritemno

column8: come, depart, go away, pass away.

Middle voice (reflexively) of  (G568) apecho; to hold oneself off, i.e. Refrain -- abstain. see GREEK  (G568) apecho

From  (G571) apistos; faithlessness, i.e. (negatively) disbelief (lack of Christian faith), or (positively) unfaithfulness (disobedience) -- unbelief. see GREEK  (G571) apistos

From  (G573) haplous; singleness, i.e. (subjectively) sincerity (without dissimulation or self-seeking), or (objectively) generosity (copious bestowal) -- bountifulness, liberal(-ity), simplicity, singleness. see GREEK  (G573) haplous
Probably from  (G1) a (as a particle of union) and the base of  (G4120) pleko; properly, folded together, i.e. Single (figuratively, clear) -- single. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G4120) pleko
Adverb from  (G573) haplous (in the objective sense of  (G572) haplotes); bountifully; --liberally. see GREEK  (G573) haplous see GREEK  (G572) haplotes

column8: hereafter, ago, at, because of, before.
column9: A primary particle; "off," i.e. Away (from something near), in various senses (of place, time, or relation; literal or figurative) -- (X here-)after, ago, at, because of, before, by (the space of), for(-th), from, in, (out) of, off, (up-)on(-ce), since, with. In composition (as a prefix) it usually denotes separation, departure, cessation, completion, reversal, etc.
From  (G575) apo and the base of  (G939) basis; literally, to disembark; figuratively, to eventuate -- become, go out, turn. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G939) basis
From  (G575) apo and  (G906) ballo; to throw off; figuratively, to lose -- cast away. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G906) ballo

column7: to look away from all else at an object
column9: From  (G575) apo and  (G991) blepo; to look away from everything else, i.e. (figuratively) intently regard -- have respect. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G991) blepo
From  (G577) apoballo; cast off, i.e. (figuratively) such as to be rejected -- be refused. see GREEK  (G577) apoballo
From  (G577) apoballo; rejection; figuratively, loss -- casting away, loss. see GREEK  (G577) apoballo

column7: to be away, be removed from
column9: Past participle of a compound of  (G575) apo and  (G1096) ginomai; absent, i.e. Deceased (figuratively, renounced) -- being dead. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai
From  (G583) apographo; an enrollment; by implication, an assessment -- taxing. see GREEK  (G583) apographo
From  (G575) apo and  (G1125) grapho; to write off (a copy or list), i.e. Enrol -- tax, write. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1125) grapho

column7: to bring out, show forth, declare
column9: From  (G575) apo and  (G1166) deiknuo; to show off, i.e. Exhibit; figuratively, to demonstrate, i.e. Accredit -- (ap-)prove, set forth, shew. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1166) deiknuo
From  (G584) apodeiknumi; manifestation -- demonstration. see GREEK  (G584) apodeiknumi

column8: give, pay, or take a tithe.
column9: From  (G575) apo and  (G1183) dekatoo; to tithe (as debtor or creditor) -- (give, pay, take) tithe. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1183) dekatoo
From  (G588) apodechomai; accepted, i.e. Agreeable -- acceptable. see GREEK  (G588) apodechomai
From  (G575) apo and  (G1209) dechomai; to take fully, i.e. Welcome (persons), approve (things) -- accept, receive (gladly). see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai

column8: travel into a far country, journey.
column9: From  (G590) apodemos; to go abroad, i.e. Visit a foreign land -- go (travel) into a far country, journey. see GREEK  (G590) apodemos
From  (G575) apo and  (G1218) demos; absent from one's own people, i.e. A foreign traveller -- taking a far journey. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1218) demos

From  (G575) apo and a compound of  (G223) Alexandros and  (G3724) horizo; to disjoin (by a boundary, figuratively, a party) -- separate. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G223) Alexandros see GREEK  (G3724) horizo
From  (G575) apo and  (G1381) dokimazo; to disapprove, i.e. (by implication) to repudiate -- disallow, reject. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1381) dokimazo
From  (G588) apodechomai; acceptance -- acceptation. see GREEK  (G588) apodechomai
From  (G659) apotithemi; a laying aside (literally or figuratively) -- putting away (off). see GREEK  (G659) apotithemi

column7: a place for putting away, a storehouse
column9: From  (G659) apotithemi; a repository, i.e. Granary -- barn, garner. see GREEK  (G659) apotithemi
From  (G575) apo and  (G2343) thesaurizo; to treasure away -- lay up in store. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2343) thesaurizo
From  (G575) apo and  (G2346) thlibo; to crowd (from every side) -- press. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2346) thlibo

column9: From  (G575) apo and  (G2348) thnesko; to die off (literally or figuratively) -- be dead, death, die, lie a-dying, be slain (X with). see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2348) thnesko
From  (G575) apo and  (G2525) kathistemi; to reconstitute (in health, home or organization) -- restore (again). see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2525) kathistemi
From  (G575) apo and  (G2572) kalupto; to take off the cover, i.e. Disclose -- reveal. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2572) kalupto
From  (G601) apokalupto; disclosure -- appearing, coming, lighten, manifestation, be revealed, revelation. see GREEK  (G601) apokalupto

From a comparative of  (G575) apo and a compound of kara (the head) and  (G1380) dokeo (in the sense of watching); intense anticipation -- earnest expectation. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G1380) dokeo
From  (G575) apo and  (G2644) katallasso; to reconcile fully -- reconcile. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2644) katallasso
From  (G600) apokathistemi; reconstitution -- restitution. see GREEK  (G600) apokathistemi

column7: to be laid away, be laid up in store
column9: From  (G575) apo and  (G2749) keimai; to be reserved; figuratively, to await -- be appointed, (be) laid up. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2749) keimai
From  (G575) apo and  (G2776) kephale; to decapitate -- behead. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2776) kephale
From  (G575) apo and  (G2808) kleio; to close fully -- shut up. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2808) kleio

From  (G611) apokrinomai (in its original sense of judging); a judicial decision -- sentence. see GREEK  (G611) apokrinomai

From  (G575) apo and krino; to conclude for oneself, i.e. (by implication) to respond; by Hebraism (compare  (H6030) anah) to begin to speak (where an address is expected) -- answer. see GREEK  (G575) apo see HEBREW  (H6030) anah
From  (G611) apokrinomai; a response -- answer. see GREEK  (G611) apokrinomai
From  (G575) apo and  (G2928) krupto; to conceal away (i.e. Fully); figuratively, to keep secret -- hide. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2928) krupto
From  (G613) apokrupto; secret; by implication, treasured -- hid, kept secret. see GREEK  (G613) apokrupto
From  (G575) apo and kteino (to slay); to kill outright; figuratively, to destroy -- put to death, kill, slay. see GREEK  (G575) apo
From  (G575) apo and the base of  (G2949) kuma; to breed forth, i.e. (by transference) to generate (figuratively) -- beget, produce. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2949) kuma
From  (G575) apo and  (G2947) kulioo; to roll away -- roll away (back). see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2947) kulioo

column7: to receive from, receive as one\'s due
column9: From  (G575) apo and  (G2983) lambano; to receive (specially, in full, or as a host); also to take aside -- receive, take. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G2983) lambano
From a comparative of  (G575) apo and lauo (to enjoy); full enjoyment -- enjoy(-ment). see GREEK  (G575) apo
From  (G575) apo and  (G3007) leipo; to leave behind (passively, remain); by implication, to forsake -- leave, remain. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G3007) leipo
From  (G575) apo and leicho (to "lick"); to lick clean -- lick. see GREEK  (G575) apo

From  (G575) apo and the base of  (G3639) olethros; to destroy fully (reflexively, to perish, or lose), literally or figuratively -- destroy, die, lose, mar, perish. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G3639) olethros

column7: a destroyer, Apollyon, the angel of the abyss
column9: Active participle of  (G622) apollumi; a destroyer (i.e. Satan) -- Apollyon. see GREEK  (G622) apollumi
From the pagan deity Apollon (i.e. The sun; from  (G622) apollumi); Apollonia, a place in Macedonia -- Apollonia. see GREEK  (G622) apollumi
Probably from the same as  (G624) Apollonia; Apollos, an Israelite -- Apollos. see GREEK  (G624) Apollonia

column7: to give an account of oneself, to defend oneself
column9: Middle voice from a compound of  (G575) apo and  (G3056) logos; to give an account (legal plea) of oneself, i.e. Exculpate (self) -- answer (for self), make defence, excuse (self), speak for self. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G3056) logos

column8: answer for oneself, clearing of self, defense.
column9: From the same as  (G626) apologeomai; a plea ("apology") -- answer (for self), clearing of self, defence. see GREEK  (G626) apologeomai
From  (G575) apo and  (G3068) louo; to wash fully, i.e. (figuratively) have remitted (reflexively) -- wash (away). see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G3068) louo

Middle voice from  (G575) apo and masso (to squeeze, knead, smear); to scrape away -- wipe off. see GREEK  (G575) apo
From  (G575) apo and the base of  (G3551) nomos; to apportion, i.e. Bestow -- give. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G3551) nomos
From  (G575) apo and  (G3538) nipto; to wash off (reflexively, one's own hands symbolically) -- wash. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G3538) nipto
From  (G575) apo and  (G4098) pipto; to fall off -- fall. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4098) pipto
From  (G575) apo and  (G4105) planao; to lead astray (figuratively); passively, to stray (from truth) -- err, seduce. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4105) planao
From  (G575) apo and  (G4126) pleo; to set sail -- sail away. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4126) pleo
From  (G575) apo and  (G4150) pluno; to rinse off -- wash. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4150) pluno
From  (G575) apo and  (G4155) pnigo; to stifle (by drowning or overgrowth) -- choke. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4155) pnigo

column7: to be at a loss, be perplexed

From the same as  (G639) aporeo; a (state of) quandary -- perplexity. see GREEK  (G639) aporeo
From  (G575) apo and  (G4496) rhipto; to hurl off, i.e. Precipitate (oneself) -- cast. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4496) rhipto
From  (G575) apo and a derivative of  (G3737) orphanos; to bereave wholly, i.e. (figuratively) separate (from intercourse) -- take. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G3737) orphanos
From  (G575) apo and a derivative of  (G4632) skeuos; to pack up (one's) baggage -- take up... Carriages. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4632) skeuos
From a compound of  (G575) apo and a derivative of  (G4639) skia; a shading off, i.e. Obscuration -- shadow. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4639) skia

From  (G575) apo and  (G4685) spao; to drag forth, i.e. (literally) unsheathe (a sword), or relatively (with a degree of force implied) retire (personally or factiously) -- (with-)draw (away), after we were gotten from. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4685) spao
Feminine of the same as  (G647) apostasion; defection from truth (properly, the state) ("apostasy") -- falling away, forsake. see GREEK  (G647) apostasion
Neuter of a (presumed) adjective from a derivative of  (G868) aphistemi; properly, something separative, i.e. (specially) divorce -- (writing of) divorcement. see GREEK  (G868) aphistemi
From  (G575) apo and a derivative of  (G4721) stege; to unroof -- uncover. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4721) stege

From  (G575) apo and  (G4724) stello; set apart, i.e. (by implication) to send out (properly, on a mission) literally or figuratively -- put in, send (away, forth, out), set (at liberty). see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4724) stello
From  (G575) apo and stereo (to deprive); to despoil -- defraud, destitute, kept back by fraud. see GREEK  (G575) apo
From  (G649) apostello; commission, i.e. (specially) apostolate -- apostleship. see GREEK  (G649) apostello

column7: a messenger, one sent on a mission, an apostle
column8: apostle, messenger, he that is sent.
column9: From  (G649) apostello; a delegate; specially, an ambassador of the Gospel; officially a commissioner of Christ ("apostle") (with miraculous powers) -- apostle, messenger, he that is sent. see GREEK  (G649) apostello

From  (G575) apo and a (presumed) derivative of  (G4750) stoma; to speak off-hand (properly, dictate), i.e. To catechize (in an invidious manner) -- provoke to speak. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4750) stoma
From  (G575) apo and  (G4762) strepho; to turn away or back (literally or figuratively) -- bring again, pervert, turn away (from). see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4762) strepho
From  (G575) apo and the base of  (G4767) stugnetos; to detest utterly -- abhor. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4767) stugnetos
From  (G575) apo and  (G4864) sunagoge; excommunicated -- (put) out of the synagogue(-s). see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G4864) sunagoge

column7: to set apart, take leave of
column8: bid farewell, forsake, take leave, send away.
column9: Middle voice from  (G575) apo and  (G5021) tasso; literally, to say adieu (by departing or dismissing); figuratively, to renounce -- bid farewell, forsake, take leave, send away. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5021) tasso

column7: to bring to an end, complete
column9: From  (G575) apo and  (G5055) teleo; to complete entirely, i.e. Consummate -- finish. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5055) teleo

column8: cast off, lay aside, put away.
column9: From  (G575) apo and  (G5087) tithemi; to put away (literally or figuratively) -- cast off, lay apart (aside, down), put away (off). see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi
From  (G575) apo and tinasso (to jostle); to brush off -- shake off. see GREEK  (G575) apo
From  (G575) apo and  (G5099) tino; to pay in full -- repay. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5099) tino
From  (G575) apo and  (G5111) tolmao; to venture plainly -- be very bold. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5111) tolmao
From the base of  (G664) apotomos; (figuratively) decisiveness, i.e. Rigor -- severity. see GREEK  (G664) apotomos
Adverb from a derivative of a comparative of  (G575) apo and temno (to cut); abruptly, i.e. Peremptorily -- sharply(-ness). see GREEK  (G575) apo
From  (G575) apo and the base of  (G5157) trope; to deflect, i.e. (reflexively) avoid -- turn away. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5157) trope
From the participle of  (G548) apeimi; a being away -- absence. see GREEK  (G548) apeimi
From  (G575) apo and  (G5342) phero; to bear off (literally or relatively) -- bring, carry (away). see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5342) phero
From  (G575) apo and  (G5343) pheugo; (figuratively) to escape -- escape. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5343) pheugo
From  (G575) apo and  (G5350) phtheggomai; to enunciate plainly, i.e. Declare -- say, speak forth, utterance. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5350) phtheggomai
From  (G575) apo and the middle voice of  (G5412) phortizo; to unload -- unlade. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5412) phortizo
From a compound of  (G575) apo and  (G5530) chraomai; the act of using up, i.e. Consumption -- using. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5530) chraomai
From  (G575) apo and  (G5562) choreo; to go away -- depart. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5562) choreo
From  (G575) apo and  (G5563) chorizo; to rend apart; reflexively, to separate -- depart (asunder). see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5563) chorizo
From  (G575) apo and  (G5594) psucho; to breathe out, i.e. Faint -- hearts failing. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G5594) psucho

column7: Market of Appius, the name of a city south of Rome
column9: Of Latin origin; (in the genitive, i.e. Possessive case) of Appius, the name of a Roman -- Appii.
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of a comparative of  (G4314) pros and eimi (to go); inaccessible -- which no man can approach. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G4314) pros

column7: not causing to stumble, not stumbling
column9: From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of  (G4350) proskopto; actively, inoffensive, i.e. Not leading into sin; passively, faultless, i.e. Not led into sin -- none (void of, without) offence. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G4350) proskopto

column7: not accepting the person, without respect of persons
column9: Adverb from a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a presumed derivative of a presumed compound of  (G4383) prosopon and  (G2983) lambano (compare  (G4381) prosopoleptes); in a way not accepting the person, i.e. Impartially -- without respect of persons. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G4383) prosopon see GREEK  (G2983) lambano see GREEK  (G4381) prosopoleptes
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and a derivative of  (G4417) ptaio; not stumbling, i.e. (figuratively) without sin -- from falling. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G4417) ptaio
Reflexive of  (G681) hapto; properly, to attach oneself to, i.e. To touch (in many implied relations) -- touch. see GREEK  (G681) hapto

column7: to fasten to, lay hold of
column9: A primary verb; properly, to fasten to, i.e. (specially) to set on fire -- kindle, light.

column7: Apphia, a Christian woman in Colossae
column9: Probably of foreign origin; Apphia, a woman of Collosae -- Apphia.

Or apothomai ap-o'-thom-ahee from  (G575) apo and the middle voice of otheo or otho (to shove); to push off, figuratively, to reject -- cast away, put away (from), thrust away (from). see GREEK  (G575) apo

From a presumed derivative of  (G622) apollumi; ruin or loss (physical, spiritual or eternal) -- damnable(-nation), destruction, die, perdition, X perish, pernicious ways, waste. see GREEK  (G622) apollumi
Probably from  (G142) airo; properly, prayer (as lifted to Heaven), i.e. (by implication) imprecation -- curse. see GREEK  (G142) airo

column8: no doubt, perhaps, then, therefore, truly, wherefore.
column9: Probably from  (G142) airo (through the idea of drawing a conclusion); a particle denoting an inference more or less decisive (as follows) -- haply, (what) manner (of man), no doubt, perhaps, so be, then, therefore, truly, wherefore. Often used in connection with other particles, especially  (G1065) ge or  (G3767) oun (after) or  (G1487) ei (before). Compare also  (G687) ara. see GREEK  (G142) airo see GREEK  (G1065) ge see GREEK  (G3767) oun see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G687) ara

column7: an untranslatable interrogative particle implying anxiety or impatience
column9: A form of  (G686) ara, denoting an interrogation to which a negative answer is presumed -- therefore. see GREEK  (G686) ara

column7: Arabia, a peninsula of Asia near Africa
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H6152)  Arab); Arabia, a region of Asia -- Arabia. see HEBREW  (H6152)  Arab
Of Hebrew origin ( (H7410) Ram); Aram (i.e. Ram), an Israelite -- Aram. see HEBREW  (H7410) Ram
From  (G688) Arabia; an Arab or native of Arabia -- Arabian. see GREEK  (G688) Arabia
From  (G692) argos; to be idle, i.e. (figuratively) to delay -- linger. see GREEK  (G692) argos
From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G2041) ergon; inactive, i.e. Unemployed; (by implication) lazy, useless -- barren, idle, slow. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G2041) ergon
From  (G696) arguros; made of silver -- (of) silver. see GREEK  (G696) arguros

Neuter of a presumed derivative of  (G696) arguros; silvery, i.e. (by implication) cash; specially, a silverling (i.e. Drachma or shekel) -- money, (piece of) silver (piece). see GREEK  (G696) arguros

column7: a beater of silver, a silversmith
column9: From  (G696) arguros and  (G2875) kopto; a beater (i.e. Worker) of silver -- silversmith. see GREEK  (G696) arguros see GREEK  (G2875) kopto
From argos (shining); silver (the metal, in the articles or coin) -- silver.

column7: the Hill of Ares, Areopagus, a hill in Athens
column9: From Ares (the name of the Greek deity of war) and a derivative of  (G4078) pegnumi; rock of Ares, a place in Athens -- Areopagus, Mars' Hill. see GREEK  (G4078) pegnumi

column7: a judge of the court of Areopagus
column9: From  (G697) Areios Pagos; an Areopagite or member of the court held on Mars' Hill -- Areopagite. see GREEK  (G697) Areios Pagos
From a derivative of  (G700) aresko; complaisance -- pleasing. see GREEK  (G700) aresko
Probably from  (G142) airo (through the idea of exciting emotion); to be agreeable (or by implication, to seek to be so) -- please. see GREEK  (G142) airo
From  (G700) aresko; agreeable; by implication, fit -- (things that) please(-ing), reason. see GREEK  (G700) aresko
Of foreign origin; Aretas, an Arabian -- Aretas.

column7: her own, his own, their own, themselves, they

Adverb from a compound of  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G5401) phobos; fearlessly -- without fear. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G5401) phobos
From  (G575) apo and  (G3666) homoioo; to assimilate closely -- make like. see GREEK  (G575) apo see GREEK  (G3666) homoioo

From  (G1) a (as a negative particle) and  (G5543) chrestos; inefficient, i.e. (by implication) detrimental -- unprofitable. see GREEK  (G1) a see GREEK  (G5543) chrestos
