column9: From  (G989) blasphemos; to vilify; specially, to speak impiously -- (speak) blaspheme(-er, -mously, -my), defame, rail on, revile, speak evil. see GREEK  (G989) blasphemos
From  (G989) blasphemos; vilification (especially against God) -- blasphemy, evil speaking, railing. see GREEK  (G989) blasphemos

From a derivative of  (G984) blapto and  (G5345) pheme; scurrilious, i.e. Calumnious (against men), or (specially) impious (against God) -- blasphemer(-mous), railing. see GREEK  (G984) blapto see GREEK  (G5345) pheme
From  (G991) blepo; vision (properly concrete; by implication, abstract) -- seeing. see GREEK  (G991) blepo
A primary verb; to look at (literally or figuratively) -- behold, beware, lie, look (on, to), perceive, regard, see, sight, take heed. Compare  (G3700) optanomai. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
From  (G906) ballo; fit to be cast (i.e. Applied) -- must be put. see GREEK  (G906) ballo

column7: Boanerges, an epithet applied to the two sons of Zebedee
column9: Of Chaldee origin ( (H1123) ben and  (H7266) rgaz); sons of commotion; Boanerges, an epithet of two of the apostles -- Boanerges. see HEBREW  (H1123) ben see HEBREW  (H7266) rgaz
Apparently a prolonged form of a primary verb; to halloo, i.e. Shout (for help or in a tumultuous way) -- cry.
From  (G994) boao; a halloo, i.e. Call (for aid, etc.) -- cry. see GREEK  (G994) boao
From  (G998) boethos; aid; specially, a rope or chain for frapping a vessel -- help. see GREEK  (G998) boethos

column7: to come to the aid of
column9: From  (G998) boethos; to aid or relieve -- help, succor. see GREEK  (G998) boethos
From  (G995) boe and theo (to run); a succorer -- helper. see GREEK  (G995) boe
Akin to  (G900) bathuno; a hole (in the ground); specially, a cistern -- ditch, pit. see GREEK  (G900) bathuno
From  (G906) ballo; a throw (as a measure of distance) -- cast. see GREEK  (G906) ballo
From  (G1002) bolis; to heave the lead -- sound. see GREEK  (G1002) bolis
From  (G906) ballo; a missile, i.e. Javelin -- dart. see GREEK  (G906) ballo
Of Hebrew origin ( (H1162) Bo'az); Booz, (i.e. Boaz), an Israelite -- Booz. see HEBREW  (H1162) Bo'az
Of uncertain derivation; mud -- mire.
Of uncertain derivation; the north (properly, wind) -- north.

A prolonged form of a primary verb (compare  (G977) bibrosko,  (G1016) bous); to pasture; by extension to, fodder; reflexively, to graze -- feed, keep. see GREEK  (G977) bibrosko see GREEK  (G1016) bous
Of Hebrew origin ( (H1160) b'owr); Bosor (i.e. Beor), a Moabite -- Bosor. see HEBREW  (H1160) b'owr
From  (G1006) bosko; herbage (as if for grazing) -- herb. see GREEK  (G1006) bosko
Of uncertain derivation; a bunch (of grapes) -- (vine) cluster (of the vine).
From  (G1011) bouleuo; an adviser, i.e. (specially) a councillor or member of the Jewish Sanhedrin -- counsellor. see GREEK  (G1011) bouleuo
From  (G1012) boule; to advise, i.e. (reflexively) deliberate, or (by implication) resolve -- consult, take counsel, determine, be minded, purpose. see GREEK  (G1012) boule
From  (G1014) boulomai; volition, i.e. (objectively) advice, or (by implication) purpose -- + advise, counsel, will. see GREEK  (G1014) boulomai
From  (G1014) boulomai; a resolve -- purpose, will. see GREEK  (G1014) boulomai
Middle voice of a primary verb; to "will," i.e. (reflexively) be willing -- be disposed, minded, intend, list, (be, of own) will (-ing). Compare  (G2309) ethelo. see GREEK  (G2309) ethelo
Probably of foreign origin; a hillock -- hill.
Probably from the base of  (G1006) bosko; an ox (as grazing), i.e. An animal of that species ("beef") -- ox. see GREEK  (G1006) bosko
From brabeus (an umpire of uncertain derivation); an award (of arbitration), i.e. (specially) a prize in the public games -- prize.
From the same as  (G1017) brabeion; to arbitrate, i.e. (genitive case) to govern (figuratively, prevail) -- rule. see GREEK  (G1017) brabeion
From  (G1021) bradus; to delay -- be slack, tarry. see GREEK  (G1021) bradus
From  (G1021) bradus and a prolonged form of  (G4126) pleo; to sail slowly -- sail slowly. see GREEK  (G1021) bradus see GREEK  (G4126) pleo
Of uncertain affinity; slow; figuratively, dull -- slow.
From  (G1021) bradus; tardiness -- slackness. see GREEK  (G1021) bradus
Properly, comparative of  (G1024) brachus, but apparently in the sense of brasso (to wield); the arm, i.e. (figuratively) strength -- arm. see GREEK  (G1024) brachus
Of uncertain affinity; short (of time, place, quantity, or number) -- few words, little (space, while).

column7: an unborn or a newborn child
column9: Of uncertain affinity; an infant (properly, unborn) literally or figuratively -- babe, (young) child, infant.
A primary verb; to moisten (especially by a shower) -- (send) rain, wash.
Akin to bremo (to roar); thunder -- thunder(-ing).
From  (G1026) brecho; rain -- rain. see GREEK  (G1026) brecho
Of uncertain derivation; a noose -- snare.

column7: a biting, a gnashing of teeth
column9: From  (G1031) brucho; a grating (of the teeth) -- gnashing. see GREEK  (G1031) brucho
A primary verb; to grate the teeth (in pain or rage) -- gnash.

column7: to be full to bursting, to gush with
column9: A primary verb; to swell out, i.e. (by implication) to gush -- send forth.
From the base of  (G977) bibrosko; food (literally or figuratively), especially (ceremonially) articles allowed or forbidden by the Jewish law -- meat, victuals. see GREEK  (G977) bibrosko
From  (G1035) brosis; eatable -- meat. see GREEK  (G1035) brosis
From the base of  (G977) bibrosko; (abstractly) eating (literally or figuratively); by extension (concretely) food (literally or figuratively) -- eating, food, meat. see GREEK  (G977) bibrosko

column7: to sink, to cause to sink
column9: From  (G1037) buthos; to sink; by implication, to drown -- begin to sink, drown. see GREEK  (G1037) buthos
A variation of  (G899) bathos; depth, i.e. (by implication) the sea -- deep. see GREEK  (G899) bathos
From bursa (a hide); a tanner -- tanner.
From  (G1040) bussos; made of linen (neuter a linen cloth) -- fine linen. see GREEK  (G1040) bussos

column7: byssus (a species of flax), also (the) linen (made from it)
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H948) buwts); white linen -- fine linen. see HEBREW  (H948) buwts
From the base of  (G939) basis; properly, a stand, i.e. (specially) an altar -- altar. see GREEK  (G939) basis
Of Chaldee origin (compare  (H1355) gab); the knoll; gabbatha, a vernacular term for the Roman tribunal in Jerusalem -- Gabbatha. see HEBREW  (H1355) gab
Of Hebrew origin ( (H1403) Gabriy'el); Gabriel, an archangel -- Gabriel. see HEBREW  (H1403) Gabriy'el
From graino (to gnaw); an ulcer ("gangrene") -- canker.
Of Hebrew origin ( (H1410) Gad); Gad, a tribe of Israelites -- Gad. see HEBREW  (H1410) Gad
From Gadara (a town east of the Jordan); a Gadarene or inhabitant of Gadara -- Gadarene.
Of foreign origin; a treasure -- treasure.
Of Hebrew origin ( (H5804) Azzah); Gazah (i.e. Azzah), a place in Palestine -- Gaza. see HEBREW  (H5804) Azzah
From  (G1047) gaza and  (G5438) phulake; a treasure-house, i.e. A court in the temple for the collection-boxes -- treasury. see GREEK  (G1047) gaza see GREEK  (G5438) phulake

column7: Gaius, the name of several Christian
column9: Of Latin origin; Gaius (i.e. Caius), a Christian -- Gaius.
Of uncertain affinity; milk (figuratively) -- milk.
From  (G1053) Galatia; a Galatian or inhabitant of Galatia -- Galatian. see GREEK  (G1053) Galatia

column7: Galatia, a district in Asia Minor or a larger Roman province including this district as well as others
column9: Of foreign origin; Galatia, a region of Asia -- Galatia.
From  (G1053) Galatia; Galatic or relating to Galatia -- of Galatia. see GREEK  (G1053) Galatia
Of uncertain derivation; tranquillity -- calm.

column7: Galilee, the northern region of Palestine, also the name of a sea
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H1551) Galiyl); Galiloea (i.e. The heathen circle), a region of Palestine -- Galilee. see HEBREW  (H1551) Galiyl
From  (G1056) Galilaia; Galilean or belonging to Galilea -- Galilean, of Galilee. see GREEK  (G1056) Galilaia
Of Latin origin; Gallion (i.e. Gallio), a Roman officer -- Gallio.

column7: Gamaliel, a renowned teacher of the law
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H1583) Gamliy'el); Gamaliel (i.e. Gamliel), an Israelite -- Gamaliel. see HEBREW  (H1583) Gamliy'el
From  (G1062) gamos; to wed (of either sex) -- marry (a wife). see GREEK  (G1062) gamos
From  (G1062) gamos; to espouse (a daughter to a husband) -- give in marriage. see GREEK  (G1062) gamos
Of uncertain affinity; nuptials -- marriage, wedding.

column7: for, indeed (a conjunction used to express cause, explanation, inference or continuation)
column9: A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason (used in argument, explanation or intensification; often with other particles) -- and, as, because (that), but, even, for, indeed, no doubt, seeing, then, therefore, verily, what, why, yet.
Of uncertain derivation; the stomach; by analogy, the matrix; figuratively, a gourmand -- belly, + with child, womb.

column7: emphasizes the word to which it is joined
column9: A primary particle of emphasis or qualification (often used with other particles prefixed) -- and besides, doubtless, at least, yet.
Of Hebrew origin ( (H1439) Gid'own); Gedeon (i.e. Gid(e)on), an Israelite -- Gedeon (in the King James Version). see HEBREW  (H1439) Gid'own

column7: Gehenna, a valley west and South of Jerusalem, also a symbolic name for the final place of punishment of the ungodly
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H1516) gay' and  (H2011) Hinnom); valley of (the son of) Hinnom; ge-henna (or Ge-Hinnom), a valley of Jerusalem, used (figuratively) as a name for the place (or state) of everlasting punishment -- hell. see HEBREW  (H1516) gay' see HEBREW  (H2011) Hinnom

column7: Gethsemane, an olive orchard on the Mount of Olives
column9: Of Chaldee origin (compare  (H1660) gath and  (H8081) shemen); oil-press; Gethsemane, a garden near Jerusalem -- Gethsemane. see HEBREW  (H1660) gath see HEBREW  (H8081) shemen
From  (G1093) ge; a neighbour (as adjoining one's ground); by implication, a friend -- neighbour. see GREEK  (G1093) ge
Of uncertain affinity; to laugh (as a sign of joy or satisfaction) -- laugh.
From  (G1070) gelao; laughter (as a mark of gratification) -- laughter. see GREEK  (G1070) gelao
Transitive from  (G1073) gemo; to fill entirely -- fill (be) full. see GREEK  (G1073) gemo
A primary verb; to swell out, i.e. Be full -- be full.
From (a presumed derivative of)  (G1085) genos; a generation; by implication, an age (the period or the persons) -- age, generation, nation, time. see GREEK  (G1085) genos
From  (G1074) genea and  (G3056) logos; to reckon by generations, i.e. Trace in genealogy -- count by descent. see GREEK  (G1074) genea see GREEK  (G3056) logos

column7: the making of a pedigree, a genealogy
column9: From the same as  (G1075) genealogeo; tracing by generations, i.e. "genealogy" -- genealogy. see GREEK  (G1075) genealogeo
Neuter plural of a derivative of  (G1078) genesis; birthday ceremonies -- birthday. see GREEK  (G1078) genesis
From the same as  (G1074) genea; nativity; figuratively, nature -- generation, nature(-ral). see GREEK  (G1074) genea
Feminine of a presumed derivative of the base of  (G1074) genea; birth -- birth. see GREEK  (G1074) genea

From a variation of  (G1085) genos; to procreate (properly, of the father, but by extension of the mother); figuratively, to regenerate -- bear, beget, be born, bring forth, conceive, be delivered of, gender, make, spring. see GREEK  (G1085) genos
From  (G1080) gennao; offspring; by analogy, produce (literally or figuratively) -- fruit, generation. see GREEK  (G1080) gennao

column7: Gennesaret, a fertile plain on west shore of the Sea of Galilee
column9: Of Hebrew origin (compare  (H3672) Kinnrowth); Gennesaret (i.e. Kinnereth), a lake and plain in Palestine -- Gennesaret. see HEBREW  (H3672) Kinnrowth
From  (G1080) gennao; nativity -- birth. see GREEK  (G1080) gennao
From  (G1080) gennao; born -- they that are born. see GREEK  (G1080) gennao

From  (G1096) ginomai; "kin" (abstract or concrete, literal or figurative, individual or collective) -- born, country(-man), diversity, generation, kind(-red), nation, offspring, stock. see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai

column7: Gerasene, of Gerasa, a city East of the Jordan
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H1622) Girgashiy); a Gergesene (i.e. Girgashite) or one of the aborigines of Palestine -- Gergesene. see HEBREW  (H1622) Girgashiy
From  (G1088) geron; the eldership, i.e. (collectively) the Jewish Sanhedrin -- senate. see GREEK  (G1088) geron
Of uncertain affinity (compare  (G1094) geras); aged -- old. see GREEK  (G1094) geras
A primary verb; to taste; by implication, to eat; figuratively, to experience (good or ill) -- eat, taste.
From  (G1092) georgos; to till (the soil) -- dress. see GREEK  (G1092) georgos
Neuter of a (presumed) derivative of  (G1092) georgos; cultivable, i.e. A farm -- husbandry. see GREEK  (G1092) georgos
From  (G1093) ge and the base of  (G2041) ergon; a land-worker, i.e. Farmer -- husbandman. see GREEK  (G1093) ge see GREEK  (G2041) ergon

Contracted from a primary word; soil; by extension a region, or the solid part or the whole of the terrene globe (including the occupants in each application) -- country, earth(-ly), ground, land, world.
Akin to  (G1088) geron; senility -- old age. see GREEK  (G1088) geron
From  (G1094) geras; to be senescent -- be (wax) old. see GREEK  (G1094) geras

column7: to come into being, to happen, to become
column9: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be ("gen"-erate), i.e. (reflexively) to become (come into being), used with great latitude (literal, figurative, intensive, etc.) -- arise, be assembled, be(-come, -fall, -have self), be brought (to pass), (be) come (to pass), continue, be divided, draw, be ended, fall, be finished, follow, be found, be fulfilled, + God forbid, grow, happen, have, be kept, be made, be married, be ordained to be, partake, pass, be performed, be published, require, seem, be showed, X soon as it was, sound, be taken, be turned, use, wax, will, would, be wrought.

column7: to come to know, recognize, perceive
column9: A prolonged form of a primary verb; to "know" (absolutely) in a great variety of applications and with many implications (as follow, with others not thus clearly expressed) -- allow, be aware (of), feel, (have) know(-ledge), perceived, be resolved, can speak, be sure, understand.
Akin to  (G1099) glukus; sweet wine, i.e. (properly) must (fresh juice), but used of the more saccharine (and therefore highly inebriating) fermented wine -- new wine. see GREEK  (G1099) glukus
Of uncertain affinity; sweet (i.e. Not bitter nor salt) -- sweet, fresh.
Of uncertain affinity; the tongue; by implication, a language (specially, one naturally unacquired) -- tongue.

From  (G1100) glossa and the base of  (G2889) kosmos; properly, a case (to keep mouthpieces of wind-instruments in) i.e. (by extension) a casket or (specially) purse -- bag. see GREEK  (G1100) glossa see GREEK  (G2889) kosmos
By variation for a derivative from knapto (to tease cloth); a cloth-dresser -- fuller.
From the same as  (G1077) genesia; legitimate (of birth), i.e. Genuine -- own, sincerity, true. see GREEK  (G1077) genesia
Adverb from  (G1103) gnesios; genuinely, i.e. Really -- naturally. see GREEK  (G1103) gnesios
Akin to  (G3509) nephos; gloom (as of a storm) -- blackness. see GREEK  (G3509) nephos
From  (G1097) ginosko; cognition, i.e. (subjectively) opinion, or (objectively) resolve (counsel, consent, etc.) -- advice, + agree, judgment, mind, purpose, will. see GREEK  (G1097) ginosko

column7: to come to know, to make known
column9: From a derivative of  (G1097) ginosko; to make known; subjectively, to know -- certify, declare, make known, give to understand, do to wit, wot. see GREEK  (G1097) ginosko
From  (G1097) ginosko; knowing (the act), i.e. (by implication) knowledge -- knowledge, science. see GREEK  (G1097) ginosko
From  (G1097) ginosko; a knower -- expert. see GREEK  (G1097) ginosko
From  (G1097) ginosko; well-known -- acquaintance, (which may be) known, notable. see GREEK  (G1097) ginosko
Of uncertain derivation; to grumble -- murmur.
From  (G1111) gogguzo; a grumbling -- grudging, murmuring. see GREEK  (G1111) gogguzo
From  (G1111) gogguzo; a grumbler -- murmurer. see GREEK  (G1111) gogguzo

column7: a wailer, a sorcerer, a swindler
column9: From goao (to wail); properly, a wizard (as muttering spells), i.e. (by implication) an imposter -- seducer.
Of Chaldee origin (compare  (H1538) gulgoleth); the skull; Golgotha, a knoll near Jerusalem -- Golgotha. see HEBREW  (H1538) gulgoleth

column7: Gomorrah, one of the cities near the Dead Sea
column9: Of Hebrew origin ( (H6017) Amorah); Gomorrha (i.e. Amorah), a place near the Dead Sea -- Gomorrha. see HEBREW  (H6017) Amorah
From  (G1073) gemo; a load (as filling), i.e. (specially) a cargo, or (by extension) wares -- burden, merchandise. see GREEK  (G1073) gemo
From the base of  (G1096) ginomai; a parent -- parent. see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai
Of uncertain affinity; the "knee" -- knee(X -l).
From a compound of  (G1119) gonu and the alternate of  (G4098) pipto; to fall on the knee -- bow the knee, kneel down. see GREEK  (G1119) gonu see GREEK  (G4098) pipto

column7: that which is drawn or written, a letter
column9: From  (G1125) grapho; a writing, i.e. A letter, note, epistle, book, etc.; plural learning -- bill, learning, letter, scripture, writing, written. see GREEK  (G1125) grapho
From  (G1121) gramma. A writer, i.e. (professionally) scribe or secretary -- scribe, town-clerk. see GREEK  (G1121) gramma
From  (G1125) grapho; inscribed (figuratively) -- written. see GREEK  (G1125) grapho
A document, i.e. Holy Writ (or its contents or a statement in it) -- scripture.
A primary verb; to "grave", especially to write; figuratively, to describe -- describe, write(-ing, -ten).
From graus (an old woman) and  (G1491) eidos; crone-like, i.e. Silly -- old wives'. see GREEK  (G1491) eidos
From  (G1453) egeiro; to keep awake, i.e. Watch (literally or figuratively) -- be vigilant, wake, (be) watch(-ful). see GREEK  (G1453) egeiro
From  (G1131) gumnos; to practise naked (in the games), i.e. Train (figuratively) -- exercise. see GREEK  (G1131) gumnos
From  (G1128) gumnazo; training, i.e. (figuratively) asceticism -- exercise. see GREEK  (G1128) gumnazo

column7: to be naked or poorly clothed
column9: From a derivative of  (G1131) gumnos; to strip, i.e. (reflexively) go poorly clad -- be naked. see GREEK  (G1131) gumnos
Of uncertain affinity; nude (absolute or relative, literal or figurative) -- naked.
From  (G1131) gumnos; nudity (absolute or comparative) -- nakedness. see GREEK  (G1131) gumnos

column7: a little woman, (contemptuously) a silly woman
column9: A diminutive from  (G1135) gune; a little (i.e. Foolish) woman -- silly woman. see GREEK  (G1135) gune
From  (G1135) gune; feminine -- wife. see GREEK  (G1135) gune
Probably from the base of  (G1096) ginomai; a woman; specially, a wife -- wife, woman. see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai
Of Hebrew origin ( (H1463) Gowg); Gog, a symbolic name for some future Antichrist -- Gog. see HEBREW  (H1463) Gowg
Probably akin to  (G1119) gonu; an angle -- corner, quarter. see GREEK  (G1119) gonu
Of Hebrew origin ( (H1732) David); Dabid (i.e. David), the Israelite king -- David. see HEBREW  (H1732) David

column7: to be possessed by a demon
column9: Middle voice from  (G1142) daimon; to be exercised by a d?Mon -- have a (be vexed with, be possessed with) devil(-s). see GREEK  (G1142) daimon
Neuter of a derivative of  (G1142) daimon; a d?Monic being; by extension a deity -- devil, god. see GREEK  (G1142) daimon
From  (G1140) daimonion and  (G1142) daimon; d?Mon-like -- devilish. see GREEK  (G1140) daimonion see GREEK  (G1142) daimon
From daio (to distribute fortunes); a d?Mon or supernatural spirit (of a bad nature) -- devil.
A prolonged form of a primary root; to bite, i.e. (figuratively) thwart -- bite.
Or dakruon dak'-roo-on; of uncertain affinity; a tear -- tear.
From  (G1144) dakru; to shed tears -- weep. Compare  (G2799) klaio. see GREEK  (G1144) dakru see GREEK  (G2799) klaio
From  (G1147) daktulos; a finger-ring -- ring. see GREEK  (G1147) daktulos
Probably from  (G1176) deka; a finger -- finger. see GREEK  (G1176) deka

column7: Dalmanutha, an unidentified place near the Sea of Galilee
column9: Probably of Chaldee origin; Dalmanutha, a place in Palestine -- Dalmanutha.

column7: Dalmatia, southern Illyricum on the Adriatic Sea
column9: Probably of foreign derivation; Dalmatia, a region of Europe -- Dalmatia.
A variation of an obsolete primary of the same meaning; to tame -- tame.
Probably from the base of  (G1150) damazo; a heifer (as tame) -- heifer. see GREEK  (G1150) damazo
Probably from the base of  (G1150) damazo; perhaps gentle; Damaris, an Athenian woman -- Damaris. see GREEK  (G1150) damazo
From  (G1154) Damaskos; a Damascene or inhabitant of Damascus -- Damascene. see GREEK  (G1154) Damaskos
Of Hebrew origin ( (H1834) Dammeseq); Damascus, a city of Syria -- Damascus. see HEBREW  (H1834) Dammeseq
From  (G1156) daneion; to loan on interest; reflexively, to borrow -- borrow, lend. see GREEK  (G1156) daneion
From danos (a gift); probably akin to the base of  (G1325) didomi; a loan -- debt. see GREEK  (G1325) didomi
From  (G1155) daneizo; a lender -- creditor. see GREEK  (G1155) daneizo
Of Hebrew origin ( (H1840) Daniye'l); Daniel, an Israelite -- Daniel. see HEBREW  (H1840) Daniye'l
From  (G1160) dapane; to expend, i.e. (in a good sense) to incur cost, or (in a bad one) to waste -- be at charges, consume, spend. see GREEK  (G1160) dapane
From dapto (to devour); expense (as consuming) -- cost.

column7: but, and, now, (a connective or adversative particle)
column9: A primary particle (adversative or continuative); but, and, etc. -- also, and, but, moreover, now (often unexpressed in English).
From  (G1189) deomai; a petition -- prayer, request, supplication. see GREEK  (G1189) deomai

3d person singular active present of  (G1210) deo; also deon deh-on'; neuter active participle of the same; both used impersonally; it is (was, etc.) Necessary (as binding) -- behoved, be meet, must (needs), (be) need(-ful), ought, should. see GREEK  (G1210) deo
From the base of  (G1166) deiknuo; a specimen (as shown) -- example. see GREEK  (G1166) deiknuo

column7: to expose, make a show of
column9: From  (G1164) deigma; to exhibit -- make a shew. see GREEK  (G1164) deigma
A prolonged form of an obsolete primary of the same meaning; to show (literally or figuratively) -- shew.
From  (G1169) deilos; timidity -- fear. see GREEK  (G1169) deilos
From  (G1167) deilia; to be timid -- be afraid. see GREEK  (G1167) deilia
From deos (dread); timid, i.e. (by implication) faithless -- fearful.
Probably from the same as  (G1171) deinos (through the idea of forgetting the name as fearful, i.e. Strange); so and so (when the person is not specified) -- such a man. see GREEK  (G1171) deinos
Adverb from a derivative of the same as  (G1169) deilos; terribly, i.e. Excessively -- grievously, vehemently. see GREEK  (G1169) deilos
From  (G1173) deipnon; to dine, i.e. Take the principle (or evening) meal -- sup (X -er). see GREEK  (G1173) deipnon
From the same as  (G1160) dapane; dinner, i.e. The chief meal (usually in the evening) -- feast, supper. see GREEK  (G1160) dapane

column7: very fearful of gods, religious, superstitious
column9: The compound of a derivative of the base of  (G1169) deilos and  (G1142) daimon; more religious than others -- too superstitious. see GREEK  (G1169) deilos see GREEK  (G1142) daimon
From the same as  (G1174) deisidaimonesteros; religion -- superstition. see GREEK  (G1174) deisidaimonesteros
A primary number; ten -- (eight-)een, ten.
From  (G1176) deka and  (G1417) duo; two and ten, i.e. Twelve -- twelve. see GREEK  (G1176) deka see GREEK  (G1417) duo
From  (G1176) deka and  (G4002) pente; ten and five, i.e. Fifteen -- fifteen. see GREEK  (G1176) deka see GREEK  (G4002) pente

column7: Decapolis, a region East of the Jordan
column9: From  (G1176) deka and  (G4172) polis; the ten-city region; the Decapolis, a district in Syria -- Decapolis. see GREEK  (G1176) deka see GREEK  (G4172) polis
From  (G1176) deka and  (G5064) tessares; ten and four, i.e. Fourteen -- fourteen. see GREEK  (G1176) deka see GREEK  (G5064) tessares
Feminine of  (G1182) dekatos; a tenth, i.e. As a percentage or (technically) tithe -- tenth (part), tithe. see GREEK  (G1182) dekatos
Ordinal from  (G1176) deka; tenth -- tenth. see GREEK  (G1176) deka
From  (G1181) dekate; to tithe, i.e. To give or take a tenth -- pay (receive) tithes. see GREEK  (G1181) dekate
From  (G1209) dechomai; approved; (figuratively) propitious -- accepted(-table). see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
From the base of  (G1388) dolos; to entrap, i.e. (figuratively) delude -- allure, beguile, entice. see GREEK  (G1388) dolos
Probably from drus (an oak); a tree -- tree.
From  (G1188) dexios and  (G2983) lambano; a guardsman (as if taking the right) or light-armed soldier -- spearman. see GREEK  (G1188) dexios see GREEK  (G2983) lambano
From  (G1209) dechomai; the right side or (feminine) hand (as that which usually takes) -- right (hand, side). see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
Middle voice of  (G1210) deo; to beg (as binding oneself), i.e. Petition -- beseech, pray (to), make request. Compare  (G4441) punthanomai. see GREEK  (G1210) deo see GREEK  (G4441) punthanomai
From  (G1191) Derbe; a Derb?An or inhabitant of Derbe -- of Derbe. see GREEK  (G1191) Derbe
Of foreign origin; Derbe, a place in Asia Minor -- Derbe.
From  (G1194) dero; a hide -- skin. see GREEK  (G1194) dero
From  (G1192) derma; made of hide -- leathern, of a skin. see GREEK  (G1192) derma
A primary verb; properly, to flay, i.e. (by implication) to scourge, or (by analogy) to thrash -- beat, smite.
From a (presumed) derivative of  (G1196) desmeo; to be a binder (captor), i.e. To enchain (a prisoner), to tie on (a load) -- bind. see GREEK  (G1196) desmeo
From  (G1199) desmon; to tie, i.e. Shackle -- bind. see GREEK  (G1199) desmon
From  (G1196) desmeo; a bundle -- bundle. see GREEK  (G1196) desmeo
From  (G1199) desmon; a captive (as bound) -- in bonds, prisoner. see GREEK  (G1199) desmon

Or desmos des-mos' neuter and masculine respectively from  (G1210) deo; a band, i.e. Ligament (of the body) or shackle (of a prisoner); figuratively, an impediment or disability -- band, bond, chain, string. see GREEK  (G1210) deo
From  (G1199) desmon and  (G5441) phulax; a jailer (as guarding the prisoners) -- jailor, keeper of the prison. see GREEK  (G1199) desmon see GREEK  (G5441) phulax
From a derivative of  (G1199) desmon (equivalent to  (G1196) desmeo); a place of bondage, i.e. A dungeon -- prison. see GREEK  (G1199) desmon see GREEK  (G1196) desmeo
From the same as  (G1201) desmoterion; (passively) a captive -- prisoner. see GREEK  (G1201) desmoterion
Perhaps from  (G1210) deo and posis (a husband); an absolute ruler ("despot") -- Lord, master. see GREEK  (G1210) deo
Of uncertain affinity; here; used also imperative hither!; and of time, hitherto -- come (hither), hither(-to).
From  (G1204) deuro and an imperative form of eimi (to go); come hither! -- come, X follow. see GREEK  (G1204) deuro
From  (G1208) deuteros; secondary, i.e. (specially) on the second day -- next day. see GREEK  (G1208) deuteros

column4: AdjectivePhonetic Spelling: (dyoo-ter-op\'-ro-tos)Definition: second, after the firstUsage: second-first, a word of uncertain meaning.Thayer\'s Greek LexiconSTRONGS NT 1207: \xce\xb4\xce\xb5\xcf\x85\xcf\x84\xce\xb5\xcf\x81\xcf\x8c\xcf\x80\xcf\x81\xcf\x89\xcf\x84\xce\xbf\xcf\x82\xce\xb4\xce\xb5\xcf\x85\xcf\x84\xce\xb5\xcf\x81\xcf\x8c\xcf\x80\xcf\x81\xcf\x89\xcf\x84\xce\xbf\xcf\x82, \xce\xb4\xce\xb5\xcf\x85\xcf\x84\xce\xb5\xcf\x81\xcf\x8c\xcf\x80\xcf\x81\xcf\x89\xcf\x84\xce\xbf\xce\xbd, second-first (cf. \xce\xb4\xce\xb5\xcf\x85\xcf\x84\xce\xb5\xcf\x81\xce\xb5\xcf\x83\xcf\x87\xce\xb1\xcf\x84\xce\xbf\xcf\x82 second-last, last but one): \xe1\xbc\x90\xce\xbd \xcf\x83\xce\xb1\xce\xb2\xce\xb2\xce\xac\xcf\x84\xe1\xbf\xb3 \xce\xb4\xce\xb5\xcf\x85\xcf\x84\xce\xb5\xcf\x81\xce\xbf\xcf\x80\xcf\x81\xcf\x8e\xcf\x84\xe1\xbf\xb3 in Luke 6:1 seems to be, the second of the first sabbaths after the feast of the Passover; cf. Redslob in the Intelligenzblatt zur Hall. Lit. Zeit. 1847, N. 70; Ewald, Jahrbb. d. Biblical Wissensch. i., p. 72; (WH\'s Appendix, at the passage). The various opinions of others are reviewed by Meyer (and McClellan) at the passage and L\xc3\xbcbkert in the Studien und Kritiken for 1835, p. 664ff (Eustrat. in vita Eutych. n. 95 calls the first Sunday after Easter \xce\xb4\xce\xb5\xcf\x85\xcf\x84\xce\xb5\xcf\x81\xce\xbf\xcf\x80\xcf\x81\xcf\x89\xcf\x84\xce\xb7\xce\xbd \xce\xba\xcf\x85\xcf\x81\xce\xb9\xce\xb1\xce\xba\xce\xb7\xce\xbd). (But the genuineness of the word is questionable. It is lacking in \xd7\x90 B L 1, 33, 69 and some other authorities. Hence, Tr text WH omit the word; L Tr marginal reading brackets it. Tischendorf, after expunging it in his 2nd edition, restored it in his 7th edition, subsequently put it in brackets, and finally (8th edition) inserted it again. It is questioned or discarded, by Meyer, Bleek, Alford, Weiss (on Mark, p. 101), Holtz., Hilgenf., Volkm., Farrar (commentary at the passage and Life of Christ 1:435), others. For the evidence see Tdf.s note, and for discussions of it see WHs Appendix at the passage; Scrivener, Introduction, p. 515f; Green, Developed Criticism at the passage.)   Strong\'s Exhaustive Concordancesecond, after the first. From deuteros and protos; second-first, i.e. (specially) a designation of the Sabbath immediately after the Paschal week (being the second after Passover day, and the first of the seven Sabbaths intervening before Pentecost) -- second... After the first. see GREEK deuteros see GREEK protos g,1208,δεύτερος
column9: (dyoo'-ter-os)
column12: As the compare of  (G1417) duo; (ordinal) second (in time, place, or rank; also adverb) -- afterward, again, second(-arily, time). see GREEK  (G1417) duo

column9: Middle voice of a primary verb; to receive (in various applications, literally or figuratively) -- accept, receive, take. Compare  (G2983) lambano. see GREEK  (G2983) lambano

column8: bind, be in bonds, knit, tie, wind.
column9: A primary verb; to bind (in various applications, literally or figuratively) -- bind, be in bonds, knit, tie, wind. See also  (G1163) dei,  (G1189) deomai. see GREEK  (G1163) dei see GREEK  (G1189) deomai

column7: indeed, now (used to give emphasis or urgency to a statement)
column9: Probably akin to  (G1161) de; a particle of emphasis or explicitness; now, then, etc. -- also, and, doubtless, now, therefore. see GREEK  (G1161) de
Of uncertain derivation; clear -- + bewray, certain, evident, manifest.
From  (G1212) delos; to make plain (by words) -- declare, shew, signify. see GREEK  (G1212) delos
Probably for  (G1216) Demetrios; Demas, a Christian -- Demas. see GREEK  (G1216) Demetrios
From a compound of  (G1218) demos and  (G58) agora; to be a people-gatherer, i.e. To address a public assembly -- make an oration. see GREEK  (G1218) demos see GREEK  (G58) agora

column7: Demetrius, the name of a silversmith and of a Christian
column9: From Demeter (Ceres); Demetrius, the name of an Ephesian and of a Christian -- Demetrius.
From  (G1218) demos and  (G2041) ergon; a worker for the people, i.e. Mechanic (spoken of the Creator) -- maker. see GREEK  (G1218) demos see GREEK  (G2041) ergon

column7: a district or country, the common people, the people assembled
column9: From  (G1210) deo; the public (as bound together socially) -- people. see GREEK  (G1210) deo
From  (G1218) demos; public; (feminine singular dative case as adverb) in public -- common, openly, publickly. see GREEK  (G1218) demos
Of Latin origin; a denarius (or ten asses) -- pence, penny(-worth).
From  (G1211) de and  (G4218) pote; a particle of generalization; indeed, at any time -- (what-)soever. see GREEK  (G1211) de see GREEK  (G4218) pote
From  (G1211) de and  (G4225) pou; a particle of asseveration; indeed doubtless -- verily. see GREEK  (G1211) de see GREEK  (G4225) pou

column7: through, on account of, because of
column9: A primary preposition denoting the channel of an act; through (in very wide applications, local, causal, or occasional) -- after, always, among, at, to avoid, because of (that), briefly, by, for (cause)... Fore, from, in, by occasion of, of, by reason of, for sake, that, thereby, therefore, X though, through(-out), to, wherefore, with (-in). In composition it retains the same general importance.
From  (G1223) dia and the base of  (G939) basis; to cross -- come over, pass (through). see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G939) basis

column7: to bring charges (usually with hostile intent)
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G906) ballo; (figuratively) to traduce -- accuse. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G906) ballo
Middle voice of a compound of  (G1223) dia and  (G950) bebaioo; to confirm thoroughly (by words), i.e. Asseverate -- affirm constantly. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G950) bebaioo

column7: to look through, to see clearly
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G991) blepo; to look through, i.e. Recover full vision -- see clearly. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G991) blepo
From  (G1225) diaballo; a traducer; specially, Satan (compare  (H7854) satan) -- false accuser, devil, slanderer. see GREEK  (G1225) diaballo see HEBREW  (H7854) satan
From  (G1223) dia and the base of  (G32) aggelos; to herald thoroughly -- declare, preach, signify. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G32) aggelos
From  (G1223) dia and  (G1096) ginomai; to elapse meanwhile -- X after, be past, be spent. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai
From  (G1223) dia and  (G1097) ginosko; to know thoroughly, i.e. Ascertain exactly -- (would) enquire, know the uttermost. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G1097) ginosko
From  (G1123) graptos and  (G1107) gnorizo; to tell abroad -- make known. see GREEK  (G1123) graptos see GREEK  (G1107) gnorizo
From  (G1231) diaginosko; (magisterial) examination ("diagnosis") -- hearing. see GREEK  (G1231) diaginosko
From  (G1223) dia and  (G1111) gogguzo; to complain throughout a crowd -- murmur. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G1111) gogguzo

column7: to keep awake, to be fully awake
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G1127) gregoreuo; to waken thoroughly -- be awake. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G1127) gregoreuo
From  (G1223) dia and  (G71) ago; to pass time or life -- lead life, living. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G71) ago
From  (G1223) dia and  (G1209) dechomai; to receive in turn, i.e. (figuratively) succeed to -- come after. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
From a compound of  (G1223) dia and  (G1210) deo; a "diadem" (as bound about the head) -- crown. Compare  (G4735) stephanos. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G1210) deo see GREEK  (G4735) stephanos

From  (G1223) dia and  (G1325) didomi; to give throughout a crowd, i.e. Deal out; also to deliver over (as to a successor) -- (make) distribute(-ion), divide, give. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G1325) didomi
From  (G1237) diadechomai; a successor in office -- room. see GREEK  (G1237) diadechomai
From  (G1223) dia and  (G2224) zonnumi; to gird tightly -- gird. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2224) zonnumi
From  (G1303) diatithemai; properly, a disposition, i.e. (specially) a contract (especially a devisory will) -- covenant, testament. see GREEK  (G1303) diatithemai
From  (G1244) diaireo; a distinction or (concretely) variety -- difference, diversity. see GREEK  (G1244) diaireo
From  (G1223) dia and  (G138) haireomai; to separate, i.e. Distribute -- divide. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G138) haireomai
From  (G1223) dia and  (G2511) katharizo; to cleanse perfectly, i.e. (specially) winnow -- thoroughly purge. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2511) katharizo

Middle voice from  (G1223) dia and a compound of  (G2596) kata and  (G1651) elegcho; to prove downright, i.e. Confute -- convince. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2596) kata see GREEK  (G1651) elegcho

column8: administer, serve, use the office of a deacon.
column9: From  (G1249) diakonos; to be an attendant, i.e. Wait upon (menially or as a host, friend, or (figuratively) teacher); technically, to act as a Christian deacon -- (ad-)minister (unto), serve, use the office of a deacon. see GREEK  (G1249) diakonos

From  (G1249) diakonos; attendance (as a servant, etc.); figuratively (eleemosynary) aid, (official) service (especially of the Christian teacher, or technically of the diaconate) -- (ad-)minister(-ing, -tration, -try), office, relief, service(-ing). see GREEK  (G1249) diakonos

Probably from an obsolete diako (to run on errands; compare  (G1377) dioko); an attendant, i.e. (genitive case) a waiter (at table or in other menial duties); specially, a Christian teacher and pastor (technically, a deacon or deaconess) -- deacon, minister, servant. see GREEK  (G1377) dioko
From  (G1364) dis and  (G1540) hekaton; two hundred -- two hundred. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G1540) hekaton
Middle voice from  (G1223) dia and  (G191) akouo; to hear throughout, i.e. Patiently listen (to a prisoner's plea) -- hear. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G191) akouo

column8: contend, discern, doubt, judge, be partial.
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G2919) krino; to separate thoroughly, i.e. (literally and reflexively) to withdraw from, or (by implication) oppose; figuratively, to discriminate (by implication, decide), or (reflexively) hesitate -- contend, make (to) differ(-ence), discern, doubt, judge, be partial, stagger, waver. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2919) krino
From  (G1252) diakrino; judicial estimation -- discern(-ing), disputation. see GREEK  (G1252) diakrino
From  (G1223) dia and  (G2967) koluo; to hinder altogether, i.e. Utterly prohibit -- forbid. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2967) koluo
From  (G1223) dia and  (G2980) laleo; to talk throughout a company, i.e. Converse or (genitive case) publish -- commune, noise abroad. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2980) laleo

column7: to discuss, to address, to preach
column9: Middle voice from  (G1223) dia and  (G3004) lego; to say thoroughly, i.e. Discuss (in argument or exhortation) -- dispute, preach (unto), reason (with), speak. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3004) lego
From  (G1223) dia and  (G3007) leipo; to leave off in the middle, i.e. Intermit -- cease. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3007) leipo
From  (G1256) dialegomai; a (mode of) discourse, i.e. "dialect" -- language, tongue. see GREEK  (G1256) dialegomai
From  (G1223) dia and  (G236) allasso; to change thoroughly, i.e. (mentally) to conciliate -- reconcile. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G236) allasso

From  (G1223) dia and  (G3049) logizomai; to reckon thoroughly, i.e. (genitive case) to deliberate (by reflection or discussion) -- cast in mind, consider, dispute, muse, reason, think. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3049) logizomai

From  (G1260) dialogizomai; discussion, i.e. (internal) consideration (by implication, purpose), or (external) debate -- dispute, doubtful(-ing), imagination, reasoning, thought. see GREEK  (G1260) dialogizomai
From  (G1223) dia and  (G3089) luo; to dissolve utterly -- scatter. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3089) luo
From  (G1223) dia and  (G3140) martureo; to attest or protest earnestly, or (by implication) hortatively -- charge, testify (unto), witness. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3140) martureo
From  (G1223) dia and  (G3164) machomai; to fight fiercely (in altercation) -- strive. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3164) machomai
From  (G1223) dia and  (G3306) meno; to stay constantly (in being or relation) -- continue, remain. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3306) meno
From  (G1223) dia and  (G3307) merizo; to partition thoroughly (literally in distribution, figuratively in dissension) -- cloven, divide, part. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3307) merizo
From  (G1266) diamerizo; disunion (of opinion and conduct) -- division. see GREEK  (G1266) diamerizo
From  (G1223) dia and the base of  (G3551) nomos; to distribute, i.e. (of information) to disseminate -- spread. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3551) nomos

column7: to wink at, nod to, beckon to
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G3506) neuo; to nod (or express by signs) across an intervening space -- beckon. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3506) neuo
From a compound of  (G1223) dia and  (G3539) noieo; something thought through, i.e. A sentiment -- thought. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3539) noieo

From  (G1223) dia and  (G3563) nous; deep thought, properly, the faculty (mind or its disposition), by implication, its exercise -- imagination, mind, understanding. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3563) nous
From  (G1223) dia and  (G455) anoigo; to open thoroughly, literally (as a first-born) or figuratively (to expound) -- open. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G455) anoigo
From  (G1223) dia and a derivative of  (G3571) nux; to sit up the whole night -- continue all night. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3571) nux
From  (G1223) dia and anuo (to effect); to accomplish thoroughly -- finish. see GREEK  (G1223) dia
From  (G1223) dia and the genitive case of  (G3956) pas; through all time, i.e. (adverbially) constantly -- alway(-s), continually. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3956) pas
From  (G1223) dia and a derivative of the base of  (G4008) peran; to cross entirely -- go over, pass (over), sail over. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4008) peran
From  (G1223) dia and  (G4126) pleo; to sail through -- sail over. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4126) pleo

column7: to toil through, to be worn out or annoyed
column9: From  (G1223) dia and a derivative of  (G4192) ponos; to toil through, i.e. (passively) be worried -- be grieved. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4192) ponos

column8: go through, journey in, pass by.
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G4198) poreuomai; to travel through -- go through, journey in, pass by. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4198) poreuomai

column7: to be greatly perplexed or at a loss
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G639) aporeo; to be thoroughly nonplussed -- (be in) doubt, be (much) perplexed. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G639) aporeo

column7: to examine thoroughly, to gain by trading
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G4231) pragmateuomai; to thoroughly occupy oneself, i.e. (transitively and by implication) to earn in business -- gain by trading. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4231) pragmateuomai

column7: to saw asunder, cut to the heart
column9: From  (G1223) dia and the base of  (G4249) prizo; to saw asunder, i.e. (figuratively) to exasperate -- cut (to the heart). see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4249) prizo
From  (G1223) dia and  (G726) harpazo; to seize asunder, i.e. Plunder -- spoil. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G726) harpazo
From  (G1223) dia and  (G4486) rhegnumi; to tear asunder -- break, rend. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4486) rhegnumi
From  (G1223) dia and saphes (clear); to clear thoroughly, i.e. (figuratively) declare -- tell unto. see GREEK  (G1223) dia
From  (G1223) dia and  (G4579) seio; to shake thoroughly, i.e. (figuratively) to intimidate -- do violence to. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4579) seio

column7: generally to separate, to winnow, to squander
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G4650) skorpizo; to dissipate, i.e. (genitive case) to rout or separate; specially, to winnow; figuratively, to squander -- disperse, scatter (abroad), strew, waste. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4650) skorpizo
From  (G1223) dia and  (G4685) spao; to draw apart, i.e. Sever or dismember -- pluck asunder, pull in pieces. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4685) spao

column7: to sow throughout, disperse (in foreign lands)
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G4687) speiro; to sow throughout, i.e. (figuratively) distribute in foreign lands -- scatter abroad. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4687) speiro
From  (G1289) diaspeiro; dispersion, i.e. (specially and concretely) the (converted) Israelite resident in Gentile countries -- (which are) scattered (abroad). see GREEK  (G1289) diaspeiro

column7: to set apart, to distinguish, to charge expressly
column9: Middle voice from  (G1223) dia and  (G4724) stello; to set (oneself) apart (figuratively, distinguish), i.e. (by implication) to enjoin -- charge, that which was (give) commanded(-ment). see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4724) stello
From  (G1339) diistemi; an interval -- space. see GREEK  (G1339) diistemi
From  (G1291) diastellomai; a variation -- difference, distinction. see GREEK  (G1291) diastellomai
From  (G1223) dia and  (G4762) strepho; to distort, i.e. (figuratively) misinterpret, or (morally) corrupt -- perverse(-rt), turn away. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4762) strepho

column7: to bring safely through (a danger), to save thoroughly
column8: escape safely, heal, make perfectly whole, save.
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G4982) sozo; to save thoroughly, i.e. (by implication or analogy) to cure, preserve, rescue, etc. -- bring safe, escape (safe), heal, make perfectly whole, save. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G4982) sozo
From  (G1299) diatasso; arrangement, i.e. Institution -- instrumentality. see GREEK  (G1299) diatasso
From  (G1299) diatasso; an arrangement, i.e. (authoritative) edict -- commandment. see GREEK  (G1299) diatasso
From  (G1223) dia and  (G5015) tarasso; to disturb wholly, i.e. Agitate (with alarm) -- trouble. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5015) tarasso

column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G5021) tasso; to arrange thoroughly, i.e. (specially) institute, prescribe, etc. -- appoint, command, give, (set in) order, ordain. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5021) tasso
From  (G1223) dia and  (G5055) teleo; to accomplish thoroughly, i.e. (subjectively) to persist -- continue. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5055) teleo

From  (G1223) dia and  (G5083) tereo; to watch thoroughly, i.e. (positively and transitively) to observe strictly, or (negatively and reflexively) to avoid wholly -- keep. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5083) tereo
From  (G1223) dia and  (G5101) tis; through what cause ?, i.e. Why? -- wherefore, why. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5101) tis

column7: to place separately, dispose of by a will
column9: Middle voice from  (G1223) dia and  (G5087) tithemi; to put apart, i.e. (figuratively) dispose (by assignment, compact, or bequest) -- appoint, make, testator. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi

column7: to rub hard, rub away, to spend time
column9: From  (G1223) dia and the base of  (G5147) tribos; to wear through (time), i.e. Remain -- abide, be, continue, tarry. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5147) tribos
From a compound of  (G1223) dia and  (G5142) trepho; nourishment -- food. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5142) trepho
From  (G1223) dia and  (G826) augazo; to glimmer through, i.e. Break (as day) -- dawn. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G826) augazo
From  (G1223) dia and  (G5316) phaino; appearing through, i.e. "diaphanous" -- transparent. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5316) phaino

column7: to carry through, carry about, to differ, make a difference, surpass
column8: be better, differ from, make matter, publish
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G5342) phero; to bear through, i.e. (literally) transport; usually to bear apart, i.e. (objectively) to toss about (figuratively, report); subjectively, to "differ", or (by implication) surpass -- be better, carry, differ from, drive up and down, be (more) excellent, make matter, publish, be of more value. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5342) phero
From  (G1223) dia and  (G5343) pheugo; to flee through, i.e. Escape -- escape. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5343) pheugo
From  (G1223) dia and a derivative of  (G5345) pheme; to report thoroughly, i.e. Divulgate -- blaze abroad, commonly report, spread abroad, fame. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5345) pheme

column7: to destroy utterly, to spoil, corrupt
column9: From  (G1225) diaballo and  (G5351) phtheiro; to rot thoroughly, i.e. (by implication) to ruin (passively, decay utterly, figuratively, pervert) -- corrupt, destroy, perish. see GREEK  (G1225) diaballo see GREEK  (G5351) phtheiro
From  (G1311) diaphtheiro; decay -- corruption. see GREEK  (G1311) diaphtheiro
From  (G1308) diaphero; varying; also surpassing -- differing, divers, more excellent. see GREEK  (G1308) diaphero
From  (G1223) dia and  (G5442) phulasso; to guard thoroughly, i.e. Protect -- keep. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5442) phulasso

column7: to have in hand, thus to lay hands on (violently)
column9: From  (G1223) dia and a derivative of  (G5495) cheir; to handle thoroughly, i.e. Lay violent hands upon -- kill, slay. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5495) cheir
From  (G1223) dia and the middle voice of  (G5563) chorizo; to remove (oneself) wholly, i.e. Retire -- depart. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5563) chorizo
From  (G1318) didaktos; instructive ("didactic") -- apt to teach. see GREEK  (G1318) didaktos
From  (G1321) didasko; (subjectively) instructed, or (objectively) communicated by teaching -- taught, which... Teacheth. see GREEK  (G1321) didasko
From  (G1320) didaskalos; instruction (the function or the information) -- doctrine, learning, teaching. see GREEK  (G1320) didaskalos
From  (G1321) didasko; an instructor (genitive case or specially) -- doctor, master, teacher. see GREEK  (G1321) didasko
A prolonged (causative) form of a primary verb dao (to learn); to teach (in the same broad application) -- teach.
From  (G1321) didasko; instruction (the act or the matter) -- doctrine, hath been taught. see GREEK  (G1321) didasko
From  (G1364) dis and  (G1406) drachme; a double drachma (didrachm) -- tribute. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G1406) drachme
Prolongation from  (G1364) dis; double, i.e. Twin; Didymus, a Christian -- Didymus. see GREEK  (G1364) dis

A prolonged form of a primary verb (which is used as an alternative in most of the tenses); to give (used in a very wide application, properly, or by implication, literally or figuratively; greatly modified by the connection) -- adventure, bestow, bring forth, commit, deliver (up), give, grant, hinder, make, minister, number, offer, have power, put, receive, set, shew, smite (+ with the hand), strike (+ with the palm of the hand), suffer, take, utter, yield.
From  (G1223) dia and  (G1453) egeiro; to wake fully; i.e. Arouse (literally or figuratively) -- arise, awake, raise, stir up. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G1453) egeiro
From  (G1223) dia and  (G1841) exodos; an outlet through, i.e. Probably an open square (from which roads diverge) -- highway. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G1841) exodos
From  (G1329) diermeneuo; an explainer -- interpreter. see GREEK  (G1329) diermeneuo

column7: to explain thoroughly, by implication to translate
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G2059) hermeneuo; to explain thoroughly, by implication, to translate -- expound, interpret(-ation). see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2059) hermeneuo

column7: to go through, go about, to spread

column8: to ask about, learn by inquiry
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G2065) erotao; to question throughout, i.e. Ascertain by interrogation -- make enquiry foreign see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2065) erotao

column7: lasting two years, two years old
column9: From  (G1364) dis and  (G2094) etos; of two years (in age) -- two years old. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G2094) etos
From  (G1332) dietes; a space of two years (biennium) -- two years. see GREEK  (G1332) dietes
From  (G1223) dia and  (G2233) hegeomai; to relate fully -- declare, shew, tell. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2233) hegeomai
From  (G1334) diegeomai; a recital -- declaration. see GREEK  (G1334) diegeomai

Neuter of a compound of  (G1223) dia and a derivative of an alternate of  (G5342) phero; carried through, i.e. (adverbially with  (G1519) eis and  (G3588) ho prefixed) perpetually -- + continually, for ever. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G5342) phero see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G3588) ho

column7: divided into two seas, dividing the sea (as a reef)
column9: From  (G1364) dis and  (G2281) thalassa; having two seas, i.e. A sound with a double outlet -- where two seas meet. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G2281) thalassa
From  (G1223) dia and the base of  (G2425) hikanos; to reach through, i.e. Penetrate -- pierce. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2425) hikanos

column7: to set apart, to intervene, make an interval
column9: From  (G1223) dia and  (G2476) histemi; to stand apart, i.e. (reflexively) to remove, intervene -- go further, be parted, after the space of. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2476) histemi
From  (G1223) dia and a derivative of  (G2478) ischuros; to stout it through, i.e. Asservate -- confidently (constantly) affirm. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G2478) ischuros
From  (G1342) dikaios and  (G2920) krisis; a just sentence -- righteous judgment. see GREEK  (G1342) dikaios see GREEK  (G2920) krisis
From  (G1349) dike; equitable (in character or act); by implication, innocent, holy (absolutely or relatively) -- just, meet, right(-eous). see GREEK  (G1349) dike
From  (G1342) dikaios; equity (of character or act); specially (Christian) justification -- righteousness. see GREEK  (G1342) dikaios

column9: From  (G1342) dikaios; to render (i.e. Show or regard as) just or innocent -- free, justify(-ier), be righteous. see GREEK  (G1342) dikaios

Adverb from  (G1342) dikaios; equitably -- justly, (to) righteously(-ness). see GREEK  (G1342) dikaios

column7: the act of pronouncing righteous, acquittal
column9: From  (G1344) dikaioo; aquittal (for Christ's sake) -- justification. see GREEK  (G1344) dikaioo
From a derivative of  (G1349) dike; a judger -- judge. see GREEK  (G1349) dike

column7: right (as self-evident), justice (the principle, a decision or its execution)
column9: Probably from  (G1166) deiknuo; right (as self-evident), i.e. Justice (the principle, a decision, or its execution) -- judgment, punish, vengeance. see GREEK  (G1166) deiknuo
Probably from a primary verb diko (to cast); a seine (for fishing) -- net.
From  (G1364) dis and  (G3056) logos; equivocal, i.e. Telling a different story -- double-tongued. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G3056) logos
From  (G1223) dia and  (G3739) hos; through which thing, i.e. Consequently -- for which cause, therefore, wherefore. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3739) hos
From  (G1223) dia and  (G3593) hodeuo; to travel through -- go throughout, pass through. see GREEK  (G1223) dia see GREEK  (G3593) hodeuo
From Dionusos (Bacchus); reveller; Dionysius, an Athenian -- Dionysius.
From  (G1352) dio and  (G4007) per; on which very account -- wherefore. see GREEK  (G1352) dio see GREEK  (G4007) per

From  (G1364) dis and (probably) the base of  (G4119) pleion; two-fold -- double, two-fold more. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G4119) pleion
From  (G1362) diplous; to render two-fold -- double. see GREEK  (G1362) diplous

From  (G1364) dis; properly, to duplicate, i.e. (mentally) to waver (in opinion) -- doubt. see GREEK  (G1364) dis
From  (G1364) dis and  (G4750) stoma; double-edged -- with two edges, two-edged. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G4750) stoma
From  (G1364) dis and  (G5507) chilioi; two thousand -- two thousand. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G5507) chilioi
From  (G1223) dia and hulizo hoo-lid'-zo (to filter); to strain out -- strain at (probably by misprint). see GREEK  (G1223) dia

column9: From a compound of a derivative of  (G1364) dis and a derivative of temno (to cut); to bisect, i.e. (by extension) to flog severely -- cut asunder (in sunder). see GREEK  (G1364) dis
From a variation of  (G1373) dipsos; to thirst for (literally or figuratively) -- (be, be a-)thirst(-y). see GREEK  (G1373) dipsos
Of uncertain affinity; thirst -- thirst.
From  (G1364) dis and  (G5590) psuche; two-spirited, i.e. Vacillating (in opinion or purpose) -- double minded. see GREEK  (G1364) dis see GREEK  (G5590) psuche
From  (G1377) dioko; persecution -- persecution. see GREEK  (G1377) dioko
From  (G1377) dioko; a persecutor -- persecutor. see GREEK  (G1377) dioko

column9: From  (G1378) dogma; to prescribe by statute, i.e. (reflexively) to submit to, ceremonially rule -- be subject to ordinances. see GREEK  (G1378) dogma

column8: be of reputation, seem good, suppose, think.

column9: From  (G1384) dokimos; to test (literally or figuratively); by implication, to approve -- allow, discern, examine, X like, (ap-)prove, try. see GREEK  (G1384) dokimos

From  (G1380) dokeo; properly, acceptable (current after assayal), i.e. Approved -- approved, tried. see GREEK  (G1380) dokeo
From  (G1209) dechomai (through the idea of holding up); a stick of timber -- beam. see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
From  (G1388) dolos; guileful -- deceitful. see GREEK  (G1388) dolos
From  (G1386) dolios; to be guileful -- use deceit. see GREEK  (G1386) dolios

From  (G1388) dolos; to ensnare, i.e. (figuratively) adulterate -- handle deceitfully. see GREEK  (G1388) dolos
From the base of  (G1325) didomi; a present -- gift. see GREEK  (G1325) didomi

column9: From  (G1391) doxa; to render (or esteem) glorious (in a wide application) -- (make) glorify(-ious), full of (have) glory, honour, magnify. see GREEK  (G1391) doxa

column9: Gazelle; Dorcas, a Christian woman -- Dorcas.

column7: the act of giving, a gift
column9: From the base of  (G1325) didomi; a giving; by implication, (concretely) a gift -- gift, giving. see GREEK  (G1325) didomi
From the base of  (G1325) didomi; a giver -- giver. see GREEK  (G1325) didomi
From a presumed compound of  (G1401) doulos and  (G71) ago; to be a slave-driver, i.e. To enslave (figuratively, subdue) -- bring into subjection. see GREEK  (G1401) doulos see GREEK  (G71) ago
From  (G1398) douleuo; slavery (ceremonially or figuratively) -- bondage. see GREEK  (G1398) douleuo

column7: to be a slave, to serve

Feminine of  (G1401) doulos; a female slave (involuntarily or voluntarily) -- handmaid(-en). see GREEK  (G1401) doulos
Neuter of  (G1401) doulos; subservient -- servant. see GREEK  (G1401) doulos
From  (G1210) deo; a slave (literal or figurative, involuntary or voluntary; frequently, therefore in a qualified sense of subjection or subserviency) -- bond(-man), servant. see GREEK  (G1210) deo

column8: bring into bondage, become a servant.
column9: From  (G1401) doulos; to enslave (literally or figuratively) -- bring into (be under) bondage, X given, become (make) servant. see GREEK  (G1401) doulos
From  (G1209) dechomai; a reception, i.e. Convivial entertainment -- feast. see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
Probably from an alternate form of derkomai (to look); a fabulous kind of serpent (perhaps as supposed to fascinate) -- dragon.
Perhaps akin to the base of  (G1404) drakon (through the idea of capturing); to grasp, i.e. (figuratively) entrap -- take. see GREEK  (G1404) drakon

column9: From  (G1405) drassomai; a drachma or (silver) coin (as handled) -- piece (of silver). see GREEK  (G1405) drassomai
From drepo (to pluck); a gathering hook (especially for harvesting) -- sickle.
From the alternate of  (G5143) trecho; a race, i.e. (figuratively) career -- course. see GREEK  (G5143) trecho

column7: Drusilla, a member of the Herodian family
column9: A feminine diminutive of Drusus (a Roman name); Drusilla, a member of the Herodian family -- Drusilla.

column7: to be able, to have power
column9: Of uncertain affinity; to be able or possible -- be able, can (do, + -not), could, may, might, be possible, be of power.

From  (G1410) dunamai; force (literally or figuratively); specially, miraculous power (usually by implication, a miracle itself) -- ability, abundance, meaning, might(-ily, -y, -y deed), (worker of) miracle(-s), power, strength, violence, mighty (wonderful) work. see GREEK  (G1410) dunamai
From  (G1411) dunamis; to enable -- strengthen. see GREEK  (G1411) dunamis
From  (G1410) dunamai; a ruler or officer -- of great authority, mighty, potentate. see GREEK  (G1410) dunamai
From  (G1415) dunatos; to be efficient (figuratively) -- be mighty. see GREEK  (G1415) dunatos
From  (G1410) dunamai; powerful or capable (literally or figuratively); neuter possible -- able, could, (that is) mighty (man), possible, power, strong. see GREEK  (G1410) dunamai
Or dumi doo'-mee prolonged forms of an obsolete primary duo doo'-o (to sink) to go "down" -- set.
A primary numeral; "two" -- both, twain, two.

column7: like un- or mis- (as in unrest, misjudge), nullifies good sense or increases bad sense of a word
column9: A primary inseparable particle of uncertain derivation; used only in composition as a prefix; hard, i.e. With difficulty -- + hard, + grievous, etc.
From  (G1418) dus- and a derivative of  (G941) bastazo; oppressive -- grievous to be borne. see GREEK  (G1418) dus- see GREEK  (G941) bastazo
From  (G1418) dus- and a comparative of  (G1787) entos (meaning a bowel); a "dysentery" -- bloody flux. see GREEK  (G1418) dus- see GREEK  (G1787) entos
From  (G1418) dus- and a presumed derivative of  (G2059) hermeneuo; difficult of explanation -- hard to be uttered. see GREEK  (G1418) dus- see GREEK  (G2059) hermeneuo
From  (G1418) dus- and kolon (food); properly, fastidious about eating (peevish), i.e. (genitive case) impracticable -- hard. see GREEK  (G1418) dus-
Adverb from  (G1422) duskolos; impracticably -- hardly. see GREEK  (G1422) duskolos

column7: a setting (as of the sun), by implication (the) western (region)
column9: From  (G1416) duno; the sun-set, i.e. (by implication) the western region -- west. see GREEK  (G1416) duno
From  (G1418) dus- and a derivative of  (G3539) noieo; difficult of perception -- hard to be understood. see GREEK  (G1418) dus- see GREEK  (G3539) noieo

column9: From a compound of  (G1418) dus- and  (G5345) pheme; defamation -- evil report. see GREEK  (G1418) dus- see GREEK  (G5345) pheme
From  (G1417) duo and  (G1176) deka; two and ten, i.e. A dozen -- twelve. see GREEK  (G1417) duo see GREEK  (G1176) deka
From  (G1427) dodeka; twelfth -- twelfth. see GREEK  (G1427) dodeka
From  (G1427) dodeka and  (G5443) phule; the commonwealth of Israel -- twelve tribes. see GREEK  (G1427) dodeka see GREEK  (G5443) phule
From demo (to build); properly, an edifice, i.e. (specially) a roof -- housetop.
From  (G1435) doron; a gratuity -- gift. see GREEK  (G1435) doron

column7: as a gift, to no purpose
column8: without a cause, freely, for naught, in vain.
column9: Accusative case of  (G1431) dorea as adverb; gratuitously (literally or figuratively) -- without a cause, freely, for naught, in vain. see GREEK  (G1431) dorea
Middle voice from  (G1435) doron; to bestow gratuitously -- give. see GREEK  (G1435) doron
From  (G1433) doreomai; a bestowment -- gift. see GREEK  (G1433) doreomai
A present; specially, a sacrifice -- gift, offering.

column7: ah! ha! (interjection expressing surprise, indignation, fear)
column9: Apparent imperative of  (G1439) eao; properly, let it be, i.e. (as interjection) aha! -- let alone. see GREEK  (G1439) eao

From  (G1487) ei and  (G302) an; a conditional particle; in case that, provided, etc.; often used in connection with other particles to denote indefiniteness or uncertainty -- before, but, except, (and) if, (if) so, (what-, whither-)soever, though, when (-soever), whether (or), to whom, (who-)so(-ever). See  (G3361) me. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G302) an see GREEK  (G3361) me

From a reflexive pronoun otherwise obsolete and the genitive case (dative case or accusative case) of  (G846) autos; him- (her-, it-, them-, also (in conjunction with the personal pronoun of the other persons) my-, thy-, our-, your-) self (selves), etc. -- alone, her (own, -self), (he) himself, his (own), itself, one (to) another, our (thine) own(-selves), + that she had, their (own, own selves), (of) them(-selves), they, thyself, you, your (own, own conceits, own selves, -selves). see GREEK  (G846) autos
Of uncertain affinity; to let be, i.e. Permit or leave alone -- commit, leave, let (alone), suffer. See also  (G1436) ea. see GREEK  (G1436) ea
From  (G1442) hebdomos and a modified form of  (G1176) deka; seventy -- seventy, three score and ten. see GREEK  (G1442) hebdomos see GREEK  (G1176) deka
Multiple adverb from  (G1440) hebdomekonta; seventy times -- seventy times. see GREEK  (G1440) hebdomekonta
Ordinal from  (G2033) hepta; seventh -- seventh. see GREEK  (G2033) hepta
Of Hebrew origin ( (H5677) Eber); Eber, a patriarch -- Eber. see HEBREW  (H5677) Eber
From  (G1443) Eber; Hebraic or the Jewish language -- Hebrew. see GREEK  (G1443) Eber
From  (G1443) Eber; a Hebr?An (i.e. Hebrew) or Jew -- Hebrew. see GREEK  (G1443) Eber

column7: Hebrew, the Aramaic vernacular of Pal
column9: From  (G1443) Eber; the Hebraistic (Hebrew) or Jewish (Chaldee) language -- Hebrew. see GREEK  (G1443) Eber
Adverb from  (G1446) Hebrais; Hebraistically or in the Jewish (Chaldee) language -- in (the) Hebrew (tongue). see GREEK  (G1446) Hebrais

column7: to make near, to come near
column8: approach, be at hand, draw near.
column9: From  (G1451) eggus; to make near, i.e. (reflexively) approach -- approach, be at hand, come (draw) near, be (come, draw) nigh. see GREEK  (G1451) eggus

column7: to inscribe, to enter in a register
column9: From  (G1722) en and  (G1125) grapho; to "engrave", i.e. Inscribe -- write (in). see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G1125) grapho
From  (G1722) en and guion (a limb); pledged (as if articulated by a member), i.e. A bondsman -- surety. see GREEK  (G1722) en

From a primary verb agcho (to squeeze or throttle; akin to the base of  (G43) agkale); near (literally or figuratively, of place or time) -- from, at hand, near, nigh (at hand, unto), ready. see GREEK  (G43) agkale
Neuter of the comparative of  (G1451) eggus; nearer -- nearer. see GREEK  (G1451) eggus

Probably akin to the base of  (G58) agora (through the idea of collecting one's faculties); to waken (transitively or intransitively), i.e. Rouse (literally, from sleep, from sitting or lying, from disease, from death; or figuratively, from obscurity, inactivity, ruins, nonexistence) -- awake, lift (up), raise (again, up), rear up, (a-)rise (again, up), stand, take up. see GREEK  (G58) agora
From  (G1453) egeiro; a resurgence (from death) -- resurrection. see GREEK  (G1453) egeiro

column7: hired to lie in wait, lying in wait
column9: From  (G1722) en and a derivative of  (G2524) kathiemi; subinduced, i.e. Surreptitiously suborned as a lier-in-wait -- spy. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2524) kathiemi

Neuter plural of a presumed compound from  (G1722) en and  (G2537) kainos; innovatives, i.e. (specially) renewal (of religious services after the Antiochian interruption) -- dedication. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2537) kainos
From  (G1456) egkainia; to renew, i.e. Inaugurate -- consecrate, dedicate. see GREEK  (G1456) egkainia

column7: to call in (as a debt or demand), bring to account
column8: accuse, call in question, lay to the charge.
column9: From  (G1722) en and  (G2564) kaleo; to call in (as a debt or demand), i.e. Bring to account (charge, criminate, etc.) -- accuse, call in question, implead, lay to the charge. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2564) kaleo

column7: to leave behind, (in a good sense) let remain over or (in a bad sense) desert
column9: From  (G1722) en and  (G2641) kataleipo; to leave behind in some place, i.e. (in a good sense) let remain over, or (in a bad sense) to desert -- forsake, leave. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2641) kataleipo

column7: to settle down in (a place), reside
column9: From  (G1722) en and  (G2730) katoikeo; to settle down in a place, i.e. Reside -- dwell among. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2730) katoikeo

column7: to take pride in, glory in
column9: From  (G1722) en and a derivative of  (G2759) kentron; to prick in, i.e. Ingraft -- graff in(-to). see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2759) kentron
From  (G1458) egkaleo; an accusation, i.e. Offence alleged -- crime laid against, laid to charge. see GREEK  (G1458) egkaleo

column7: to put on oneself (as a garment)
column9: Middle voice from  (G1722) en and komboo (to gird); to engirdle oneself (for labor), i.e. Figuratively (the apron as being a badge of servitude) to wear (in token of mutual deference) -- be clothed with. see GREEK  (G1722) en
From  (G1465) egkopto; a hindrance -- X hinder. see GREEK  (G1465) egkopto
From  (G1722) en and  (G2875) kopto; to cut into, i.e. (figuratively) impede, detain -- hinder, be tedious unto. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2875) kopto
From  (G1468) egkrates; self-control (especially continence) -- temperance. see GREEK  (G1468) egkrates
Middle voice from  (G1468) egkrates; to exercise self-restraint (in diet and chastity) -- can(-not) contain, be temperate. see GREEK  (G1468) egkrates

From  (G1722) en and  (G2904) kratos; strong in a thing (masterful), i.e. (figuratively and reflexively) self-controlled (in appetite, etc.) -- temperate. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2904) kratos

column7: to judge in, to reckon among
column9: From  (G1722) en and  (G2919) krino; to judge in, i.e. Count among -- make of the number. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2919) krino
From  (G1722) en and  (G2928) krupto; to conceal in, i.e. Incorporate with -- hid in. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2928) krupto
From  (G1722) en and the base of  (G2949) kuma; swelling inside, i.e. Pregnant -- great with child. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G2949) kuma
From  (G1722) en and  (G5548) chrio; to rub in (oil), i.e. Besmear -- anoint. see GREEK  (G1722) en see GREEK  (G5548) chrio

A primary pronoun of the first person I (only expressed when emphatic) -- I, me. For the other cases and the plural see  (G1691) eme,  (G1698) emoi,  (G1700) emou,  (G2248) hemas,  (G2249) hemeis,  (G2254) hemin,  (G2257) hemon, etc. see GREEK  (G1691) eme see GREEK  (G1698) emoi see GREEK  (G1700) emou see GREEK  (G2248) hemas see GREEK  (G2249) hemeis see GREEK  (G2254) hemin see GREEK  (G2257) hemon

column8: lay even with the ground, raze
column9: From  (G1475) edaphos; to raze -- lay even with the ground. see GREEK  (G1475) edaphos
From the base of  (G1476) hedraios; a basis (bottom), i.e. The soil -- ground. see GREEK  (G1476) hedraios
From a derivative of hezomai (to sit); sedentary, i.e. (by implication) immovable -- settled, stedfast.
From a derivative of  (G1476) hedraios; a support, i.e. (figuratively) basis -- ground. see GREEK  (G1476) hedraios
Of Hebrew origin ( (H2396) Chizqiyah); Ezekias (i.e. Hezekeiah), an Israelite -- Ezekias. see HEBREW  (H2396) Chizqiyah
From  (G2309) ethelo and  (G2356) threskeia; voluntary (arbitrary and unwarranted) piety, i.e. Sanctimony -- will worship. see GREEK  (G2309) ethelo see GREEK  (G2356) threskeia
From  (G1485) ethos; to accustom, i.e. (neuter passive participle) customary -- custom. see GREEK  (G1485) ethos

column7: an ethnarch, a governor (not king) of a province
column9: From  (G1484) ethnos and  (G746) arche; the governor (not king) of a district -- ethnarch. see GREEK  (G1484) ethnos see GREEK  (G746) arche
From  (G1484) ethnos; national ("ethnic"), i.e. (specially) a Gentile -- heathen (man). see GREEK  (G1484) ethnos
Adverb from  (G1482) ethnikos; as a Gentile -- after the manner of Gentiles. see GREEK  (G1482) ethnikos

column7: a race, a nation, the nations (as distinct from Israel)
column9: Probably from  (G1486) etho; a race (as of the same habit), i.e. A tribe; specially, a foreign (non-Jewish) one (usually, by implication, pagan) -- Gentile, heathen, nation, people. see GREEK  (G1486) etho

column7: custom, a usage (prescribed by habit or law)
column9: From  (G1486) etho; a usage (prescribed by habit or law) -- custom, manner, be wont. see GREEK  (G1486) etho
A primary verb; to be used (by habit or conventionality); neuter perfect participle usage -- be custom (manner, wont).

A primary particle of conditionality; if, whether, that, etc. -- forasmuch as, if, that, (al-)though, whether. Often used in connection or composition with other particles, especially as in  (G1489) eige,  (G1490) ei de me(ge),  (G1499) ei kai,  (G1508) ei me,  (G1509) ei me ti,  (G1512) ei per,  (G1513) ei pos,  (G1536) ei tis,  (G1537) ek. See also  (G1437) ean. see GREEK  (G1489) eige see GREEK  (G1490) ei de me(ge) see GREEK  (G1499) ei kai see GREEK  (G1508) ei me see GREEK  (G1509) ei me ti see GREEK  (G1512) ei per see GREEK  (G1513) ei pos
Second person singular present of  (G1510) eimi; thou art -- art, be. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi

column7: if indeed, seeing that, unless, with negative otherwise
column9: From  (G1487) ei and  (G1065) ge; if indeed, seeing that, unless, (with negative) otherwise -- if (so be that, yet). see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G1065) ge

From  (G1487) ei,  (G1161) de, and  (G3361) me (sometimes with  (G1065) ge added); but if not -- (or) else, if (not, otherwise), otherwise. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G1161) de see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G1065) ge
From  (G1492) eido; a view, i.e. Form (literally or figuratively) -- appearance, fashion, shape, sight. see GREEK  (G1492) eido

A primary verb; used only in certain past tenses, the others being borrowed from the equivalent  (G3700) optanomai and  (G3708) horao; properly, to see (literally or figuratively); by implication, (in the perfect tense only) to know -- be aware, behold, X can (+ not tell), consider, (have) know(-ledge), look (on), perceive, see, be sure, tell, understand, wish, wot. Compare  (G3700) optanomai. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai see GREEK  (G3708) horao see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
Neuter of a presumed derivative of  (G1497) eidolon; an image-fane -- idol's temple. see GREEK  (G1497) eidolon

column8: meat offered in sacrifice unto idols.
column9: Neuter of a compound of  (G1497) eidolon and a presumed derivative of  (G2380) thuo; an image-sacrifice, i.e. Part of an idolatrous offering -- (meat, thing that is) offered (in sacrifice, sacrificed) to (unto) idols. see GREEK  (G1497) eidolon see GREEK  (G2380) thuo
From  (G1497) eidolon and  (G2999) latreia; image-worship (literally or figuratively) -- idolatry. see GREEK  (G1497) eidolon see GREEK  (G2999) latreia
From  (G1497) eidolon and the base of  (G3000) latreuo; an image- (servant or) worshipper (literally or figuratively) -- idolater. see GREEK  (G1497) eidolon see GREEK  (G3000) latreuo

column7: an image (for worship), by implication a false god
column9: From  (G1491) eidos; an image (i.e. For worship); by implication, a heathen god, or (plural) the worship of such -- idol. see GREEK  (G1491) eidos
Optative (i.e. English subjunctive) present of  (G1510) eimi (including the other person); might (could, would, or should) be -- mean, + perish, should be, was, were. see GREEK  (G1510) eimi
From  (G1487) ei and  (G2532) kai; if also (or even) -- if (that), though. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G2532) kai
Probably from  (G1502) eiko (through the idea of failure); idly, i.e. Without reason (or effect) -- without a cause, (in) vain(-ly). see GREEK  (G1502) eiko
Of uncertain affinity; a score -- twenty.
Apparently a primary verb; properly, to be weak, i.e. Yield -- give place.
Apparently a primary verb (perhaps akin to  (G1502) eiko through the idea of faintness as a copy); to resemble -- be like. see GREEK  (G1502) eiko
From  (G1503) eiko; a likeness, i.e. (literally) statue, profile, or (figuratively) representation, resemblance -- image. see GREEK  (G1503) eiko
From  (G1506) eilikrines; clearness, i.e. (by implication) purity (figuratively) -- sincerity. see GREEK  (G1506) eilikrines
From heile (the sun's ray) and  (G2919) krino; judged by sunlight, i.e. Tested as genuine (figuratively) -- pure, sincere. see GREEK  (G2919) krino
A prolonged form of a primary but defective verb heilo (of the same meaning); to coil or wrap -- roll together. See also  (G1667) helisso. see GREEK  (G1667) helisso

column8: but, except that, if not, save only.
column9: From  (G1487) ei and  (G3361) me; if not -- but, except (that), if not, more than, save (only) that, saving, till. see GREEK  (G1487) ei see GREEK  (G3361) me
From  (G1508) ei me and the neuter of  (G5100) tis; if not somewhat -- except. see GREEK  (G1508) ei me see GREEK  (G5100) tis

column8: am, have been, it is I, was.
