column9: From a compound of the base of  (G3357) metrios and  (G3806) pathos; to be moderate in passion, i.e. Gentle (to treat indulgently) -- have compassion. see GREEK  (G3357) metrios see GREEK  (G3806) pathos
Adverb from a derivative of  (G3358) metron; moderately, i.e. Slightly -- a little. see GREEK  (G3358) metron
An apparently primary word; a measure ("metre"), literally or figuratively; by implication, a limited portion (degree) -- measure.
From  (G3326) meta and ops (the face); the forehead (as opposite the countenance) -- forehead. see GREEK  (G3326) meta

Or mechris (mekh-ris'); from  (G3372) mekos; as far as, i.e. Up to a certain point (as a preposition, of extent (denoting the terminus, whereas  (G891) achri refers especially to the space of time or place intervening) or conjunction) -- till, (un-)to, until. see GREEK  (G3372) mekos see GREEK  (G891) achri

column7: not, that...not, lest (used for qualified negation)
column9: A primary particle of qualified negation (whereas  (G3756) ou expresses an absolute denial); (adverb) not, (conjunction) lest; also (as an interrogative implying a negative answer (whereas  (G3756) ou expects an affirmative one)) whether -- any but (that), X forbear, + God forbid, + lack, lest, neither, never, no (X wise in), none, nor, (can-)not, nothing, that not, un(-taken), without. Often used in compounds in substantially the same relations. See also  (G3362) ean me,  (G3363) hina me,  (G3364) ou me,  (G3372) mekos,  (G3373) mekuno,  (G3375) men,  (G3378) me ouk. see GREEK  (G3756) ou see GREEK  (G3362) ean me see GREEK  (G3363) hina me see GREEK  (G3364) ou me see GREEK  (G3372) mekos see GREEK  (G3373) mekuno see GREEK  (G3375) men see GREEK  (G3378) me ouk
I.e.  (G1437) ean and  (G3361) me; if not, i.e. Unless -- X before, but, except, if, no, (if, + whosoever) not. see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G1437) ean
I.e.  (G2443) hina and  (G3361) me; in order (or so) that not -- albeit not, lest, that, no(-t, (-thing)). see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G2443) hina

I.e.  (G3756) ou and  (G3361) me; a double negative strengthening the denial; not at all -- any more, at all, by any (no) means, neither, never, no (at all), in no case (wise), nor ever, not (at all, in any wise). Compare  (G3378) me ouk. see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G3378) me ouk see GREEK  (G3756) ou
Adverb from a compound of  (G3361) me and amos (somebody); by no means -- not so. see GREEK  (G3361) me
From  (G3361) me and  (G1161) de; but not, not even; in a continued negation, nor -- neither, nor (yet), (no) not (once, so much as). see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G1161) de

Including the irregular feminine medemia may-dem-ee'-ah, and the neuter meden (may-den') from  (G3361) me and  (G1520) heis; not even one (man, woman, thing) -- any (man, thing), no (man), none, not (at all, any man, a whit), nothing, + without delay. see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G1520) heis
From  (G3366) mede and  (G4218) pote; not even ever -- never. see GREEK  (G3366) mede see GREEK  (G4218) pote
From  (G3366) mede and  (G4452) po; not even yet -- not yet. see GREEK  (G3366) mede see GREEK  (G4452) po

column7: a Mede, Median, an inhabitant of Media
column9: Of foreign origin (compare  (H4074) Maday); a Median, or inhabitant of Media -- Mede. see HEBREW  (H4074) Maday
From  (G3361) me and  (G2089) eti; no further -- any longer, (not) henceforth, hereafter, no henceforward (longer, more, soon), not any more. see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G2089) eti
Probably akin to  (G3173) megas; length (literally or figuratively) length. see GREEK  (G3173) megas
From  (G3372) mekos; to lengthen, i.e. (middle voice) to enlarge -- grow up. see GREEK  (G3372) mekos
From melon (a sheep); a sheep-skin -- sheepskin.
A stronger form of  (G3303) men; a particle of affirmation (only with  (G2229) e); assuredly -- + surely. see GREEK  (G3303) men see GREEK  (G2229) e
A primary word; a month -- month.

Probably from the same base as  (G3145) massaomai and  (G3415) mnaomai (i.e. Mao, to strive); to disclose (through the idea of mental effort and thus calling to mind), i.e. Report, declare, intimate -- shew, tell. see GREEK  (G3145) massaomai see GREEK  (G3415) mnaomai

I.e.  (G3361) me and  (G3756) ou; as interrogative and negative, is it not that? -- neither (followed by no), + never, not. Compare  (G3364) ou me. see GREEK  (G3756) ou see GREEK  (G3364) ou me see GREEK  (G3361) me

Or me pote (may pot'-eh) from  (G3361) me and  (G4218) pote; not ever; also if (or lest) ever (or perhaps) -- if peradventure, lest (at any time, haply), not at all, whether or not. see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G4218) pote
From  (G3361) me and  (G4452) po; not yet -- not yet. see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G4452) po
Or me pos (may poce) from  (G3361) me and  (G4458) pos; lest somehow -- lest (by any means, by some means, haply, perhaps). see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G4458) pos
Perhaps a primary word; a thigh -- thigh.
From  (G3361) me and  (G5037) te; not too, i.e. (in continued negation) neither or nor; also, not even -- neither, (n-)or, so as much. see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G5037) te
Apparently a primary word; a "mother" (literally or figuratively, immediate or remote) -- mother.

column7: can this be? (interrogative particle expecting a negative answer)
column9: From  (G3361) me and the neuter of  (G5100) tis; whether at all -- not (the particle usually not expressed, except by the form of the question). see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G5100) tis

column7: let alone, much less, much more
column9: From  (G3385) meti and  (G1065) ge; not at all then, i.e. Not to say (the rather still) -- how much more. see GREEK  (G3385) meti see GREEK  (G1065) ge
Or me tis (may tis) from  (G3361) me and  (G5100) tis; whether any -- any (sometimes unexpressed except by the simple interrogative form of the sentence). see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G5100) tis
From  (G3384) meter; the matrix -- womb. see GREEK  (G3384) meter
From  (G3384) meter and the base of  (G257) halon; a mother-thresher, i.e. Matricide -- murderer of mothers. see GREEK  (G3384) meter see GREEK  (G257) halon
From  (G3384) meter and  (G4172) polis; a mother city, i.e. "metropolis" -- chiefest city. see GREEK  (G3384) meter see GREEK  (G4172) polis
Irregular feminine of  (G1520) heis; one or first -- a (certain), + agree, first, one, X other. see GREEK  (G1520) heis
Perhaps a primary verb; to sully or taint, i.e. Contaminate (ceremonially or morally) -- defile.
From  (G3392) miaino ("miasma"); (morally) foulness (properly, the effect) -- pollution. see GREEK  (G3392) miaino
From  (G3392) miaino; (morally) contamination (properly, the act) -- uncleanness. see GREEK  (G3392) miaino
From  (G3396) mignumi; a compound -- mixture. see GREEK  (G3396) mignumi
A primary verb; to mix -- mingle.

From  (G3565) numphe; the bridal room -- bridechamber. see GREEK  (G3565) numphe

A primary particle of present time; "now" (as adverb of date, a transition or emphasis); also as noun or adjective present or immediate -- henceforth, + hereafter, of late, soon, present, this (time). See also  (G3569) tanun,  (G3570) nuni. see GREEK  (G3569) tanun see GREEK  (G3570) nuni
Or ta nun (tah noon) from neuter plural of  (G3588) ho and  (G3568) nun; the things now, i.e. (adverbially) at present -- (but) now. see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G3568) nun
A prolonged form of  (G3568) nun for emphasis; just now -- now. see GREEK  (G3568) nun
A primary word; "night" (literally or figuratively) -- (mid-)night.
Apparently a primary word; to prick ("nudge") -- pierce.

column7: to nod in sleep, to fall asleep
column9: From a presumed derivative of  (G3506) neuo; to nod, i.e. (by implication) to fall asleep; figuratively, to delay -- slumber. see GREEK  (G3506) neuo

column7: lasting a night and a day
column9: From  (G3571) nux and  (G2250) hemera; a day-and-night, i.e. Full day of twenty-four hours -- night and day. see GREEK  (G3571) nux see GREEK  (G2250) hemera
Of Hebrew origin ( (H5146) Noach); Noe, (i.e. Noach), a patriarch -- Noe. see HEBREW  (H5146) Noach
From a derivative of  (G3541) nothos; sluggish, i.e. (literally) lazy, or (figuratively) stupid -- dull, slothful. see GREEK  (G3541) nothos
Of uncertain affinity; the back -- back.
From  (G3581) xenos; hospitality, i.e. (by implication) a place of entertainment -- lodging. see GREEK  (G3581) xenos

column7: to receive as a guest, to surprise
column9: From  (G3581) xenos; to be a host (passively, a guest); by implication, be (make, appear) strange -- entertain, lodge, (think it) strange. see GREEK  (G3581) xenos
From a compound of  (G3581) xenos and  (G1209) dechomai; to be hospitable -- lodge strangers. see GREEK  (G3581) xenos see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
Apparently a primary word; foreign (literally, alien, or figuratively, novel); by implication, a guest or (vice-versa) entertainer -- host, strange(-r).

column7: a sextarius (about a pint), a pitcher (of wood or stone)
column9: As if from xeo (properly, to smooth; by implication, (of friction) to boil or heat); a vessel (as fashioned or for cooking) (or perhaps by corruption from the Latin sextarius, the sixth of a modius, i.e. About a pint), i.e. (specially), a measure for liquids or solids, (by analogy, a pitcher) -- pot.
From  (G3584) xeros; to desiccate; by implication, to shrivel, to mature -- dry up, pine away, be ripe, wither (away). see GREEK  (G3584) xeros
From the base of  (G3582) xestes (through the idea of scorching); arid; by implication, shrunken, earth (as opposed to water) -- dry land, withered. see GREEK  (G3582) xestes
From  (G3586) xulon; wooden -- of wood. see GREEK  (G3586) xulon

From another form of the base of  (G3582) xestes; timber (as fuel or material); by implication, a stick, club or tree or other wooden article or substance -- staff, stocks, tree, wood. see GREEK  (G3582) xestes
From a derivative of the same as  (G3586) xulon (meaning a razor); to shave or "shear" the hair -- shave. see GREEK  (G3586) xulon

column8: the, this, that, one, he, she, it
column9: Including the feminine he (hay), and the neuter to (to) in all their inflections; the definite article; the (sometimes to be supplied, at others omitted, in English idiom) -- the, this, that, one, he, she, it, etc.
From  (G3590) ogdoos; ten times eight -- fourscore. see GREEK  (G3590) ogdoos
From  (G3638) oktos; the eighth -- eighth. see GREEK  (G3638) oktos
Probably from the same as  (G43) agkale; a mass (as bending or bulging by its load), i.e. Burden (hindrance) -- weight. see GREEK  (G43) agkale

Including the feminine hede (hay'-deh), and the neuter tode (tod'-e) from  (G3588) ho and  (G1161) de; the same, i.e. This or that one (plural these or those); often used as a personal pronoun -- he, she, such, these, thus. see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G1161) de
From  (G3598) hodos; to travel -- journey. see GREEK  (G3598) hodos
From  (G3595) hodegos; to show the way (literally or figuratively (teach)) -- guide, lead. see GREEK  (G3595) hodegos
From  (G3598) hodos and  (G2233) hegeomai; a conductor (literally or figuratively (teacher)) -- guide, leader. see GREEK  (G3598) hodos see GREEK  (G2233) hegeomai
From a compound of  (G3598) hodos and  (G4198) poreuomai; to be a wayfarer, i.e. Travel -- go on a journey. see GREEK  (G3598) hodos see GREEK  (G4198) poreuomai
From the same as  (G3596) hodoiporeo; travel -- journey(-ing). see GREEK  (G3596) hodoiporeo
Apparently a primary word; a road; by implication, a progress (the route, act or distance); figuratively, a mode or means -- journey, (high-)way.
Perhaps from the base of  (G2068) esthio; a "tooth" -- tooth. see GREEK  (G2068) esthio
From  (G3601) odune; to grieve -- sorrow, torment. see GREEK  (G3601) odune
From  (G1416) duno; grief (as dejecting) -- sorrow. see GREEK  (G1416) duno
From a derivative of the base of  (G1416) duno; moaning, i.e. Lamentation -- mourning. see GREEK  (G1416) duno

From the neuter of  (G3739) hos and the third person singular present indicative of  (G1510) eimi; which is -- called, which is (make), that is (to say). see GREEK  (G3739) hos see GREEK  (G1510) eimi
Of Hebrew origin ( (H5818) Uzziyah); Ozias (i.e. Uzzijah), an Israelite -- Ozias. see HEBREW  (H5818) Uzziyah
A primary verb (in a strengthened form); to scent (usually an ill "odor"): stink.
From  (G3739) hos with the directive enclitic of source; from which place or source or cause (adverb or conjunction) -- from thence, (from) whence, where(-by, -fore, -upon). see GREEK  (G3739) hos

column7: fine linen, a sheet or sail
column9: Of uncertain affinity; a linen cloth, i.e. (especially) a sail -- sheet.
Neuter of a presumed derivative of  (G3607) othone; a linen bandage -- linen clothes. see GREEK  (G3607) othone

column7: to have seen or perceived, to know
column8: those of the his own household.
column9: From  (G3624) oikos; domestic, i.e. (as noun), a relative, adherent -- (those) of the (his own) house(-hold). see GREEK  (G3624) oikos
From  (G3611) oikeo; a fellow resident, i.e. Menial domestic -- (household) servant. see GREEK  (G3611) oikeo

From  (G3624) oikos; to occupy a house, i.e. Reside (figuratively, inhabit, remain, inhere); by implication, to cohabit -- dwell. See also  (G3625) oikoumene. see GREEK  (G3624) oikos see GREEK  (G3625) oikoumene
From  (G3611) oikeo; a tenement, i.e. (specially), a jail -- prison. see GREEK  (G3611) oikeo
Neuter of a presumed derivative of  (G3611) oikeo (equivalent to  (G3612) oikema); a residence (literally or figuratively) -- habitation, house. see GREEK  (G3611) oikeo see GREEK  (G3612) oikema

From  (G3624) oikos; properly, residence (abstractly), but usually (concretely) an abode (literally or figuratively); by implication, a family (especially domestics) -- home, house(-hold). see GREEK  (G3624) oikos
From  (G3614) oikia; familiar, i.e. (as noun) relatives -- they (them) of (his own) household. see GREEK  (G3614) oikia
From  (G3617) oikodespotes; to be the head of (i.e. Rule) a family -- guide the house. see GREEK  (G3617) oikodespotes
From  (G3624) oikos and  (G1203) despotes; the head of a family -- goodman (of the house), householder, master of the house. see GREEK  (G3624) oikos see GREEK  (G1203) despotes
From the same as  (G3619) oikodome; to be a house-builder, i.e. Construct or (figuratively) confirm -- (be in) build(-er, -ing, up), edify, embolden. see GREEK  (G3619) oikodome

Feminine (abstract) of a compound of  (G3624) oikos and the base of  (G1430) doma; architecture, i.e. (concretely) a structure; figuratively, confirmation -- building, edify(-ication, -ing). see GREEK  (G3624) oikos see GREEK  (G1430) doma
From the same as  (G3619) oikodome; confirmation -- edifying. see GREEK  (G3619) oikodome

column7: to be a steward, to manage
column9: From  (G3623) oikonomos; to manage (a house, i.e. An estate) -- be steward. see GREEK  (G3623) oikonomos
From  (G3623) oikonomos; administration (of a household or estate); specially, a (religious) "economy" -- dispensation, stewardship. see GREEK  (G3623) oikonomos

From  (G3624) oikos and the base of  (G3551) nomos; a house-distributor (i.e. Manager), or overseer, i.e. An employee in that capacity; by extension, a fiscal agent (treasurer); figuratively, a preacher (of the Gospel) -- chamberlain, governor, steward. see GREEK  (G3624) oikos see GREEK  (G3551) nomos
Of uncertain affinity; a dwelling (more or less extensive, literal or figurative); by implication, a family (more or less related, literally or figuratively) -- home, house(-hold), temple.

Feminine participle present passive of  (G3611) oikeo (as noun, by implication, of  (G1093) ge); land, i.e. The (terrene part of the) globe; specially, the Roman empire -- earth, world. see GREEK  (G3611) oikeo see GREEK  (G1093) ge
From  (G3624) oikos and ouros (a guard; be "ware"); a stayer at home, i.e. Domestically inclined (a "good housekeeper") -- keeper at home. see GREEK  (G3624) oikos

column7: to pity, to have compassion on
column9: Also (in certain tenses) prolonged oiktereo oyk-ter-eh'-o from oiktos (pity); to exercise pity -- have compassion on.
From  (G3627) oikteiro; pity -- mercy. see GREEK  (G3627) oikteiro
From  (G3627) oikteiro; compassionate -- merciful, of tender mercy. see GREEK  (G3627) oikteiro
From  (G3631) oinos and a derivative of the alternate of  (G4095) pino; a tippler -- winebibber. see GREEK  (G3631) oinos see GREEK  (G4095) pino
A primary word (or perhaps of Hebrew origin ( (H3196) yayin)); "wine" (literally or figuratively) -- wine. see HEBREW  (H3196) yayin
From  (G3631) oinos and a form of the base of  (G5397) phluaros; an overflow (or surplus) of wine, i.e. Vinolency (drunkenness) -- excess of wine. see GREEK  (G3631) oinos see GREEK  (G5397) phluaros
Or (shorter) oimai (oy'-mahee) middle voice apparently from  (G3634) hoios; to make like (oneself), i.e. Imagine (be of the opinion) -- suppose, think. see GREEK  (G3634) hoios

column8: so as, such as, what manner of
column9: Probably akin to  (G3588) ho,  (G3739) hos, and  (G3745) hosos; such or what sort of (as a correlation or exclamation); especially the neuter (adverbially) with negative, not so -- so (as), such as, what (manner of), which. see GREEK  (G3745) hosos see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G3739) hos

column7: to shrink (from doing), to hesitate (to do)
column9: From oknos (hesitation); to be slow (figuratively, loath) -- delay.
From  (G3635) okneo; tardy, i.e. Indolent; (figuratively) irksome -- grievous, slothful. see GREEK  (G3635) okneo

column7: of the eighth day, eight days old
column9: From  (G3638) oktos and  (G2250) hemera; an eight-day old person or act -- the eighth day. see GREEK  (G3638) oktos see GREEK  (G2250) hemera
A primary numeral; "eight" -- eight.
From a primary ollumi (to destroy; a prolonged form); ruin, i.e. Death, punishment -- destruction.
From  (G3641) oligos and  (G4102) pistis; incredulous, i.e. Lacking confidence (in Christ) -- of little faith. see GREEK  (G3641) oligos see GREEK  (G4102) pistis
Of uncertain affinity; puny (in extent, degree, number, duration or value); especially neuter (adverbially) somewhat -- + almost, brief(-ly), few, (a) little, + long, a season, short, small, a while.
From  (G3641) oligos and  (G6590) pshar; little-spirited, i.e. Faint-hearted -- feebleminded. see HEBREW  (G6590) pshar see GREEK  (G3641) oligos
From a compound of  (G3641) oligos and ora ("care"); to have little regard for, i.e. To disesteem -- despise. see GREEK  (G3641) oligos
From  (G3645) olothreuo; a ruiner, i.e. (specially), a venomous serpent -- destroyer. see GREEK  (G3645) olothreuo
From  (G3639) olethros; to spoil, i.e. Slay -- destroy. see GREEK  (G3639) olethros

From a derivative of a compound of  (G3650) holos and a derivative of  (G2545) kaio; a wholly-consumed sacrifice ("holocaust") -- (whole) burnt offering. see GREEK  (G3650) holos see GREEK  (G2545) kaio
From  (G3648) holokleros; integrity, i.e. Physical wholeness -- perfect soundness. see GREEK  (G3648) holokleros
From  (G3650) holos and  (G2819) kleros; complete in every part, i.e. Perfectly sound (in body) -- entire, whole. see GREEK  (G3650) holos see GREEK  (G2819) kleros
A reduplicated primary verb; to "howl" or "halloo", i.e. Shriek -- howl.
A primary word; "whole" or "all", i.e. Complete (in extent, amount, time or degree), especially (neuter) as noun or adverb -- all, altogether, every whit, + throughout, whole.
From  (G3650) holos and  (G5056) telos; complete to the end, i.e. Absolutely perfect -- wholly. see GREEK  (G3650) holos see GREEK  (G5056) telos
Probably a contraction from Olumpiodoros (Olympian-bestowed, i.e. Heaven-descended); Olympas, a Christian -- Olympas.
Of uncertain derivation; an unripe (because out of season) fig -- untimely fig.
Adverb from  (G3650) holos; completely, i.e. Altogether; (by analogy), everywhere; (negatively) not by any means -- at all, commonly, utterly. see GREEK  (G3650) holos
Of uncertain affinity; a thunder storm -- shower.

column7: to consort with, to converse with
column9: From  (G3658) homilos; to be in company with, i.e. (by implication) to converse -- commune, talk. see GREEK  (G3658) homilos
From  (G3658) homilos; companionship ("homily"), i.e. (by implication) intercourse -- communication. see GREEK  (G3658) homilos

From the base of  (G3674) homou and a derivative of the alternate of  (G138) haireomai (meaning a crowd); association together, i.e. A multitude -- company. see GREEK  (G3674) homou see GREEK  (G138) haireomai
From  (G3700) optanomai; a sight, i.e. (by implication) the eye -- eye. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
A prolonged form of a primary, but obsolete omo, for which another prolonged form omoo (om-o'-o) is used in certain tenses; to swear, i.e. Take (or declare on) oath -- swear.
Adverb from a compound of the base of  (G3674) homou and  (G2372) thumos; unanimously -- with one accord (mind). see GREEK  (G3674) homou see GREEK  (G2372) thumos
From  (G3664) homoios; to resemble -- agree. see GREEK  (G3664) homoios
From  (G3664) homoios and the alternate of  (G3958) pascho; similarly affected -- of (subject to) like passions. see GREEK  (G3664) homoios see GREEK  (G3958) pascho
From the base of  (G3674) homou; similar (in appearance or character) -- like, + manner. see GREEK  (G3674) homou
From  (G3664) homoios; resemblance -- like as, similitude. see GREEK  (G3664) homoios
From  (G3664) homoios; to assimilate, i.e. Compare; passively, to become similar -- be (make) like, (in the) liken(-ess), resemble. see GREEK  (G3664) homoios
From  (G3666) homoioo; a form; abstractly, resemblance -- made like to, likeness, shape, similitude. see GREEK  (G3666) homoioo
Adverb from  (G3664) homoios; similarly -- likewise, so. see GREEK  (G3664) homoios
From  (G3666) homoioo; assimilation, i.e. Resemblance -- similitude. see GREEK  (G3666) homoioo

column7: to speak the same, to agree
column9: From a compound of the base of  (G3674) homou and  (G3056) logos; to assent, i.e. Covenant, acknowledge -- con- (pro-)fess, confession is made, give thanks, promise. see GREEK  (G3674) homou see GREEK  (G3056) logos
From the same as  (G3670) homologeo; acknowledgment -- con- (pro-)fession, professed. see GREEK  (G3670) homologeo
Adverb of present passive participle of  (G3670) homologeo; confessedly -- without controversy. see GREEK  (G3670) homologeo
From the base of  (G3674) homou and  (G5078) techne; a fellow-artificer -- of the same craft. see GREEK  (G3674) homou see GREEK  (G5078) techne
Genitive case of homos (the same; akin to  (G260) hama) as adverb; at the same place or time -- together. see GREEK  (G260) hama
From the base of  (G3674) homou and  (G5424) phren; like-minded, i.e. Harmonious -- of one mind. see GREEK  (G5424) phren see GREEK  (G3674) homou
Adverb from the base of  (G3674) homou; at the same time, i.e. (conjunctionally) notwithstanding, yet still -- and even, nevertheless, though but. see GREEK  (G3674) homou
Of uncertain derivation; a dream -- dream.
Neuter of a presumed derivative of  (G3688) onos; a little ass -- young ass. see GREEK  (G3688) onos
From  (G3681) oneidos; to defame, i.e. Rail at, chide, taunt -- cast in teeth, (suffer) reproach, revile, upbraid. see GREEK  (G3681) oneidos
From  (G3679) oneidizo; contumely -- reproach. see GREEK  (G3679) oneidizo
Probably akin to the base of  (G3686) onoma; notoriety, i.e. A taunt (disgrace) -- reproach. see GREEK  (G3686) onoma
From  (G3685) oninemi; profitable; Onesimus, a Christian -- Onesimus. see GREEK  (G3685) oninemi
From a derivative of  (G3685) oninemi and  (G5411) phoros; profit-bearer; Onesiphorus, a Christian -- Onespiphorus. see GREEK  (G3685) oninemi see GREEK  (G5411) phoros
From  (G3688) onos; belonging to a ass, i.e. Large (so as to be turned by a ass) -- millstone. see GREEK  (G3688) onos

A prolonged form of an apparently primary verb (onomai, to slur); for which another prolonged form (onao) is used as an alternate in some tenses (unless indeed it be identical with the base of  (G3686) onoma through the idea of notoriety); to gratify, i.e. (middle voice) to derive pleasure or advantage from -- have joy. see GREEK  (G3686) onoma

From a presumed derivative of the base of  (G1097) ginosko (compare  (G3685) oninemi); a "name" (literally or figuratively) (authority, character) -- called, (+ sur-)name(-d). see GREEK  (G1097) ginosko see GREEK  (G3685) oninemi

column7: to name, to give a name
column9: From  (G3686) onoma; to name, i.e. Assign an appellation; by extension, to utter, mention, profess -- call, name. see GREEK  (G3686) onoma
Apparently a primary word; a donkey -- an ass.
Adverb of the oblique cases of  (G5607) on; really -- certainly, clean, indeed, of a truth, verily. see GREEK  (G5607) on
From  (G3691) oxus; vinegar, i.e. Sour wine -- vinegar. see GREEK  (G3691) oxus
Probably akin to the base of  (G188) akmen ("acid"); keen; by analogy, rapid -- sharp, swift. see GREEK  (G188) akmen
Probably from  (G3700) optanomai; a hole (as if for light), i.e. Cavern; by analogy, a spring (of water) -- cave, place. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai

From opis (regard; from  (G3700) optanomai) with enclitic of source; from the rear (as a secure aspect), i.e. At the back (adverb and preposition of place or time) -- after, backside, behind. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai

From the same as  (G3693) opisthen with enclitic of direction; to the back, i.e. Aback (as adverb or preposition of time or place; or as noun) -- after, back(-ward), (+ get) behind, + follow. see GREEK  (G3693) opisthen
From  (G3696) hoplon; to equip (with weapons (middle voice and figuratively)) -- arm self. see GREEK  (G3696) hoplon
Probably from a primary hepo (to be busy about); an implement or utensil or tool (literally or figuratively, especially, offensive for war) -- armour, instrument, weapon.

From  (G3739) hos and  (G4169) poios; of what kind that, i.e. How (as) great (excellent) (specially, as an indefinite correlative to the definite antecedent  (G5108) toioutos of quality) -- what manner (sort) of, such as whatsoever. see GREEK  (G3739) hos see GREEK  (G4169) poios see GREEK  (G5108) toioutos
From  (G3739) hos and  (G4218) pote; what(-ever) then, i.e. (of time) as soon as -- when. see GREEK  (G3739) hos see GREEK  (G4218) pote
From  (G3739) hos and  (G4225) pou; what(-ever) where, i.e. At whichever spot -- in what place, where(-as, -soever), whither (+ soever). see GREEK  (G3739) hos see GREEK  (G4225) pou

A (middle voice) prolonged form of the primary (middle voice) optomai (op'-tom-ahee); which is used for it in certain tenses; and both as alternate of  (G3708) horao; to gaze (i.e. With wide-open eyes, as at something remarkable; and thus differing from  (G991) blepo, which denotes simply voluntary observation; and from  (G1492) eido, which expresses merely mechanical, passive or casual vision; while  (G2300) theaomai, and still more emphatically its intensive  (G2334) theoreo, signifies an earnest but more continued inspection; and  (G4648) skopeo a watching from a distance) -- appear, look, see, shew self. see GREEK  (G3708) horao see GREEK  (G991) blepo see GREEK  (G1492) eido see GREEK  (G2300) theaomai see GREEK  (G2334) theoreo see GREEK  (G4648) skopeo
From a presumed derivative of  (G3700) optanomai; visuality, i.e. (concretely) an apparition -- vision. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
From an obsolete verb akin to hepso (to "steep"); cooked, i.e. Roasted -- broiled.

Apparently from the base of  (G3796) opse and  (G5610) hora; properly, even-tide of the (summer) season (dog-days), i.e. (by implication) ripe fruit -- fruit. see GREEK  (G3796) opse see GREEK  (G5610) hora

From  (G3739) hos and  (G4459) pos; what(-ever) how, i.e. In the manner that (as adverb or conjunction of coincidence, intentional or actual) -- because, how, (so) that, to, when. see GREEK  (G3739) hos see GREEK  (G4459) pos
From  (G3708) horao; something gazed at, i.e. A spectacle (especially supernatural) -- sight, vision. see GREEK  (G3708) horao

column7: the act of seeing, a vision, appearance
column9: From  (G3708) horao; the act of gazing, i.e. (externally) an aspect or (internally) an inspired appearance -- sight, vision. see GREEK  (G3708) horao
From  (G3708) horao; gazed at, i.e. (by implication) capable of being seen -- visible. see GREEK  (G3708) horao

Properly, to stare at (compare  (G3700) optanomai), i.e. (by implication) to discern clearly (physically or mentally); by extension, to attend to; by Hebraism, to experience; passively, to appear -- behold, perceive, see, take heed. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai

From  (G3713) oregomai; properly, desire (as a reaching forth or excitement of the mind), i.e. (by analogy), violent passion (ire, or (justifiable) abhorrence); by implication punishment -- anger, indignation, vengeance, wrath. see GREEK  (G3713) oregomai
From  (G3709) orge; to provoke or enrage, i.e. (passively) become exasperated -- be angry (wroth). see GREEK  (G3709) orge
From  (G3709) orge; irascible -- soon angry. see GREEK  (G3709) orge

column7: a fathom (the length of the outstretched arms)
column9: From  (G3713) oregomai; a stretch of the arms, i.e. A fathom -- fathom. see GREEK  (G3713) oregomai

column7: to stretch out, to reach after, to yearn for
column9: Middle voice of apparently a prolonged form of an obsolete primary (compare  (G3735) oros); to stretch oneself, i.e. Reach out after (long for) -- covet after, desire. see GREEK  (G3735) oros
From  (G3735) oros; mountainous, i.e. (feminine by implication, of  (G5561) chora) the Highlands (of Judaea) -- hill country. see GREEK  (G3735) oros see GREEK  (G5561) chora
From  (G3713) oregomai; excitement of the mind, i.e. Longing after -- lust. see GREEK  (G3713) oregomai
From a compound of  (G3717) orthos and  (G4228) pous; to be straight-footed, i.e. (figuratively) to go directly forward -- walk uprightly. see GREEK  (G3717) orthos see GREEK  (G4228) pous
Probably from the base of  (G3735) oros; right (as rising), i.e. (perpendicularly) erect (figuratively, honest), or (horizontally) level or direct -- straight, upright. see GREEK  (G3735) oros

From a compound of  (G3717) orthos and the base of  (G5114) tomoteros, to make a straight cut, i.e. (figuratively) to dissect (expound) correctly (the divine message) -- rightly divide. see GREEK  (G3717) orthos see GREEK  (G5114) tomoteros
From  (G3722) orthros; to use the dawn, i.e. (by implication) to repair betimes -- come early in the morning. see GREEK  (G3722) orthros
From  (G3722) orthros; relating to the dawn, i.e. Matutinal (as an epithet of Venus, especially brilliant in the early day) -- morning. see GREEK  (G3722) orthros
From  (G3722) orthros; in the dawn, i.e. Up at day-break -- early. see GREEK  (G3722) orthros
From the same as  (G3735) oros; dawn (as sun-rise, rising of light); by extension, morn -- early in the morning. see GREEK  (G3735) oros
Adverb from  (G3717) orthos; in a straight manner, i.e. (figuratively) correctly (also morally) -- plain, right(-ly). see GREEK  (G3717) orthos

column7: to mark off by boundaries, to determine
column9: From  (G3725) horion; to mark out or bound ("horizon"), i.e. (figuratively) to appoint, decree, specify -- declare, determine, limit, ordain. see GREEK  (G3725) horion
Neuter of a derivative of an apparently primary horos (a bound or limit); a boundary-line, i.e. (by implication) a frontier (region) -- border, coast.
From  (G3727) horkos; to put on oath, i.e. Make swear; by analogy, to solemnly enjoin -- adjure, charge. see GREEK  (G3727) horkos
From herkos (a fence; perhaps akin to  (G3725) horion); a limit, i.e. (sacred) restraint (specially, an oath) -- oath. see GREEK  (G3725) horion
From a compound of  (G3727) horkos and a derivative of  (G3660) omnuo; asseveration on oath -- oath. see GREEK  (G3727) horkos see GREEK  (G3660) omnuo

column7: to set in motion, to hasten on
column9: From  (G3730) horme; to start, spur or urge on, i.e. (reflexively) to dash or plunge -- run (violently), rush. see GREEK  (G3730) horme

column7: a rapid motion forwards, onrush, assault
column9: Of uncertain affinity; a violent impulse, i.e. Onset -- assault.
From  (G3730) horme; an attack, i.e. (abstractly) precipitancy -- violence. see GREEK  (G3730) horme
Neuter of a presumed derivative of  (G3733) ornis; a birdling -- bird, fowl. see GREEK  (G3733) ornis

column7: a bird, a rooster or hen
column9: Probably from a prolonged form of the base of  (G3735) oros; a bird (as rising in the air), i.e. (specially), a hen (or female domestic fowl) -- hen. see GREEK  (G3735) oros
From a compound of the base of  (G3725) horion and a derivative of  (G5087) tithemi; a limit-placing, i.e. (concretely) boundary-line -- bound. see GREEK  (G3725) horion see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi

Probably from an obsolete oro (to rise or "rear"; perhaps akin to  (G142) airo; compare  (G3733) ornis); a mountain (as lifting itself above the plain): -hill, mount(-ain). see GREEK  (G142) airo see GREEK  (G3733) ornis
Apparently a primary verb; to "burrow" in the ground, i.e. Dig -- dig.
Of uncertain affinity; bereaved ("orphan"), i.e. Parentless -- comfortless, fatherless.
Middle voice from orchos (a row or ring); to dance (from the ranklike or regular motion) -- dance.

column7: usually rel. who, which, that, also demonstrative this, that
column8: one, other, some, that, what, which
column9: Including feminine he (hay), and neuter ho (ho) probably a primary word (or perhaps a form of the article  (G3588) ho); the relatively (sometimes demonstrative) pronoun, who, which, what, that -- one, (an-, the) other, some, that, what, which, who(-m, -se), etc. See also  (G3757) hou. see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G3757) hou
Multiple adverb from  (G3739) hos; how (i.e. With  (G302) an, so) many times as -- as oft(-en) as. see GREEK  (G3739) hos see GREEK  (G302) an

Of uncertain affinity; properly, right (by intrinsic or divine character; thus distinguished from  (G1342) dikaios, which refers rather to human statutes and relations; from  (G2413) hieros, which denotes formal consecration; and from  (G40) hagios, which relates to purity from defilement), i.e. Hallowed (pious, sacred, sure) -- holy, mercy, shalt be.  (G342) anakainosis see GREEK  (G2413) hieros see GREEK  (G40) hagios
From  (G3741) hosios; piety -- holiness. see GREEK  (G3741) hosios
Adverb from  (G3741) hosios; piously -- holily. see GREEK  (G3741) hosios
From  (G3605) ozo; fragrance (literally or figuratively) -- odour, savour. see GREEK  (G3605) ozo

By reduplication from  (G3739) hos; as (much, great, long, etc.) As -- all (that), as (long, many, much) (as), how great (many, much), (in-)asmuch as, so many as, that (ever), the more, those things, what (great, -soever), wheresoever, wherewithsoever, which, X while, who(-soever). see GREEK  (G3739) hos
From  (G3739) hos and  (G4007) per; who especially -- whomsoever. see GREEK  (G3739) hos see GREEK  (G4007) per
Or contracted ostoun (os-toon') of uncertain affinity; a bone -- bone.

Including the feminine hetis (hay'-tis), and the neuter ho,ti (hot'-ee) from  (G3739) hos and  (G5100) tis; which some, i.e. Any that; also (definite) which same -- X and (they), (such) as, (they) that, in that they, what(-soever), whereas ye, (they) which, who(-soever). Compare  (G3754) hoti. see GREEK  (G3739) hos see GREEK  (G5100) tis see GREEK  (G3754) hoti
From ostrakon ("oyster") (a tile, i.e. Terra cotta); earthen-ware, i.e. Clayey; by implication, frail -- of earth, earthen.
From a derivative of  (G3605) ozo; smell (the sense) -- smelling. see GREEK  (G3605) ozo
Of uncertain affinity; the loin (externally), i.e. The hip; internally (by extension) procreative power -- loin.

From  (G3753) hote and  (G302) an; whenever (implying hypothesis or more or less uncertainty); also causatively (conjunctionally) inasmuch as -- as long (soon) as, that, + till, when(-soever), while. see GREEK  (G3753) hote see GREEK  (G302) an

column8: after that, as soon as, when
column9: From  (G3739) hos and  (G5037) te; at which (thing) too, i.e. When -- after (that), as soon as, that, when, while. see GREEK  (G3739) hos see GREEK  (G5037) te

column8: as great as, as many as
column9: Neuter of  (G3748) hostis as conjunction; demonstrative, that (sometimes redundant); causative, because -- as concerning that, as though, because (that), for (that), how (that), (in) that, though, why. see GREEK  (G3748) hostis
For the genitive case of  (G3748) hostis (as adverb); during which same time, i.e. Whilst -- whiles. see GREEK  (G3748) hostis

Also (before a vowel) ouk (ook), and (before an aspirate) ouch (ookh) a primary word; the absolute negative (compare  (G3361) me) adverb; no or not -- + long, nay, neither, never, no (X man), none, (can-)not, + nothing, + special, un(-worthy), when, + without, + yet but. See also  (G3364) ou me,  (G3372) mekos. see GREEK  (G3361) me see GREEK  (G3364) ou me see GREEK  (G3372) mekos
Genitive case of  (G3739) hos as adverb; at which place, i.e. Where -- where(-in), whither(-soever). see GREEK  (G3739) hos

column7: ah! ha! (an expression of wonder or surprise)
column9: A primary exclamation of surprise; "ah" -- ah.

column7: alas! woe! (an expression of grief or denunciation)
column9: A primary exclamation of grief; "woe" -- alas, woe.
Adverb from (the feminine) of  (G3762) oudeis; by no means -- not. see GREEK  (G3762) oudeis

From  (G3756) ou and  (G1161) de; not however, i.e. Neither, nor, not even -- neither (indeed), never, no (more, nor, not), nor (yet), (also, even, then) not (even, so much as), + nothing, so much as. see GREEK  (G3756) ou see GREEK  (G1161) de

column5: oudeis and outheis, oudemia, ouden and outhen
column9: Including feminine oudemia (oo-dem-ee'-ah), and neuter ouden (oo-den') from  (G3761) oude and  (G1520) heis; not even one (man, woman or thing), i.e. None, nobody, nothing -- any (man), aught, man, neither any (thing), never (man), no (man), none (+ of these things), not (any, at all, -thing), nought. see GREEK  (G3761) oude see GREEK  (G1520) heis
From  (G3761) oude and  (G4218) pote; not even at any time, i.e. Never at all -- neither at any time, never, nothing at any time. see GREEK  (G3761) oude see GREEK  (G4218) pote
From  (G3761) oude and  (G4452) po; not even yet -- as yet not, never before (yet), (not) yet. see GREEK  (G3761) oude see GREEK  (G4452) po

Also (separately) ouk eti (ook et'-ee) from  (G3756) ou and  (G2089) eti; not yet, no longer -- after that (not), (not) any more, henceforth (hereafter) not, no longer (more), not as yet (now), now no more (not), yet (not). see GREEK  (G3756) ou see GREEK  (G2089) eti
From  (G3756) ou and  (G3767) oun; is it not therefore that, i.e. (affirmatively) hence or so -- then. see GREEK  (G3756) ou see GREEK  (G3767) oun
Apparently a primary word; (adverbially) certainly, or (conjunctionally) accordingly -- and (so, truly), but, now (then), so (likewise then), then, therefore, verily, wherefore.
From  (G3756) ou and  (G4452) po; not yet -- hitherto not, (no...) As yet, not yet. see GREEK  (G3756) ou see GREEK  (G4452) po
Apparently a primary word; a tail -- tail.
From  (G3772) ouranos; celestial, i.e. Belonging to or coming from the sky -- heavenly. see GREEK  (G3772) ouranos
From  (G3772) ouranos and the enclitic of source; from the sky -- from heaven. see GREEK  (G3772) ouranos

Perhaps from the same as  (G3735) oros (through the idea of elevation); the sky; by extension, heaven (as the abode of God); by implication, happiness, power, eternity; specially, the Gospel (Christianity) -- air, heaven(-ly), sky. see GREEK  (G3735) oros
Of Latin origin; Urbanus (of the city, "urbane"), a Christian -- Urbanus.
Of Hebrew origin ( (H223) 'Uwriyah); Urias (i.e. Urijah), a Hittite -- Urias. see HEBREW  (H223) 'Uwriyah
Apparently a primary word; the ear (physically or mentally) -- ear.
From the feminine of  (G5607) on; substance, i.e. Property (possessions) -- goods, substance. see GREEK  (G5607) on
From  (G3756) ou and  (G5037) te; not too, i.e. Neither or nor; by analogy, not even -- neither, none, nor (yet), (no, yet) not, nothing. see GREEK  (G3756) ou see GREEK  (G5037) te

Including nominative masculine plural houtoi (hoo'-toy), nominative feminine singular haute (how'-tay), and nominative feminine plural hautai (how'-tahee) from the article  (G3588) ho and  (G846) autos; the he (she or it), i.e. This or that (often with article repeated) -- he (it was that), hereof, it, she, such as, the same, these, they, this (man, same, woman), which, who. see GREEK  (G846) autos see GREEK  (G3588) ho

Or (before a vowel houtos hoo'-toce adverb from  (G3778) houtos; in this way (referring to what precedes or follows) -- after that, after (in) this manner, as, even (so), for all that, like(-wise), no more, on this fashion(-wise), so (in like manner), thus, what. see GREEK  (G3778) houtos
Intensive of  (G3756) ou; not indeed -- nay, not. see GREEK  (G3756) ou
From  (G3784) opheilo; an ower, i.e. Person indebted; figuratively, a delinquent; morally, a transgressor (against God) -- debtor, which owed, sinner. see GREEK  (G3784) opheilo
From  (G3784) opheilo; indebtedness, i.e. (concretely) a sum owed; figuratively, obligation, i.e. (conjugal) duty -- debt, due. see GREEK  (G3784) opheilo

column7: that which is owed, a debt
column9: From (the alternate of)  (G3784) opheilo; something owed, i.e. (figuratively) a due; morally, a fault -- debt. see GREEK  (G3784) opheilo

Or (in certain tenses), its prolonged form opheileo (of-i-leh'-o) probably from the base of  (G3786) ophelos (through the idea of accruing); to owe (pecuniarily); figuratively, to be under obligation (ought, must, should); morally, to fail in duty -- behove, be bound, (be) debt(-or), (be) due(-ty), be guilty (indebted), (must) need(-s), ought, owe, should. See also  (G3785) ophelon. see GREEK  (G3786) ophelos see GREEK  (G3785) ophelon

column7: would that (used to express an unattainable wish)
column9: First person singular of a past tense of  (G3784) opheilo; I ought (wish), i.e. (interjection) oh that! -- would (to God). see GREEK  (G3784) opheilo
From ophello (to heap up, i.e. Accumulate or benefit); gain -- advantageth, profit.
From  (G3788) ophthalmos and  (G1397) douleia; sight-labor, i.e. That needs watching (remissness) -- eye-service. see GREEK  (G3788) ophthalmos see GREEK  (G1397) douleia
From  (G3700) optanomai; the eye (literally or figuratively); by implication, vision; figuratively, envy (from the jealous side-glance) -- eye, sight. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai

Probably from  (G3700) optanomai (through the idea of sharpness of vision); a snake, figuratively, (as a type of sly cunning) an artful malicious person, especially Satan -- serpent. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai

Perhaps from  (G3700) optanomai (through the idea of the shading or proximity to the organ of vision); the eye-"brow" or forehead, i.e. (figuratively) the brink of a precipice -- brow. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
From  (G3793) ochlos; to mob, i.e. (by implication) to harass -- vex. see GREEK  (G3793) ochlos
From  (G3793) ochlos and  (G4160) poieo; to make a crowd, i.e. Raise a public disturbance -- gather a company. see GREEK  (G3793) ochlos see GREEK  (G4160) poieo

column7: a crowd, multitude, the common people
column9: From a derivative of  (G2192) echo (meaning a vehicle); a throng (as borne along); by implication, the rabble; by extension, a class of people; figuratively, a riot -- company, multitude, number (of people), people, press. see GREEK  (G2192) echo
From a remote derivative of  (G2192) echo (meaning to fortify, through the idea of holding safely); a castle (figuratively, argument) -- stronghold. see GREEK  (G2192) echo

Neuter of a presumed derivative of the base of  (G3702) optos; a relish to other food (as if cooked sauce), i.e. (specially), fish (presumably salted and dried as a condiment) -- fish. see GREEK  (G3702) optos
From the same as  (G3694) opiso (through the idea of backwardness); (adverbially) late in the day; by extension, after the close of the day -- (at) even, in the end. see GREEK  (G3694) opiso
From  (G3796) opse; later, i.e. Vernal (showering) -- latter. see GREEK  (G3796) opse
From  (G3796) opse; late; feminine (as noun) afternoon (early eve) or nightfall (later eve) -- even(-ing, (-tide)). see GREEK  (G3796) opse

column7: the act of seeing, the sense of sight
column9: From  (G3700) optanomai; properly, sight (the act), i.e. (by implication) the visage, an external show -- appearance, countenance, face. see GREEK  (G3700) optanomai
Neuter of a presumed derivative of the same as  (G3795) opsarion; rations for a soldier, i.e. (by extension) his stipend or pay -- wages. see GREEK  (G3795) opsarion

column5: ho ón kai ho én kai ho erchomenos
column9: Ho erchomenos (ho own kahee) ho ane kahee (ho er-khom'-en-os) a phrase combining  (G3588) ho with the present participle and imperfect of  (G1510) eimi and the present participle of  (G2064) erchomai by means of  (G2532) kai; the one being and the one that was and the one coming, i.e. The Eternal, as a divine epithet of Christ -- which art (is, was), and (which) wast (is, was), and art (is) to come (shalt be). see GREEK  (G1510) eimi see GREEK  (G2532) kai see GREEK  (G3588) ho see GREEK  (G2064) erchomai
From  (G3803) pagis; to ensnare (figuratively) -- entangle. see GREEK  (G3803) pagis
From  (G4078) pegnumi; a trap (as fastened by a noose or notch); figuratively, a trick or statagem (temptation) -- snare. see GREEK  (G4078) pegnumi

column7: that which befalls one, a suffering, a passion
column9: From a presumed derivative of  (G3806) pathos; something undergone, i.e. Hardship or pain; subjectively, an emotion or influence -- affection, affliction, motion, suffering. see GREEK  (G3806) pathos

column7: one who has suffered or is subject to suffering
column9: From the same as  (G3804) pathema; liable (i.e. Doomed) to experience pain -- suffer. see GREEK  (G3804) pathema

column7: that which befalls one, a passion, a suffering
column9: From the alternate of  (G3958) pascho; properly, suffering ("pathos"), i.e. (subjectively) a passion (especially concupiscence) -- (inordinate) affection, lust. see GREEK  (G3958) pascho

column7: a trainer of boys, a tutor
column9: From  (G3816) pais and a reduplicated form of  (G71) ago; a boy-leader, i.e. A servant whose office it was to take the children to school; (by implication, (figuratively) a tutor ("paedagogue")) -- instructor, schoolmaster. see GREEK  (G3816) pais see GREEK  (G71) ago
Neuter of a presumed derivative of  (G3816) pais; a little boy -- child, lad. see GREEK  (G3816) pais

column7: the rearing of a child, training, discipline
column9: From  (G3811) paideuo; tutorage, i.e. Education or training; by implication, disciplinary correction -- chastening, chastisement, instruction, nurture. see GREEK  (G3811) paideuo
From  (G3811) paideuo; a trainer, i.e. Teacher or (by implication) discipliner -- which corrected, instructor. see GREEK  (G3811) paideuo

column7: to train children, to chasten, correct
column9: From  (G3816) pais; to train up a child, i.e. Educate, or (by implication), discipline (by punishment) -- chasten(-ise), instruct, learn, teach. see GREEK  (G3816) pais
Adverb (of source) from  (G3813) paidion; from infancy -- of a child. see GREEK  (G3813) paidion

Neuter diminutive of  (G3816) pais; a childling (of either sex), i.e. (properly), an infant, or (by extension) a half-grown boy or girl; figuratively, an immature Christian -- (little, young) child, damsel. see GREEK  (G3816) pais
Feminine diminutive of  (G3816) pais; a girl, i.e. (specially), a female slave or servant -- bondmaid(-woman), damsel, maid(-en). see GREEK  (G3816) pais
From  (G3816) pais; to sport (as a boy) -- play. see GREEK  (G3816) pais

Perhaps from  (G3817) paio; a boy (as often beaten with impunity), or (by analogy), a girl, and (genitive case) a child; specially, a slave or servant (especially a minister to a king; and by eminence to God) -- child, maid(-en), (man) servant, son, young man. see GREEK  (G3817) paio
A primary verb; to hit (as if by a single blow and less violently than  (G5180) tupto); specially, to sting (as a scorpion) -- smite, strike. see GREEK  (G5180) tupto
Feminine of an adjective of uncertain derivation; Pacatianian, a section of Phrygia -- Pacatiana.

Probably another form for  (G3825) palin (through the idea of retrocession); (adverbially) formerly, or (by relatively) sometime since; (elliptically as adjective) ancient -- any while, a great while ago, (of) old, in time past. see GREEK  (G3825) palin
From  (G3819) palai; antique, i.e. Not recent, worn out -- old. see GREEK  (G3819) palai
From  (G3820) palaios; antiquatedness -- oldness. see GREEK  (G3820) palaios
From  (G3820) palaios; to make (passively, become) worn out, or declare obsolete -- decay, make (wax) old. see GREEK  (G3820) palaios
From pallo (to vibrate; another form for  (G906) ballo); wrestling -- + wrestle. see GREEK  (G906) ballo

From  (G3825) palin and  (G1078) genesis; (spiritual) rebirth (the state or the act), i.e. (figuratively) spiritual renovation; specially, Messianic restoration -- regeneration. see GREEK  (G3825) palin see GREEK  (G1078) genesis

Probably from the same as  (G3823) pale (through the idea of oscillatory repetition); (adverbially) anew, i.e. (of place) back, (of time) once more, or (conjunctionally) furthermore or on the other hand -- again. see GREEK  (G3823) pale
Dative case (adverb) of a compound of  (G3956) pas and  (G4128) plethos; in full multitude, i.e. Concertedly or simultaneously -- all at once. see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G4128) plethos
From  (G3956) pas and  (G4183) polus; full many, i.e. Immense -- very great. see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G4183) polus

column7: Pamphylia, a province of Asia Minor
column9: From a compound of  (G3956) pas and  (G4443) pura; every-tribal, i.e. Heterogeneous ( (G5561) chora being implied); Pamphylia, a region of Asia Minor -- Pamphylia. see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G4443) pura see GREEK  (G5561) chora

Neuter of a presumed compound of  (G3956) pas and a derivative of  (G1209) dechomai; all-receptive, i.e. A public lodging-place (caravanserai or khan) -- inn. see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
From the same as  (G3829) pandocheion; an innkeeper (warden of a caravanserai) -- host. see GREEK  (G3829) pandocheion
From  (G3956) pas and a derivative of  (G58) agora; a mass-meeting, i.e. (figuratively) universal companionship -- general assembly. see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G58) agora
Adverb from  (G3956) pas and  (G3624) oikos; with the whole family -- with all his house. see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G3624) oikos
From a compound of  (G3956) pas and  (G3696) hoplon; full armor ("panoply") -- all (whole) armour. see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G3696) hoplon
From  (G3835) panougos; adroitness, i.e. (in a bad sense) trickery or sophistry -- (cunning) craftiness, subtilty. see GREEK  (G3835) panougos

column7: ready to do anything, crafty, skillful
column9: From  (G3956) pas and  (G2041) ergon; all-working, i.e. Adroit (shrewd) -- crafty. see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G2041) ergon
Adverb (of source) from  (G3837) pantachou; from all directions -- from every quarter. see GREEK  (G3837) pantachou
Genitive case (as adverb of place) of a presumed derivative of  (G3956) pas; universally -- in all places, everywhere. see GREEK  (G3956) pas
From  (G3956) pas and  (G5056) telos; full-ended, i.e. Entire (neuter as noun, completion) -- + in (no) wise, uttermost. see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G5056) telos
Adverb (of manner) from  (G3956) pas; wholly -- always. see GREEK  (G3956) pas
Adverb (of source) from  (G3956) pas; from (i.e. On) all sides -- on every side, round about. see GREEK  (G3956) pas
From  (G3956) pas and  (G2904) kratos; the all-ruling, i.e. God (as absolute and universal sovereign) -- Almighty, Omnipotent. see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G2904) kratos
From  (G3956) pas and  (G3753) hote; every when, i.e. At all times -- alway(-s), ever(-more). see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G3753) hote

column8: altogether, by all means, no doubt.
column9: Adverb from  (G3956) pas; entirely; specially, at all events, (with negative, following) in no event -- by all means, altogether, at all, needs, no doubt, in (no) wise, surely. see GREEK  (G3956) pas

column7: from beside, by the side of, by, beside
column9: A primary preposition; properly, near; i.e. (with genitive case) from beside (literally or figuratively), (with dative case) at (or in) the vicinity of (objectively or subjectively), (with accusative case) to the proximity with (local (especially beyond or opposed to) or causal (on account of) -- above, against, among, at, before, by, contrary to, X friend, from, + give (such things as they), + that (she) had, X his, in, more than, nigh unto, (out) of, past, save, side...by, in the sight of, than, (there-)fore, with. In compounds it retains the same variety of application.

column7: to go by the side of, to go past
column9: From  (G3844) para and the base of  (G939) basis; to go contrary to, i.e. Violate a command -- (by) transgress(-ion). see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G939) basis
From  (G3844) para and  (G906) ballo; to throw alongside, i.e. (reflexively) to reach a place, or (figuratively) to liken -- arrive, compare. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G906) ballo
From  (G3845) parabaino; violation -- breaking, transgression. see GREEK  (G3845) parabaino
From  (G3845) parabaino; a violator -- breaker, transgress(-or). see GREEK  (G3845) parabaino
From  (G3844) para and the middle voice of  (G971) biazo; to force contrary to (nature), i.e. Compel (by entreaty) -- constrain. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G971) biazo

From  (G3846) paraballo; a similitude ("parable"), i.e. (symbolic) fictitious narrative (of common life conveying a moral), apothegm or adage -- comparison, figure, parable, proverb. see GREEK  (G3846) paraballo
From  (G3844) para and the middle voice of  (G1011) bouleuo; to misconsult, i.e. Disregard -- not (to) regard(-ing). see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1011) bouleuo
From  (G3853) paraggello; a mandate -- charge, command. see GREEK  (G3853) paraggello

column7: to transmit a message, to order
column9: From  (G3844) para and the base of  (G32) aggelos; to transmit a message, i.e. (by implication) to enjoin -- (give in) charge, (give) command(-ment), declare. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G32) aggelos
From  (G3844) para and  (G1096) ginomai; to become near, i.e. Approach (have arrived); by implication, to appear publicly -- come, go, be present. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1096) ginomai

column7: to lead by, to pass by or away
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G71) ago; to lead near, i.e. (reflexively or intransitively) to go along or away -- depart, pass (away, by, forth). see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G71) ago

column7: to set forth as an example
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G1165) deigmatizo; to show alongside (the public), i.e. Expose to infamy -- make a public example, put to an open shame. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1165) deigmatizo

column7: a park, a garden, a paradise
column9: Of Oriental origin (compare  (H6508) pardec); a park, i.e. (specially), an Eden (place of future happiness, "paradise") -- paradise. see HEBREW  (H6508) pardec
From  (G3844) para and  (G1209) dechomai; to accept near, i.e. Admit or (by implication) delight in -- receive. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1209) dechomai
From a compound of  (G3844) para and  (G1304) diatribo; misemployment, i.e. Meddlesomeness -- perverse disputing. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1304) diatribo

column7: to hand over, to give or deliver over, to betray
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G1325) didomi; to surrender, i.e yield up, intrust, transmit -- betray, bring forth, cast, commit, deliver (up), give (over, up), hazard, put in prison, recommend. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1325) didomi
From  (G3844) para and  (G1391) doxa (in the sense of seeming); contrary to expectation, i.e. Extraordinary ("paradox") -- strange. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1391) doxa

column7: a handing down or over, a tradition
column9: From  (G3860) paradidomi; transmission, i.e. (concretely) a precept; specially, the Jewish traditionary law -- ordinance, tradition. see GREEK  (G3860) paradidomi
From  (G3844) para and  (G2206) zeloo; to stimulate alongside, i.e. Excite to rivalry -- provoke to emulation (jealousy). see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2206) zeloo
From  (G3844) para and  (G2281) thalassa; along the sea, i.e. Maritime (lacustrine) -- upon the sea coast. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2281) thalassa
From  (G3844) para and  (G2334) theoreo; to overlook or disregard -- neglect. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2334) theoreo
From  (G3908) paratithemi; a deposit, i.e. (figuratively) trust -- committed unto. see GREEK  (G3908) paratithemi
From  (G3844) para and  (G134) aineo; to mispraise, i.e. Recommend or advise (a different course) -- admonish, exhort. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G134) aineo

column7: to beg from, to beg off
column9: From  (G3844) para and the middle voice of  (G154) aiteo; to beg off, i.e. Deprecate, decline, shun -- avoid, (make) excuse, intreat, refuse, reject. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G154) aiteo
From  (G3844) para and  (G2523) kathizo; to sit down near -- sit. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2523) kathizo

column7: to call to or for, to exhort, to encourage
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G2564) kaleo; to call near, i.e. Invite, invoke (by imploration, hortation or consolation) -- beseech, call for, (be of good) comfort, desire, (give) exhort(-ation), intreat, pray. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2564) kaleo

column7: to cover (by hanging something beside), to hide
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G2572) kalupto; to cover alongside, i.e. Veil (figuratively) -- hide. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2572) kalupto

From a compound of  (G3844) para and  (G2698) katatithemi; something put down alongside, i.e. A deposit (sacred trust) -- that (thing) which is committed (un-)to (trust). see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2698) katatithemi
From  (G3844) para and  (G2749) keimai; to lie near, i.e. Be at hand (figuratively, be prompt or easy) -- be present. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2749) keimai

column7: a calling to one\'s aid, encouragement, comfort
column9: From  (G3870) parakaleo; imploration, hortation, solace -- comfort, consolation, exhortation, intreaty. see GREEK  (G3870) parakaleo
An intercessor, consoler -- advocate, comforter.

column7: a hearing amiss, by implication disobedience
column9: From  (G3878) parakouo; inattention, i.e. (by implication) disobedience -- disobedience. see GREEK  (G3878) parakouo

From  (G3844) para and  (G190) akoloutheo; to follow near, i.e. (figuratively) attend (as a result), trace out, conform to -- attain, follow, fully know, have understanding. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G190) akoloutheo

column7: to overhear, to hear amiss, to take no heed
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G191) akouo; to mishear, i.e. (by implication) to disobey -- neglect to hear. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G191) akouo

column7: to stoop sideways, to stoop to look
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G2955) kupto; to bend beside, i.e. Lean over (so as to peer within) -- look (into), stoop down. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2955) kupto

From  (G3844) para and  (G2983) lambano; to receive near, i.e. Associate with oneself (in any familiar or intimate act or relation); by analogy, to assume an office; figuratively, to learn -- receive, take (unto, with). see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2983) lambano

column7: to sail past or coast along
column9: From  (G3844) para and the middle voice of  (G3004) lego (in its original sense); (specially), to lay one's course near, i.e. Sail past -- pass, sail by. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3004) lego

column7: by the sea, the sea coast
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G251) hals; beside the salt (sea), i.e. Maritime -- sea coast. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G251) hals
From a compound of  (G3844) para and  (G236) allasso; transmutation (of phase or orbit), i.e. (figuratively) fickleness: variableness. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G236) allasso
From  (G3844) para and  (G3049) logizomai; to misreckon, i.e. Delude -- beguile, deceive. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3049) logizomai
From a derivative of  (G3886) paraluo; as if dissolved, i.e. "paralytic" -- that had (sick of) the palsy. see GREEK  (G3886) paraluo

From  (G3844) para and  (G3089) luo; to loosen beside, i.e. Relax (perfect passive participle, paralyzed or enfeebled) -- feeble, sick of the (taken with) palsy. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3089) luo

From  (G3844) para and  (G3306) meno; to stay near, i.e. Remain (literally, tarry; or figuratively, be permanent, persevere) -- abide, continue. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3306) meno see GREEK  (G3306) meno see GREEK  (G3844) para
From  (G3844) para and the middle voice of a derivative of  (G3454) muthos; to relate near, i.e. (by implication) encourage, console -- comfort. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3454) muthos
From  (G3888) paramutheomai; consolation (properly, abstract) -- comfort. see GREEK  (G3888) paramutheomai
Neuter of  (G3889) paramuthia; consolation (properly, concretely) -- comfort. see GREEK  (G3889) paramuthia
From a compound of  (G3844) para and  (G3551) nomos; to be opposed to law, i.e. To transgress -- contrary to law. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3551) nomos
From the same as  (G3891) paranomeo; transgression: iniquity. see GREEK  (G3891) paranomeo
From  (G3844) para and  (G4087) pikraino; to embitter alongside, i.e. (figuratively) to exasperate -- provoke. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G4087) pikraino
From  (G3893) parapikraino; irritation -- provocation. see GREEK  (G3893) parapikraino

column7: to fall in, into or away, to fail
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G4098) pipto; to fall aside, i.e. (figuratively) to apostatize -- fall away. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G4098) pipto
From  (G3844) para and  (G4126) pleo; to sail near -- sail by. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G4126) pleo
Neuter of a compound of  (G3844) para and the base of  (G4139) plesion (as adverb); close by, i.e. (figuratively) almost -- nigh unto. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G4139) plesion
Adverb from the same as  (G3897) paraplesion; in a manner near by, i.e. (figuratively) similarly -- likewise. see GREEK  (G3897) paraplesion
From  (G3844) para and  (G4198) poreuomai; to travel near -- go, pass (by). see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G4198) poreuomai
From  (G3895) parapipto; a side-slip (lapse or deviation), i.e. (unintentional) error or (wilful) transgression -- fall, fault, offence, sin, trespass. see GREEK  (G3895) parapipto
From  (G3844) para and the alternate of  (G4482) rheo; to flow by, i.e. (figuratively) carelessly pass (miss) -- let slip. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G4482) rheo

column7: marked amiss, marked at the side, marked with a sign
column9: From  (G3844) para and the base of  (G4591) semaino; side-marked, i.e. Labelled (with a badge (figure-head) of a ship) -- sign. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G4591) semaino
From  (G3844) para and a derivative of  (G4632) skeuos; to furnish aside, i.e. Get ready -- prepare self, be (make) ready. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G4632) skeuos

column7: preparation, the day of preparation (for a Sabbath or feast)
column9: As if from  (G3903) paraskeuazo; readiness -- preparation. see GREEK  (G3903) paraskeuazo
From  (G3844) para and teino (to stretch); to extend along, i.e. Prolong (in point of time) -- continue. see GREEK  (G3844) para

column7: to watch closely, to observe scrupulously
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G5083) tereo; to inspect alongside, i.e. Note insidiously or scrupulously -- observe, watch. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G5083) tereo
From  (G3906) paratereo; inspection, i.e. Ocular evidence -- obervation. see GREEK  (G3906) paratereo

column7: to place beside, to set before
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G5087) tithemi; to place alongside, i.e. Present (food, truth); by implication, to deposit (as a trust or for protection) -- allege, commend, commit (the keeping of), put forth, set before. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G5087) tithemi

column7: to happen to be near or present
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G5177) tugchano; to chance near, i.e. Fall in with -- meet with. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G5177) tugchano
From  (G3844) para and a derivative of  (G846) autos; at the very instant, i.e. Momentary -- but for a moment. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G846) autos

column7: to bring to, to carry away
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G5342) phero (including its alternate forms); to bear along or aside, i.e. Carry off (literally or figuratively); by implication, to avert -- remove, take away. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G5342) phero

column7: to be beside oneself, to be deranged
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G5426) phroneo; to misthink, i.e. Be insane (silly) -- as a fool. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G5426) phroneo
From  (G3912) paraphroneo; insanity, i.e. Foolhardiness -- madness. see GREEK  (G3912) paraphroneo
From  (G3844) para and  (G5492) cheimazo; to winter near, i.e. Stay with over the rainy season -- winter. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G5492) cheimazo
From  (G3914) paracheimazo; a wintering over -- winter in. see GREEK  (G3914) paracheimazo

From  (G3844) para and  (G5536) chrema (in its original sense); at the thing itself, i.e. Instantly -- forthwith, immediately, presently, straightway, soon. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G5536) chrema
Feminine of pardos (a panther); a leopard -- leopard.

From  (G3844) para and  (G1510) eimi (including its various forms); to be near, i.e. At hand; neuter present participle (singular) time being, or (plural) property -- come, X have, be here, + lack, (be here) present. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1510) eimi

column7: to introduce, to bring in secretly
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G1521) eisago; to lead in aside, i.e. Introduce surreptitiously -- privily bring in. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1521) eisago
From  (G3919) pareisago; smuggled in: unawares brought in. see GREEK  (G3919) pareisago

From  (G3844) para and a compound of  (G1519) eis and  (G1416) duno; to settle in alongside, i.e. Lodge stealthily -- creep in unawares. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1519) eis see GREEK  (G1416) duno
From  (G3844) para and  (G1525) eiserchomai; to come in alongside, i.e. Supervene additionally or steathily -- come in privily, enter. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1525) eiserchomai

column7: to bring in, to supply besides
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G1533) eisphero; to bear in alongside, i.e. Introduce simultaneously -- give. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1533) eisphero
From  (G3844) para and  (G1622) ektos; near outside, i.e. Besides -- except, saving, without. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1622) ektos

column7: to put in beside or between, interpose
column9: From a compound of  (G3844) para and  (G1685) emballo; a throwing in beside (juxtaposition), i.e. (specially), battle-array, encampment or barracks (tower Antonia) -- army, camp, castle. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1685) emballo
From  (G3844) para and  (G1776) enochleo; to harass further, i.e. Annoy -- trouble. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1776) enochleo
From  (G3844) para and the base of  (G1927) epidemeo; an alien alongside, i.e. A resident foreigner -- pilgrim, stranger. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G1927) epidemeo

column7: to pass by, to come to
column8: to pass by, pass away; to arrive
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G2064) erchomai; to come near or aside, i.e. To approach (arrive), go by (or away), (figuratively) perish or neglect, (causative) avert -- come (forth), go, pass (away, by, over), past, transgress. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2064) erchomai
From  (G2935) ktetor; praetermission, i.e. Toleration -- remission. see GREEK  (G2935) ktetor

From  (G3844) para and  (G2192) echo; to hold near, i.e. Present, afford, exhibit, furnish occasion -- bring, do, give, keep, minister, offer, shew, + trouble. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2192) echo

From a compound of  (G3844) para and a derivative of  (G58) agora (meaning to harangue an assembly); an address alongside, i.e. (specially), consolation -- comfort. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G58) agora
From  (G3933) parthenos; maidenhood -- virginity. see GREEK  (G3933) parthenos
Of unknown origin; a maiden; by implication, an unmarried daughter -- virgin.

column7: a Parthian, an inhabitant of Parthia
column9: Probably of foreign origin; a Parthian, i.e. Inhabitant of Parthia -- Parthian.

column7: to pass by or over, to relax
column9: From  (G3844) para and hiemi (to send); to let by, i.e. Relax -- hang down. see GREEK  (G3844) para

column7: to place beside, to present, stand by, appear
column9: Or prolonged paristano (par-is-tan'-o) from  (G3844) para and  (G2476) histemi; to stand beside, i.e. (transitively) to exhibit, proffer, (specially), recommend, (figuratively) substantiate; or (intransitively) to be at hand (or ready), aid -- assist, bring before, command, commend, give presently, present, prove, provide, shew, stand (before, by, here, up, with), yield. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G2476) histemi
Probably by contraction for Parmenides (a derivative of a compound of  (G3844) para and  (G3306) meno); constant; Parmenas, a Christian -- Parmenas. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3306) meno
From  (G3844) para and  (G3598) hodos; a by-road, i.e. (actively) a route -- way. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3598) hodos

column7: to dwell near, reside as a foreigner
column9: From  (G3844) para and  (G3611) oikeo; to dwell near, i.e. Reside as a foreigner -- sojourn in, be a stranger. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3611) oikeo
From  (G3941) paroikos; foreign residence -- sojourning, X as strangers. see GREEK  (G3941) paroikos
From  (G3844) para and  (G3624) oikos; having a home near, i.e. (as noun) a by-dweller (alien resident) -- foreigner, sojourn, stranger. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3624) oikos

column7: a byword, a parable, an allegory
column9: From a compound of  (G3844) para and perhaps a derivative of  (G3633) oiomai; apparently a state alongside of supposition, i.e. (concretely) an adage; specially, an enigmatical or fictitious illustration -- parable, proverb. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3633) oiomai
From  (G3844) para and  (G3631) oinos; staying near wine, i.e. Tippling (a toper) -- given to wine. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3631) oinos
From  (G3844) para and oichomai (to depart); to escape along, i.e. Be gone -- past. see GREEK  (G3844) para
From  (G3946) paromoios; to resemble -- be like unto. see GREEK  (G3946) paromoios
From  (G3844) para and  (G3664) homoios; alike nearly, i.e. Similar -- like. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3664) homoios

column7: to sharpen, to stimulate, to provoke
column9: From  (G3844) para and a derivative of  (G3691) oxus; to sharpen alongside, i.e. (figuratively) to exasperate -- easily provoke, stir. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3691) oxus
From  (G3947) paroxuno ("paroxysm"); incitement (to good), or dispute (in anger) -- contention, provoke unto. see GREEK  (G3947) paroxuno
From  (G3844) para and  (G3710) orgizo; to anger alongside, i.e. Enrage -- anger, provoke to wrath. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3710) orgizo
From  (G3949) parorgizo; rage -- wrath. see GREEK  (G3949) parorgizo

column7: to urge on, to stir up
column9: From  (G3844) para and otruno (to spur); to urge along, i.e. Stimulate (to hostility) -- stir up. see GREEK  (G3844) para

From the present participle of  (G3918) pareimi; a being near, i.e. Advent (often, return; specially, of Christ to punish Jerusalem, or finally the wicked); (by implication) physically, aspect -- coming, presence. see GREEK  (G3918) pareimi
From  (G3844) para and the base of  (G3795) opsarion; a side-dish (the receptacle) -- platter. see GREEK  (G3844) para see GREEK  (G3795) opsarion

From  (G3956) pas and a derivative of  (G4483) rheo; all out-spokenness, i.e. Frankness, bluntness, publicity; by implication, assurance -- bold (X -ly, -ness, -ness of speech), confidence, X freely, X openly, X plainly(-ness). see GREEK  (G3956) pas see GREEK  (G4483) rheo
Middle voice from  (G3954) parrhesia; to be frank in utterance, or confident in spirit and demeanor -- be (wax) bold, (preach, speak) boldly. see GREEK  (G3954) parrhesia

Including all the forms of declension; apparently a primary word; all, any, every, the whole -- all (manner of, means), alway(-s), any (one), X daily, + ever, every (one, way), as many as, + no(-thing), X thoroughly, whatsoever, whole, whosoever.

column7: the Passover, the Passover supper or lamb
column9: Of Chaldee origin (compare  (H6453) pecach); the Passover (the meal, the day, the festival or the special sacrifices connected with it) -- Easter, Passover. see HEBREW  (H6453) pecach

column7: to suffer, to be acted on
column9: Including the forms patho (path'-o), and pentho (pen'-tho), used only in certain tenses for it apparently a primary verb; to experience a sensation or impression (usually painful) -- feel, passion, suffer, vex.
Probably of foreign origin; Patara, a place in Asia Minor -- Patara.

column7: to beat (of the heart), to strike
column9: Probably prolongation from  (G3817) paio; to knock (gently or with a weapon or fatally) -- smite, strike. Compare  (G5180) tupto. see GREEK  (G3817) paio see GREEK  (G5180) tupto
From a derivative probably of  (G3817) paio (meaning a "path"); to trample (literally or figuratively) -- tread (down, under foot). see GREEK  (G3817) paio
Apparently a primary word; a "father" (literally or figuratively, near or more remote) -- father, parent.

column7: Patmos, an island in the Aegean Sea
column9: Of uncertain derivation; Patmus, an islet in the Mediterranean -- Patmos.
From  (G3962) pater and the same as the latter part of  (G3389) metraloias; a parricide -- murderer of fathers. see GREEK  (G3962) pater see GREEK  (G3389) metraloias
As if feminine of a derivative of  (G3962) pater; paternal descent, i.e. (concretely) a group of families or a whole race (nation) -- family, kindred, lineage. see GREEK  (G3962) pater
From  (G3965) patria and  (G757) archo; a progenitor ("patriarch") -- patriarch. see GREEK  (G3965) patria see GREEK  (G757) archo
From  (G3962) pater; paternal, i.e. Ancestral -- of fathers. see GREEK  (G3962) pater
From  (G3902) parasemos; a father-land, i.e. Native town; (figuratively) heavenly home -- (own) country. see GREEK  (G3902) parasemos
Perhaps a contraction for Patrobios (a compound of  (G3962) pater and  (G979) bios); father's life; Patrobas, a Christian -- Patrobas. see GREEK  (G3962) pater see GREEK  (G979) bios

From  (G3962) pater and a derivative of  (G3860) paradidomi (in the sense of handing over or down); traditionary -- received by tradition from fathers. see GREEK  (G3962) pater see GREEK  (G3860) paradidomi

column7: of one\'s fathers, received from one\'s fathers
column9: From  (G3962) pater; paternal, i.e. Hereditary -- of fathers. see GREEK  (G3962) pater

column7: (Sergius) Paulus (a Roman proconsul), also Paul (an apostle)
column9: Of Latin origin; (little; but remotely from a derivative of  (G3973) pauo, meaning the same); Paulus, the name of a Roman and of an apostle -- Paul, Paulus. see GREEK  (G3973) pauo
A primary verb ("pause"); to stop (transitively or intransitively), i.e. Restrain, quit, desist, come to an end -- cease, leave, refrain.
Of uncertain derivation; Paphus, a place in Cyprus -- Paphos.

column7: to thicken, to fatten, to make dull
column9: From a derivative of  (G4078) pegnumi (meaning thick); to thicken, i.e. (by implication) to fatten (figuratively, stupefy or render callous) -- wax gross. see GREEK  (G4078) pegnumi
Ultimately from  (G4228) pous; a shackle for the feet -- fetter. see GREEK  (G4228) pous
From a derivative of  (G4228) pous (meaning the ground); level (as easy for the feet) -- plain. see GREEK  (G4228) pous

column7: to travel on foot or by land
column9: From the same as  (G3979) peze; to foot a journey, i.e. Travel by land -- go afoot. see GREEK  (G3979) peze
Dative case feminine of a derivative of  (G4228) pous (as adverb); foot-wise, i.e. By walking -- a- (on) foot. see GREEK  (G4228) pous

From a compound of  (G3982) peitho and  (G757) archo; to be persuaded by a ruler, i.e. (genitive case) to submit to authority; by analogy, to conform to advice -- hearken, obey (magistrates). see GREEK  (G3982) peitho see GREEK  (G757) archo
From  (G3982) peitho; persuasive -- enticing. see GREEK  (G3982) peitho

A primary verb; to convince (by argument, true or false); by analogy, to pacify or conciliate (by other fair means); reflexively or passively, to assent (to evidence or authority), to rely (by inward certainty) -- agree, assure, believe, have confidence, be (wax) conflent, make friend, obey, persuade, trust, yield.
From the same as  (G3993) penes (through the idea of pinching toil; "pine"); to famish (absolutely or comparatively); figuratively, to crave -- be an hungered. see GREEK  (G3993) penes
From the base of  (G4008) peran (through the idea of piercing); a test, i.e. Attempt, experience -- assaying, trial. see GREEK  (G4008) peran

column7: to make proof of, to attempt, test, tempt
column9: From  (G3984) peira; to test (objectively), i.e. Endeavor, scrutinize, entice, discipline -- assay, examine, go about, prove, tempt(-er), try. see GREEK  (G3984) peira

From  (G3985) peirazo; a putting to proof (by experiment (of good), experience (of evil), solicitation, discipline or provocation); by implication, adversity -- temptation, X try. see GREEK  (G3985) peirazo
From  (G3984) peira; to test (subjectively), i.e. (reflexively) to attempt -- assay. see GREEK  (G3984) peira
From a presumed derivative of  (G3982) peitho; persuadableness, i.e. Credulity -- persuasion. see GREEK  (G3982) peitho
Of uncertain affinity; deep or open sea, i.e. The main -- depth, sea.

column7: to cut off with an ax, to behead
column9: From a derivative of  (G4141) plesso (meaning an axe); to chop off (the head), i.e. Truncate -- behead. see GREEK  (G4141) plesso
From  (G4002) pente; fifth -- fifth. see GREEK  (G4002) pente

Apparently a primary verb; to dispatch (from the subjective view or point of departure, whereas hiemi (as a stronger form of eimi) refers rather to the objective point or terminus ad quem, and  (G4724) stello denotes properly, the orderly motion involved), especially on a temporary errand; also to transmit, bestow, or wield -- send, thrust in. see GREEK  (G4724) stello

column7: one who works for his living
column9: From a primary peno (to toil for daily subsistence); starving, i.e. Indigent -- poor. Compare  (G4434) ptochos. see GREEK  (G4434) ptochos
Feminine of  (G3995) pentheros; a wife's mother -- mother in law, wife's mother. see GREEK  (G3995) pentheros
Of uncertain affinity; a wife's father -- father in law.
From  (G3997) penthos; to grieve (the feeling or the act) -- mourn, (be-)wail. see GREEK  (G3997) penthos
Strengthened from the alternate of  (G3958) pascho; grief -- mourning, sorrow. see GREEK  (G3958) pascho
Prolongation from the base of  (G3993) penes; necessitous -- poor. see GREEK  (G3993) penes
Multiplicative adverb from  (G4002) pente; five times -- five times. see GREEK  (G4002) pente
